I've been using WAZE for a few years now and it has been a pretty solid and reliable navigation app to use. Like anything and everything it's not perfect, but it's free, it's ad free and has a great UI that's easy to use. The maps are good and for the most part, the routes worked out for you are quick and painless. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is due to its tendency to, at times, just stop working in middle of a route and leave you hanging. But that can happen with any GPS app.

The only thing I wish I could do is when I report an accident or police or hazard, that I could press on the map the exact location because by the time I report seeing the police officer or a hazard I'm already past it.

content: We love this app for daily driving directions. It provides an ability for the user to report circumstances that might otherwise impact other drivers from getting from point A to B.

Ok so idea is great and I gave it a try and ignored some of the lesser issues for a while. The result was:  1) No riders whatsoever - for 2 weeks I tried to find someone to carpool but didn't get any single request or notification or whatever it is supposed to be. 2) Adding a corporate email didn't work for me - I received no verification  email. 3) Adding a facebook account simply didn't work at all 4) The app fails silently if network connection is lost, even if GPS is  still working. When connection is resumed it doesn't resume the navigation to the previously selected location but instead just shows your position on the map, again without any warning. In practice it means that when you're driving and for a short time you're out of a network what you see is the app just suddenly stops giving you directions or showing the way.  Of course, I thought maybe I'm doing something wrong and asked about these issues via feedback form. At which point I was literally banned and it was the *only* answer I received from them. Well, that kind of does it. Still wonder what was going on in the head of the person who was doing it though. I guess they just felt a bit Stalin today?

content: Love this app! I use it everyday! It's definitely helped me not get any speeding tickets thanks to everyone updating in real-time!

For this to be one of the most popular navigation apps it has some serious flaws and poor design choices.  First my biggest complaint, the "speedometer" feature.  This feature is implemented in the stupidest way possible.  It focuses on showing you a small speedometer of your speed.  Why do I need another display for my speed?  My car already has this function.  What I want from it is the speed limit display.  But you only get this in a very tiny bubble next to your current speed,.  Unless you are going exactly the right speed for your setting then it shows the speed limit fully. USELESS!  Whoever designed that had no clue what they were doing.  There should be an option to simply show the speed limit only at all times.  Maybe an optional speed display if you are exceeding the speed limit.  Next, the alerts.  These things are about as reliable as weather forecasting lol.  8 times out of 10 when there is something on the map like a cop or a car on the shoulder of the road it is not really there.  Also the route algorithm is horrible.  I don't know what it prioritizes but it often wants to take me down a route that is 10  miles longer on a normally 20 mile trip.  Very poor routing.
Need a clear legend of the different symbols. Also needs a volume control button. Voice is way to loud. Option for fastest route and direct route ie interstate and 2 lane highways

content: I used to love this app. I still use it for work. I work in Pittsburgh. The view of the app is good. Easier to use than Google maps. The maps ran me in circles a few times. Trust me. Driving in Pittsburgh in circles is a very bad thing. Especially with a truck and trailer. Some detours it put me on streets, you could barely fit a car through or it was like it confused itself and made me turn around. I'd like to knit pick a little and request a satellite view. Maybe an update on your mapping.

And the best feature it had was the ability to share your drive with a friend, so they can see where you are, well this feature is totally broken and useless.  Even if you just try to share your ETA, its off by a mile.  If they ever decide to fix at least the ride share issue  I will gladly give it back to 5 stars.

Been using this since it came out and it's more of a necessary evil.  It puts Google maps to shame in that it's much more accurate and update with traffic and alerts. I only use Google maps with a downloadable map locally now. Hence the problem, Waze, like Google, is a data hog. Not a problem if you have unlimited data, but be careful if you don't and you use it a lot or go on a week-long trip and use it all the time. It also will not turn off when you turn it off. It stays on in the background. I use an app called Hibernate, which takes care of this and others, but have to remember to hit it every time. It also routinely crashes on my Android and will lose it's satellite connection if you were connected to WiFi and then drive away. Not sure what's up with that, but it will give you a bad connection and can't find your address. You can't just turn it off and start again. You have to go to your apps and force stop it, then restart it. Real PITA. It's been like this for years, but you get what you pay for and the ads are too obnoxious, not like Zynga, who are complete jerks. It usually finds the  best way home and I've learned not to second guess it, but watch the residential routes.
I appreciate the ability to get alternate that, even though they seem weird, get me where I'm going.

content: Oh Waze, what happened? This app used to be reliable and accurate! Sometimes, I would be later than my estimated arrival time but that is fine however, the last few months, my commute has been extended at least 20+ minutes! I understand where I live has high traffic areas but Waze used to notify me once traffic is building up ahead, not anymore! Now, once I turn into a road with traffic or construction, Waze will increase my commute tremendously and there is nothing I can do about it. It tells you that you will be stuck in traffic ONCE you are IN the traffic areas. If I hadn't made that turn, I could have avoided those roads. Why bother choosing which route is best when it would actually be the longest to take? Please fix this, this app used to be the very best.

this used to be an amazing app. it has now become cluttered with ads and ever since they removed the option to disable the auto zoom, it has become unusable for my job. this is disappointing as I would use it for the entire course of my 10 hour shift. content: Great app. I like it. Can you add the ability to resize the speed icon and speed limit icon? Because now it's too small for me and it's hard to see.

I'm a huge fan of Waze, which is why it pains me to give it 3 stars. The functionality, mapping, planning, and ability to share what is happening on the roads in real time is brilliant. On a shorter journey it froze within 5 minutes of launching, which this occurring repeatedly until the app cache and storage was wiped and started afresh. It needs to be sorted out.
Too much ads!

Waze is great at finding the best routes to get you where you're going quickly and easily. I'd give it 5 stars if pop-up ads didn't appear over the map while I'm driving and if it were possible to truly turn the sound off. I could even live with the stupid chime tone interrupting my music if not fit the ads. I would happily pay for an ad-free version--and more than I would for most apps. The fact that there isn't one says a lot about the priorities, and the user clearly is not the customer here.

It kept rerouting our course, took us in circles, and took us down roads that were closed resulting in us missing part of the show. I ended up having to look at the map and find my own way to where we were going. I would not recommend this app to my worst enemy.

what an abysmal piece of software. it crashes so often when you first start it up and it says" Uh oh! Something went wrong" like talking to a toddler. usually you have to clear the cache and force stop the app and start again 5 or 6 or 10 times before it finally gets ahold of the network and downloads traffic data. I also love the fact that will make you zig zag across town turning left and right to save you one whole minute as opposed to just going all the way up and then turning left once.

Would totally give this app 5 stars if there were an option to disable the chirping redirect notification sound (or at least replace it with something less shrill) ... I know others have voiced the same complaint ... Here's the thing ... I sustained a severe concussion as a result of a flight accident while in the Navy. Now, loud, shrill noises at certain decibel levels trigger debilitating migraines. It would mean so much to people like me if we could just replace it with a softer tone.
Have used Waze for over a year. Have found it superior to any other program i have seen.

when it works it works, this app constantly crashes and times out all the time, even when driving. I'm constantly closing and restarting the app and even sometimes that doesn't work. I'm not sure if there's another alternative to google maps and Waze, but I'll be looking for something more consistent. (I'm on wifi when entering in routes, and I'm using a Samsung Galaxy 8)
Great! Have missed a few police but i was aware
Lately the nav is unreliable.

This app used to be amazing but they have ruined it! It used to show you ways around backups. It used to show you shortcuts. It used to adjust for traffic as you drove. All of those things that made this app so good and incredibly useful have been removed. You might as well use Maps, which is usually installed on your phone when you get it and safe the memory space. This used to be awesome but now is no better than maps! If you check out the ratings they have significantly gone down for the latest version.

Seemed like a children's game at first, but I'm used to it now and really like it. I like the displaying, reporting & confirming of things like roadworks and accidents. Re-routing is instant. No time is wasted continuously telling me to do a U turn like other apps. Search function could be better. The display is easy on the eye and accurate. The obtrusive Car Info button isn't important, so should be built into the task bar below.

I used to love Waze! I use it with Android auto in Sonata and it worked great up until about a month or more ago when it keeps saying no service. Keeps losing signal! I use this every single day as I freelance and have to travel for clients. Nothing like not knowing where you're going in the middle of a trip! I've uninstalled and reinstalled numerous times. Please fix this issue! I see a lot of other recent reviews with the same experience! Went from 5 stars to 1! Back to Google Maps now!

An alternative to Google Maps that works just as well. I like that speed cameras are on it. It is underused in the rural area that I live in so live traffic updates are not good. The big downside is that it only intermittently syncs with my calendar, so it is completely useless when I need to navigate somewhere without knowing the address off the top of my head. For that Google Maps is far better.

At first, it was the best GPS I had ever used, but then, it became the worst. It started getting me lost by rerouting out of nowhere, constantly. It also kept getting me through tolls when the "no toll" option was on. It would tell me to keep straight but the screen would show me to turn somewhere. It would also not complete my trips, it would tell me that I had reach my destination in the middle of nowhere. I really wanted to like this, but it was the worst GPS ever. Don't waste time and space.

Good app. I've used this to get around new cities and a couple of long road trips and the navigation is solid. The police reporting feature is helpful especially (I'm not usually speeding, but it puts me at ease, to know when the cops are coming up!) It's also helpful because when there's an accident or traffic along the freeway, the app tells you where it is on the road. This is because of reporting done by the user base, and in my area at least, users are pretty reliable.  However, when I'm going a significant distance, navigation will suddenly stop after 100 miles or so. The app doesn't turn off, but I have to put in my destination again so I can see how many miles I have to my next turn. It makes it difficult because I have to adjust the screen again when I'm driving alone when I should be focusing on the road.  Also, it would be helpful if the voice told you which street to turn onto instead of just the distance to your turn. I travel alone, and I'd rather not be looking at the screen all the time. Usually it's fine, but when I'm driving in a city and the intersections are close together, it gets confusing. This app is much better if you're traveling with a passenger.
Excelent app. I'm using it becuase I don't know very well the El Salvador's streets. It's like a tutor that show me the correct way to my destination.
Bugging Out. Adds stops midroute forcing you to reset your navigation and restart your drive. Constantly dumps to route overview forcing you to recenter while driving to keep directions current.

content: This is the absolute best app I have ever downloaded of any kind! I downloaded it to help navigate through the myrtle beach area just a few days after hurricane Florence hit. It helped so much! So many roads have been shut down and there are so many detours! This app shows those closed roads and any other hazards that may be around and helps you get around them! If it doesn't show a closed road, you can add it to the map as well as car accidents, police sightings, traffic flow and so much more! Thank you for creating this app! It truly is a life saver!

Recently on my Note 5, the Google Maps app has just been the crashing everytime I open it. So I decided to go back and re-download Waze, and it's improved a lot! content: Waze is great until it's not. Downsides are the distracting ads that seem to pop up only when your lost or confused (but not when I'm actually looking for something along the way). It's an OK app, but have other navigation options, too. ALSO they need to fix the whole "new phone, new account" required bs.

Trashy app. It used to be good but they merged with google and Waze is now a dumb app. Bad directions, slow, full of ads, map shows business icons and gimmicks like "drive with boy George". Some people just want directions, it's not rocket science
Who would have thought that we can easily modify our maps for updates and to make users more friendly in identifying your desired destination. I'm glad to have this Waze App for life.

It's a great app. It helped me on my road trips even when I lost Service, as long as I didn't shut it down I was able to keep the map up for directions. 1. A thing to change/add is make it easier to report issues on the road for other drivers. I kept getting notified of issues on the road that were 1-2 miles behind me, and I was unable to make a report while driving. Maybe a talk to text... not sure. It would help in traffic/construction/road closures etc... to either bypass or plan ahead.
bad apps slow and wrong direction..not updated

Uninstalled 30 minutes after download. It makes it hard to see the directions step-by-step (I couldn't find an option for that), the real-time directions don't alert you to lane changes/turns as far in advance as Google maps (makes it harder to use in traffic), and the distracting, jarring beep noise when you go off course even a little bit was just the icing on the cake as I was driving through the parking lot at my destination. Not a good first impression.

Just one very big problem: the voice prompts for turning or exiting need to be more specific. Some times it says to "turn right" and i have three options to turn right onto. I'd have to look at my car's screen, or my phone, to know exactly where i need to go. Having the street names and exit numbers told along with when to turn or exit would be very nice. Until that happens, I'm going back to GoogleMaps, even if that one takes forever to load up and search for locations.

I really like the content of this app but have to give a low rating, as after only a couple months of twice daily use during commuting to/from work, some of the static headings are already starting to burn in to my screen. Don't use it any more for fear of making it worse. Hoping to get an Android Auto head unit installed soon that might alleviate that issue.

I have unlimited data unlimited everything but still the Waze app does not load, it constantly loses connection to the server, does the same thing on my husband's phone, we have both uninstalled and reinstalled it, reset our phones to factory settings, and we started our phones multiple times trying to get it to work. content: I've been through 5 phones and all the major carriers over the past several years and no matter what I'm using I always have issues with a network error. If I go through a dead area it says searching for network but even when I get cell service back the error won't go away until I force stop the app and restart. And until I do that I can't send or receive reports of any kind. It's to the point now where unless I know I'll need Waze to route me around traffic in major cities I just stick with Google Maps.

They must change how they choose to market. I'm done with the app until they do. The app frequently interrupts navigation while the car is in motion with prompts that have nothing to do with the trip and require the attention of the driver while in heavy traffic or at high speeds. Many times requiring a button click to remove the distraction. The app is aware that the car is moving and yet waze continues these distractions without any way to shut them off during the trip.

Traffic updates are not shown. No updates on construction sites. The main purpose is defeated when you can't figure out how much time will it take to ride till you reach your destination. That's the main drawback. Visual graphics and options are awesome. Easily got addicted to it. However later I had to switch on to Google maps for better traffic updates.

I don't know what's happened lately but the suggested routes that Waze has been recommending are not the best routes. On at least three occasions I purposefully went a different route (one that I knew to be faster and have least traffic) and ended up having up to thirty minutes on my commute. The takeaway for me is that while it's nice to have Waze as a copilot but you shouldn't rely on it solely for the best route.

I'm very satisfied with this app. I open the app every morning as I leave the house. Even though I already know how to get where I'm going, if there is a major problem or crash, it automatically reroutes me and gets me there as fast as possible. I would recommend this app to anyone who has to commute or drive in rush hour traffic or do long term driving. It's great for just a normal Mom like me that has to take my husband to work and daughter to school. Then I have to go to work myself. It's saved my butt several times from getting stuck in traffic. I also recommended it to a close friend that drives a tractor trailer for a living and now he constantly uses it to drive from state to state.

Very handy in every aspect. Day or Night. Especially at night. Love the hazard warnings. Nice to be warned when driving home from work and there is a worning. Going home at night this app has save me from possible encounters of bad road conditions. I can't say enough about how helpful this app is. I feel SO SO MUCH SAFER on the road. Thank you for this wonderful app. P.S. I use a Tracfone and I am limited to Data uses. The app uses very little Data. Thanks again.

the only thing that is missing from this app is that it doesn't allow you to downsize the screen so you can continue to see the actual directions vs just hearing them. Fantastic app. Serious A plus. My only suggestion is to add a dipshit alert. Either sound bit or a physical badge

It was pretty much fine until the last update. Now, it's harder to use. Waze removed the always lock north up feature, so every time I open the app I have to manually reset it. The rest of this review applies to Waze overall, not just the last update. Route options are strange. Say I'm driving to point B. It will give me two different routes to point B that intersect at some point. So the two routes vary in the first half of the trip but should be the same once they intersect. It should be XXXZZZ and YYYZZZ. Instead, it gives me alternate second halves too. So it's XXXZZZ and YYYNNN. This makes it impossible to really compare routes by their ETA. So I end up doing two trips first one to intersection point. Second one from there. It takes a ton of clicks just to start a drive. 1) click in search bar. 2) type destination 3) pick from a terrible list 4) location opens, click go 5) route opens, click routes to see route 6) select route you like 7) click go again 8) click compass to lock north Just terrible. The search function is terrible too. It brings up weird results for businesses and is hard to read. It's hard to view businesses on a map. The "are you a passenger?" Is beyond frustrating. It's too easy to accidentally swipe open their carpool page that I don't use. There are way too many icons on the map. It's confusing. The bubbles are childish and block your view. I DON'T CARE IF SOMEONE REPORTED HEAVY TRAFFIC ON THE OTHER SIDE OF THE ROAD. Why does it show me reports from the other side of the road? All it does is confuse things and make it hard to see what's actually on your route. It's not very good at re-routing. I have to manually re-routing multiple times during my commute. There's probably other things that I can't think of right now. Basically, use Google Maps for directions and this for alerts while driving (police, etc).

I was misled as the congestion on the suggested route was far worse. I managed to work my way back to the route that I was familiar with and the traffic flow was much better. So this app had left me confused. Can I trust it for future road traffic situations?

Love the app for the most part.... But recently it started leaving pop up ads on my home screen which is super annoying, especially when I'm trying to use my phone for other purposes. Also it seems to no longer show "the best time to leave" feature properly, instead always showing the same travel time no matter what time I'm intending to leave or how traffic conditions are. Please fix.
Must-have for any driver

It's great but ... if you don't have GPS signal then this app is completely useless. This is particularly problematic in tunnels. It should be able to use the "assisted" GPS feature to continue to provide information visas mobile internet, and more importantly, the input features should work so that one can update any traffic information for other users.

I think you've got the carpool idea completely wrong: The idea was to be eco friendly, neighbor friendly, traffic reducing solution. But you've designed it to be an Uber alternative or a pay-as-you-go franchise. For every hitchhiker I take, I get tens of results that aren't relevant to my way home/work. Personally, I don't do this for the money (and I wish I could've donated it directly to some better transit solutions), but I will not add 20 to 30 minutes to my drive home for a few coins.

Love everything about this app. It calculates your arrival time, with & without traffic. It notificies you if there's any police ahead, fog, speed camera, red light camera, hazard, stopped vehicle, every little detail to make your trip safer and easier. Only problem is, sometimes it takes me to the longest routes, even when I choose the shortest. It doesn't give me all the possible shorcuts, until i realise that I could have saved a good 5 to 10 minutes drive. But other than that, Thumbs up and 5 stars!
Awesome best one out there informed you on what's going on around you.

The app works very good but has some room for improvement, would like to have a quick access to the next gas station or how far is it, while driving you can not distract your eyes from the road much, now in the app you have to do about 5 touches in order to select and try to understand the app on where is the next gas station, confusing while driving to be honest, a single tap to select the next gas station will help a lot! more focus on the road!

This app used to be great, much better than either Google maps or Apple maps. However the most recent update has not only made it much worse, it seems to have become quite dangerous. We live in Qatar, which is a desert. When you drive out of Doha, the main city, you can go for a long time without seeing anything except sand and heat. My wife and her family used Waze to navigate to a kayaking place up in the North of Qatar, about 45km north of Doha. Waze took them almost to the southernmost point of Qatar before turning back up north, but also repeatedly directed them to nonexistent petrol stations. They finally ended up at a petrol station with little more than 5km left in the tank. By definition the people who use maps apps are the people who DON'T know enough about the route to sanity check the app. My wife shouldn't have to zoom out of the map to check that Waze isn't taking her in the completely opposite direction and tripling her travelling distance and possibly putting her life at risk by leaving her stranded in a desert. The fact that we now need to do so makes the app useless. Another case, i had to drive to an animal shelter last week, a 40km trip. Waze's initial route wanted me to drive 80 km. By making one change and driving straight instead of turning when Waze wanted me to, it immediately dropped to 40km with traffic showing as all clear. Why doesn't it pick that route in the first place?!!! It's extremely frustrating, a waste of our time, fuel and patience. The previous version was much much better. Is there any way to downgrade to an older version until you fix whatever issue you are having with your new algorithms?
Like it caused it warn you to about the road
Easy and accurate...mostly

Great idea when it works. The problem is all of the bugs in the app. During the load, the screen renders over and over again looking like it wont load, but it eventually does. Then you get to a login screen for Facebook. When you edit your list so that you don't share your photos and friends list, the app rechecks everything you unchecked and tries to run anyway. it never does. just gets caught in the same loop.

There used to be an option to cancel the audio directions but you removed it for some weird reason that is unknown to me. Now I am forced to listen to the voice directions. I tried to lower the audio fully in settings which is the only thing I can do about that but it's still muting my music every time its supposed to give a direction. Give us the option back and let us decide for ourselves.

By far the best GPS app I have ever used. The alerts feature for traffic, police accidents, etc are spot on and very accurate. only issue I have is turn-by-turn navigation on city streets could give a little more warning. Depending on where you are and your speed, turn-by-turn is a little slow in some places. Other than that this app is amazing. Also love the option of have spotify interact with Waze so I don't have to flip from screen to screen!

I used to LOVE this app. I honestly used it every time I drove anywhere (even as a passenger). Now, ever since the last update, every time I open it, it cannot locate me and behaves as if I don't have GPS turned on when I do.. I checked my Samsung device maintenance manager and this app is #1 on the "App Issue Report" list. Waze has crashed 21 times since January 28th, 2 weeks ago, and I've hardly even used it because of the issues so 21 crashes is a massive number. PLEASE FIX! I miss this app!

Prior to its acquisition by Google, Waze was a solid app, although it had a major blind spot (inability to anticipate traffic problems when rush hour approaches). Now that Google is determined to monetize it through Carpool, there are constant popups asking if I want to use Carpool, and even "reminders" to use it - none of which mention a cost. It's too bad, because the crowdsourced traffic information was really useful, even if only in heavily-traveled areas, but Google has a history of terrible app decisions, and I suspect this is more of the same. I'll be looking for a non-Google navigation app.

It likes to pop up with promotions they are trying to do while I drive. I constant have to hit the screen while driving to get it to go back to the map. It does this about once a minute. Once it took me out of the map as I was about to get off a highway exit to ask me survey question; the question was to the lines of, "have you seen any Dr. Pepper bill boards...?" Today, it kept harassing me while I was trying to drive because it really wants me to immediately attach my Spotify account and re-enter my home and work address again, even though they are already on there. It asks too many questions taking people out of maps and having people hit buttons and read questions on the screen while driving. Sometimes people that always give Waze feedback while driving really scare me because they are so distracted with their Waze profile. I wish it was less pushy and would just keep the map up. This isn't supposed to be a social media app, but a navigation app; or so I thought....

I like Waze but I had two tickets and Waze didn't aware me of police around. The app used to be quicker to receive addresses but since Google Assistant is in Waze, it takes longer for Waze to set the address requested. But thanks Waze for your great features

This app used to be good. Now, it's literally unusable if you listen to anything through AA while navigating (my primary use for it). I have a long commute, so I frequently listen to podcasts and music. But Waze cuts in and lowers the volume temporarily every 3-5 seconds now (as if there were an alert or direction coming) when using Android Auto. This also means that my phone beeps incessantly when I'm on a call to let me know there's a background notification coming in. Seems like this has been an issue, but no one seems to care enough to fix it. Bummer, because this was way more reliable than GMaps in my city.

Bottom line, good navigation app. Would still like to see: 1. Constant 2 turn notification. This way I know what lane to get into before I turn. 2. An visual indicator of what side of the street my destination is on. Verbal is incorporated, but I use alerts only mode most of the time. 3. An option to turn off the automatic navigation feature when the app is started. I often use the app for traffic and alerts only, but the app starts navigation to where an algorithm predicts I'm going, forcing me to stop it each time. Cash wise it's free. Data wise, well, it's developed by Google so they already have access to anything on an Android phone anyway.

App tends to send you on side streets that take longer than remaining on the freeway. Too many times in an effort to find a quicker route the app will end up wasting time and cause worse delays. I tested this repeatedly and found more times than not I was better off remaining on the freeway. I tried to reach out to support by they required I create an account in the waze app, which requires my phone number. God forbid I create an account with an email address.
Best traffic app I've ever had

First, I think this is a phenomenal app for driving and finding 'short-cuts.' Sometimes it takes me over excessive bridges and tolls. I cannot just say 'fewest' tolls for a driving experience. Also, I have been experiencing issues with the Planned Trip portion. Why does it keep saying 'Uh-oh- Server Timed Out? Its always, unless I am sitting in my car, in the middle of traffic, rubbing a genies bottle and praying to God. Need this bug fixed, please!

This is great app - when it is working! I have now had to load this app three times from scratch over the last few weeks. On each occasion I have had to add my favourites again which has become very tedious. The app crashed again this morning and is constantly saying it is initialising. As a consequence I am about to give up on it as it is not reliable which is essential for as a navigation app
Great, except it would be nice to put in your tank size and have it account for stops to refuel in the ETA

Waze is essentially a better, more complete version of Google maps specifically for driving (no walking, bussing, et cetra). My favorite features include the speed limit warning, red light camera warning, and, above all else... the Police Reporting. If you live in an urban area this functions even better. When you see an officer doing radar/laser report it to help out potential-victims and fellow wazers. If you drive by a report where there is no officer, just suggest it be deleted. The app is very intuitive and there are many features. In fact, there are so many features it may be confusing at first, but you should definitely stick with it as the app is awesome once you get to know it.

I enjoy the app. It allows me to see what hazards, car wrecks, police and other things are going to be on my route. It helps to plan how I am going places. Sometimes when it gives directions it will put you back where you were trying to avoid. I use this app almost daily. I would recommend this app. Also, getupside for gas savings. Together they are great.

It was a great app when it first came out but now it's just garbage. It takes me long, unnecessary routes, and occasionally when I click to go home which I have on my favorites, it will take me somewhere completely different. Also is very slow and difficult to reroute if you miss a turn for example. Do not recommend, although the police and construction alerts are helpful when they show up.

seems to work well so far,using it on my android radio in my car,only problem is when you use it and you are listing the radio it shuts off the music every time it tells you to turn or to get ready to turn,i have to keep switching back to the radio and turn it on again,very annoying,,is there a way to stop this from happening ??

Works like a dream... most of the time, more often lately though it says check my connection. Even though I've got 4 bars of 4G signal? Giving me no choice but to use Google maps. Usually when i need it most to avoid rush hour traffic jams. Frustrating, used to be great, but it's just good... when it works. Tried airplane mode for 10 seconds, tried turning my phone off & on again. Same problem keeps happening.
loading detect location..
replyContent:
Hey there! If you're having trouble using Waze, we're happy to help you with that. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook with more details about what you're experiencing?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Horrible interaction with Android Auto. Can't add supplemental stops or search along route. Freezes or automatically shuts down on a regular basis. It used to be a great app - now I'm back to using Google maps. Even though Google lacks many of the features that Waze promises, it at least is reliable and gets me to where I'm going. What a shame.

Great app to get you to your destination with feedback on road conditions from other users which is fantastic. I would prefer if it showed map overview like Google maps when making the route so I can instantly see if I the chosen route is to my liking and if I definitely chose the right place to go to. Also if you don't have the address to a place you want to go to, it's sometimes hard to find them here, and I have to check it on maps first.
Not Cool we need 4 digit drive license we have it

Got me completely lost. It took me over 30 minutes away from where I was supposed to be. Instead of getting on the highway and going there exits to where I needed to be it took me down all these back roads to the wrong location. That's with the correct address used in the program. This app used to work great but recently it's been HORRIBLE. I hate getting lost especially when I use a GPS.

I love this app, however, I'm constantly having to uninstall and reinstall it. After a short while it does the same thing, over and over. "Waze is trying to connect to GPS" despite my location and all the jazz being on. I have friends with the same issue (they have iPhone I have Android). Can we figure this out maybe?

Tried a few free gps apps in the past but this is by far the best. Up coming roadworks. Safety cameras. Hazards or broken down vehicles. It even tells you the cheapest fuel in the surrounding area. It does consume a fair amount of battery but if I don't have my charger I just dim the brightness before a long journey. Or you can lock the screen and just follow the voice commands. as free apps go this is excellent

love the app and the ability to report and receive reports road hazards, traffic, hiding cops, traffic cameras, Etc. the only reason I'm not giving it five stars is the Annoying new pop-up ads that I have to clear to see my maps, and the constant reminder that I can't get to stop coming up every time I open it about ride-sharing, which I don't want to do

In a frustrating traffic jam, the app took me to a road that was blocked by police due to the traffic. This route added another hour to my drive. The app is not trust worthy and I wish it would spend more effort on providing accurate information and less time on cartoonish bubbles. Very disappointed and will never, ever, use this app again

Unsafe! Because waves are so concerned with promoting their carpool feature and supply and advertisers it will block the screen and make you have to press a button to resume navigation. This can be very distracting while you're driving. I almost hit a pedestrian this morning because I had to push a button to unblock the map. I'm I'm very upset. I'm deleting this thing now.

This used to be a great app. Then, a long time ago, the intrusive adds starting appearing. Then, sometime ago, there were issues with the language and voice, then, not too long ago, problems started to appear with gps - until gps failed to work completely. Which is fairly essential for a navigation app. The last drop was the complete mess with restoring the account after multiple failed log in attempts after a reinstall. Starting to look for alternatives.
replyContent: Hi Dani√´l, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about all the issues. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: USED TO BE SUPERB! I am not sure what happened to Waze. It used to be so reliable. It is now constantly crashing and then will only work with a reboot. There IS no time for that when you are wondering what your next turn is. It is therefore becoming unusable and unfortunately I need to switch over to my other map program frequently.

Can't avoid a specific part of the route. It's nice having the fancy traffic and road works routing but you sometimes the driver knows best, something the algorithms don't, and you want to say no avoid that bit. For whatever reason, maybe auto traffic hasn't picked it up, maybe you know it's not busy now but it's going to get busy, maybe it's not suitable for your specific vehicle, maybe it's just personal preference. Whatever the reason you should be able to manually adjust your route
replyContent: Hi Al, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. Please share your ideas for the app to Waze's suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Overall, I like that Waze updates the traffic situation.  That's the major reason why I use it, although Google does provide the same features.  A few points , though.  1) I find that the estimated times are ALWAYS substantially less than actual.  On a normal one hour drive that sees added traffic, the estimate will be off by as much as 50%.  Surely with all the data available, including historical traffic and speed data, they can do better.  My old TomTom device would be the opposite, overestimating but at least close.  2) I detest the way that Waze selects routes.  Older devices allowed an option to ignore the local area.  Especially for repeated drives, everyone has their preferred local routes, and having Waze define the route as it chooses just makes it less useful. I'd like the app to allow me to ask for 'Most direct' route.  I don't want to zig zag all over the city, I want to go directly there  I know that I can edit the route to some extent, although that doesn't work on mobile very well, the system is awkward to use and faulty.  Perhaps the app could allow saving of specific ROUTES as well as locations, for those of us who merely want time and traffic information.

This app used to be great, but I've had nothing but problems since the last update. The map skips around and says there's no network connection. It's not usable. I contacted support and was told to completely uninstall and reinstall the app. No surprise, but that didn't change anything. Looking at the recent reviews it's clear there's a problem. Take accountability and fix your app! Back to Google Maps I go.

I would have rated it a 5 but there is no walking option. We were in Savannah for the weekend and wanted to use it for getting from place to place walking. We ended up trying it on driving option and it didn't work as well as we hoped. It was great for driving since there were a lot of roads closed downtown due to the rock and roll marathan. Still recommend adding walking option, if possible.

It is good for the most part. However, i have submitted a speed limit issue several times over months and it has never been fixed nor acknowledged. Even sent email about it and they never responded. Most of the time when i try looking at route and/or surrounding route it doesnt show when there is a traffic jam, accident, etc. It sometimes does when move around, going back to it, etc. But the other ones i was watching disappears then reappears later again. I know its not because there is no longer a traffic jam, it was already there. After this last update i have to force close 2-3 times because it keeps saying it cannot calculate route. It did it before but only once in a while, not everytime i first use it. Also, would be nice if had more alternate routes and/or can maybe saving a route that just did. Theres a different way i would take in the morning that saves time and miles yet the option never comes up. Maybe even be able to click on road line and slide/move it to another road to see what difference is to maybe create own alternate route.

I'm so disappointed. When the app is working, it's great! However, last couple months have been rough. The GPS was having tons of trouble, and couldn't find me on the map half the time. Now the app doesn't really work at all as intended. For the last few weeks, it has been having "connection issues". If I'm lucky enough to actually get the app to function (it's often blank when I connect to Android Auto), I usually get a connection error, which means no real time information. App is unusable.
Can't travel without it !!! Love this app!!
Best GPS app on market
The only thing I wish that would be added is to tell us what our next turn is going to be as we are making turns kinda like Google maps does.

For the most point it does what it suppose too. But there are times that i am needing to go like on the west side and it directs me to the east side. And will not acknowlege the address that i need to get too
It's good >but NEEDS a CLEARLY VISIBLE "SHUT OFF" BUTTON!!! *Almost wrecked trying to figure out how to shut off!!!! >>THAT IS NOT OKAY!!!!!!!!
replyContent: Hi , thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Worst app ever! Did not go to the right route at the crucial time! The app ask to turn left when there was no route at all!!!
Very helpful application
Best GPS app. Let's you know what's going on around you and will take you around traffic jams, accidents... All kinds of stuff.

I have recommended this application to everyone I know. It has some flaws but the pros outweigh the cons. One major con I've recently noticed is that I can no longer use the "OK Waze" voice command to enable Waze to listen to my commands whilst driving. I no longer report traffic incidents due to the removal of this function. I would have to touch the screen to turn on voice commands each time I want to give one now, which is illegal in Australia. The GPS speedometer function is great and having the ability to display the speed limit is also great. In heavy traffic, in unknown areas, sometimes speed limit signs are obscured from vision by vehicles or other objects, being able to confirm this by looking/listening to alerts alleviates some stress. The speed limits are not always up to date, particularly if the road is under construction. Re-routing directions based on delays/accidents in traffic is good, though, sometimes the full effects of a traffic incident is not known until it's too late and you're part of the slow traffic by that stage. The opposite can also be true - heavy traffic may be reported along your route but by the time you reach that section, it has already cleared up. If you make a mistake and need to make a U-turn, Waze doesn't specifically tell you to make a U-turn. The developers have done a great job - 5 stars if you bring back the voice commands.
Miles better than all OEM satnavs. Regular updates, opportunity to advise on issues, and also whether those issues are still there or not. Highly recommended

Numerous complaints but here are the big three. One, I prefer driving in overhead view, but it doesn't show ETA or turn-by-turn instructions or anything. Two, I was waiting at a light when it decided to change my route and told me to turn. Of course I wasn't in the right lane. Absurd to change route literally a few feet from an intersection. Three, and the source of the one-star rating, on a 40-minute drive it blocked the map with an ad twice. What good is a GPS that blocks navigation?
Excellent app always reliable!!

Easy to use. Offers alternative routes for routes with built up traffic, helping to keep journey's moving, and delays to a minimum. The ability to relay/receive traffic information eg, crashes or slow moving vehicles, is a great function on the app. It works abroad as well! Can't fault it, though the opportunity to download other voices would be appreciated. My go to app for travelling, whether walking, driving, or, using public transport. Keep up the good work. Kind Regards

Really like the app (its graphics, interface, alerts are often helpful). A couple issues that make it very agravating: was on a 400+ mile trip and it only worked about 1/3 of that trip. It kept telling me it couldn't connect to the routing server. I spent probably an hour trying to troubleshoot it. Uninstalled the app, reinstalled, restarted my phone, etc. It just randomly would work then wouldn't. Also, a big issue I have is the absence of ethanol-free fuel as an option. Please, add this, Waze!

Over the years it has gone from being highly accurate to often, less than accurate. My understanding was that it's supposed to learn routes I take and become more accurate, but often it tries to re-route, me after I've taken a shortcut, and it's re-route is often wrong or adds extra time to my trip. The nagging carpool messages have got to go. If I want to carpool, I'll get a carpool app. At the very least, ask me once and never again. Finally, please stop advertising over my route guidance.

I normally use google maps and have always sworn by it, refusing to use anything else for years. I just had to drive cross country though on a tight schedule so I decided to run both apps at the same time. By the end of the trip I was just using Waze. I sware atleast 20 times it saved me from getting pulled over. Thank you to everyone that takes this app seriously and throws a marker on those pesky porkers sitting on the side of the road waiting to get you. Gives you plenty time to slow down!

I wanted to like Waze. The traffic and hazard warnings are really nice. Yes, I know Google Maps offers this as well, but only while in navigation mode. Unlike Google Maps, Waze gives these warning if the app is open; it doesn't even need to be on top. I drive professionally and find the feature very helpful. What I can't stand, and would pay to disable, are the ads that pop up every time I stop at a traffic light. I had to delete it. Because of this, three stars until there is some way to pay for these to go away.
Has many great features, my favourite being showing the speed limit, but unfortunately it keeps giving me longer routes than Google. I've tried changing settings but nothing helps.

The app was great for quite a while, proved very useful to find alternative routes and I use it very frequently. However, I had to uninstall it after multiple times when it froze my phone touch screen completely, so ended up having to reset my mobile (I ran numerous trials to check with other apps, but definitely came from Waze) or would not find the GPS signal which is working fine otherwise, so it became more frustrating than anything. if these issues get sorted, I will gladly reinstall it..

Just started to use it but have encountered quite a few problems. Doesn't load right all the time and the GPS constantly gives me bad directions. It tells me to turn before I am supposed to. To get it to work right, I have to close the app and restart it. Very inconvienent when I am already driving! It needs a lot of work. Still needs a lot of work. Gives wrong directions now and cuts off mid sentence when giving directions. I hope that this app gets fixed but I will no longer be using it.
replyContent: Hi Lacey, we're sorry to hear about your issue. Let's get this figured out for you. Please message us on Facebook with the details so we can investigate further. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze will take you on little test trips where the way you're going makes no sense but you assume there must be a reason it's sending you that way, only to find out that it's just testing out a new way to go somewhere that will take you twice as long as you expected it to twice as long as they told you it would and therefore cause you to be late. It happened to me so many times that I finally uninstalled. if you know your area pretty well and you only need a couple of turns do not trust this.

Awesome app! Great for finding out if there are faster ways to your intended destination, whether there are hazards or cops on your path, and much more! The only thing I wish Waze had was a feature that lets you know which lane(s) to stay on. I've missed exits due to this. Otherwise, it also syncs with your Google calendar so appointments are all there!
Informative and reliable
The best navigation app!!! üî•üî•üî•

The app is constantly crashing mid travel. The only way to get it back is to go to apps, force quit, and then restart. This is NOT something you want to do whilst driving.  Also the insistency of the app to drive you into traffic jams without  (or when it is too late) informing you about it is annoying. Especially when there are options to avoid them.   A positive way to say this is: It would be nice if Waze could inform a little earlier about upcoming trouble. The "Five minute delays" warning is not easy to navigate. There is not difference in trying to click the small X on the top right of the little window, or simply tap the message itself. It does NOT change the route to combat the delay, nor does it make you take the faster route if offered.   When you have your navigation set to Avoid High/motor ways, and you DO decide to go on motorways after all, you should have a simple on off option to (de)activate that route setting. Instead of having to go through the route setup completely.  When trying to get an overview of the REMAINING travel route, it ONLY shows you the complete route,  without indicating where you are NOW.  Just some of my thoughts...

Way more good than bad! Obviously, Waze not sharing/selling our data is a huge point in its favor (I'm not being naive, I just like to make things a bit more difficult for the giants). The social aspect of the app - having drivers report events - is very appealing to me as well. Sure, there are things to improve, mainly in the UI. I'd compare this to the Fairphone: you know you buy it out of awareness for what it stands. (things certainly are more complicated, but we can try).
Application shows No network connection error

This used to be the best app. Not anymore. I have turned up late for meetings several times because waze keeps saying " No GPS connection" . First I thought it was my internet connection but I had YouTube playing without any problem. Then I thought I needed to update waze. I updated the app but the problem is still there. I thought it was because I'm using an old phone ( samsung s8+) but it appears many people are facing this same problem . So annoying
replyContent: Hi Betrand, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've been using Waze for about five years. However, recently after purchasing a new phone, I went to load up all of my old data and it was lost. I started over. Yesterday I received a replacement phone from my insurance and backed up all of my information on Waze and then attempted to transfer it over. Again, it is lost. My rankings, my car pool data, and everything else is pretty much lost to the ethos. What is the point of putting all that information in if you're just going to lose it?

Good pros but beware the cons! This is more accurate than Google maps and I love the automatic traffic reroutes. Very intuitive. Now the bad- Sometimes it changes your destination without you knowing. Sometimes it's to go to one of those popup ad places, other times, who knows? Case in point, using it to go from South Padre to DFW. Magically changed route to a tire store in Victoria Tx. Now know where Victoria is, but added time and miles to a long trip.

Don't like giving up my personal information like home address. Tried to get traffic updates on a route for a friend. Go figure. It let's me change a starting point from my location. But never acknowledges the new destination. The wheel kept spinning on wifi for 2 minutes. Google maps much faster and has traffic and construction updates. Lame.
Really really enjoy the police feature

1. Please distinguish between flyovers and road directly above ground, perhaps using very different colors or very apparent difference in road width. 2. If the app can show the current lane of the vehicle and the lane to use like Google Maps, that will be great. 3. After updating the app on 18.01.2019, I cannot fix the zoom function, making the map constantly zoom in and zoom out depending on vehicle speed. I prefer the old app, because I can disable the auto-zoom function.

I installed it, set up everything, then I put in an address and then it crashed. Now it instantly crashes everytime I open it, as soon as I opened it. Voice recognition does not work, it couldn't even find my home. I checked if it was an issue with my GPS or signal but nope, google maps worked perfectly fine. Was looking for an app to better my experience with deliveries... this is certainly not an app I would recommend let alone be able to use because of its constant crashing.

Great app.... until you change your phone. I broke my screen, got a new phone, but kept the same # and sim card...only to discover for whatever reason my account is gone. But I can't create a new one since my number, email and FB are still connected to my old one. So yeah loved this app on my first phone 5 out of 5...but the minute you change phones 1 out of 5.

I Was turned on to Waze by my sister. I love it and use it all the time. This app has saved me from lots of fines. It shows you all the information you need, like if you have not seen a speed limit sign in awhile , just look at the app. The users on the road report information so the app is " real time " if you hear "police reported ahead" you better check your speed. All I can say is the app is AWESOME!!! Thank you for an excellent app.

its very cute and looks nice. Very nice option to point out what is going on on your route with two tap. But this is where it stops for me. Major fail when i connect it to my car to have it on my car's display. Everything stops if my phone is locked. Not the automatic lock. i know there is an option to prevent that. But i don't see the reason why my phone should be unlocked while i drive. if anyone has a fix for that let me know. I would consider trying it again.

Well I'm having a problem reinstalling . And I had it before and I love it goes great and talks me on the road to take it's grrreeeaaattt. But this time I'm having. An Issue but I'm Shure it will work out . I hope
Thank you Waze. Great app!

I love Waze. But it loses a star because I can't use it without internet / network connectivity, and it doesn't let me download maps for offline navigation. If these 2 features were available, I would probably never have to use Google Maps again, at least not while driving. (I'm guessing this could be the reason Google doesn't enable these features, since that would cannibalize users from the other app?!)
Great App. Thanks Waze

I absolutely love this app, and it is my go to navigation application and I recommend it to all my friends. I'm only reading 2 stars, because upon switching phones and signing back into Waze. It treated me as if I were new and made me a Baby Wazer. Even though I've driven 1000s of miles using Waze. I hope there's a way to work around this, so I can change my review to 5 stars!
Always use Waze whenever I need to have a satnav or just to see where cameras and closed roads are. Helpful lane diagrams and useful in journey updates. Very intrusive ads too.

I love this app. I love how fast it moves and just the awareness of it just excellent. But I think u guys should make it a little bit easier to zoom out and in, like simply double tapping and dragging, and also i think there should be a faster and easier way to see different routes and overview in general, something like google maps has

The app has been crashing on me if I decide to turn off my phone screen for more than five minutes. Im a delivery driver and I need my phone all day, so I shut the screen off to save battery. Then I need to reopen the app on the road, probably right before a turn I'm about to miss, because Waze turned off when my screen was off for more than a few minutes.

Pretty good, when it works... I found the maps to be accurate and traffic reports speed camera locations are all very handy or would be. The trouble is most of the time it just sits there trying to find a GPS signal. I've waited it out a couple of times and it takes nearly 30 minutes. I've given up trying to use it now but hopefully a future update will fix this.

A recent Google maps update basically broke itself, so I was temporarily forced to use another navigation app, which lead me here. The app is very polished, very fun to use, with speed limit display, traffic and closures, etc etc. But it has one fatal flaw. It likes to take you to the wrong street. A lot. Even with the finish flag on top the road you want to end up on, if there's a parallel road nearby, it'll just take you there instead. Makes the app mostly pointless. Please fix!
Simple to use, effective, helpful

The best interactive navigation device I've ever found. Very easy to use, saves all your recent destination. Notifies you when you're breaking the speed limit notifies you when police are reported ahead notified you and red light cameras are within a half a mile of you it's a great app get it. Not easier to use than Google Maps and more up-to-date on accuracy.

Wish I had known about this app along time ago, it has so much more to offer than Google maps. I love how drivers can alert other drivers of anything going on later down the road & when there is a delay it alerts you ahead of time & how long the delay is estimated to be. So easy to use & plan trips ahead of time so you are always on time!

Why is the panning/scrolling of the map such a hideous experience?! I have a OnePlus 5T and the whole map scrolling is so scattered, jammy and ultimately just annoying. Isn't there a way to give it some extra smoothness to the touch? I really like scrolling the map in all directions sometimes and I think it shouldn't be as painful as it is. Thanks. That's my only concern, everything else is as good as it gets.

The speed zone indicator is TINY!!   Yet the instructions for the next turn (which could be 100km away is HUGE).   The screen layout doesn't tell you simply what you need to know.  The first road/location I searched for simply didn't exist.  It is a major regional road!   If this is missing, what else is??  I suspect waze is only good for urban navigation

Generally very good, but it really would benefit from a more clever routing algorithm. At the moment it optimises based solely on journey time, but it would be so much better if it had a sliding scale to allow optimisation to be based on a combination of arrival time and fuel efficiency. This would take into account junctions, gradients, regenerative braking and speed limits and would be easy to toggle (I'm usually rushing to work but more leisurely on my way home).
Great GPS with Traffic updates cop reporting and bonuses or delays and wreck on whatever route your traveling. Also has a community basis which can be used on family trips.

An app with huge potential but falls down on buggy and what seems like perpetual Alpha development. I run it on an Android in car system that displays Waze somewhat like on a tablet. It seems to behave better on a phone.  Speed cameras are randomly announced; sometimes they are and some aren't, even though they appear on screen as being present. The direction announcements are clipped short - missing the first two words of every direction given. Maps seem adhoc in there updates. Speed signs are always out of date, and in the most recent map update (for Australia at least) have regressed to no signed speed at all - even on major roads like the Gateway Highway Streets that were previously signed with a speed now have no speed sign advice at all. Registration and sign in takes me in perpetual circles. I could go on. It is a highly frustrating app. But I am hooked on its "live" reporting feature and that is the only reason I still put up with it..
Having my own voice as the GPS is both dope and freaky. The "12 radar" is a godsent.
Descent navigation app however it doesn't allow me to accumulate points anymore (I'm capped at 650) & also doesn't seem to tally the mileage I drive accurately either.
Having the same issues as others lately. I use this app daily for Lyft but the last 2 weeks app freezes, no gps connection, wrong routes. Without the problems always 5‚≠ê
replyContent:
Hey there, Steve! We're sorry to hear that this issue is occurring. We'd like to learn more about what you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app used to be great, but over the last 6 months the glitches have made it completely unreliable. I'm currently sitting in traffic for an accident that happened and was reported on Waze before I left my house. The app didn't show it until I closed it and re-ran my drive...this kind of glitch happens weekly if not daily...I just can trust the drive stats anymore. The app was great...not anymore.

This app used to be the best one 'on the market, but it's gone from hero to zero. For some reason Waze seems to think that no one should make a journey lasting more than 2 hours, and it shuts down with no warning. I recently found myself driving in the middle of nowhere, at night, with a sat nav that suddenly switched off and left me to guess where to go next

I used to love Waze, but several things began to weigh this app down compared to Google maps. 1. Can't stand the recalculating "beep". You can't disable it either. 2. I DO NOT WANT TO USE CARPOOL. I don't want my directions to be covered because I accidentally touched the wrong area. 3. Crashes or auto-shut downs because Waze thought I didn't move enough. No, I was just at a stoplight on the beginning of my drive. 4. No lane guidance. If Google maps has it, Waze should have it. No excuses for a driving app.
There is no features to put manually location instead of result search. There is no option to choose different path direction.Waze always give not the best path direction..
Fast and easy to use

I love this app. It is more accurate than my Garmin, even when I update it. Waze gives me road hazards, police locations, and construction sites if they have been reported by other Wazers (which is almost always) and lets not forget the all important detours for backed up traffic!! It's amazing. I never travel anymore without using it, thank you for such a great product!

Once it calculates the route, it runs. However multiple times I had issues at the beginning while trying to get route. E.g. If you try to set the route in an undergroung parking area where internet receiving is low or none and hope it would work when connection is better, it just freezes and never wakes up. Please use more non blocking async calls. Sometimes similar happens even when there is connection. The app just says no routes could be found. If you spend some time on it retrying, it eventually finds. So the bottom line is, similar issues do not happen in Google maps, I know because I switch to Google Maps in such cases and it just works. So it is possible to make Waze more stable and robust. Please do it.

I've used Waze for many months with no issue. Suddenly it refuses to launch and has signed me out and lost my account, with no way to recover it because there was no email address assigned to it even though there was my Google play account, phone number, and Facebook connected to it. I've now lost all my saved locations. Time to start again. My review would be 5 stars if not for how unstable the app is. (Galaxy S8)

I've never had a problem with this app. It has helped me greatly in my times of need in the past when I was moving along to new places in my life! Thanks to Waze! Also the fact that you tell me the speed limit so clearly is awesome. And the customization concerning the speed limits- the speed you're going within alerts is cool beans too!!! You can set it to alert you when your speeding a certain mph over the limit (which normally 3 or 5 over is fine!). Thanks for the great app- OnePlus 5 user.
Rediculiusly difficult to even open a new account, stuck in a constant loop of confirming email address but receiving no activation code, why so hard
replyContent:
Hey, Berty! We're sorry to hear you're having trouble creating an account. We'd like to help you with that. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Please please all Aussie driving people this is the best driving app out there completely free great and very easy to use lots of different alerts about police... I never use the gmaps never again only Waze for me I have not been pulled over by the police force for years

I prefer this app over Google Maps. I switched back to Google Maps due to one day while using this app. When I came to a stop at a red light. The ads that pops up cause the app to close somehow. I noticed after riding so long and not hearing any navigation commands. So at another red light. I checked to see if it was still running. Very disappointingly, it was not. Google is constantly gaining more of Waze features. So eventually Google Maps will be both itself and Waze. Just without ADS.
replyContent: Hi Carl, thank you for providing your review. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: No big surprise i had to uninstall this app again. It's so quick to ask questions about my car and the fuel type. But when I try to get directions it searches and than tells me the routing server timed out. I had the same issue 2 yrs ago when i got rid of the app and it hasn't changed. Worthless app. Im not sure why it says "for an older version" when i JUST downloaded it 5 mins ago. This is not a review for an older version, it's a review for the version downloaded on 12/14/18...

I used waze long enough to realize it's not for me! The fact here is simple, you should design an app to be a clean gps for fast looking with clear screen and minimum distractions or you are going to make an app to be more informative. Mixing these two in one app regardless of the few optional style to choose from the setting creates dissatisfaction. It gets even worse if you are driving a lot. If you are using it once in a while, waze will do the job but it is very far from being great.
replyContent: Hi Jay, thank you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about your app experience, please send us a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I really like the app,it actually saved my life warning me of something in the road. I also like getting police warnings because sometimes I have a heavy foot. The thing that needs improvement is when it tells you directions it says it too close to turn and I've missed it. For when it rerouting it doesn't always reroute well and makes it a much longer drive. Overall I love the app and recommend it.

Waze is probably a good app if you want a pre-planned route. But it will not allow the user to modify routes to suit individual preferences. This is unfortunate because the advantage Waze offers above Google Maps is that it relies on users to contribute current info for others to follow. Had I been able to add more than a single stop to a route, this would have been a good app for my purposes. Thus, I can only offer two stars for the app. I will not be using the app again.
replyContent: Hi Russell, thanks for your feedback. You can add a stop to your route, using these steps: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6262564?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The only complaint I have is when you type in the address you want to go to in the tab that says "where to" it gives you similar addresses to choose.  You select the one you want but here's the problem, it will tell you how many miles away it is.  Ok good, but when you click on the address you want, it pulls up a new screen with a map that will also say the street name and the same mileage.  Ok good so far.  But when you click on "Go", the actual mileage can be 8 or more miles further than the first two screens told you.  My example I did an address of a friend.  It said it was 30.0 miles away.  When I finally got to the actual turn-by-turn guidance it said the address was 38.1 miles away.

App has a great potential and is much better option for drivers compared to Google Maps. However there are still a lot of issues occurring on daily usage. For example, it can start to miss alerts for unknown reason unless restarted; arrow on the map can become permanently rotated 90 degrees to your orientation. And there seems to be no option to report an incident outside of your current position. I really hope that developers will continue improving it.
replyContent: Hey Alex, thanks for the feedback and suggestion, we‚Äôre always open to hearing feedback and will make sure to pass it along to the team. If you have any questions or additional feedback, reach out to us through Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love the app! I've used it for years since it first launched. the only thing missing is the ability to add a recurring drive and not have to save it in a calendar.. idk about everyone else, but I definitely do not need my M-F/9-5 work schedule saved in a calendar? I do need a reminder and notification to leave though since its 30 miles away and people don't know how to driveü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
Just garbage and unresponsive

shuts down too often and is no longer reliable like it used to be. too many ads and pop ups. It's textbook distracted driving Even the pop up road reports are distracting. to return to an unobstructed, full view of the map, you have to tap on the screen a thumbs up or that red button. terrible for remaining focused on the road. why is this even legal? The map needs to remain in full screen mode. Put the ads at the bottom. put the reports at the bottom.
Don't drive anywhere without first using Waze
Best car navigation app by a mile

I used to love this app. It's very frustrating to use now. It regularly cannot connect to or locate GPS. It's not updating with shorter routes fast enough or at all. I usually have to reset where I want to go for it to find the better route when, based on road signs, I know there's a better option. It's only sometimes accurate with arrival times. Since it's not finding better options there's constant delays popping. Please stop the ads that take up the majority of the screen. The only thing I appreciate about the app is the warnings people can add. It's the only positive at this point. I won't be recommending anymore.

Love the interface, love the features. However... sometimes it doesn't know that roads exist when Google Maps does. It also sometimes sends me to the side of the motorway or similar, as if I'm supposed to scale a fence at the back of a business address. I love it but i can't trust it, I'm often checking the overview and zooming in to the final destination to make sure before setting off.

Used to love this app. And used it every day. Now, I get " no network connection" 90% of the time. I thought might be my phone but google maps works fine. Waze, please fix these issues soon as I love your app, but I have to have it working. Soon I'll have to begin looking for another app to use as I dont like the layout and features of google maps. *update. No connection 100% of the time. Uninstalled.

Love it! Not only has it gotten me to some pretty tough destinations, it had kept me from being stopped by police. I am a pretty aggressive (but safe) driver. My input has also helped other drivers. Another important item is its knowledge of accidents ahead and redirects my route to keep me from getting involved in timely traffic jams caused there from. Rarely drive without it, even if I know my route. Randy (the voice option I have chosen) have become close friends :)

I use this app DAILY because I have a ridiculous commute and I depend on Waze to give me the mose efficient route. Lately, the app has been closing on it's own. I put the phone down after looking at the initial route...and then I realize it hasn't talked in a while, only to find out the app has somehow closed. This is starting to happen everyday, I almost missed a change in the route because the app had shut down.

It WAS awesome. I have had it for years. But here recently it has started to give false information. When I put in an address as I am approaching my destination and it tells me "you have arrived" but it's still a good half a mile away from where I am going. I will try to uninstall and reinstall to see if that will fix them problem. I uninstalled and reinstalled and it was worse. This app is now useless.
replyContent: Hi Marcelo, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: For some reason it started to randomly misplacing me. I am driving along and it would just freeze. It would take from a few seconds to a couple of minutes to catch up. This caused me to miss a turn and revert to Google Maps. I do like the warnings, but I wish you could edit which warnings it alerts to. I also like that the voice is much more succinct than Google. I don't want a novel telling me where to turn. The lagging issue is why I take points off. If it doesn't know where I am, useless.

I have to take long commute, every morning. I've always hated highway drivingüöòüöò But this application, makes it a breeze. No more worries about what might be ahead on the road. This app. Will pinpoint anything that might be in the line of driving, it's already proved it's worth by alerting me about an obstruction up ahead. Thankfully I was able to avoid it. As for the patrols out in force Waze will give you a Heads Up, as to where their hiding. Great Job

Great for so long but recently, it's unusable. It struggles to calculate routes, and to find a GPS signal, resets mid-route, crashes constantly and now the directions seem to be losing accuracy. By comparison using Google maps, I don't encounter any of those issues. Even had both maps running concurrently on different phones in the same car and G was flawless. Sorry Waze, was a fan for so long but we've fallen out of love

Great when it works but bug ridden. Keeps crashing , usually about 3 to 4 times on a 280 mile trip. Notifications often don't sound so unless you are looking at the screen you won't see them. Doesn't always auto reroute, if the manually select to look at the routes often there is a quicker one. Seems to be getting worse and more unreliable as an app.

Used to be amazing but doesn't find my GPS location properly anymore, not even when I'm standing still. If it does, I need to wait 10+ minutes while standing still and then it still often loses the signal while driving. EDIT 6/4/2020: Kept the app for it's "Tell me to leave" but doesn't work anymore either. I cannot insert a starting point other than "your location". It wants to have location access all the time. Not going to happen.
replyContent:
Hi Sophie, we‚Äôre disappointed to hear about your constant GPS issue with the app. Have you checked the location services on your device yet? Here‚Äôs how: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6083679?hl=en

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Super long routes. I entered my home and work information (a trip that usually takes me 43 minutes with Google Maps) said that it was going to take 1 hour and 3 minutes with Waze. I'm sorry, but you want an extra 20 minutes of time and gas? No thank you. A lot of the features were really cool.
