I especially liked the planning feature to help manage my mornings and the police reporting feature so I know to stop going 70 down the interstate haha. Could've been a really cool app. I see the appeal.
replyContent: Hi Xander, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app is very inconsistent. Today, despite not telling the app that I am exempt (I am not), it sent me through the congestion charge. I cannot believe it. Let alone all the times it changes directoon at the very last second, like as you are turning it then says go another way. And the times when you ignore the direction it gives you, and the alternative that you took is actually quicker (and the app knows this, because as soon as I ignore it and take another route it calculates the length of time accordingly, displaying the fact that it won't take as long as its own designated route). I am amazed this app is so well reviewed. Maybe people review it too soon, when nothing has yet gone wrong? Use it for at least 6 months before leaving a review.
Gives the ways even you not familiar where you going. But sometimes it gives you far directions than normal route
Toilets app. Useless. Google maps more good to use
The new update doesn't work üòï, How can I back to previous üò´

The app is great! But it has a super busy design which can be a bit hard to use or distracting while driving. There are so many features that pop up on the screen or ads that slide down while at stop lights that it puts me off the app. Also, there is something about how it is designed that at certain times it's hard to tell on the map if if it is time to turn as compared to Google maps I've never had that problem. Using waze voice control sucks. Overall great features, but has some downsides.

Was a good app...but the lastest update lost the lock North up function o the map. Very annoying and now unusable. Having to touch that small compass all the time while driving is not necessarily the safest move. Why dod this go away??? Also cannot stop navigation. It seems the only way to do that is to shut down the app and open it up again. Then select no to resume navigation. That is rather annoying. When you send updates please do not "take away" features.

Used Waze ever since they created the app. last year, extremely dissapointed. Constant crashing, having to restart my phone to bring the app up after a crash without it being a black screen. Many times saying there is no network when there clearly was. Not being able to use the maps after a crash until I am able to get service. Hardly any selection of voices. Used to be I used this app for everything, loved it showed me the speed limits. But now the constant crashing is too much. I use maps now.

Even after the update, it still does not tell you to exit before the detected traffic. You can save me half an hour every week if you could tell me to exit 20 seconds earlier. What's up with that? I'm pretty sure Waze used to tell you to exit before heavy traffic. Now it does not. Maybe the update was supposed to fix this, yet the bug remains.

The full-screen ads that require a click to dismiss have ruined a practically 5-star app. Can't interact with the app's functions while the car is in motion unless you're "a passenger" - but they don't mind covering your directions/map with popups. 4 in a 15-minute drive last week? Nope. It's also frustrating that the app will "get stuck" on the last location it knew me to be at and try to navigate my next route from there. No obvious fix except to open/close/wait/repeat. Or use a different app.

Doesn't learn or provide the fastest route anymore. I drive the same way to work every day, which uses a toll road. I have driven this same route for over a year now. The 3 options it gives are surface streets and feeders that take 20 minutes longer and are similar mileage or another toll road that is 15 miles further and takes 10 additional minutes than the route I take. I just want an accurate eta and traffic before I leave my house, but no. Get it together, you used to be better than this.

Cannot login. I have used this apps for several months. Got longed out with the last update. When I try to login now it says my account is lost. This with when I tried to help update the map to make the sevice better I was told I could not edit the location. It worked better then Google maps but it not working as good now. I guess I will go back to using Google Maps at least until the issues are fixed.
Getting worse day by day. Sometimes crushed, cannot detect gps, and not telling the alternative routes as it should be. UNINSTALL!!
replyContent:
Hey there! We're sorry to hear that these issues are occurring. We'd like to learn more about what you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great for around town I suppose, but the app crashes every 20-50 miles on long trips. Also... Want to report a roadside hazard? Nope. Crash. Oh hey, a new, faster route. Great. Let's check it out. Nope. Crash. Now you've restarted the app, re-entered the route, and just missed your turn. Tbh, if Google Maps showed police there would be no need for Waze.

Right now I'm pretty unhappy with Waze. It's gotten awfully buggy lately. Fortunately my husband was able to keep restarting it when it stopped working or crashed on our trip today. At one point it kept warning of terrible traffic up ahead, but there was none. It even tried to reroute us, but then seemed to forget that it did. Fortunately I knew my way and was just using Waze for timing, miles and police notifications. We eventually gave up and used Google Maps.

I don't know what happened in the past couple of months, but now Waze routinely crashes or freezes during trips. It's done this on multiple phones on multiple trips longer than an hour. Worse, it dies silently, with no error message, so I'll be driving along expecting directions only to realize I don't have any. Even worse, it's done it in areas where I had no reception, so I couldn't get new directions! I have no use for a nav app that crashes and strands me. Bye Waze!

I'm not sure what happened but just recent ly when using my Pixel 2XL with Android Auto it continues to show alerts on my phone. This is even after a full device reset. The problem is that it prevents the user from being able to listen to any streaming service because it continues to pause/mute the sound because of the continuous alerts. I have had to go back to Google Maps. Please fix!

I genuinely love this app! I choose this app over my Google Maps and phone GPS all the time! I love all the features on it, police tracker, the fact that you can see other ways users, and many more useful features too many to list lol! The one and only thing that I can think that I would like to see added is for background music be allowed to add Pandora or music playlist from your phone rather than just Spotify. Other than that thank you ways Creator this app is amazing!
Many times tagging to wrong location

Point blank it pretty much spot on. I have been using it for a little over a month now and it has put me at the front door every time. Appears to be a little more accurate than Garmin. Sometimes the adds get a little annoying however. All in all I really l8ke it. My wife likes it because if you make a wrong turn you do not hear RECALCULATING. That was a little annoying I admit. From potholes to police cars and stalled cars on the side of the road. Give it a strong four plus.

I was really enjoying this app and then the "add a stop" stopped working. Now when I add a stop it replaces my entire original destination. I have tried doing it through the add a stop button within the original destination and through hitting search. No luck. When it was working it would not allow more than 1 additional stop in the current trip. If this gets fixed I will change my rating.

I really like this app. It is accurate and clear to use. There is one suggestion I want to mention. After I drop down music section to go to next music, the section occupies half of my screen. I wish the app could close the section by itself after 10 sec without people touching it. So, I don't need to click one more time to get a full view map.

It's a good app, but my only issue is that it loses my Waze friends. I would try to find a specific person and they would not show up. I had a list of people I know use the app but when I go to find my friends it always pulls up inviting someone or come back later yout Facebook friends will show here,but they never do. When it does it's not all of them.

Used Wase for the first time yesterday. Was recommended by store employee when we stopped to get fuel. The traffic alerts are real time including cars stalled on side of road, police radar checking, accidents & slow or stopped traffic. You can add your reports as you go. It also gives you alternate routes to get around stalled traffic. We actually added an accident after we saw it happen, stopped to help & called 911. I am definitely recommending this to everyone. Thanks Wase!!!!

The Waze navigation app is a whole lot better than the regular one. The regular one that's more often used either wouldn't start when I'm driving or it usually takes me to the back of the designated locations! Waze tells me soon after turning it on. And it takes me on the back roads and not the freeways, which I like better.

App is ok, generally works well for the most part but for some reason always tries to send me the long way home instead of the quicker and more direct route. Fails to connect to iHeart radio, would be good if I could also access my own music on my phone instead of relying on streaming apps. Also fails to record my rides and therefore I am unable to access any of the reward content (mood icons etc). Over all ok at best, with some disappointments
This app is not as good as it used to be. It always takes me through alleys instead of the front of the destination. It also changes directions while you're driving.
replyContent:
Hey there, Giselle! If you're experiencing problems with routing, we'd love to help you with that. Would you mind submitting more information about this issue here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Difficult to use. Make my phone lag. It give the longest way to the destination. This app have a lot of problem. Fix it!

This app no longer works on iPhones. It is inaccurate and iffy. It was awesome when it cam out, but now it sucks bowling balls. I've gotten lost and wandered for hours trying to get the damn thing to work. The Apple genius bar guys said they couldn't get it to work and that they had "tons" of people who had the same problem. It's worthless.

The first time i used Waze was around 2 years ago and it led me to a random and dead end route. So Disappointed. Second time I used it was today and it was horrible. Calculate the fastest route but it was the longest route to the destination. A 30 minute estimated driving becomes 2.5 hours of driving. Google map is so much better compared to Waze. The only thing that is good about Waze was the notifications but, not the route options. Still dissapointed with this app after 2 years.

I've used the app for several years and generally liked it, but lately it feels like it sometimes routes me down random streets just to check road conditions. Twice in the past 30 days it's sent me on a route where traffic wasn't moving...as soon as I went the way it indicated, my ETA jumped by 10-20 minutes. Today the directions indicated one route and the map indicated another- by the time it clarified which I needed to take, I'd missed my exit. I like Waze, but lately it's caused frustration.

This navigation app is the worst of the worst ever. Used to be very good, but now all it does is bring you to the longest route with the longest duration. Totally not worth your wifi or internet data to download this app. Just go for another navigation app out there. Could not recognise an easier route for a destination, instead showed a lengthy old and abandoned route. Stay away from this app. Recommendation: ZERO!

I use to love Waze and use it every day to get to work, despite knowing HOW to get there on my own. Since the latest update, Waze does not work with Android Auto. It consistently tells me there is no network, tries to calculate the route for several minutes, or completely crashes. I was looking forward to using Waze for an over 3,000 mile solo road trip I am currently on. Unfortunately, I had to switch to a different GPS application that works with Android Auto.

I love this app. This is by far the best GPS app that I've ever used. The only problem that I ever have when I first turn on the app it takes about 10 minutes before it gets my location right. Usually has me about five or six miles off from where I actually am. Usually this isn't a problem, but sometimes it's a real big problem. But other than that the app is great. It's saved me a ton and tickets Thank you. If there's anything I can do to fix my location problem please let me know

Previous versions (1 year ago) gave bad directions (strange routes on well traveled roads) as some others have described. I stopped using Waze for this unreliable behavior. Decide to give it another chance with latest version. Waze is unable to find a route to towns that are on major highways but is able to find a route to a town 40 miles from that one. Looks like its good-bye Waze.

I like this app because it provide lots of live updates, speedometer, and re-route to avoid traffic. Although it would be a 5 if, it include a view in which lane you need to be, especially when getting close to the destination, and also never crash when using it. Fortunately it crashed in multiple occasions creating confusion.

Love the app, it's easy to use and wonderfully smart. The navigation voices are nice and smooth (except Simon who becomes a demon when he announces an average speed zone). The integration with Spotify is nice but I'd like to be able to like songs from Waze. I'd also prefer if the app didn't automatically take me on a 20km route for a 5km trip, if there's a small delay or slightly more traffic lights I'd really rather take that over wasting petrol.

I love this app. I use it 10 years and it is great. 3 things I would like to suggest: 1. Can you give option for RV or trucks routes? Some roads are not for trucks and RVs. 2. Can you update the app for iPhones and Android the same time? 3. When we carpooling, it would be nice if we can put all addresses and Waze will tell us which is the best and most efficient route to go by. Thank you ‚ô°

One route available from Indianapolis to Denver; they wanted me to take 80 through Nebraska not a single alternate route option was listed. I was sure to check if "avoid tolls" was ticked (it wasn't), and I ticked then unticked just to be sure. Still only the route through Nebraska was offered. To further my pain, the estimated time of arrival is shown in the wrong time zone (this happened there *and* back). It's a known issue that has caused MANY people to miss their flights. This app has caused me so many problems over and over again. I keep trying to give it another chance, but I am uninstalling now. EDIT: The "we want to help" response is BS. Any person who uses Waze to travel from one time zone to another can easily see that the ETA is given in the WRONG TIME ZONE (ETA is given in current time zone instead of arrival time zone). This has been an issue for years! And in regard to "replicating the suggested route" issue... good luck getting Waze to do the same thing twice! It's all over the place. I'm done with it.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out to us. We'd like to hear more about the routing and ETA issues you've experienced to investigate further. If you‚Äôre still seeking help, please fill out our support form here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It works fine, but I have 2 issues: The contacts on my phone don't show up, which it did in a previous version - that's seriously annoying... It also puts a massive strain on the battery, which always overheats after about 15 minutes, no matter the temperature in my car. But please please PLEASE fix the contacts!!!!!!!
After the update it gives me ridiculous routes that don't make sense. A shame what was done to the app. I don't trust it anymore and neither should you.

Waze used to be the best app. However since a few weeks i don't know what happened, but the routes are terrible. A 15 minute trip is 30 mins or more now because waze takes a touristic route. I have seen parts of my city that I have never seen before. And I don't like it! I removed the app...if you somehow fix it i consider to install it again, but for now i am done.

Excellent... when it works. This little Sat-Nav really is a godsend, hundreds of thousands of uk users who regularlly update any and all issues on the road, including traffic, accidents, roadworks, closures, hazards onroad, and those cheeky hidden speed vans, (who are clearly only there for our safety and not as a revenue stream nudge nudge wink wink). However recently it has really been struggling with the dreaded "Searching for Network" error, which is fine if it already has the route and that part of the map cached offline, you lose all but the most basic functionality including voice directions, but the route still shows on screen. However if that particular location isn't already cached you are SOL, e.g. last night I drove 55 miles to a location at 4pm, no issues, full connectivity, driving home at 11:30 (same route, other side of road) still 4g connection most of the way, "Searching for network" the whole way home, including when connected to the WiFi outside my house, so clearly an issue on their end not mine.

In general, this app works very well.  I like that it is real time and includes updates from other drivers making it more effective.  It does have a few problems. 1. It is often off by 25-100 feet and many times it has said "Turn right (left)" just as I pass the street.  This is more of a problem in areas with streets that are close together (e.g., residential) and that don't have clear street signs.  I've also done the opposite by taking the earlier street knowing that the distance is sometimes off.  2. It keeps telling me to turn right on my own street (Drake Ln, Ledgewood NJ) and take the long way around the circle.  3. Sometimes it says "stay right/left" when it just really means don't exit (duh!)  4. Sometimes it doesn't say "stay right/left" when it needs to on a road that forks and it is unclear which side is which road (again, lack of street signs in many areas makes it confusing).
Easy to use and understand. I also enjoy the temporary novelty voices Waze occasionally has. Elvis was my favorite followed by Cookie Monster.
Useful and reliable

Review is for Android Auto integration. Automatically selects destination below chosen option. Doesn't ask to confirm, so you think you are going to the destination you picked. I ended up an hour off course the first time. Luckily caught it the second time. This makes the app unusable. Should display more information about the destination at minimum as well as ask for conformation to prevent such mistakes.

I had been using Google maps on my Samsung 8+ and was very frustrated with Google maps always misdirecting me wherever I wanted to go. I found Waze and installed it! This is a great app! It never misdirects me! it gives me several routing options! And stores a history of places I've been. It always me to delete places in the history that I don't need to keep! I give this app a 200% !!! rating

I have been fighting and fighting to get waze to do basic things like keep track of where I work and live, and it never misses an excuse to forget. It went into an endless wait when I tried to change my password, and it won't send a code for me to log in again. It gave me a message about keyboard disabled while driving when I was sitting in my office too.

I enjoy using the waze app EVERYDAY. I use for work or just for everyday use. I love üíò the features that come with it such as letting me know if there's heavy traffic, accidents, vehicles pulled on the shoulder or nearby police. I can also set the time to inform me what time is the best time to leave my house to arrive at my destination on time. Wonderful features and more.

Such an intuitive app that has lousy optimization. I've always been back and forth with this app because it tends to eat my battery like none other. I'm still giving this a shot, but it's not looking very promising yet. And this is coming from a 3 year user (on and off). Google Maps doesn't drain nearly as much if you're trying to be comparable.
I don't what's happened seen last year doesn't working?
replyContent: Hi Yonas, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this app issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Perfect app and a big race with google maps Waze its nice app for map But there is some bugs

I've never had to give an app a 1 star rating, however, Waze has demonstrated that it's so unreliable that it's unusable. I have a new phone running the latest version of Android. The latest Waze update constantly lost track of where I was on the road, and was constantly restarting itself. Today, Waze crashed and burned so bad it rebooted my phone while I was driving. When my phone recovered, Waze said it hadn't been set up. After getting home, I tried to log in to my account, only to find out that the Waze servers don't recognize my number, AGAIN. I've had to create three different accounts since Waze refuses to recognize my account, and I'm not doing it again. Enough of this b******t. Fix the damned thing.

I like the app and its functions. there is one thing that I am still trying to get use to - determine the distance of up coming turn. it's not as easy as Germin to determine the intersection of next turn. July 7 2019 update: lowered the rating to 1 star because I constantly received "Routing Server Timeout" message during my recent 2 trips. Made it useless. Unibstalled.

User interface takes some time to master. Not very intuitive. Like most apps and devices, it has option to AVOID interstates & highways. Other than toll roads do people actually use that? It really needs an option to PREFER highways, so you are not constantly sent off exits to two lane roads, traffic light intersections, and low speed limits through towns - Ugh. Otherwise, this app is OK.
Since the last update, horrible app, always loosing location and map keeps turning into circles
replyContent:
We're sorry to hear you've been experiencing issues with Waze, Victor! It looks like this issue has been resolved and things should be running smoothly in our next version release. Please be sure to download the next version once it is available in the google play store.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: VERY UNRELIABLE and pretty useless. Went back to using Maps. "Plan a drive" feature that is supposed to load travel time estimates for future days almost never loads, the voice command feature "processes" my request but doesn't actually DO anything, and overall, it is laggy and struggles to connect to GPS upon start up. Restarting and re-downloading proved useless; just like this app. It was once reliable enough; a year ago (2018). Now? (2019). NO.

The App crashes a lot. Has very poor search capabilities compared to Google maps. It takes too many clicks to share objects on road and speed traps. lots of ads. The only reason I liked this app was that you could share with fellow users what the road conditions were. Now they added a block that prevents you from reporting road conditions/speed traps etc if they don't agree (some type of automation). I will dump this app and will no longer recommend its use if that isn't fixed quickly....

My single and only negative thing to say is how its last minute reroutes/notifies me of a direction change. I'm not sure why it does this. At first I thought my phone was the issue but once I saw the same situation on two other wazers phones while they navigated with me in the vehicle, I saw k was wrong. It's a Shame that it has this glitch every so often because other than that, this app is by far my favorite to use all the time, I love the fact that I can always see the speed limit even when theres not any for miles

This app used to work until I bought a new car and tried using it, but then I had to download android auto and then the problems started. The app freezes and works sporadically and that's not good when you're lost. Where are the fixes or updates?   I've deleted and reinstalled the app several times, but it still isn't working properly.    David Smith

I never liked it because of the experience basically being social media with a map in the background. But I kept it around because of the more aggressive traffic avoidance routing algorithm. But now they have implemented large ads on top of the map whenever the car is stopped. And in side-by-side tests with Google Maps, Waze is consistently less accurate on time as well. Now that Google Maps has user reports there is no reason to keep Waze around.

I like the notification about police ahead. I have avoided many freeway traffic jams by checking routes before I leave. I also like the best time to leave feature. It is somewhat problematic when there are 2 routes in a neighborhood as it often selects the longest route. It is best to check alternate routes if you are not familiar with where you are.
Stupid Waze Giving Wrong Direction... So many Roads are closed since few months. Still giving direction...
replyContent:
Hey there! If you've encountered an issue with the maps, we're happy to look into that to get everything corrected. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook with more details about this issue?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Garbage app. The directions you get from the audio are always last minute and will say to turn right when you are supposed to turn left. I thought I was going crazy at first, but after focusing on it I can honestly say that 1/20 directions will tell you to turn the wrong way. On top of that, the automatically changing routes will drive you nuts if you are anything like me. I dont want to think I'm taking one route and then end up on a street I wasnt expecting to take.

I love the Waze app. It's been very helpful on my business trip to a large city that I'm unfamiliar with. I drive roughly a 150 miles a day back and forth from where I am staying to my job location. It gives great options for traffic,slowdowns / wait times . The arrive on time feature does not always work well for the city I am in traffic is heavier than the app allows for .The two improvements that I would like to see is a 3D version that shines on the window at night when you drive I use that in a different app and it was very helpful. Also I would like for the app to pause the Spotify when the directions come on so that podcast and or songs are not missed. üòÅ

Totally wish it would work as described, it definitely doesn't. Using it in the Nation's Capital, it never gives me proper updates or routes. I am constantly suprised by traffic I can see, and it then tells me it's ahead. It also can't tell major route choices...as I come up upon a huge interstate, it doesn't give me an option for it, just the road I'm currently on. Only fairly useful thing is knowing where Police are, & who gives a hoot about every disabled vehicle, yet my song quiets every time

Is it possible to have an audio notification when GPS is lost?  I had this issue (no idea why my phone dropped the signal) and as I was not constantly looking at the screen I did not realize I had lost the signal until I was obviously on an incorrect route.  The notification could be activated after a set time (one minute?) of lost GPS signal to allow for momentary loss situations.

I really wanted to like this app because of the reviews I'd heard and read, but I've been nothing but disappointed so far. 1. It seems very unstable and unexpectedly crashes, which causes it to quite inconvenient. 2. It causes my phone to overheat which then causes the app t lag. 3. I can't tell if the ETA calculates the time zone difference. I used another GPS app (which clearly indicates that there's a time zone change) and got a difference in ETA of about 1hr 20min- that's a pretty significant esp. when calculating travel time. 4. It won't register some of profile/settings changes.

This is a great app overall for when I'm driving around and need to take a detour from my route. My only real complaint is that my notification settings get reset to the default on every single update. It's really annoying when I'm driving and I have an alert for something I don't want to know about come up because the app updated recently. It does this..every single time. Please fix that so the update keeps the settings we have from the previous version then I'll consider giving it 5 stars.

Used to use this a lot and got away from it for a bit. Not happy with current version. Don't know if you can still install custom voices but settings aren't intuitive. Also, more apps need to learn this basic concept: aggressively pushing spotify on me (every time i come back to the window i get two pop ups) won't get me to link spotify. It will get me to stop using your app and theirs.

App works fine, but it is made that you do all your trip plan before you sit in the car. When I try to use it on the fly (e.g. I smell a traffic jam and I would like to check if there is a better route) it is soooo many clicks to get to the suggested route, it is almost ridiculous! I even have to disconnect it from the car to choose destination and connect it again.

This app was really good. The voice guide is accurate and usefully tells me which side of the road to be on for tricky one way systems etc. I would have given 5 stars but recently it has started crashing and so I have to stop mid drive and restart my phone and re-enter my destination. Irritating! Even worse, now after having reinstalled waze they require my contact list. Why? I'm going elsewhere.
I like it, hopefully they'll keep adding newer upgrades.

I've been using Waze for years, however the last few updates are broken and have led to the app crashing around 10 minutes away from the destination, typically at a critical point where having the directions is super important. Not sure why it's been doing this, but this has persisted through two phones. Hopefully this gets fixed, as Waze used to be the best GPS app out there.

So I have always been obsessed with waze and have always recommended it to friends and family. I am also VERY happy to see that waze actually listens to the reviews. I really like how it extended past 100 miles since I travel long distance all the time AND that it calls the states out when you pass them. Sometimes that's all the encouragement you need to keep going on that last leg of travel. I would love a pop up on the screen. I am one of those ones who like to screenshot when I cross state lines and I'm sure with Waze it would be catchy and cute. Thanks for making an awesome product.

I just updated and seemed to have misplaced the "prevent auto zoom" option. I find it annoying when it auto zooms at intersections. I don't need that and would like to disable it. I also wonder if my postings for cops on the opposite side of the road actually get sent. The app doesn't show the symbol. other than that, this is a great app and I rely on it more every day. I drive about 50,000 miles a year in my car and use this every mile.

Hi Waze, great app but a couple of features let you down. 1, it would be good if there was a "free driving mode" where there was no programed route but it still came up with camera warnings etc. 2, an audible speed warning, I'm on a motorcycle and looking at the screen for the speed is too hard, but having the choice of a voice warning "speeding" or a "beep": on once, on every 5 sec, off - this would be awesome to help avoid those speed tickets. 3, the option to turn on constant routing.

This is the best navigation app, i drive for work and generally love driving so i do it a lot and this app is just amazing at how helpful it is at tracking traffic, finding the best route, tell you if you're going to have to pay tolls, rerouting you if traffic is building up ahead and it's also super accurate at doing all of that. This app is so good that it is one of the very few pieces of software in the world that i'd pay for if it ever went to a subscription based plan!

Convenient. Accurate. A True Know-It-All. I appreciate the recalculation to avoid the delays I can not see ahead. I would like an option for audible directions to come sooner, particularly with regard to areas where multiple exits and on-ramps are present. I can see the path, but, remember, I am not looking at my phone shut operating in another app that minimizes the Waze visual. When I get to such territory, I want the option to hear directions multiple times.

I have been using this Waze app on Android devices for a few years now. It works great for most of the time, however.... my main concern is with the built in premium Spotify floating widget icon. It deffenilty has a mind of it's own. I have LTE+ data coverage 90% during the day and I find it doesn't want to appear in the top right corner as where it should be. I checked my settings and made sure that the Spotify icon is check marked as well. Soft restarted my device daliy as well. To the devs; What could be causing the Spotify widget to act up like this?
Is very good app and easy to use

It doesn't even matter if this app gives you decent routes at this point- it's incessant pop-up ads telling you to go to starbucks, Mcdonalds or any other myriad of fast food places are down right dangerous. These banners pop down from the top, block your view of your route, and facilitates distracted driving because you a) are drawn to look at it and b) you have to touch the screen to get rid of it- especially annoying if you are coming up to your turn and have to scramble to swipe the screen.
replyContent: Hi Rae, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit the changes you wish to see regarding the display of ads in the app to Waze's suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Sorry but Google maps is far better. First, no matter what I did in the settings, voice does not work! Contacted customer support, tried everything they said,still nothing. I am using on a brand new LG V40 phone. Second, using it on my home from work just to try it out, the directions were totally wrong. Tried to put me on local roads with lights, and longer distance than my normal much faster route!. If you obey local speed limits, knowing where police are hiding is no reason to use this app.

I've been a Waze user for years, and I love it. However, within the past few weeks the app has become unusable. When using it with Android Auto, it constantly will lose my location and just replace the arrow with a dot on the map that usually is not on the road I'm on. I've cleared the cache and data, reinstalled Waze, but nothing works. It's definitely the app though as Google maps works fine. For now, even though I prefer Waze, I'm using Google maps since that works.
I do not like the pop up adds when driving. I understand this is your source of income. Would like to be able to X the add to close or close by voice

A little messy to use... Needs to be more simple and clear... My problem is that when im free driving without a dedtination entered the car info text is shown on the bottom instead of the car icon... Also i want to check gas prices when i want, not when the app suggests. I cant find either button for free nav. or near gas prices.. also would be nice if you could allow people to request free lifts to drivers that allow it. I mean what is the difference with private and taxi mode? I cant figure these thinngs out. 5 stars when explained or and fixed. Thanks for this great nav. app! Great job! Love it !

Used to be a good GPS app, now it just crashes and freezes a lot. Now when ever I type in an address it no longer gives me the correct ETA nor does it tell me if there is any traffic, accidents, road construction etc etc it just gives me a clear shot to my destination like if there is nothing to worry about along the way. WRONG! Used to be good, used to recommend this app, now it just sucks. Dont download it, wasting your time. Straight up!

This was decent when i first stared using this but as with all free apps, ads destroy it. Apart from the regular crashing (even when I'm not using the app) I've had ads appear at the most inopportune times, such as navigating a busy and major roundabout and then being asked for a coffee from the local coffee shop covering the essential directions, or asking you of you want to change the icon for the vehicle. Both distracting you from safely driving and is a nuisance. Shame...
Please bring back the normal reach, & remove this so called mywaze it's horrible
replyContent:
Hey there, Mahmoud! If you'd like to request changes and/or updates to Waze, feel free to leave us a note in our suggestion box for further consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app but has some major problems, it crashes alot, always loses connection even when I'm full service 4glte. The plan a route feature doesn't work most of the time. It would get 4.5 stars of it didn't have these issues, the routing is good, don't really understand why it has houses for sale on the map thats a waste of resources when navigation parts are not working.

Waze is a great product, but today for whatever reason, the language has changed to a forien language that I do not understand, I can't change it back because all the symbols have changed.. It's really messing up my day and work schedule. Please help, you don't have any phone number listed which I think is unfair to the users of the app. Please email me or call, your directions are not clear because it's in a different language other the English, further more this should be a lock on this option
replyContent:
Hi Matthew, thanks for your feedback and reaching out for assistance. We'd love to assist you in detail with changing back the language to English. To do so, please send us a private message on Facebook. We look forward to helping with you.
 
For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Absolutely love Waze! I love that users can update traffic info, so you're getting up to the minute alerts. Arrival times are very accurate and chang based on flow of traffic and potential hazards or events reported. I also appreciate the options/hazards you can report and the app connection to music apps!! The only thing I wish it could to is stay "pinned" at the top of the screen, even if you click out of the app.
Terrible, worst app to be honest. It make no sense, shows you to a way more far route. Also not a friendly apps. I'm uninstalling. #isrealterrorist #koyak #shameonyouandyourancestor #yourfathershead
An absolute must on a trip.

Got stuck in traffic and my phone died. Discovered I'm lost without Waze. It's so much more accurate than my car's GPS. Would be nice if it were easier to choose from different paths. Sometimes I don't want to get on the Hwy for example. Also has a bit more going on the screen than I like. I'm guessing those people pay to have their business pop up but it gets in the way of my map sometimes.

I really love this app, but there are a few MAJOR flaws. When a road is closed, and I'm trying to submit a report to the app, more often than not the particular roadI want to mark as closed is unable to be marked as closed. I should be able to tap on any road in the area but the appropriate arrows aren't available on certain roads. The other major problem is the ads. They're supposed to only pop up when the car is stopped, which is bad enough, but recently an ad popped up while I was in a tunnel because the GPS was indicating that I want moving. This is DANGEROUS in a mapping app. Please remove ads entirely. Another problem, less critical but still bad, is sometimes it tells me a certain destination is in a tunnel, when any human can tell you there will never be a destination in the tunnel. The destination is actually on a different road on the surface. It should be easy to program the app to not make this error.

This used to be a great app to find your navigation to destinations. Ever since I updated it, it completely messes up and sends me the wrong way. Re-downloaded it and installed back on to my phone and now it doesn't even recognize my email. Completely useless. Really disappointing because it does have great features as in showing police, traffic, and alternate routes to where you're going. Now moving on to mapquest as if I'm back in the year 2007. Thanks waze, fix your app.
replyContent: Hi Hannah, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about your email and routing issues to investigate further. To best assist, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Good app but the red light traffic camera notification is incredibly annoying and I can't turn it off. It takes up a portion of the map at the top of the screen and I have to click it to get rid of it, not a good idea while driving! If u run a red light that's my problem, I don't think it's necessary for you to tell me so please remove this and let me see the whole screen! Also, a paid version would be great as I'm sick to death of seeing adverts while I'm at a stop light, again, I have to click the screen to get rid of them and I'd rather see the map to know where I'm going after the light turns green.

always crashes or freezes. doesn't notify of speed traps until it's too late. heavy traffic isn't accurate. it'd be nice if there was an option of why the car is pulled over. example: if my car got a flat I can update this info & a good samaritan would see I need a simple tire change & they can pull over to help. but if it's a blown engine nobody can fix this on the roadside.

Best navigation.. EVER!! Notifies ahead of time that there's a cop ahead or vehicle along side the road or object in the road though it does not tell you which side of the road a vehicle is stopped on but the heads up so you are aware is awesome!! Definitely my go to app for navigation!! No hesitation to get in the vehicle and just go.. I know waze will make sure I arrive at any destination I choose!! Amazing job developers!! Thank you!! üòä
Not accurate always make problem even on city never use it againn
This is my motto. Wise is more truthful than God and the Prophet And In my opinion, this program is one of the highest apps in the world
Doesn't work! Just keeps saying "something went wrong try again." Close, clear, reopen does nothing. What's wrong with this app??
replyContent: Hi there, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is great!!
This app used to be much better. Recently I am noticing many bugs. While other GPS and Map apps improving, Waze is going backwards.
replyContent:
Hey there, Jacob! We're sorry to hear that this issue is occurring. We'd like to learn more about what you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I was going to submit a report via Waze itself but even that process is questionable. Where to start? Don't use this if you don't know where you're going - for some reason the actual place you want to go is return dead last in the results list and doesn't actually mean where you want to go. The app launches in day view even at night and takes a good 5 or more seconds to switch to dark mode, blinding you in the process. Recent update has killed the overview function. I've run out of room to whinge

Uery disappointing. Doesn't allow for course option. I wanted to take a specific route and once I started on that course, it continously directed me back to the app's chosen route. It should recognize the alternate route and course correct. Luckily I could figure it out on my own. It would also be helpful if the app had the ability to save routes. Learn. Turned off Waze.
replyContent: Hi there! We're sorry to hear about your bad experience. If you send us the route details, we'd be happy to look into the issue further. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I used to really love this app but now the location detection is all out of whack. And it is not my phone because Google maps works perfectly. But this app shows me to be facing opposite directions than what I'm actually travelling and also can't even determine the correct street I'm on. I'm not sure what happened but at this point it is absolutely garbage.
Pretty good but has too many limitation for someone on the go who has to plan ahead. Checking an alternate starting point has too many limitations.
replyContent: Hi Jerry, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app ideas you have for sudden driving plan changes on the go to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Worked great until last couple weeks! Says no network connection, even when I can play music or use Google maps. Screen doesn't work with Android Auto. If I try to search, it endlessly cycles until I cancel. Seeing all of the other reviews, it's extra disappointing that this hasn't been addressed yet. It did start working one day and then stopped when I had only a vague idea of where I was. One more week and I will uninstall forever. If it's not reliable, I will use something else.

I'm having the same problems many others mention, following recent updates. The app will lose where you are and which way you are driving, even when the phone has a GPS signal. It is unable to extrapolate which way you are heading when the GPS signal is lost (an issue when you live in a mountainous region with lots of tunnels!). The arrow will face the wrong way, then become a spot, then the map rotates so north is at the top, usually meaning you cant's see your route properly any more. It's basically unusable - please fix it so it works like it used to!
Absolutely love using this navigation system.

Used to love Waze until the last update. It no longer finds destinations, even my saved work and home. It just sits there idle, spinning. Not even the GPS works when it finally does work to go home. My car avatar spins in the opposite direction, corrects itself, then does it again. Switching to Google Maps, everything works fine with maps. Uninstalled.

Drove to Florida from Illinois, the plan was to to use Waze from start to finish. The app kept having to be told where we were going, had to force stop the app twice, and restart my phone 3 times. When we were in Atlanta, it said that there was an update on the route that was going to shave over 280 minutes from our trip. Alas, we never found out what this miraculous worm hole actually was, since the app stopped responding; only occasionally sounding the 'recalculating tone,' and doing a loading animation for almost 20 minutes. We had to admit defeat and switch to Google maps. I was a heavy Waze user for a couple of years, then the bugs and issues made me uninstall it. This will probably be my final trip where I am using the app.

On the one hand, i love this app. it's my app of choice for road trips for three reasons: 1., it has faster travel times (it usually says I'll arrive faster than google maps does), 2., it lets me see and make user reports (police, road hazards, etc.), and 3., it shows my current speed and the speed limit. those features are all awesome. BUT... i have never, not one single time, has Waze work for an entire road trip (on a single day) work without crashing, freezing, or just not working.

It depends on the phone and the quality of the built-in GPS chip I guess, it often fails to detect accurate where I am and calculate or recalculate the route fast enough to mimic real-time. This is comparing to when using Google Maps. However when it works, it qorks like a charm. Maybe the updates are making the app bulky. Not sure. Still love it. Using S8+

Whilst this is an excellent navigation app for short journeys I have not had a good experience with journeys over 150 miles. On the occasions that I have used it for such journeys it freezes and then crashes between the 150 and 200 mile mark. Which isn't good when your southbound on the A1 and your just about to hit a junction and you don't know if you need the A1M or the M1!  Others have commented the same and yet still it happens. Like others I don't like the adverts that take prominence usually just at that vital time when directions pop up.  Others have said that Waze is now owned by Google, so surely its only a matter of time before all the good bits of Waze are combined with the reliability of Google Maps? If it wasn't for the reliability issues, always halfway through a journey, then I'd stick with Waze but sadly its not so unfortunately my go to app for navigation has gone back Google Maps.

I love this app and use it everyday for work. One thing I would add would be a cow (or any farm animals) on the road hazard. I drive on 160 to West Plains MO all the time and occasionally come across a stray bull or cow while driving. Just like other hazards cows are just as dangerous and can sometimes be worse. Thank you for adding. Wish I could give 10 stars. Amazing App all around

I'm a taxi driver, and so I use this app for a minimum of 8 hours a day. There are a few quite major issues which really affect the app. If I switch to another app for 15 seconds or more, WAZE has lost GPS connection and freezes, necessitating a program reboot. EVERY time! Also, when first entering a location, it will bring up a completely inaccurate indicator of distance. Sometimes the real distance is over 3 times higher!
replyContent: Hi Matt, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more about the freezing and GPS issues you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further for you. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: used to be my favorite gps app by far, but now they've added ads in a way that not only destroys it's functionality, but could probably be dangerous as well since it can become a distraction. several times now I've glanced at it to get a quick update on my position, only to have it block my view with an intrusive ad, distracting me from the road as i try to figure out how to remove the damn thing without accidentally clicking on it and getting redirected to the advertisers website while driving.

I used it on my way home from vacation. I hate traffic and love back roads. I don't mind leaving earlier and taking a longer less stressful route. The route it gave me to take home was relaxing and beautiful. Im a huge fan of being able to eliminate dirt/gravel roads. I've only used it once so far but I'm loving it. Oh also you can tie your music and audiobook apps so you don't have to leave your map page to navigate your playlist or book.

Love the app overall, especially how it takes traffic issues into account and will redirect around problems. I wish there were some way to pause a trip, say, when you pull off for gas or a pit stop, and resume, without the voice telling you how to turn around in the meantime. But otherwise, a super app! Love the cookie monster voice!
Works good is very helpful

Takes the stress of driving on the highway away. Tells me which lanes I need to be in for the turn-offs coming up. Appreciate that very much. When traffic backs up it'll find an alternate, quicker route. #1 driving app.
I really have likes this app. I've never had any problems when the address is put in correctly . 5 stars ******
All of a sudden the app says no GPS location. I am unable to use the app.
replyContent:
Hey, Tammy! If you're having trouble with your GPS, we'd love to help you fix that. Take a look at this guide for more details on resolving this problem: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051?hl=en Let us know how that goes.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Inoperative when lose data signal, like in mountains, etc. Will freeze without notice. This app is a TOTAL battery HOG. Google Maps is still vastly superior! Even worked overseas in a foreign country with your GPS signal. Waze is more "cutzie" than substance. In addition, way too many insignificant user notifications, ie: "car on the side of the road", etc. More than 50% wrong anyway...

Since the update its haphazardly picking up my planned trips, failing to search and find locations and the app totally freaks out if you try to set it up, without GPS (even when I used to get GPS from top floor in my building) and then move to having GPS available. It just refuses to accept there is now GPS. Sometimes have to restart my phone to get it to work.

This app was working well until recently. I liked it much better than Google Maps via Android Auto. Unfortunately, now every time I try to use Waze, the app indicates I either have no network connection or it will just spin trying to find a location. When I am able to get navigation working, it will keep resetting the directions or just stop navigating entirely. I have gone back to using Google Maps without any issues. And yes, I have checked all of my location settings.

The app is actually the best GPS, when it's usable. As a full-time driver the serve issues it's been happening as of late are simply unacceptable. There's minutes where it won't load a route and has to be reopened multiple times or it just crashes and the route disappears. When it works, it's fantastic, but that seems to be less and less common
Normally when I use the app it works fine lately it keeps we're experiencing problems or the app will log me out of it
replyContent:
Hey there! We're sorry to hear you've been experiencing issues with Waze. We'd like to learn more about what's occurring, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Totally useless. Several u turns. Driving in circles. Horrible app.
replyContent:
Hi, Grant. If you're having issues using routing, we're happy to help you with that. Would you mind submitting more information about this issue here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Frequent connectivity issues and startup bugs. I love this app WHEN it works, but getting it to work seems to be half the trick. Even with good internet, there always seems to be a 50/50 chance the server times out before it can calculate the route, even with clearing cache and restarting the app. All the features on this app are great, and the community is helpful and plenty, but it may not be the most reliable source of navigation right now.

Route calculation is atrocious for journeys more than about 50 miles; the quickest drive is usually completely missed and we are sent the 'scenic' way. In any case I'd rather save 10 miles than 10 seconds but there are no configuration options for that. The app has gone rapidly downhill since being taken over by Google and it's clear they are trying to run it into the ground so we all use Google Maps. But that's even worse; Google seem to have no understanding how roads work outside the USA.

This is the **BEST** gps app I have found! Much, MUCH better than Google! We live out in a rural area and have to travel roughly 55miles one way into the city a couple times a month for doctors and groceries and the help that other Waze users give about road construction/detours, highway patrol hiding spots, etc. (even potholes!! üòÆüòÅ) and the general help Waze, itself, gives is absolutely invaluble! I feel lucky I came accross this app a couple years ago and recommend it to everyone I can!

After one day and many hundreds of miles I'm not super impressed. For an app designed specifically to save drive time it fails completely. Used it on a 10 hour route I drive every day. it took me to every possible worst choice adding between 2 and 25 minutes each time. Voice directions periodically stopped working, several times the map would disappear showing my home screen while all the HUD overlays remained. App crashed several times. Speed limits were frequently incorrect and correcting anything over 45MPH required typing it in which also resulted in a prompt to tell me not to type while driving but still allowed it. it just added more steps taking my eyes off the road longer. ened up running it side by side with Google maps which is overall a better experience. most humorous moment was on a 75MPH road warning me of a difficult to see turn 1 mile out then just as I was passing it with "turn right"...This App has ADHD.

I use Waze on almost every drive Whether I know the route or not, Waze helps me stay a step ahead of regular traffic, accidents and construction; from speed traps to potholes to idiots. Hands down, the most useful smartphone tool for the road. User friendly interface by keeping it simple. I would like to see the ability to mark obstacles and hazards on the other side of the road, like you can police.

the only good thing about waze is it's communal aspect - pointing out road hazards and cops. as a map application, it's garbage. rerouting is glitchy and doesn't tell you plainly when you're rerouted, so if you miss a turn, it might reroute you on a 2+ hour detour without telling you. the ads are obnoxious and intrusive, with no option to purchase a premium version. great idea, but this app sucks.

1. Your ad pop-ups suck!!! 2. You need to add the ability to easily click on the map to select an alternate route. 3. You need to add the ability to see the lane we should be in during turns. 4. When I make a call or receive one your app locks up. Get some real design update please! Did I mention drop the stupid ads!!!
I wish I could give zero star rate. You're welcome.
No complaints on this one

Great app. I don't use the ridiculously slow Google maps ever anymore. Waze has good directions and up to date hazards. The only issues are that the alerts to leave are way off. It tells me it's a 20 minute drive to work when it's not that short even with zero traffic. At the same moment the widget says 40 minutes. So the notifications are basically useless. Also, sometimes it wants me to double back on my own route or go out of the way. Not as a detour or reroute, but ones that make no sense.
Great app, just wish the colour scheme could be adapted for colourblind people. Very hard too see upcoming traffic in dark red with the dark blue navigation route over it
replyContent:
Hi, Matthew! We're always looking for ways to improve our product and your Waze experience. We welcome you to submit this request to our suggestion box for further consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I''ve been using Waze for years and mostly love it.  One complaint is it seems to really hate changing from WiFi to cell data.  I start waze in the garage for my morning commute and many times as the phone loses my home wifi and switches to cellular it will hang for many minutes displaying the 'Searching network...' message.  The GPS tracking continues to work, and the phone has a data connection because I can stream spotify at the same time the message is appearing.  This can also happen out of the blue, driving along and it will complain with the same message even though I'm getting notifications and listening to music.  It seems to eventually self correct, but I don't get any traffic notifications while its busted.  Galaxy S7 running 8.0
This app takes me from door to door. You just put in the address you want to travel to and a map and voice directions takes you there.
Prefer Google. Less friendly... Regret for installing it.. My worst decision ever in my life..
Best App I Use. Helps me travel the fastest route, detours me around accidents, construction zones, other traffic slow downs & where the speed traps are. üòá

If you want to get to the wrong address and make sharp turns as you're told too late to turn here and there, then this is your best worst app yet. I've been taken to the wrong address 3 TIMES NOW! For the love of GOD! YOU'RE a GPS SYSTEM. It's a very simple job to just tell someone directions. that's what the app was made for and it can't even do that!

This app makes me so god damn angry. So much work has obviously been put into it, but its semi-functional at best. All it does is display network issues while it's still actively tracking my location then constantly takes me out of my destination. Then when I re-enter my destination it just displays oops something happened. I think what happened was one of the developers smashed his head in on the compiler button when adding this app to the play store and screwed up some of the basic network coding. I can immediately go back to Google Maps with ZERO issues at all. Already tried re-installing and clearing all app settings.
Very useful while driving

Waze used to be my everyday navigation app. For the last few months however, it has been unable to maintain GPS lock, and reverts to cell-site triangulation, which makes it useless for navigation. All other GPS-enabled apps work fine - only Waze has this problem; it's clearly a problem with the app, not the phone, which is a nearly-new S10e. I wish Waze still worked, as I really liked it as an app. unfortunately, it no longer works, so I had to switch to a different app for navigation.

Waze used to be utilized daily by my husband and I to send to ETA's and track progress. However, this feature was lost several months ago and the only way to connect with friends in Waze is through Facebook which we never use. Waze clearly had the functionality before to connect with your contacts, please bring it back. Until then, I've gone back to Google maps which has the extra feature of showing you lane configurations at turns. Waze is just another map app with nothing special about it unless you want to connect to Facebook.

I am done with this. Time and time again, I type in an address and it sends me to the wrong location, down a walking path, or makes me take unnecessary "shortcuts" Perhaps this was not ment to be used in markets like Seattle. Or small populated towns. It's really ment for tiny 300 people hollows where there is one road, one gas station, and one post office. But I'm pretty confident this app would f- that up as well. Bad directions, shortcuts, traffic alerts and no lane directions. Uninstalled.

I have a love-hate relationship with this app. I tend to use Google maps because it provides me with the most direct routes to my destination while Waze has me turning into way too many directions. However, I do use it when Google maps has me stuck in traffic and it seems like it can't find an alternate route. I also like the fact that you could report speed traps accidents and things like that while Google maps doesn't have it or has it buried in an inaccessible place.

Constantly says "cannot detect GPS" as well as "unexpected error occured" even on clear weather days with full data connection. I've had to exit and reopen the app several times or entirely restart my phone to get it to work. Voice recognition software consistently fails to understand basic street names. Takes forever to locate destination and I have to manually refresh the Routes button several times during the drive if I want to see updates.

Uninstalled from Android. iPhone performance is similar. This is a crowdsourced police speed trap app. For navigation use Google maps. Coming out of a parking lot you have a 50/50 shot since all you will see is a long blue line in front of you. Pick the wrong option, and you'll go for miles and then be told to turn around. There's no lane differentiation like Google. Hopefully Google imports the police function and folds this -- why would they maintain two apps?

I love Waze when its working and when I'm driving but there are a couple things that really bring the rating I give down. Firstly the navigation can not be started at home if you are connected to wifi. It completely stops as soon as you connect to LTE on the road, the navigation should automatically reconnect when that happens. Secondly. I ride a motorcycle and like to have Waze running g for obsticals kn the road but when I try and use the voice control feature the location I ask Waze to go to pops up but I have to stop, pull the phone out of my pocket and press go to continue. It should just take me there when using the voice command especially for favorite locations.

Full of glitches. No network issue. Re routing takes ages. Waze gives you the worst route available. So always check google maps even though waze is owned by google too. Only thing this app is good for. Live police and traffic info. And drains the battery lot faster than any other app i have used. And one more think why do navigation has to always i mean 120% of the time has to start in the opposite direction. Just get the direction right once. One star for traffic info.

I loved the app, but since the last update it crashes when opened from Car Home Ultra! Please fix this!! UPDATE:  I emailed Waze about this problem and their response was:  "Please make sure you are using Waze with a compatible in-car solution. Waze on Android Auto Waze on WebLink/AppRadio Waze for AppLink/SmartDeviceLink  Waze for Apple CarPlay If you encounter any other issues outside of these platforms, please reach out to your device manufacturer or car dealership as we do not officially support it."  Not very helpful Waze.  It worked before.  Did you intentionally make it NOT work with Car Home Ultra to try to force your users to use those apps?  Now that's bad customer service!  Not going to work either.  Back to Google Maps.

Works well for navigation so far. I reported an address error. Got a notification that I had a message in the app, the message features does not work. I tap a message and get a blank screen. Got an email, which comes from a noreply address, so I can't answer. The email has a link to a map editor, which doesn't work. I haven't needed to mark road issues, so all I can contribute at the moment are thumbs-up/not there taps. Edit: I don't do Facebook. Found the support address and wrote to it.
replyContent: Hey Mike, thanks for letting us know. Please send us a private message on Facebook with more details and we'd be happy to look into your issue. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Worst buggiest app I've ever downloaded. I redownloaded this from 3 years ago hoping it got better. You can't plan long trips (mine was 3 hours), so I put a midpoint and routed me there and it took me this long convoluted route that made absolutely no sense. Makes my phone overheat, get bogged down and run slow, and just overall doesn't work. By far, best advice is just use Google maps.
replyContent: Hi, Megan! We're sorry to hear about your experience. We're always looking for ways to improve user's experiences, so we appreciate the feedback you gave. We'd love to help you with the issues you experienced. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app at the time I was driving cross country a lot about a year ago was really great! Unfortunately, I can't and will not say that now. Before, you could zoom out to where you could see the entire country. The way it is now, isn't even worth having it on my phone. I'm sorry, I really am, for I honestly loved the app. I haven't used it for Almost a full year. I even had a expert tech working on optimizing my phone for me who wanted to delete it. I said Waze stayed. Now, I deleted it myself!
replyContent: Hi James, thank you for your feedback. We hope to see you return to Waze in the future, as we‚Äôre always looking to improve. Feel free to provide any new additions you would like to see in the app to Waze's suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Its a great app, but there is room for improvement. I think Waze should probably include 'emergency' options like petrol station (bubble on the screen) as the person heads to a destination. This option would help the driver get to the nearest petrol station along the assigned route without having to create a new drive there or type for that matter.

This app used to work so much better. You used to be able to share your ETA with other users and they could track your progress so you could meet at same time. This feature no longer works and always says ETA is 10 minutes and the program bar comparing you and the other is gone. This was the whole reason I used this app.

Not sure if it's just me but in the past when searching for a location, let's say Starbucks, you would be able to open the map view and click on one of the points. A pop up would say to preview location and then you could choose to navigate to said location. Now when you open the map view of all locations, you cannot click or preview the points available.
replyContent: Hi Mike, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to be great but I hate when it asks me if I am a passenger then takes away the keyboard input then after finally getting to enter an address it says "go" then another screen pops up only to say "go" again? Why the redundancy? And if I'm in a parking lot trying to navigate to next address, it tells me I'm somewhere else, then when I start driving it flips around the map 360 degrees to tell me I'm going the wrong way. If I'm in a questionable area I don't use waze at all and here lately to avoid the app or Google I have memorized all my regular routes. If I'm at an intersection and need a split decision, waze is unreliable: it thinks I'm across the street already and says "go" and are you sure about going? and now I am going the wrong way.

This app could be great but it uses too much data so I had to uninstall. Compared to Google Maps, Waze used at least 10 times the amount of data (270 MB) for one trip. For one navroute calculation, Waze used 18 MB. For me, this is too much data usage. I gave it two stars since it was easy to read and it has many POIs already on the map.

I give one star to have the attention of the developer. I start to drive and I have internet connection, later during the way I don't have internet or I just turn data off. Later when I have internet the app it's still searching for connection and it's offline. It happened many times. With GPS, when I start to drive it asks me to turn on the location and it doesn't find the GPS signal, even after driving for a few km. I reported the issue and they answered sending a link how to use gps. funny

that fact that it's free is more than enough! but how actively accurate it is and the ease for new users to learn what to do make it incredible! together paired with my radar detector, it's pretty much fool proof.. recommend to everyone and anyone, not just to avoid tickets but all inclusive with weather reports, hazards, roadkill, etc.. really a time saver and can help detour traffic effortlessly!

I use to use Google maps and hop onto this one because it was more accurate. Past few months it has gone down hill. Taking me on longer routes that take more time and 2-3 times to a unknown address when I double check the address too! Sometimes it takes me a few miles away from where I'm suppose to go! It also use to tell me which side the location is on, now it doesn't. So when I get to the location spot I have to search for both side of the road. SMH!!! Waze you disappoint me now.

I once loved this app, but not anymore !! Until you all fix the glitch of navigation to Alley, each and every time I get directions, I will not use it !! The directions in the beginning are fine then at the end they are not... "Take a right to alley. Turn left to alley." why is this glitch still on there? Don't anyone on the software team realize that? ü§™
replyContent: Glitches are annoying - and we can completely fix them thanks to users like YOU! Thank you for sharing your feedback. Please don't hesitate to alert us of any future issues you're experiencing, so our team can work to resolve it ASAP. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've used Waze on & off for the past few years. There are numerous reasons for not, which were mostly settings that I was unaware of (such as directions during calls--I once took a call, not realizing the directions were not provided during call, & after my 40 minute conversation I realized I was 40 minutes out of my way). Now I have decided to try again & the app is just all out of whack! Not navigating, not saving info etc, & keeps freezing & shutting downüôÑ ugh, not helpful when esp for GPS!

I used to love this app, but with each update, it's gotten worse. Right now my main issue is: 1. If the location isn't on BEFORE starting up the app, the app just won't work. It never shows me current traffic information and will not detect the location even if it's on. Also, if my location isn't on for a few minutes, it doesn't work. I thought maybe it was a phone issue, nope when I upgraded my phone it was STILL happening. It's extremely annoying and makes my commute even more frustrating.

Not one-star because it does not crash ALL the time. Not any more than two stars because it does crash, it cannot sort favorites, and when feels like it, it occasionally scrambles the favorites that I have taken the time to sort manually. Oh and also because it believes that it is perfect, since it is associated with Google.

The app works ok. Huge drain on phone battery and RAM so it slows your phone. NEEDS to have a drop down notification of next upcoming direction similar to Google maps. "Planned Drive" only works if you plan on driving in the vicinity of your home area. Planning a road trip 300 miles and I'm unable to "Plan" the trip,. Good luck receiving any help from customer service. Just like every app, "it works perfect"

Waze is the best!!! They always, always, always take you the shortest and fastest way possible to your destination while keeping you safe. All the other people that use this app help you avoid the traffic, make you aware of accidents, hazards and let you know where the potholes are located. Let's work together and help each other out by pointing out hazards, traffic and potholes. Click that üçä button in the bottom right section of the screen!

The app is greatly improved over the years. But there is still a ways to go, often GPS is lost, often it can give a confusing instruction like stay to the right when it is a 90¬∞ turn. also it gives instructions so far ahead that one can often be confused. But this app is much better then the Google maps app, more accurate and precise
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or have ideas and/or feature requests you'd like to share, feel free to leave us a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This used to be a great app - always got me where I needed to go usually on the best route. it would occasionally take me through neighborhoods on weird routes, but I got where I was going. Lately though, I end up sitting in traffic on service roads while traffic on the adjacent highway is moving. While driving on a highway, it will start telling me to make turns. my Waze lady has basically lost her mind. I don't recommend and am going back to google maps.

Really wanted to like this app, but mine has been plagued with connectivity issues while other map apps are running just fine. Waze drops connection often, forgets the route and tries to recalculate constantly, and gets several errors saying it can't connect to the routing servers. This renders the app completely useless since after it drops connection it only displays a blank screen. The app does have many nice features, but that's a moot point if it can't function reliably.

This application has lots of things done right for using it while driving such as reverting back to original zoom soon after the user changes the pan/zoom for checking something real quick, or asking to confirm exiting application to prevent accidental shutdown etc. But it has lots of small, annoying glitches that are not addressed for the last several years which makes me wonder if this app is still maintained seriously at all. Here is a quick example Me: OK waze, exit navigation Waze: stopping your drive is that right? Me: yes. Waze: turn left ... Waze: sorry for the interruption, what were you saying? Me: yes Waze: in 1000 feet turn left

One of the worst navigation apps I've ever used. Constantly lost my GPS. Thought I was going backwards. The arrow was pointed to the side the whole time so i couldn't see what was coming up. Pulled over twice before just using google maps which worked perfectly fine. It was unusable. This navigation app failed to navigate
replyContent: Hi Kevin, thank you for bringing these issues to our attention. We'd like to investigate further. Please send us a private message on Facebook with the details. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I have been a Waze user for almost as long as it has been out. Across iPhone, Android, Apple, Nokia, Samsung etc... For the past few months this program has become worse and worse. Either not able to find route, or the GPS going absolutely insane. My car looks like I'm drifting on the screen and will leave the road entirely and be out in a field then slingshot back to the road. . If I could attach a screenshot I would cause it looks amazing but not helpful when you're trying to get somewhere.
