It is a very useful app but I can't give it 5* because of two things. The app cannot work while screen is off/device is locked. For instance I know the route and would like the app to notify me about accidents, alerts or speed cams while the phone is in my pocket. Second, the sound before recalculating the route if you don't chose the suggested one is extremely annoying! It almost makes me stop using the app for navigation. It would be good if the app is able to use external GPS too.
replyContent: Hi Vasil, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We'd like to hear more about the issues you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Highly overrated. It's indeed good in warning the driver about incidents, but the navigation is horrible. In my opinion, the driver can still look outside the car and see what's going on so the warnings are a nice-to-have. The primary purpose of a navigation app is NAVIGATING, and it is horrible in that aspect. Can't download maps, sent me around in a circle a couple of times, takes weird routes which take longer than the normal route. So yea, not so great...
replyContent:
Hi, Ernest! Thank you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about the issues you're experiencing, please send us a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've been using Waze for years and it really worked fine until last update on December 2019. Since then, I wasn't able to use the app properly. I was always routed to unknown roads and I kept on losing. It always says, "no gps detected" and the likes. Most of the time, couldn't detect traffic unlike the old waze, always consistent that you can rely on it. I hope this will be fixed soon. By the way I am using oppo f9, maybe it'll help for the next update. üôè

Tried scout because I own a Toyota and it is the one that will come up on the car screen. But it is terrible. Waits till the last second to tell you to turn. So I tried Waze. It is amazing, if it would cone up in the Toyota car screen I would give it five stars. Great directions and gives plenty of warning. And would direct me around roads that were closed.
Its always choose the wrong direction..

A few times in the past after either android or android auto upgrades the app has become unusable. It was usually working again in a few days. About 3 weeks ago the same thing happened but it still isn't working. I contacted Waze 2 weeks ago and sent logs. No help there. I am about to uninstall it. It cant find my route to work until I am almost there, it loses the route and constantly freezes. Considering the fiddling I constantly have to do with this app while driving it is very dangerous.

When I enter a location name such as a store or restaurant, the app might suggest ONE relatively close to my location, but most if not all will be several states away. When I am at a location in a mid-atlantic state, it is HIGHLY unlikely that the grocery store I want to map to is in MA, or the restaurant in GA. The quality of this app has degraded substantially.

Used to be a fantastic GPS app. Now it will not connect or says "searching for GPS". I have tried everything. Un-installing & re-installing, hard rebooted and restarted my phone, checked all settings, calibrated my GPS, updated the app and created a new sign-in...nothing worked. Finally I gave up and un-installed. I have read that this is an on going problem so I'm sure its not my phone or something I did. To bad, it was a good app while it lasted. Galaxy A51.
replyContent: Hi John, thanks for contacting us. We hope to see you return to the app because we'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. If you're still seeking assistance, please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Best Navigation App Peroid! Nice to know when your approaching a Speed Trap, it being so interactive makes it work so well, this is a must have Nav App, great to use for all your driving you know exactly what's ahead, and if there's any delays it knows exactly where, how long and does it much more accurately then anybody else. Easy to give it 5 Stars. Only complaint is I lost all my progress each time I switched phones, so maybe research the best way to log in there it will keep your info.

Tried this for a few days, but I really could not see what all the fuss was about.  I was using this on my pioneer head unit, compared to google maps the detail on waze is hard to see. I struggled to identify street names as it didn't seem to zoom in as close as google maps. It would zoom out no problems but the closet view  was still too far away for me.  It was showing heavy traffic on roads that had barely any traffic and yet the road that was bumper to bumper was a clear run.  The only good thing I liked about Waze was the speed indicator. I have deleted the app and gone back to using google maps.

This will be awesome once you iron out some bugs. My setup seems to forget where it's going if I loose signal and certainly if I disconnect the phone (road-side service stop) Interesting that your Google Maps suggested alternative routes to avoid traffic, yet Waze remained silent. It also appears that the reaction time between seeing something and logging it is too short, resulting in objects being flagged past their actual location. 09/10/2018: Still forgets where it's going when engine is stopped. Think petrol station, rest stop etc...

I really wish I could give this a higher rating, but this app is embarrassingly bad, especially for what is a Google product.   A sample of the problems I had just on my most recent road trip:  1. The app doesn't gracefully handle going in and out of cell signal range -- the screen goes white and then comes back, and some of the time, it will simply stop navigation when it restarts. Other times, it will inexplicably try to re-run the last search,, and fail.   At any rate, a navigation app that can't handle loss of cell signal is pathetic. Google Maps doesn't have this problem, so why is it tolerated in Waze?  2. You can't simply navigate to a city. It will return a search result, but then will go back to the map view, with most of it shaded out except for a small spotlighted area. It never actually returns any routes, and you cannot enter navigation mode from this point. Searching for a specific address does not have this problem.   3. Speaking of search, for a product owned by Google, the search functionality is pathetic. Results are slow, inconsistent, and often not at all helpful.   (I have a lot more issues, but Google Play limits the maximum length of reviews)

Great app but does not work. It bugged out on me and after every install/uninstall available to me, clearing every cache, etc. the app freezes and bugs. I have had only generic responses from waze support. Clearly they do not care to solve anything not included in their "FAQ" section. The bug is theirs, rendering the site unusable - and there is simply nothing I can do about it. Sad, because it's a great app - but if it doesn't work, it's nothing. Hint for users: NEVER link your google account.
replyContent: Hi Mila, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I like this app but cannot find a use for it. Spotify have just contacted me with a proposal to stem my contenten on my TV out to others; not sure how this happens her.

I'm completely done with Waze! I've had at least 15 bad map routes in just this past month!   If you deviate from waze directions (especially when they are bad) it won't re-route you ... It instead gets mad and makes you go in circles to retry the original route.  I've started testing the app for solid directions. It's a huge fail. Yesterday it made me go a 2 mile loop for zero reason when I could have just turned left from the beginning since the loop took me back to the original start point ...

I'll keep it short and sweet since there's countless other dissatisfied user reviews with the same issues. Keep getting black screen, shows "No network connection" even though everything else works fine and constantly loses it's location on the map while navigating. All of this in the last month or so. Already tried all the "fixes". Might as well uninstall if it's not going to work or be dependable.

Hasn't been working. Won't give accurate directions. Arrow facing wrong direction. Also directed me on a huge detour telling me to make a huge circle rather than merging onto the highway at the next entrance. Instead, it said go to next interstate, turn left to go back on the highway to the next interstate then turn left again to be able to merge onto the highway again. Added 19 minutes extra to do a major circle. I knew where I was so just continued straight but would have been a huge mess.

Its accurate and the ads are smart. They pop up related to where you like an upcoming store close to you and only show when stopped. The smartest ads I've ever seen. Then add in the user added situations like accidents, police, pot holes.. Only negative is when you need to do something else on your phone the app doesn't continue, you have to tap to reopen then it will resume , so basically it's not running or directing you unless its open

Since last week, my waze ETA in motorcycling mode is permanently set to 4 mins, regardless of whether the destination is the next road, or the other end of the country. In car mode it still provides correct calculations but in motorcycling mode (the only one I use) it always returns an erroneous time. I can't find any info online about this (only about slight inaccuracies rather than an entirely missing calculation) and am therefore leaving 1 star in the hope it is picked up by developers. I have cleared cache, uninstalled etc etc. Help.

Bit of a mixed review. There are some things I love about this app, and some things that I don't. To start with positives. Real time traffic speeds are pretty accurate, and it really trumps Google maps with some features, such as telling you what speed your going and the roads speed limit, which is pretty accurate, it also tells you about potential hazards such as stopped cars on a motorway, police etc which is surprising accurate. The eta for journeys is also accurate most of the time. But on to the negatives. Despite loving many things about this app, I feel it's sometimes tries to be too clever for its own good. I have experimented using navigation on the way back from work hoping to spend less time in traffic, so I let it choose a route and it said 45 mins, perfect. But what I didn't realise is that it took me on some really strange roads, single track in the middle of nowhere. Usually my commute is 19 miles and takes 55ish mins with rush hour traffic, the route it suggested was probably around 30 miles (after all the route changes) and took just over 50 eventually. So generally, I'd recommend the app, but just be careful where it want to take you sometimes!
Waze displays ads everytime your car stops moving along the route. A boring dystopia indeed.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or have feature requests you'd like to submit to us, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I have been using this app for 4 years now. Up until this past year it was a great cop that gave you the alternative routes that were faster and saved you time. For the past Ford five months this app has been a big disappointment. It no longer gives you quicker alternate routes but instead gives you the regular route which is in traffic. No more shortcuts as options. I've been using Google Maps as a better alternative.

Ever since the updates in late November, I was having a massive loss of GPS that was hit or miss (sometimes it would load, other times not). Never, in all my years using this app on various platforms, has it been this bad. It is pretty much unusable as is. In order for it to work, I had to download a separate GPS app to reset the gps and everything runs fine now. This app should have worked right off, but at least I now have a cooler app on my phone?

used to really like this app, but after the update, it totally sux! everytime i type in a destination for directions, its says something went wrong, try again later, and if by some miracle, i am able to get it going, all i can see are the different icons on the screen, but the map never shows up, and the distance and time doesnt update. make it work again, and it'll get a better review

The UI is bad and the app is too heavy and clunky and does not integrate well with android auto. It fails to load too many times and have to wait forever for it to detect a already running carpool and let me take actions about it. They have also been paying less to the carpoolers. They have not paid me for multiple rides of mine multiple times. They dont seem to care enough to fix it even though it was brought to their attention multiple times.

I like that it tells me in advance when there are pot holes and objects on the road way. I like that it tells me when there are cars stopped on the shoulder ahead. I like that it tells me when a police car is ahead. It's also very nice to help me avoid the toll roads if I want to. The only thing I didn't like was where it would have me get off the road several miles in advance when there was supposed to be congested traffic ahead. It did this three times in one evening and the traffic wasn't bad at all. (Please note that I am rating this after only one day of use.)
This is the fastest GPS of the 3 that I use. I'm finding that I use the others less now.

This is a great App. The MAJOR problem with this App is the auto log in features. Every time I use the app it tells me to log in and EVERY time I log in ALL my favorites and travel history disappears and I have to add them all again. I'm a Simple guy, All I want is a GPS that tells me the estimation of travel and where the cops and road closures are. THAT'S IT!!

Got the app to be made aware of traffic issues but what a farce. It never takes the traffic issues into consideration. It will often direct me onto a secondary road and direct me in an impossible manoeuvre such as crossing a very busy 6 lane road while I have a stop sign. Maybe I'd get across at 3 a.m. but not between 7 a.m. to 7 p.m. This has happened so many times. Another trick is to take me off the street with a left turn signal and then direct me to make a left turn 2 blocks later. It works to let me know where somplace is but is terrible at getting me to the actual site.

Loving it so far. Much better accessibility than Google Maps, some delving is necessary in the menus to get things 'comfortable' but, nothing extraordinary. So, in summation, I've finished . Deary me, it seems I have not, in fact, finished. My earlier enthusiasm for Waze has sadly, declined, declined the point of Google maps, yes, driven away by the near constant adverts for, to me at least, local businesses. I'd not gladly, exactly, but still willingly, pay for a less intrusive version.üòò

Always faster than other map apps (might sacrifice in milage but still faster). Shows you current speed and speed limits. You can add your toll tags. You can see where police are setting up speed traps. You can plan a drive that incorporates morning traffic so you know when to leave (great for huge cities like Houston!). I always recommend Waze over every other app.
Its really joke when you have to plan routes, it cant change your start point, its always from your actual location
Very bad. Inaccurate and causing confusion.

I used to use this app all the time to go from Wisconsin to Alabama. I tried to program the address on again on my new phone and it only gives me one route going through all the big cities. When I hit alternate routes it only have me the one that I didn't want and says "permit Required" I messaged them on Facebook, but no reply. Even gave them a screen print.
Don't like this app. Does not show clearly the directions I'm going. Not showing roadblocks, closed road etc. Always crashes.

Would be five stars but some genius decided that you should not be able to turn off autozoom. I zoomed out for a reason, if I wanted to zoom in I would do so or turn autozoom on. Also would be nice if when coming to an intersection, exit, fork in the road if it displayed a picture of the lanes and which one you should be in like Google maps or any actual gps unit. And finally, would rather pay a fee than see all the freaking ads, I am fat enough without an alert every time i pass a Dunkin donuts

Downloaded this app for a recent business trip. Love the social aspect of Waze. The warnings (hazards and police) were great. But it did a terrible job with estimating time, construction notifications, and most importantly navigation. Routes were inefficient to say the least. Google Maps use a more direct route and saved me almost 10 minutes.

Generally good, but a few glitches. 1. When parked in a lot it has a hard time determining which way the car is facing and always sends me in the wrong direction for 5 seconds until it corrects and I have to make a U-turn 2. If a U-turn is necessary to reach an address on a divided hwy, it does not say "make a U-turn", it says "turn left, then turn left"
replyContent:
Hi John , thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about issue to investigate further. To do so, please submit create and submit a ticket here:
https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9557145?hl=en Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This is a great GPS app, never have gotten lost and has helped me to avoid traffic, accident etc. as promised. However, when attempting to put a destination for a future trip, it just spins and stays blank for so.e reason. It didn't do that before! It was cool when I've planned a trip and it automatically pops up with the direction ready to go. Can you please look into it? Other than that, this is an excellent app.

Pros: Good navigation app. Cool features Cons: Constant ads every time the car slows down. Ads are irrelevant and take up half the screen. Does not have an ad free version. Cannot run without 4G LTE speeds due to bloatware Difficult to report any kind of hazard. Regularly underestimates time of arrival, my drive time is anywhere from 5 to 20 minutes longer than the original time given.

Been using this for a few days now. I like that I can turn off the voice because I know where I'm going I just want updates if my route is backed up. The carpool function is RIDICULOUSLY annoying. I can't figure out how to turn it off and being asked 4 times a day if I want a carpool (even when just going to a store), my answer is NO. I would carpool with work people if we had the same schedule. I'm not carpooling with random people. Make this a function we can turn off and I'll up my rating...

I use Waze every day to get me everywhere around Chicago. If I'm on the Dan Ryan and traffic is backed up it will put me on a detour that will save me time. You can change the type of car the voice. You can also sync your music to it rather you use Tidal, Spotify or Pandora. Of course when you're driving you can respond to the warnings to alert other Wazers of cops, or broken down vehicles. Otherwise my most used app.

I don't usually do reviews but waze use to be such a good app. Now not so much. I use to use it every day because i drive far everyday I'm finding myself using google maps more often now. Recently it would take me on the longest route possible. Even if I start on a shorter route it will try to force reroute me to take the longer and worse route. Once it finnaly decides to take the short route my ETA changes from 50min to 30min. Even if i check the optional routes the others are a better and faster than the default route Not to mention the connection issues. I usually set my route up in my apartment with my wifi to check for traffic. The last while it takes me increasingly long to connect to the waze server and even if the route is plotted and I'm ready to go it just resets my trip. Sometimes i will find my destination and while its trying to find a route it just days there are connection issues. Then there is the traffic notifications. I use to trust ways blindly with my traffic reports but ive had too many occasions that it tried to reroute me because of traffic that did not exist.

I tried this app and several others before giving up. I bought a Garmin Gps and i couldn't be happier with it. Sure it will cost you money in the begining but the headaches it saves you is well worth the cost. Make sure you get one that includes free map updates and you will Never have to pay for an update. It has never let me down on directions anywhere!!
Solid app. Real time goodness.
Why isn't there an option for Satellite view ?
replyContent:
Hey there, Donald! Waze doesn't currently offer a satellite view, however, w welcome you to submit this request to our suggestion box for further consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box/suggestions/20454145-offline-maps

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to be great, good for police locations, but it freezes and crashes in Australia all the time, i have used for years, and drove 16,000km across the USA, didn't crash then, but in Australia before i left and after i guy back it will randomly freeze all the time. Cleared the cache, uninstalled, still does. Crashes all the time, never rely on this app!!!!!! Ever!!!!

Great app when it works, I use it in SoCal and it's usually right on and is never more than a few minutes off unless something happens on the road after you've started. The problem is for the last few weeks maybe, the app has been incredibly buggy. It's been closing when I try to look at other routes. The initial route calculation frequently doesn't work. It starts, takes forever, then fails. Other times it doesn't even try. After crashes, there'll be no directions at the top of the screen.

I had this app when it was still new and it was fantastic. what the heck happened? I got rid of it, then the other day, gave it another chance. It took me almost 4 miles past my destination, when I literally drove right past my destination, and dumped me not even at an address, but on a street, in the middle of nowwhere. In the middle of nowhere, in the dark, all I need was a breakdown for Waze's horror movie recreation to be complete.

I have a love hate relationship with this app. When it works it beats all other GPS apps unfortunately it doesn't work most of the time. The only way I can get it to work is to enter the address before plugging in into my car that supports Android Auto. One plugged into the car I get network not found. My wifi is off and I don't have any issues with any of my other apps. I'm not a huge fan of Google maps but I don't have much of a choice. Please Waze test your app before you release an update!

A few areas for improvement-- 1: text size adjustment (far too small for dash-mounted use) 2: allow voice control to automatically start navigation instead of only pulling up a search (which you then have to take your hands off the wheel to click!) 3: map themes (colors etc... Pure black mode to save battery on AMOLED devices). The first two are deal-breaking omissions.

Keeps crashing and giving bad directions. I cant recommend to anyone for this. If it works, it is a great app, but Google Maps seams to be dependable and more direct. in short: ways has 1. given bad directions 2. crashed in the middle of my drive 3. has refused to boot up 4. missleads me into wrong direction due to this, I have been late for work and school. I can not promote this to anyone who commutes.

Edited: everythings back to normal, easy to use, good with direction, its just a very useful app my friend. Feel disappointed with the service. It used to let me know in about 300 meters to take turn or how many KM the next turn, now it just tell me take left or right and i always miss the turn, i realy need the directions from the waze since i work not in my hometown. Please fix it and i will change into 5stars. Thanks

Used to be great. Now it's pretty terrible. Sometimes you just need to know where you're going quickly, and that's impossible with this app. First you have to accept pages of agreement you don't have time to read. Then it wants you to log in or create an account. Then it says your password is wrong. Then after you reset it, you have to verify your email. Then it wants to know what kind of vehicle you drive and what your home address is. I got what I really needed but tapping on Google maps once.
replyContent: Hi , thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Disappointed going from ios to google play. IOS updates the drive as you go. Once you pass a hazard, it disappears when you look at your overview, and also updates as they are tagged. My google play app does neither. i have to constantly exit and restart my drive to check for new tags. Overall, it's a great app. But I definitely miss how it worked on my iPhone.

It's "bar-none" one of the coolest navigation sources I've used yet. I have a Garmin GPS system in my truck but never use it anymore for the fact that my phone is now my.... Well.. Everything. GPS, music, media and needless to say, communication center. I love all the features this app has won't be changing it ever. Thanks Guy's, you get all 5 Stars!!
I m unable to connect with GPS, I delete then app then reinstall still can't connect to GPS.
replyContent:
Hey! If you're having trouble with your GPS, we'd love to help you fix that. Take a look at this guide for more details on resolving this problem: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051?hl=en Let us know how that goes.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I can't stand this app. There was a time we could type an address and get directions. This app makes you push a bunch of buttons just to go. You can't type your destination and look at directions before a stupid countdown starts happening. Why isnt looking at routes before leaving an obvious option? If I can get to where I'm going without virtual assistance I'll take it every time. This app throws ads in the middle of your navigation. It totally sucks! All the map apps are horrible now days

4.5 - Most useful GPS there is: calculates time perfectly, alerts you about police while driving, and it is constantly updating, thanks to drivers inputting traffic/road issues. I also love that it reroutes whenever and wherever unlike other GPS apps, they make you take their route. Only reason for 4 stars is because sometimes when I search for a location, there's a problem and I have to restart the app a few times.

Great concept, works good! I love that it's almost like a game. Notifications for car stopped on the side of the road, police, and traffic jams are great. I wish it was easier to post, when something is in the road, or black ice, etc while driving. It's easy to tap on the police icon, but not easy to put slippery road, etc. Esspecially when driving which is dangerous. I know...common sence, but there have been times, that i wanted to warn others, but couldn't!

WAZE IS AMAZING!! I travel from NYC to LI for work so there are several route options. Most days the routes are about the same amount of time, so I can opt for the no toll route. But, Other days the routes can be off by 30 min due to construction or an accident, so I will pay the toll to get to work on time. There is a setting option to alert when it's time to leave. Yeah... I should probably use that. But, sometimes it's worth paying the toll to stay home a few extra minutes.
Ur navigator took me to nowhere, sometimes it took me to untaken road, ungazetted road.. it scary though üòë navigator should helps in finding place and destination no making user lost in nowhere.
Waze is the best app to be use

I really want Waze to be what it claims. Crowd sourcing traffic and driving data is such a good approach to navigation. unfortunately there are too many issues with functionality and accuracy at this point. On my Pixel 2XL, Android 9, the planned trips feature rarely works. Also, ETAs are consistently 10+ minutes earlier when you start than when you actually arrive. I've had a couple trips that were more than 30 minutes off! Can't you use the traffic data to make accurate predictions?

Love this app. I've been using it for a few years for my daily commute without issues. This past year i started using it on longer trips and noticed it crashs about every 90 minutes. I restart it, resume trip and all is well. I just thought it was my phone (G note 8). Today I'm taking a trip with my Dad who has Pixel 3 and it does the same thing in his phone.

Pop up point of interest ads are not acceptable while driving. They cover a large portion of the screen and can be distracting or dangerous. They should only be allowed at a full stop... I'm reading others that say it only happens while they are not in motion but I get them while IN motion. I'll give waze 5 stars if this is fixed. Please fix it.

The ultimate data collector!!! Shocked at the level of privacy invasion!!! At least they're up front in the privacy policy about most of it, but tracking and maintaining virtually EVERYTHING you do, what you have on your phone, who you know, everywhere you go, and if that's not enough, it broadcasts your every move. Turned off or not, everything you do is monitored and archived! No warning before install! Immediately uninstalled. Tradeoff of privacy not worth it. Selling your soul if installed.

Names of the streets and cities are not accurate, design of it looks old (about 2009-2010), for some reason it has to download voice packs, it constantly searching for network even with good signal, the alerts and reports are mostly fake or not accurate. Even some of our radio stations are using Waze for traffic reporting, but then most of the reports are just not existant. What is wrong with people? Why is there so many 5-star ratings?

I enjoy the app but there are a few things to improve, mainly the zoom buttons, there are so slow and cumbersome to use, not always responding, unable when driving. Make 2 big buttons far apart or better still double tap and swipe up or down like google maps for good one handed use. Also, cluttered screen, I'd like to be able to easily remove the car info button from the screen. A useful feature would be to color code dual and single carriageways so I can plan my route according to those.
Not accurate at all üëéüëé The service are so poor. How do you manage? Don't you have a skill? #freepa.les.tine

This app is ok, but honestly I Removed three stars for the interruptions. This app won't let me interact with it unless I click that I am a passenger, which is an extra click while driving. Further, it places ads in my maps window, obstructing and again requiring a click to clear. Finally, clicking the x on a notification inside the application often triggers the "invite to waze carpool" which is both a nuisance, distraction, and useless feature. Stop nagging me to car pool.

This app use to be amazing but lately it's all errors. 1. Cant find GPS signal 2. Forces closed 3. Ads block directions 4. Takes me 20 miles out of my way for no reason. Must be all those gas station ads! Taking the longest route versus the fastest now. I can run Waze and Google at the same time.and Google will get me there in a shorter distance and faster EVERY time.

I love this app, however since moving to Ohio I find waze takes me in all different directions to and from and these are places I frequent alot. Waze is my best friend in my new town but I'm not liking how it changes what routes it takes me. I don't like driving through shopping center parking lots to get to where I am going. please let me know if U have missed an update.

I rely heavily on voice commands for navigation. If waze is currently navigating me to a destination I am not headed toward it is constantly interrupting me while im trying to change destinations or cancel navigation as it rerouts. (because I'm not going to the destination navigating me to) This usually occurs because the destination was not where waze said it was, either way if a user says "Ok Waze" it shouldn't interrupt them, ever. It's very frustrating to be interrupted and told "go on".

I've used Waze for 4 years. It was great in the past, but recently it has often frozen and has even more often complained about having no network connection in places where there is definitely network connection. I uninstalled the app today and installed it again, and surprise, it isn't working at all. Map isn't loading and when I try to specify a destination, it says something went wrong. The app has become worse and worse, especially recently. In an attempt to improve it, it's been made worse.
replyContent: Hey Eva, we're here to help. Can you please message us on Facebook with more details and a screenshot of the issue? Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I'm better off navigating myself. An ad pops up when I'm at a stop, which is basically when I have a chance to verify my course. The voice navigation will also wait until I'm on top of my turn to tell me I need to move several lanes over to get to it. Additionally it sometimes doesn't tell me after I completed a turn when the next one will be, couple that with the app sometimes assuming I'm done driving and stops giving directions entirely. It'll, often, start facing the wrong direction so drivers that need to leave a parking lot will be navigating blind until it recalculates and good luck with that if you're signal isn't great.

Waze use to be awesome but it has progressively gotten worse in the past year. It no longer shows the actual fastest routes and pushes you to expressways regardless of settings. It ignores secondary roads that would save time. I'm having an increasingly difficult time connecting when there should be no problem and it crashes too frequently. I use to recommend Waze to everyone. Now I'm waiting for a new start up to replace it. Go back to the way it use to be.. it wasn't broke.
Itll take you through some side streets and neighborhoods but it'll get you there the fastest way

This used to be a very useful app. Unfortunately, it switches to a different route without your permission (unlike google maps). So, if I initially chose a route (e.g. without a toll), in the middle of driving it switches back to the one with toll. Yes, there is an on screen notification. But, if you are driving, you might not see it. And, even if you see it, you have no way to forbid that switching. This behavior cost me money, when the app sneaked in a toll route when I chose a free one.

Started using in Oct 2018.The only reason is the cute user icon,but you won't be able to change your moodd until you drove for 160 km!Still a bit of fun,on some good days a lot of user response on traffic, especially the accident and police.A bit more than the Google Map.However, not sure how it works? How long the accuracy last?You cannot update the information. Need to improve if want immediately update from user of the road condition changed. If school zone alert can be added will be better.

If you want an app that distracts you while driving, this is it! The final straw for me was an advertisement that popped up in the middle of driving. I was wondering if Waze was a better Google Maps as others have recommended. While there were a few situations that might've been more accurate by 1-2 minutes, I just couldn't handle the much larger UI compared to maps and the surprising *ding* when I picked up a candy (a game Waze wants you to play while driving) that I pulled over for because I didn't know if my car was having issues. If Waze wants me back they gotta get rid of everything that isn't helping me navigate to a destination.

getting worse and worse since Google bought it. directions are now crazy way too often (taking me 100 miles out of the way, if i hadn't ignored Waze). I've taken this trip before and the directions were correct, but not now. also ads in a nav app while you're trying to drive? I'll try sygic, it seems to get better reviews lately.

The app has been sub-standard for too long now. When you shut it down it continues to run in the background and even telks you it is! The 'close' button does nothing. As for routes, clearly not enough people are bothered to inout data as it frequently sends me towards what I can plainly see are traffic jams. Yup, pretty much done with it now. Can anyone recommend something that is as good as Waze used to be?

This app is great but there is just one flaw but it could be a major one. Please admin team incorporate the feature that tells which lane to choose while turning right or left just like google maps. i.e. turn right from the second from the left lane etc. Because sometime just aftet turning you gotta turn to opposite side. And this could be a huge problem if you are in wrong lane. So if you know it beforehand would be great.

Needs more work. Don't take me wrong, I do appreciate your app and the community contributions. I do contribute alot too. However I am impressed by waze that it cannot give you an option to choose which bridge I want to use. I live in London and I don't have a lot of options when it comes to using the bridges or the tunnels. At the moment london is undriverable with almost every road is closed or blocked permanently. Put the option of choosing different bridge or tunnel.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for your review. We love feedback to get better! Please share this idea of having the option to choose bridges to the Waze suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Hello, if you could add the Lane assistance and Junction view that would make you the perfect Navigation apps in the world. Thank you for your efforts. Is there a way you could make something like that of Sygic navigation that when you have to change the lane that we can see the actual road picture with an arrow showing us to move and change the lane. Thank you for your great service to the public.

I really love this app, my TWO complaint is that it doesn't save my favorite routes and it often gives you directions that aren't the most direct route. It often directs you to go "the long way" to a destination even if obstacles are not present. You are given three opto find your way, and often does not include the most direct route again, this has nothing to do with any traffic slows down, for any reason!

I always liked this app but I just downloaded it again after years of not having it. And I tried to mark a closed road but was not driving near it anymore and it was only going to let me mark it to an area closest to me. Also if you're driving it just redirects you to where you're driving so it's hard to look at other stuff on the map. IDK maybe I'm doing it wrong? Is there a way around this?
replyContent: Hi Michelle, we're happy to hear that you're Wazing again! And thanks for reporting. Please make sure that you report as close to the actual incident as possible. Learn more about reporting here: tinyurl.com/ya8dlngg For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This is a really good traffic map system. Its search system is limited, but it does have the benefit of being category-based, which is great when looking for gas or coffee on the go. The traffic and hazard warnings are SO useful. I'm also a big fan of it being integrated with Spotify and Pandora for music on the go. If the map is ever outdated, you can also suggest map corrections, and the team actually listens! Great app, so user-friendly, totally recommend it!

I cannot adequately emphasise just how much I love Waze. I've had it for years and it improves exponentially as more people get the app. The reporting function allows users to auickly and simply log incidents and conditions (roadworks, accidents, traffic jams and more) as they drive, and the app then uses their location to create reports for other Wazers in the area, sometimes suggesting an alternate route. Users update fuel prices as they drive so finding the cheapest place to refuel is easy.

pretty good for most things. Can be a bit slow for example When road changes happen-like if you need to be on the left lane to make that split it won't give that to you till it's too late. Really like it since it gives you police/hazzards and the such. But to confirm or deny that those are still there it dissappears too quickly. Trying to find gas stations and such is too complicated. So not too good for that.

This app would be very good and useful, but ... Navigation within biult-up area works wrongly. Instead of one simple and safe turning, it navigates into a lot of zigzag operations on minor roads which result unnecessary turnings and dangerous situations (more crossings, etc.). Other applications do not do this. Otherwise, out of built-up areas, works well. Navigation mode should be able to set by the user, or make some fine tuning on that. Until this is not solved and it can not be used in cities or villages in normal mode, only one star is given.
replyContent: Hi Tam√°s, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit your ideas for the app to the Waze suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It is amazing app but from last couple of months or so i am struggling with the GPS. Mostly i have to restart my android phone to get it working again but sometimes even that doesn't work. Please fix this issue ASAP. I have seen feedback of other users as well they are also struggling with the same problem. I would also like to give you a suggestion....that please provide the offline maps facility similar to the way Google Maps provide. Thank you.

This app is terrible it constantly is wrong I've been in traffic for an hour and a half only to learn the HWY is CLOSED!!!! Thanks a lot!!! This is ridiculous!!! This is not the first time I understand if it's a back road however when it comes to a main hwy 610 and your app doesn't know it's closed!?!?!? Why am I even using it. I'm done!

"Server time out" errors happen more than half the time I try to use this app for directions. The other half of the time the app freezes after about 1 hour. Some of the features are nice, but the glitches and issues are too much. I am using a Samsung Galaxy S9. If I learn that this app has been optimized for Apple, then I will uninstall and rate 1 star.

Excellent navigation app. The shortest path algorithms typically allow me to avoid heavy traffic or delays caused by obstructions. I just wish there was an option to avoid left turns across busy highways. I have been put in situations where I was routed to a left turn and there was a left turn option with a traffic light one block away.

Waze used to be amazing. Lately when I've used it for my daily commute, it's just awful. The routes it chooses are terrible and sometimes dangerous. I can be sitting in traffic, no movement in 5-10 minutes, and the app will insist nothing is wrong. I don't believe it can be trusted to get me places safely anymore.

Works OK when it works but can't always get it to give directions from current location. It frequently wants to start from previous destinations. Also had problems on turnpikes a few times. GPS signal is consistently lost when I need to get on or off. On my last two trips I went in circles and out of my way for an hour because of lost signal or bad directions. Often told to take streets or exits that did not exist. Also it keeps giving me traffic updates for areas I visited months ago. I like when it gives me speed trap warnings and road hazard comments but I don't like it coming on when I'm not using it. It feels like a huge invasion of my privacy so I'm uninstalling.

1). Reports intermittently not showing on map. 2). Usually automatically starts navigation to home position without asking first when you first open application. 3). Intermittently doesn't notify you of police traps or hazards with ample time to stop for them. 4). Some reports disappear too soon. 5). Some reports don't list author. 6). Lousy demeanor of service. If you post negative public review depicting truth they tell you to create a deadend ticket on their funhouse unhelpful website.

I've used Waze before and not had many issues, but it became very glitchy when used with Android Auto in my car. Sometimes the map would go completely white or show blank spots with no road, occasionally telling me to turn around because it didn't recognize that I was already on the road it was telling me to get on (and going in the right direction). Not sure what caused this, but I had to switch back to Google Maps which was working just fine.

I have been using Waze for a really long time now. Lately I have been using it with Android Auto which worked even better. However since a couple of months it loses its gps location while driving? It goes all over the place or just doesn't update at all. When I switch to Google Maps it works fine again so it is not a GPS problem. It has to be in Waze. Do you guys have any idea what the hell is going on? I love the traffic updates and it has helped me out a lot of times where I have to take a weird route only to find out later that there was an accident or traffic jam or my normal route. So if the GPS is working correctly again I would really recommend Waze. Not with the current problems I am having.
You are forced to create an account to use it. And if you have used to login with facebook, it doesn't work anymore and you have to go into a browser amd migrate that account. What.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback, Bogdan. We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or need assistance resolving an issue that may be occurring, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Excellent gps app; been using it for years & love it way better then Google Maps until the last update. Since the update a few weeks ago, or whenever it was, the actual gps is all out of whack. My car or icon disappears as if I lost satellite signal and then will reappear. Lots of times, it'll reappear on a side street or side road way away from me. The icon will be sideways at times not facing the way my vehicle is actually facing. I've uninstalled and reinstalled several times. Fix this!
replyContent: Hi James, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more about this issue with the disappearing car icon to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I'd give a 5 star but I've recently come along a very big issue. Due to either software updates from the application itself or the Android OS, it no longer works. I've tried multiple hotfixes from; clearing cache/storage data, location permissions, uninstall/reinstall, restarting, cellular data, and messing around with my GPS to fix the issue. All of it coming up with no result. The issue being "no GPS, showing approximate location" and in addition not being able to register an account.

Don't know what's going on but the app has become pretty unstable in the last couple of months. Crashes randomly while driving once a day, forcing me to start fiddling with my phone. This never happened in the past and I can't imagine my OnePlus 6 can't handle it... Moving to another app underlying issues get resolved.

Concerning safety issue. Since the last update, Waze cannot maintain GPS location as many others have complained. This is with the latest and greatest Waze, Android Auto, and Sync 3 SW updates. I consider this a safety issue as this is Road-borne SW. The frustration of the sporadic location is distracting, but at night when the position updates the screen refreshes flashing a bright white light in a dark cabin impacting driver vision. Consider additional test points.

More and more I find myself being directed through unsafe areas. Please consider adding a report for routes that are not safe, or an option to avoid unsafe areas, because the app will try find the shortest route and then direct you through an area of town known for its high crime rate. I would rather pay a toll or travel an extra 10 minutes on a highway than run a serious risk of crime.

Great app, but lacks some of the features and mechanics of Google's map app. Needs more satellite connectivity and loses signal often. When it does so, it makes no computation for navigation to compensate. Leaving you lost. Therefore, if you know where you're going to and just using the app to avoid traffic? Great. But if you're trying to find something, use Google.
The app works fine for me but sometimes it tends to overflow GTE capacity of my cellphone

Very clunky design, awful controls, also doesn't show nearby landmarks. - Design is not sleek, very old-school looking. - The controls aren't smooth, tends to rubber band a lot or snap around while dragging. Zooming out sometimes doesn't register and when it does it zooms out insanely quick and far. Can't change map angle only zoom in/out. - Doesnt show nearby landmarks similarly to Google Maps when you zoom in (Hospitals, colleges, stores, etc.) Love the concept, it has a lot of potential.

If you don't mind being late; than use this app. Lately, I have discovered that this app sends you into "tracfic", rather than redirect away from traffic. This morning I had an instance where I was on a major highway; directed to the collector lanes "the faster route"; as soon as I hit the collectors...this app added 10mins., then 20 mins to my route. How is this okay when I was directed to this route only 1 minute before merging onto the collecters? CRAZY!!!
Easy, quick, accurate.

I disabled Google Maps, because I got tired of the runaround directions it was giving me. As a full time delivery driver, I don't have time for pointless turn here/turn there directions! I prefer a direct route with extreme minimal turns during my travels. I thought using this app would solve all that, but it's no better than Google Maps! Very disappointed!

Fed up with the constant crashes, cleared my cache, cleared all data, reinstalled. Crashes at least 3 times on a 4 hour journey, requiring resubmission of route destination, which of course shouldn't be done while driving... Rarely resumes the route after a crash. Crashes appear to be related to route recalculation, bit it's been like this for years now so only 1 start from me
Anytime problem.... Waste my time use this apps

Overall the map is well-designed but the issue I have is, I logged out twice and twice I had to start a new account. The first account I opened up ask me to login with Google and when I logged out and I tried logging back in Google was gone only Facebook was there and I don't use Facebook. I switched to a different email address and it keeps reverting back to my old one

This app sucks now... If I need navigation Im usually driving more than 100 miles. The last 15-20 I've used Waze, it's been for trips to Mexico, 205 miles, but this stupid app can never calculate a route longer than 150 miles or so, and always gives me an error message saying we cant calculate your route. This app use to be great, but now only 1 star.

Would use over google maps except one very critical issue. The map guidance doesn't direct you into the parking lot or space at your destination but ends on the main road and that's it. Driving down the main road and the arrow ends and you have no way to park or even realize that you're at the building. Google maps would actually tell you to merge off and direct you in the lot. Missed many turn offs due to this issue and I had to dump it

App works great with Android Auto and has greedy functions and features. But as soon as I pick up a call it freezes. The GPS takes forever to update and begins to lag. I have missed many turns because of this. That's the main reason I use Google maps because it never has an issue like that, and really there is no reason it should.

This just keeps getting worse. Yesterday the app sent me down the worst possible route... I recently moved to the North West and I rely on GPS. Every update seems to result in GPS being wrong and waze doesn't know where the car is. Unfortunately I got badly lost today, took a wrong turn on the motorway and this resulted in roughly an extra 40 minutes on the road. Not good enough, really. We provide you with data, it's not exactly a "free" app! We're not stupid and we expect a better service.
replyContent: Hi Vladimir, that sounds frustrating! Thanks for letting us know. We'd like to investigate this issue further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with the route details? Thanks again. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I had this a few years ago, but wasn't into it.. I decided to try it again and must say, the interface and map seems much better. Also the music feature is a sweet touch.. Maybe road conditions, Camera traffic lights, current weather conditions and read incoming texts and quick voice replies would be nice features too.. keep up the nice work..
More covinient, tells u the fastest route, nearby gas station, stores etc. Also let's you know there's accident ahead, construction, objects on the roads love it!!!...

This is a freaking great app that let's you help others on the road, makes me feel safer using it and has some really cool features....when it works! Everytime I boot it up and select my destination it fails the first time, every single time I have to enter it again and wait for it to load. Then if I have a longer than 45 minute drive it will randomly completely shut down the app middle of my drive. Now I have to set the GPS back up while driving. Hope they fix these minor bugs soon.

Some functionality issues: 1) if you're making a turn, and then have to make another in (approx) 400m it first says the next turn will be in 800m and then again for 200m 2) can't remove wrong reports when there's a new report soon after (like a notification about accident is 50m before a permanent speed camera, so you can't press like/remove before you get the next report and can't access the one you needed to edit)

I love to both use and contribute to the traffic alerts, how ever it would be very helpful to be able to add alerts like crashes, obstacles or stalled vehicles in the oncoming lanes. Like the police alerts are handled. Also app stops alit mostly during in route searching. Alot of "uhh owes". Need away of searching during trip of POIs in pins, can't tell difference if searched result is behind or in front of, because it routes you to uturn and go back not just show ones on the way. Seems to be a really intitive app. Love to see how many sees and counts the alerts, with ability to comment or clear pin.

The app will consistently lose its way on trips longer than 100 miles. The app can (less frequently) lose its way at random on shorter trips, it even did so in Clearwater Beach Fl. It will say is something along the lines of "error connecting to routing server". Funny thing is, I can then change my destination to something in the opposite direction and all of a sudden it will work, but then try to switch back to the first destination and it will not work agaIn. Reinstalling didn't help.
Needs tweaking love it though
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback. We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or need assistance resolving an issue that may be occurring, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: As an old user i believe this app has some fundamental weaks: 1) It doesn't show all of streets and allies name at the same time on user's path during navigation on map. In case cellphone cannot receive the gps signals it can be useful to find your path by using around streets' and allies' name on the map as clue and guide. 2) For navigating a location from other apps, when you click on destination to launch the Waze , it only runs and doesn't begin the navigating process and the most of times you should try it several times so that it starts the navigation process by chance. 3) The most of times before beginning the navigating process, the Waze shows to the user the "send location" balloon that it causes to interrupt the navigating process as a bothersome. 4) In term of distance-time to find an appropriate path, sometimes it cannot do it well

Exceptional app! I use Waze for all of my trips, even local. With real time traffic, you always get the fastest way to get to your destination. There have been a few times where my husband and I questioned why Waze was taking us the "long way". So we would go the way we knew to be faster and there would end up being an accident or construction. We would then realize too late, why it had directed us the "long way". We now have a saying and we live by it "never doubt the Waze". üòÇ

Extremely useful app. I use it virtually everyday. The eta on my commute is usually very accurate. It's also good for finding out what's causing a jam. Enabling you to avoid trouble. Worth paying money for but it's free! I especially like the idea of helping others by providing your own info. That's a genius idea.
Stupid waze..maps better than waze..

Waze used to be great but lately (last few months) it has trouble getting GPS lock (unless another app like Google maps or Glympse is actively using the gps at the same time. It also crashes constantly with Android auto. It will reboot/recover if it is navigating to a destination. Hope they resolve this since I've heard from friends who are having the same issues.

Room for improvements: Lack of lane display similar to Google map. Police notification etc are not accurate anymore as users seem to have lost interest in reporting. Traffic data seems to be less accurate as before !!! For little time saving you are often taken to bendy and very urban areas. Reporting while driving is very unsafe and prone to accident. Average speed zone check areas need to be inspired by that of tom-tom showing the average speed in the zone.

A really great concept but still needs A LOT of tweaking and updates. The app will randomly recalculate your route and tell you to take turns and exits that end up being wrong and making your trip longer, then recalculates again and tells you to go back. It's pretty annoying, especially in areas where you can't u-turn or go back for a couple of miles. If this was fixed I would give it 5 stars.

My favorite navigation app. Used it to drive across the country a few times. Great to know where Cops are, red light cameras or objects on the road (I also ride a motorcycle). One time I was alerted an object was on the highway while riding my motorcycle and it turned out to be a 10ft ladder laying across two lanes. Because I was made aware ahead of time Waze likely saved me from serious injury or death. Use it. Better to be Wazey than last.

Marginal utilty. It would be nice to know why known alternate routes are not appearing as an option. A road was closed due to weather so my regular route, which would have taken 8 hours was not shown. Instead, I was shown only one option: a route that takes 13 hours. I didn't know about the road closure so I ignored the suggestion. Present options but warn why they are not recommend.

I see very few advantages compared to Google Maps. Furthermore it can happen that Waze just doesn't propose the fastest route. I had several times the case where I choose an another route and it resulted in a closer ETA. Also Waze just removed a feature (voice recognition in non English speaking countries) without warning the users and without actually remove the feature icon. A shame.

1 star for the way to add your current location easily, in an obvious way! And horrible way to try and edit it afterwards. You need to research online how to do these basic tasks if you're not a frequent user. Come on Waze it's not that difficult designing an intuitive app is it??? Ps. Apart from that it is a good app

This app does not alert you to which lane you should be in while approaching a fork and several other situations compared to Google Maps. While I do like when the app will sometimes get you around heavy traffic, I don't like that you might travel close to 10 miles or more with an alternate route. I do not always want the fastest route. I would like a route that would save on gas as an option. The app really do need alot of work for improvement. So much so... I'm checking out other apps.
Like it, but wish you can save popular routes
Great app shows everything I had police activity on the map and when something's in the road Etc it can redirect you for less traffic and to avoid tolls overall great app highly recommended
Very cool technology is so good üëçüëè

I am an Uber driver and swear by Waze. It economizes my routes. Downside is it has a tendency to route in weird "Waze" just to save 1 minute. One thing I really hated was I had my Elmo mood and lost it when I switched my phone. I emailed support and got the brush off saying you lose it when your phone updates. My phone didn't up date I just switched phones it should be attached to your account. I know it's not a big thing but I really loved my Elmo. Don't appreciate being brushed off

When I first downloaded this app, it was working great. I had no issues; maybe a small glitch here or there, but I was able to get to my destination. But now, I either have to restart my phone because when opening the app, it'll take you to other options or reset on its own, causing it to redirect me to unknown areas. At times I feel like my phone is being hacked, but realizing its the app crashing. It causes so much problems at time I want to delete it off my phone altogether. Fix the issue.

Up until recently this was a 5 star app easy. Now that they've added the carpool function it's annoying and a risk as a driving distraction. I don't want to carpool. I won't be carpooling. And a slight swipe to the left causes it to pop up. So now I go to report a hazard or something and because I didn't tap it just right it's on the carpool screen AGAIN. Waze please please give us the ability to turn off the carpool function if we won't be using it.

I downloaded this app because I heard it was much more efficient than Google Maps. In my experience with in the Suburban Philadelphia area it doesn't appear to take traffic patterns into account. The data that Google collects seems to help it predict high traffic times. Ways on the other hand seems as if it is just giving me directions based on that snapshot of time and then I have to watch as it adds time minute by minute while I sit in the traffic it's brought me to. I gave it a few different trips to try it out and without fail each one started with some estimation of time and then added 20 minutes to that estimation while I was in route. Going back to Google Maps

When it works, it is one of the best and most user friendly GPS applications. However, Waze has a habit of turning off the current route with no notification as well as moments where it does not work at the start. Additionally I wish that the notification in the lock notification screen had more functionality, like telling you how much distance you have left on a road. Waze should also make it easier to see how long a trip would take when your starting point is not your current location.

Used to totally love this app, would have given it 5 stars but I now have a serious issue. Full page ads pop up while I'm driving, blocking my map and I have to close out of the add in order to see the map again. That forces a person to handle their phone while driving. That should be unacceptable. The small adds at the top that disappear on their own are annoying but understandable, and at least they do disappear. While the full page does not. Still love the app, but that's just dangerous.

This was working great, until today. On our way home from Virginia, to Pennsylvania, both our phones kept getting routing errors. We like the up to date information, but several times, it sent us to place, we had been to before, and it wasn't the same place. Tried updating but still having same problem. Google is what we are using now, to get home.

community based app, that I have absolutely NO complaints about. popups can be limited, and are designed to be of interest to each individual user. report everything you find including potholes, flooding, police activity, and if you are the first wazer to find slow traffic, Waze asks if it is traffic, and reports automatically. data usage is minimal for the amout of information provided by the app. simply love this app; cannot imagine driving without it. Thank you Waze! keep up the excellence

This APP has turned into a pile of steamy (insert your own word) in the past few weeks on my Moto G7 with Android Auto in my 2017 GMC Acadia Denali 1. GPS looses track of where it is. 2. App Crashes and reboots 3. 8/10 times it resumes. 2/10 it is reset. 4. Locks up some times when trying to launch. I have uninstalled and reinstalled many times with out any change. It is being uninstalled now and I will again try in a few months to see if it has been fixed. Google Maps works flawlessly same phone, same car, same AndroidAuto

Waze deteriorated during the last few months to the point that I went out shopping for another navigator. To illustrate it, it has been for over 2 hours as it's been happily calculating a route while I had to use the sun, the road signs, and to certain extent my car's 10-year old navigator to get to my destination point and back.... That's right! Today, I hated it with passion.

The app kept closing on me for unexpected issues. For some reason this was the only app that wasnt functioning after a few hrs of use on my phone. Kept having to pull over and restart the app. However, the features implemented on here are decent and while it worked, I did find it useful. However constant shutting off while on the road traveling is a nuisance.

I like the concept, hope we get alot more people's to use this to increase more Eyes on the road. Users should be able to click on their location to ADD police (highway patrol)position. Very DANGEROUS to have to go into a menu system to make choices. That being said I saw 8 Highway Patrol cars on Interstate 71, and Waaz notified me of all 8. Thankyou
This app is a little crazy. And it will make your Spotify act a little nutty too.
replyContent:
Hey there, Alessandro! We'd like to learn more about what you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Gave it another try after 2 years. Still is buggy, freezing up a few times on trip. I can't plan trips. When I put in a day later than current day, nothing shows up after it thinks about it. How about options for: cops moving, expire cop locations if no updates within 30 minutes, disabled vehicle on right shoulder, left shoulder, other side of road, potential DUI with hot link to call 911, scheduled breaks (long trips), integration with Gas Buddy and Yelp, options to avoid 2 lane roads, etc.

Very good app. But could be better as a navigation app by reduce or even removing multi-language voice-navigation; use English-only voice so make app smaller, and have more on-the-road information (such as Gas Stations, traffic lighted intersections, one-way roads guide, etc) rather than multi-language voice navigation. Overall very nice navigation app

One of the slowest buggy apps I have encountered. The Finding riders on the route takes forever to load and even though ride is completed, still it says "still looking for carpool" Half of the time it throws network connection error no matter how and where I am connected. Seems like Waze is only concerned with advertising, because no issues with that feature.

Great app. Love the crowd sourcing features to accurately predict travel times. The issue reporting is great, too. Has probably saved me time and money on many occasions. My only suggestion, keeping me from leaving a 5 star review, would be to speed up initial app launch activities. It often takes a few minutes to get a route displayed. It's especially frustrating when you're ready to go, not sure where you are, and must wait for directions.

Meet the GPS that loses its way.. I'm terribly disappointed with this app, especially that it is owned by Google...This GPS has on many occasions taken me to another destination than the one I specified, and on several occasions, unnecessarily rerouted me through corn fields, small villages with roads in bad conditions and speed traps, totally preferring to avoid (or to be honest, control) traffic to driver safety...

The app is basically unusable at this point. Bugs out and closes randomly, wont connect to GPS and calculate routes (tested this on multiple samsungs at the same time), its interface with Android Auto is an absolute nightmare. I would have switched to another app by now if it werent for the social reporting part of the app. The fact that the app won't even function has me switching to a new app after YEARS of using Waze.
Slow and bad info from waze .

I love using this app -- I use it every time I drive. However, I have a Galaxy S8+, and this is the second phone I've had that has experienced burn-in specifically from this app (the first being on a Galaxy S6). After reading other accounts from other users online, it seems that this is not an isolated issue. One potential solution is to manually lower the brightness of the display, but that makes the screen difficult to see, especially in bright sunlight. Another option is to use the battery saver function to dim the screen, but it only triggers automatically when the battery is low, and turning it on manually when starting up the app is a pain (not to mention it is easy to forget to do so). I would like to see an option to automatically enable the battery saver for every drive, or even to make a separate option for the auto-dimming feature of battery saver that can be automatically enabled. I think this would go a long way toward sparing many of your users' displays.

I've been using Waze for about 4 years now, and l think now what I thought then; it's the best, most detailed, and still the only interactive Navigation system that l know of. Waze will sometimes misdirect you, but these times are rare. I would say that it's 98 to 99 percent accurate, it's become an absolute necessity for me.

Until you implement a way to remove your own reports and mark a report for a remote location it gets one star. Now have a police report accidentally marked outside my own house that I really don't want there, absolutely ridiculous that I can't remove it, and the last thing you want to be doing as you drive past a police car is touching your phone, unless you want a massive fine for your trouble. People have been asking for years to enabled these functions but Waze doesn't listen!
Not accurate sometimes when needed

Used to love this, but ever since recent updates I'm lucky if it works at all. Has sent me down wrong routes on numerous occasions, stopped working mid-trip, and now it even has deleted my account with the whimsical "guess it was lost in the stratosphere." I hope this gets fixed soon, because as I type this I'm stuck in the middle of nowhere having to call family for assistance since I can't download a different app at this time.
Map doesn't stay on top and no option for picture-in-picture mode. Isn't that an essential feature the app should inherently have?
replyContent: Hi Jennifer, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Keeps shutting down on me, I ride a bike so the cel is in my pocket with the screen off, but after a couple of minutes I start riding and after a couple of directions the app shut down by itself and I have to pull over to start it again. App has all permissions granted (battery, mobile data, GPS, etc) but it keeps shutting down If it didn't stopped it would be an easy 5 stars for them, but no. Tech support doesn't answers.

Fantastic app. I enjoy being able to "beep beep" my friends who are also online. It lets me beep my mother in another state. It warns you of hazards and even cop traps! While it allows you to see places you've visited before, it doesn't let you see the route you took or time done so. If you need to see past trips in a timeline like Google maps does, you should just stick to Google. This app is amazingly well built and maintained. I don't use it as much anymore, but still very worth the download.

Heard good things about this app however was very disappointed in my inability to establish an account with them. Spent most of my morning chasing my tail and getting nowhere . It all ended in nothing but a lot of frustration. If they would make it easy for those who are not Facebook users to connect and establish an account that be awesome. Wait for the upgrade maybe next time

Great app but a massive battery drain. Everyone says this is due to the app constantly being online but wait a minute, isn't google maps always online but a 30 min journey on Google maps only uses 10-15% of my battery, if that, whereas waze uses nearly 30-40%!! This puts me off using the app so even though I have it installed, I see myself going for Google maps over Waze on most journeys. The community support however is great, alerting to stationary cars, potholes, police and the like.

I used to use Waze all the time and it was great. Recently whenever I attempt to use it the gps is spotty and inaccurate andit takes minutes to calculate a route, that's if it ever does I once left it calculating for the entire trip 30minutes and it was still trying. I've tried reloading the app, restarting, nothing works. My device is not the issue because Google maps works fine, Waze just seems to be garbage these days.

Only useful feature is the alerts, since they are provided by users.  That is the only reason I use it for my commute on familiar roads . Pros: alerts  Cons: Voice control has only 20-30% of what you need.  If I am driving and want to add a new waypoint, simple to do in my voice controlled Garmin.  Waze pops up an unreadable list and expects me to tap on it.  Half of the things found are not even navigable.  How about sorting by distance, or by nearness to my existing route  Should stay in voice mode until you explicitly ask to end it.  Also, there should be a help location with using voice commands, it is hard to remember how to update alert statuses.  Starting Waze for my commute usually results in "Updating Voice Commands".  Yeah, right.  Not when I am trying to get going.  Always tries to take me around our subdivision for 3/4 mile to get to an intersection that is 500 feet away from my starting point, and it is not a busy street.    I would not want to use this on unfamiliar roads due to the lack of lane assistance.  Overall, the real time alerts are the only redeeming feature. Too bad, it has such potential.

Everything is fine, except when you try to change where you start your travels. I'm trying to plan a trip that doesn't start my current location, but it keeps changing the destination instead. Also, there are times when the app calculates a route to a destination, then midway through loading, it gives up and says "error calculating route". I have to re-do the search several times until it successfully calculates a route. I'd rather it just keep calculating than just give up so easily.
Nice app but ot does not work

Zero stars. Waze is constantly trying to brainwash you to make you follow the "covid-19 guidance". Apps that are supporting restrictions imposed by tyrannical governments will be permanently removed and blocked.

Doesn't understand traffic. Yesterday it predicted 25 minutes in the middle of rush hour. Actual was 45. I was rightly skeptical of the routing. Today I used Google maps, it took me the normal way and was accurate. Now that maps allows you to silence the voice I don't have a reason to use waze. I filed feedback and they blamed lack of user reports. No way. They have tons of traffic data, they should use it.

"WTH i'm on the fwy to work and it changes routes ...EN ROUTE! 5 lane changes to get to the exit in less than a 1/4 mile at 70 mph? Yeah, that's a Real good idea...not distracting at all..."-that was a few months ago and it's still changing routes during travel...I UNINSTALLED THE PROGRAM DUE TO UNSAFE ROUTING. IF I COULD GIVE IT A NEGATIVE STAR, I WOULD! I'M BACK TO GOOGLE MAPS and navigation app...don't waste your time and risk your safety using this app on the freeway! ü§®üíØüí©
replyContent: Hi Mark, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this routing issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I had a job interview yesterday that thankfully went well, however, waze almost made it not happen. It decided to take me not to the destination but to the building down the street from it. I had to ask around frantically to find the exact place. For some reason this has been happening more often lately with this app regardless of how accurate you put in the address. If your using this app for something time sensitive dont trust it. Also, all the ads covering the map while driving(Dangerous)
replyContent: Hey Legro, we're glad to hear that your interview went well but sorry about the bad experience on your way there. If you send us the details of the wrong location, we'd be happy to look into it and update the map as needed. Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Works very well most of the time

Honestly I love the IDEA of this app. All the extra stuff is awesome.
