The problem is I need it to NAVIGATE, not loose where it is, actually find gas stations that are right in front of me, not direct me the wrong direction on a consistent basis. I wanted to love this app because it could easily be 1000x better than google maps.

This is great in concept. For me, its not working quite as well as I'd hoped for the following reason. I use android auto in my car and if I use Google maps, the car's inbuilt gps receiver ensures a solid gps fix but it appears that waze is still trying to use the phone's inbuilt gps so, combined with the phone's location under the centre console, I'm left with a very unreliable gps signal. I can balance my phone on the dashboard for a better signal but it would be much better if waze could utilise the cars gps receiver like Google maps does.

Not what I was looking for, can't drive and watch the phone. Not a lot of difference from texting and driving. If navigation systems can't speak directions ahead of time, they should be made to cease and desist. Maybe Waze should start making gum, walking and chewing gum is easy enough, and traffic is easier to watch then. Waze shouldn't offer drivers directions out of their league.

This app always gets me to a different address, usually 50-100 meters away from the destination. This is really bad for delivery services. Also, if given the opportunity, it will take the driver in the back alley, which has no entrance in the building. This is terrible for delivery services! I ride a motorcycle, I do NOT need to get to the back alleys and I need to deliver FAST, not search for the building entrance! L. E. I just messaged Waze on FB, nobody bothered to answer!
replyContent: Hi Razvan, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more details about this routing issue to investigate further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I like this app...use it all the time. But what happened to the "Listen for OK Waze" option? Its not working on my phone anymore, and I can no longer see the option to toggle it "on" under voice and sound settings. Permissions are set properly. Not sure what happened. Did something change on the dev level for this app that this is no longer an option? Using Android. Thanks!

The quality of Waze has gone down to the point the software is not usable. The issue is not that Waze released a catastrophic bug with safety issues, but rather their lack of response to it. There has been no communication about what is happening. The instructions attempting to fix the issues are hidden in their support site, and don't work! There is no indication that Waze cares at all about their software becoming unusable, which feels disrespectful. Unfortunately, I will be moving on.

Good features but requires a lot of physical interaction while driving. I mainly use the features to help others as a passenger. The search function of the navigation leaves a lot too be desired. I can give an exact street address but it cannot get me there. I end up going back to Google of I am in a hurry. It will give a list of streets near the address but not exact. Some are kilometres away. If this could be improved I will happily increase my rating.

worst GPS app ever. it's unbelievably slow and I've had this app on two desperate devices. I've missed multiple turns and exits because it wouldn't tell me when I needed to turn until my front bumper was LITERALLY right at the corner of the turn. the re-routing was very slow. often it would think I was on the road next to me while I was driving on the highway so it would give me the wrong directions. terrible GPS app. it almost caused an accident because I had to slam on my breaks to make a turn

The app is good but I think much update is needed. it frequently have network issues. at times it will take up to 10minutes searching for network or searching for a route. that's disappointing. also, it takes you very close to an exit before telling you to exit. Google maps tells you to take the next right when you're like 200 feets away. that's enough time to slow down and take your exit. it doesn't give you the names of the streets unlike goigle maps.

The updates have ruined a once brilliant app. I have deleted it and reinstalled it and now I cannot log in. It's says it has lost my account details. This is extremely disappointing. The app cannot get a GPS location again. I deleted it and re installed and the problem is back. The updates have once again made the app worse.

To test this app out I used it to drive myself to work. Well it was very disappointing, a 40-45 min ride with traffic took over an hour, and I ended up on streets I've never heard of. I've taken the hwy and street way to get to work and have never taken over an hour to get there, so based this I won't be using this app as it seems inaccurate with directions.

Overall a true 5 star app. I love the notifications for road hazards and police, area like mine with lots of people using the app it is virtually instantaneous. I like that they include the spedometer which shows the listed speed limit for the area if you are unsure or in a new area. There are some ads but for a free app like this that's the norm, and complaint if I have one.

I have a love hate relationship with this app. It had features I appreciate but could use a few more. Lately it hasn't been giving me accurate results. Super annoying when it tells me I've arrived but I have not and it's still a couple buildings/homes ahead. Also, it doesn't tell me if it's on my right or left just you've arrived. So unless it's located in the middle of the road, I have not!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Alicia. If you notice an inaccuracy on the map, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can look into it. Also, please feel free to add you vote to this suggestion box submission regarding the destination side of the road: tinyurl.com/yysoj48s For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love this app, however I have two comments I would like to make. 1.) If am on a whatsapp or messenger call, a notification will constantly pop up every 4 seconds, can you please allow the operator to acknowledge the message once and thereafter allow Waze to operate normally and when the call is complete to reactive voice commands. 2.) For the future update please add a feature, which informs drivers of the numbers of lanes which go straight or turn.
Some place waze miss guide

This app use to be amazing but recently it has been nothing but a headache. I constantly get an "Error calculating route" even for a short drive. It takes me into traffic constantly, promising it's a shorter trip when in reality it ends up adding an additional 20 minutes to my ETA. At that point I'd rather take a longer route with less traffic. And a few days ago my GPS will not connect properly with my map causing me to rely on the step by step list to get to my destination.

Works pretty well in combination with Android Auto. The only thing I would like to see changed is the way day_mode or night_mode is selected. Add another user selectable mode where this selection is based on the current time. My headlights are always on, so waze is always running in night_mode when used in combination with Android Auto. This shouldn't be to difficult to add...

I love the app, and it usually knows the best way to go. I love that I can alert others of hazards, and they can alert me. The one thing that could be improved on is when indicating there is a crash or other hazard, there is a section to type something but if I'm driving alone I can't populate. It would be great if we could click on buttons to indicate where the hazard is (right lane, center, or left lane, or right or left shoulder). This way we won't be "texting while driving". Thanks

great app, but the amount of bugs makes it painful to use. Some examples: - manually changing camera angle feels weird and behaves weird. - Inability to add friends, when trying, gives an unspecified error message (uh oh - something went wrong). - Cant see iOS users even when carpooling. - username generation is broken, displays 'nickname is already taken' while it is not.

I have been using Waze for quite some time now, as I actually prefer it above Google Maps for all the nice features and Map reports that come wit it. However today I was disappointed by the fact that I was not re-routed to to another route due to road closures. I marked out the road closures from 3 different directions showing that the road was closed, yet Waze kept on taking me back to the same closed road.

Excellent app for drivers, but what's wrong with today? I just opened it and my account just gone! I tried to login with my phone number and verified my account by entering the verification code given, but for some reason I couldn't! It keeps saying something like "Sorry! We couldn't verify your account. Your account seems lost in the stratosphere." Please help! Thanks

Great concept, great features but crashes so much it's unusable. Yes I cleared the cache which didn't help and shouldn't be necessary. This on a Galaxy S8 so it's a current phone. Worse, when you restart it, it forgets that you were in the middle of a trip and loses your destination. I don't like using Google maps but at least it never crashes. I hope Waze gets fixed. I'll gladly switch when it does.

It's a good app WHEN IT WORKS. I do a lot of DoorDash and Postmates and use navigation apps on a daily basis. Postmates has an extension for Waze that make Waze really useful to use along with the Postmates Fleet app. However this app has soooo many problems extracting addresses from other apps. Honestly every other time I open Waze it crashes. If I'm working and trying to use Waze and I get an address to use from Fleet or Dasher app, my screen just goes black and its all because of Waze. I like the app, I like the mechanics, but... Too buggy. I've stopped using this now. Google maps for me I guess.

This a pretty good app but its missing a couple things which would have gotten it five stars. First it really needs to be updated so that it can work with mutitasking/ multiwindow similar to that as google maps whic is why I took one star off. The second reason are minor details like being able to make a route with more then two stops, adding schools zones, and offline maps would be great features to have but not necessary.

Impressive app. I use this as my 'go to ' when I have places I need to 'go to ' it does speed, speed limit, users can report traffic or disabled cars, different voices. I like boy band. It's funny. You can set a reminder message when you arrive like to remind you to get your groceries out or don't forget your child inside or pet. That could be a life saver. Cool free app. thank you for letting us use it without cost. Its well worth trying out.

Something's different. I don't know what algorithms you guys changed or shut off, but I never get the quickest route anymore in my area. I rely heavily on GPS for navigating from job to job, and almost always get sent down a road that's either closed or has construction backups. No longer relying on Waze and will only use as a last resort.

I gave waze a try for 8 months. In the beginning it was great, but it dropped the ball in the past 2 months. It started routing me through weird places where there was the same amount of traffic as on the highway. Then I was forced to create an account for the commuting service. Decided to delete it after that.

I have used this app for years with no issue. Recently, it suddenly stopped working. Okay, so there were issues. Cool. I waited. Now it works. All of my account stuff is GONE. Saved addresses, home, work, recent travel... I am thoroughly unimpressed. I only use one email, so for it to neglect to remember my account after years of use, it is infuriating.

Have been using Waze for many years. There're some bugs on the current version. The map was showing to turn right but the voice was telling me to turn left. I still prefer the pervious version as it won't suddenly pop out funny left/right arrows without road name while driving. Lastly, please always have an updated map so that it won't bring us to a longer route. Thanks.

Doesn't deliver. Used to be great. Fails to bypass large traffic jams even when on long drives and have a 50+ mile notice of impending traffic on interstate. Sends you down torturous, indirect paths all the time, unless there is traffic on a major road, in which case it will keep you on it. Inaccurate and will have you driving in circles and missing turns with unacceptable frequency. After more than 5 years using it, I'm done. Went downhill and is worse every time I use it.
replyContent:
Hi, Josh. We appreciate you reaching out to us and giving feeedback. We would love to hear more about what we can do to improve your experience. Feel free to contact us through Facebook and we will be sure to help. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It worked fine before the latest update but now it just keeps saying "No network connection. Try again later." and boots me out the app even thought both data and location are turned on and working on my phone. In short, I can not use this app anymore. Edit: if anyone else encountered the same issue, you may want to try uninstalling and re-downloading the app. It worked for me. I honestly should have done that before rating the app 2 stars. I will now rate the app 5 stars.

Very disappointed with Waze. Whilst in a hire car in Cyprus, used the app to go to a venue I didn't know the location of. Physically copied and pasted the location from Google Maps into the destination and the app took me a destination 15 Km away from where I needed to be, in hills and onto a housing estate. The road wasn't even named the same as the designated target location. Uninstalled the app & won't be using it again!

cuts out constantly, gives wrong directions, takes you far out of the way to go through extra tolls, freezes and won't close or restart when you make or recieve a call, disregards what you search and just directs you to a different place, doesn't have roads updated so sends you down dead ends or takes the long way, can't figure out how to turn around so it will instruct you to drive for 50km's until there is a roundabout, does save you from the occasional fine.

The worst technical support EVER. I have submitted several recent bug reports about problems with voice commands, navigation problems, etc. So-called "tech support" has been totally useless. This review is getting one star, but it should be more like zero stars. Really disappointed because this app has been reliable in the past, but not now.

I really do love this app! And I am super impressed with the Head up where theirs a car on the hard shoulder half a mile up the road.. Maybe it's human (me) error...but when I search for a location via google, and want to get immediate directions, Waze opens, but doesn't have any routes loaded.. does Waze not communicate with google? Or is it something I'm not doing as to why both google and Waze cannot communicate? Thanks in advance
Crashes and never opens. Was the best app now I can't even open it. and if I do it just crashes and/or says no internet connection. What's going on with this app?
replyContent: Hi Tamika, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app but needs offline maps options. Really leaves you stranded if you don't have data or a loss signal. Not to mention outages etc.

The app does not give you the easiest route. So I used this app to go to a restaurant. It made me go to a small road with zigzag route I got to the restaurant but my friend told me that there is a easier way in the main road it is a just straight path and more easier to get to the restaurant, less time wasted and there are no traffic that time. I do not trust this app anymore. My time is precious so please fix your app.

Like the app. I have a feature request to automatically measure and log the shocks on the road due to potholes using phone's accelerometer. This data can be used to show how horrible the road is. I had to pay a stash of cash today to replace broken coils and steering parts, it would be good to have the data for proof to attach to a complaint.

Got back to our home in the Carolina's after the hurricane using Waze. This navigational app was a lifesaver. None of the other navigational apps were worth a damn. They kept sending us down flooded roads and closures. I was about to give up when a friend mentioned Waze and I loaded it on my phone. There is NO WAY I would have ever gotten home without it. If I could give this sucker 10 Stars I would!

**edit** 2021 and I am getting the SAME issue again. Keep getting NO NETWORK CONNECTION. Why does this keep happening? ***** I used to love this app!! Used it everywhere I went. Now I get a black screen, "no network connection", the GPS gets stalled for MILES at a time. As much as I am not a fan of google maps, at least I know it'll get me where I need to be without making me miss exits (many times in the past two months) and costing me a lot of time and gas money.
replyContent: Hi Brenda, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I loved waze and am a long time user. However lately the app just became unreliable: crashing, hanging up, map not showing, "waiting for data signal" and on and on! This is happening not on some cheap phone but a Pixel 2XL! All with latest updates. If the pixel doesn't work I don't know what does. My wife's iPhone gets the same issues too.

Pretty good. 2 issues. We should be able to change what we see at the share ride screen or at least make one a default so we dont have to search. The share ride should be on screwn when androud auto has it on the car screen as well. The worst thing about the app is the fact that it freezes your location when you are on the a call. I have tried it on different phones and cars and its always the same. Please fix these issues
replyContent: Hi Joshua, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more details about this freezing issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: ‚ô° This app is the coolest, on point, Traffic Alert GPS Map out there. You get a heads up on what's going on and when it was reported, you can also give reports. I love it. It's fun. Real, live action. It's like we're a big family looking out for each other on the road. I never take a trip without my Waze! It's been on point like every time I've used it. It just keeps getting BETTER! But, the first time I run into some BS, I will MOST DEFINITELY update my comment i got here. But until then. üíØ‚úî‚ô°

You can't search along the route after you started it (okay you can, but it only shows results near your destination, not close to you. Not helpful on a long drive.), the beep and message functions don't work, and it crashes a lot. It's got potential but somehow after years these things still don't work. Stick with Google for now.

this app has become the absolute worst navigation available. Consistently takes me the long route and doesn't know where I'm at most of the time. can't count the times i missed an exit because it would show two directions and not give you if you should take North your south until you pass the exit. used to be decent but now it's trash. Google maps gets the job done now

Ok at best, Google maps kept freezing on my S5, so I tried this app instead. although the information on route you will get seems pretty accurate, the navigation part of the app is not that great. often uses the longest route, there is no lane information you'll have to pay close attention where you're going or you can miss an exit and things like that. my mayor issue was that it got my phone very hot all the time to the point where it would close the app to cool down just after 15 mins.

Along with the other reviews, I'd like to add that I absolutely hate that you've changed the alerts. They used to be more specific about what we needed to watch for. Now, all it says is "Hazard ahead", leaving me to have to look at the screen, taking my eyes off the road, or trying to determine just what the hazard is. This may seem minor, but it's a feature I really found useful.

Waze does not recalculate to a new route quickly enough. it's very stubborn trying to get you back to the point where you left the navigation. While I've set the app top not avoid highways, I would like to if I prefer. There seems to be a bias toward taking highways, while on the other hand, it's pretty good at getting us off the highway and back on at a different location to avoid congestion slow downs.

It's the best GPS around, but I find I'm having to delete the app every couple weeks and then reinstall because the map ends up being blacked out and cannot see where I am going. This seems to be happening more and more often. I then reinstall it and it's back to normal, until it bugs out again.. Any reason for this? I've tried the various options that is mentioned on various help sites, but nothing really helps other then starting again.

This app is fantastic !! Used today to take my kids on a educational day trip, got to every destination perfect and not only that, but it told me warnings of accidents, broken down cars ,fog and road closings due to flooding and basically saved our trip and made it wonderful despite the rain . This app deserves 20 star's! ! Thanks devs!!
In spite of reinstall no network error does not go away. Pl fix this
replyContent: Hi , thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this network issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app is fairly annoying. It waits too long to tell you when to turn so that half the time I am passing the turn when it tells me to make the turn. In a side-by-side comparison with Google maps it is typically 5 minutes slower. It does not find the fastest route. And what is the point of the candy and the beeps? All of that is distracting and not necessary. Today I had to go back to Google Maps because Waze no longer works with Postmates since one of them updated. Waze now thinks every destination Postmates sends it is more than 3000 miles away.
replyContent: Hey Nathan, thank you for your feedback! We'd love to hear more from you about your app experience and help with any issues or questions you may have. Please message us on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: the app will just shut down in the middle of a trip for no apparent reason? Just stops. It's extremely aggravating when you are in the middle of nowhere and the app just stops. I have to pull over and try and get the app going again if it even comes up. Most of the time I have to reboot the phone to.get it to come up properly and go find my destination and put it back in. It just sux. Sometimes I can't pull over to get going again on an interstate.

This is almost the perfect Sat nav solution for me, and there is only two things that stop it from being perfect and that is the lack of lane guidance and the lack of offline maps. I still have to give it 5 stars as it has been flawless to use and I've never experienced so many features in one single sat nav app.

Wouldn't be surviving right now without Waze. But they're are a few options that would make it better. I'm in Korea right now and sometimes find myself trying to match signals, when driving, because the system doesn't convert all content into English. Even if you search sayyy Hamburgers...5% of the results are in English the other 95% is in Korean. My thoughts, it you search in a specific language show results in same language. But I'm no dev. üòÅ

Keeps resetting and doesn't allow me to login to my account. I have used Waze for years and was very good but since it started to use Google it has become really bad it doesn't show road works and has failed to show road closures! I have had to take a 20 mile detour twice recently due to using this app! I used to rave and tell everyone how good it was but now I will tell everyone how bad it has become sadly. I have submitted my issues to wazes but still no replies. I think Google has spoilt a gr

After spending some time setting up and customizing the app, I took it out for road testing. It failed me miserably. It just shut down, went away. When it did this twice, I pulled over and switched over to Google Maps just in case the problem was environmental. Google Maps worked just fine.
Great app. Bring me through short cuts instead going a big turn. Colour is v contrast, easy to view. THUMBS UP.
Changed my rating after buying a new phone and figuring out that the problem I was having was on my end and didn't notice. Great app
replyContent: Hi, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this Android Auto issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I like the fact that a lot of people use Waze and can note police, cameras, debris in roads etc., and the traffic avoidance route. A few things I don't like: -The map has been wrong more than once. I start typing an address, it shows it on the list, I click on it, but then it enters an address that is across town with a totally different number. Instead of placing me near the entrance of a park, the destination is right in the middle of a highway. Other stuff too but google wont let me type it
replyContent: Hi, Yianni! Thank you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about the issues you've been experiencing. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Meh. Great idea, but very rough. With the downloads and ratings they have, they've got to have the money to fix this app, so lack of care? More times than not, it takes forever to load my route, and often has errors calculating and doesn't start the navigation. The directions often reroute after I've already followed what it said, and then I'm off course. There's also, often, not enough time after their prompts to execute the given directions safely, if at all. I only use it for cop tracking now.

I use the app for Lyft. Half the time the app takes too long to reset the new directions. Sometimes, causing me to miss an exit. Especially if on the highway. There's also an issue with the app telling the driver that they've reached their destination. When in actuality, the driver is about a 1/8th to a 1/4th mile away.

I have been using Waze for at least 4 years now. I would have given it five stars however the App always and I mean always crashes over long distance around the 3 hour mark and requires a reboot. It's a fault that has occurred with every device I've used the App on, the producer's really need to work on getting rid of this glitch once and for all.

Utterly disappointed. Let's start here. This is the first app that froze my phone. They have carpool app and it takes forever to load. It's not well integrated with map feature. Not exaggerating but it takes more than a minute just to load a message. It feels like a college project newbies trying their hands out. Step up "waze" people. It's been a while u started this feature. Even map service is not convincing enough to use over other app these days.

Uninstalling for 2 main reasons. First, I have virtually no warning time before a turn comes, aside from one way before the turn. In unfamiliar areas this makes it nearly unusable for me, as I have to be constantly looking at my phone or I nearly miss a lot of turns which is dangerous. Second, the way the map orients on loading is inaccurate, and it's difficult to find which way I need to head. Google wins until these issues are resolved. I do like the features and UI, but not worth it for me.

Why does my music app (Pandora) now start playing AS SOON AS I open the app before I even start a drive let alone start my linked music player!! Waze now starts my music player as soon as I open it, and no option to disable that!? It's beyond disruptive and irritating so now I have to make sure my phone's media volume is off before I open the app. I can't even give an actual review of the navigation (there are pros and cons) because of this new unwanted "feature." Fix it please!!!!

This app has gotten remarkably worse in the last six months or so. It will send you on the most congested routes when there are open routes a block away. It will suggest that you take multiple turns wasting time when you could have just taken a single turn. It's terrible I preparing you for quick turn that you have to take right after taking a turn. I am truly amazed at how useless this app has become.

I love the social aspect of real time traffic alerts to construction, accidents, and police. I wish there was a way to support Dark Mode and even satellite view. Also the ability to show rest stops, gas stations, restaurants, etc would be great. Having to do a search each time for any change in original destination is cumbersome. The ETA is fantastic as well as sharing route are top notch.

I hate this app. It can get you to public buildings or stores just fine but it sucks trying to find apartment complexes and some houses in suburban neighborhoods. I have made so many late deliveries because this stupid GPS fails to pinpoint the exact location. And I almost got mauled by a dog because this stupid thing took me to the wrong house and the crazy owner thought I was trespassing. That was the final straw, deleting this stupid app.

I have loved this app from the beginning, it's always been fantastic. However, I went on a 10 hour road trip by myself relying on this app to get me there and it crashed MULTIPLE times or just totally froze without warning and almost got me lost way too many times for my comfort. Won't be relying on this app ever again.

I don't know what happened to Waze but I drive Uber and Lyft and it was always my go-to nav app!! I can't even trust it to get me down my own street anymore!!! Literally over the past month or so it will take the longest and most complicated routes. And the old issue of the arrow suddenly facing backwards came back. For the last few days I'll start driving, turn a slight corner and the arrow will be at an angle all the way to the next actual full turn...
replyContent: Hi John, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this constant routing issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. To best assist, please follow these steps to report this issue: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Overall a good app. It is inconsistent on showing distances to hazards, police, etc. Sometimes it counts down the distance and other times it doesn't. Randomly stops working while being used for navigation. Also needs to be able to select which warnings you want to see/hear. I don't care about every red light camera and stopped vehicle. An observant driver will be aware and most are wrong or no longer relevant.

Used to love Waze and for now it's still my go-to app for driving directions. Unfortunately, there are two big annoyances, both of which have crept in slowly over time and become more and more annoying over time. 1) It talks too much! Way too much. It has always talked too much and now it's talking even more. They need a 4th setting under "Voice and Sound". Right now, we get Off, Alerts Only, and On. We need one between Alerts Only and On called "Directions Only". I don't want to know about railroad tracks. I don't want to know that my route is 23 minutes faster than some other route. I don't want to know that my route is similar to other routes. Just give me the fastest route, take me there, and talk as little as possible while keeping me from getting lost. 2) As they have continued to find new ways to monetize the app, the ads have become more and more annoying and intrusive. The pop-up every time you come to a stop is the biggest annoyance and let me say this: I have never - not once - been convinced to go into a business based on an ad in Waze. As a matter of fact, all my brain registers is "annoyance" and I touch the screen to click off of it. Waze needs to continue to monetize. I get that; but they need to figure out how to do it less intrusively and maybe more intuitively. Waze used to be four stars on their way to five, but they are slipping and in it's current form with all of the annoyances it is only a three star app at present. I WOULD BE HAPPY TO PAY FOR AN AD-FREE VERSION! Are you listening, Waze?

I love the extra features, but I have things to say about the navigation. Compared to Google Maps, navigation is just okay. Sure, Waze gets you there, but it expects me to shoot across a main road with two lanes on each side from a small side street that doesn't have a traffic signal light. Good luck with that during rush hour lol. This needs to be updated so that Waze actually thinks about that during heavier traffic times.

The new updates created two things that people don't want. The 1st is the annoying random pop-up that offers to navigate you home when you open Waze. this only gets in the way and necessitate closing it out to continue. The 2nd is the even more annoying pop up at the bottom that gives you the option to verify whether or not you see something that was reported. This draws attention away from the road and shouldn't be used for your marketing analysis. There is no way to opt out under user setting
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Was my go to app for navigation for many years. However, I was frequently plagued with the "searching network" warning message when other apps worked fine. This weekend I took a trip of 700+ miles and on several occasions family that went with us were navigated around heavy traffic with Google Maps while Waze failed to do so. Plus there is no offline map feature that Google has which is very handy when traveling in spotty signal areas and/or for Project Fi users. Removed Waze from my phone

It is a good app which allow users to shares information on the road (police ahead, road work, animals, roadkill, traffic, detours). There's one downside which the development team needs to work on; that is when you are in a non-major road(1 lane road for each direction). Assuming you are on the road, heading east with no traffic, but west bound traffic is 5 mph, you will be seeing waze showing traffic with 5 mph. that is the traffic for the other side, not your east bound.
Best driving navigation I've used so far

Waze is full of useful features, keeping track of accidents, traffic, speed limits, and police, with the help of users. That said, I can't rely on it in unfamiliar areas. It consistently takes me on more difficult routes to avoid tiny amounts of time that end up not getting me there any faster. "Cutting through this neighborhood and making a left turn across multiple lanes with no light will avoid you a minute of waiting at the other light!" Really messes me up - I need to stop using Waze.

It used to be Awesome but lately it always says no internet or when you click on it, it pulls up for a second & then just does a blip on the screen & exits without me touching a thing on my phone. Very frustrating when your in the middle of a trip & it starts acting up and you're in a strange place. I guess I will have to just go back to Google maps. Was very nice and useful when it worked & gave info on bad traffic ahead so you could go around. Hope they fix this problem!!

Waze is a cute idea, but after using I really dislike it. 1.) I dont like how big all the buttons are in the UX. 2.) Scrolling around maps is jerky instead of smooth. 3.) Sometimes there are so many fast food ads it makes the map unreadable. 4.) It disturbs me that Waze promotes and encourages other people to report roadside events. I dont want drivers around me looking at their phones to report stuff, I want them looking at the road.
It sucks! Always recalculated. It is not correct

I don't know what happened to this app, but for the last week it stopped working. When I search for a route it gives me a server time out message. I tried it both on wi-fi and mobile internet, at home and out and about. I deleted the app and reinstalled, nothing seems to be working. I have a Huawei Nova 5t. My husband has the same problem and he owns a Galaxy s9
replyContent: We're here to help, Suzana. Please make sure that you are using the latest app version. If the issue continues, please message us on Facebook with more details and a screenshot of the error message. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I would be able to use this app more if it showed detailed maps like Google Maps does. I need to see all of the streets around me when I'm driving to know where I'm going. Also Google search does not work when I'm using Waze which really sucks! And now the app has all kinds of little icons all over the road which is very distracting. I have not been able to figure out exactly what they're for but it looks like they are other Wazers. For what reason who knows??

Waze, once my favourite navigation app is falling apart. My fiance lets me know every day when she leaves for work and I could see her route and where she was. Now her ETA is always wrong. Can't see her route, and no idea where she is. The routes are not even reliable. Now I am looking at other navigation apps.

I have made a horrible mistake...I had forgotten why I swore never to use waze again. It's all coming back to me now. For some reason the app thought it would be a great idea to take me an hour into the mojave desert only to reroute me and backtrack on a different highway so that I could sit in on an additional hour of construction traffing, before returning me to the route that I was on in the first place...my passengers are getting hungry, and supplies are running low. Pray for us.

In the past I used to turn to Google Maps to take my location and direct me along the way! Well that was long before I personally met the Waze app and was totally mesmerized with the capabilities, features and options of this one single app!! I'm so happy and pleased to have an awesome app such as the Waze app to be able to turn to (turn by turn) for my driving navigation now!! I've not had one single issue since making the brilliant choice to use the Waze app instead of Google Maps!! Thank you!

Completely unusable with Android Auto at this point. It randomly shows me in places I was days ago upon start up. I've sent logs, I've emailed them and all the do is and me a reply telling to log errors and submit back. Still, no change, no fix. Google maps still works perfectly and I've had to use that instead....maybe that's what they want to happen....I dunno. Confounding to me that an app like Waze would let this go for so long considering the number of people having issues.

This used to be a very reliable app but I've been having problems with this for MONTHS now. Chief problem: repeatedly claims it can't find or connect to GPS on my phone. Haven't been travelling in remote areas and it wouldn't even connect in Rochester NY today. EXTREMELY frustrating!! I even searched online for a fix and found out it had been enabled in my app settings -- still would NOT work. This is a problem I've seen many other complaints about and needs to be fixed universally NOW.

I love this app!!! The directions are WAY BETTER than Google maps. I love how you are able to choose your route from a list given by the app. You are able to use the app without using the navigation; you can see where police are, hazards along your current road, and see how many "wazers" are around you to determine the accuracy of the posts.

I have had the app for about a week now and like it, but the listening function of "OK Waze" is very unreliable and the other thing was the having to drive 160km to unlock other features. I have driven well over that, and it still tells me I'm a newbie. Mostly I want to be able to see the gas prices.

This is a first class navigation app I use it every day it's brilliant for getting round traffic download it now it's owned by Google Maps and it's better than Google Maps! however it is not perfect I have never been able to log into my account on a new phone because it never recognises my login details, also some of us wazers drive wider vehicles so it would be brilliant if we could have more choice of vehicles because of width restrictions on some roads they are a pain.

As far as navigating and giving traffic alerts, it's great. But it's not showing my points so I can level up. According to my achievements, I should have 125 bonus points. But my all time points total is 0 and it's not levelling me up. I had waze before and was able to level up then without a problem. I'd love to do things like report gas prices since all of the ones in my area are very outdated, but I can't do that since it's still showing me as a baby Wazer.

The developers can't seem to get it right for very long. For a few months, it worked flawlessly. Now, it's back to the same nearly useless app that it was before. Takes me on random, completely unnecessary roundabout routes, it won't find addresses, it delivers me to the completely wrong address... The list goes on. Back to Google.

I use Waze to drive to work, which is over an hour. I love how it informs you that there is an obstacle or an accident nearby, but it would be really useful if you could see/say which side of the road it is on so you can get over instead of guess which lane you should "wait" in.  Another cool feature would be vacation route planning. I recently went on vacation to an area with bad reception. When I would go from one attraction , I would lose service and not be able to get directions to the next one. Thankfully the road map and GPS still works without directions, so I was able to find a place with signal.

This app USED to be great! It was my go-to map over Google for directions. Recently, when I started opening it, it never even updates or finds my location to even start giving me directions. It has just become a source of frustration, so I am deleting it and just going back to Google Maps because at least they're maps open and start giving you directions right away. This app doesn't seem to work at all anymore.

it has the potential to be a good app but I've now uninstalled it after it showed slow traffic not on the main road where it was, but going round and over farm land back down to the front end of the slow traffic?? How do I know it's wrong well it was just down the road from where I live so I do happen to know its a bit out of sync with reality, be careful of this app it's not accurate....

9 times out of 10 waze estimated time of arrival is off. The route which is meant to take the shortest amount of time ends up taking the same amount of time as the longest if not more. The back street routes take you down narrow streets that are usually hard to navigate and full of other waze drivers trying to save 3 minutes by avoiding the main roads. From now I I will only use waze as a guide and not trust the app to select the "fastest route"

Calculated routes are awful, especially compared to Google Maps. No offline maps. The app can only add ONE stop on your trip, and then you can't customize your trip anymore. It has problems when starting trip and turning around properly. The app design is ugly and outdated. The UI is confusing and counterintuitive. Editor is horrible and lvl 1 can't do much on his own, only via bothering people on forums. Traffic reports are its only upside, but they can't be reported from remote location.
replyContent: Hi Dino, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit the changes you wish to see in the app to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Considering it has more negative reviews than a 2 star that should be a red flag. More people hate this app than would give it 2 stars. Google bought the app (competed with theirs) has changed gps algorithm, not the fastest just will get you there via what everyone else route shows. glitches with new updates loses a lot of old features that the original developers had ( shame they sold it, was so good back when it came out) . Is now owned by a conglomerate company that got bought and used by ford navigation would not recommend this app anymore it used to be great and when Google maps is on par and it used to be and im serious i have screen shots 7-8mins faster. Maybe ill go public and try to get google to stop being a moron.

Can't get Waze to play audio to car stereo interrupting radio. This worked perfectly on my old Windows phone. And I believe iOS (for at least Google Maps) has option to "play as bluetooth phone call". This function needs to be added and I will increase stars (and use). Also found OsmAnd and Sygic have bluetooth phone call option so is possible on Android.

..has neat features (speed limit, crowdsourcing), BUT $#!+s the bed with Nav time and time again, offering horrible routes, refusing some roads, or not using obvious shorter-route. Someone please explain what the heck it's thinking? If considering traffic, then illustrate it. If considering fuel economy (gas, electric) illustrate it. And it would be useful if it could learn from my driving for future consideration, so it doesn't keep making mistakes.

I used to love using this app because it would constantly taking to me, sending alerts of car accidents, backed up traffic. But, the other day while traveling on the highway from Hanson to Wilmington Ma, it barely spoke,went for miles without it saying anything, was constantly looking down at it to be aware of where I was. When it happened to speak, it was sending me alerts of things ahead example: "car accident ahead" yet when I passed the spot, there wasn't anything there. Very frustrating

I would love to give this app a 5 star but ai can't stand the constant annoying carpool reminder. I drive for my job and can't and wouldn't carpool. If there was an option to both turn off these reminders and the dang carpool button I would happily give this a 5 star! read a thread that said you were fixing ASAP but that was back in July of 2018. Please fix this I beg of you.

Great app, useful to get information about the traffic provided by a large community... but when you really need, it will let you down. Not reliable at all! When I'm lost, with bad internet, slow phone etc, only Google maps will save me. In different occasions, the app won't start, takes too long to respond or freezes. Waiting for improvements in the next updates

Seriously? This app is a freakin joke. First off, no satellite view that I could find. Then I punched in a simple 2 turn route to the nearest Lowes. Started off going in the opposite direction where there is construction and congestion. Added almost 2 miles to a 3 mile trip. Then out of curiosity tried Home Depot. Same thing, starting in the opposite direction, exactly the way it should have started for Lowes. Never even used it once, uninstalled. Absurd. Pointless to even have in my phone.

This app worked very nicely for me, but today, I tried to get direction to the Artscape and it block me from getting directions due to the displayong of an advert. It had two buttons on the advert, a cross and a < if I tap the cross it closed the search, if I click the < it displayed a photo and asked me if it was usefull by giving me a click here if it was useful link. Great work, I could literally not use the app for its intended use. I can understand adverts but give me something in return.

The app is good and all but you can't rely on it for alternative routes even if you have the option for it checked, it doesnt give you alt routes when you are on the road. The gas prices that displays when looking for gas stations around you, are not updated. I understand it can't be updated every day, but for 72 days?!! or it gives you a gas station that no longer exist. I hope these issues get fix, so that my commute can be easy sailing.

This rating would be 5 stars if I could read the font on the screen when using android auto. The font used is terrible, can't read any street names at all! Can't change the font either. such an awesome app let down by something so simple. Apparently there is no interest in fixing it either, since I've read the same font complaints going back to when it was first released. I love the features, they all work well, but the font issue makes it useless.

For me, this would be the ultimate in navigation, if only I had the ability to identify my vehicle a little more accurately - for instance, if I could just let the app know that my vehicle is taller, or longer, than "car" . . . But for navigating an RV, or a pickup pulling a stock trailer, well, it is not real helpful in the routing department.

Your map resolution issue needs work. You need to let people respond to the email for clarification. Your Waze editor has never worked for me. Never. And I've provided almost 10 map issues over the last couple of years. Usually a new location or a D.C. intersection change, so all understandable. But you all always want us to clarify further and direct us to that map editor that doesn't work. Other than that minor thing, this app is my favorite for navigation, hands down!

Waze would be great if it wasn't crashing frequently. It doesn't seem to last for more than two hours of driving before freezing or crashing. Just today, I used a voice command and it froze to a black screen afterward. It's unsafe for me to have to keep force closing and restarting the app while I'm driving. I am switching back to Google Maps.

Just installed this app to use with android auto. A lot of times when I search for a location it can't find anything but if I try to search again it will come up but sometime when I select the location it just goes back to a map and doesn't give me directions. Then I have to start the process all over again. Also if I am driving on a road and it wants me to make a u turn it will say make a left on the same road I'm on instead of saying make a u turn. Would also recommend making the speed limit sign larger. It is too small very difficult to see which ends up being a distraction to driving

The function to look out for issues on the road is fantastic, but when I ask it take me from nelspruit to joburg, when I'm on the n4, and it decides to take me off the n4, circle around to Sabie, through white river and back into nelspruit to put me back on the exact road I was, which would have added an hour and a half on my trip if I followed it..... I start to lose trust.
Cool n all but please make it less power hungry.

So disappointing. I had this app on my phone for four years. Just bought a new phone. Tried to install app. It says my email can't be verified. I went to my desktop and clicked on the link and it said it was verified. I go back to my phone, pull up the exact same email I just read on the desktop computer. I click on the button and it says email cannot be verified. I contacted customer support. They said they don't show my account; not by email or by my name! I had a personalized picture on it, my car information, my list of places, and like I said, I used it for four flipping years. I wonder what the heck it was I was using if all that input doesn't exist!!! Customer support was a total waste of time. I guess it will be Google Maps from here on out!!

I became worried when it asked for permission for contact information. How ever I found no need for it in the app or ability to connect with any of my phone contacts. It would only connects with people via Facebook.... I then attempted to go back and refuse the permission but was unable too. I was also unable to get any timly help from developers so I just uninstalled it.

I tried to use this joke of an app while on a delivery run for DoorDash yesterday. The update ruined Waze completely! It constantly tells me "No GPS. Showing approximate location." as the map constantly spins around unable to find my exact location on the map. I will be switching to Google Maps from now on until this problem is fully resolved.

Used to be good but now I have nothing but problems with it after the last few updates. My rating went down from Lyft from the stupid routes it suggests. I have to keep looking ahead on the map where it wants me to go so I can l find a better route. I switched to a different app because that defeats the purpose of the app.

Horrible search results when being used on Android Auto. I have to be very specific when searching for store, fast food restaurants, etc or it'll give me a location that's not even close to me. Also, it never remembers me when I try to sign back in. It says something like "despite all our efforts your account seems to have gotten lost in the stratosphere" and wants me to create another account where I have to remember all my favorite places all over again.

This app is ok, but it doesnt always give the quickest route nor the shortest. Several times it has directed me to drive in circles, or squares, and never considers going a few blocks backtracking and instead will send you several miles further off the most direct route. I believe its designed to have you pass by stores that advertise on the platform.
replyContent: Hi Michelle, thanks for your feedback. Waze uses real-time data to suggest the most optimal routes to your destination. While they may not always be the shortest routes, they have fewer obstacles that could slow you down. But we‚Äôll continue to collect data to improve routing options. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This used to be a great app until the recent updates. Now it either just goes waiting for data signal forever or it kicks me off and asks me to log in. Logging in with mobile number takes forever while logging in with username gives a failed login even after when I reset the password already. Uninstalled and reinstalled a lot of times. Rebooted device as well. Why break something that has been working? Google maps doesn't have the same issues.

The app's voice command is terrible. It hardly ever successfully recognized street names. Google can instantly recognized. Also, the response of my car is slow comparing to google. After my car turned, it always took more than 5 sec for it to follow. There are many cameras for bus lane and not available. There is no reverse destination like google so I can track how long it takes to come back from destination. Still needs many to improve.

I have been using this app for quite some time and it worked great and I always used it. Recently, over the last month or so it has taken a complete turn. It cannot find my location and just says no connection to GPS. I have rebooted my phone number of times, re-installed the app and still no luck. Hope you guys can fix this. I am close to uninstalling this app and relying on other navigation apps.

I used to LOVE this app and used it all the time, but then they took away the Morgan Freeman voice. I stuck with it because they had the funny Cookie Monster voice, but now that that's gone away all they have are the same boring voices that other apps have, including the one that already came preinstalled on my phone, so now I don't use it anymore and it's just taking up space on my phone.

Waze is awesome, as it helps to notify ahead of time, allowing me to ensure i am in the right place in order to go in the right direction. Also, by letting me know about red light cameras, police alerts, and automatically re-directing me in the best path, it is invaluable. My only issue is that it does not work with Uconnect in my Jeep. it will stay silent until after i am in the midst of making a turn or have entered an entrance ramp and will then mostly cutoff where it is i am going.

Was on a frequently travelled journey and just want traffic information while using Waze on the route. Between junctions 4 and 5 of the M25 MOTORWAY, it kept on and on telling me to do a U turn then turn left. Unbelievable. It didn't pick up the correct route again until I was within 500 metres of my destination. Won't be using this again, free or not.

I, like many others, used to love this app, but its performance has diminished. it used to reroute for traffic slowdowns, but it doesn't seem to be checking for alternatives. The last time I used it, it told me there would be a 25 minute delay because of construction traffic. I rerouted myself on a known alternate route and dropped 20 minutes off of my commute. Using google maps now.

Will send you through tolls even if you turn tolls off. Toll controls are hard to find and control. While panning/browsing the map always adjust itself. App constantly assumes you're driving while using it and locks you out of things. Terrible job. Uninstall. Use Google maps. 10x better w.o half the headache. Not a fake positive review. Honest review.

I been using this app for many years,I was really satisfied with its operation but recently I noticed the blunders in this app, it doesn't take you the best route anymore, infact on some occasions it don't give you choices of more then one route and you know that's not the best route, it has also taken me in middle of nowhere few times even with full postcode and road names entered correctly.

Routinely crashes on its own, sometimes if I switch apps and sometimes if I try to report something on the road. Lags like crazy, made me miss numerous exits consequently. If it manages to load and correct itself after missing an exit, the new route won't make any sense and will add a significant amount of time (compared to using Google maps to correct same error). Police reporting is nice, but having a reliable app is even nicer.

This is more than a map system. It allows for the immediate notification of traffic jams, accidents. Police speed traps. Potholes, broken down vehicles animals in the road. Debris. anything that'll make your drive even more infuriating. You can find alternative routes with it. You can find petrol stations, restaurants and other food outlets. I use it six days a week and i can plan my rest stops. The only downside is you cannot plan more than 2 stops. it would be 5stars if it had that capability
Pro tip- don't challenge Waze when it takes you a way that doesn't make any sense. I've been stuck in traffic for not listening. The Waze knows what the Waze does lmao

Loads faster than Google maps and has loaded when Google says lacking connection. However.. Google is more specific on when to turn. Waze can be a street early, or silent. With Google you click on directions and it shows your route, then you click a second time to start the talking. Waze just starts talking right away and you have to take action to see the map. Then, with Google, you can stop navigation and just have the map open. With Waze, I don't see a way to stop it except to close the app.

geat app, It tells you everything you need to know as a driver or a passenger, it tells you if there's a Hazard, A crash, Police, etc... its very useful and super easy to use. also you don't have to touch or interact with it, it can speak and tell you where to go and if something is wrong on the road, and it supports so many languages, like SO many.
Extremely helpful for long trips between the cities or if you want to avoid the police at night during the curfew. Highly recommend

Overall a pretty good application. My biggest problem with this app, and should really be taken in consideration for driver safety reasons , is when you are trying to report a road condition, the application wants to ask you a question whether or not you are a driver or a passenger. This is not only a major distraction, but a huge hinderance in a driver safely reporting a potentially dangerous situation on the road.

A great app with room for improvement One major issue with the app is "reluctance to direct drivers the opposite direction, eg I had to go to an island where a ferry would need to transport me and the car across the river. I didn't proceed to the island again, but when I opened Waze to put a new address, Waze still insisted that I go all the way to the island just to make a u turn. Another issue with Waze is some times it does not recognize that you have changed route if going same direction

Absolutely love this app! I travel long distances frequently and this app has made my travels safer and also provides a sense of camaraderie with other drivers on the road. People helping people - I like that. A note of caution , do not depend on this 100%. I have found certain areas in various states where it is obvious by view of icons that there are many other Waze users out there but they aren't reporting things; for example, police with radar guns üòñ. I still absolutely love this app!

It used to be the best GPS app. Now it's just full of 'oh-oh error in reroute calculation' or something like that. I'm a grab driver and I depend on Waze it never used to be this way only until the recent update. The location that I want to go would be on the other side of the road and directions to my destination would end at this side of the road itself. What's going on seriously. Especially during rush hour and busy traffic it's really not safe when it just leaves you stranded. Please do something to fix this asap.

I have always like this app. we haven't had a far trip since November though. went to use it today and it beeps with a route change every few minutes with this really loud beeping. please stop it. make an option to turn that off please. it says no time change. no route change that I can see but it beeps sometimes 5 times in a row.
Useless this waze.. Always bring me to road motorcycle..

I use Waze everyday and it's very accurate but the reason why I liked Waze than Google Maps was because there were no additional times shown on certain roads that weren't part of the ETA. This misleading feature is now on the current update so I gave my review 4/5 stars. It's better to report a later time because I don't mind if I arrive earlier than expected rather than later.

When the app works I absolutely love it, I use it through android auto on my cars screen and if my phone turns off the GPS quits working. One day I was all sorts of confused going to a place I had never been. So I keep my phone awake, but I still have issues. The screen will just go white but still. Shows the GPS target. I prefer to use waze because it gives details about why traffic is slowing down and I am not going to lie, I love that cop feature. I get going a little too fast sometimes and it's nice having a heads up. Really hoping the bugs will get worked out. I switch over to Google maps when waze is on the fritz and have no problems on that app.

When a friend told me about this app I was apprehensive. I used it for a long time and was very pleased. Impressed even my wife. However, I am not sure what happened but there came a time when I couldn't log into my account. I contacted support and they couldn't find it either. Was told to create a new account. Problem is I lost everything. All information from previous account. Loved it when you actually were able to use it and didn't lose access to the account.
replyContent: Hi there, we're sorry to hear about the lost account. If you have any more issues with logging in your account, check out this article from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/troubleshooter/9950115?hl=en&ref_topic=10006745 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app has been wonderful in the past, I never questioned it! I am wondering what has happened because the last few times I've used it, it is taking me through neighborhoods unnecessarily-no construction around. The last time this happened the app directions caused me to miss a freeway entrance. Update: we are in Silver Spring, MD and app will not navigate to our home in Michigan. Will have to find another navigational app :(
replyContent: Hi Marsha , thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Pretty cool overall. I like a lot of the unique options & features you have. However, could you make it so we could zoom out farther on the map so we can view the whole country? Also it would be nice to be able to customize our routes. Sometimes I want to take a different street, or route that may not necessarily be faster or less miles. I may have other reasons for wanting to take that route. So far I haven't found an app that lets me do this. It would be great if you were the first!

I drive for a living, every second counts, so to me this app is useless. Don't get me wrong it's a great satnav, warns about problems ahead, allows you to add a stop to your route. All great. It just takes so God damn long to calculate the route. !!! I don't have time to sit at the side of the route watching a little circle spinning round. Unfortunately for me this is a deal breaker, uninstalled. üò≠

I'd give you five stars but I don't like the new design. I am constantly hitting the carpool button instead of the the search button!!it was bad but it was in the right corner before, but now that it's half of the entire screen it's impossible to miss. Also, it sometimes does not accurately update the amount of traffic you're in or what's around you so it doesn't reroute you accurately or timely. In addition, and you're sitting in traffic too long the app just shuts down .

Back to its greatness again. The only app I use and continue to use for over 10 years now. The only thing I wished it would incorporate would be one or two customizable reporting shortcut buttons on the screen. For example, one to report speed trap and another for car on shoulder or other frequent choices. Right now, you have to go through several menus to report these while driving. That's unsafe at times. I never use carpooling, I work from home and that button is not needed for me.

The app is very good. One thing I don't understand is the lack of a button on the map page to allow a quick report of an event. Using the phone is dangerous, it takes 5 button hits to report a vehicle on the side of the road. I use this report probably about 90% of the time. I would like a shortcut button I can program for a common event. There is plenty of real estate to put it on the screen and even allow it to be in a user defined position.

I dont know what's been happening lately but I feel like the app has taken a downgrade. It use to be really awesome and very easy to use. Got me where I needed to go, no problem. In the last few months tho, I feel like the routes arent being calculated right. It sends me into traffic but doesnt show there is traffic. It tells me the trip will be 20 minutes, but really takes me an hour. I live in a major city in the U.S, believe me... things should be updated.

Waze is a great app. We use it on every trip. There is an issue with the route changed notifications. We're driving from Knoxville to Cincinnati; the route change notice pops up every 10 seconds. We're aware there's a route change. There's a closure in Cincinnati, but we don't need updates all the way there. Maybe change the notification to 50 miles from the change then 10 miles then 2 miles. It makes it difficult to see road hazards, police, etc. as it takes up screen space.

I love this app when it works. After the most recent update, this app crashes on my samsung note 8 multiple times a day or it just wont load the destination saying something along the lines of Uh oh something went wrong. Im tired of uninatalling and reinstalling this app that i love with such a passion. Please fix this asap. i refuse to use google maps again.
You should have kept the speed trap warnings, as it was interactive anyway, don't be so politically correct..... Ok

Great app, most of the time. Issues could be with deeper mapping which isn't the fault of Waze. For carpooling, there should be more options in how one gets paid. Please reach out to me personally for more details. Once this option has been expanded, another star may be granted. Thanks

One star because: 1. There is no synchronization of the "Recent" tab on my other devices of the same account. 2. When I choose an address from "Favorites", this address does not appear later in the "Recent" tab. 3. When I search for a place through a Waze search engine, for example, a gas station, I can't click this position on the map to start driving, but I have to scroll the search list and select address... 4. Even when I turn off all notification and alert sounds, when playing music from any source, Waze silences my sounds during notifications. I fixed it on the phone by uninstalling and installing the program again but I do not want to do it in the car android and on the tablet because I do not want to lose everything again from the "Recent" tab. This is a huge inconvenience for me. There will be 5 stars when you fix it all.

This used to be a great app. It have the best GPS, fastest routing, way to build a full route. After the recent updates the usefulness of this application is worse than Apple maps. It seems to be from all of the integration with Google maps. Now it takes even longer to calculate my route, and it constantly tells me searching for network. If the rest of my services on my phone are working correctly it should not be searching for network. This has been a known issue for months.
Nice and good apps.tnx

my phone says it has been loaded by Google Play won't pull it up at all. Plus, my phone is showing a message app from Google play and the only information I've located to fix it involving loading all my contacts and imported data on a Cloud if I'm not mistaken--turn the phone off possibly deleting everything--just danged wack. it has been this way for a while and I cannot locate help. to fix it. that's why I have to get this review when store. I don't have nothing formation to write it other than it doesn't work!

This waze app is garbage. I used this app a few years ago - it was very good, trying to avoid those pesky cops milking law abiding drivers. Now, it's garbage. I installed it to know what's up with people leaving bad comments. It is true, the application is garbage. You need to make sure to turn on the GPS even I had my wifi is on. So I turned my GPS and wifi on, and typing the destination will just show you the area, but it wouldn't give you a route, not a single route. This waze is trash!!

Stopped using Waze after my third fine (yes, I know, I should have paid more attention) whlist following some obscure route and last straw; audio off-button has disappeared, instead there is volume zero, but audio instructions still appear you just can't hear them (music stops for it). However one more star as when motorway were shut, I was home on time

Good for police, bad gps...always takes me on different routes, even when the road is clear, and is the worst with destinations. Once, I wanted to go to a lake, that's in a village in the mountains. Waze wanted me to take it offroad and jump with my car in the lake, literally. Needs a little bit of work.
replyContent: Hi Balanean, we appreciate your feedback! For GPS issues, please follow this guide: tinyurl.com/ydbf57pk We're sorry to hear that you were routed into a lake, that's not good! If you could please send us the route details via Facebook private message, we'd be happy to look into it further: https://m.me/waze Thank you!

content: I'm the same as everyone else, this app used to be fantastic, but now I have nothing but issues with android auto in the car. Constantly says no network connection, cannot locate me on the map, cannot enter a location into the search, most of the times the car screen is now pale blue and absolutely useless. Please fix ASAP. I love this app

Ok, Waze is a great map app. The pothole, cops and construction are absolutely awesome! Here is why I can only give a 3 star review. On my 450 mile trip, the app crashed 5 times. There are no choices on routes that I see. Waze wanted me to drive an extra 1.5 hours out of the way so had to turn the volume off so I didn't have to hear that chirp for 2 hours. So fix the crashing and give choices on the routes and this is for sure a 5 star app.

Okay, but avoid it for commuting. Often makes terrible calls where it doesn't have info. For example with unreported Road closures, it doesn't question there being no traffic on the road, it sees an open road... Fast forward and you're finding out the hard way as you hit traffic in a diversion. Will also send you down roads that get jammed up by smaller volumes of traffic - just because a waze hasn't gone down it doesn't mean it isn't piled up!

I love this app but after the last update, it cannot keep track of my location when in Andriod Auto. I emailed tech support and I was told it was my USB cord (which is hard to believe because all the other apps for Andriod Auto worked just fine). I replaced the cord with the shortest cord I that would fit and the issue is the same. I'll bump it back up once the issue has been addressed.

I've been using Waze for over a year with decent results. In the last couple of months the bugs have gotten ridiculous. It has immense trouble finding network. When it does, I begin my 5 day a week exact same commute & it shows me going down side streets when I'm on the highway. At first I thought it happened when I changed lanes, but it's now happening on every drive. I was driving yesterday on two lane road & it showed me on different streets I've never been on. Please look into this.

Waze doesn't keep navigating when running in the background (phone locked/screen off). I have to constantly reopen the app and remind it of my destination if I leave the app running in the background. I used to love the app and have been using it for years, but over the last year or two the app simply won't stay running while the phone is in lock/sleep mode. Reaching out to the support team has been useless and a waste of time. I've opened 2 tickets and got nothing but generic canned responses.

I love waze so much! It is the best GPS app and my favorite. It always finds me the fastest routes, and the reporting is very helpful when out on the road. It is my goto GPS always! There are only 2 things that really would help me when I'm driving, and that is making you able to have trips over 1000 miles, and telling exit lane directions and which lane to take for turns and such. Google maps has this and it is the only reason I ever consider going away from waze at times. It would be perfect for me if those things could be implemented. Thank you for making the best GPS app I have seen.

Great design but somewhat inefficient navigation. Seems like the app is unable to differentiate between heavy traffic jams and minor stop-and-goes. Today it redirected me several times avoiding the highways which cost me 1 hour of time and many nerve cells because of driving some tiny suspicious roads and serpentines that could have been avoided. It's OK to be used purely for speed limits notifications when travelling abroad but not as a primary means of navigation. Use Google maps instead.

Like many, since the most recent update, when using in a car through Andriod Autoplay, the app is very unstable. Most often, it is very slow to update routes (causing you to miss your turns) when driving and sometimes goes to a black screen. In addition, when calculating routes, the app will get stuck and spin and spin forcing you to close the app. I have to force quit the app and relaunch numerous times before the route(s) will finally update or recalculate.

I used to love the Waze app because it gave the most up to date directions with traffic taken into consideration. It did this while only using a small amount of data, about 10 mb for an entire day. Now, this app uses 25-30 mb just to look up the address and an additional 10 mb per half hour of use. I'm not sure what has changed but with only 2 gig of data per month, I can no longer afford to use the app.

if I could give this app no stars I would. I have tried to enter my home and work addresses more times than I care to admit . i type the address save, then I get asked to put in the address again. over and over and over again . I have tried clearing my cache I tried uninstalling and reinstalling . please fix this problem

I used to love this application, now I am looking for alternatives. My problems are: - a ton of ads added recently which even affect navigation. The app is great so I would pay for ad free version. - Annoying pop-up comes in every minute about adding my vignettes despite I already added it.. - Recently I get a lot of 'Error calculating route' errors..

Waze use to be amazing but now it's forever glitching. When I try to look at other routes, it won't connect to the server, often it's not calculating the best route and sometimes I can't open the app at all. I have uninstalled and reinstalled, but no improvements. Switching back to Google maps until the reviews improve
Unreliable, took us down a route that had 2 massive landslides resulted in road closures for more than a week ago, had to double back to another route, wasted more than 2 hours.
replyContent: Hi Andy, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. If you run into routing issues again, please private message us on Facebook or reach out to us in the app so we can assist. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Best free interactive gps road guide ever, never lose your way or time driving to work or anywhere in the world, traffic avoiding turn guide up to 1 meter accuracy 3 different routes to choose from depending on time - distance, everybody should use this, as a professional driver I did gain 45 hours per week when NOT stuck in traffic. Keep this app free with no adds as you have untill now, it can become the 'FB' of the road. Good work and job well done, perfect app. Thank you highly recommend it!!

1.has trouble finding some places that Google maps easily finds.
