Has shown me random list islands in the middle of the ocean sometimes. 2.stops giving directions when no wifi signal (although map for the area is loaded and on screen. Have had to stop and scroll and search frequently because of this. 3.no bicycle as transportation method is supported. So when I take my bike and need a little extra help this app doesn't help. Google maps supports bikes though, not sure why they don't.

very slow. Almost always takes longer route, for only God knows what reason. l would rate this app a zero, except for the fact, that it does give you a heads up regarding red light cameras, potholes, vehicles in distress, and the presence of police along the route you're travelling. But in regard to navigating, which is supposed to be it's primary function, it is an abysmal app.

Was pretty upset yesterday as I noticed that the recent Waze upgrade changed 3 things at the same time. All of them unwanted changes. 1.) The volume of the voice was changed to full volume. 2.) The voice itself changed from "Jane" to "Amy". Having had the "Jane" voice doing all of my navigating for years it was difficult to get used to the new voice. 3.) With the change to the "Amy" voice I lost all of the street name navigation. I have now changed everything back. Stop changing my stuff Goog!

I use Waze frequently. It's usually quite good at helping me avoid traffic. What I don't like is in planning my route, I often want to add a stop for coffee or something. When I search for the coffee place, Waze just gives me a generic list - this is irritating. I want Waze to tell me "you're going to take route X, so this stop is on your route, or 2 minutes off your route." I think it might do that while on the go, but, for planning purposes, this strikes me as something so basic....

I've always used Waze on my regular routes to get around traffic jams but lately it is just awful. It never takes you by the fastest route. I often ignore its suggestion and suddenly the trip time is 5 minutes faster - so it knew there was a faster way but didn't tell me! And don't get me started on the GPS issues that everyone else is complaining about. They seriously need to fix this app or finally integrate it into Google Maps like they do with everything else they buy.

I really want to like it but the app crashes a lot on my galaxy s8. I installed and used it on a trip from Chicago to Virginia and it crashed at least 4 times, usually when I needed it most. Has a lot of useful features that I wish Google would just integrate into Google Maps. Google Maps rarely crashes... One other observation is that Waze is more optimistic in the ETA estimate than Google Maps but Google Maps was more accurate. My wife had Google Maps running on her phone while Waze was running on mine. Waze predicted that we would get to our destination 40 minutes earlier than Google Maps but in the end we arrived exactly when Google Maps said we would.

I use the app daily to track my work ETA based on traffic. Same route, same phone, same cars, every day. Lately it has started recalculating repeatedly, for no reason, along the route. Why is that? And, can we turn off the "recalculating" chirp noise? It is so annoying! Or at least disable it with "alerts only" chosen for sound? It can be nearly useful when using directions, as a cue to look and see if a change needs to be made, but when using it only for alerts just disable the noise!
replyContent: Hi Joe, thanks for the feedback. A similar suggestion was added to our suggestion box by another Wazer. Feel free to add your vote here: tinyurl.com/yxpbrfv3 Also, please send us a private message on Facebook with more details about your recent issue. Thanks again. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: My go to app for travel, commuting, speed cameras and up to date live traffic reporting!! Finally an app that is always accurate on the road! A must for everyone on the road!

I like the fact that it lists the steps very clearly when you click on the top. And I like the overview feature so that you can get a general idea which direction you'll be going. But there is a major flaw in user-experience. It takes way too many clicks to get going. This is user experience 101. The less clicks the better. I already clicked on the directions button in Doordash why do u give me a list of other addresses? I have to go back to Doordash to verify, then click on go, then go now.

Update. I don't know what's going on, but for months the app has been unusable. The GPS won't connect, the screen becomes unresponsive and resolution isn't consistent on Android Auto. I use to consider this app so critical that it should be considered a utility. I've given up and uninstalled the app - it's just simply too troublesome to try and use recently.

So happy with Waze! I was using Google Maps, but all of a sudden it was never able to find a signal. Frequently. In a large metropolitan area. So I got Waze, and it can ALWAYS find the signal. These aren't really complaints, just heads-ups. (1) Waze will always take me on a freeway if it's comparable travel time to taking surface streets, even if it's way around the long way. (2) The voice doesn't always give you enough warning to turn, so keep your eye on the map.

The concept is awesome, but not having the ability to toggle off some or all of the alerts is a dealbreaker for me. specically the red light camera alert. What a useless alert, I dont run red lights so why would I care about the camera. this is a waste and has caused me to use a different app. Please let me know when this is fixed.
Happy with the app. Would prefer that the notification for vehicle stopped on the side of the road could be muted.

This is the best navigation app. I use Wase with every trip I make. It is always on. When I have an appointment I always use the reminder on Wase to remind me when to leave to be in time for my appointment. Love this app

Update: as you can see the developer replied with INCORRECT info. The link they gave me are directions for the error message "no gps". Not the actual problem I had. Changed review!! several times when I lived in Seattle and now SA Texas. I have gotten lost because the GPS is not correct or the location is not correct when it comes to Waze putting me in the right direction. they need to update or fix whatever needs to happen because I should be able to put in an address and not get lost.
replyContent: Hi Shelly, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. If you run into GPS issues again, please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I'm giving this a 2 star rating for now because I love the fact that I recorded my own voice for navigation and that keeps everybody entertained. However recently the GPS isn't working much at all. It's having a tough time locking in and staying locked in place. I know it's the app because I get so frustrated after awhile that I close the app and use Google maps. Google maps works perfectly fine.

technogically disgusting! Not as it used to be. after over 5 years of heavy use, something happened with waze, the app now CONSTANTLY drops and looks for sattelite connections, its almost unusable. i have to constantly refresh the route just to see where the hell i am. Im baffled over why it has 4.6 stars. back to google maps, SO happy to uninstall.

This app use to be fantastic. I use to drive to work and a road was closed for a month and google maps would always route me that way. One day with waze and it never routed me that way again. Now this app always messes up the distance when you search for a buisness. It said 1.8 in the search actually 3 miles when it routes me. Then it ALWAYS suggest tolls first even if its longer. And the routes are not what they use to be. This really make me feel like Waze is bought and paid for.

This app used to be great, but for the past week or so it has become totally unusable. And, based on the numerous other reviews, my experience is not unique. It is constantly searching for GPS (when, by the way, all other apps on my phone have no problem whatsoever getting GPS location data), it can't figure out which way I'm going, so the map is always turning around showing me going the wrong direction. It's literally useless at this point.
replyContent: Hi Doug, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Good ... BUT it's Buggy and Crashes Often - I want to like this app a lot.  As far as I know, there is nothing else out there that gives you better advance notice on speed traps and obstacles.  BUT ... it crashes at least every hundred miles on my Moto Z6.  And the voice recognition has never worked.  And it just feels "clunky" when compared to Google Maps.  That being said ... I use it everytime I do a long drive and just live with those weaknesses.

I really love this app and would otherwise give it 5 stars, the rating is because I cant use it on my Nexus 7. Everything works exept the maps, which is the whole point..... No maps appear, just a black screen. Do you guys have a fix for that? an older version release perhaps?, I heard you changed your map engine. I really dont want to have to go to your competition. Help.

Waze has probably wasted more of my time than its saved. It has recommended some baffling routes that end up wasting my time. It has even directed me to locations that are closed, why on earth would it do this?! More annoying is when I picked a route home, added a stop and then changed settings to avoid freeways. It then deleted my stop without informing me. I would love to see these problems fixed but I can't overly recommend this app.

I was using a Garmin that I like. This was a little better. Latest version sucks with a capital SUCK. Doesn't comprehend English, will randomly select a saved place and direct me there even if I am going the opposite direction. I have double checked my settings, have I told you that the latest version sucks. Makes me want to go back to Garmin.

This gps app really rocks. Yes, most of the apps around have generally the same features, however I like this one the best and I think it's more reliable and more user friendly. Google App may be a bigger name, but they have so many products, programs, apps, etc. That are all good but not all excellent, whereas Waze, because they specialize in directions and navigation, can put all their time, energy and resources into making this an excellent app, which it most definitely is!

This app is very helpful but it seems too many times it sends you out of your way to get to the same location. For example, when you can make a quick easy turn to get onto the main thoroughfare, it has you go the other way around, wasting time and energy! Also, please, please bring back Cookie Monster as a map/alert voice. His comments always brought a smile to my day! His voice made my constant traffic movement funny & less stressful.

App is good, but one thing I would suggest is to add in a standard time option for store hours. I have dyscalculia which makes it so that converting times (whether it be from an analog clock or from military to standard time) extremely difficult. And it's often disruptive when I'm trying to get store hours in a hurry. Despite that, Waze is OK, except that occasionally it takes me to a completely different destination. Routes can be confusing, and I can't check them easily before/during driving.

It's a good app, the only problem I have it's that it doesn't download voice with street names, Wich I had before I change it to listen the different voices they have available. I've tried to contact them but their instructions are useless. For now I'm stuck with Federico. Another problem is that if there's not a lot of people in your area the traffic it's not accurate all the time.

This used to be a very good app, now it's the worst. I have been driving for a long time and know a lot of short cuts to go around, Waze would sometimes bit me in determining the quickest routes, now it seems like it's working for the oil companies, i.e. taking you the long way. So I am very disappointed and I just deleted it from my phone.
Misleading destinations! Unacceptable for you guys to put misleading destinations. Ads or not you guys took it to far. Time to find something else for navigation.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit the changes you wish to see regarding the display of ads in the app to Waze's suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Use it for police, everything else is doesn't measure up. Navigation is decent, though limited for go cross-country. Wish one could get active updates if a traffic stop is reported on your route and, if it's bad enough, the app provides an alternative route. The advertisements and featured locations/prefered search results are annoying, wish I could pay $2 or whatever to not get them. Add options to disable the passanger warning in search bar, and to disable poorly located carpool button.

I used it for traffic and I love it my son show me how to used it on his phone is the best. also for all those crooked cops, I'm already installed it in my phone. I got a ticket and the police lied, but I'm going to fight so they can remove. is lots of crooked cops out there. they should be honest but no because they are require to meet their quota, Is all about money now, is not about public safety anymore. I was going to be a police officer after I retire from usmc, I can't be crook cop.

I downloaded waze as an alternative to google maps, however this navigation system is terrible. No walking or public transit option. It drains my battery faster than any other app. So if if you dont have a charger good luck because its going to kill your battery in no time. Also, it sends me on wild goose chases all the time while.im driving for work, sending me to the wrong locations all the time. And it also crashes atleast once a day while trying to use it. Redownloading google maps now!

This Application is awsome however, bare in mind the Police officers who are also motorists have this app too and can tell that motorists know their locations so they move around quite frequently making it rather difficult for you to know when they are actually sitting monitoring traffic. No motorist should souly rely on this app. Just do the speed limit and you will be fine. Also this app doesn't always give you the option to reroute fast enough thus taking you into traffic. i was stuck 5 hrs.

Well it's not as crappy as Google. But not all that great either. The functions to warn you of traffic and cops and update yourself is great which of course Google sucks at. However if I go away from Waze to another application for more than a few minutes say to go into a gas station. It loses my directions and I have to re-enter them. Just now it can't find a route to Denver, it doesn't seem to know where Denver Colorado is even though I'm on I-70 done with Waze any suggestions on apps that work

Did a long distance trip back home from Nebraska back to NY the other day. I had used Google maps from NY to Nebraska originally. Waze crashed a total of 8 times during the trip. Which for safety concerns while on a highway doing 75 mph it's kinda bad when you need to reach up and reopen the app and restart the trip in it. Although it's good for real time notifications as far as road hazards or police, the fact that it would crash so often makes me never want to use it again and urge others to use another form of GPS. It's way too unsafe and not always the best way anyway. Whenever I'm in an Uber I always have to give my driver an alternate way to drive me home because Waze is never accurate or takes them out of the way.

I've been using Waze for many years. Up till recently it has been very problematic for me. It always searches for network (even when my network is working fine). Also, it keeps crashing halfway while navigating to my destination. To add on to this, the route constantly recalculates and brings me to a wrong location. I deleted and reinstalled Waze a few times hoping it'll be better but it still sucks. I don't know what's wrong but please fix it.

The most awesome map app. Several different voices you can choose from, even the cookie monster. Very interactive program. The first time i used it, it told me there was road kill on the shoulder. I thought how good is thier satellite? Then i learned you can put in almost anything, good or bad to help fellow motorists. The app even asks you if a cop, road hazard, or whatever is still there and you can tell them immediately. The app tells you how many people you have helped with your reports.

Edit: Ads popping up WHILE you are driving. Are you kidding me? They cover half the screen and dim it! --------------------- It would have been perfect only if it showed you what lane you should be in like Google Maps. I have to switch between the two ad frankly, would choose Google Maps over Waze from a functional point of view.
I used before this app. But seems this app not helped at all. Keep bugging. Keep lagging. Showing roads that let me more lost. Doesnt helped at all and pretty disgusting.

Overall good with navigation. Problem 1. It takes way too long to figure out where to go when you enter an address. Sometimes it will take up to 30 seconds to calculate and address, even if it is only a half mile away. Problem 2. It Takes Over The Voice entry on Samsung S9. You cannot do voice to text even in the Waze app.

Waze cannot handle toll roads. I made sure to select a route from the list that was not marked 'toll'. The second turn in the route was to get on a toll road. Second, I don't know what algorithm Waze uses to calculate routes, but it seems to have no basis in reality. Waze actually recomended driving down a 35 mph road with stoplights every half mile instead of the 65 mph highway next to it.

I always drive with Waze when going long distances. Very useful and other users tend to provide helpful information. The only thing I don't like is how stopped cars in the shoulder are always considered a hazard. A lot of cars and trucks pull over in the shoulder, and so the app tells me "Hazard ahead" for every one. It tends to make me desensitized to paying attention to the hazard warning. Maybe if there was a separate sound bite that specifically says "car stopped" so I know when it's something else.

Not recommended for delivery routes. If it didn't show you that you're on a road facing east for example when you are still pulling out of a parking lot facing North in an unfamiliar area and makes you turn around after you pull out. It is also annoying after setting the route there is constant pop ups that need to hit ok on even pops up during driving. Takes you down too many back roads and doesn't alert or have alternative routes when there are roads closed.

My review is based on using it through Android Auto only and I am comparing it to google maps via android auto. there are two features Waze does not have that are deal breakers for me, It does not show exit lanes position for upcoming intersections. which is extremely helpful. It does not show gas prices when searching for stations along your route. Something else that is mildly infuriating is the directions box, how far it is away from the left side of the screen, it needs to move over to the left more and allow more of the map to be viewed. I ended up deleting it and going back to google maps.

this app is good to give different routes. But on my Samsung galaxy phones all it does is tell me distance but never reads out the street or freeway names. I find myself always looking away from the road. It makes me panic as I try to read what it really wants me to do. I will switch back to Google maps.

I've been pulling my hair out trying to figure out how to play as a Bluetooth call. I just switched to a Pixel 4 XL from an iPhone and loved that with Google Maps or Waze on my iPhone I could get directions without having to use my phone for music. Now I have to listen to Pandora or Spotify in the car instead of Sirius in my truck just to get my direction notifications. Unless I decided to wear a Bluetooth headset for the directions.   Please bring that feature.

I'm Knight level on the app. Would be 4-5 ‚≠ê if not for one glaring deal-breaker. As you near your destination, the "take a picture" option will pop up, and the address text will similtaneously get reduced to a font that is too small to read at a glance. I need the # for the address, not a prompt to be taking photos of people's houses like a weirdo. Have you clowns not heard of Google Street View? It's even worse if you're around a corner or two, yet within proximity of the picture prompt.
replyContent: We appreciate your feedback, Mark. Could you please send us more details in a Facebook private message? We'd like to investigate this issue further. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: My favorite GPS app but reporting location is a problem, accuracy it's off. Most reports are done in motion so by the time the button is hit you're not in the same place as the actual issue. Person who makes the report should be able to pick it up and drop it correct location even if it's for only the first 30 seconds it would be a huge Improvement
I used Waze navigation until they took Cookie Monster out... Bummer, No cookie for you!

I've loved Waze from the start! I had an iPhone and just switched to Samsung Android device. The App works as expected when used in the device but when used in the car with Android Auto (where you would need it most) it is basically unusable. The map freezes making following the route imposible. I want to give it a five star rating but as it stands I just can't. I don't know which app is the issue if Waze, Android car or the combination of both. Hope this is fixed soon.

As a Goggle Map user there's a few things that bugged me on this app: 1. The interface design is a mess. Personally I prefer a cleaner look on the screen rather than Waze clunky semi 3D design. I found it more confusing and distracting. 2. More simplicity. The screen was filled with small text that can pop up, causing me to be slightly distracted because I tried to read it. That's a very dangerous especially when I'm driving. Overall this is a decent app.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Kasyidie! Waze does offer a way to customize the map to your liking. Just go into your Settings > Map display. content: I love this app. The reason I dropped my rating to one star (previously) is because the app has grown so large that I have not been able to update it for 3 weeks. I have unistalled every app that is not essential, cleared my storage, and moved every app that would relocate to the SD card. To no avail, I still don't have enough space for the update. I am very disappointed. Please rethink what is in the app, and what is server side, and get as much as you can server side.
Way better than Google Maps!

I want to give this 5 stars but I can't for one big reason: this app frequently shuts itself down for seemingly no reason in the middle of a trip! I'll be following its directions, then suddenly it will go silent. When I look down, the app is completely off. When I restart it, it asks if I'd like to resume my previous drive. I never wanted to end my drive in the first place! In fact, now I'm three turns past where I was supposed to be because the app simply shut down! Extremely frustrating.

I would actually prefer this over Google maps if it's search function was better. With GMaps i can just enter my destination by voice (or type it) and the first result is the correct address. With Waze it gives me a whole bunch of results that i have to sort through to find the correct address. Not cool. Even with the correct destination it only takes me to the street not the numbered house. Also not cool. I hope you improve the search function so i can use Waze because the rest is great.

Would be 4 stars, but only now can add one stop makes it stupid, having to stop turn of engine, just to re do the sat nav. At a min 4 stops so u can choose the way u wanna travel. Like the route today I need to travel, yesterday it had loads tipper trucks full of dirt, stones flying everywhere so I choose to go the long way around until road works have finished as I don't want any more damage to my screen, but sat nav makes it impossible to do just one journey the way I want to go. Could dobetter

Waze is like that front seat passenger, who is supposed to be paying attention to the road... But, keeps falling asleep. Halfway through your trip, it shuts off completely. It "wakes up" just in time to tell you you're going the wrong way. The other half, Waze takes you to a private driveway, instead of to the main road... Or to a gas station that's no longer in operation. Better off asking a stranger who speaks Klingon for directions.
replyContent: Hi Brian, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app was great at first, but after several times of it sending me the wrong way, putting me in the wrong lane then telling me at the last minute, having no GPS signal and constantly asking me things on screen while I'm trying to drive! I've had enough your app is being deleted I'll just buy a new sat nav its less hassle and much safer!

Only problem I have with this app is that when ask to find or type in something such as gas station, McDonalds, etc. it does give me locations, but does not display on map where they are. I know it will show the nearest location but just prefer seeing them on the map. It's just a personal preference and would be nice if waze could add this.
There's only so many times that I can deal with this app either freezing up and not displaying the address I am looking for or losing gps signal in the middle of a navigation before uninstalling it.

content: I tried using this app with Android Auto to integrate with my car stereo. Like Google Maps, Waze will also interrupt your car audio when giving you driving directions. Unfortunately, Waze interrupts the car audio even when you have disabled the voice navigation. You just hear silence instead of driving directions. This means that if you're trying to listen to the radio, it will cut out for seconds at a time as you approach and complete turns along your route.

Not useful for planning. If you are trying to plan a future trip and you are not at the location from which you will start your trip, the app is useless. I even went in and entered data about my departure time and place but the app still insisted on giving me directions from my location and not the place I was planning to leave from. Either the app cannot accept different starting points (does not have this feature) or it is not a very user friendly aspect of the app.

Used to be a great app. Until my android ran the software update 10/1/2020. Now waze is completely useless. It can't find any routes. Ever. And errors out. Turned my phone off and back on. Uninstalled and reinstalled the app. Still doesnt work. Please fix this issue. If resolved and back to working, I will edit my review. But for now, I give it 1 start since you can't even use it anymore.

content: it was working fine few months before but after the update, keep getting server error, time out error. Was using it just now & selected the route with no toll. halfway on the road, waze route suddenly blank out which left me stranded. restarted the waze, selected the same route but it suddenly brought me to the toll route! Wasted my money & time. great "job" waze.

I used to love this app. There are some things I still do. I use it with Android Auto. But recently, even though I have all sound off, whenever I turn on my right blinker on and the camera comes on the screen, it stops whatever audio I am listening to and gives me a loud notification. It also has a default to take you in hov lanes. I see no setting to change this. Some hov lanes take you a different way than others and it is too late to get out of it.

This program used to be pretty good. It got me through Chicago without hitting any toll roads, it got me through Ft worth without any issues, but after the past couple of updates this is now trash. Waze can't seem to figure out where I am, it chirps and redirects me constantly, without even leaving the road I'm on.
replyContent: Hi Christian, that's no good. Can you please send us a private message on Facebook? We're here to help! Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: A learning curve to learn all the ins & outs of this great APP., but once mastered, such a great Community app on the Mobile.

Great App, but there are things which could be optimized, for example, using multiple devices with the same account doesn't synchronize the history of your search. Currently I use one smartphone as a navigation in the car, the another one is my personal smartphone, early morning when I plan my travel I search the destination on my personal smartphone, and later when I get in the car I have to search again, instead of selecting the destination from the history.

I was disappointed in this app due to the single stop option during a route. I feel as if the developers focused too much on the small details such as the customizations. What i did like about the app was the ability to see other waze users that may be near by. Im surprised by all the hype it has recieved from family members. I personally would not recommend the app to someone unless they were looking for a more animated GPS.

Have had many issues for the past two weeks with lost GPS signals. This is not an app issue because Google Maps is worse. This is a GPS issue, not a cache issue. Either there are maintenance issues with relation to the new 5G conversions, or there is a major bug that is being overlooked. Google Maps is even worse. I'm only rating a 3 star so that maybe u will consider what a lot of ur customers and I r trying to say

content: I'm going back to Google maps. Whatever short bus AI they're using now keeps giving me ridiculous directions. Just today it told me to circle two blocks instead of just taking the right turn. Another example, had me go there exits south on an interstate, turn around and go back the way I came. No construction, no road closures, guess the app thought I needed to spend more time in traffic. Get yer app sorted out and ditch your AI.

I tried to use this on a whim while travelling. I admit I did not study on how the features, but most things are intuitive. It was PARTICULARLT HARD for me to interpret the ICONS used for roadwork, slow traffic, etc. I did figure out "constructios, police presence, etc, but the icons were too cutesy and stylized and hard to read in a moving vehicle even form the advantage of "shotgun" seat.

I've been using Waze for a very long time, but up until recently I've had to switch back over to Google Maps. I guess the shortcuts aren't so great now that everybody is taking them; but aside from the mass popularity of the app, I've noticed some major problems its been having. It won't be able to locate me, it'll get stuck in crash loops, and it's been consistently sending me down routes that end up taking significantly longer than what it says. Most times it sends me directly into traffic.

They are updating the app....will review again when I get a chance to try it out. ....old posting:This app does not give me enough notice to make a turn, you cannot tell me half a car length away from the turn that I need to turn right or left. I need to know way before that to make changes in lanes and evaluate current traffic, etc..

content: I absolutely love this app! It has helped me avoid traffic so many times, and its so easy to use and has many features. Only thing is though is I cannot figure out how to add stores to my favorite stores. I looked it up and it said to find the address and click on the heart, but there is no heart, just a star, which adds places to just your normal favorites. Its not a huge deal just wish I could use that feature, that's all! Thanks for the great app!!

All of a sudden things aren't working correctly. My car icon is now just a blue dot with an arrow. The map keeps reorienting itself from north up to my original setting, even when driving on a straight road. Now the alerts are only working some of the times. Sometimes I hear the audio alert, and sometimes I only get a popup. This all started happening about 24 hours ago. It is all really frustrating. Update: I sent a facebook message like you asked and never got a response!!

content: Useless, does not work anymore. The address that's entered is not used to navigate to the last stop. Had me 10 minutes away from my actual destination twice in one day after it says I have arrived. What happened Waze? I used this app in other countries and other stares and never ran into a problem like this. I will delete and try it again, I will have to go back to Google map.

content: I LOVE this app. The amount of time it has saved me by showing traffic issues and automatically rerouting me is impressive. So is the issues in the road. We have a large camper and avoiding some of these huge potholes listed by users of Waze is really helpful. I can't recommend this app enough. If you travel a lot, then this app is a must for you!
Love it! More choices for routes and way better detailed instructions!

Like everyone else is saying, fix the dang thing! I've been and avid Waze user, promoted it to anyone I would com across. it's recently become completely unusable. As others mentioned, I get the black screen, it loses track of where I am, will say I have no service connection when I have full signal, and I've had to recreate my account several times. I'm moving on until I know that it's fixed and reliable.

I use this App 12 hrs daily !!! No other navigator can be better than this !! Is same like you send somebody in front of you to check your way !! I recommend WAZE because I use it every day at my work being a delivery driver . Speed cameras, police , accidents , portholes on road , avoid route to not get stuck in traffic !! In one word WAZE is like a good friend ! Thank you for the App . And I would give more stars than 5 lol TY TY

Used to love this app. But the last couppe of months it keeps crashing and freezing mid journey on my Pixel 2XL. It's caused me to miss turns and arrive late so many times now. It also always seems to tell me to take roads throigh the country instead of motorways which are clearly quicker. My settings are all tripple checked and I havent set it to avoid motorways or anything like that. I only use waze over google because of the speed cameras and speedometer... but now it's good bye! üëã

This is a really good app when it works. It will tell you where accidents or stopped cars or traffic jams are and even reroute you, but it recently received an update. Now the voice no longer works, the background is now black so you can't see the roads anymore and the reroute now lags to the point that its sending you another way that's just as contested as the highway. If they could work out the operating issues then this app then it would be a top of the lime GPS system.

I love this app, perfect for driving in the city. I use it every day. The only problem I have is the difference between driving the Gardiner Express Way (above ground) vs. driving the Lakeshore (surface street). If there was a pop up to ask which road you are on, it would make traffic times more efficient. Thank you for keeping me on time!
Shortcut/widgets for addresses on home screen for Sony z5 premium pls.

content: Iffy. I have this installed on two phones. It works more smoothly on the iPhone than the Android phone. Often I find I can't even get a route at all. Today I can't plan an arrival time. It sometimes tries to save a minute over a tiny part of the journey by sending you via a route full of difficult junctions that actually takes longer, there should be a bit of intelligence applied to the threshold. Must useful for road closures!

I love this App. Can I make a suggestion? Do you think you can create notification in a ringtone when a certain point is near, bank, pharmacy, hospital...something that creates some sort of little alert that one of the destination points are nearby while we're driving and they'll stay in our maps all the time w/out having to select it each time. We can spend more time w/ our eyes on the road instead of trying to focus on a tiny map. If you can make that happen this App will be dope üòéüí™üëå

Much more informative than Google Maps - I'm enjoying using this app. Only criticisms would be that the last couple of times I've used it, the map has frozen and I've only become aware of it once I've started off, so therefore have had to find a safe place to pull over, stop the app and clear cache before continuing. Also I find it odd that you can't sample a Voice before selecting.

What's the possibility of including the following features? When you add a stop the ETA shown is only for that 1st stop - can't the ETA for the final destination also be shown (in parentheses maybe)? Also, I find that we can't go back to a location to report an incident after we've passed there. Very impractical. Can't just stop in the middle of traffic just so that we can report the incident at the correct location. Would be good to go back to the location once we've found a safe place to stop

This is to Waze development. Why did you remove a feature that the whole purpose is to voice navigate without touching the phone while driving. Removing that feature encourages accidents may happen. To many it makes total sense for youth and unexperienced drivers to have that feature to save and protect drivers. Now some of us will have to use other apps. Makes no sense. Maybe you need a better development team!

content: Creators must work with gas companies. Too many times the GPS suggests a road that isn't even needed for your route. Literally had it say to go down a road, pull a u turn then go back on the same road I came from just to continue driving in the same direction. Just randomly decides to add time to your trips. Do not waste your time or gas money.
replyContent: Hi Pop, we're sorry to hear about your bad experience. If you send us a private message on Facebook with more details about this route, we'd be happy to look into it further. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app is hit or miss. Sometimes it is good and other times it is not so great. I like that it alerts me to red light cameras as well as speeding cameras. There are tons of speed traps in Chicago, so being alerted to the speed and red light cameras is a fantastic feature. I wish it would speak/talk when there is a police car nearby. I don't know what some of the WAZE symbols mean. SOMETIMES it talks. Other times it doesn't. Very odd/weird.

At the beginning, this app was amazing. User submitted reports, a community, and also accuracy. These days, there's some community reports, but you don't get the same notifications as before. Also, what really makes me mad is that it will give me really bad directions. It will make me take a route that was completely unnecessary from the usual. Ever since the Google acquisition, it has only been a slow death to Waze, which is so unfortunate. It's obvious, that Google wants gmaps to be better.
Always taking me through the highways, regardless if there is a shorter way, and the road traffic is not updated to the present time.

I use the app most days for work, even if I know the route, but I could be working anywhere in London. 9 out of 10 times it will be great, but I guess there are times when no route options are good. I think that the app would be improved if you had the ability to select a road to always avoid, like how you can avoid toll roads but more specifically. For instance, the route planner will try to take me through Rotherhithe tunnel in London but my vehicle cannot go down there. Good work, everyone!
replyContent: Hi Thomas, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. content: If I was just driving a vehicle with car plates, I would give 5 stars. However, there is no option for a pickup truck. In Chicago, there are special rules about driving on LSD as well as boulevards. That would be a nice option between car and semi truck. Adding height and width would be nice for trailer hauling as well.

Used to be a great app, but hasn't worked since March. It's quite literally unusable right now on my Android. Which screws me, because I relied on it for Postmates integration. Can barely find GPS, cannot hold a lock, slings you around the map when it doesn't freeze you, constantly has trouble connecting to network. Google maps doesn't work well in my area for Postmates, so it would be nice if this eventually gets fixed. So far about 4 updates with no improvement whatsoever.

The best navigation app on Google Play. Always shows the best and most logical route to take, shows railroad tracks (unlike Google Maps) and is built for hands free driving with little to no interaction ever needed. Has its own standalone report system on top of live traffic data, and is the only app that's going to get you the information you need, right when you need it.

Best app, specially with speed cameras, it gives you a real time update with traffic with a 5-10 min margin error sometimes,the GPS location plays up specially when near motorway there are small side roads but it calibrates instantly, I have not found a better app, no Google maps,tomtom nothing and its free. Only think would be nice if once you finish your journey you can add it as favourite for example if you have an account so every morning based on your commuting can give you real time updates or traffic support. Also the meniu for the most used road obstacles or police would be nice to e added instead of going through all the list while driving, it takes to much time but 10/10 10* iy is the best for todays apps.many thanks
To many problems after the new update. It doesn't load anymore even after I uninstalled it and installed it like 6 times.

content: 1st of all.. this app usefull.. after several day.. this app give complicated route.. and the information on the road(map) 50% true, 50% more go to river.

Where I lose my sense of direction, Waze helps me. The new update has also better pronunciations for Farsi words, so while driving, I just listen to what it says without loosing my concentraion on the map. Things that can be improved. One is that sometimes voice has delay, and second when there is multy exit way in front path explanation is ambiguous and one must look into the map. In all it is quit satisfying.

I have raised my review score because the routing display issues have been corrected. I now use this product to guide me in daily navigation for my delivery job. I still have an issue, with the colors on the screen not displaying the same when connected to my car head unit. I know that it can be done, because it happened by accident one day, and returned to what it had been doing when I turned engine off and tried to restart it.

Appreciated that if the team could take a look on the application bugs. Waze is my best companion when I'm driving. On 10 May, I'm using waze as usual for my driving. However, the direction wasn't correct. It lead me to the opposite way of my destination. Say for example, the way I suppose to go, road board refer me to the right. However, waze refer me to the left.

content: Location on screen is off just enough to make me miss turns. Several times I've been instructed to make a turn one direction only to be told to make a u-turn immediately after. Facebook integration is not something I want. I started a Waze account for the wife so we could share easily but that's not possible anymore; fb required. The only thing Waze really has going for it is the ability to flag dangers on the road.

I enjoy using Waze, and there are days I hate using Waze. Yes, it (usually) does give me the fastest route, but sometimes it doesn't update the route. Sending me a back way when traffic has cleared up and I have could of taken my normal way. Also the ads are annoying, I'm not interested in going to additional places. If I was I would of put them in to go there.

Used to be 5 stars, but since the latest uodate the app will not close now. I have to completely restart my device for it to go away. Also, for some reason they have made it next to impossible to leave reports of accidents, traffic, etc. while driving. I looked everywhere for the option to leave a report. Used to just have to touch the screen, quick and easy. While I sat in stand still traffic, due to a road closure because of a fatal accident, I looked but couldn't find it anywhere. üò§üò§

content: I've been using Waze for 6yrs. I absolutely love it! Until recently... I bought a 2020 F150 and it worked great with Android Auto for 4 months. Last week when I connected via Android Auto, my car icon doesn't show me facing the wrong direction. IE- I'll be facing/driving north and my icon continues to show in facing southeast. It's because of this, i think my direction guidance keeps lagging. It'll freeze location, then jump/speed up to catch up. I've tried everything to fix, but doesn't work.
replyContent:

content: Awful Sign-in Process. If you change phones and can't remember the random nickname assigned by the app, you can't retrieve it using your email or phone number. It would keep saying it found an account under my number, but then say it was lost. When I requested to change my password, I was able to do so, but sti couldn't figure out what my random username was. contacted support, but they never replied.

Very useful. However, one big complaint. I'll just be driving along and it decides to shut out of Waze randomly especially if its in the background. It might have to do with that I have a Pixel but still. I will think Waze is still on since I never turned it off and all of a sudden I realize it's been quiet for far too long. Then I have to go back into waze, wait a long time for it to recalculate my route, and then waste time and gas turning around since it had never told me to turn.

I agree with the most recent Waze users. The GPS signal...there is none. While I DO know how to read a map, it is too dangerous to reference your map or paper kr whatever rather than keeping both eyes and ears on the road. It's not practical. In its inception, Waze used to be on point, healthier confidence than with Google. This app used to provide real time updates, real time short cuts, and reroutes during heavy traffic. Waze has lost luster and user confidence

Great navigation app but I would love for there to be a shortcut to change the voice prompts volume on the go without having to go through entire settings as I sometimes have music loud and sometimes not and then I don't hear Waze. Also Wazw does not work for me through Android Auto on my new car which is frustrating. Keeps telling me I haven't finished setup for the first time, when I've been using Waze for a few years now. And Waze doesn't even open on my phone when connected via USB

Still drains your battery REALLY fast, even when it's charging. The user interface is far from user-friendly or easy to use. No lane guidance so it's very very easy to miss your turn. Save time, petrol, headaches and your battery, use Google Maps. It's not perfect but it's a shitload better than this garbage. Obviously built by amateurs who learnt app development from a free online course. You get what you pay for.

The routing algorithm in this app is so terrible. There have been many times where Waze will tell me to take an incredibly complicated route when I know from experience that there is a much much simpler and faster path. Apart from knowing where speed cameras are, this app doesnt do anything else well.

Domino's Delivery Driver‚Äî Map was good/accurate for about 3 hours. Then it started asking for location permissions over and over, as well as taking me around the block a few times before it could figure out the destination. Sometimes would take me to the incorrect destination blocks away or give unavailable routes. Would not recommend or download again. Ever.

It used to be the best gps free app and i really enjoyed,but from 2 years now it's keep freezing,or giving errors like "no connection" and closes alone,also on the highways force you to go out and come back again,last updates was terrible wrong,must to add that don't show additional routes,afterwards good job guys,but please improve it...

Used to work perfectly but since Google has gotten its hands on this app it's been all down hill! Thanks a lot!! For the past 2 weeks everytime I try to use this app it's either showing as connection issues, which is bull as all other app work fine, just tries to load or crashes. I tried to delete and reinstall it over 20 times and the issues has only gotten worse. This is all on top of all the bogus routes, redirection and general nonsense that it's been up to up until these major issues

I like this apps a lot. The map was easy to follow and the traffic information was superb. But this past few months, the apps need longer time to load, searching for network and GPS. Sometimes it take longer to search for routes or unable to search routes. When try to reload the apps it freeze. What happen? You need to fix this issue.
Fab on the road Friend always looking after you .

The app works great, aside from frequently opening itself unprompted. However, the amount of data it collects on my driving habits, even when I don't use the app, is disturbing. The app has repeatedly correctly predicted my destination as soon as I opened it, even though that destination is farther away than a "favorite" destination. I rarely use this app outside of work, so for it to predict my destination when I'm not working is incredibly creepy. I'm uninstalling this immediately.

This used to be my favorite GPS app, but my biggest complaint is that it doesn't take me on the easiest, quickest, and straight forward route which is annoying...for an example if Im going somewhere and the best and fastest route is to go straight on 95, it will make me exit, and take me on a winding course only to end up back on 95.... when I could've just stayed straight on 95 and arrived at my destination sooner...what happened to this app???

I just installed Waze. It seems like a really neat application. It's very user friendly. I can even customize the voice. One problem I noticed right out of the chocks, though. I selected a complete address from my Google calendar but Waze didn't see the street name, city, state or zip code. It only presented a list of addresses that had the same house numbers, some more than two thousand miles away. I had to go through that list to find the one I needed. I'll update after i use longer...

Easy to follow instructions. Reroute automatically but sometimes it will give you longer distance route just to avoid traffic which for me is not really necessary depending on the situation (if the usual route I take is not really heavy in traffic, it will just waste my time having to take the longer route). Overall a really good app. Helped me a lot. Thank you developer.
Me & my hubby Love this app, But u need to add an Icon for people who have ELECTRIC CARS, So we can fine places to charge our cars. Especially places with SUPER CHARGERS!! - That'd be AWESOME!!
Utterly useless. The app can't get a GPS signal with wifi, GPS and mobile networks all turned on in central Glasgow. 'Waze'? More like whazz.

content: I want to love it but there are a few issues. Great for short distance driving but when you do long distance it tends to freeze or crash at the worst times being that youre driving. This has happened with multiple phone's ive used. Those have been the only problems I've had with this app. The live traffic route updates come in handy and are great. Also the way you can get live updates on the road from other people ahead of you is an amazing idea.
Abu Dhabi road speeds not updated & speed cameras not updated
it's a slow apps and confusing user. could lead accident since its late give direction. always changing recommandation while journey. i guess google maps more better

Waze has lost it Waze! Sure it wasn't perfect at times, but now it's completely gone off the grid & for the longest time (over a month easily) without a resolution or even an attempt in sight. If the hardware manufacturers don't let you down the software developers will, then they'll blame each other leaving you frustrated & stranded. Planned obsolescence at it's finest!

Awesome Map! I love the live information it gives you! I got rid of our GPS in the car because this has so much more and the information is VERY accurate. I've been using Waze for several years now and it just keeps getting better. It's so personable and accurate for my daily needs and then when we go on long road trips its e even more exciting to use!! Thank you Waze developers!! You got a great thing going here!!

So I have few problems and suggestions all which based on Android Auto: 1. If your GPS settings are changed then I it doesn't notify me and can't find my location so I need to go to Google maps and then maps will suggest me to change settings and then it locates my location 2. Speed changes on the roads are not informed before hand. I drive with 100 and suddenly 60. So annoying. 3. App sometimes does not respond on Android auto screen. I can't click on icons or report. I do see the road and all the reported incidents but it doesn't log my reports or doesn't let me select an incident on the map. 4. Previous addresses are not cached hence I need to enter the full name each time. It suggests most unrelated places until I fill the full name.

So many problems with this app compared to Google Maps especially when using Android auto on my trucks display. First of all user interface is clunky as I am always looking for places in areas I'm not familiar with. It only shows how faraway a place is not if its along my route. My biggest gripe is that it seems to avoid toll roads even though I tell it not to when the time difference is within a minute or two. My company pays for my tolls and I want to get where I'm going as fast as possible.
It was ready. To take me whatever I want to go.

This used to be a good and interactive driving navigation app. Now it has a very clumsy and non-intuitive* user interface, and function-wise comes nowhere near the usefulness of Google Maps. *For example, who would guess you need to tap the search icon to go to settings. Or when the app knows there is road work somewhere on your route, it refuses to show you any details, such as WHERE it is.

I have had the same phone number and email address for years and when I downloaded this app it worked okay until I got a new phone with the same phone number and email and it couldn't seem to find my account I tried to recover my account several times& it would not. In the past four months on three different occasions it has deleted all of my trip history so I am done with this app I will no longer use it! The Updates are horrible. As soon the app updated All of my trip history was deleted.
Couldnt pick up up my GPS signal, after several attempts and restarts

content: I love the app but dont like how some imformation is blocked until you are a quarter or half mile away from it (reason for only 4 stars).There is nothing wrong with people sharing information with people. I also think there should be an option to time stamp moving public service or hazardous vehicles to show that "at that location said vehicle was driving at said time" and maybe an option to leave a comment bubble at any specific location clicked that others could click on to see what you said.

Absolutely loved this app especially cookie monster as my guidence and have had it on most all my phones since 2016. That being said I need to know if my destination is on right or left side of the road, it always lags right as I'm arriving. The biggest annoyance is that it force closes my Google playstore. Only reason I deleted it. I can't open playstore without it continuously crashing and then I'm left with a bugged out phone. What a joke. Make an ad free paid version.

As a regular Waze user, I would say, overall, its good but lately Waze has been showing me a longer route. Eg. I am supposed to go straight at a junction but Waze showed to turn left, then make a U-turn and go back to where I was. I went straight instead (ignoring Waze) and resulted in shorter distance and time. Hope something can be done about this. This has happened to me quite a number of times. Thank you.

Took me the most indirect route imaginable that I had to correct myself, and added about 15 minutes into my 20 minute commute as a result. Did not give me enough notice of when I needed to turn, and did not say street names when approaching the street (only when giving the initial direction some 3km away), so I didn't know which street to look for. Sounds were also alarming. Was very stressful.
Sometimes, it is very stupid like its brother, the Google Maps üò†üò†üò†üò†
replyContent: Hi Aris, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more about any issue you're experiencing with the app to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The best navigation app ever! I am writting this review right now that the app helped me find my parked car. And i didn't even know that it had this feature. I just etered the app to see the roads and it showed me my car's location. Moreover it shows the police's cars that wait for speeding tickets. Really love this app.

Used to love this app but it's slowly going downhill! Things popping up distracting you when you are driving, taking ages to load and reroute, never updates for closures and when you are driving and want to quickly change the voice commands when you have no chance to pull over its like 3-4 different options distracting you from driving. Also typing in addresses it can take a while to load which never used to be the case. Then you are driving and adds pop up blocking your view. Getting worse
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Stephen! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. content: I like the app a lot, esp. the ability to report hazards. The search function is not great, often returning far away results. The search should include and prioritize saved/favorite locations in results, for example "Mom's House". Also, I would like the ability to have the app avoid specific roads. There is a road that the app suggests on my way to work every day, but I bypass it every day because it has difficult intersections. Let me block it from being used for navigation.

Good for shorter trips but cumbersome for long trips. Rerouting on major highways to save 2-3 minutes of overall drive time is ridiculous. It should give you the option to reroute instead. Also, it does not give enough advance warning of turns and doesn't have accurate info on one way streets in cities. I'll stick with Google.

garbage app. couldn't calculate a single root to my destination, (which Google maps had no problem routing to) I was hoping Waze could provide a better service, but it couldn't even manage its base function, just a repetitive "uh oh couldn't find route". I popped in some other nearby locations to see if the gps was working, and it managed that. But for any big outings, it cant do a thing. back to Google I guess.

The app itself is useful, easy to use. But it some times decides to stop working while I was driving. And then it couldn't find my starting point and then it couldn't connect to the system. I had to uninstall and install back, reset my connection, flight mode on and off. Come on la.

It's good app, but it is lug in Android Auto. There's delay between you position and on the map. It would be great if it's an option Detour just traffic, instead of find a new route. The finding route algorithm is not perfect. It gives you options of 3 route, but often it's the same route just 2-3 streets are different. And no choice to escape traffic. It doesn't work great with bridges. It suggests routes after the bridge. I have been using the app during 2 years in daily basic.

I rideshare, so having a good navigator is essential. Waze was awesome, but over the last 6 to 9 months it has tanked. I'm in the Portland market and most locations are inaccurate. They also have a lot of connectivity/freeze issues. I love the speedometer feature, even though their speed limit is inaccurate in many locations. I also drive at night and it has a night time option, so it's not as bright. The real time traffic and hazard notices are still great.

Great App generally, however since about 2-3 updates ago, the screen to add traffic reports etc no longer formats correctly on an android car stereo headunit, so the only reports you can add are anything from Hazard reports to the right. You cannot scroll to the left to add a crash, police, traffic etc. Also the screen to add road closures is far too complicated to use whilst on the move, if you could add later when safe to do so, then it would be much better. Great app otherwise.

Love Waze. It's a better app and easier to use than Google maps. It clearly shows obstacles ahead. Due to the fact it's used by so many people who update it constantly. If you see an issue, animal or people on motorway you touch screen to update and it's related instantly to all around you. It also has a help button if you need help. If you are in an area you don't know it shows all the local shops, garages etc to find just what you need with distance and time

My experience with Waze is awful. Definitely the worst GPS app I have ever used. Whenever I have used it, it would take me the long route, instead of the shortest. Or even sometimes, the incorrect route. If you are using this app because of community based reporting, I would recommend Google maps instead. Google maps let's you do the exact thing, with a far better GPS system, with the quickest route, including best accuracy.

content: Updating my review again. 1 star for being practically useless the past few days. It takes forever to find the network/gps/ calculate route. Meanwhile, Google maps is able to do all this in less than 5 seconds. Edit: it started to work a little better for a while. But as of today Waze could not connect to gps for the past 4 days. Even restarting my phone could not fix it like it used to. It's only barely usable as it can still somehow show my location as I drive along the route.
Best Waze around town!

Waze is definitely NOT supported the same as it was. wrong directions. not suggesting quicker routes. no indication of road closures (but they are on google). something has changed for the worse with this app. Do not install it. Find something else. or just use Google maps. which probably why Google doesn't support waze the same as when it was privately programmed and awesome. Was great, now it is acutely inconvenient and will give bad directions.

I love this app, I use it for every trip and it always gets me to my destination without any issues. But, with my most recent situation, it would be great if Waze could add a feature for vehicles like moving trucks. For example, adding in the dimensions of said vehicle to know about certain clearances for the height of the truck for bridges and going to get gas to fuel up. Until that feature comes, I had to install a different app to help with this.

Not working as it did in the past. This was previously my preferred app for navigation, but have barely used it in the last three months due to persistent connectivity issues. I consistently receive an error message about being unable to connect to the routing server or whatever when opening and attempting to use. Too bad, since I enjoyed using the app up until now.

Waze needs a way to report traffic light outage. I can think of a group of 3 buttons, total outage, flashing red, or flashing yellow. In Denver today, due to heavy blowing snow, there were 2 outages already on Santa Fe, which is a major road going through town. I didn't see the option to report that, unfortunately.

Very disappointed in Waze. I downloaded this app to help us navigate home after Hurricane Florence, as many roads were flooded or closed. Waze showed NO information about weather-beaten closures. The info it did have was out of date, like a note about road construction that was 2 months old. Waze may work well for some situations, but it was useless for me.

It's difficult to use - you can't read the instructions in full (as in a list), only use it in navigator mode. No option for people that feel centered on where North is, don't need a spinning map to read and want to read through the route before leaving, and maybe even drive without GPS on (Gasp!). The screen is so cluttered with logos you cant see the streets properly. The zoom is extra touchy so you're in to street level or out at full 5 sq.miles of city.
