content: Love the app, it keeps improving every update. I gave it 3 star because of the account recovery, they don't even try to recover it, it will straight up tell you that they can't. First, it will tell you that your number is familiar, then will send you a code to verify your account, 3 seconds after sending the code, it will tell you "sorry... despite all our efforts, we are unable to verify your account" I discovered that just by re-logging you current account will make waze forget everyrhing.

I love my waze!!!! Can't get in the car and drive without it. Gotta know where them cops are üòâ but the one thing I find as a negative, I wish it would show details like Google maps when you get to your destination. Like the picture of the place, and also walking distance. It kinda just dumps you off at the end of your route. But I still love my waze.

I rated maps rather poorly a number if months ago and try to avoid using my phone in my car anyways. Today I decided that if you don't know to get where you're going it's best to just plan ahead and use MapQuest or something. This app sucks and will direct you to places that no longer exist or just it will operate incorrectly to the point directing you to go the wrong way altogether. I don't care to share details, I've now given enough information for your consideration.
Brilliant real time navigation app

Popup ADs are really annoying. BUG REPORT: The "car info" button stays on the screen and covers the car pointer. WORKAROUND: swipe the map in any direction and then recenter: it will disappear. Shoudn't this work: flip the phone in portrait mode, then flip it back to landscape, then do the map swipe and recenter. Developers, move that silly "car info" in the preferences! I declassed the app to 3 stars (for the ADs!).

Mostly a great program especially when paired with Android Auto.Several nitpicks: why not leave the speed limit sign full on the side instead of shrinking it to a size too small to see on most car screens with AA or Apple CarPlay? It seems like such a little fix that is really a big annoyance. Wouldn't it be safer to be able to glance at the speed limit sign then try to hunt for it (because it's so small) when you're driving? Second- what's with the zoom buttons? Why is it such an effort to zoom in and out when using Waze with Android Auto (causing more of a distraction?). Can we just have "always on" zoom buttons or a slider? Finally, why is it so hard to report a vehicle stopped on the side of the road? This is the "report" used by probably 90% of your drivers- it should be a one or two touch process (not four or five steps like it is now). Again- think shorter keystrokes (touches) to reduce distraction. And if there's one final suggestion to make your app the best in the business (it's pretty damn good anyway), give users the ability to overlay live weather radar on the map. Countless times I have driven into a rainstorm (because, Florida) that I could have waited out or avoided if that info was available. Just a suggestion... =)

Would be nice if there was a way to change the route it suggests to get to and from work. The route it suggests every morning is not the shortest or quickest. While I am not 100% sure, it would seem you have to sign in with FB to be able to send msgs thru Waze. Wazer's should be able to msg each other on Waze even if they are not signed in on FB. You should also be able to pin an event within a certain distance of where the wazer is located. This allows the person to wait until they come to a red light or parking lot to pin an event they just passed.
Great app. I recommend it to everyone,never let's me down

It looses the route. When this happens, the app is unable to get back the control over the route. Just calculating, calculating and it says it unable to find a route - driving on a motorway.The app is not reliable, at all. It looks clearly, the Google wants to kill this app to take its Google Maps into a better position. Eradicating the competitors...

BRING BACK COOKIE & MR. T! I live in a very rural area, so going anywhere takes at least a 45 minute drive (which my kids HATE). Having Cookie Monster navigate the route made a huge difference in how our trip would go. Now he's been removed and it's INCREDIBLY DISAPPOINTING!! My husband also enjoyed Mr. T, who is also gone. The current voice options are lame AF.

okay I'm really impressed with this app it have saved me time. I'm usually going to work during the peak hours and it has picked up stalled cars objects on the road. Rerouted me so I did not get caught in traffic. This is a good app, I'm really not one to get in impress this one impresses me. I am getting rid of its competitor and using this one for now on. Good job to the Creator's.

The best drive mapping app out there, cant say enough good this about the Waze app, I've used it for years. I would like to see them interface the app with radar detectors or maybe dash cams. I have am Escort Max 360c detector and love it but the mapping app that comes with it is awful. If only some how that device could be integrated so that the buttons on the Radar detector could mark or notify or even confirm other drivers input that would be huge! Also a suggestion would be to add weather mapping over lay so you have an idea of the road conditions before you travel or maybe want to avoid areas due to weather or hazardous events like forest fires, just a though. Great program, highly recommend... perfect would be to add interface to other devices.

When I first used the app, it was great. However, now it rarely can find my location. Also, it is really annoying that when a friend shares a drive, it doesn't work. I only use this app when I am at home and starting a drive. It will give me an eta. Besides that, it is useless. It must have some sort of tech bugs.

The idea and design of this app is very nice. I love the communal aspects of it, how you communicate with others about hazards, the amount of detail you can add to hazard reports, and the ability to rideshare. My only gripes with the app are that it doesn't always give you the quickest route when compared to Google Maps, it doesn't have a satellite map, and for some major locations, it doesn't put the most known/visited location as the top search result.

The RR crossing warning is great but put a button on it to mark the crossing as blocked and a warning to show that it is blocked. Also give me a 10 minute warning ahead of reaching the track on my trip to select an alternate route. Lastly, give me a 1 mile warning for upcoming obstacles and reports, by the time it shows it's usually to late to make accommodations
replyContent: We appreciate the feedback, Andrea! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you have more ideas you'd like to share with us, feel free to leave us a note in our suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: please fix it! Waze has been my go-to nav for many years. We could share our drive with real time ETAs. The nav is still great but months ago it broke. ETAs are no longer anywhere near accurate and you can't actually follow someone's drive. I keep hoping for a fix but updates come and go leaving some of the best features completely not-functional. Please return Waze to it's former glory and superiority.

I really enjoy this app! I've moved from Google maps to this and I really like the more personal touch it has, with profiles and the ability to change your little waze icon~ I have a small issue and can't find a fix for it, though. It still keeps me as a baby wazer even though according to my dashboard in a web browser, I've driven more than 100 miles :< I wish there was a way to see miles driven in the app, too!

This used to be a great navigation app. It seems to be having a major issue now. I use it when driving ride share, relying on it to get me from point to point quickly and safely. It has started freezing up several times a day and giving me trouble. It blacks out my screen, and won't let me shut it down. I have to restart my phone in order to get it to reset. It worked good when first installed, but now is more of a pain than a help. Phone is a Galaxy J7, new in April. It is mounted on a vent moun

I always use this app for traveling. I mean I am a speedy person. So of course I want to know where's the coppers? Sometimes it isn't always accurate. 2019 I got a ticket for speeding in St Charles, La. The cop display didn't pop up on the app. However, this is about 95% accurate of what is on the road. To be honest this app is way better than Google gps in my opinion. The app appeared on my local news because of the police icon warns you to look out for them on the road.

I was hoping to replace Google Maps with Waze but Waze has some significant limitations. With Google Maps I can download off-line maps for areas with poor cell signal. If I start my drive in an area with no cell signal Waze cannot work at all to find a route. At least with off-line Google Maps it will plot the best route (with no traffic data) and then will adjust the route when I return to an area with signal. Google Maps will warn me if the destination I've selected is closed - like a store's closing hours. Waze will direct me to a store regardless if it's still open or not. With Google Maps I can drop a pin and start driving navigation - it will find a route as close as possible to where I dropped the pin. With Waze, if I cannot give it a street address it cannot navigate.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Yvette. Please feel free to add your suggestions to our suggestion box: tinyurl.com/jo3484d All feedback added is considered and examined in regards to our product. Suggestions that are found relevant will be transferred to our product management team. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I didn't have the upgrade previously that said there were some issues. Overall Waze has helped me out a whole lot, exception being those moments of inaccuracy. So perhaps the upgrade with my knowledge of the roadways I will keep my passengers safe and happy to the best of my ability. HAPPY HOLIDAYS OR THE BEST OF THE HOLIDAY SEASON! THANK YOU!

Worked well for a while. Now it loses GPS connectivity during every trip. I have to reset my phone GPS, takes it forever to finally re- connect, just to lose it again not 5 min later. I've updated, reset things. Basically have to restart my phone to get it to work right for an hour. This is an issue for someone like me that runs service driving from home to home throughout the city all day. Any help would be great

The ideea behind the app is great. The functionalities are great. Interface is great. But, when i turn on my GPS and the app says no GPS all the way home (just had a 30 minute drive with this message), then, all the great features are in vain. This is not a problem that i have, iPhone users, Samsung, Huawei have the same issues and this is causing people to look for alternatives. I need to get to where i nees to go, and i don't trust waze to help me with that lately.
replyContent: Hi, Dumbrava! We‚Äôre sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I enjoy this app so much, except for one aspect: every time I upgrade my phone and have to install the app and log in, it can never locate my account (I'm 100% sure I'm using the correct info) and makes me create a new one. This is the 3rd time, I've never once had my account activate on a new device correctly. Really, really annoying and makes a lot of the features useless.
replyContent: Hi Moxie, thanks for the review! For quick account recovery for when you get a new phone, we recommend enabling Smart Lock backup (Android). For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: A great app once. But, recent updates have made this app worse than google maps. Servers always time out, and usually that means the app can't get me any further than 10 miles away. Was a good run, but I'd rather use an app that'll get me where to go, and actually work. If it ever gets fixed, I'll make sure to use again. But until then, so long.

Great app, notifications are almost always spot on. Warned me of many slowdowns ahead of me and may have had accident without the app. Keeps you alert. If notification is no longer relevant you can dismiss it, and others will know also. Has a speed indicator, and other helpful features that most standalone GPS devices dont have.
Slow apps function, not easy to use...

The app no longer allows me to know if an accident is on upper or lower level of bridge. And the yellow, orange and red colors that denote traffic ahead disappear when I try to swipe ahead to see how long that particular kind of traffic will last. When I re-center it reappears. And when there's actually heavy traffic ahead I sometimes see clear/no colors ahead and then I get slammed because Waze had it all clear then up pops the red. And now I'm stuck. Didn't use to do that. At a loss.

Waze is the best GPS/ navigation app there is. I have been using it for almost 2 years now & it has never been wrong. It tells you how long your journey will take & what time you'll arrive at your destination. It tells you the best time to leave too. I love that you can immediately report crashes, heavy traffic, bad weather & other hazards to let other 'wazers' know about them. It also lets you monitor your speed & alerts you to any upcoming speed cameras, heavy traffic, or other delays.
Never bring me to the right way. Google map much better.
too big space usage. slow in detecting pinpoint location. doesn't work well in background will automatically restart journey.
replyContent: Hi Iskandar, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this location issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Has fundamental flaws that a satnav should never have. Top of the list is that you can't tell it to plan routes based on vehicle restrictions, such as height, width, and weight. It will insist on taking a van through rotherhithe tunnel, which will result in a heavy fine. Further to this, there is no way to add roads or areas you wish to avoid at all times, and no way to easily modify your current route to bypass something.

Had Waze since the early days and it used to be good, but in the last month it says there is no network connection, won't let me log in to my account, when I do get logged in, logs me out, takes ages to load traffic. I've even uninstalled and reinstalled it. It is virtually useless!

Everytime the app updates, I have to start from scratch, and reauthorize everything from login to carpool information. This is a real hassle when you're on the road, and all you want is directions. Thanks. While you're at it, there's another bug. When I tried to log in to my Waze account, I was presented with a notice that Waze was texting me a security code. Since my phone doesn't text, I chose the option to get a call. Almost 24 hours later, and I'm still waiting for that call.
replyContent:
Hey Donna, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. Our team is handling it right now and it should be solved soon. 
For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app. I've only used it in the UK but it does everything that I need from a satnav app. Picks the fastest route avoiding traffic jams but gives you the option to choose other routes. Will reroute to avoid jams whilst you are driving. Shows your current speed and the speed limit. Also shows speed cameras with a warning noise if you are exceeding the speed limit. Very clear maps and voice instructions.

This app sucks. Tells you you'll arrive and then it takes an extra 15 minutes. I don't know about anybody else but it never reroutes due to traffic and does not account for construction. I have uninstalled and will be going back to using Google maps, very dissatisfied with Waze and will never use again.

I loved Waze but this week, oh dear. Randomly I found I was logged out. But no, actually the account was no longer recognised. No problem I thought, I'll register again. Nope, now an endless loop of verification emails: This account no longer exists. Yes Waze team I know, it's because you erased it. So it turns out this is all caused by an update. One in which your software QA team was evidently asleep at the wheel. It works again after another update. Testing? guys? It's Software 101.

Two faulty directions and I'm done with this... Both are known addresses. The first one took me off the road I was on, through a neighborhood in a circle and back out, the same way it sent me in. The second one sent me in an odd direction, but I followed for a minute then stopped to look. It was taking me someplace else. It was crazy. The thing is, there are ten ways to reach either address. I was just looking for the quickest route. Back top Google maps for me...
replyContent: Hi John, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this routing issue you're having. To best assist, please follow these steps to report this issue: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Last weekend I lost all trust in this app. So not connected to what was going on the road. If I did follow its directions I would have arrived home an hour later. In the past I noticed that for a minute difference it would take you on a weird journey through complex route. So not efficient! I do not trust it. Always be suspicious of Waze's route. You will find yourself wasting time on roads you never thought relevant to your trip! In my view, Google maps does a better job in route planning.
replyContent: Hi, Naftali! Sorry to hear about your experience but we appreciate the feedback. Please note that routing issues sometimes happen because the system works on real time and average statistics. We suggest that you take the suggested route a few times so that Waze can learn from it. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: When it works its flawless, and has helped me out of numerous "jams". However, it is increasingly timing out more and more when requesting the initial search and mapping. After trying a dozen times to map out a less than 3 hour drive it gives me the "uh-oh". This is forcing me to abandon the app and use the google mapping instead. This is why I give it 3 stars. This is the type of tool that either is 100% or 0% in its function.

Ever since I installed this app several months ago, I have had nothing but dissappointment. Instead of taking you through the simplest routes, it takes you through a hundred shortcuts that delay you a half hour more. HAPPENS EVERY TIME. Officially done with Waze. It's a shame, because I like that it's user-friendly and it has a simple design, but I just can't trust it.

I get lost in a paper bag. This app works well. I've never had it crash on me. The pop ups for accidents, traffic etc. is nice. Only thing that irritates me from time to time, which probably won't bother others, is one minute it tells me to travel for say 2.3 miles and later it will say travel for 4.5 minutes. Thats kinda special. Other than that minor thing...app works well.

Would not let me send my wife an ETA even though we were both logged into Waze. Geolocation accuracy is lacking . directions sometimes confusing as it thinks that ypu are facing a direction other than the direction that you actually are facing. On the plus side, store locations are pretty accurate and being able to update driving conditions is helpful to others.

Waze puts my home on the wrong street. Unlike other map apps, there does not appear to be away to adjust my location pin. I tried a few years back then uninstalled. Tried again today. Still an issue. In my case, the streets aren't connected, so one store over is about 5 minutes difference which affects routing. I googled many people with similar issues.
replyContent: Hi Todd, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to help with this map issue for your home. To get this corrected, could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Best app ive ever used in years.. i have only one suggestion,. I would like to see my saved places on favorites on display on the map. Because in my job as delivery, it is very important to know who are our next customers that are saved on favorites. Please do make it happen.. it is very very useful.. thank you so much and i hope you will work on my suggestion sooner or later.

there are almost constant ads. there are no easy, obvious voice commands o use while driving and yet half of the appeal is in the crowdsourced features. sometimes it gets map elements very wrong for seemingly no reason. when i tried to submit this as an error, the support request was sent to a team of volunteers who could not help me at all. but usually it gives better routes and real time updates than Google.

I absolutely love both the concept & functionality of this app, and want to be a regular participant. However, there appears to be no basic GPS/Tracking algo/logic. If my phone doesn't have clear line of sight of the sky, the map stays completely idle. I found myself driving with one hand, whilst the other holds my phone outside the car window to make this work. No such problems with Gmaps, or any of my running apps, and I'm afraid a deal breaker. Please fix / improve this. Note9.

Twice in the past week the app overrode my planned destination to send me to the wrong place. Today it rerouted me so badly it added 30 minutes to my commute. It told me that it was sending me to the wrong destination, but only after I had to turn my focus solely on the phone --- a dangerous thing in traffic. If this is how Google technology works, you should never buy any Google vehicles or traffic technologies.

I tried... As far as giving directions, it's great. But adding to the route, trying to find app options, searching for a place on the map instead of the list was all difficult. When Google maps is already standard on my phone, I see no reason to have this. GMaps is far easier to use in every one of those areas and has much more features. It even has reviews for the places your visiting. This app is just too difficult to use when it's redundant anyway.

For the most part I use Waze when I'm traveling. However, I'm not sure how up to date the roads are because because it doesn't always give the shortest routes. It takes me around the world first. Also the planned trips feature doesn't always update, I have to turn the setting off then turn it back on to update my trips. Also wish it gave alternate routes during traffic jams like Google maps does.

I hope the customer experience team, if it exists, reads these comments. Like many others, I use to love this app. Unfortunately, for the past few months, the app keeps having a hard time locating me and cycles forever on "finding route", while Google map works great. Same issue with Android Auto. 3 months ago I would have given you 5stars...

I really like this app. I know there are limitations to a free app, but with that said Google maps is also free. this app really gives Google a run for the money!! the fact that it works seamlessly with my Ford Sync is a huge bonus. the fact that is ALSO works with Pandora at the same time is even more awesome. If there was one thing I wish that could happen it would be that street names were part of the instructions, or even just a tiny bit more notice when to turn.

I've used this app for the past few weeks. I drive long distances in order to get from home to work using major highways. Today the app decided that in the middle of my drive that it would keep telling me that there were no routes available to my job but I could set the destination to a city closer to me and it would pop up our route within seconds. Fix this now.

Put the routing feature of routing by shortest distance back in. This use to be a user selected preference. Until then, I want to downgrade Waze to the last version that had this user selectable option. Some of us need this option to save wear and tear on our vehicles or so we don't go over the allotted mileage for a vehicle lease. --- Update; Waze support is giving me the run around on downgrading to a feature I require. I'm thinking about taking this to Twitter and we can let social media decide.

Functional app works good, detects broken down cars on the side of the road always as cops. Better safe than sorry but they are busy if making a stop. and the turn indication seems off making me pass my turns sometimes. and 1 address i drove to it was several houses off, but close enough that i found what i was looking for. It is better than google maps‚úî for sure, much more easy to just get on and going down the road. thanks!
Wave always gets me where I need to go, and reroutes are a time saver. Love that it tells me current speed limit along with speed I'm going.

Update. Latest version of Android Auto allows easy selection of waze or goggle Maps on the cars infotainment system. once you've selected waze in Android auto you can't return to using Google maps unless you delete waze, crazy, someone I use one sometimes the other. Also impossible to place my work location in the right place, in the right road but I can't move the marker. Google maps for me.

account login problem since ages ago, your app is not stable on handling user data/acc on the phone, one day it just stuck and force close then re-run it and my account is gone, have to re-login. but stuck at the "you look familiar" screen where i click "yes it's me" button, either it keeps on loading or it shows "login failed: wrong login details"... tried Facebook login also stuck at loading forever... after all these years i thought this stupid issue has been fixed but apparently not.

This used to be the king of all navigation apps. Since Google acquired this app,they redesigned the user interface to be maximally annoying. Everything now beeps pops jumps or hops onto the screen. and at all times, there is now a ride share button at the lower right-hand corner of the app. If you touch your phone at all while driving,Waze will constantly bug you to tell it whether you want to share your car with random strangers. This app was useful in 2015, but it's terrible now.
replyContent: Hi John, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze.If you have anymore future feedback to share, please contact us here: https://goo.gl/XVy4HE

content: Always lead to end road.
Excellent! I don't get lost anymore and am always on time

The features for reported accidents and other hazards on the road is the only thing going good on the waze app. However the GPS portion is horrible while using it on Android Auto. I know this is an app design flaw as the gps sucks on both iPhone Carplay and on my Pixel 2 Android Auto. GPS location accuracy and rerouting works perfect on Google Maps but never on Waze. One irritating thing I have found is that Waze gives you a route and waze keeps moving along the route even when I decide to go a different route. It takes waze about 3 or more minutes to detect I am not following its suggested route. Thats stupid. It should be tracking my GPS and rerouting as I move along the maps. This is constant. Really wished Waze would fix this. Its the one reason I rather use Google Maps than Waze.

I love that the routes use current info, and the ETAs are right on time & it tells you of it's being updated; that way you can keep your family/friends informed of any delays or travel time changes so no-one worries. I also really like that other people post updates, like where the police are, construction, accidents, stopped vehicles, things in the road, etc.

App Starts Randomly: I do NOT like that the app starts randomly and without apparent cause: just sitting on my desk. I sent an email to Waze expressing my concerns and asked how to make the poor behavior stop. The response from Waze "customer service" assumed that I didn't know how to stop an app and instructed me on how to stop it under normal use circumstances. I am inclined to uninstall due to both the erratic and the pathetic tech support service.

Nice enough, but I'm tired of Waze locking up whenever I'm using my phone (bluetooth) and driving. Also not happy with how I'll take a detour without consulting Waze and Waze will recalibrate and tell me that my detour is taking 5 minutes or so off my drive -- then why didn't Waze send me to the detour? Why was it telling me to take a longer route?

I thought I loved this app but it makes me "create" a new account everyone I sign in. None of my points were saved, none of my favorites were there. The only time this app was better than google maps was during NC's state of emergency and roads were closing due to a hurricane faster than google could update its map. Not worth the space it takes up if I can't save my places.
Verytime Give a wrong direction . Stupid aps

I frequently travel for work and Waze used to be my navigation app of choice, mostly for the hazard warnings. Now it has become so slow it is virtually unusable, fails to calculate some routes, takes ages to recalculate if I miss a turn or pass a route I know isn't quite as good, and on a recent cross-country run, logged me out of my account mid-trip and lost all my data. I made a new one only to have that lost too a couple days later. Uninstalled. I miss when Waze was better than Google Maps.
It used to be ok. Now after removing a bunch of features (speed cameras etc.) It's a complete garbage Would not recommend.
replyContent: Hi Alex, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app is great, and I really like to use it while commuting both in city and across country. However, there is one big and very annoying bug which I'm really looking forward to be fixed. When I chose alternative route, for example the blue one, and click go, I manage to notice that before opening big map it switches back to original route, which is awful. Only after second attempt I can switch to the route I want to drive. It has made me several times to drive the route I didn't want to(
replyContent: Hi Bohdan, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I think Waze is great with the exception of "my places" it would be nice if the places could be alphabetized. The most recent places i use and the frequent ones should at least stay at the top but they just get mixed in. So aggravating. Also it would be nice to add more then 2 addresses to a route. I walk several dogs and it would be nice to add at least 4-5 address. Other then that it gets me to where i have to go.

Very slow to recognize you have left the suggested route. Google Maps picks up the change by the time I'm at the end of the exit ramp. Waze says I'm still on the freeway even when I've been off for a quarter mile. This wouldn't be a problem except that the routing is often not efficient - there are minutes to be saved by such changes and Waze doesn't suggest them.

I like the look and simplicity of it and the navigation is great but, the main reason I wanted to use Waze was for the music integration but, it won't connect to spotify. I tried uninstalling it and reinstalling it but, it still won't connect. Definitely 5 stars once it's fixed. ALSO, it would be really nice if we can download maps or routes for offline use. thank you.

Waze works so well, I have just one suggestion. I wish that a user could enter a specific highway or road that must always be excluded. When I select an alternate route that does not include a highway that I will not take, Waze will recalculate the route and that highway comes up because it is much faster. However, it is a mountain road with sheer drops. When I am driving at freeway speeds it is unsafe to have to go back and find my originally selected route on the app.

lately waze has been inaccurate in its navigation. i use it in neighboorhoods and roads im familiar with and the waze suggested navigation is clearly slower. today i used waze and there was an accident on the highway. we were not moving. waze did not redirect. i went local and was able to get to my destination in 15 minutes. i would still be there now if I had followed waze. when I first downloaded waze it worked as promised. not sure what changed.

Easily the best navigation app I've used, with one glaring flaw. It will nag you to sign up for their carpool matchmaking service, and you can't remove the reminders unless you sign up for it, link a social media account, THEN disable it. Even if you do this, it always has an easy-to-accidentally-press button for that service on the interface.

driving hazard at first this app works fine, but after several updates, it keeps on rerouting randomly. it keeps on getting its gps signal lost even though I have a full signal reception. tbh its a driving hazard, the way it suddenly loses its gps lock and rerouting even if you're just stopping in a traffic light. the randomness is something that is a hazard and must be fixed

Was great for 7months, but is now awful. Had to uninstall b/c it kept ending my drive to work a few miles early, which was hard to tell at first glance on the overview, but had me 5-10mins off in my ETA (NYC traffic) & late for work a few days before I realised (it was ending on the highway). I reported to Help x3 to no avail. Reinstalled & now it keeps reloading the user agreement page over & over. If I am able to scroll down& click Accept, it still reloads page over & over & over...

Such a great app, but it's riddled with bugs that make it dangerous to use! The app is constantly crashing when using Android Auto and loses GPS location all the time. As much as I love Waze, I've had to switch to Google Maps because its just too dangerous when you're relying on it to show you around unfamiliar roads. Every update brings a new bug and the support team just aren't interested in solving them.

Got it specifically for the Mr. T voice. Not only was it not available, there were no celebrity voices at all. I'm not going to bother with it if the one gimmick that sets it apart doesn't work. 2 stars because the directions might work. Never tested them due to disappointment as listed above.
The apps was superrr laggy :(

always crashing at random times during trips. over the course of a 1700 mile trip, it crashed on average... every 30-50 miles. also, it seems as though no one uses the app anymore. no road markers the entire trip. this was the last chance for Waze. I'll never go back to it.

I tried this app at the recommendation of several people. Not only was it a little tricky to figure out how to use, it crashed multiple times on my drive to somewhere I had never been before. I had absolutely no clue where I was. One of the crashes happened in the dark, in the rain, with heavy traffic and right before I needed to make an interchange. NOT reliable at all and it put us in a very scary situation. Luckily I had another adult passenger who was able to pull up apple maps on her phone and get us on the right track.

This is my go to for driving. Great app. Wish Waze would actually shut down after I hit shut down button, tho. Instead, it has to be closed, which would be fine, but then I have to go thru settings and force stop or it sucks battery life by running in the background. If it actually shut down when I hit the shut down button, I'd give it 5 stars.

Unreliable. Takes long time to calculate a route. Sometimes it won't find a location & just does nothing. When it does start navigating the screen will completely go off, reappear without the route, & then eventually startup the route again. This happens about every 10 min or so. Other times, while navigating the arrow will disappear, replaced by a circle & the map will spin sideways & completely lose where you are. I cant believe it is my phone, Google map starts up instantly & never drops.

This app took me some convoluted way to my destination that should have been a mostly straight drive and then it had no idea where I was, or what roads were where or what they were called. I missed a turn because it told me it was much farther up than it was, it couldn't get me back to where I needed to be and stopped working completely. When I got back and made the turn it wanted it still had no idea where I was and wouldn't tell me where to go next.

Disappointing when the app took me down 30 minutes of single lane roads (near Llandovery) with only a few passing places, to bring me back out to the main road at a point that would have taken me 10 minutes to reach if I'd stayed on the main roads. Not an easy journey in a motor-home. It would be better if different size vehicles could be selected instead of taxi or car.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your review. We appreciate your feedback and understand the inconvenience. Please submit a suggestion for the addition of other vehicles types and sizes to the Waze suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Ok here we go. i used this app to go home from San Antonio to Missouri. To the owner of this app WOW cool. I love the icons that told me where everything was. There were a lot of pluses the big one was the police popups letting me know about where they were. There might be a few things that i might change or look at. The app is very interactive hands on. Now being safe is the most important, so being able to interact and drive was a little bit tricky. But over all I loved it. Thanks

The app is great! The problem are the ads during the route. Sometimes, I take the wrong street because an add just pop up when I need to look the map. This is quite dangerous too. I know they need to make money, but the way they do really affects the quality of the service. Sorry for criticizing so much.

In the middle of my drive the Waze carpool option popped up blocking my map and asking me questions and to agree with carpool terms of service. This is dangerous. I also noticed Waze requires a lot of buttons so at times to accomplish things. These are the things that make people get into accidents. Developers need to simplify things rather than thinking cartoony is simple but rather putting themselves in the driver's shoes and thinking about safety.

I absolutely love Waze, I highly recommend it! Its the only navigation app I'll use! Its reliable, accurate and easy to understand. Most importantly, it will save you from speeding tickets, it alerts you when there's a cop up ahead! It indicates you when your speeding, when there's an object on the road or a parked car long road. You can't get better than that! Everyone needs to be apart of the Waze Family üë™!!!!

A great app with a couple of very basic and obvious flaws. 1. The app doesn't offer Optimum Route So it sometimes takes you through tiny roads with horrible humps and hazards just to save a minute or two. 2. The app displays your speed rather than the speed limit of the road you're on! This is the most bizarre feature! I've been driving and riding for almost 30 years and haven't come across a motor vehicle without a speedo. So why show the speed that is already there instead of the speed limit!

Set up, √¢nyway. So far, very good. The Waze App security settings, I (can't hardly wait) to use! However, I am cautious of this "Mother App" having permission with my personal info. Especially contacts. Leading to the most "trivial" concern.. Ads, spam, and solicitors, not policed to major consumers standards. It's Okay; L¬©¬©K for "contains ads"; You Got It! Steel Trap! I prom√≠se not to allow "Any 3rd Party Info legally Obtained" Accepting Terms and Conditions, to insult Americas Civil Liberties.

After using the app for a couple of weeks i have to say the experience has been quite pleasant, that was until i tried my hand at editing a coulpe of errors i reported. I was instantly crucified by user "ituajr" for not letting them fix the error first so they could get the credit, even though they were asking me what the errors were. If you dont want to be thrown into the lions den then i suggest you stay away from the map editor. Only problem is you'll have to deal with incorrect navgation.

I dont understand why evertime I type in nearest 7 eleven on my route it will never find any on my route it will always put me in an entirely different city. When I try to find any other store itll find them in my route easily it's only with 7 eleven stores. Even on my wife's phone it does the same thing. We can never find 7 eleven on our route but there are definitely 7 eleven everywhere cuz we will pass them and wonder why they didnt pop up.
replyContent: Hi Sam, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this search issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Very accurate, right down to street potholes & other road hazards! I used to be devoted to Google Maps, but I grew frustrated with my music app always shutting off, while I'm using Maps to commute to work. With Waze, I can truly enjoy my music on my daily commute while being updated on ETA, traffic, road hazards, etc. I don't know why I hadn't switched over sooner, I love it!

Tried to use it on a motorbike with vocal direction via my earpiece, it remained silent and didn't tell me anything. Tried to use it for a London to Liverpool journey, it couldn't find a route. Tried to use it for a 30 mile journey, it placed me several streets from where I was the whole time and even then wanted to send me on a weird detour doubling the usual time the journey takes. Nice idea, but doesnt work. Deleted.

I just bought a kenwood ddx6705s with Waze navigation on it. I've used it 4 times everytime being within a couple miles from my turning point Waze freezes up. I'm quite disappointed, that can be very dangerous with some drivers who like to bow up in the middle of the road at the first sign of being lost. I mean I bought this unit cause it had every single option I wanted, Waze is the only thing I've had an issue with so far.

When you click on an address in your browser, it brings you to this app, but then the app doesn't haven't the address so you can't get the directions. You have to write the address down (or memorize it) then put it into this app. For some reason you can't even copy/paste. Unfortunately Google Maps has a strong hold on the map apps :( which I loathe

Good... but can be better. It does not highlight the correct lane to take, for example, in multi lane highways where left, middle, right lanes lead to different routes ! Only voice directions gives this indication but one has to be quick to listen and adapt. Google Maps has this functionality and because of that I missed 2 times the right direction before realising the defect!

Great navigation. Very accurate. Shows all ptoblems, traffic and hazards on the roads. People can comunicate between each other by leave notes, photoa and reports of the traffic situation. Best app I have try so far for getting from point A to point B safe. Only trusted users can share information and everyone can confirm, cancel or give more information about a car crash, stopped vehicles, havy traffic, bad weather or any other thing that may get on your way. Can be used together with Spotify.

Very buggy, particularly when used with Android Auto. It often can't keep a GPS location for you when driving. Each time I reinstall to try and fix it, there's the rigmarole of entering a mobile number and getting the code. It always has problems recovering accounts and I now must have 4 email addresses registered as the account recovery never works. This means my saved locations get lost every time. I also lose whatever points etc etc that I have gained between each reinstall. A frustrating app.

It's pretty good apart from a few niggles for those who drive on the left or use the Imperial system. E.g. roundabout symbols are the wrong way around and the app uses feet as units rather than yards. In the UK, 1000 feet implies height, not distance. Update August 2019 I don't know what's going on with the voices but it seems every day I'm getting a different voice. I'm supposed to be using Kate (UK) but have had three different voices in the days now.

Went a direction I know 3 times just to test it out. Failed each time to register turns down certain streets on the route it selected. Sometimes fails to recognize when you go off course, it still registers as if you were on the same route. Very slow to reroute sometimes.The relation between car location, street location, and distance is very misleading. Selects awkward routes.

Mapping is solid, have noticed some lag since Google took over. Not surprising, Google maps took me through Detroit to a dead end at 1am, I hope Waze doesn't turn into GM. App could be better if it remembered what route is taken when it's on a continuous basis. I have to keep going in and choosing the route. Just minorly frustrating.

Dangerous with Android Auto - The contrast between normal button colour, and the colour of the highlighted button is impossible to see, which leads to a very very distracting experience trying to use the features or when trying yo start the journey aftet you have spoken the location and the location has been found (non touch screen). When speaking 'stop navigation' with Android Auto, google assistant narrates a web search for 'Stop Navigation' rather than stopping navigation.

Used to be good. This app used to be great, now it takes forever to connect to the network (about half the time you need to closer and re-open it). It's a real shame because once it gets going it's great, but I'm not going to sit in my car for minutes waiting for the damn app to work every time I want to drive somewhere.

As I'm on my way to get vaccinated and glance at my phone to make sure I'm taking the correct action - I see an ad covering about 1/3 of the screen. Not only is it covering the screen, the remainder of the screen is darkened to the point you have to take a closer look - while driving! Hard to believe it's even legal to do this on a navigation app. At the next stop light I deleted the app and went back to the good old fallible google maps.
replyContent: Hi Sam, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. Please submit the changes you wish to see regarding the display of ads in the app to Waze's suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Same as Maps - in the beginning magical and very helpful. Now it's turned into the most frustrating part of driving. The application is very slow (quite often I've already taken wrong turn by the time it shows me route), inaccurate (position of roads or proposed turns often incorrect) and pauses almost non-stop. Plus, it's ETA has become incorrect. I do not have a fancy phone which is why it might be like this, but it was not initially a problem. Officially I'm looking for a new GPS now

I used this app a few years ago and uninstalled it for a couple of reasons. Decided to try it out again after trying to use our state roads app. Waze is absolutely amazing! Ive used it several times on long random trips here and its very accurate with the community postings. Also when your stuck in a traffic jam, its got a "time" on the side that gives you an idea of how long you'll be stuck. Its been pretty spot on! I love this app!

Wife shared location. Was not able to use it to find her to help with car trouble. Even after she sent the trip information. It would have been a good app, if I did not have to use find my iPhone to locate her and help. Everything else is great. But this problem trumps everything to me. I specifically kept this app for my wife and I to find each other in case of emergency. Other features work very well.

on phone its great. works really good and a lot of cool features. BUT, the android auto application is awful. barely have any of the functions that you do on phone. there is no search bar to type in, only voice control. and no way to adjust any settings. you have to unplug from your car to adjust anything. very inconvenient. its trying to force you to be hands free, but ur gonna use it the way you want, or you just wont use it. its more dangerous trying to get it working with no options

Horriable direction app. This has sent me on a loop 4 times that added 45 minutes to.my trip. I would prefer apple maps to this junk. The directions come at level 65 while the music is 10 with no way to correct that. There is noticeable lag and the app encourages playing with your phone while driving. I had better luck with being blind folded to drive.

So glad Waze is back up and running after a couple of months of being offline! The only thing that isn't working is it gives me 3 route options, and shows the 3 different colored lines, but the actual directions for the 3rd option is ALWAYS identical to the first and doesn't take you on that 3rd route option. So, for now, I'll be appreciative of the 2 real choices I have.

Lately the map freezes & claims to find no GPS signal in places where that has never happened before. If it's not safe to pull over & restart it, then no navigation services for me! Also, today, not for the first time, Waze decided I needed to take the back roads, scenic route, instead of getting me back to I-495 & reaching my destination faster. I was starting out not too far from home but didn't know the best way to 495 from there, & assumed Waze would do that because it's the fastest way. No
replyContent: Hi Lis, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this GPS and freezing issues you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is a great app for travel, but I dont see any maps app that showing the right route for heavy trucks. Sometimes, we fail to track the destination and got apprehend because of the direction we use to, because there are so many places having the truck no entry and we violated this rule and implementation because we followed the ways you are showing for trucks. All truck drivers hope you make routes for us. If you do that, more users will come here. we are 20000 on TDSP. (trailer drivers)PH

Great for getting around but this app needs major improvements. Way too many bugs, app crashes non stop. I drive uber and this can be the most annoying app ever. You're a billion dollar company. Quit hiring kids for the job and get better developers for your app. This app should still be listed in BETA stage. The other reviews are mostly fake, if you're looking for an honest review here it is! Forget what everybody else is saying on this thread. This app needs to be 3 stars

You gave us the ability while on the road to give a heads up to others on the road, which we love. Yet the only things you can link are your music apps and Facebook which sucks because I'd love to transfer my Google maps saved locations to here. Plus I can't swipe across on the upcoming turns so I can get over ahead of time. I'm an explorer, but I'm not going to add locations I've saved all one by one. That's a major waste of time. All-in-all, we appreciate your making this app. Updates=‚≠ê, edits

Traffic update is great, but it still couldnt assist the general condition. For instance, smaller road may give you faster route, but the chance to meet a car from opposite direction, will slow your time about 5-10 menit per car. So when traffic update gives you 4 menit faster route, it would be a wasted time when when you passing 4 or more car, makes you 20 menit slower. Different small road may have different route characteristic.

This app can good, and can be bad the reasons why one is because you can get wrong information on police and traffic jams.Also if you like sharing your location and letting people be able to message you yeah I think that will be invading my privacy. Now don't get me wrong this app gives good information it's just the fact that people can post information just ruins it. I would just stick with Google maps so I don't have to worry about all this.

Samsung S10 user It's a little weird and frustrating when the GPS circles around and my location cannot be pinpointed therefore misguiding. But when it works the detours are lifesavers. Overall, I would still refer my friends to use the app cuz nothing's ever 100% without challenges. I just wish you could send out a notice of technical difficulties and an ETA that the problem is known and will be available shortly.

The voice instructions keep failing and this is happening for a while. For example "in 200 meters, at the roundabout(silence)...."" and comes back later on with further instructions but, again and again, stopping when it would be crucial to know what to do..

Hey first I want to say your app is great. Use it all the time. I do have a suggestion or more like a request. Can you please add the option to input vehicle  height and width. For example a camper trailer. That way those of us who pull trailers around will know whether or not we will fit in certain tunnels and bridges.  Not sure what kind of data you would have to collect to make this happen but it sure would be awesome to have said feature.  Thanks for such a great navi app and keep it up!

Love the app content, but I really hate the battery usage this app uses. Even with charger plugged in (factory charger) it drains battery faster than it can charge and since I take 6hr+ trips I am often unable to use thru the duration of my travels and am forced to memorize the route or switch to Google maps which uses virtually no battery life. This needs serious improvements!

I loved Waze until recently. I've been using Waze pretty religiously for several years. But over the past 3 days, Waze has failed to notify me of several large highway accidents, when there was an alternate route that would have saved me an hour. Instead I got caught in horrible traffic, and my typical 1 hour commute turned into a 2 hour nightmare. I've lost my faith on Waze now.

The more you updated the more app sucks!!! Traffic jam don't exist on this app anymore!!!!! Not getting any warnings when traffic jam is a head. Have to use google maps in same time, which has improved very much for reading traffic towards destination! Option to see multiple rutes once you choose direction and them choose which one you want would be amazing!!!! Ikon for sound is to small once you start navigation!! Make it bigger, you have space!! Come on guys. Do I have to do your work or what?
replyContent: Hi Roberto , thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The community aspect of waze is great and it functions alright. My main issue derives from the banner suggestions that cover up a decent amount of the screen. These appear when you are at a stop (and very seldomly while driving in my case) and really obscure the map at the one time you should actually be looking at it. This makes using the app annoying and maybe even dangerous. There are already tons of advertisement pins in the map so this layer just seems unnecessary and obnoxious.

This used to be a 5 star app, Goggle has turned it glitchy with this last update. It incorporates Goggle in it. However my arrow was going backwards down the highway for about an hour. It let me know Police ahead after the front of my arrow past the Police. Yes I got pulled over for doing 7mph over, more so because I was wondering what the he*! is going on with this app

This is what Google Nav should be... Recently started using the app as I've been hearing about it. Must say, I love it! Fantastic real-time nav app and the community based updates are f'ing awesome! I love how fast it changes the route if needed. You're never left waiting even a few seconds for an alternate route. It just happens and you keep going. Love that you can schedule a drive too! Very well thought out! This'll most likely be my go-to nav app moving forward. Using Google Maps more so for information now...

I have an issue with the new update, everytime I open the app the music app attached to it automatically starts playing. Also this is a carry over from the last version, but when I hold my phone upright and search and go to put my phone on the holder in panoramic view it won't show the route and won't work again until the app is shutdown and restarted.
replyContent: Hey there, Neil! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We're happy to investigate this further. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: When using Android Auto, the navigation system stops working when on a phone call. The location freezes at the point when the phone call begins. The turn by turn function stops to work until the phone call ends. Once the phone call ends, it relocates new coordinate and continues to function as if nothing happened. Recent update did not fix the problem. Please fix as this program has now become useless unless you make no phone calls. Google Maps has not been affected with this issue.

Ads are distracting. Too many options for end address/location without route modifications on the fly. The alerts are distracting as well and have literally seen other "Wazers" get a pothole alert and hit the brakes(live in Portland, there's a lot of potholes) Google maps definitely has it's flaws and I have a Google phone running the newest version of Android and maps but functionality wise, has Waze beat. I drive for a living and grew to hate Waze quickly. Put a little work into the app with all of the ad revenue, you have a good idea but lacks in development.

I don't like how much this app delegates tasks while driving to the user. That can be very distracting and Google Maps makes it much easier on certain tasks than this app does. I can appreciate the depth of letting other driver's know what's going on, but it shouldn't overcome the safety of using the app. My favorite feature is being able to just drive and it follows where I'm going. The worst feature is reporting issues on the go, and how distracting that is with all it wants you to do.

Unfit for purpose with Android Auto. As so many people have said, the GPS is woeful. Waze used to be great but it appears that Google have ruined the app (? purposely). Support doesn't really care and appear to be in complete denial about the GPS issues, trying to blame users instead. Until these issues are resolved, you simply can't use Waze with Android Auto.

The usefulness of this app plummets year after year. I used to swear by this app. As a ride share driver, delivery driver, and traveler who used this app for over 2 years, I can honestly say that this app has become the worst GPS I've ever used. My out of date circa 2006 Tom Tom gives better directions. The default directions are to take you to expressways, regardless of how far out the way it'll take you. And sometimes it dumps you in the middle of nowhere. I lost TONS of money using waze.
Confusing interface but I figured I could get used to it. Didn't save my "achievements" which was frustrating and immediate uninstall.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It is getting worse for the recent version. The choice of route has been removed where we can't choose the shortest route or fastest route no more. Hence if we choose a route which is not the default and waze will just change to the default selection if "something" is detected wrong. Always lead to the farther road, so frustrating. And for toll, even you choose non tol road, and after self adjustment by waze, it will turn back to toll road. The "common sense" by waze is no longer there!

The fastest route is usually the slowest This is the 2nd time the app took us on the "fastest" route. What is the slowest option in reality out of the 3 possible routes! (tried to select another route but still taken us on this one!!!!) The app does not take in consideration the fact that you are only able to drive quite slow on narrow, curvy, bumpy country roads with huge potholes all along, what also shake the heck out of you. We were late both times, thanks to this! Google Maps is better..

It has saved my car so many times I have rims on my car and let's me know when pot holes are there if I'm going a little faster than I should it lets me know if there's a place up ahead or a car or something in the middle of the road it literally is the best app I've ever used for navigation I use it even if I know where I'm going every time I get in my car I put it on

Edited to change to 4 stars as it's the most accurate I've tried. I don't believe the not connecting to GPS is their fault, I've tried 3 in town the last few weeks and none work! There's something weird going on with GPS around here. This worked great for the first several months and now the last couple days and it won't connect to GPS and sends me all over the place. What's going on?
replyContent:
That sounds a bit frustrating, Angela. Let's get that fixed! Please follow the steps in this article to connect to GPS. For the best results, ensure that Waze is updated and your mobile device has a strong data connection: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6083679?hl=en ensure

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Switched from Google maps to Waze and it's wonderful. Google breaks their app constantly whereas I've never had an issue with Waze... Bye bye Google maps!

I love Waze but can't stand Car Info! it's ruined the map view always overlaps my car icon and is super annoying. I'd go five stars if this button was made as option to remove from map. Option is available in settings in two places, why must it persist on main map? Please give us option to remove. I see this reported all over by lots of users, yet Waze chooses to ignore it's customers. I'm quickly starting to hate something I once loved and evangelized to my friends.
Could not create the account. Tried 5 five times, always failed.
replyContent: Hi Emiliano, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this account issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: im not sure what the hell is going on but after the update I can no longer use this app. tried uninstalling and reinstalling it but it still doesnt work. it keeps telling me it cant connect to a network but I tried google maps and it works perfectly fine. ill rate this one star unless you guys can give me a solution on how to operate this again. something is wrong with your app

This app has given me nothing but trouble since I downloaded it. It constantly has issues with crashing and losing connection when other apps have no issue maintaining connection. The biggest issue is everytime I rotate my phone from landscape to portrait so I can use my phone mount, half the screen goes black and only half my screen shows the map. The only way I've been able to fix this is by shutting down the app and restarting it, when this happens I am automatically logged out while driving
Really bad directions, through construction roads

I recently downloaded this app because I had issues with Google Maps. So far I really like this app however I find myself always adjusting my brightness because it's very difficult to see turns and directions. The top navigation bar when you're driving is black. It difficult to see in direct sunlight. I tried to find any customizations options but I was unsuccessful. Please allow other users to customize the color of the top navigation bar that shows directions, street names, and turns.

This is one of the best apps to have on your phone. I always use it before and when I am out driving just to check ahead on all the roads to avoid traffic jams and construction! This app has kept me from going where there are traffic backups, accidents and of course road construction! The best part is it gives you alternative routes when you want to avoid the headaches on the road!

Great app. Use it whenever I am in my car. Sometimes glitches and can't work out why. It will be following the map on the highway and then it will think I'm on a random side road. Sometimes it just doesn't know where I am and keeps jumping. This is really frustrating when I am trying to get somewhere. Brilliant features and enjoy the app except those issues.

I used to only use Waze, but the last few weeks have been really bad as the app keeps freezing. I stopped using the app and started using google maps, and although i prefer Waze's interface atleast google maps is more reliable. Just now ive noticed my phone freezing and lagging extremely bad, i have a samsung s9 so its quite a new phone, and i think its due to the waze app, ive had to completely delete the app from my phone and so far my phone has been fine since.

It's ok, but I don't really see how it's any better than the directions given by Google maps. It takes me to small residential roads where there are school zones (30km/hr) just to save a max 2 mins on a 30 min trip. What's the point? I'd rather be stuck for 2 extra mins on a straight road than take 5 extra turns and go through a school zone.

This app has gotten me lost more than anything. The GPS can rarely find my location, when it does it constantly changes routes on me last second all to reroute me back to my original route that I was on initially. I think the old school Thomas Brothers map is more accurate. I uninstalled and will never reinstall again. Eff this app.

I'm having the same issue as many others. While using for navigation in Android auto the audio continually keeps ducking for notifications every 3 seconds with no notification given. Cycles repeatedly between normal volume and volume for notifications. I use Waze for every drive I make but I'll be stopping until this is fixed. Hopefully I can find an old version and roll back.

This is one of the best things to happen to driving! It is such a time saver when it can route you around closures and accidents and detours because of construction! LISTEN TO THE WAZE! I Was skeptical When I 1st started using WAZE. I couldn't understand why it was taken me so far off of my planned route... and did not listen to 'THE WAZE' suggested route and learned a HARD lesson... 4 hours of my life was wasted that day! And it was a corridor that you could not get off! NO ESCAPE.

I have a long commute to work and I've been using this app for a while now. It has caught a wreck a couple of times where Google Maps did not and rerouted me well. But I changed carriers and got a new phone and it refuse to let me log in on the new phone. I lost all my information that I've had . It would not take the button where it says yes it's me and would did nothing. Lost all my information lost all the points and all that jazz.
Please make easy to view in advance, exactly where is the accidents, police, or a problem reported on the route.

I cannot depend on this application because I never know if I will be able to get audio. Every time I am in a rush No Audio. I end up guessing and driving blind with no easy way to fix it. Once in awhile I am totally shocked when I hear the audio but the next time nothing. To me the voice directions are the most important part. What's with the silent treatment / no audio? Not happy Not able to give review because No Voice comes wirh Warnings .
Great traffic alert

The app is very good. There are a few improvements however: 1) There is no option to setup for using highway/interstate EXCLUSIVELY. We are not familiar with the area and hesitate to take small roads. 2) Add option to save a particular route based on your preferences and recall it when using. 3) Allow set up particular road with via points.

Hello!!! I am OTR driver. This app is overall for me and my wife a GREAT APP. Yeah it crashes from time to time...so what. Nothing works 1001% of the time. And maybe some off yall should attribute the app malfunctions to your phone or service. With that being said, have all thought about making the app or adding CMV features to the app. E.g. bridges heights, truck routes & restrictions in the inner cities?

For the last 2 months I have been driving back and forth from Charlotte North Carolina 2 Washington DC. Waze has been the best GPS I have ever used. I love how it informs show me where all the Virginia cops are hidden. If he even tells me when there is a hazard in the road. Best all it help us figure out how my daughter got $1,000 in speed camera tickets in one month in DC. It also gives you a warning when the traffic is slow and the estimated time it will take to get through the slow traffic.

I love Waze! Without it, I never would have made it to some destinations over a long time. After finding a way with Waze and an Internet connection, you can find your way out there without needing the Internet afterwards. Awesome App *****

This used to be a good GPS (non offline) navigator about a year ago. Better than Google Maps. However, successive updates have made the Waze unusable. After selecting a destination to navigate, "no GPS signal" appears at the top. Under Settings, Location Mode is set to High Accuracy; and Waze is granted Location permissions. I don't know what else to look at in Android settings to diagnose. Help!

I love the app but give us a choice in how to view the interface. I usually have my map in split screen with Google Maps and the swipe up menu blocks some of it. It was great how it was before...why change it? I didn't even update the app! Sometimes I just want the regular screen to follow me and give me alerts.

content: One of the latest updates has an issue with Android Auto. I play waze Information through my phone's speaker even while connected to the car. The latest update stopped that from working so i had to go back 3 previous versions to get it to work again. while the radio is on, the sound would dim slightly while waze was announcing a direction to take, or a warning like object on road ahead. after one of the previous few updates, that function stopped working. only works if playing google play music.
replyContent: Hi David, thanks for reaching out to us. We'd like to hear more about this sound issue via Android Auto you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I went from loving Waze to hating it. It frequently takes me off the highway to avoid traffic to immediately put me back on (on literally the same exit number). Traffic detection is garbage. It took me off a diff exit so I could sit in stand still traffic for 15 min on a side street. It was cuz of construction which has been going on; it should've known to avoid this route. I end up 10-20 min late everywhere when I should be 10 min early. Also, ads shouldn't be popping up over my route!

the worst app experience ever. It sent me to a totally incorrect location twice and when they get the location right it sends you there in the most out of they way inconvenient ass backwards twice as long as it should be go around in circles method i wish i could give it negative 10 and kick the developers in the throat for getting me lost on the way to the f***ing hospital ..real piece of s*** app i would not recommend it EVER

Great app. The crowd sourced traffic data is great. The app can also find the nearest petrol station which is a life saver. *Update March 2020*. The "submit fuel prices" feature works fine now. Changing my review to 5 stars. The only draw back is the "submit nearby fuel prices " feature , which rarely works. It normally claims it can not find a GPS signal, even though other location based parts of the app are functioning fine.

Lately GPS won't work correctly when used in Android Auto. The car icon will become a blue dot, I'll be driving sideways down the road, suddenly it thinks I'm driving down a side street perpendicular to where I'm actually driving. The speedometer no longer shows and I don't get any alerts. It works fine on it's own, but horribly in Android Auto. I uninstalled and reinstalled, and it worked again for a little bit, but it's back not working.

content: Way too buggy for a google product. Although it has better features I will stick with Google Maps. I like the speed and alert notifications. However, I saved my home, work and a few other favourite addresses several times and they kept disappearing. Created an account and it never stays logged on, etc. using Galaxy S9+ 256gb.
App has been crashing constantly. Uninstalled then re-installed, but still crashing if you have to answer the phone or go to another app. Almost worthless now.
replyContent:
Hey, Jeff! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to work really well. Then like many others have said it became worthless. I noticed it after the most recent update 2 days ago. Now it loses my GPS shuts down abruptly and has overall not worked even close to how it used to. If this was a new app I would have already deleted it, but since it has worked well in the past I will give it a little time to see if they work our these major kinks. But as of today its WORTHLESS

My opinion, by far the best app for directions and multiple stops with very quick live updates. Each time I tried to go against it, I regretted it and it proved me that it was right. I have had only one thing that I noticed. When you pass a speed limit sign it changes immediately. Only once was it off. And it wasn't very far it changed. Never one problem with the app and it's operations. ‚úåüèº

Same issues as a lot of people have already mentioned. App is unusable lately. Car spins and drifts erratically around the map. I won't get any alerts until I have already driven passed the area because GPS cannot pinpoint my location. Screen goes black randomly. Anything I try to report doesn't get added to the map. I hope the developers fix this soon!

Map data is poor, it lacks roads that are on all other apps I've tried (including sister product Google Maps). You'd think Google would be able to sync map data between the two. This is exacerbated by the app being poor at choosing the nearest endpoint if there's not a road it has in the immediate vincinity. It'll show a search result, and go "Uh oh, no endpoint found". Needs serious work in maps and routing...

Right now you get a low score for sure. I have written other reviews in other places but I read many other reviews from users having the same issues as mine. Im sick of it not connecting to my many delivery routes across the state. I know where I loose signal in the state and its normal and for too long, even being in my own city, i cant find anything. I have tried all of your suggestions that you guys told people and they dont work at all. Its not the users....its your glitches. Fix it please!
replyContent: Hi Aaron, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more about this signal issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Last update messed up the app work Android auto where it lags, car looks diagonal on the screen, the screen is just acting weird going from showing the car to a blue circle then back. Update: if you turn in Google maps first then go to Waze it seems to correct the issue. Developers perhaps look there to see why that corrects the issues temporarily until you restart the car again and have to do it again.

Since the update before last the waze widget crashes everytime. I get the notice that Waze has stopped when trying to open te widget. It keep searching for connection while the Waze app has connection and shows me while driving. This is very irritating. I also sent feedback. I had hoped that the last update had fixed this but alas... Otherwise I love this app.

BEST NAVIGATION APP BY FAR!!! Won't use Google Maps again! Provides the best routes, unbelievably accurate length of commute times & remaining time of travel. Very Acurrate Real Time traffic details. Automatically Reroutes you around wrecks/traffic jams/road construction, to avoid any delays. Has an travelers assist feature where you can let other travelers know of speed traps, debris in the road, wrecks, etc...which notifies you of any and all of these, if it is on your route..THIS FEATURE HAS SAVED ME FROM AT LEAST 10 SPEEDING TICKETS OVER THE LAST COUPLE OF YEARS!!

Everything was working fine untill recently. Today, everything was off. The app was telling me to do U turns, was telling me about non existent roundabouts and so on. Its like the accuracy of the app was off by like 5km. Also the arrow that represents the car was sideways the whole way. 5 stars usualy, but today was completely useless. UPDATE: The issue was rezolved by clearing the cache
replyContent: We're here for you, Damian! Have you tried reinstalling the app? Also, please make sure that you are using the latest version.
