For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I have thi app for a few months. Every time I open Waze, it craches or crash my phone. I have to restart the phone every time. But a few times it worked, and still froze in a few hours of driving. I have Samsung Galaxy note 8. All phone software is up to date. Not sure why it is happening with my phone.

I absolutely love waze its saved me so much time!!! Only one issue for the past week there's been glitches. It doesn't recognize where you are and constantly tries to reroute. Lucky for me I use it only for traffic I know where I'm going. But this is still very annoying and must be fixed

For awhile now, when turned to landscape mode, half of the screen turns black. This is only remedied when I turn the screen again and then back to landscape. In addition, Waze has been losing GPS signal while navigating for the last few weeks. Closing, clearing the data, reinstalling doesn't seem to resolve this issue. Only closing the program and not using it for a few hours seems to help.

content: After update to this 4.47.0.3 version on my phones, always keep searching network shown while using the app, and it also have problem when checking the routes. Previous version was better than this version! This issue happened in my 2 Android phones. Please do something with it. I love to use this app while traveling around daily.

Nice app....when it works. Today is the second time I've been out of town trying to get to a location and the app either has an error or server is timed out so I cant get directions. I've tried for over 10 minutes. We tried it on multiple devices and even used 1 phone as a mobile hotspot and it still wont connect. I liked the app because of the up-to-date information, but it does me no good when I can't get directions.

My driving app for years. Until I got a car with Android Auto. It actually worked ok for a couple of versions but then started loosing GPS signal, rendering the app totally useless. Even reported the issue to support and collected debug logs on their request but a couple of months later and never heard back from them and issue remains. Oh well, gotten used to Google Maps which works perfectly.

Been using waze for years on nearly every drive i take. It's been solid all around & I've had no complaints until recently. Some time in the past several weeks the app decided to give notifications about upcoming railroad crossings. Not a huge deal except for the fact that when these notifications pop off it kills my system sound. I use my phone for my radio so this is pretty annoying. Please add a feature to turn off these notifications and/or fix the bug that nukes my audio. Galaxy note 9

It takes way too long to find addresses. The app asks you 3 times if that's where you want to go after searching for it. YES, I WANT TO GO THERE. JUST LET ME. Also it won't show you which side of the road your destination is. This makes working a delivery job a nightmare. You roll into a neighborhood and you just have to guess whether the place will be on your right or left. For some places it won't even guide you to the neighborhood, it'll just tell you they live on the street. Super annoying.

This app puts me in traffic every morning. Update. 7/19 so this app is garbage. I've no idea why I still use it but I do. when using this app I have to cross reference with google map to see if its putting me in traffic, sometimes its okay sometimes I just use google maps google maps seems a little better. I still stand by my initial comment & yes this app puts you in traffic. Would definitely not recommend.

I've used Waze every day since 2012. The app knows my user habits and the routes I drive very well. Since the last update, automatic rerouting no longer works. When I approach traffic on the freeway, it no longer suggests taking the side streets that it used to recommend. And yet, when I exit and take the side streets anyway, Waze suddenly updates the route and shows that it will now take less time to reach my destination. Um, Waze is supposed to tell me that BEFORE I hit the traffic!
Bye2 waze. Will never use it forever.

EDIT; the app has since improved on this complaint, I was able to map a trip from eastern Pennsylvania all the way to Michigan. It did still take a little time for it to process, but it no longer winds up endlessly trying to load. works fine for trips for short trips up to 2 hours or so (although the routing time is rather high), but completely flounders if trying to map a drive that's about 6 hours out
Love the "real time" navigation and adjustments to directions. üëç

It used to be awesome, but something happened. It stopped working with Android auto. If you use it on the phone it works, but if the phone is connected to the car it always sais that there is no gps signal. I am not sure what happened, but my two guesses are that it aither has something to do with new phones or some recent updates. Such a shame.
replyContent: Hi, Eglƒó! We're sorry to hear that you're having trouble using Waze on Android Auto. content: One of the fundamental apps to have on your device, and I'm as demanding as I am picky, best part, it free!!!
I absolutely prefer Waze to google or any other navigation app. It's imformative and only has let me down once in a backwoods area and well it was warranted
Does this tell you which lane to be as Im a new driver and struggle which lane to be in. Been using google maps and this doesn't help me.
replyContent:
Hey there! Yes, Waze highlights the lane you should be in for upcoming turns. Additionally, it tells you when to keep straight. When approaching an intersection or highway exit, all lanes on the road appear at the top of the map. Hope this info helps.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Honestly, Waze works much better than Google Maps, and I've been absolutely loving the app for navigation! The alerts are timely and accurate, and I've been able to get safely from place to place while taking the fastest route! The voice of the GPS is also super charismatic! I have yet to try the carpool features, so I can't comment on that, but this app is great for navigation!

I had the app on my old phone and it worked great. Unfortunately, when I got a new phone, it wouldn't let me sign in to my account. Every time I tried to log in, it had me acknowledge the end user license agreement and it sent me new sign in code as if it were a new account. As such, I will not be using Waze. Very frustrating üëé

I have been using the app for more than a year as a motorcyclist. I can say it has been improved in terms of crashing, which was a real pain on the past, as I was using only the audio for guidance, I sometimes wouldn't know if the app was still active or not. I recently purchased something to hold the phone on the handle bar, and on my first trip with the app. After like an hour and a half of riding. It showed a prompt to link the google assistant that never disappeared since I had gloves on!!!
replyContent: Hi Antonie, thanks for the feedback. Please feel free to send us a private message on Facebook with any issues or questions you may have. We're always happy to hep. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Very helpful! I really like how it stays up to date with traffic, hazards, road blocks, alternative routes, etc. I also like its connection with spotify. Sometimes I don't feel like it gives enough warning before a turn, other times it is just fine with that. I love the community involvement throughout this app. Highly recommend.

App is very simple and for the most part works ok. Navigation messages take up to much of the screen real estate to the point you can hardly see the map. Red Light camera warnings cannot be muted and drive me absolutely mental. 6 on my way to work over a 20 minutes trip and six on my way home. Why can't you mute them like all the others? Please get rid of them or I'll go to another app.
replyContent:
Thanks for the feedback, Luke! Have you tried disabling the alerts? To do so, go to settings > alerts & reports > reports > speed cams > toggle 'alert me while driving' to the off position. Hope this helps! 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: the damn waze lead me into traffic jam with stand still traffic. my friend took a different way without the waze and reached much earlier. if you are in kuala lumpur area and want to get out to your destination, the waze will always lead you into the heart of the city where the massive traffic is eventhough there are other routes to use. very often as well, the communucation with the server is down leaving the user in a lurch. there was once it lead to the front of a military installation!

I like waze 10000 times better than google maps, it's user-friendly and is in 3d mode so you never get confused midway, and it also follows you even when you run out of data. Although when it comes to searching for groceries, parks etc. it has limited information. I think I'm not the only one who thinks about that in here, so developers, get your hands on developing that feature PLEASE... YOU GUYS ROCK!!! üëè

I really like the design of this app, and I would prefer to use it as my GPS app. Unfortunately it is too complicated to use hands free and it crashes too often. The integration with Google Assistant is poor. Until these bugs are fixed I will go back to my 'old' app. Please always keep the Assistant microphone on top. Searching for a destination should be easy-to-use in an app designed for driving. It should not be the cause of distracted driving. Not recommended for Android 10 car head unit .
replyContent: Hi Barry, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze gives strange alternative route suggestions without giving a reason why. Government has a low tolerance for distracted driving here. This app is unfortunately dangerous. It distracts the driver while driving by repeatedly presenting multiple alternate destinations that are really ads ex. fast food etc. I've had six in a row crossing one overpass before. It also encourages illegal device interaction while driving.

I used to love Waze. Now it is constantly rerouting me for no reason. I will be driving straight and it suddenly has me mapped in some other location trying to reroute me back to where I already am. Over and over again. Super frustrating! It also now has me pass a highway on ramp, to drive in town 10 min out of my way, to then get on at a different on ramp. If you are unsure where you are, Waze will get you to your destination...but in a long, out of the way, hour later.
replyContent: Hi Elaine, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this constant rerouting issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great idea and getting better over time, however it needs a couple essential things: [Edit: They added a Compass, thank you! (it's an essential aspect to any navigation.) 2. Report closed lanes and construction: somewhat self explanatory, I've been caught by road and layne closures that haven't and can't be easily reported. 3. When I most recently used the app with Android Auto, Waze sometimes doesn't track my vehicle even though Google Maps can. This makes it unusable.

Lousy! It will do what all the others do, but it only allows you to make one change in your pre-planned route. God forbid that you should deviate from what it directs. It will redirect you around your elbow to get to where it has decided you should be. Google owns Waze and Maps. Waze gets all the hurrah, but Maps is much more user friendly.

Great app 4 updates on trip hazards such as weather, accidents, hazards and potholes on the road, Etc. I cannot use the routing option because I drive an 18-wheeler. If you could create a plug-in with trucker safe routing, I know thousands of Truckers that would gladly pay for that portion. It would also give you many eyes on the road to update the various warnings. Most truckers I know that use this app, love the way it performs.

I travel from west LA to orange county every day. Every once in a while i download waze try it and then get pissed off and uninstall it. It's almost always the same scenario. It shows an ETA which exites me in the beginning then slowly increases and a message pops out half way through saying there is unusually heavy traffic and jacks up ETA another 10 mins and takes me through supposedly short cuts which ends up in a jammed street or dead end street. It's LA for gods sake and there is always traffic and it's not UNUSUAL at all.

For the past few months I haven't been able to establish a connection for GPS even though it can find my starting point. All other apps requiring location and GPS are still able to work. Have been too unstable to even use anymore. Although it was helpful with traffic and details in the beginning, would probably stop using until this gets fixed.

It simply fails at creating directions for any trip longer then 100-150 miles. Tried to make directions for a trip about 500 miles long and many attempts later it always timed out. I then tried to break it up into shorter 200 mile segments and again failed. Twenty mile trips I tested worked fine, but that is not good enough. No other app that I tried has this issue. This happens both in the app or in a web browser on my computer.

I hate this app so much... does not work like it used to anymore.. can't get ROUTES or times to pull up to plan my trips. I've uninstalled and re downloaded the app. I've turned data on and used wifi only and vice versa. I've tried it on different devices and other phones of my friends. same issue. nothing works and it searches for the network forever. even tried it in a different state.

After switching to Waze from Google maps, I've come to the conclusion that all GPS apps suck. I gave this a fair shake I really did. But, today was the last straw for Waze with me. It was legitimately sending me to the wrong locations, by a block in most cases. Between that, the UI that requires too many button presses to get started, the length of time it takes to calculate a route, etc, I'm considering going back to Google.

Waze is absolutely wonderful, I talk about it to all who will listen. I begrudgingly upgraded my phone and started using apps only five years ago. I'm sort of a senior ü§ó so I thought it would be difficult, instead it's been a joy. I've traveled alone for some time, usually reading directions from a printed page, can you imagine that? Now I have my Waze, I call her 'my girl'. I enter the destination and my girl says "let's go". I just laugh.

Used it for years, but after logging out and trying to login, the app never manages to validate my phone number. This led to my account getting deleted. I guess I shouldn't care too much about all the stats from my account, but definitely not a pleasant experience and am switching to Google Maps from now on.

My experience with your waze app is horrible. It's the worst app ever. I have downloaded this app three times and it has never worked. Every time I try to open it, it pops no network connection. What is wrong with your waze app? Fix it then I will rate your app because right now I will rate it minus FIVE. That one star has happened by mistake, as I said I rate it minus FIVE.
replyContent: Hi Amir, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to help with this network issue you‚Äôre experiencing. To best assist, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Is a nice app for navigation and I really like the feature where you can warn and be warned of obstacles on road, cars on shoulder, construction, etc. Is one of the best features from my point of view. The only thing that truly annoys me is the speed limit icon. I like to know what the speed limit is, as sometimes they are not posted clearly on the road. Waze shows your speed in an icon, then has this little bitty one on the side of the posted speed. I DO NOT need to see my speed. I have a speedometer built into the car! I would rather see the posted speed instead of what GPS says I am traveling at. Can this be fixed? Perhaps giving a choice of what is shown?

in 6km do... in 1km do. too much anticipation is actually useless. if you didn't hear clearly you start looking at the map in case there is something urgent and it is for +10 mins in the future. Google maps anticipates 300 or 200 m from the maneuver and on the spot. that's how it should be. language: my phone is in English, i like apps in English, Waze thinks that if I'm in a spanish speaking country, I must have the app in spanish, no, thanks. and the voice is awful. 3D and dark map look too bad

What happened This used to be my go to app. The extras it has that out perform google and even the different voices it was awesome. Past several months it's all wrong. It has me lost more than once doesn't find my location. It's literally turned into one of the worst navigation apps and I dont know what happened. I'm going to uninstall it and go back to google. They are adding similar features that once made this a great app
The apps great, but doesn't speed track that much. Before this, they inform there any speed track around, but not anymore. Please upgrade.
This is so cool! I just wish you could add a Sonic voice.

I like the app but because it freezes all of sudden in the middle of the road, it makes my travelling dangerous. Previously it was not the case but now it first tells me to go towards one direction and after a while switches me to completely another direction. It is very dangerous and should be taken legal action if continues as such. Please fix it.

Good for getting to where you need to go in smaller cities. App makes you take shortcuts to get around slow parts of traffic, but doesn't account for traffic on those shortcuts, turning what could be five saved minutes into more time lost getting to your destination. Would recommend default Google Maps over this, rather get there and sit in traffic for a bit than end up in an accident taking a shortcut that saves a whole two minutes.

Each update breaks more and more stuff. Is this not being tested before updates go out? I now have to tell Waze at least twice where I want to go (even when choosing from favorites while sitting at my house connected to fiber WiFi), when playing music on the radio or Spotify on Android Auto volume continuously rises and liwers whether it's speaking or not, and Audible refuses to play now because it thinks Waze is always talking. Is there any way to roll back to an older version? Thanks for breaking Waze right before a major US travel holiday - probably why this release wasn't properly tested, which is exactly why this release should not have went out.

Waze is no longer accurate. While driving it's telling me I left my route and I need to turn here or there to get back on route. Sometimes tells me I have arrived when I'm actually still several miles away from destination. Thinking it may be my location on my Google Pixel, I went to Google Maps. 100% accurate. Went back to Waze. Started telling me I was of route and where I needed to turn. All this on a 20 mile strip of interstate.
replyContent: Hi David, we're here to help! Please send us the details in a Facebook private message so we can further investigate. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I think on the surface waze is really great it's a great app I enjoy using it and has a lot of great features one thing I would suggest though is that you give the people the ability to do reviews on the companies and that will make it more user-friendly for people that are trying to get to a place and know if it's good enough. it's certainly a great app for people like me better delivery drivers professionally and helps us get to our destination and do what we need to do so great job guys

Too much clutter, the team seems to need to show that they are working and the only way they found is adding more and more stuff on the screen. And when you make abstraction of the visual clutter you realize that the app is no more accurate. Last and most important thing is that the app is becoming DANGEROUS. I spend more and more time on screen closing banners, where my eyes should be on the road. So, this is really not the good way to go.

content: The overall is really useful. There a couple of things that can be improved: 1) Sometimes the arrow on the map falls behind, so you might have made the turn already, but the arrow is still lagging. For an inexperienced user this might cause confusion. 2) Sometimes you are being directed on a "shortcut" on very narrow streets, to avoid traffic on the main roads. But this overall takes more time ans effort, than just using the main streets.

I used to like this application more than Google Maps. But now every time when I used it, it keeps saying "No GPS. Showing approximate location." I've already tried "Force Stop" and "Clear Cache" in order to fix it, unfortunately it's still not working.....

This app works great is very good navigation. But when you are using it While playing music on the radio it turns the volume down when it starts to speak the next turn and then it keeps it down and doesn't turn it backup you constantly have to re adjust volume to listen to the radio this makes it very frustrating and needs to change . Then I would give it a 5

Was working great until recently. No matter what I did to my location settings, updated the app, restarted my phone. It wouldn't give me my correct location and I'd only figure it out while driving, which is really unpleasant when you're going somewhere you don't know and your GPS has you somewhere else altogether.
replyContent:
Hi Jasmine, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks.

content: This use to be my go to app for navigation but not anymore. It is always freezing with android auto. I can't click on the alerts. It won't let me zoom in and out on the map. I even tried removing and reinstalling it. Until these issues get fixed I won't be reinstalling the app again.

Really liked app, until sound became so low cant hear in traffic even with media settings at max. That resulted in an uninstall reinstall. Other issues; it doesn't provide alternative routes like Google does. Also doesn't seem to recognize where No Right or No Left turns are. For the most part it is better than Google. If I wanted to spend $$ on a professional trucking GPS, I would

content: So Waze is nice for police feature, but the "alternate routes" load VERY SLOWLY. Additionally, you miss a turn and some exit/merge/enter notifications are delayed. Have been using Google Maps more because it's much faster. Many times the map routes me incorrectly/other than what I want, and doesn't load enough alternatives either. I've used it long and short distance. While it's a solid app at baseline, but it needs A LOT of fine-tuning.

content: It use to be good. now I am having to uninstall and reinstall the app 2 to 3 times a day. It has been freezing up. Whe you try to exit the app it dont let you. Then when you try to go back in ot dont let you. Now that you install the app you loose everything that was stored there. I will wait to see if there is another update. I'm going to miss the app because it helps me in new cities.

This app is pretty good to give real time directions but the thing I absolutely HATE about waze is that just when you need the direction a f*****g pop up appears. I am trying to navigate traffic and I have to close the damn pop up to get the direction. Very dangerous!!!!!ü§¨ Change this PLEASE or I will use another app. Disgraceful!!

Solid GPS. I give it a 4.5. Is much more built up in Seattle than it was 5 years ago when I first installed it. Only thing it needs for me to give it 5 stars is more accuracy at the destination. When I am on the correct block, it should show the individual buildings or houses so I know where the destination is. Currently, the endpoint can be 1-3 houses away from the correct address. I often find myself opening Google Maps for that last little piece of info as to which house.

I have had great experiences with Waze. The estimated time is usually correct unless I try to beat it. üòä There have only been a couple of times when my directions were slightly flawed and those were usually when there were recent changes on the road. Sometimes I know some routes that will be quicker than the directions provided by Waze, though. When I take them, my time does change to the earlier arrival time.

I used this in place of Google maps. Big mistake. It told me about a stalled car, debris in the road, and a cop that wasn't there. But didn't warn me about a major traffic jam on the interstate. Added 20 minutes to my trip home from work. Immediately uninstalled. Sorry Google! Didn't mean to stray..

Meh! I decided to uninstall Waze. I was in a Motorway (in UK), Waze told me "you've arrived at your destination" while I was still driving in a Motorway!!! Not only once I had this experience, but twice!! Bloody useless!! Very dangerous! Really waste my time using this app! It was supposed to be a 20 mins journey, I arrived 1 hour later. What a stressful journey I had that night.

Been using Waze for a very long time now. Up until October 5th it worked excellent with Android auto. Now I cannot load Waze through Android auto. Everytime I try to launch Waze I get a black screen that freezes everything. Oddly enough both programs and my phone say no updates were installed. Can't figure out. Looks like it's back to google maps.
How do I stop waze from taking me to the back of an address? I want to go where I need to, not somewhere else.

content: Navigation needs to add the Street names and what lane to stay on when driving highway's and and toles. Apple does that. Why can't we? But android is superior. Idk if google takes suggestions on here but if they made directions and navigating more accurate that'd be way more efficient. For example Which lanes to stay on, what street to turn on. Or merge this with google maps all together to make google maps better. Thanks google. I like the different themed characters for navigation. üòé

content: It worked fine for a few months then I got the message that it was not connected to the GPS. I have done several uninstalled and reinstalled but it is still not giving me directions. I'm driving do I can't hold the phone and find the "highlighted area" and there seems to be no way to contact the app to find out what is wrong This app sucks!!!!

First run, I had it take me home. I go by a rest area, and Waze kinda went nuts. Zoom in, zoom out, zoom in, zoom out, zoom in, zoom out, until I got past the rest area. Other issues as well, such as paragraph size messages that pop in for like 1.75 seconds then disappear. On my cellphone. Mounted on the windshield, at arm's length. I can't read that. I guess I need to spend more time with Waze, so I can disable such nonsensical actions.

This is the worst GPS navigation I have ever tried...   Early 2019 in North of Germany. Winter has arrived and there are many dangers for the adventurous driver to come from one place to another. After hearing so much praise - let's try...  Map coverage is poor. Main exits and entries to freeways (Landstrassen) are missing. Speed limits are missing for entire cities. Speed limits are missing for areas.  So, yeah, let's drive additional 15km as this simple GPS does not know the exits, entries of roads built 15 years ago. No problem. But hell, I DO know better...  When Tom Tom Go snaps to a new route in a split second, Waze gives you memories of the 80s. Just turn into an "un-planned" route and Waze re-calculates... and re-calculates... and re-calculates... and re-calc..? No! A new route has been found? Let's see? Oh, turnaround an follow the first calculated route again? Gnaaarrrghh....  Waze is being praised for community content of maps - okay, let's fix that. After signing up, after six days, after recording like 20 new routes - they simply do not show up on web editor. And yes, I am logged in with the same account details.  Never again. Back to Tom Tom Go.

I prefer this app to other GPS apps.. WHEN IT WORKS! It suddenly started having issues today. I have had to uninstall and reinstall 4 times today! It will work the first time I use it, but when I try to use it again, it freezes and closes and won't reopen. I don't know what happened since Saturday, but it's been quite frustrating today. As an Instacart shopper who uses this app up to 12 times a day, it is annoying to have to uninstall & reinstall every time I want to use it!
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this app issue you‚Äôre experiencing to help. To do so, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The following was fixed at one point and now with an update it's back to the same. Constantly crashing in Andiod Auto MyChevrolet after recent update. Locks up during Navigation then jumps back to where you are, then puts your GPS location way off the road you are on and then jumps back to where you really are. It is horrible!!! Also would be nice if there was a Commercial Truck mode that routed you correctly so you don't encounter restricted roads and bad / too sharp of turns.
replyContent: Hi there! We're sorry to hear about your issue. Please send us a private message on Facebook with all the details so we can look in to it further. Regarding truck mode suggestion, please feel free to vote for this idea on our suggestion box: tinyurl.com/yao5pza4 Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love it. I couldn't not drive outside my home town with out this app. I would get lost. I like how it shows you in what I call slow down for dummies mode. Let's me know in advance to slow down so I don't miss my turn off. Also it doesn't say turn around at this exit or point. It recalculates your route. So if u have to make an emergency detour it helps a lot. Keep up the good work.

Used to be 5* Fantastic - in last 12 months gradually getting worse as Google (who own Waze) seem to be putting less and less effort into it in fvour of their own Google Maps (which is still rubbish). Reports are not updated, Speed Limits on M20 still show old data despite me hitting the Map Error button every day for 3 weeks, Speed Cams that are no longer there are still reported, despite me hitting the X button every day for weeks, and so on. Its got to a point where it is now diverting me around roadworks and Speed Limits that are no longer there, adding 20-30mins to my daily drive. Resintalled, updated, everything tried. Seems to be an App Problem

Inaccurate , Dangerous, Anoying , Professional Driver. pop ups want to use your camera for Google stock at most destinations as you arrive. Many distractions while driving, it frequently sends me in the opposite direction, changes to non optimal routes, adds crazy round about ways. Wrong way on one way street, no clue about restrictive traffic navigations such as Traffic patterns that are not wise or even possible to navigate as it proposes. It has glitches all night, sadly we caution use.

I do food delivery services so I'm using waze everyday I've noticed it can get confuse, for example I got an order for a place called pressed cafe and it was trying to send me to another pressed Cafe that was in another direction. When you're coming out of a turn and there is s quick right or left it doesn't come on quick enough to tell you which direction especially when you have position your vehicle in the correct lane must turn left or right if there's no car behind me cool!
replyContent:
Hi Ramon, thanks you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about this issue you're experiencing, please send us a private message on Facebook.

content: Last month, it took me to the wrong address 4 plus times, maybe it's only good for iPhone users because when I had iPhone th iui s was excellent

content: Waze Team ‚Äì Love the app! but have some suggestions for improvements. 1. Reduce the number of icon/button presses for Traffic, Police, Hazard, etc. When the orange icon is pressed the new window would have Traffic icons across the top row, Hazzard across the second row, Police across the next row. This would be way better than having to go through multiple button presses to get to the Traffic, Police, Hazard icon selections. Also, give the option in setup to eliminate the Submit button. Should on

Indispensable, I don't drive without it! It helps me find different routes to my destination if the traffic is congested. I love that I can plan ahead for a journey later in the day, & it will remind me when it is time to leave, taking into account any traffic holdups that have occurred in the meantime. I can let other Wazers know when I've come across a hazard, like an accident, or vehicle parked at the side of the road, so they're aware ahead of time. You can locate mobile Police cameras.
Real good app.gets ya right there.
It's too easy to know where is the location to head to the destination

Now it no longer opens. Stuck on initialising because there's "no network connection" bwahahaha. Used to love this app but recently it has more issues than worth it. Can't even report bugs using the in-app service. Constantly locks up. Can find a place but can't select and navigate to it. Can't plan a drive anymore, etc etc

This was fantastic, I really loved the interaction and accuracy. But lately it has really been degraded. Location tracking has been way off. Especially when stationary or moving slowly, I often see my position catapulted between a 1/2 mile radius. Worse experience was when my location and voice instructions were out of sync. Being told to make a turning quite some time after the junction was bad. Really hope they sort these issues out as this used to be my go to nav app.

Don't drive without Waze. Walking thru a hotel lobby full of people, a friend asked what was the best app for driving. Another friend with us said Waze. I said Waze. Two people walking the other way stopped to endorse Waze. I heard a couple other voices endorse Waze. So, yeah, Waze. No, it's not perfect. No software is. Waze is just the best at what it does, get you where you're going with minimal delays.
Really good app. However won't let you enter details on the map once you've moved from the location.

Almost lost 3 hours on the road because of waze. I was driving through Hungary and it seemd weird that it pointed me off the highway. After 30 minutes of pointless driving I checked other gps and it showed me the right route of 9 hours instead of the 12 that waze was taking me... and I've checked all the possible settings in waze, it's set to fastest route. The long distance routing calculation is just so bad, not the first time it happened... It's a shame, I used waze alot before but I'm done.

I cannot find a way to change the setting to take me on the route with the shortest time versus shortest distance. I use Waze or Google Maps every day on my commute to avoid traffic, but Waze is always trying to take me off the highway through a town where it takes much more time. Changing routes whike driving is also not working so I can't tell if I'm going the best way. However, it is good seeing what hazards are on the road based on what people post.

It's a pretty good navigation app except a few things. You can't report things like roadkill on the other side of the road. You can't delete police reports from the other side of the road. Sometimes, when you don't have mobile data signal, when you report something, it just tried to send them to the server once and of it fails, it just removes the report instead of waiting for mobile signal and sending it then to the server.

The app really sucks, it constantly crashes, constant errors and when you are trying to communicate with others the messages sometimes won't go through or the will crash as it loves to do. I've sent feedback about it and I just get a message stating they're working on fixing the issues but with how horrible the app continues to act I think they need to hire better programmers because it has a lot to wish for.

Last update broke waze. I use it with android auto and I thought it was a number of things (android auto? My car?) before I discovered that it was waze. Constantly says no network connection, constantly disconnects while driving, but Google maps works just fine. I uninstalled waze after it spent 5 minutes on the screen showing my car driving in the ocean. Google maps is now my daily driver again. Maps looks nicer anyways. Waze UI and appearance is extremely dated. 2009 anyone? Needs a makeover.

Does not work with android auto. I plug into my radio, turn on waze, set a destination, and the icon just sits there and never moves. It does not record my trip. Also trying to submit a report is frustrating. It keeps telling me my email is invalid. I have already deleted waze and android auto and reinstalled them. Did not fix it.

I've used Waze for years but recent changes have made the app illegal to use in my state (MA). The OK WAZE feature was removed which makes the app illegal due to new hands free laws. Waze says to use the microphone button (which is hidden behind the search button requiring two button presses) but when you issue a command like "go home" it literally puts the words "go home" in the search bar instead of navigating to home. Please restore OK WAZE finctionality.
replyContent:
Hi, David! "OK Waze" has been replaced with Google assistant, so you can still use voice commands. To switch it on, open Waze > Search > Settings > Voice & sound > Tap Google Assistant. More info here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9332876?hl=en


For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Add more vehicle types... I drive an 18 wheeler for a living it would be good to have that as an option, you give 3 options "Private Car", "Taxi", and "Motorcycle"... i have to use private car, which is i guess the same... just consider this though cars can go where a lot of trucks can't due to restrictions weight, height and hell maybe a 53' trailer strapped to my back... please consider adding this as an option

I usually absolutely love this app. I bought a new phone put it on my phone and it now will show the first screen and then it's off. And then it comes on and then off. So I cannot even get it past the opening screen to do anything with. I've undownloaded it or uninstalled. And reinstalled multiple times. Is there any reason it's doing that? Because I do miss this app terribly
replyContent: We‚Äôre disappointed to hear you‚Äôre having issues accessing the app, Davie. Let us help! To best assist and investigate this issue, please send us a private message on Facebook. Thank you.

content: Gets you where you need to go most times. Has a problem putting you in alley ways behind the address you put in. And also will not give you the most efficient way. If 2 routes will take the same about of time, it ALWAYS gives you the longer route. It will also send it several miles out of the way to save 1 or 2 minutes. It needs work, but it didn't seem they care enough to fix simple issues.

Turn by turn directions do not update. The iphone version of the app is much better. I dont need to watch the map when I'm driving. I want to see the directions listed but the list of turns does not update as I complete each step. I have to keep refreshing the list to see the next turns ahead, which is a driving hazard. Please fix this. It should run the same way it does on the iPhone.

Totally useless at best and dangerous at worst and should be removed from the play store. It usually doesn't work, GPS is frozen in a single location, never moving except the few rare times it does work for a few minutes before locking to a point while in the middle of a drive, leaving you to try to find somewhere safe to pull over and load Google Maps to get you where you need to be.
replyContent: Hi Shawn, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about GPS issue to investigate further. content: It is accurate most if the time. You do need to watch out for it does not like to tell you to turn around and will sometimes take you way out of the way just to back track instead of having you do a u turn. Also will have you avoid taking a left on a busy intersection and take you through a neighborhood to avoid it which has you turn left on a busy street with no stop light which takes twice as long.

Great app and with the network of everyone that uses this app is a plus. Easy to put in police, hazards and etc. while driving. One thing i would add to improve is the amount of police people see at one location and if there is a cop moble on the road with the direction they are heading. Besides that a must have app!!!!!
This is a good app but sometimes it will confuse by giving directions that takes you out of the short way.

Performance on roads/maps accuracy = fine, no issues, perhaps take into consideration that on small roads also slow drivers drive (with actual speed half of allowed = e.g. 40 km/h instead of 80 km/h); app performance = terrible, sometimes loosing points, also would like to have an option to report road issues from the app - if its there, it's pretty hidden = not very user friendly

A good navigation app. But have some room for further improvements. 1) The live navigating panel should display the ADDRESS of the "destination", on the blank unused space at the top of the screen, and perhaps also display the "distance to" destination too, in real time navigation. 2) The audio announcement at reaching destination should inform the user whether the destination is on the "Left" or "Right" side, just as the Google Maps App does.

I love Waze, however for the past few weeks it's been taking a long time to lock onto satellite signals via Android Auto. Switch to Google Maps and it locks position almost instantly, back to Waze and it's still not found where I am. Yesterday it took 15 minutes of a 20 minute drive before Waze locked my position. Anyone else suffering the same issue? I'm feeling that I cannot use Waze until this is fixed. üò¢

This is an all inclusive app for traffic and directions. I'm so glad I don't have to use a second app to check my routing to or from work for road closures, road construction, etc. This app combines directions and traffic into one app with the added convenience of gas prices and speed trap information. Awesome app!

I used to love this app. Now everytime I use it its constantly re routing me for no reason in the middle of my drive and losing my spot on the map. Yesterday it keeps telling me to turn onto a street I was already on or telling me to turn onto a street I had passed blocks ago. I cant rely on it anymore to get me to places that I'm not familiar with. Please fix these bugs

Worked OK initially, but then intermittently lost GPS and didn't know where it was. I use it with Android Auto which continues to work well using Google Maps with no GPS issues. I seems to me that the GPS issue is with Waze. I note that there are many other reviews stating similar problems. The developers should investigate and fix these issues because Waze is a good concept if it worked properly.

When it works, it is great. The only reason I used the app previously was it was super easy to plan trips for future times...that just full stop doesn't work since the last update. I cleared the cache and user data, but that only worked for the first go around. Starting the app again...ready to start my trip...it doesn't load the route.
replyContent: Hi Michael, it seems like there may be an issue here. If you could share some details with us via Facebook private message, we can help get this resolved as soon as possible. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love the idea but it doesn't give the quickest routes. The other day I was driving about 30 miles to my house. It told me that it would take 1 hour 30 minutes and to take the local route with all the traffic lights. I decided to get on the interstate instead and travel time dropped immediately. Then it told me to get off at every exit, trying to get me back on the local route. As I passed each exit my travel time went down. It ended up taking me about 45 minutes to get home. USE GOOGLE MAPS!!!
This apps always lagging and location not always accurate. It is annoying when i cannot use this apps on place that have slow internet. Please do better.
This is a great app. Im writing to make a suggestion. This app wld be great if it had satellite view and 3d street view.

Previously rated 5 stars but it takes weeks to update new red light/speed cameras even though I repeatedly report them. Waze should at the very least instantly pin such items on the map of the user that makes the submission. Also I find Google Maps better for navigating to places by name and finding POIs w/ reviews. Also unlike Google Maps, if you leave another app up on the screen for too long Waze will stop navigating.

I had great hopes for this. Slow, to the point of being worthless. I'd input an address, and 10 minutes later it is still thinking about it. On the few occasions it did load, if I changed course it would again start thinking about it and neved come up with a route. Don't waste ur time with this.

Overall it is a good app, estimated time of arrival is as good as it can get, sharing collisions on the road and so on is also well done,... But one reason why I always get back to Google Maps is the bug in Android Auto that puts Waze into category of barely useable apps in terms of compatibility with AA. When that gets fixed I will be glad to edit this to 5 stars.
replyContent: Hi Stanislav, thanks for contacting us and your feedback. We'd like to hear more about the Android Auto issue you mentioned to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This seems like it'd be a good app but touching the screen anywhere at any time has unknowable consequences, frequently involving the map throwing wildly and spinning randomly, or having dozens of cards appear at once and severapll of them start shouting at you while the back button has been changed to a third function that also throws up a bunch of cards that start talking. Even when it does behave, panning and zooming on the map snaps weirdly to just not where you put it for no apparent reason and trying to select a place on tue map invariably selects something else nearby.

This application is very good, but the problem is that you can not save a lot of places. I have saved about 70 places now and it does not save more than that. The next thing is that you can not sort the places you saved For example, in another application, the option is named in order of distance or in order. You can even categorize For example, put the locations of one country in one file and place another country in another file. Solve these few issues, your application will be better th

Great app but compatibility could be improved. I noticed that when I'm using Waze as navigation system with my Skoda Swing infotainment system, Android Auto constantly crashes or freezes (after a car restart for instance, or when switching between Waze and Spotify for instance). When I'm using Google Maps, this issue does not occur.  Is this something you are aware of? Are you planning to solve this bug in an upcoming update?

Like many, I too loved this app but as of late it is unreliable. It loses connectivity if it had any to begin with. It will bounce all over the map and lose track of where it is. Delays of up to 30 seconds if I'm lucky enough to have work even close to correctly. Have had to start using google maps...

I use this on my everyday drive. I live in a small city I never really thought anyone actually used this app but when there was super backed up traffic I used the app to look further down the road and low and behold it said there was car crashes. I always make sure it's up and running before I roll out of my driveway.

Works well, but I encountered an issue recently with Chevrolet MyLink. With my phone connected to MyLink via Bluetooth and Waze running, if I accept an incoming phone call, the car's phone chime will continue forever until you shut off the car for 5 min. Also, you cannot answer the call. This only happens with Waze running.

Waze keeps disconnecting from GPS and won't connect back. I have to turn it off and on again. But when it connects to GPS, it gives this unwelcoming message "Something went wrong..." Power cycling the phone doesn't help. Waze is practically unusable. NOTE: 2 stars and not 1 star because it worked literally once. That one moment, it was very helpful.

I've been using Waze for about 7 to 8 years now. Everyday it gets better and better. Unfortunately it is not perfect. one thing that I don't like about it is that an effort to save time, even 30 seconds, it'll take you on the back roads instead of taking you on one straight main road. Other than that. Waze is definitely much better than most other map and softwares. This especially comes true with the possibility of giving warnings about police, and other things on the road.

It will get you to your destination but terrible for predicting arrival time and avoiding traffic. If there is no traffic you have to drive way above the speed limit to get there at the predicted time. If there is traffic or an accident it is terrible for routing you on the best route. Google maps is way more reliable for giving you the fastest route.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback, Brian. Waze is a crowd-sourced real-time navigation app and it is possible that due to different reports by other Wazers and changing traffic conditions, the route you got was not optimal. If you notice a recurring issue with a route, please send us a private message on Facebook with the details: https://m.me/waze

content: I love using Waze and use it almost every day, even if I know where I'm going. It's a great app and has helped me countless times get around the crawling traffic of Atlanta. My only problem is that it occasionally says "Searching for network" and I either have to restart the app or put the adress back in. Something that I would like to see on Waze is a feature, like on Google Maps, where you can check the distance between two places. Otherwise, Waze is an amazing app and I highly recommend it.

There needs to be a paid version with no ads. The voice commands also need to be more prompt, without the delay before you can respond. There also needs to be a setting for Waze to not try to connect to nearby WiFi. There should be customizable quick icons on the map to report common hazards with one click.

Waze is excellent for routing and as a sat nav can't be faulted. But one thing is EXTREMELY ANNOYING. You can set up alerts for speed, accidents, police etc but the audible alert volume is so low you don't hear them. You can turn the volume up but then the voice directions are far too loud. If alerts were louder and possibility to have different sounds for different alerts this would be greatest app ever
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Brendan! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. content: The best app for finding the best root while driving üôÇ

It's very good how the app is designed but the only thing missing is that waze don't tell you on which lane you need to stay or you can use to make your turn before just tell you the indication, it will be more useful if you do it like Google maps does it and so if you are in a new area and not familiar with the roads you already now which lane to use. I hope you guys make this change because it can be really helpful. Thanks

I've been using your app for a week. And I really think you're at sucks. Compared to Google Maps. There is no comparison. Google Maps I deliver food for GrubHub hey Google Maps will take me straight to there your map your GPS takes me around about way to get somewhere I use more gas I use more time and I've traveled more miles using this app then any other GPS have I ever used. replyContent: Hi Larry, we're so sorry to hear that! Thank for bringing this issue to our attention. Could you please send us more details in a Facebook private message? We'd like to investigate further. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: What a gem! I found waze so easy to use, realtime updates from other people around you which you can communicate with. Advanced warnings of accidents, traffic, hazards etc and speed, both current and legal limit for the road you're on. You can change so many details to make it work for you such as car type, fuel type and speed can be changed from mph to kmh for driving on the continent. Highly recommended.

Great GPS navigation app. Always correct info on speed limits, speed cams, hidden police, traffic etc. However, since the last update of Waze, the new voice recorder option was changed from default of Waze to the F-ing Google Voice Speach and it is a real BS. Totally making the good experience WORSE. Furthermore, before the last update Waze was able to find roads that were not visible in Google Maps and other GPS apps, now its even worse and can't find a simple location. 1/10 stars.

content: I see a speed camera and I want to pin it on the map. I can only do this safely some minutes later WHEN I AM STOPPED! Some really OBVIOUS UI behaviour missing; does Waze allow me to pin the report to a specific location other than where I am at that moment? NO. Does Waze allow me to pin that report with my GPS off? NO. Does waze allow me to access the report icon when NOT in navi mode? NO. Actually, given how Waze wants you to operate the report features is downright dangerous. Dumb & dumber.

This app from good to bad & bad to worse. When I on the road I know which way is faster but it keep ask me go long way. When I at Robinson road going to AMK, wave show me turn 1 big round & use long way back while I can just turn left & go straight to CTE back. I use CTE going to AMK it keep ask me exit every exit there is near by while I go all the way straight is AMK exit. I just need use it for police reporting around. Today I try to use again of the way they give & I go my way to destination end up it will not recalculate bring me to location i want & suddenly just stop it without reporting. Police near by also no reporting. Last time this app is ok but not now. Hope it will improve & not getting worse. Pls do something on this.

So tired of this app's BS. i started using it before the Google acquisition and it has steadily deteriorated into a worse and more buggy Google Maps with the ability to put some bubbles on the road. 5 times in the past two weeks it has told me to go to the side of the NJTP with worse traffic and i ended up sitting there literally staring at traffic moving with no problem on the side i was told to leave. A great feature is the way it says "uh oh! error calculating route" 6 times in a row. eff off

This is an excellent application that has accompanied me for several years. Its not perfect but definitely one of the best. Unfortunately, after updating the device to Android 10, the option of "keep waze on top" disappeared from the application. This is a feature that is important to me (and may save lives!). I hope that soon the application will be updated and the feature will be restored. Only then can I give waze the stars it deserves. Update 6.12.20: Its been over a year and today came an update that includes the feature of "keep waze on top". End of the tedious games of having to fiddle with the mobile while driving to get the application back. It's just a shame it took a year. Now the app should take care of more swift traffic updates and better AI route planning. Update 8.12.20: I was happy too fast. There is a bug that does not allow the use of "keep waze on top". If the device is in landscape mode, I get a wonderful black screen and I need to remove the device from the car holder and rotate it to portrait mode for the screen to turn back on. Really useful :-(. For now I keep the mobile in portrait mode, but I hope to return it to portrait mode which is much better for map viewing. You asked to reach to you in facebook, which I did few months ago. ZERO replies, like I am writing to myself. Next time when you ask for something at least have the curtesy to read it please. The bug still exists....
replyContent: Hi Thomas, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this Keep Waze on Top issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The problem with the screen changing as 1 person stated. Also, the Voice doesn't work all the time. I've got everything possible in hi sound mode and nothing! It never remembers my choices. It used to. I love this app when working. Definitely needs work. Thanks for your time.

content: Don't always keep on my phone for space reasons but I love this app especially for long drives. It gives you everything you need real time and is so user friendly. Only complaint is ability to map out long trip all at once... I had to put destination at half way then when I got to a certain point could extend the destination but wouldn't allow me to go from A-B. (This was from NY-FL) However, even with that & having Ggl maps pre installed I HIGHLY recommend this app it's capabilities make getting directions and conditions of trip and even driving speed (gives the speed limit as well as speed you are going and if you are over etc)

I really like the app. It is very accurrate. My only problem...and its a big one is that ads pop up while you are driving which is very dangerous. When Im driving I ONLY want to see the mavigation screen. I almost had an accident bcuz some ads popped up while I was driving and I almost had an accident. PLEASE refrain from ads until the trip is complete Thanks from Carl

I'm a share ride driver, i really whish this app would communicate with my lyft app easier! it just have the thinking icon most of the time and i have to switch to google maps. also once i got the app working, a lot of the area it would have network error or serching for network, it's frustrating! also why they don't have Cantonese a option for the voice? even google maps has it!

UPDATE: I redownloaded the app and now it works, seems to be some sort of downtime that occurred when I tested it. Amazing app! ORIGINAL: Used to be excellent, now it doesn't load, says there is no network connection. Google Maps loads without issue, I'm listening to music through the internet in the background - I assume the service has been discontinued since I last used it, sadly.
replyContent: Hi William, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I got this app for 1 reason only: to forewarn me of speed cameras. It shows me where they are, but doesn't give me any warning tone whatsover. You're supposed to be watching the road, not looking ahead for cameras on your phone. I have a brand new BMW w/ better gps than this. All I needed was warnings for speed cameras. The app failed. I'll look for a better app.
The UI looks like it was designed for children. Instant turn off for me.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or have feature requests you'd like to submit to us, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Generally a good app for navigating efficient routes from point A to B. I find a lot of the notification icons (other than "traffic") to be less than intuitive and to require too much hunting for someone focused on the road. The GPS cannot discern Rt 278 (exits 47 or 48) from the adjacent Bruckner Blvd service road in Bronx NY. Everytime single time I drive the latter it thinks I'm on the former and directs me to exit miles after I've already done so.

Used to be perfect. Then they let pop up ads ruin experience... In California you can get fined for touching your phone, this dumb app now asks idiotic pop up questions like 'set up a ride share with folks who live by you?' and they STAY ONSCREEN! They block your view of the map and won't go away until you tap the screen! Add to that the fact that the voice commands only work some of the time which makes it necessary to look at the screen in order to stay on track, but the ads block view. Ugh.

How did a great app.get sooo outdated, bad? Bought a 2019 vehicle WITH actual sat.nav. It has traffic,and will work in the middle of nowhere. Tried to use Pie, nothing.Plus Oreo still isn't compatible with auto.OEM AA. OEM auto.&Google need to talk,and issue updates to the app. Like Google nav.,it now wants EVERY access to your mobile. Eg. I don't WANT my SMS visible on the infotainment if certain people are in the vehicle.

Give an option to remove the carpool notifications. I drive a company vehicle to different locations every day. I won't be using it. And this morning, I'm navigating city traffic, and instead of seeing where I'm going, I get "Welcome! Let's set up your carpool!" So I have to take a hand off the wheel to turn it off. This is dangerous, and unacceptable.

Great app for car travellers. I would really appreciate if you could add in Germany the possibilty to avoid Umweltzone. It will be of a great importance to have a possibilty to set a car type, for example Euro 5 Diesel, and to avoid forbidden roads / city districts - where only Euro 6 norm is allowed. Looking forward for your support!
For the past 2 days it has been saying searching for network but I have full service. Then I Uninstaller it amd reinstalled it and now it won't even let me log back in.

Had you asked me a year ago, I would have given it 5 stars and directed you to download the app and use it. It WAS very handy, very informative and actually pleasant to use. Since about nine months ago, (not sure if this coincides with an "update" or not, but it doesn't matter at this juncture) it stinks to high heaven. First, it can never find my account any longer. "Disappeared into to the ether" I think is the message conveyed. Well, then you have to initiate another account, and within a day or two, when opening the app again, that account, too, has "Disappeared into the ether." So, like anything else, you mess me up a few times, and I start to look elsewhere for the services I utilize. Google Maps is it. The interface is more user friendly, projected alternate time and routes are right there on the map should you chose to use them, the my account never "disappears into the ether" and forces me to waste time creating another account that I'll never use for anything else nevers pops up, and when you attempt to use your current email or phone number, it says there is already an account with that name/number! How is that physically possible, when you just got done informing me that my account has "disappeared into the ether"? Nah... done with this app, and I will confidently direct you towards Google Maps for a try. Too bad you can't give it zero stars.

This USED TO BE the best app for traffic until Google bought the rights to it. Now its nothing but ads OVER the driving instructions and that is when you can get it to load. It changes its mind at the last minute on highways and I can't tell you how many times it has directed me down closed roads or told me to turn where I can't. When maps is better then this sad.....Stop screwing with this app Google!!!

The app did not update my location as I drove my vehicle. It also wanted to take over the "search for directions" button on the GPS, this action was confusing and infuriating. It did not stop until Waze was removed. The default Google maps on my phone is much better, it updated my location as I drove and showed traffic congestion.

Vignette storm. I don't like the way adding vignettes in advance (luckily there is no end date feature yet) to have "best routes". What will be the next step, must we add insurance copy or tank level starting a miserable journey? For me it was more than enough the possilbility disabling/enabling "toll roads". Are you going to step into vignette selling business? Or why this "feature" is good? If I not count that the application wants to rule me, the navigation, the look, the handling is OK.

"Sorry something went wrong" message is what I get every now and then and it always happens when I am heading to work or leaving work. Even now I am parked trying to figure out how to get around traffic and get to work on time. This app has glitches or losing its routing connections and I am thinking I can't rely much on this app anymore.
replyContent: Hi Kadijah, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It was great, but lately it is full of bugs. You start a new route and he does not start with your present location. Instead, he picks a spot and asks you to come to this spot - even if there is no road to it. And it is CONSTANTLY changing route and updating it. Also, have a feeling many users left the app because live feed is not anymore as it was - shows fanthom speed cameras, no works where they are etc.
replyContent: Hi Luka, thank you for the feedback. We're happy to help. Please feel free to message us on Facebook with more details about these issues. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: For the most part I've had no problems with the app. But can you link Waze to a different platform other than Facebook. I was thinking like Instagram or something like that? Also when there's an accident or object on road can you add a button that says which lane. Left, middle or right lane so we can get out of the lane before we get to the issue? Thanks

app is becoming increasingly less reliable; sending me down longer routes, changing the route after i've selected my preferred option, & abruptly ending directions before i've gotten to my destination. it's handy that you can pinpoint a difficult spot in the map when you get to it, but not great that it asks for a description while you're driving; would be safer if it pops up at the end of your trip.

content: Waze is always Dependable. I really like that it shows you where police officers are and red light cameras Etc. It's good that other users participates and r open to sharing what's going on around them. It's a great way to be social and keep people safe and out of a ticket. maps are up-to-date and traffic jams are usually right on. I like that you can also use your own voice!

Uh oh routing server timeout. This is the story of my life when trying to use Waze navigation. Completely useless. And the solution listed on Google is to break up my search into segments? So what am I supposed to do navigate to a random spot on the highway then enter another segment while driving? For an app that's been around as long as Waze, the performance is an absolute joke. Google Map navigation has no such issues.

Went from the best app ever to the worst in 1 update. Constantly cuts off in the middle of navigation. It apparently thinks that I now drive sideways. Fix these errors or role back to the prior version until you iron them out..... if not it will be google maps from now on. While it is free they sell expensive ads that i have actually used to advertise. Wont be doing that until this is fixed and usable.

There is one BIG reason I cannot use Waze. The adds pop up during navigation and cover the directions. This is a huge problem. Just yesterday I decided to give it another try. At least three times during my trip adds covered my directions at a time when I was approaching a turn and I couldn't see in advance which lane I needed to be in. If ever there is a paid version or at least one where the adds don't appear while driving I will gladly try again.

content: Isn't working properly, won't load when I am trying to find out traffic and times to get to places at different times despite the fact I have full wifi and no issues with google maps so it isnt my phone... Gets worse with every update!!! When it works its great but so unreliable and faulty, especially when using it for work!

The app used to be awesome. I've had to delete it, as with so many others, it doesn't keep my location consistently. I live in one of the biggest tourist areas in the country, Orlando, so it really should not be losing the signal here. I'll keep coming back checking comments before I reinstall

Used to be great. over the last year, however, the "plan a drive" feature has gone terribly down hill. I'll plan my drive every week, going to the airport at 4pm. Everytime it says 32 minutes, right in the thick of rush hour, and every time it takes ke 70+ minutes. Now granted I know I need to leave 80 minutes ahead juat to be sure. I just wish waze would give an accurate or at least semi-accurate estimate. I do like the other features though (not the ads... so many ads!!)

Since Waze was taken by Google its service is gradually deteriorating. Many times it seemed like there's no connection between the guiding map and the actual situation. Sometimes it shows traffic jams while no car is seen ahead or anywhere around. Other time it tells you to take a detour while even on the map the road ahead looks free. Frankly speaking, I am afraid to download the update as I don't trust them too much. I'm using Waze as a kind of recommendation advisory, no more.

content: Very slow. Can't process on the fly. You have to slow down or stop. I've had this app drive me down the wrong way and suggest a 6 mile drive and I was sitting right in front of the location. Needs longer notification time before turn. Needs a 'shortest distance' button. Doordash uses this application and it seems to add miles to every drive. When I use this app outside Doordash, the mileage difference can be substantial from when using Doordash. I would like to know why.
