content: Waze is so much better than Google maps! The routes are more up to date & more convenient than the ones that Google would always choose for me. Google was under the impression that an exit was closed due to construction & took me well out of the way & added several minutes to my trip. Waze saved me time because the exit was in fact open! I love that you can pre-set a destination & time so it notifies you when to leave. Connecting to music apps saves you from app switching while driving.

Shame only 1 star is the lowest.    A while back, I started to not use Waze because it was unreliable with getting traffic information.  I'd start my daily commute and start up Waze and the maps would have absolutely no information on the traffic I was in.  Sometimes I would have to restart Android Auto to fix it.  But even then it would randomly stop updating information, like data was interrupted and waze just couldn't recover itself.  The there's the random resetting I got.  Driving along, the app would blank out and then come back after a few seconds, usually at the same spot in my commute.  This usually accompanies the data interuption like I described before.  Now, Waze is 100% useless to me because it absolutely will not start in Android Auto anymore.  I've tried reinstalls, data wipes of both Waze and Android Auto, all kinds of stuff.  It just crashes immediately when trying to start.  I've moved on to Google Maps because it just works.

It gets lost when you mostly need it It makes you go on dead end roads and then tells you to make a "U turn" It takes the most rugged streets most of them even more crowded than the main road The "oops, passenger" thing it does when you want to write an adress even if you have a 0 km/h speed is very dangerous because you loose more time selecting "passenger" instead of verbally introducing the adress simple and easy. It s only good because it tells about the police and speed limit.

I don't get why the Android version of this app is any different than the ios version. I have used waze for years on Android, then ios, and now I'm back on Android. For some strange reason the Android version of this app doesn't pause your music to announce directions like it does on ios. That's so foolish. Just make the app have that feature. If it's possible on one operating system, then it can be done on the other. Not cool, Waze. Not cool.

I love this app because its live and get smart updates. I would like the if they could please add a compass on the face of the map somewhere to give us the proper direction of what direction we are currently heading in. This is the only flaw I see with this GPS. Thank you. Please fix this. A compass on the face of the map somewhere. Thanks.

Great app idea, however the functionality just isn't there. I find myself constantly fighting with this app, it CONSISTENTLY force closes regularly!! I drove from Denver to Seattle using Waze and it crashed 16 times on the way!!! The only way to get the app to open again is to go into settings and force close it, or restart the phone completely. Is that efficient when you're going 80mph down the interstate? Or safe? This app is just riddled with bugs, and needs a LOT of work!

I really don't know what's going on with Waze lately the past month it is been loading Maps extremely slow, it's was not letting me report for the entire month if there was an accident a stranded vehicle or police on the road nothing at all! And now when I load directions it just takes forever and I have to open Google Maps to get where I need to go! And tonight it sent me to the wrong location and said I have reached my destination and I put in the correct address and it sent me two blocks away

I used to like using Waze and actually drove from NY to FL without any problems. Lately I find that while using Waze to get to a location, Waze will indicate that I have arrived at my destination but I am actually in the middle of a major roadway or out on the street. It does not actually take me to my destination. This is extremely frustrating and I find myself driving in circles to get to my destination. Can this issue be fixed!!!
replyContent: Hi Ethel, thank you for contacting us. We'd like to look into this routing issue for you. To do so, please report this issue by using the following steps: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I downloaded and started using this because I heard it was good at figuring out the fastest route, and the design is cute too. It's total garbage though. Several times I've put in my route and it takes me to a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT destination. Just now I selected a particular location, and I guess it completely ignored my selection because it took me towards work instead. I've been late to stuff because of this. It also has distracting ads. I'm uninstalling & going back to plain ol google maps.

downloaded this app as everyone said its better than google maps. initially I enjoyed it then got to realise it's very slow and doesnt navigate as fast as google maps which leads you to take the wrong exit or road. Also it does not update road closures and therefore takes you to them and then you have to figure out what to do next. Google maps shows Road closures and doesnt take you to them and gives you another route. I have now decided to uninstall Waze and go back to using Google maps.

this apps starts to get into my nerve. before it is very reliable, now often waiting for server or could not connect to the server. i though my old phone got the problem, so i installed it to another phone, problem continues. so apparently not my old phone fault, plus i uses 3 providers GSM Internet service, please don't tell me they are the problem. oh btw, i drive MPV/van like car, not motorcycle. please do not direct me to street that is less than 4 meter wide with 2 directions. fix it
Good app but....need to be able to add multiple stops on a trip. Would be much more useful then I'd give 5 stars

Love, love, love this app! Only wish it gave back street routes more often in heavy traffic hours. But no real complaints here! It really helps me because I'm always running late, so it lets me know when I must leave and what my expected arrival time is, as each minute goes by. I recommend it to everyone I know. Thanks Waze!!

Like: Display, friends can view drive. Hate: Waze hit road closures (checked Google Maps and they show the closures and avoid). Annoying beep everytime you go off route and it replans, you cant switch the sound off without removing all other sounds. Google Maps shows on screen the time difference of all other roads during your journey should you wish to change routes. I've been delayed many times as a result of Waze. Google Maps shows road colours based on congestion.

The idea of Waze is great. What isn't great, however, is that fact that the app keeps turning on and running despite me force closing it to save battery. This is ridiculous. Apps should run when the user wants them to, not when the apps want to. I'm uninstalling it, despite how helpful it could be.

OK app. Great idea to combine live driver input to help others. Had previously installed and hated, then uninstalled. Gave it a fresh try while delivering Postmates. Current version is pretty good with 2 exceptions: 1. Graphics do not render at correct speed, or scale so I miss a lot of turns which sucks in Austin Texas where you really need the real time info. 2. The app talks way way way too much. My stero is constantly being interrupted so this app can repeat things 500 times.

I love Waze. Use it all the time; it has features I think are super convenient, but what's the point of GPS that cant connect, even with a 4G unlimited plan??? Connectivity issues are ABUNDANT, routes are long and often over complicated, and even if u take off difficult roads it still sends you to red light cameras, rather than avoiding them??? Recently I've began using Google Maps. I hate it, what choice do i have? Many reviews have the same complaints- yet I see no difference in functionality.

GPS issues when connected via usb to android auto. Works fine without usb. Changed usb still glitchy. Arrow turns to a dot or arrow changes direction. Contacted and sent in bug report and still no answer to fix the issue. Tech support Tells me to "have a clear view of the sky". Used to work excellent, now it's a waste of time. I'll go back to google.

WAZE is Good in terms of GPS Navigations compare to others. It will more better if it can lead driver to a Direct Pick Up or Drop off points directly. Some of the places in Singapore Navigations still have an issue to leads us directly...sometime it leads us to side or back of the building...such building like Hospital and Shopping Centre. Inside Tunnel, the connections still poor. It will be better if WAZE can have Auto Tunnel mode means when Driver drive into Tunnel, the Navigations works.

content: Used to be the best gps system. Google bought it and ruined it completely. In the past few weeks it often tried to take me on 30km/h roads for 20+ km instead of taking the highway next to. content: This app works well in the standard mode, however in the Android auto mode it's different and worse. The experience in the AA mode is constantly changing, there is no graphic lane guidance, no avg speed camera progress bar and last but not least you or the passengers can not interact with this stupidity when the car moves. content: Quite the cute app, sometimes it goes nuts with the maps ‚òª like, the road is closed, but it insists that I should go that way ü§£ other than that, it's pretty cute .. hope there was an option to tell us when we go over the speed limit, more route options and less wrong roads ... like, if there was an option to manually update the road to: closed/ reopened/ not working .. and change the path so that other users won't have to go through that same wrong path again and again and again .... thank you
I really like this app, but currently, the 'real time updates' do not update. More 'updates' are added, but historical ones are not removed

content: My go-to directional app. I love that it gives you traffic updates in real time and usually picks the fastest route to my destination. Just wish it would show arrival times based on speed limit as not everyone goes the speed of traffic (if it's going over the speed limit). Also would like to see lane suggestions; as in which lane you should be in for the next upcoming turn. It currently tells you that info if the next turn is IMMEDIATE, but not if the next turn is close and you have to move over quite quickly, so it would be nice to know which turn lane to be in. Kind of like what Google maps does.

Excellent to stay out of traffic. Works well to give you alternative routes. My only complaint is the reminder to leave: 1.) It doesn't always remind. Actually it rarely works. 2.) You can only set it in 15 minute increments. If i need to be somewhere at 2:40, the only options are 2:30 or 2:45.

I used to like Waze, but I don't know why it's error like "No network connection", the navigation is very very slow, and when i'm driving the navigation doesn't move at all! It's ridiculous how waze try to find my way back to home but its just sending me to somewhere and its starting "no network connection" that the navigation doesn't work at all!

Good: Alternate routing to avoid heavy traffic. Bad: Voice recognition tool needs major work. When I tap microphone icon, I should NOT see 'Updating Voice Commands, Try again a moment' nine out of ten times. For an app that we mostly use WHILE DRIVING, this is completely unacceptable. Ugly: The 'Updating Voice Commands, Try again in a moment' message is completely unacceptable. 3/5 stars: Get your voice recognition functionality together, Waze.

I tried to sign in with my phone number. The only thing app said it found me but an error pops up saying unable to verify account. Facebook sign in also has a similar issue. UPDATE: It did not give an option to change the password only to create a new account. I clicked back on the verify error message, the app froze for a second and then signed into my account. So at least I have access once more.

content: Decent but slow updates, it informed me of an accident but didn't change the route... after I passed exits it updated and said 30 minute wait but same route since I had already passed exits
