content: At some point in the last month or so, Waze has stopped looking at my calendar to let me know when I should leave for appointments. I tried disconnecting and reconnecting my calendars; it worked once after that then again quit alerting me. Please fix ASAP. (orig post 12/2018. now 3/2019 & still having this issue.)

Hey Guys the app sucks, Maybe its a good app as far as North America is concerned, but the maps of my city are at least 6 months old.The route being shown is over bridges that have since collapsed and routes which I take does not show a road where one does exist. The app has lot of potential, but then it has to be relevant for it to be effective.Do inform me when u guys put your act together, would love to be part of the team.
Some times it acts up but its good in general

This app broke when I connected it to Android Auto. Was working great not hooked up. Cookie Monster hungry. Then...I hooked it up to AA and it completely feel apart. Says no signal, can't find a destination, freezes. Now even when not hooked up same thing happens. Unusable now. Too bad because I really liked it.

Waze was horrible this past weekend. Took me out of the way, didn't update my drive, stopped in the middle of my drive during a phone call on my Bluetooth, and did not match up to my speed limit in my car! Seriously fix it or not just me,but several of my family and friends are uninstalling this app!

This app worked well for years, however after upgrading my phone I hit issues. Waze recognised my number as being linked to an existing account, but when I put my account details in, it just stated there was an error fetching my account and I would have to create a new one. I got in touch with waze who couldn't have been less helpful. Has anyone else encountered the same issue? I feel like they're not telling me something.
replyContent: Hi Dan, we're happy to help you log back into your account. You can log in using a username and password or an email address. Here's how: support.google.com/waze/answer/9757024?hl=en If you're still experiencing an issue, please send us a private message on Facebook. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze thought the entrance to a highly trafficked Men's Fashion store was behind the store, where the loading dock was. Waze never knows what direction you're facing (even when your phone is on your windshield facing the street), so heading in the right direction, leaving any driveway OR parking lot is near impossible UNLESS you know the area already.
replyContent: Hi Cedric, thanks for your feedback. We can look into this navigation issue you‚Äôre experiencing. To do so, please follow these steps to report this routing problem: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The features themselves are amazing. But the app needs a bit of work. Because it crashes in the middle of driving. If your driving long distances with someone not a problem. But alone big problem you can end up an alert on the side of the road. Please fix so I can give it 5 stars

I like this app, but it has problems on Android. I have glitches pretty often, and it is very frustrating where it freezes or will not load. I use Google Maps instead of Waze most of the time because of this. Also, I LOVE the new carpool features, and it has helped me save some money, but I HATE that it really seems to have bad algorithms for the scheduling. If i change my pickup location or time even SLIGHTLY, suggested riders disapper. I know i could have more riders, but bet I can't see them.

just started using couple days ago, not bad i must say, but there can be lots of improvements/updates, like we should be able to use the app while doing something else, like in picture mode, we should still be able to get directions while not in the app, maybe i didn't explain this in the best way but i hope y'all understand and work on this! thanks.

App works great when it works, but every single time I get a telephone call when the app is open, it causes the app to freeze and crash hard when the phone call is ended.  Occasionally it even locks up the phone, requiring a restart.  This is on a Galaxy S7Edge.

Heard good things, but experience has been poor so far. Slow searches, occasional crashes and fails to search when Google maps has no trouble at all, particularly using voice. That's the problem, Google maps is so easy that any competition has to be as good or better. Basic searching for addresses and route planning are unreliable and slow. You'll need to know where the cameras are because you've just wasted 10 minutes on your driveway! (I do not condone speeding even if waze made you late!)

Used to be OK, but the language reverts to wherever location you are at. For example, I'm currently in Israel, but when I type an address, everything is shown in Hebrew instead of the language set on the phone. It will be nice to have a feature to download maps for offline use.

It's a great app. I'm giving it five stars on the sole condition that you NOT GET RID OF THE COOKIE MONSTER VOICE!! PLEASE!! It's really is a great way to road trip and navigate in general especially because you can report traffic accidents and hazards etc., but having my homeboy Cookie Monster give me turn by turn directions really did improve my driving experience. I'm not being sarcastic in the least either. The only thing I struggle with is inputting multiple stops. Keep Cookie Monster plz!
Great navigation! Some of the apps internal navigation & search options are not intuitive and challenging to work through.

This app literally will not work. I've installed and uninstalled then reinstalled it several times and it will not connect to the network. No maps. No addresses. No nothing. Maybe there is an update I need? I remember ditching this a couple years ago for connectivity issues and apparently they haven't been solved
replyContent: Hi there, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Fine in a car useless on a motorbike. Crashes constantly without notice, so if you're driving the motorways in Europe and you're on a motorbike listening through headphones then you can miss your turning by several hundred miles without knowing when it crashes. If you're on a 400 mile long road without any junctions, you won't get any notifications til you're exiting. If it's crashed you just keep going. Was trying to get to Spain. Ended up in Germany. Only noticed when the car plates said DE.

Was a great app, until they change your voice command if u have cookie monster. Also it says u can use sesame street characters and now it's only at times that u can use that function. Also the ads, ugh always block your map. Not as good as it was. I still use it. It should show your location like Google maps live pictured.

Loaded app and tested by giving it a address I have been driving to for 6 plus years daily. It starts out showing me "best route" 18 miles 27 minutes, Starts by sending me 2 to 3 miles in wrong direction - thats a time saver for sure. My personal route time is 18 minutes daily. If I cannot trust it on a route I know well sure not going to trust it on a route im not sure of. App uninstalled waste of my time.

Honestly made me late more often than not. Routes have had me make 3 lefts instead of a legal u-turn, app often directs me on a longer route for some reason. Think you need to make a left on first and in the left lane? Make a u-turn, make another u-uturn, Make a right, go down two blocks, then make a u turn. There's your left on first. The report features are amazing but God save the actual Navigation. "Longer routes" usually aren't longer and shorter mileage. Take roads less traveled.

There's something wrong with this app and Android auto. It does not even show up on the screen of my car at all when I connect the phone to the car via android auto. Only google maps is available for me on AA. It seems to be a general problem with Waze and AA. I certainly hope they fix it soon, I miss the speed limit alerts the app provides. Common Waze, get your stuff together!
replyContent: We're sorry about your issue, Jeezy. Our team is handling it right now and it should be solved soon. Please feel free to send us a private message on Facebook if you have any questions. Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Overall very good, with a couple of infuriating issues. Can't handle scheduled A-B-C trips, despite the menu structure pretending it can (it just ignores the B-C part of the trip). The 'report an issue' form is nonsense: asks for a username and instructs how to find it, despite there being no username there, and I cannot submit the bug report because it says my email address is not valid. Makes the whole thing feel a bit amateurish.

I have used Waze for years, but updated yesterday and was pretty distracted on my morning commute. The app notified me as I passed every highway exit that I should continue travelling straight, which was incredibly distracting. Why would I need to be updated NOT to take an exit, when mine is 20 miles away? Otherwise, it's great and gets me where I need to be!
replyContent: Hi Aimee, thank you for your feedback. It sounds like you could be describing the lane guidance feature. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We appreciate your review. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Loved the app until it stopped working on Android Auto one day during a drive. Now it fails to show the map. Works fine on the phone. Google maps works fine on Android Auto. Tried all suggestions. Reinstalled etc. No map shows in the car. Phone is Nokia 7.1, with Android 10, car has Ford Sync 3. I've now given up on this.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Mikko. We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue with Android Auto. We'd like to investigate this a bit further, would you mind submitting more information here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: On the very first attempt to use it in the city I kept getting a "no GPS coverage, make sure you're outside" message. This was happening with all permissions allowed and while moving down the interstate. Only one time throughout the entire trip did it ever show me even close to my actual location. Most times it wasn't even in the same area. Not worth keeping just for traffic notifications and events since navigation is nearly impossible without GPS coverage.

App worked great for over a year. Then... I mapped my AM trip, it shows 51min and some weird route. There's no traffic so I ignore and risk it. Made my own route. The entire way it keeps re-calculating. With each defiant move I make, it shaves off a few minutes. I arrived in 36min. Second time it's happened so I'm never using it again. If this is a glitch in the system, a known issue, or a setting I need to fix please inform me so I can change this review back to a 5-star.

Love this app, will always recommend over Google maps üëå, only gripe is that you can only have 2 stop for the route, with the ability to have more than 1 extra stop, more professional driving jobs(UPS, DHL, DPD etc, as I work for UPS) would utilise this app into there daily delivery routes thus adding more live traffic data and reports. Will add 5th star üåü when this feature becomes available.

I usually love Waze. It's a nice community. People report when there are accidents, traffic, or hidden police! It will also reroute you if there's a blockage, which is super nice. It got 4 stars for the annoying safety messages it puts out. During the shut down, I couldn't open the app without it asking me if I really needed to drive. Yes, I need to go to work. Also when it tells me not to type and drive, I get super annoyed. I use Waze when I need help. Sometimes I can't pull over.

I absolutely love this app..such a cool idea to make a GPS app with a social media vibe to it. Love all the options that come with it, like how you can report anything and everything that other drivers would want to be and should be aware of ahead of time. Also while letting people report minor things as well. I could go on but I think you get it lol. Good job waze team I know I'll be sticking with you guys!

When I'm out of town using this app numerous times it has told me to exit the highway go like anywhere between 3-7 miles then make a uturn then get right back on. There was no accident or anything that was on the roadway for that to happen. Once it even had me exit way before an accident do the uturn and I listened because there was an accident but it led me right to the entrance where it was closed due to the accident.
replyContent:
Hi! thanks you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about this issue you're experiencing, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I use it because It is the only app available that tells you where the radars are, that's about it. As for the rest it is bad: crashes while your are driving, cannot connect to server/internet although other apps are using internet, the "uh sorry" message comes around way too often when looking for addresses shared in other apps, very very slow at suggesting new routes when you miss a turn. And no, my phone is new and has lots of memory, that's not the problem.

Great app and, when it works properly it tends to be better than Google Maps. However it occasionally glitches with searching for locations and with finding a GPS fix. It also relies more on user updates reporting on slow traffic rather than taking feeds from GPS data. Whilst Google maps may be reporting slow traffic, if you've got Waze and are first to a traffic jam you won't know it's there. So Google Maps tends to have a better idea of traffic data, but Waze is better with time in traffic.

"Sorry, despite all our efforts we are unable to verify your account. It must be lost somewhere in the stratosphere." Every time I try to login, I get this message after inputting the verification code. My number hasn't changed in 20 years, the email and account name are the same. I really like the way the app works, HOWEVER since I've had this account for a couple of years it is baffling that it will not log me in. Can this be fixed (and don't tell me to uninstall and reinstall)?

Safetly arrive always! Easy, useful app to get to your destination always. One thing It would be nice to have changed is for the fastest, easiest route to be suggested first. I find if I set my destination too 'home' it brings me one route an when I make my destination 'subway' (which is 2min away from home.) it brings me a different route. I think maybe it is this way because 'subway' is located on a main st. When you get off the highway and 'home' is located on a side st. Still love tho!!

Initially I was rather happy using Waze, although I had read that when crossing a border, it would stop giving directions. That is indeed annoying, as when your phone loses connection to the internet, the same happens and nothing will be mentioned any more. It is an interesting app, but not for me.

This app was great until you need to go to the JFK airport. Everytime I search for JFK airport it says server time out. Even when I tried to put in my destination from the airport it also timed out on me. This has happened to me for 4 days now. My brother in law also tried putting in the JFK airport on his iPhone and he was getting the same server time out message as I did.

Ride share screen makes this formerly great app a "poor" app. The develops left no opt-out for the new rideshare screen which will pop up at the most inconvenient traffic moments. I used to love this app. As soon as they fix this, I'll love it again. In the mean time, I'll use Google Maps.

I've been using this app for years, planned drives & all, even for interstate traveling without issues. Lately the planned route feature will not load with traffic or at all. 2 months ago, it worked. Now it doesn't. Fix the issue & it'll go back to a 5 star rating. Issue is valid on S6, Note 5, Note 8, Tab E & Tab S4

I like the way to get to report construction, but I dont like how it is implemented. you have to have directions that take you through the construction zone tp report it. why can't I do it after arriving at the destination, or that night after work? also put a time option in the forum because there is a street here there are signs that say it is going to be under construction until September but every day waze tries to send me down the road.
replyContent: Hey there! We very much appreciate your feedback. Please feel free to message us on Facebook and share more about you app experience. If you have any ideas or suggestions, you can also submit them into our suggestion box and our team will review them: tinyurl.com/jo3484d Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: waze is a good app , helps with finding quick routes and traffic jams. Waze is good with letting driver report accidents, road closers and police location with in you driving commute. The only thing about Waze is that it drains you battery fast when not in use. this is one problem that need to get fixed. other then that great driving app.

Waze was my go to app for navigation, i commute on a motorcycle, and when i need to go somewhere new its critical to have the navigation not stop working, bc its impossible to look at your phone, while riding a motorcycle thru millions of people who are looking at their phones. Waze constantly stops working. Im back to google maps, which sucks. My navigation choices in 2020 are like the presidential election choices. One is so bad, the bar set so low that anything else is going to be better.
replyContent: Hi Mr Pistol, we're happy to help. Try reinstalling the app and make sure that you're using the latest app version. Please add an email address to your account before reinstalling (Menu > Settings > Account & Login > email). If the issue continues, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can further investigate: https://m.me/waze

content: It's a solid maps app, but no where near Google maps. Why I won't continue to use this is that it doesn't give you the option to choose a different route, just one route. Also, when you enter an address you go through 2 other screens after that before you can start heading to the destination. It pops up with 10 other addresses which confused you and you may accidentally click the wrong one if you don't pay attention. That's time-consuming and doesn't allow you to get straight to the point.
replyContent:
Hi Joseph, we appreciate your feedback and would love to hear more! Please feel free to send us a Facebook private message and tell us about your app experience. Thanks! 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app is a joke! All it does is pop up ads while you are trying to drive! Very dangerous, I am expecting someone to file a class action suit against them when people start crashing because of this horrible app! I tried to uncheck all of the notices but it just defaults back to all checked. The routes take Longer than Google Maps and seams to take me into heavy traffic instead of fastest routes.

This app is terrible. After following all the instructions, creating an account, saving favorites, and adjusting all the settings the app promptly forgot all the changes I made. It also deleted all the favorites I entered, my home and work address and all other settings I changed. I tried uninstalling and re-doing all my changes and entry only to have the same thing happen again.

This app is all about drivers helping each other, and it works great. Really helps in long hauls. One problem is the warnings are far too short. 0.5 miles is nothing when driving on the interstate. If you can change the distance you're warned, I haven't found out how, if it isn't a feature, it needs to be. I would much prefer 1 mile warnings. Still the best travel app.

I love, love, love this app! First and formost it runs in real time so you can rest assured it will take you the fastes route. At least that has been the case with me. I run it even for everyday, I know like the back of my hand, routes. It had me get off the freeway two offramps before I typically do. I hesitated for abour 5 seconds then took it. I was zig-zaging around thinking what had I gotten myself into when all of a sudden the frreway reappeared. It was backuped all that way! Amazing!

Love this app it's very helpful! I didn't even know that it existed but I am very thankful for it. I think every one should download it because it's very helpful when it comes to driving local and while traveling to any destination near you and when you're out of town in another city. I don't know what I would do without it. It shows me how traffic looks weather I'm home ate out of state, from disabled vehicles to police üöî hiding or road blocks and check points. This app reveals everything.

Used once on a known route. Checked and double checked my destinations address. The app said I was 2 miles from my actual starting point and I could never get it to correct. Halfway to my destination the display showed my location satisfactory though the little animated car was moving sideways. Within about 1/4 of a mile of my destination, which was straight ahead, the app was trying to send me in the opposite direction. Shortly after I arrived, the app began to ask if I was stuck in traffic.

The app will randomly close if I turn off my screen, not all ways but enough for it to be a problem. Aside from that it's great, it's routes are better than Google maps (at least this is true a while ago) because Waze will give directions based on traffic on the 401 collectors and express where Google maps will go with a longer route because it has fewer changes

App is yet to be super refined. Animations are okay but seem sluggish at times. I have a constant message on overhead saying "waze preparing navigation voice 0%", when when I have a active internet connection and have the app on for 2 hours. Traffic features are very useful but google maps is copying everything from Waze and unfortunately seems to do just as well if not better. Have loved waze for a long time and the community that uses wze are way more actuive on actually posting road updates, so it is sad to see people leave waze to Maps. Waze also needs a dedicated android auto Interface as the current one is somewhat lackluster and hard to use espeicall the side hamburger menus for favourite and planned drives. Overall, useable, if you like waze. If you just want a map with no hassle, Google maps seems to be in the lead this year.

At first we loved this app. Its the only navigation app I would like to use with a young child in the back seat during long trips, it really helped having the different voices to choose from. Would be nice if there was a way to get some better voices for android based phones. My daughter loved cookie monster but sadly hes gone. And now there are no good voices at all just plain ole ROBOTS TALKING. Would definitely be 5 stars if it wasnt for this downfall.

I don't know what changes were made to the app in recent months, but Waze has turned into a major data hog. Both my wife and I are consistently going over our monthly carrier allotment, and when I looked to find the culprit, it is Waze by a huge margin. This never happened before July/August 2019. So far, in the first 10 days of September, Waze has used a total of 547 MB on my phone! The app in second place for data usage is my mobile browser, with 190 MB. Just out of curiosity, I drove half the day today using Waze and half using Google Maps. JUST TODAY, Waze used 117 MB, while Google Maps only used 13 MB. (There is no logical explanation for this. Doesn't Google own Waze anyway?) I love Waze in so many "ways" but I simply cannot afford it anymore. I have done everything I could find to fix the problem - un-installed and re-installed Waze, turned off Waze's background data usage, tried starting my trips while on Wi-Fi when possible. Nothing works. I have a Samsung S7 and my wife has a new Pixel 3a, both running the latest version of Android.

Downgraded my rating. When Android auto is running on my Ford sync3 interface, the app will not open on the phone. Destination setting does not appear to be possible from the waze app displayed on Android auto. i have to unplug the phone, close waze, reopen and then set the destination. Once set i can plug it back in and Waze is then available with the destination on Android auto. the app still locks up and looses the destination settings it had which requires the destination to be reinput.

It worked well but it's about almost a year now that it says that there's no gps and can't show exact location. Thing is that for sure is not my phone since it works with other apps that require GPS. I also sent and email for assistance months ago but nothing; no sign from them. Too bad; I used to love it but now it's suddenly useless for no apparent reason. ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

This used to be one of my favourite apps with Android Auto but in the last 2 months it has been unusable almost all of the time. It won't find a route & keeps spinning away. On the few occasions that it has it has frozen on the map mid route. It's now totally worthless & I've had to start using the infinitely duller but more reliable Google Maps. Great shame.

navigation feature is okay. I already use Google maps and what i really wanted this app to do is give me alerts of hazards along my daily commute. I encountered numerous unreported hazards such as stopped vehicles, road construction, etc. The hazards that were reported either didn't exist for me or were stupid, like pothole ahead. I live in PA, there are potholes everywhere and those reported were not even bad ones. I realize this is dependent on other users so not directly a fault of the app.

Annoying. Get rid of this stupid railroad crossing alert. I've dealt with railroad crossings for 20 years and don't need an annoying sound to play. It's unsafe to try and distract my attention by playing annoying sounds while I drive. Why did you add this? There is no settings menu. There is nothing to change or disable. I hate everything about the UI of this program. Yet another company thinking "less is more" and taking the ability to customize the experience away from the user.
replyContent:
Hi Dan, thank you for the review. We understand your concerns. You can turn off alerts by tapping Search > Settings > Alerts & Reports > Reports > select report type > turn off the 'Alert me while driving' option. 
For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: As much as I am upset with it, I would like to come up with a fair review: 1. The app is fun. It makes driving become more fun. I love the batman narrator. 2. Sadly this app is poor in navigation. The estimated arrival time is inaccurate 90% of the time. 3. The most problematic part is I can't read the route with ease compare to Google Maps. For countless time, I drove to the wrong route which end up late arrival. Come on Google, you can rectify this. Please impose the practicality from Google Maps to Waze. 5 stars for the fun user interface.1 stars for the practicality. My two cents.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for for your feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We also want to help with this ETA issue. To best assist you, please follow these steps report this ETA issue: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is trash. Look, it's fine, but use Google maps instead. Waze doesn't let you turn off restaurants/POIs on the main map view. Google has transit and driving directions all in one app. Google has better info about traffic jams. (this one instance, Waze said there was a traffic jam along my usual route and gave me a wide detour... Google told me to go the usual way, saved me ~10 mins). Waze doesn't have offline maps. Waze crashes Android Auto (RAM over use), Google maps doesn't.

google maps who?! Waze is here and here for good. Great app, user friendly, make your own voice your main navigation voice and the best feature of all....................(The Cop Spotter > Very accurate and alerts you with plenty of time to tap ya brakes and get back down to the speed limit)!!! No reason you should be stopped now....... Lol Suckas

Don't know what happened lately with the app but I just return from my vacation and the instructions were awful: not being able to connect to the internet even if the internet was working, a continuous loading state when eventualy was recognizing the internet connection, constant crash and a have 100% steps to reproduce it. One thing to mention here is that on the same route last year worked amazing. And I'm really disappointed to see that it was not working now.

This is the best sat nav you would ever want. The picture and direction on you incar link system screen through either apple play or Android Auto are really crystal clear view. The sign, marking and information is brilliant as are the alerts of what is happening around you. Finding a address is a piece of cake it such a simple system to use. This is one of the best apps on the market and it really does get you from a to b with no problem. FANTASTIC! ‚ò∫

This app used to be the best. Ready to try something else. Seems like they don't update the app and i get alot of "timed out" errors. Also, the alerts like red cameras and speed cameras are not accurate or updated anymore. Used to work great, not anymore.

have tried this app a few times and find that it keeps searching for signal when Google maps works fine at the same time. Also the app keeps crashing when using it. I have gone back to Google maps as never had a problem with it. the idea that they have is good alerting other driver about things ahead but that's all.

Great, when it actually works. Unfortunately, it doesn't do that very often anymore. I constantly lose GPS signal. I used to *love* the features it brought to the table, but - as a delivery driver - I simply cannot trust it anymore. Even just having it open in the background kills GPS tracking for *other apps*. I have to restart my phone to get other navigation apps working. --- Also, I wish I could disable the carpool-stuff, but that is *far and away* secondary to the gps issues.

Terrible, literally never works. Times out everytime I type in an address and hit go. The best time to leave function has never once worked and if I get the GPS to actually function closes out half way through my trip. Used to love this app but it's literally hot garbage and can't even keep up with it's most basic functions. Boooooooooooooooooo

I love this app and the new updates a lot. If I may suggest one update for the developers... When the app is in the nighttime mode and the little screen pops up to ask me if there's an accident still there, it's extremely bright as compared to the nighttime mode. If you could make that as dark as the rest of the screen on your next update that would be most helpful.Either that or send me some sunblock SPF 50 for my eyes. Thank you and keep up the good work.

This app is excellent, superior to Google Maps in every way. For one, it actually works and does not crash 30 consecutive times as soon as you tell it to begin navigation. No, this magnificent program helps you to your destination using smart technology developed by intelligent people who should overthrow Google and burn that sleazy empire to the ground. Waze is even so kind as to tell you about objects in the road that you may want to dodge. There are many nice features here.

Crashes during just regular driving for no reason. It restarts then crashes again. Rinse and repeat. It happened 3 times in a row before i just unplugged my cable. This was my first time using it and I only installed it because I read an article about its update and stability. Not to stable if you ask me. Ill continue to check it out and give it a far chance but you only get 1 first impression.
replyContent: Hi Rob, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more about this crashing issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. To best assist, please fill out our support form: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9557145?hl=en Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've used this for years on several different android phones. Ok for short trips but always crashes after an hour or so on longer trips. Even worse is that the screen freezes - so you're often unaware that it isn't working and I have missed a turn! No such problem with google maps and Waze seems more stable on iPhones.

I've been using this app for over a year now and I only wish I'd downloaded it sooner. It blows my stand alone satnav into the weeds in every respect. The graphics are very clear and the live alerts are a god send, informing you of things that a stand alone system just wouldn't register. One example is object in road, alerted in good time I was able to make a safe and timely manoeuvre instead of having to take evasive action. Height restrictions in car parks is all that's missing.

Inaccurate and gets stuck when losing connection while in a tunnel. Other navigation system at least try to follow the route to keep you on track. Also the routes chosen are not ideal ones. Needs to learn better and shorter routes. Pity, as the rest of the app is really good.

This app consistently underestimates the amount of time it takes to get through the toll booth at the SF Bay Bridge by ~ten minutes. I was ok with it being off a few times, but after using this for ETA over the course of a few weeks, I'm disappointed. I look at the ETA and *know* that I have to add time. The app should know this better than I do, otherwise what's the point of the app.

So much lagging. Always shutting down. FINALLY, waze add an option for additional riders after the 1st ride is confirmed but "No riders on your route" always pop up. I honestly dont see what the point is Waze Been struggling with this app and its bugs for 2 years now commuting as a driver mostly, and sometimes as a rider. But still better than the other carpool apps once u get lucky enough to connect w a couple of people and have them as regulars

Its Android Auto integration has been broken since the november 2019 update, to the point where its totally unusable unless you have it running in standalone mode (on just your phone). Not only is it always searching for a gps signal it hangs up on callers when you try to answer an incoming call. Everything worked flawlessly prior, now I've had no choice but to go back to google maps which gets me where i need to go and my handsfree for incoming calls is working again thru regular bluetooth.

Has potential but has let me down too many times. The alternate routes avoid a little traffic but never beats the routes I make for myself. The huge problem waze has is that it keeps shutting down without notice when you start your route and lock your phone. The biggest thing for any motorcyclist is that they cannot touch their phone as soon as they start driving. So many times Ive started riding and waze just stops. The amount of times Ive gotten lost because of this is why I give 1 star.

Was working great for a couple of months. All of a sudden seems like after midnight, it starts giving me issues. Losing navigation mostly. A couple of times I had to uninstall and then reinstall it works for a few days, then I would have the same problem. Now I can't even download it. Tried about a dozen times from different Wi-Fi and my unlimited Verizon postpaid plan. So I know it's not the data overuse. Something is recently gone wrong with this app.
replyContent: Hi Bob, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Not the best apps...i prefer to google maps

It shows the worst direction ever available in the world. In the highways when there are direct smooth and fast ways it leads me to drive to somewhere where it was farmland full of cows and goats and slowest my driving more than 2hours. At first I thought that there should be something wrong with the highway, but after 2h driving it directed me to back to the highway, right before the exit it told me to go out. It would be better if it shows different routs and we can choose among them.

Usually good but sometimes it will send you off an interstate instead of simply using an interchange. Frustrating when you don't know the area, just weird when you do. Also, in more rush hour (or others), I don't really want to cut through a neighborhood and then making a left without a light--oh hell no!
replyContent: Hi Tamara, thanks for the feedback! We always try to find the best routes. If that wasn't the case for you, please send us a private message on Facebook with the route details and we'd be happy to look into it. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: UPDATE: Newest updates seem to have fixed the bugs. It is working well again. Old comments: Recent update broke Android Auto functionality. Calculates a route, but does not display it nor keep up with location of my car. Also does not provide user reports of road conditions, police, etc. Often crashes midway through long drives and claims to be searching for a network when it is available. When it works, it works great. Only wish it worked more often.
Amazing 10/10 I can see accidents before hand and not get stuck hours in traffic and put imput as well. Everyone who drives should use this app.

Used to love this when i lived in a large city. Moved to a <500,000 people town and it doesn't just not save me time, but makes me waste longer than a "vanilla" route by going in these searches for El Dorado through back roads. Handful times I've tried to use it I got a decent 40-45 minute estimate for the "main" route, and a Waze alternative saying it would take 35. That Waze alternative invariably took 50+ minutes.

I used to use this as my main navigation app when taking long trips. Last time I tried it couldn't find places to add to the route, or figure out how to get to certain spots. And just recently, I've started to get pointless notifications every day. Opening nthe app to try and turn them off showed the notification part of settings completely blank.
replyContent: Hi Cliff, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: In theory this is a good app, but the integration with Android Auto is terrible, it keeps freezing as if my GPS isn't working yet Google maps works fine, my phone is plenty powerful, fix the Android Auto navigation and I might actually consider using the app, other than that it has plenty of features and a friendly UI but because of the Android Auto it's unusable for me, if you're using it natively on your phone then I'd recommend.

Horrible routing! Unnecessary loops and turns to get to position driver to main route. It is happening more than ever. Waze just sent us for a long local out of the way route when the cleared highway way near by. Wasted 30+ minutes of my Sunday drive with a newborn. Don't use this app if you don't know where you're going. It often can't find my location either. Which makes this app useless. This app used to be useful, now it's trash!!

Used to be a great app. Server now "times out" trying to find a route. Google maps had no issue finding route at same instance. Really no reason to use any longer except for warnings, but if you can't get a "route", it really doesn't matter.

Been using Waze for years and it's been great but something has changed recently that makes it almost unusable. It's still ok if there is no traffic, but As long as there is traffic at all it doesn't know what to do anymore. It somehow keeps finding the absolutely slowest and worst routes.

Waze has been unusable w/ Android Auto. Keeps freezing, glitching, going dark & reloading Waze, shows wrong GPS location, wrong direction of N-E-S-W, "center" button not working, speedometer/zoom not working either. Other GPS apps still seem to work except for minor glitching on Google Maps on AA. Reverting to previous Waze version is better but still reloads. Seems to be related to AA. Reverted to previous AA version & now seems to be working great again on my 2016 Escape. Reposting to AA revie

The app features are excellent but It always tends to use a zigzag route. This cases delay caused by unnecessary turns to go from point A to point B. Another problem if the GPS enabled after opening the app It will never be recognized unless we close and reopen the app. Update . Im glad that the GPS activation issue is solved "Great Job Developers" Still the number of turns is not taken into account when calculating the best route leading to delays and making the trip more complicated
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback, Mohamed. We'd be happy to look into these issues further. Please send us a private message on Facebook with more details. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Unusable as of 2 months ago with android auto. I have written for support but gotten minimal response. This morning it marked me in the wrong side of a river traveling in the wrong direction in rush hour traffic. This is just plain DANGEROUS. Since Waze is owned by Google, who also owns Map's AND Android Auto, I have to wonder what is actually going on here since Maps does not have the same issues. Are they trying to consolidate? Why doesn't Maps offer the same functions as Waze? No response?
replyContent: Hi Sherman, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Works alright once it really works. Running the latest version of Waze on Sony XPERIA XZ1 with android 9 and conatabtly having issue with navigation. - Living in Latvia and the language is being conctantly changed to Russiam (–ú–∞–ø—É—Å—è) - what is that about if there is clearly a Latvian version or staying with user defined would be a good solution. - After few of the latest updates Waze is just not performing and cannot establish a connection to GPS, it takes just so long to start.

I have the motorway just down the road and instead it tells me to go through a much longer road to end in a waste of time. Also, a few days ago I went to Bournemouth and on the way back home ( High Wycombe), it told me almost to go to London by wasting a lot of time for nothing. It normally works very well but sometimes, it ends to waste a lot of time
replyContent: Hi Matteo, thank you for bringing this to our attention. We'd like to investigate further, please send us a private message on Facebook with more details about the route so we can look into it. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app! I have a suggestion for improvement:  If Waze decides to re-route me due to traffic or accident, the app should tell me what's going on AND allow me to choose to maintain my current route or accept re-route. I hate when I"m going somewhere I know how, and Waze tells me out of the blue to take an unexpected exit. I never know if I should trust Waze or not. A couple times it really messed me up, costing me hours.  I'll often just turn it on without entering a destination. I still receive hazard reports but don't need directions.

Generally a good app, but the time neeed waiting for network to get the result is getting longer and longer, no matter how good or bad my network signal was at that time. Please look into issue and hope that it will not keep showing "something went wrong".

I've used this app for years but recently the lack of route options is just sad, to the point I went back to Google maps. For example, I was driving from Ohio down to South Carolina and was only given one route to follow. I've driven this many times and I75 is a trash road, so I normally take I77 which is only a 6 minute difference on the overall drive. But waze only offers the I75 route. Please fix your app and give us more route options.

Not bad. When I tried to navigate to work it kept telling me to circle the block at come back the opposite direction so I would turn left on to the street in front of my work instead of turning right. Also when reporting police you have to be standing next to then in order to report it. It's illegal to hold my phone while in a running vehicle making reporting accurate police locations impossible . It should be possible to select a location and direction of travel remotely when reporting.
replyContent:
Hi, William! Thank you for the review and feedback. To learn more how Waze works: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6078702?hl=en 

You can also report issues through our Live map. More info here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7101380?hl=en 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Using 1* rating to get developer attention. Love the app but 2 problems over past several months. Since Waze was connected to Assistant, Assistant hasn't been working properly. Perhaps some permissions need to be cleared but it's unclear. Cannot look up locally stored contacts or business numbers, making the feature useless. Cannot text at all. Assistant alone has no problems doing either so it's the interface. Second, map screen occasionally goes completely black, particularly during phone calls

Could be better. Having just bought a new car I am using waze for the first time. I have been a dedicated gps user for years. I find there are features missing. Definitely need a on screen current route option to allow you to add, delete or cancel current route. Very annoying when driving. There doesn't seem to be an exit option other than through the phone.

Buggy app. Sometimes I turn it on, it shows me I'm in another town on a different road. I let it run for few minutes to see if it will correct itself. But nope. I have to restart the app. Sometimes traffic info is incorrect and it redirects you to some other road that takes you even longer to get to your destination. One time it took me 2 hrs to get to my destination because it keeps telling to turn all over the place. It usually takes me 1 hour.

Much better than Google maps. Was sick of getting lost with Google but I've tried this Waze several times and you get a much simpler easier ride. I think some of the Uber drivers use it. Took me a much better way avoiding a lot of traffic. I like that you can set a time and location and it will alert you when to set off. Only thing is it does give you a lot of alerts while driving which seems a bit dangerous. Speed cameras, roadworks, places to eat etc. Could be distracting but you can disable.

Great app. I like it better than Google maps. This app tells you when there's cops in the area, and where they are. It also lets me know about 'Red light cameras', which is awesome. I can't keep getting those $180. tickets anymore. Plus, I listen to Spotify and it connects me to it anytime I press the Spotify tab. Im happy!!

Where is the lane guidance? I keep reading about the new android auto with the lane guidance. It's December now and there's no sign of this function to be seen. Come on, how hard can it be, you are probably the last Sat Nav app In the world, which does not have this feature. And please add more settings in android auto. It's annoying to disconnect the phone to change certain settings and then plug it in again. Thank you.
replyContent: Hi Radovan, thanks for contacting us. The lane guidance feature is available in the app. You can read more about it here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/10002827?hl=en If you're not able to see lane guidance, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can help. Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Add school zone report please !!.

Good luck running it in the background. Constantly closes itself after an hour or so and doesnt even have a "continue route" option when it is reopened. Why even have an option to run in the background if there's no option to actually allow it to do so? 3 stars is the highest I can go and that may be too generous. It doesnt even have a mini map if you try to run other apps

PLEASE get rid of the STUPID "uh oh passenger?" rubbish. It serves no purpose other than being annoying and being a FALSE indicator of your emphasis on safety. At the very least make it pop up BEFORE my passenger starts typing, not after the first 2 letters. Annoying as hell. Else 5 stars. it may seem trivial, but I am a high user of Waze, and seeing uh oh passenger 10 times a day is too much.

Terrible app. Always loads with error. Slow and unresponsive on a high end mobile. Won't update and forced me to do research. Total waste of my time. Found an easier solution: Uninstall Waze. Problem solved. Will check back in a few months and update review accordingly. For now I give this app one out of five stars. Cheers!

I really like the app for the most part, lots of good, robust features. I only have 2 major issues with it. The main reason I usually use Google maps is that Waze can't tell you what lane you need to be in. This can be VERY important where I live. I'm sure there is a good reason for doing things this way, but it's harder to actually close the app than it is for most.

It's a great app for its usefulness in avoiding traffic jams, hazards and the law enforcement. But the routing engine got issues by not giving the route that takes the least amount of time often. I hv to make a manual detour for the app to show me that the route i took is shorter than the app shows me before i start my journey.

ETA does not adjust for time zone changes on route. I recently took a trip that changed from Central to Eastern halfway through the trip, and when checking my ETA before leaving, it gave me an inaccurate arrival time. Almost made me late for the event I was going to. Otherwise, I love this app for short distances and my commute. I sadly won't be using it on long trips for this reason though.

It's a fantastic app! The ability to to access road conditions and traffic and contribute in real time, on the fly, is really awesome! I'm holding back the other star until it gets an update that'll keep it open, even as a small active tile over all apps (including phone calls) so its never off the screen while driving. I'm keeping this star ‚≠ê until you do that.

Ads while driving. Because profit is more important than your safety and the core function of the application. If I could pay to remove ads and "point of interest" suggestions as well as hide the carpool feature that I would never use, this would be a pretty decent navigation app. As it stands this is an annoying safety hazard far more than it is a useful tool.

I really wanted to like it. I really did. I hate Google maps, but waze is somehow less intuitive and more frustrating to use than even that massive train wreck. Unless you plan your entire life around your GPS app, the way waze works will probably forever elude you. As for me, I use it maybe once or twice a month and it never seems willing to do what I really need it to. Guess I'm going back to Google with my tail between my legs. At least Google won't start up my Spotify for no goddamn reason.
replyContent: Hi Ivan , thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I wi rate this 4 stars. Is almost perfect but I have two issues. Some time ago you were trying voice commands? I can't find this option anymore. Also, apparently the last updates are using a considerable amount of data compared to previous versions. I even maxed my data plan (small 2gb) using the app. This wasn't happening before, and I am not sure what changed or if I can configure something.

I can't plan trips ahead of time anymore. I search the address, click "later" and it just says "somethings wrong, try again in a few moments". On top of that the routes have changed from taking me around traffic to taking me straight into it. This app was much better before, now it's basically useless since I mainly used it for trip planning and avoiding traffic.
replyContent: Hey there! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've been using waze for the longest time. I sometimes have to use Google Maps for specific streets that are not updated with Waze. BUT AFTER THE LATEST UPDATE, I CANNOT RELY ON WAZE ANYMORE. It can't connect to GPS anymore so it can't tell which side of the road I'm on. The routes loads in every turn. I am using 2 phones and it's the same on both phones. It makes me lose my way.

love this app. drivers work together for safer driving. easy to follow. i could set it up to keep me from speeding. what i appreciate most is knowing where the police are, and helping show others what is going on along the way. construction, wrecks, traffic jams, and vehicles parked on the shoulder.

I think the app sometimes tries to save you time that aren't really that much help. It's trying too hard, just give me a few options and don't try to send me around the block to save me 2 minutes off my route. When driving to Mexico and into border crossing, Waze sent me through DOT entrance and again was trying to save me a few minutes. I was promptly turned around and shown the correct way.

I love many things about Waze, specifically the speed limit feature. But it never seems to properly display where my vehicle is on the road. I end up missing my turns too often. I've reinstalled the app three times in the past year hoping to see it corrected, but I'm always disappointed and have to uninstall.

BEST GPS I'VE EVER USED!! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!! I'm from a small town so when my family had a medical emergency and had to travel to a hospital in downtown St Louis, I was less than confident about driving in such a busy area. I was told by a coworker to try Waze, she said it would help with my anxiety. She was 100% correct! With all of the different, easily accessible features on Waze, I can drive anywhere with very little anxiety. Real time alerts from other drivers is one of the best features!

This last update to Waze is horrible! You cannot choose shortest time, it now automatically defaults you to the shortest distance. This has taken my normal drive time from 1 hr and 10 min (typically in the am) to almost 2 hrs! And this is just going to work! Takes even longer to get home. Yes, you have taken me from 74 miles to 62 but a 50 min difference in time driving is just crazy! Please fix this issue! I cannot be driving for 4 hours a day.
replyContent: Hi Barb, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more about this routing issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: No other navigation app better than waze periid

How is it hard for this app to get that sometimes people prefer the shortest distance over the shortest time. That's what I chose to do when going to Philly. When they gave me route options, I chose the shortest distance 23.2miles which would take me 20 mins longer. In the middle of my driving y'all just rerouted me without my consent and made me take a longer distance that was gonna make me get there earlier. Can y'all at least ask for our consent before you reroute us cause there's afaster way

Keep LOSING GPS lock on ANDROID AUTO when the phone screen is off. No, it's definitely not my phone. It's not an old phone either (Samsung S10+). And I'm not the only one. And guess what? Google Maps works completely fine on AA. What's the point for a navigation app when you keep losing the GPS? WORKAROUND: In Android Auto (on your car screen) > switch to Google Maps > switch back to Waze > then Waze can get the GPS the whole way (because Google Maps is locking the GPS on background)

I'm not sure whether I need to blame on this upgrade but the GPS signal extraction issue comes back again when it is working with the Andriod Auto since the last several updates. The symptom is all the same as it previous looked like which loses the route track on the map. I have to switch to Google map and it works good for getting the GPS signal. I cleared all the buffers, memory but didn't work.

There is something seriously wrong with the app when it comes two accounts. For some reason when you login after having to reset your phone it will not find your account. I have tried about five different times where I try to log in with my phone number or my username and it will not find either. Twice I've had to uninstall the application completely because trying to add a profile photo corrupted the app to the point where I couldn't do anything (change username, set addresses, search map)
Love it , better than Google maps

Maybe instead of saying "Uh oh, cannot find a route", say "Cannot find a route without tolls, here are a list of routes with tolls". Even then it's still insane because in a state of Delaware where I had this problem, there are MANY roads you could have given me to avoid a toll. I'm leaving this as a one star for the inconvience until they fix this BS joke of a problem that should not exist!
replyContent: Hi Daniel, thanks for the review. Did you turn on the avoid toll roads option on your route settings? Here's how: tinyurl.com/y57csc5w We hope this helps! Please send us a private message on Facebook with the route details if the issue continues. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Fun and useful App!!! Allows drivers to communicate Real Time issues such as hazards, accidents, traffic conditions and more on the spot! With more experience, you can even help edit Mapping issues such as turn restrictions and even update roads! This allows for an even more accurate driving directions rather than finding yourself wondering and hoping when someone will fix an issue. And it's FREE! Good Stuff for a good price :) There's a points system too which makes it Fun! ^^ Enjoy.

The ability to add stops is a great feature, but in my experience, this app is simply UNRELIABLE. When driving distances longer than an hour, it almost always crashes for me. It has also re-routed me on multiple occasions in an attempt to save time (I assume), but ended up taking way longer than Google Maps' suggested route. It is a bit of a letdown because the app has so many great features that Google Maps doesn't have, but it fails at the most important thing I need it for: GPS. Uninstalled..
replyContent: Hi Andrew, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Decent app. VERY slow searching for addresses. Should also move the vehicle icon up about 1/2 inch on the screen. Miss alot when in tight areas because map doesn't move fast enough. Like the traffic, construction, police features. Updates on roads frequent and up to date. Google maps is faster, though. It's also a huge data hog. Again, Google maps wins out there. Overall has some great features but still not up to par enough to use exclusively.

Up to the last update the app worked perfectly. After the update on April 18th 2019 the "planned trip" functionality ceased to work. On the screen that previously presented the estimated time to arrive and the duration of the trip now nothing appears. Please correct it, this functionality is crucial to some of us that need to plan ahead! (my device is a Samsung S9, with Android updated)

Over all this is my favorite navigation app. However, I am getting very disappointed with several things one of them is I like the compass to be locked in to North being up. I am constantly having to tap the compass to make North be up. I do not want the map to turn around constantly if I'm going South I don't want the map to look like I'm going North if I'm going South I want the map to show I'm going South. Frankly, I'm afraid to update because it seems like this compass changed after the last update and now I wonder if we're gonna lose another feature then I'm used to

Hi, love this app was using it all the time but unfortunately it doesn't work anymore. The navigation is very clunky the GPS doesn't follow real time moving. Connection issues, No internet connection error and a host of other issues. Please fix the app I love using this through android auto I'm using a galaxy 10 plus. Thanks

This app used to be great, but it simply doesn't work with Android Auto since the last couple updates. It will show blank screen in black or yellow once unplug and plug in. It will take super long time to calculate routes with spinning circle. Sometime even when phone is fully functionally with no reception issue, it will say no network and couldn't display distance and arrvial time. Disappointed that it took the developers a few updates and issues are still there.

I've used this app for years with no issues. My most used app on my phone. Then a few weeks back something happened and its more of a pain than helpful. My screen is constantly zoomed in so I can see surroundings. If I zoom out it refocuses back to zoomed in within seconds. My icon is sideways and glitches and lags badly. Unfortunately if it doesn't get fixed soon I will uninstall it and have to look for something else.
replyContent: Hi Lindsey, Thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about these issues to investigate this further. To best assist with doing so, please submit debug logs and create a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app will sometimes go crazy. Where you will be driving and the it will re-route like 5 times for no reason. It's a bit scary driving on i-4 when it first happened. Now for the GPS not available. Sometimes you'll be driving and it will not respond. For this you have to turn your GPS off for 3 minutes and back on. It's very buggy now. Verses the 5 stars of before.
replyContent: Hey Ron, we're here to help. To fix GPS issues, try following the steps on this guide: tinyurl.com/ydbf57pk Let us know how it goes by sending us a private message on Facebook. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app has several benefits and easy to use, however recently the app just closes without warning. Also, after purchasing a new phone when I downloaded Waze, it asked for contact permission and will not accept no for an answer. I have not given permission and will not, so I will have to find another app. There is no reason why I should be forced to share contacts. I understand why they want permission, but making it mandatory is not needed, especially when I don't need assistance to them.

This is hands down the greatest travel app ever created, it not only allows you to point out speed traps and road hazards but is accurate and user friendly. It unfortunately is 100% dependent on user input but for the most part every person who has this app inputs keeping it updated. With that being said, do not be lazy. Pls mark everything you come across as long as you are in a safe position to do so. If you havnt seen any hazards for a min, slow down cause you're in the lead!

I had to remove this app. Your update is so cluttered. It used to be enter address, go. Now I've got pop ups and a new screen and more things to click before I can start. very disappointing. the directions have been really off as a result. this app used to be perfect. now its awful.

Incredibly bad routes sometimes. Update: routing just got worse. It's like the app purposely selects sub-optimal routes. Additionally, the app can't make up it's mind about the best route, every recalculation gives different routes. Also, when going off-route, the app wants to navigate back to the original route instead of finding a new best route.

I'm a truck driver and was given a load assignment going to a new warehouse on a new street that had yet to be updated in the navigation system that comes with my truck or even in Google maps. It was in this app though and it got me straight to where I was going with no problems. The only reason I didn't give this five stars is under the choices of transportation restricted trucks were not included. I would love to see that added to assure it won't try to send me down restricted routes.

Please fix the Waze app. It used to be stable enough but now it crashes all the time (four different phones; two different users of 4 years). Icons are constantly messed up. ETA updates are incoherent and not reliable. I want to use Waze but it's too glitchy. I miss Waze! It should be great! It isn't even good! :'(

This was my go-to for getting around town until recently. Like many others, the app sometimes loses my location, freezes, or goes black on Android Auto (seems the black screen is related to rerouting me). When it works, it's great. Unfortunately it's not working right now.

All this app does is pulls up a map and shows your location. I do not see any alerts I have looked all over the US map in the app and still no symbols of road hazards on the map anywhere in the United States. What am I not doing right? Nobody else has complained about this. How come I don't see anything in the database the app is useless

Speed camera notifications disappeared first, and back on road th icons also entirely for the same road. Fixed speed cameras, stayed there on road, but not on Waze map. Shall the driver keep looking the phone while driving for icons? Actual speed: varies constantly while using tempomat, can only assume the real one. Direction changes are indicated far too late.. I already changee the road when receive notification to do so. Unstable with Android auto sometimes, while Maps is stable.

(update) The issue with the music cutting out and voice prompts not being passed through the speakers has been fixed. (older version) I love this app but since the most recent update while running navigation on Waze through Android Auto my music volume constantly minimizes every 2 - 3 seconds as if a navigation voice prompt is occurring. Afterwards the sounds returns to normal for 2 - 3 seconds and then the cycle repeats. Once this glitch is fixed in the next update I will upgrade this rating.

I'm not sure what happened with this app, it used to be amazing but for the last few months it's been slow, lagging and freezing. it doesnt work or respond when I take off the wifi and open the app. It freezes and shuts down when i minimize the app to open Pandora, Spotify or check Facebook, When I get a WhatsApp video call the app does not work at all it will just freeze and not close. I've had to start using google maps instead of Waze. I haven't used Maps in roughly 3 years since Waze.

Would be better if... Could preview turn by turn directions Provide actual location (left, right or straight) if using a delivery app. 12.19 Feedback... Please update so one can preview the route without having to "plan" it...that's too much. Also, the history doesn't provide the actual start and end times...click on info, and only gives the address which is redundant.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback! We're always looking for ways to improve our product.
