content: Waze use to be my go to GPS, due to the multiple route options, traffic feedback, red light camera warning, etc. However, in the last 2-3 months I have noticed Waze telling me to take unnecessary turns or roads when the usual back roads are flowing smoothly, and not providing accurate live traffic feedback. it also does not show the fastest way to some places anymore, sometimes it takes me on longer routes. also it likes to give me HOV options when I do not have such pass or meet the requirement

Why is Waze so terrible at predicting traffic. It doesn't tell you that there's traffic until you are already stuck in it. Then it jumps your ETA out 10 min, after it's already too late. This is an almost everyday routine when I use Waze. Please fix that! It shouldn't be that way!
This app used to be excellent recently it has been taking me the wrong way over 10 times in one drive where it has worked perfect on the same drive before.
replyContent: Hi Chantalle, thanks for reaching out. We want to hear more details about this routing issue you‚Äôre experiencing to help. We'll need to gather more details. To do so, can you report the routing issue using these steps: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Good gps And accurate

I've loved this app for years, it's been great in so many situations. But in recent months it just opens on its own when I'm closing other apps. I tried every troubleshooting step I could think of, but to no avail. It's extremely annoying and unfortunately I had to uninstall. It's a shame. When it worked it was an easy 5-stars.

It's a fun app for driving. The only changes I would make are: Automatically Tell me which lane I should be in before I turn, so I don't have to tap and read directions while driving. Every time I switch phones, I have to create a new account and my previous account gets lost. It would be nice to keep my data and not have to keep starting over. Another thing that would be cool is to notify me when I cross into a different state or country like Google maps does. (;

Horrible. I search for "Arco" and first result is an ad for one 13 miles away while the all the results are Arco gas stations with the closest one being at almost the bottom of the list. Often shows me as being out a block to the side of actual position or as if I am driving sideways down the road the entire time. Even while simultaneously another gps app works properly.

The latest update to the hazard notifications has crippled that feature for me. It used to be a yellow popup and the notification would give you just the right amount of time to confirm or dismiss the report. Now, the notification is the same color as the map, completely blending in and they dismiss way too quickly. I actually thought the notifications were broken because they now blend into the map so well and didn't see them. Not a fan of this update to one of waze's main selling points.

Used to be a good app but degrades every months. Today it waited until I am on the part of the highway I cannot get out before telling me "estimated time in traffic 20 minutes". I know out of my head 3 completely different routes that could take me to the final destination in 10 minutes instead of expected 5 minutes by highway. Why it took me to highway is beyond me. Traffic according to radio has been there for a while (turned it while in traffic). Anyway, I hope new app will come out.

Brilliant app, works well when you have heavy traffic on the road, for instance coming from Crawley to Croydon and heavy traffic on M23 it will take you to A22. The main issue is, when android auto updates, waze doesn't update meaning it keeps crashing evrerytime you try opening the app in the car! It takes them 4-6 months to update, and when it does Android auto updates a week later! Attention to the Android side of this app is required by the developer.

This app started sending notifications even though I hadn't opened it and wasn't using it. Tried to disable the notifications but they still kept coming. Tried to force close the app; still notifications. It was a useful app, but I'm not driving much anyway due to the pandemic so I guess I'll just uninstall. Real shame.
replyContent: Hi Tobias, thank you for your feedback. We hope to see you return to Waze in the future, as we‚Äôre always looking to improve. Feel free to to reach out to us via private message on Facebook, if you want us to look into this notification issue. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app has always worked perfectly. However, after their most recent update, Waze has gone haywire. Case in point, ill be driving in one direction when Waze will suddenly think I'm going in the opposite direction or think that I've made a turn, thus, it'll continously recalculate. I've also found that its giving me terrible route suggestions. Cmon guys, don't reinvent the wheel! Please address these issues!
replyContent: Hi Christian, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. If you run into a routing issue again, please feel free to contact us. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I used to really like this app, ditching all Garmin etc. devices. But I wonder what happened in the couple of last months? Waze keeps crashing without apparent reason (during a routine trips, or outright after starting the app), has problems with route calculation or declares that it cannot connect to the network. Displaying ads when stopped in a traffic jam instead of more useful information is adding insult to injury. These days I am one step from uninstalling Waze.

Thought initially this was a good App, but now I've downloaded the voice says let's get started and then the voice (which is the reason I downloaded this) stops. Can anyone tell be a way around this? However, it's great for information on police, road works etc showing them on the Nav screen. Please can someone help - Thanks

I love Waze. Simply the best GPS app that runs well and isn't clustered with information. However, Waze does need to be more specific of what kind of hazards or delays are happening in real time and it needs to inform you when you need to make turns quicker. For example, if i am driving during a bright-sunny time of day, I can't see my phone to know where to turn or what specific lane to be in because i need to focus on the cars around me. Thank you for everything Waze!

I loved Waze BUT am one of thousands with the volume control problem when connected to AndroidAuto. My car is a 2018 Seat and the volume control of the unit has no effect on Waze (but does on GMaps and others). Even worse is that directions come out quietly at first but raise to a shout as they finish. Turning voice off is the only option.

The app is great and useful. Except for the pop up of undownloaded voice. It's disruptive, and cause trouble by requiring you to press the button for its removal. Please, make the download manager more capable, or at least, make that pop up time limited. Thank you. I put 1 star because of the pop up. 5 stars, when it's fixed.

You guy have been awesome until now. almost a week ago I reseted my cell phone and when i redownloaded waze and try sign back in it just doesn't want ti sign in now even with my email or my phone number... when i put the cell number to send a verification code and doesnt send it i even try ti request the call and still nothing please help!!!¬°!!!!¬°

Rarely works. Often glitchy and buggy. Will stop working randomly. Won't restart and will often not start routes. Multiple error messages without saying what went wrong. Despite having connection to the internet I get nothing. The UI is hard to use and the map is cartoonish looking. Only thing good about it is that it'll save time when it works which is about a fifth of the time.

Buggy lately. The arrow consistently is pointing the wrong way. I've tried to shut this app down unplug it reinstall I keep getting the same problems. Paired with my Ford it just seems to not want to alert me tell me the speed. It's almost like it's having a hard time keeping up with the GPS. When this app was working it was fantastic. I also noticed that about a month or two ago I had to completely start over because it wouldn't find my login and I lost all my points and how far I've been.
replyContent: Hi Adrian, thanks for contacting us. The speedometer issue you have reported has already been fixed and should be run smoothly in our next version release. Keep your eyes out for the next version to download it when it's available. For the arrow issue, please send us a private message on Facebook: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze used to be the best lately your gps function has sent me to the wrong place sometimes miles off forcing me to use Google maps. Who now is actually working. I still use your app but only if I know where I'm going for road alerts. Thank you for that. However looks like googles Is adding the features that set you apart from everybody else you might want to get your stuff back together.
replyContent: Thanks for letting us know, Matt. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details about the bad route? We'd like to investigate this issue. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Awsome app but for a couple of days it is all mixed up. It get me to different directions and start turning me around even in places that I was before. I was unable to use it yesterday to navigate to a friend location. I had to give the coordonates to my brother who was in the car with me and navigate by his phone who has not update. This is happening since something from waze came up on the screen like some updates and I choose ok. Since then, stuck in the middle of the road.
This app allows you to notified unusual activities on the roads. Giving other drivers a heads up. Giving them time to observe the activities and adjust their driving üöó

Totally inaccurate and annoying. Not trying to listen to the "rerouting" chirp loud as hell for 45 minutes straight when I'm on the highlighted route! It shows the arrow traveling directly NEXT to the highlighted route, not on it and keeps chirping and telling me to get on the highlighted route which I'm ALREADY ON. It also does the same to my husband. It's been doing this for months. I was trying to give them the benefit of the doubt but after months there's no fix? Trash
replyContent: Hi, Jasmine! You can always go into invisible mode by tapping your Search > your icon > toggle on Go invisible. More info here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6268714 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Would like an easy way to send corrections and to change the font sizes. If there is, I haven't found it. Accuracy is very good.

Been using this for many years now. While it has improved over the years, I have one little problem. Roundabouts should be a lot more clearer. Instead of a simple circle and the exit number, there should be a virtual image of the roundabout so it's easier to read while driving. Most other nav apps use the same principles. I hope this will be noted and applied in a future update. It is still a great app to use.
replyContent: We appreciate the feedback, Mo! Feel free to post this suggestion in our suggestion box where our team carefully examines posts for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

content: The app messes with any music/audio apps that are being used in tandem, constantly pausing and playing it and making it near impossible to shut down, and the spotify controls have never been able to connect to my spotify. App will "lose connectivity" while I have a full signal and has made me late twice now because it takes 10 minute to reroute when I misunderstand directions. Got recommended this when I needed something that would take detours into account but I wont be using it again.

content: It worked pretty good to me it always wore me of speed stops on the freeway also crashes also closed Road also how to navigate around damages roads I like it I used it for traveling all the time

Usually pretty decent when it comes to finding the best route. Occasionally doesn't pick up traffic that shows on Google Maps which can be annoying. My biggest gripe is not being able to search on route, and not showing search results on the map, when using Android Auto.

i enjoyed this app, superior to Google maps in most ways. stability of waze is terrible at the moment, it tends to crash mid journey which is devistating as it is distracting and uncorrectable. if you can't fix the stability issues at least gracefully recover ie automatically using something like a watchdog timer that replots the last route. i have had to leave this app until i feel it is trustworthy

was great till last update, now it takes me on unnecessary detours into main roads instead of staying on highway, added lots of time to an already long road trip. going to use an alternative til I see it update again and hopefully fix these issues. barely works now, will only give me one route, no alternatives. if you were planning a trip and wanted to get an idea of how long it'd be if you left at a certain day and time, that no longer works either. was a five star app until recently.
My waze keep crashing today. Try to uninstall and reinstall, but didn't help at all. Can help to figure out why? Im using Realme Pro 5. Thanks

in the car it doesn't work hardly at all. I have a rectangle screen and it doesn't adjust it like on the Android phone. It also lags! I have been home for a couple of minutes and it just recognized I have reached my destination. On the phone itself it works great...not so much when plugged into the car GPS system. Google Maps is not any better.

I can't remember how long I've had the app but I just started using it more frequently thinking it was better than Google maps. Nope. This morning proved me wrong. I understand that arrival times are estimates but I don't think Waze is synced up with the traffic properly. I started to add on 5 minutes to the estimated arrival because it usually works out that way when I use Waze. This morning the estimation jumped up to 10 minutes which I was not pleased with.

Does not show exit numbers on interstates. Makes it difficult to look ahead. The questions in the review were poorly chosen. Vehicle selection was completely wrong. I do not own a taxi, electric or smart car. Add truck SUV, sedan, van, etc. Also now it interrupts with questions about commuting and carpooling. Not good questions while I am driving. If I want to share my travel information I will do so before I start driving. Waze is becoming stupid. I will probably go back to Google maps.

Some questionable turns in places where it's not allowed, but am never quick enough as a driver alone in the car to mark them. Buttons too small. Buttons should be a bit bigger, most of them at the moment smaller than a finger tip. On bouncy roads or in bouncy car very easy to mis-punch a button. Some of the voices really inaccurate with distance remaining, or simply triggered too late. Only when using default voice with streetnames do distances seem accurate.

Waze has consistently gone downhill. I do not understand it. The only saving grace is the speed limit information.  When searching for a locaion, even if I have been many times before, the top results will be over 300km away (even if the actual destination is within 10km and has the exact same name).  After setting a destination, turning on music, and driving, it will pop up and ask "Are you on your way home?" and then begin a series of actions that attempt to reroute me away from where I am going to go home. Even though I have manually set a destination, and am now actively driving.   Sometimes waze does not request the GPS properly, and GPS never starts, thus Waze has no idea where I am. I can turn on the GPS Status app or Google Maps and instantly have location information, but Waze requires a restart to get this out.  I have a OnePlus 6, so a modern phone only a little over a year old.

"NO GPS, lost connection" While running is doing this, and if I go on another app for a short time it's freezing and losing GPS and connection.... replyContent: Let's get this fixed, John! Please follow these GPS troubleshooting steps: tinyurl.com/yabujh54 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great GPS-navigation app! I couldn't find a way to turn to the metric system (kilometers). Signing up for an account isn't straightword: I stopped trying after a few times. Local, short-distance maps should be more user friendly and have a nicer look too. However, Waze clearly beats Google Maps for long-distance driving, for which I only use Waze. I REALLY would like to use only Waze, including locally in the neighborhood.

Both waze and google maps are terrible if your area has lots of toll roads. I live in Washington DC and the app keeps putting me on toll roads, even though I set it to no tolls. There are roads that have tolls during certain times and other roads that are tolls but aren't marked as such because they are transition roads to a main road. content: This used to be an awesome app. The last 4 trips the routing has been utterly useless telling me to turn in one direction when my destination is in the other direction. Now it just told me to turn left in 100 metres and when I got to the intersection in told me to turn right in 100 meters, nearly causing an accident. It told me this 6 times evan 250 meters after I turned. It is now totally unusable. Will not use again until you tell me you have fixed the routing algorithm. Extremely frustratin

The best navigating app ever!! it shows you the way very clearly, it gives you updates about traffic jams according to the hour of the day, it gives you info about interruptions throughout the way, about cops and speed traps, etc... It also shows you the estimated arrival time to your destination and sometimes changes according to the variable traffic conditions. Briefly- Amazing and convenient.

Waze used to be my go-to, tell everyone how awesome it was navigation app. Latley it has been very disappointing, such as trying to send me on a road that had been closed for hours, and trying to send me on weird routes that, if i ignore, it recalculates and shaves up to 15 mins off my ETA! What's going on?? Until i have evidence of a resolution, I'll be using google maps from here on out

I used to love this app! used to boast about it. But over the last few months the app has been doing weird things. It makes my music skip ahead when the audio on Waze is on. I've uninstalled, shut my phone down and reinstalled and still the same. So now I can't listen to my downloaded music or Google play music or I have to turn the navi audio off. The song skip about 5 -7 seconds ahead. I like to sing to the top of my lungs in traffic! Then it loses signals frequently and randomly. Fix it plz

So far the only thing Google Maps has over Waze is that it will minimize to a smaller window that you can move around the screen so you can still see your navigation while accessing other apps, if they could add that feature it would be ideal! I love Waze for so many of its features but I still use Google Maps because it's missing that feature and I need that option often with my job and I drive over 200 miles a day

Very good until it shuts down..at the moment you really need the directions and you can't stop to mess with it. And that's with 4 bars of 4G. Restarting the app repeatedly results in "Ah, oh. Something is wrong" with no further explanation. Only rebooting the phone fixes it...for a couple hours. Back to Google Maps for me.

(using Android auto) Until recently, it was perfect, 5 stars. Best interface yet. Now, the location and speed is erratic. Recalculating all the time, constantly zooming in and out. Two other improvement could be unique to this app, chimes instead of voice indications for turns, and last minute chime on upcoming hazard or police. The warnings come to much in advance. Perhaps if the app determined an estimation of the time to the event instead of the distance... Yes. I'm a programmer.

content: While I love the way WAZE guides me to where I need to go overall, including the warnings, there are two things that REALLY need to be improved. First and foremost, if you end a trip and forget to CLOSE the WAZE app it WILL EAT YOUR BATTERY. Seems logical that the developers should close the app when you reach your destination or at least have a pop up to ask whether you want to close the app. If you do not it will continue to run and delete your battery very quickly while using your internet connection even while your phone seems to be 'sleeping' (blank screen). Second, the update of the visual display of YOUR position relative to your next turn is not very predictive of where you need to turn. The voice prompts are also often nowhere near timely to avoid last minute lane changes or turns. Compared to Google Maps WAZE gets one star on this point while Google Maps gets 4 stars. If Google maps added the reporting functions of WAZE then WAZE would be obsolete. I don't care who gets it right first, but perhaps Google Maps is a better choice for most if you are not in a situation where traffic reports and "police spotted ahead" are important to you. WAZE is quite nice but other than the more real time reporting by other WAZE users of incidents and police activity I prefer Google Maps for better map view, not draining my battery if I forget to close it, and better advance warning of turns and which lane to be in for my next turn.

I've had Waze for years now and it just had some kind of update and signed me out and when I signed back in with my number it said I don't exist. I had so many addresses saved that I needed and now I have to go back and try and find the addresses again! Not every happy with the app. Going to go back to google maps!

Used to love this app. App either "uh-ohs, server issue or must be restarted 3,4 or 5 times to get it to accurately show construction and other traffic obstacles. Often will not route around traffic. Two of us will leave the house at the same time for the same destination and get different routes. Forget it working with Android Auto. You need to go though the above procedures then hook it up to your vehicle system otherwise it just runs and runs, never showing the route. Back to Google maps.

Used to be my go-to app for GPS, and I haven't really had a lot of issues, but the one I have is a deal breaker. I use android auto, and no matter what I do, can't get the night (dark) theme. I've got it set on the phone, and it shows up on the phone, but Android Auto only displays the day screen, which is far too bright and kills my night vision for about half the road. Had to go back to Google, just for safety's sake. If that's not important to you, I'd give it four stars. If it is, then two.

This app sucks! It even has my own address in the wrong location! using this stupid app. put me directly into traffic jams!!! I watch the route that it has plotted for me and I clearly hear that route is backed up for an hour!!! this has happened several times. I no longer even use it. Google maps is much better and more accurate.

Stick with Google maps, this app loves to bring me to unnecessary traffic circles. One time it brought me to a neighborhood to use the tiny traffic circle and then bought us back to where we were 5 minutes ago. The user generated stuff is sometimes nice but there isn't a need to know where every stopped car that isn't impeding traffic is. This might be an app that people who need to stay awake or something need since it is always reporting useless information (small puddle != flood).

Not that great. Recently the app took me through random neighborhoods to get from one highway to another instead of just going a mile down the highway and interchanging there. It took close to 20 minutes as opposed to 7 minutes via the highway and there was no traffic on the highway. At least I know to be on the lookout for the lost cat from the neighborhood. Also tells you about turns after you drive by them and I missed several turns as a result. Use Google maps.

Marking low because Waze still hasn't provided an option to turn off red light camera alerts. This is the most infuriating thing with the app. I live is a city where almost every third intersection has a red light camera. Do you have any idea how much it drives me insane hearing that message go off constantly. Honestly, look at the number of forums screaming for this simple change. Thousands of users want it. Why isn't Waze responding?

content: Theoretically it should be brilliant. But it constantly says cannot cannot calculate route, the guidance always lags behind so you end up missing turnings and a lot of the time it just gets hugely confused and stops working mid route. Stick with gmaps, it's more reliable although fair enough without the bells and whistles Waze has.

I work as uber driver. Waze needs to be more transparent for e.g. if i take a right turn i would like to see what's up ahead before I take that right turn so i know whether to use the right lane or the left lane before hand. There are also cases that that i need to take a right turn and then a left lane closely follwed- Waze is so slow in this case. I would also like to know my start up location's direction. If i use waze i wouldnt know what direction i am facing until i travel forward a bit

Laggy, slow and frustrating. I like the concept of this app: being able to know about real time updates, like the traffic and if a car is stopped on the road. But I've had way too many issues with the map being behind and getting lost because it's giving me slow directions. It's frustrating and I don't trust it anymore. Back to Google Maps for me. Sorry team.

This app does not work as intended. It freezes and it also freezes my phone; very annoying, dangerous and unpredictable especially when you are driving and can't stop to try to fix it like highways or areas where immediate parking is not available. Manufacturer, please fix this issue, other than that, the app has good features and is easy to navigate.

content: App keeps crashing, not usable. Please fix. Edit: the issue was with a different app (Android system webview) and has since been resolved.

content: This used to be an awesome navigation app, my only go to. However in the past 6-9 months its ineffective for trips beyond 2 hours, "router times out." Therefore you have to put in milestones along the way and then add new stop to get to your destination. NOT useful for long trip when I do not know the route. Fix the issue please and you would have 5 stars!

Appears to take the long way around! Also I cannot stand it's constant alerts that there's a stopped car ahead! First I heard I almost freaked out as I was moving quite fast on interstate. I absolutely feel these alerts must change their wording or go because they can cause their own accidents, my stopped, crashed car on the road to be specific! Be careful with this type alert, keep in mind users are DRIVING and false alarms are not acceptable!!

I have gotten lost about 4 times using Waze and I had to switch to Google. Once it was supposed to take me to a Walmart but took me to a cornfield. Another time, it took me to a Burger King that had been closed for a while, had to switch to Google. Many times I have to cancel because that circle keeps spinning. Hopefully it will get better with some updates because when it does work, I love how it has such details and zooms in when it lets you know you'll be turning soon.

I have been using this app for the past month for probably 6000+ miles. I love the concept of telling about police, obstructions in the road, vehicles on the side, etc. But one of the most basic routing options is missing. Waze has a habit of routing me some obscure way because the route is the shortest, not the fastest route. I have found lately I find my route on Google Maps and then just run Waze on the route for the information. If there is a conflict, I have not been listening to Waze lately. I would like to just use one but have lost confidence in Waze routing now.
replyContent: Hi Daniel, thanks for the feedback. To find the best route for you, try viewing the alternative routes option when searching for a destination. Here's how: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6262424?hl=en&ref_topic=7059900 We hope this helps! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: very disappointed in this app all was well then all of a sudden it timed out in the middle of driving home from vacation in the middle of nowhere land leaving my family and I absolutely lost having to pull over and figure what else to use thank god for google maps!! I swore by this app guess I was wrong to 2hrs later and uninstalling and reinstalling 2xs and still nothing!!!! wanted smash my phone thinking it was phone it wasnt it's this stupid ass app!!!!

This app was GREAT before Google Maps and Waze started working together. Waze lacks the ability to give you the fastest and/or shortest route with user input. There has been a lack of notifications for speed cameras and have also been led off the road, and into some weird places using this navigation app. The user interface is amazing but everything else fails. I noticed that for Android users it was impossible to make additions to the map. I'm disappointed with Waze. It used to be great.
Easy to use.... üëçüëç

This is a good app with the potential to be a great app. It has a lot of useful information in it and the fact that other users can add updated current information about accidents, cars on the side of the road, and police presence and construction make it very timely and useful. The only problem that I have with it is its stability. It crashes constantly. I drive OTR and I can count on it to stop working at least twice every trip and that is a nuisance when I am trying to pay attention to the road and the traffic

content: I used to love this app. I never drive without it. Since the most recent android update, it doesn't work at all. I've tried clearing the cache from both Waze and Android Auto, still not working. The GPS doesn't sync or show you moving along the route at all. The map doesn't update as you go to show any hazards. It's like it's frozen at your starting point. If I switch to Google maps in Android auto, Google maps works. So it is Waze and not my android auto. Fix it!!!

Extremely frustrating trying to get it to follow a desired route. Makes all sorts of unnecessary detours even on routes where the destination is on the road you are on and won't give an option for staying on the road no detours. Used to be awesome but something changed and route generation is horrendous. Need to be able to correct the route when you see a bad choice.

I used the app every single day and everything was just fine but after the last update (from yesterday) is not working properly. During navigation the map is not rotating anymore to follow the direction (when taking the curves), but it goes diagonally and very often the blue dot goes out from the highway to the fields even if I continue my itinerary on the road. My phone's compass is calibrated, Location is switched On, I have the last version of Google Play Services and the OS is Android 9.

Great App for drivers and navigators. 1 suggestion is to indicate exactly which lane/s the driver should take to make a turn at junction or exit/enter highways. 1 issue i have been facing and even submitting debug log has not fixed it: incomplete voice direction. It will tell me "in 500 meters...." but doesn't not tell me to turn left or right after 500 meters. Hope this can be fixed by 1 day...
The UI is very childish and unprofessional. It gives you long routes. I'll be sticking with Google Maps.
replyContent: Hi, Jacob! Thank you for the feedback. We take consider all feedback to help better the app, so we appreciate you taking the time to write a review. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Normally it is good experience using the app. However many times i got network problem and it doesnt tell me what kind of network issue is that. Its most of the time 101 error code. Also at those times i am connected to internet. For example i was trying to accept a car pool ride and it kept on giving me network problem as error message but i was able to surf internet at that time.

This is a must have app for anyone who travels. It alerted me of a accident on my way home from work, and detoured me away from it. I didn't even have the app set to give me directions, as I knew how to get home from work. It was simply installed on my device! Time saver for sure. Love this app!

Been using Waze for years but lately less and less because I started doubting the sincerity of the routing algorithms they use. Routing me to the other side of a city to save a few minutes of traffic, but standing in twice as many traffic lights ending in longer drive times. Routing me back 15 km to the original route the app suggested, when I am 2 km from the destination, etc. etc. Yesterday though was the last straw, there was a road closure and police closed the on-ramp to a highway, this was in the news. When I wanted to drive home I hit the Waze/livemap web page (and then the Android App) and both suggested a route on that highway exactly, so I thought that maybe the road was open now. Unfortunately, police were there, the on-ramp was closed and I had to double back quite a bit. So if you made it this far, you might think that I have nothing better to do but the crux of the matter is that the road closure sign was VISIBLE on the map - someone had already reported it, it's the algorithm that ignored that and routed me there - right over the road block. Waze - you are NOT a startup, you are part of Google since ~2013 and traffic routing is what you do. There is no excuse for this.

Early on, this app was unbeatable. But currently, it purposefully auto-fills and displays incorrect addresses, leading to arriving at locations miles from my destination, it no longer allows placement of new cameras, and purposefully plans routes through red light and speed cameras, when the camera-route would be a lot faster. Its only redeeming qualities is occasionally showing dense traffic and police reports, when users report them. Fix the mapping issue!
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about these issues you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

I got so frustrated after it wasted almost an hour of my time taking a huge loop around 3 different freeways when all I needed was to get on 1 to head straight north to my destination. At that time, the ETA was completely wrong saying it would take 20 minutes and then I noticed that the path I was on was not a shortcut at all. Going with another gps app now.

content: It crashed as soon as I downloaded it. Once I got it open, it seemed fine created an account. It wouldn't save my home or work addresses, no matter how many times I tried, and it crashed after taking over 5 minutes attempting to calculate a route for me. As a first impression of it, I wish I could give it 0 stars

This app used to be great but lately it just trying to be smarter and smarter!!! Stop taking a detour for a 10 seconds saving in time for God sake or warn drivers of the difference in time all the time. There is no point zigzaging at six o'clock in the morning when the road is clear.

I only been on this app for 20 minutes & am already hating it. No sattelite imagery, can't hear any voice navigation samples when trying to select a voice, only have motor vehicles when trying to select method of commute (I ride a bike), & crashed on me when I clicked on a random venue to go to just to see what the navigation will do. Immediately deleted my account.

I am driving on the motorbike around the city. So i choose the destination, plug my earphones, turn off the screen and drive. Some times it works perfect, but now my phone just keeps shutting the app. I changed the power manager option for waze. No help. And app is going off silently.On long trip its very frustrating when you miss your turn. So have to step back to Google maps... unfortunately. Never used Waze with "screen on" so can't say anything about. For my way of use Waze is now useless.

I really like Waze -BUT- how the f... It won't translate the name of the major city in English. There are different labguages that we don t really know how to pronounce like greek, turkey, bulgarian, chinesse, arabic. FOR THIS REASON EVERYTIME I TRAVEL TO ANOTHER COUNTRY I USE GOOGLE MAPS! Maybe you can reconsider and add also the names in English. I don t have time to drive and try to prounance the name of the city on audio.

The app was great when I initially installed it. Then after driving a certain distance and being promoted from a "baby wazer", ads begin popping up. Very annoying and dangerous for a navigation app. Unfortunately, there's no way to get rid of them since there is no pro or paid version.

It was quite good. But has a few issues you cannot set destination by pointing to a location while the app is on a car screen. Have to disconnect. Uses Google maps but search give different results and not good ones, etc And for some reason location services become cr*p. So GPS position and speed is shown only for a few seconds. Most of the time the app has no idea where am I. First I thought my phone is wrong. But started using Maps and no such issues. Not sure how it's possible...

Please fix this. It is no longer usable. Google maps does not have even half the features. Use to be my go yo and recommend it to anyone, but now it has to be uninstall as even having it there is causing issues!! Update: I am pleased to note that waze is now more stable and i am back having it as my default.

Great when it works. I can drive for more than an hour and it will continue to say "searching for GPS". If I try and is it with Android auto, it has no idea where I am, showing me in the middle if a field somewhere when I'm on a highway. When it does connect it works great and gives a heads up about road closures, police, etc.

content: frequently won't connect to network,. WHY WHY WHY! so, i thought this may just be a flukey Samsung thing, but am beginning to suspect otherwise. I would go through this whole process of shutting off my WiFi, turning my data off then on-and still nothing. Most times i would need to reboot my phone to get it to work. It appears that other reviewers are experiencing a similar thing, so **Waze**, instead of assuming it's just our phones malfunctioning, how about you try to figure it out and fix!

Installed the app. Then saw a map filled with houses for sale, coffee shops, and other stores I have no interest in. Spent time trying to see how to remove the useless clutter and visual noise. After finding no option, uninstalled. I installed the app thinking it would bring me useful information, but only found useless information forced upon me. Total waste of my time.

Absolutely the best GPS I've ever used! I tell everyone to download this app. My friend was just using some phone GPS and all the roads had different names than the signs...she said that they had changed names recently but GPS hadn't updated them...I told her to use WAZE bc they update all the time! I love the way it tells you about objects on road, construction, police, traffic jams, etc. It'll give you the best directions and if you miss a turn, it'll get you back on track in 2 seconds flat!!
Used to avoid jammed in hiway but still bring to jammed hiway..

So much better than google maps. When it finds a better route on long drives, it doesnt send you back 20 minutes the opposite direction like maps did many times, it offers sensible route changes that actually save time. It has the most live map; I like that i get warned when theres an obstacle in the road approaching. There's so many settings to fiddle with and customize, especially the alerts. I like to have the speedo on all the time and noise when I exceed it. 100% will shout about it!
Apps keep crash everytime so I have to reopen the apps so many times so that I can use it again. Pls fix it. It wasting my time to do that first everytime i want to use it.

App keepa asking me to connect to NPR One almost everytime i navigate, despite repeated selecting no. i might connect it if it didn't cause NPR One to autoplay when Waze opens, even if i already have music playing or even if I'm not connecting to Bluetooth. if i open waze at work to schedule a future drive, NPR One will start playing. i only want it to play if im connected to my car's Bluetooth, and i dont want it to play if im already playing other music.

Half the time lately it tells me it cannot calculate route. That is unacceptable for a GPS to be that unreliable. Also I have noticed that the app must be receiving kick backs of some sort from these toll roads. I will see a route that is full of the most expensive toll roads in my area and when I ask for the toll free option, the ETA goes down. Considering I ask for the shortest timed route so that shouldn't happen. With the unreliability and clear corruption, I will be uninstalling WAZE.
Not really showing the best traffic. Get stuck several times because of waze, and google maps showing better traffic.

Pros: Everything except for one HUGE problem. Cons: Essentially pop up ads during trips asking if you'd like to navigate somewhere other than where you are currently navigating. I was SUCH a fan of Waze until it started delivering pop up ads! Which is reeeeeaaaaaallllllyyyyyy bad/borderline dangerous to be in route somewhere and an ad pop up asking if you'd like to navigate somewhere else instead. Ads would be fine between trips, but these things during a drive completely ruined Waze for me.

I haven't tried the latest update but for some reason my earlier review is missing. I like the idea of the app, and I wanted to enjoy using it. But i can't get its hands-free commands to work in Android Auto. Its search function is disappointing. I wish you could use search and continue a navigation from Google Maps. I'd write more specific comments but I don't want to waste more time if they're being deleted.

Just reinstalled app after factory reset. When I log in it sends me a code to enter. I enter it and nothing happens and there are no buttons either. So, what the heck am I supposed to do. Oh, I know.....go back to Google Maps. I've never had any issues with that app!

When you're good, you're good!! Absolutely fantastic! There are many Nav apps out there claiming to be the best, yes yes yes, I've heard it a thousand times before! Then I saw the light, aaah yes! There is a Waze! The Only WAZE is forward! I absolutely love the Waze you can share your drive in real time, Live up to the minute incident reporting, Wazer messaging, the list goes on! Thank you Dev team for a fab app!

Waze WAS the best app of all of them IMHO. Then Google bought them and have developed several irritating behaviors: if you stray from their route, they used to recalculate based on your change. Now it tries to make you double back at every opportunity to make a turn; when you switch from phone to car navigation, it changes the route you chose back to the Waze preferred route. Even with this & other small inconveniences, the police, speed trap, & speed limit notifications are priceless

Waze is such a life saver!!!! And I mean that to the fullest. I'm a new drive so I didnt feel comfortable taking the highways, but google map kept sending me there even after putting avoid highways and toll. I ended up getting lost because of this. So I downloaded ways and a completely different experience, it made my drive easy to get around. Thank you soooooo much waze
This app is way better than my standard Google GPS. It knows all the hidden shortcuts and is even accurate about a pothole in the road! Would give 10 stars if I could :)

This app has been vert disappointing. I was looking for a simple GPS navigation app. with voice instructions as well as visual navigate. What I hot was little to no voice activation. when there is voice the volume is so low as to be unintelligible. Then there are the distractions of multiple menu options that distract the driver, where arr the gas stations with the lowest prices, and unwanted questions like am I a driver or a passenger in a car or am I a pedestrian, this when I said I'm driving
Bad sat navigation app don't use it

What happened to my last review? Anyhow, happy to come back and rate this one star. Whatever your QA team is doing, they failed. This update completely broke Android Auto. This went from being the best maps app around to the absolute worst. You can no longer make phone calls, listen to music, or listen to audible whine this is running. There appears to be done invisible notification constantly going off. It is at least once per second. Constantly lowers the audio volume for music, maddening beeps while in a phone call, and constant pausing during an audio book. Literally this is unusable now. Congratulations on releasing the update that forced me back to Google maps. I've been using waze for more years than I remember until now. Sad times.

Definitely love this app as it's super helpful with speed limits, police radars, speed cameras, stopped cars on shoulder and much more. Although, one thing I'd love of you guys added the following: 1) An Offline and downloadable map so that when I go outside of my data coverage I can still use the map, although I do understand that won't want be notified of stuff like cops. 2) Would be helpful if we could add shortcuts to homescreen of certain addresses. thank you!

content: Love this app it is more accurate than other GPS functions and it gives great information on traffic around where you are driving.

not working. rebooted the phone. force stop the app and relaunched it as well. endlessly waiting for it to connect to my mobile network. doesn't prompt for GPS like it normally does when launching. when GPS is recognized and I'm traveling, it plots my route and tracks my movement; however, the lack of network connection prevents my ability to provide input (i.e., potholes, traffic, police, etc.).

Ok what is going on. Lately when I use Waze, it shows me all over the map. It constantly loses my location. It's almost like its lost in cyberspace. I am having the same black screen problem. Also the No Connection Error too. When I switch over to Google Maps, no problem at all. Please fix.. Using Android Auto and Samsung Note 8.

I wanted to thank this great application as it's with sadness that I'll to stop using it, after soo much hassle and frustration I decided to look for an alternative, so far Google Maps seems to be doing great, I'll miss Kate n her marvelous english accent n having the option to report, but the frustration of not having reception, not getting GPS or the same old tired UI that is slow to help u find the right thing to report, all these things that weren't there a few years back. Miss old Waze!!!

it has very aggressive re navigation which is really good for avoiding traffic or road closures. It also shows cheap fuel spots. the fatal flaw of this app is that the little arrow that represents you on the map is about 5 or 10 m behind you in real life so you will drive past your turn without even realising it until it's too late and this makes it fundamentally broken as a navigation app and therefore I don't use it. Also it displays ads while you're driving so I uninstalled it immediately.

Waze always finds a way to let me down during my trips. Sometimes it will crash, others it will ignore my destination and reset as if there's no destination set (all that in the middle of a highway). I used to be a huge fan, but now I've been using Google maps more and more.

Seriously almost always unuseable on my OnePlus 7 Pro. GPS connection issues, frequent app crashes, error calculating route even when I'm connected to 4G+. Whenever Waze doesn't work, Google Maps works perfectly fine and seamlessly. The only reason I'd pick Waze over Maps would be the user reported alerts, voice options and the overall design language, but it's not worth putting up with all these fatal issues. Being an older app, you would think they'd fixed these issues by now, unfortunately no
replyContent: Hey Jasdev, we'd like to help! Please make sure that you are using the latest app version. If these issues continue, please send us a private message on Facebook with more details. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: ive used 3 device still all gt problem. redmi note 3 network problem same with redmi note 4. then change my phone to latest realme 3 pro also same kind of problem. end up using Google maps for all 3 device with no problem at all. there only few times when my phone able to run properly ,just only few times. at first i thought mybe im using Chinese brand phone this app always have problem but ive seen samsung user also face this kind of problem. so this means yr app thrash.

Was supposed to be a 32 minute trip home ended up being over an hour due to terrible directions. First, it didn't recognize stand still traffic that I was sent into, then it tried to get me to take a detour even though the road was open. It ended up sending me back the wrong way down the highway. The fact that both these mistakes were made in the SAME DRIVE really had me concerned. Also, ads every time you stop... really? Uninstalling and never using again.
replyContent: Hey Matt, we're so sorry to hear about your experience. Waze is a crowd-sourced navigation app and it is possible that due to different reports and changing traffic conditions, the route you got wasn't optimal. content: Genius app. I was a G**gle M*ps user for years, and my cousin from Tuscon told me about it when he and his wife visited. The speedometer and hazard features are fantastic, and it's very user friendly. I appreciate how interactive it is, and the real-time alteration of your route depending on live traffic.

Routing from Sacramento to Yorba Linda wanted to go east to US-395 and down the eastern side of the Sierras (631 mi.) instead of down CA-99 or I-5 (444 mi). Asinine. And last week, app worked just fine. Arrived in Yorba Linda and tried to route back to Sacramento and app can't even find it. Piss poor job, Waze.

A terrific app, though it does have its quirks. Searching for places can be less than ideal, I don't care for the cartoonish aesthetic and I'm not sure you can make reports at all via Android Auto. But! The ability to tell the system what conditions are like on the ground, and to counicate with someone who can update the map, is fantastic.

the worst app. it is always wrong on arrival time by over 30 minutes. I hate this app, it just gets worse every single time in use it. not only is it wrong with time by 45 mins but it will tell you to zigzag to your destination which ends up adding double the total time. This app is a waste of time, if you like being late or wasting time, this is the app for you.

I don't know if it's because I'm used to it, but this does not compare to Google Maps. Literally did not tell me about a 2-lane closure after telling me there were over 4,000 "wazers" near me. Uninstalled and going back to Maps. PS I do like the Batman voice over though!
replyContent: Hi Jeff, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

IT ONLY PROMOTES STRESSFUL RISE IN MISTAKES. THAT MUCH THOUGHT AND STEPS TO CHART A ROUTE? REDUNDANT I'D SAY. THANKS

Worked ok, had a lot of hiccups. But, when I really needed it, it needed an update, after closing out my route. updated it and it STILL wont work. I'm in the middle of nowhere and now I have to use Google. which will add 2 hours to my trip. Not impressed.

Awesome, reliable, legit, simple GPS application. I love it. I love the boy band GPS voice too. It's HILARIOUS. I set that as my default narrator that way when driving accompanied with friends, it brings endless laughter to our day or night. So I recommend WAZE GPS system to EVERYBODY! Decided to deviate from my normal route and follow this app. I effectively lost 40 minutes sitting in traffic. Initial eta looked promising. It does not recalculate eta ahead of time, search for alternate routes, and only advised on the traffic jam when you get stuck in it. The app has become very generic. Next time I'll rely on my instincts. Uninstalling.
Need more data on routing options and businesses. Keep up the good work and improve. You will lead the pack.

content: I think this app is great! I love that there are navigation voices to choose from and that there are live updates on road conditions. I'd like to suggest having a HUD function though! Also I think functions on the app could be clearer? It's a mess to try and change or add stops sometimes. Might also be nice to have the projected costs of erp haha

Not what it used to be. Removing the option to report speed cameras takes a lot away from this app. It now takes months before a speed camera is shown, even longer (if ever) if you don't live in a big city. I understand the volunteer editors hate them as they're often erroneously reported, however, I'd rather have one erroneously show up than have one that's there not show up on Waze, which is what has started happening since this option was removed. There has to be some sort of happy medium.
replyContent: Hey Paul, we appreciate your feedback. If there's a missing stationary speed camera, please send us a private message on Facebook with the precise location and any additional information, and we'll look into it. Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Could be better! I've come to this app after 8 years of Google maps. I think this app would be perfect if it took a page out of Google maps book. Seeing a list of alternative routes and times is old news & outdated and reminds me of an old sat nav from 2009. It's much more convenient to physically see them on the map while showing you the way you will be going & the time it will take, while also providing continuous alternative routes visibly along your route. Waze get some ideas from Google!

I originally gave a 5 star rating for this app but I regret having to reduce it due to their demand for email confirmation, or the app would stop working and I'd lose my settings. Only to find that they know about a fault that stops you from doing that. They cannot be bothered to email everybody again to say that and this is in addition to small faults with their app which have gotten more irritating as time goes by. A good idea that has gotten worse with bad programing, poor support and staff.
replyContent: Hey David, we're sorry for the inconvenience. Are you still experiencing this issue? Please send us a private message on Facebook and let us know. We're here to help! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Garbage. Used this app for the first time today during a 13 hour drive from NY to KY. App crashed every 2 hours which is exactly what you don't want a navigational app to do in the middle of NYC or a rural interstate. Dangerous to use considering once it crashes you are forced to use your phone while driving to reboot it. I'll just stick with Google Maps.

Good at letting you know where there are issues. Not so good at removing those issues. I have been told of an accident ahead and several miles later there is no evidence of an accident. The app also seems to be power hungry. Keeping phone connected to a charger is necessary.

Google killed it. I was never a big fan of Waze as it shows me other Waze users on the map. That seems pointless. But there were other promising features like reporting hazards and traffic cameras.. Google simply stopped improving the app months ago while moving the key features and benefits to Google Maps. The navigation voice was never improved. The only thing I liked, frankly, was the better map color pallette. It's only a matter of time before that is moved to Google Maps. This app is dead.
replyContent: Hi Brendan, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. content: Works great with my Google GPS Locator. Not sure how often the location updates the data I track, though. Regardlesss, its easy to use. It was cool to see the icons of police cars & EMS vehicles that are actially in transit on the roads, even in the same lane ahead of me, while I was actually driving! Its def cool. Seeing my fam & friends icons actually moving along on the map as they are driving on the road is great esp if I have to wait on them. Its a parents must have. Love this app.

Frequently loses track of where I am which makes it so it will change route so quickly that I dont have enough time to keep following the directions. Also frequently directs me to make illegal maneuvers even when I have not gone off the planned route. Do not use unless it is specifically for interstate driving, because it just makes city driving more difficult.

Seen wazers in your map is completely pointless if you can't beep, It'd be better to be able to wave other wazers and for them to be able to wave back, and for option to be active for all wazer not just "friends". Otherwise just go with regular Google Maps clean and simple. Also the wazers in your map are not truly live. there is latency. This app was fun and great to use few years ago but it's changed a lot, pretty lame.
replyContent: Hi Dea, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I need to know precisely where an address is at and figured I'd give Waze a try. I've used Google Maps and it has been flawless with what I needed but figured with the community input that knowing updated road conditions would be helpful. That aspect is very helpful but this app is not accurate at all with putting me in the driveway of my customers. It would always tell me that I was at my destination at a neighboring home and never the house I needed.

Most of the routes are ... With the occasional round-the-block, unexplained odd route.... Like (I assume) most or all other navigation systems. I like the speedometer... And the real-time hazard alerts. One thing I would like... A "Pause" function, for when my wife and I get distracted by (for example) a garage sale.

Helps you get around traffic. But takes you miles out of the way if you miss a turn. Programmer forgot to program it to tell you to make a u-turn. Therefore you can drive miles and a huge Loop before you realize it took you in a loop. What a huge waste of time when you simply could have made a u-turn!

Good, but ads pop up sometimes while driving blocking the map, forcing you to take a hand off the wheel to close it so you can see your next turn. This is unsafe. Either show the ads when the vehicle is stationary, or offer a way to get rid of them (paid version).
GPS error on the middle of the road with google maps it wouldnt happen very annoying
replyContent:
Hey! If you're having trouble with your GPS, we'd love to help you fix that. Take a look at this guide for more details on resolving this problem: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051?hl=en Let us know how that goes.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Overall a great app! The alerts for crashes, slowdowns, police, objects on road, construction, and more. Check gas prices is nice too if I could figure out how to update the prices, which are sometimes old. They also have different voices to choose from for the direction announcements and alerts. The only quips I have are sometimes it gets thrown off at the beginning of the drive not pinpointing your spot and leads you the wrong way as a result.

This app is total garbage now. It used to get me to my destination quick and easy. Now it takes me way out of the way through horrible neighborhoods and down pothole filled streets to save 2 minutes, and that's only if it doesn't try changing the address you put in for one that is similar but miles away. If i cut and paste 123 Main St? It will just change it to 122 Main BLVD for some crazy reason.

This app has changed drastically, in the beginning it was perfect. Now, it seems something has changed it always select the most non direct path and takes you completely out of your way. The direct path is not an option anymore and this I have seen over many trips. I have removed waze, I feel for some reason that marketing is a factor in the directions being implemented.. ie.. McDonald's pays waze and waze directs you to travel by it or another company. Just my though, why add 25minutes...

I used to love this app, but lately it gives the worst directions. It starts with the longest distance and longest travel time. And when you ask for alternate routes, it doesn't give good alternatives. I often just go my own way and beat waze. Super lame.

Routes have been either inefficient or stupid. It's not outsmarting traffic anymore, but finding alternative routes to enter the same traffic area you were hoping to avoid in the first place. There are times it strays me from the usual path to which when I refuse and stick to the usual route, it recalculates and tells me I'll arrive earlier. If it doesn't have traffic data on alternative roads, you won't be routed there, even if it's wider and empty, it will still choose the usual traffic-laden

Great application!  However, I've recently discovered an interesting bug in Android Auto - the area on the left side of the screen, that has information about the distance and direction to the next turn/exit (like the one that says "In 1.5km exit to Highway 401 West") sometimes loses the big piece of information (mostly related to the turn/intersection/exit name). The same happens with route reports, e.g., if there's a car stopped on shoulder, it displays the icon on the map, but doesn't display anything on the left (where 'Thumbs Up' and 'Not There' buttons are supposed to be).  However, based on my experience, this happens only after an ETA update message is displayed (e.g., 'Traffic is building up ahead...' etc.). This behaviour is pretty consistent, so it seems like there's something wrong with either layer re-drawing or visibility indicators for the layers responsible for route events.  My hardware is: - Head Unit - Ford SYNC 3.0  - Phone - Samsung Galaxy S8 (North America)   Let me know if you need more details on that.

Hands down the best navigation app ever. It Always takes the route with least amount of traffic. I use it even when I drive across town as it knows if there is slow traffic or any other issue. Literally the best. I actually do some network flow analysis for a living and have no clue how they developed this system. Even Uber uses it for their drivers...which makes me nuts when an uber driver ignors it during rush hour because they think the route makes no sense... until they hit the traffic.
Waze is great, the more people who use it, the more helpful it is. I prefer this over any navigation app
I enjoy the app, I use it every day. I think its great.

Promotional ads are quite disruptive, annoying, and not needed. The push notifications for road statuses (law enforcement, car on shoulder) block the view of routing; can only work with a cellular signal and will malfunction or not operate with out it based on change in signal strength due to location. Routing will be changed if phone physically falls the floor in the car. This is an app only for those who wish to speed and not get caught by law enforcement primarily.
replyContent: Hi James, thanks for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit the changes you wish to see regarding the display of ads in the app and notifications to Waze's suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Newest update has rendered app unusable. I loved Waze and considered this a 5 star app. Recently the app has completely changed and is no longer reliable. It will drop out in the middle of routing me somewhere or will not update my location as I drive along which rendered this app useless to me. I'd love for them to fix this issue so I can get back the app I so enjoyed.

Like seriously, this app gets on my nerves. When all my other navigation apps work fine to get GPS signal, waze just idles, even when i have perfectly good reception. Dev team, please, rectify this stability issue. I love the app, but i seriously hate how it manages to mess up something as easy as getting the gps signal to work. I will not recommend this to anyone, at least until this issue has been fixed.

Great app. Better that Google maps for me. I love the community notifications. But we need a way to make map annotation in offline.mode. also a way to download offline maps and last traffic information. Because I. Mexico there are some roads that don't have cell signal and some time we want to add warning annotations to other drivers o search the map for a specific point.

Let me down big time on a road trip through Europe. Worked entirely fine until we stopped for a break on our road trip in Belgium, then it just refused to calculate a route saying "Uh oh" and that it couldn't contact a server or something despite internet working on the device just fine. Then it tried to send us over a bridge in Antwerp that is closed and under construction. We had a 1 hour de-tour around Belgium that was completely un-necessary I had to resort to using google maps to finish the journey. Not happy.
replyContent: Hey Matt, we're sorry to hear about your bad experience. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with the route details? We'd like to look into it further. Thanks and safe travels! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: While I prefer Waze's maps and navigation, almost every update brings with it more bugs than features. Android Auto integration constantly breaks, forcing me to delete all of my data and to reset all of my settings. I'm just tired of it. If they focused more on stability and less on stupid social features no one can use while driving, it might be a five star app.

Best Sat Nav out there. See other users live, users can add stuff such as police, pot holes, speed cameras. It's totally free,which blows my mind. Forget TomTom and other sat navs where you have to pay with this you don't pay a penny. Users can add locations such as car parks, so you can easily find the car park. Brilliant!!!

I simply love this app!! My only issue with it is that the notifications for police control should pop up 1 km before (NOT 500 m before). When you are on the highway and you're going with 170 km/h, 500 m is almost nothing to be able to react. So developers of this beautiful app please make this change to help me and many others! I promise I'll give 5 stars if this happens.

I absolutely LOVE this sat-nav app!!!! It is 10000x better than most of the expensive'paid apps'!! I love the ability given to you to report any incident, potholes, road works, different types of traffic and many more options. Thank you for making WAZE available to all for FREE, I recommend this app to family, friends, even strangers multiple times a week. ***BEST SAT NAV APP ON GOOGLE MARKETPLACE/STORE***

A lot of "error calculating route" messages recently. I've had to use Google Maps a few times. Force stopping sometimes helps but not every time. Please fix that. I never had so many problems trying to get somewhere with Waze before :( September 12 update: not sure if this is an Android 10 issue, but now the app always says that there is no GPS. It was ever since I gave it only while is use location permission but then I put it back to always on. Still says no GPS :( please fix this!

No better way than Waze! I have used this app for a few years now. I honestly prefer it over my Durango's Navigation System, AND the Google Maps app. In fact I just ordered a phone holder for my car (from Amazon) based on all the positive reviews that mentioned Waze being easy to use when the phone is in this holder. P. S. I only wish Waze would come inside vehicle navigation in the future!! :)

I have used Waze for years but in the past 6 months it has directed me incorrectly and when it mattered most: I missed 2 of my son's basketball games. It navigated me to the middle of nowhere and yes, I input the address correctly. Also, wake often navigates through neighborhoods instead.of main roads so you find yourself driving in 15, 20 mph zones with multiple 4 way stops. I dont get it. Im back to Google maps and much happier.
replyContent: Hi Karen, thanks for your feedback. We'd would like to help with the routing issue you're having if you're still interested. If you would like still like help with resolving this issue, please following these steps to report this: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270994?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: After using Waze for years and loving it, I uninstalled this app because of all the now ever-present bugs and glitches. It's all too annoying and found I can't trust this app anymore so it's useless to me. Oh, and I'm sure I'll get the generic Waze reply to this review too because they're actually really not interested in any resolutions.üòÄüòÄ Update: Yep, just as I expected, a generic reply from Waze. Still not reinstalling it!
