To do so, please create and submit a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I absolutely love this app! It is way better than Google maps, which caused me many issues in my daily commuting. I love all the added features, settings, accuracy, and most of all, HOW EASY IT IS TO USE! Waze gives great information & it has never failed me!!! I am so glad I downloaded it & I have forced many family members go ditch their old app & give Waze a try. No one is sorry they did! Thanks for making a brilliant application!
No satellite option. For a company owned by Google for over 10 years now, you would expect better map options!

Uninstall after 2 years. Takes up too much memory space and data usage. Takes me round and round and even a further distance and end up longer time, just to save that 1 minute, stuck in traffic lights or housing areas where too many turns. Trust own instincts better, reach faster and smoother driving. Google maps suggests better routes options.

I've been using this app for 5 years and was very helpful. But just recently I noticed that it's been taking me to wrong places. I got lost three times. It was really frustrating. I wasted hours of driving and wasted gas and never found the places I was looking for. I will have to stop using Waze for now. I don't wanna get lost again. Hopefully this could be fixed and return to how good as it was.
replyContent: Hi Lovelie, we're very sorry to hear that! Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with the route details? We'd like to look into it so we can fix any map issues. Thank you for your help. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Supposed to give you alerts for cops, potholes etc. But the people giving the alerts are almost always incorrect or putting alerts they know aren't true on purpose. 90% of the time, it takes 5 minutes to load a map because it says no gps. When I have data, or wifi and location is on. It likes to direct you to different routes that don't make sense. And often only alerts traffic when you're almost in it. Same results on 3 different phones btw. Currently it's telling me I'm in NJ.... I'm in PA.

The worst navigation what I have used so far. In order to save 1-2 minutes it takes us off the highway. Finally we are already in 30-40 minutes late. Or other example, a highway turns the get around a hill, it takes us off again from the highway and navigates us though some mountain road, resulting 40-60 minutes late.

Since two months, there's an issue in connecting waze to Audi MMI (Q7 2018) via Android Auto. It gets disconnected every now and then, with a yellow screen on the phone. I need to unplug the phone from USB, stop waze manually, restart it again, which does not guarantee that the problem will not be repeated because it does. I have bought a new data cable but the issue persists. When I do not activate waze when connected to the car screen, there's no issue at all. When's the next update???

The one thing that would make this 5 stars is being able to add multiple destinations in at a time. I usually have a route to drop off checks at different locations and I haven't found a way to use Waze to do that. Unfortunately, I have to use Google Maps to do that, or take the time to enter each new stop. There only seems to be a way to add one additional stop and no way to rearrange the stops to make a more efficient route.

Lately my favorite maps app has been very buggy. I run the latest Android OS and keep Waze up to date. It disconnects from GPS frequently in areas that I know from experience are solid. Most often it will disconnect just driving around town, or on the freeway at the edge of town. Some days it states I have a network connection problem and tells me to try later. All my other apps work fine during all these unfortunate events. I have a good carrier and 4g connection most of the time.
Uninstalled.. Always send me to death road

i don't know why but the waze apps now gettin worse. sometimes it not shown the red color line. sometimes it say the road is clear until i got stuck into the jamn then suddenly it says "20 min jamn ahead". it very very irritating. also giving very far routes and false information. always re-routes without any reason. before this i was very happy to used this apps but now is useless. better used your head than used this apps. not helping at all.

Terrible since November update. Similar to others the app is currently terrible. Used to be my go-to but now I use Google navigation. I have a OnePlus 7 pro. Problem is with Android auto. Won't use GPS correctly if launched first. Have to use Google navigation then go back to Waze. Even then there are random blackouts and resets of app. Please fix! I loved this app but don't use it at all in it's current broken state.

While I am sure Waze considets opup ads that plaster over important content improve the chances of getting "eyeball" time from drivers, they are distracting when driving. Worse, many are ads for chain reataraunts nearby that I hate going to, and there is no way that I can see to get rid of them. This "feature" seems to be fairly recent as I do not recall seeing it a few.years ago. Uninstalled it.as, to be honest, these popup ads are so distracting they are a safety hazard.

A few issues stop me giving 5 stars. Other than the problems I mention this is a brilliant tool that I use all day and don't intend on changing. 1: I have screen burn from speed limit signs. 2: Integrated music player/controller will refuse to work from time to time. 3: Freezes when used with Android auto and SYNC on ford systems. (Unsure if issue is with you or Google) 4. Audio selection (On, alerts and off) will not "pop up" to intended place. Instead it sits near the bottom. Please fix!

Nice app is fun to use. Adds a little to a otherwise long and boring drive. It is basically google maps but easier on the eyes. (Well it is owned by google) what would you expect. The preference can be hard to find and they blur the top inch of the android auto screen which is really really annoying. There is no reason for that.

I do not know what happened, but Waze is worsening by the week. Not good. No bueno. I have been using this app for more than 3 years and it has gone from awesome to trash. It needs an update almost daily and now it takes forever for Waze to connect to gps. Waze... Please fix the issues and become awesome again. I travel too much. I need Waze to work every time!

Many great features and I use it literally every day. But could you please stop messing up my favorites set order every time there is an update to the app? And if make an unexpected turn please route it from there instead of trying to get me back on the original route for the next couple of minutes. Please provide a way to indicate that the current street from here is closed and I need an alternate routing.

Waze is a great app to have on your phone. especially if you drive a lot. it has a spark of interest by adding little emojis and "level up: emojis. the app itself is easy to use and can be read easily. It is very handy being able to report incidents on the road when stuck in traffic. I usually use Google maps but all that shows sometimes is red roads and you often think well why is it red. Waze has an option to suggest what has happened I.e a pothole or a crash etc. I recommend !

My most used app! Waze has, for me, went from a pretty gimmicky app to one that I couldn't do without. I never leave for a journey without firing it up and I've found it incredibly useful once hooked up to facebook. It will alert you (unprompted) if there is a delay in getting to events and also is extremely accurate when it comes to journey planning via times. Brilliant app. Keep up the good work, Devs!!
Genuine garbage. No matter your signal strength or wifi, this app will make your trip longer.

This app is spot on! Obviously the input from people using it is key. I am new to it, about one month now. I use when highway driving. Works great on my droid. I have no issues of it working improperly. Driving to summer home on weekends brings us through some thick traffic at times. it has always notified us in advance and rerouted us to save time. Hasn't disappointed yet.

What happened? I loved Waze. It was my favorite app to use during my drives but now it's laggy, crashes, and barely works 80-90% of the time, which leads to panic if I'm going somewhere I'm not entirely familiar with and Waze just decides to lag and crash the route, leaving me floundering to reload it or resigning to use Google maps. Now, GMaps has to be my go-to because I can't deal with the constant Waze crashes. Please fix this issue so I can go back to using Waze!

Doesn't work, doesn't find location, takes forever or doesn't find a route . I wanted to use it with Android auto but I give up, Google maps works just fine , same phone same car . It's an app problem. I'll hold on to it for one more update. update your phone display can not turn off when using Android auto or you will loose connection. I will try tomorrow to see if the settings I changed have worked

Great app... may I offer a suggestion? Clicking thru 2 or 3 icons to report an incident can be very hazardous. Maybe create 3 very small shortcut buttons of our choosing (choose from a list) which can be displayed at all times on either side of the main GPS screen, which can quickly and safely report something like, Car on the shoulder, or Police ahead or Pothole. When you're driving, sometimes just taking your eyes off the road for 2 secs can be enough to be bad. This idea would help a lot!

I love Waze it's been great! I'll say that it's sometimes hard to do, Road Closures or Construction especially if you're not in or driving in that area & want to do it after you've already had to work around it. I use to live in an area where they were randomly closing the neighborhood streets due to a new condo building construction & it would be nice to be able to just add that in for the day whether or not you end up driving or not, but just to be helpful. I want characters back as options!

Can't rate it no stars, would if i could. This used to be wonderful, now it's useless. Don't know what happened, but it's no longer worth keeping it installed. 9\30 Everytime i go on a trip, i install this app hoping that it has been fixed so it works as it did in years past. Today, i tried again and today i was again disappointed. It actually worked for about 30 minutes after install, then the map disappeared and it could not find the network connection, tho, 4 bars, all apps working.
replyContent:
Hi, Rick! We're sorry to hear that you've experienced this issue. We'd like to look into this further, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I had discovered WAZE several months ago when I had to travel to Cleveland Oh. I had no problems with it at all. yesterday, was the first time I needed to use it to go to Columbus Oh. I was trying to get out of town at rush hour. Waze directed me to make a turn, then froze up, no next turn designated, I was in a panic. Finally, I pulled over and activated the Google Map app. very disappointed.

I don't know why, but sometimes it dose not connect with my 2018 Ford Fucus RS and 2018 Ford F150 Platinum with usb cable. Even the cable is working, it gives an error that cable is not working. Also, I cannot get connected if someone calls while I am using Android auto, I have to unplug the phone and answer. I can call out no problem.

content: Whatever changes you made in the recent update has broken a working app. Although it gives a route it won't provide turn by turn instructions and hangs at the initial screen. It just says "proceed to suggested route". It can't find GPS and approximates my location with a blue dot well off my route. It is useless in its current form and will force me to use something else. FIX THIS PLEASE!

I love everything about this app except that it does not alert you there are traffic lights ahead. I hate it when it mention 'in 200km turn left' !!!! How on earth do I know how far is 200km, I miss almost every turn because I can't tell the distance. Hope you can be more precisely to help people like me. More precise in describing what is ahead or what building to look for or traffic light ahead...etc.
replyContent: Great feedback! Thanks, Eliene. We'd love to hear more from you. Please add your suggestions to our suggestion box so our team can review them: waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks again! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: on more than one occasion now when I've been running a bit late I have put in my destination to get the fastest route. It is sent me fruits that have heavy traffic then it did not count for yet should have been able to see as it was Construction. I could have just gone the normal way that I go and got in there right on time versus going the way it told me to go and being 10 minutes late. Screw this app I'm going back to Google Maps

I used to use this app constantly, but as a lot of others have said, the app is horrible lately!! It never knows where I am and shows me driving through areas where there are no roads!! I've gone back to Google maps and have no problems. The features aren't as good, but at least I know where I am and where I'm going! Frustrating!!

Disappointed. Following the May 29th update, Waze is no longer able lock my GPS position. This is the case for both standalone and Android Auto use. Google Maps and other location based apps still work fine, so is definitely not my device. All the usual reset tricks have been tried to no avail, and I live in hope this will be resolved following the next update. Until then its Google Maps or native Sat Nav use for me, which is a pity, as on its day, it's the best navigation app out there.
replyContent: Hi Nick, we're sorry to hear about your issue. Let's get it fixed. Please follow the steps on this guide: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051?hl=en&ref_topic=6273402 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love how it tells me about cars, cops, and accidents that are coming up. Also when people confirm that those things are there I know that the accident hasn't been cleared, so it gives me a chance to take an Alternate way. Or when it's gone people are on it and take it down. Awesome app and when people put up an accident, car on side of road, something in road, it's within a few feet which is very appreciated!!

This used to be the best navigation app ever, but over the past few weeks and updates it has progressively become unusable. As a rideshare driver I rely on this app all day long, but with constant crashes, "no network connection" when I have full 4g lte bars, it taking two or more times to navigate out of the lyft app (when it used to only take one click and multiple clicks are very unsafe), and when you look up a gas station or address it tells you ex: 1.1 miles away when it's really double. :(
Great experience every time!

its an epic app but its major downfall is this major app crash while driving on motorway. I drive 2-3 hours from Middlesbrough to Edinburgh and back fortnightly and the app always crashes mid drive. Pisses me off soo much when it does that. i can't even report it when I'm driving so have to multitask fearing for my life that i may crash as i hate touching my phone while I'm driving. i hope the devolopers read this and get finding a solution.

Fills me with rage every day. Its meant for driving (hands free) so why do I have to press at least 3 buttons to start navigating!? Search results by voice suck so you need to type in a search instead. Can't choose routes easily. Basically it's not easy to use whilst driving which is it's main purpose. Why can't they just add all the useful functions to maps and be done with this terrible piece of software. Can't rate journeys either so if it takes you a rubbish route then no way of it learning.

Completely broken as of last patch. Won't maintain GPS location or direction of travel. Tried reinstalling and is not completely broken with Android Auto. Says I need to do first time setup by opening on my phone and the app immediately closes if you try. If you open waze before connecting it will immediately crash. Google maps works just fine. Fix your app

Keeps telling me I have to set it up every time I try use it in android auto even though I have many times. Also lags behind and locks up then jump back up then lags some more. If I can run Google Map in satellite view and have zero problems with it keeping up with me then I would figure Waze should have no problem doing the same .Guess not .Use to be decent app now its not . Got deleted

You can always reach out to us via a private message on Facebook if you need help with something in the app. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: We almost had an accident going back to Manila from Antipolo. Waze was telling us to pass through a one way high way! Then the last time, I searched for antipolo church, it took us into unknown subdivision. You guys should not be downloaded at all. You may have just caused our familys life. Jusko for the love of your life guys, dont use this at all. Use google map instead. So unreliable!!!! I will even be posting this on my FB account.

Its very buggy these days. It loses connectivity sometimes, in crucial moments.There's often a delay with the next turn. It changes routes so quickly sometimes. For example: In the same minute it tells you to turn left, then right, then goes back to left. If sticking to the original route adds 2-3 minutes, then it shouldn't change routes. The flip flop decision is not worth it.

Best GPS App. that I've ever used. The only problem that ive experienced was whenever I upgrade to another phone is transferring the app and everything i had saved and built up on Waze, its happened 3 times over the years and I had to start over each time, if only they had an 800 number or anyone to talk to, to help with the transfer. Thanks.

I have yet to get my issue fixed. I sent a request to the help desk but haven't heard a response yet. I posted my issue on the Waze forum and haven't received a response. I currently use Waze on my android auto receiver (on a 2018 Escalade) hard wired with my phone being a Samsung S8+. I'm an avid user of Waze (literally use it multiple times a day) and i'm always on the phone. i know there is a feature to allow Waze to give direction while on a phone call. content: Just started with Waze yesterday, and spent a couple of hours with it. Here are the main issues I have found which a beginner will find useful: 1. Creating a login was a frustrating process. Don't log in with your Google account because you allow Waze full access to lots of your Google details. 2. I found that the street I live on was named wrong, likely based on an error over 20 years old. So I created a login, then had to use the app to create and drive to, a destination from my home. That allowed me to edit the map error. It will take a day or two for the correction to show on the live map on the app, I am told. Why does Waze have errors that are decades old??? 3. I told the app I'm driving an Electric vehicle, but it still asks me what type gas I use, whether regular or premium! Crazy! Their suggestion box has suggestions about EVs since 2013, but Waze says "we're working on it." Even now in 2020, Waze maps do not show EV charge stations, despite choosing "Electric Vehicle" in settings. What the app desperately needs is to ask the user what the driver's EV's range is, and plot suitable locations to charge on the way. Waze MUST make sure that they only point to chargers that provide no less than 50 kWH charge rate. Tesla Superchargers provide 120+ kWh. Our Tesla is very smart, and tells us where to charge on the way. Not sure about non-Tesla EVs, whether they have that capability. So is there any advantage to using this over Google maps on my Android phone? NO. I thought about deleting the app after I verify that they did fix the map error, but eh, what the heck, I will just leave it on my phone! :) A positive thing: customer service was great with email support, and the Waze community is very responsive. I just hope I can come back in a year and give this app 5 stars!
replyContent: Hi Raja, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience and glad you gave us another try. Also, please submit your idea of suggesting EV charge stations in the app to Waze's suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

This is a great app, there is just a few suggestions i have which i think was really something noticeably absent from this app unless i did not know how to access is: 1. There is no way to edit extra stop points within one route 2. no way to properly plan your own route because of the no edit function to insert extra stop points 3. the time calculation for the arrival time needs some looking into, for instance i was driving a road that was clearly marked on waze as having construction and traffic is moving at 30kmp/h in a 120kmp/h zone but still somehow the arrival time showed that i will be driving this road as per the normal time which was 6 hours, i clearly knew this was not going to happen, as soon as i started to enter the road works my arrival time went up quite dramatically throughout the time adding another one and a half hours to the arrival time, could this not have been calculated before hand? 4  . could the app user not mark something in the road and act upon it later?  I would give this app 5 stars as soon as this is looked into, i hope you will find this review to be a review from a client that is looking to use this app permanently rather than as a degrading review.

content: Been using Waze for several years. Excellent for directions but they have continually driven the user to operate through FB "NO"!!! Now they have removed all my family members and I can no longer use it to know when family will arrive or notify family of my location and destination. Several emails into Waze, ZERO support.

I have this issue in multiple vehicles so I don't believe it is the vehicle equipment. When this happens I can use Google maps but the Google maps app doesn't have the same capabilities as Waze.

You have to use the phone, which defeats the point of Android Auto. 2. You have to be NEAR the closed road to report it. Not always convenient if you're driving and you don't have time to stop. 3. Whereas in Google maps you CAN search and view the surrounding area map, in Waze you can't (you have to choose "Go" and let it calculate a route.)

content: The app was working good but apparently this recent update messed it up. I try to login with the same information I used to setup the account with. Now it says it doesn't recognize me & I to start all over. It doesn't show the speed limit nor is it showing cops or items in the roads. Once the app is working properly again, I'll raise it to a 5 star where it used to be for me.

What happened? In the past week, this app has started to lose its mind. The map freezes, then a few miles down the road, catches up and my car icon will "float" to my actual location on the map. It's glitchy at best and annoying!! Before last week, I had no complaints, but now, this app is a glitchy mess.

I've used Waze for many years on many different phones and I've loved it the entire time. Keep up the good work. I recommend this app to anyone that asks about a good GPS app. I would love to be a part of the beta tester group. The last time there was openings i hit the link to join but for some reason it wouldn't let me & I was going to try again a day or 2 later but there wasn't any openings left. So I've been waiting & checking frequently hoping to join.

OK, but would be better if; 1. Road names increased in size when map size is expanded. 2. Vehicle Type included RV with LxHxL info. a. Warnings of route segments that might not be passable based on Type of vehicle information entered. 3. Top speed, or % of speed limit could be entered. 4. Fuel tank capacity could be entered and location of service stations shown when logically needed. 5. Menu access more intuitive. 6. Offer the option to superimpose current weather map over route.

The app does not give you accurate locations. Most often times it gives you the name of the business instead of an address. And address is more accurate then a business name. Many times ways inform you that you have arrived at your destination and you haven't. This is a huge problem.

Great! But... I always find my self going back to Google maps because on Google you can download the maps to be used 'offline' with no Internet or 3g/4g connection. Otherwise it's better in everyway. It would be nice to have more sweets/milestone rewards like, number of roundabouts or time spent on a 70 or 30 or time spent in traffic (statistics)

I've used this app a couple of times in the past. The where to voice action understood every street perfectly, in ICELANDIC. I loved it. Until i opened it this week and was confused as to why google was all of a sudden integrated into it. Oh well, maybe I hadn't noticed it before. Wrong. It doesn't understand anything I say in Icelandic and when I type it in the app now often confuces where i'm actually at when i'm driving. Apologies, there is no reason for meto use this app over any other now.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for the feedback. We understand the inconvenience but Google Assistant is currently supported only in English. content: I loved the easy the app worked especially giving an approximate planned arrival time. All of a sudden, it would stop working. I would uninstall and then install. It would work for a little bit and then again, it would not open. sounds like Google maps is next in line.

Happens on both Samsung Note 9/10 and has been before on other devices. The features are certainly cool, I just hope google doesnt abandon this app, starting to look its age with the graphics and getting too buggy

Love the app. I use it everyday. Sometimes slow on the traffic updates. Crashes a little too much in my opinion and completely shuts down after navigating for 2hr trips. Great navigation. However, since they added speed camera alerts, the menu option to turn off red light alerts has been missing. Excellent app. If you have Android Auto it is even better. The app will work and give you updates even not in use.

content: good start to a great idea. would be helpful if you could edit the radius around your home and work locations, have more than one person in your carpool, and request to see people even if they don't fit in your schedule/route (for example, being able to take the same person to work and back home in a day even if one way isn't as convenient)

it's a tool filled with navigation errors. Other than that from the 8 months I've been using it, I can say that not everyone on waze reports or just cancels stuff, I next time around just rereport. Route choices are idiotic, regularly safe myself 20-30min not driving the routes on it. Sucks at navigating, warns you to late about the turns. Had 20 such events. 8 of them where missed meetings costing my company work.

Almost every cop is marked on main highways and interstates that are heavily used- hands down best part. Shows speed and speed limits and is pretty damn accurate on the limits.

So, like others have mentioned, I have loved WAZE....but that time has come and gone. Too many network issues, searching for neteork, map freezing and more. Definitely not Android Auto friendly. However, this has not always been the case. Troubles started several months ago and generally WAZE is unusuable for navigation. Sorry, just my experience.

content: Waze is better than some other cellphone navigation apps, but is inferior to installed navigation applications that I have used. The options available and status information available while the map display is being presented is nearly non-existant. it is difficult to even find out where Waze is sending me - especially if a previous trip was not "completed." The use of on-line Google maps slows down display responsiveness. The interface with the car's GPS breaks down from time-to-time. Poor app.

In android auto, the arrow is not always facing straight on the screen so as I pass side roads, it often thinks I'm driving down them so the route jumps around and then corrects itself. It is also about 100 yards off, so as I'm approaching a turn, it looks like I have a block to go but I end up passing the turn. I can't seem to find a way to calibrate and it's driving me crazy.

The best GPS app out there. Social GPS. Can even report cops hiding and road hazards! Just love this app and use it daily!

Love this app! I wish more ppl used this cause the more ppl using it while driving means we know 4 sure where cops,accidents,hazards are. mainly where the cops are lol I like the GPS more than Googles.I have my voice set 2 boy band it's funny & helps 2 keep a stressful drive less stressful. content: I use my phone in landscape mode while driving my car using navigation. I don't like this new version of the app with the My Waze, Carpool buttons and search bar on the bottom of the screen. Great app when it works. Now i constantly get "searching for network". I live and drive in the detroit area, hard to believe there are network issues. It will start a trip and quit with no notice and go back to start. Or the trip will start and say " no reports on route " which is not only wrong but hard to believe during rush hour AM and PM. And I've unistalled and reinstalled only to lose all my travel history even after i log back in. Frustrating.

I don't go anywhere without Waze! Hands down, it's my favorite GPS app. I don't ever open Google Maps to compare my routes bc I know Waze is current. My favorite part is the several options it gives you for routes, the updates on police, traffic, potholes, etc. I know Google is making improvements but IMO they don't come close to Waze!

Does what it needs to do, but recalculates routes too early. When traffic is standard and there are only a couple side roads available, the route and ETA is accurate. When I use this app for evening rush hour traffic though it recalculates my route sending me on side roads that everyone else is using too. I tested a few days where I stayed in traffic on the freeway and I ended up getting to my destination faster (usually 10 or more minutes), than the side route Waze suggested.

Used to be good but recently it doesnt keep me on the road and routes are the worst available. Cynically, it seems to take you past the advertisers where possible and tells you to stop there. I've given up. Went back to Google Maps. Typical case of good app being destroyed as business gets greedy. A start up done a better job than a corporation, explain that.

Totally Loved it. I'm using this app on daily driving routes. Traffic Updated Accident Updates Radar updates Policeman updates Road conditions updates Hazard Updates Road diversion and no entry updates. Many... 99% It shows the best route to reach on time. Specially in Middle East you need it as Home Screen App. Not informative enough about places like Google maps does but for Driving, it's the best driving partner. You can even update about all conditions while driving to help fellow drivers.
Worse apps.. always give the wrong location

Brilliant graphics and great app! but I really dislike the new (bold) font, when it goes back to the old font (or a setting that changes the font to the old one) it's definitely a 5 star app. also lately when opening the app it doesn't go straight to the map it firstly goes to the Waze app logo for a second and it's really annoying. PLEASE GET IT FIXED!

When it works properly, it's the most amazing app. When it doesn't, it gets pretty annoying. Voice commands stopped working all of a sudden, doesnt get addresses right sometimes and takes you to mysterious places. Good for finding cops and speedtraps, hazards, etc

How silly can it be. I took a shortcut and deviated from the route. After which Waze's ONLY MISSION is to bring me back to the point where I made the deviation. I had to put up with its endless prompts to make U turns for the next 30mins of driving down a highway as I couldn't stop to shut it up! Even having reached my destination eventually, this stupid app still wanted me to head back to the point of deviation! Can someone please tell me how to give -5 stars for rating please. Not happy!!!

Its like Waze has some kind of a business deal with toll companies. I don't mind taking the tolls but it's always recommends tolls as the best option. Luckily, I know the area very well and I find my routes faster than taking the tollway. What about the areas I don't!

content: What annoys me is that I've been driving in circles, but when i used Google Maps, it's just a straight line. ü§£

This used to be a super app but as most apps the developers just can't leave a great thing alone. The first thing to stop working properly was that when asked for nearby gas stations it wouldn't show recent gas prices (it would show prices from 3 months ago). Now it just gives a message that no stations are found at all (as I pass a station that has always been listed in the past). It used to warn of road hazards, debris on road, vehicle on the shoulder or police ahead none of these work anymore.

The apps is okay, but missing few items, such as a transparent or black navigation key for apps with soft navigation key (back home and app switch). In landscape view there's no overview bar (traffic from blue to red which I believe could easily add at the bottom or top of the screen), and there's no lane assist like google map. would give it 5 stars if it actually brought you to the address you entered all the time. it will bring you to the alleyway behind the house, across the river from the house, it to the street behind where you'd have to walk through a forest to get to your address. thanks you trying to save me 15 seconds usually costs me 5 minutes plus. 50k miles a year driven on app.

Two recent changes have made the app far less user-friendly and helpful: (1) The option to turn off map auto-zoom has been removed. (2) the option to turn off voice directions (whilst retaining sound for speed camera alerts etc) has been removed. Why did they think this around be a good idea?
This app is awesome!

I hardly used it, but it's good so far It have more features but you have to pay monthly I wish to have a feature that it gives predriving viewing on the map so I can observe it before i go on the route, it will make life easier for me as i'm dyslexic and i only drive locally to be safe. I used to have this function on tomtom so it helped me to to go out of my area and found myself more confident and prevented to have panic attacks.

Can't use this app especially with android auto. When the voice is telling you what you next turn is, of course it kills the volume on your music, however after the voice is complete, the music does not return to its previous level and must be turned up manually every time the voice is activated. This does not happen when using google maps and is specific to waze rendering the app annoying and useless.

The program is OK, but if it had traffic sign recognition it would be great. In most cases it does not tell me the option of which is the shortest way to go in the destination. It has often introduced me to HW, when there are plenty of other options. In Google Map you can see some options to go in the destination. When you are in HW 400 you know to show in advance the lane arrows you have to follow and not at the last moment

The speed cam warning stays on far too long so 2 cameras in close proximity can be confusing. Worse thing is any time after about 90 it shuts itself down. I do 3.5 hr commute twice a week and every time it switches itself off partway into my drive. Fix the last 2 issues and it would be mint.

I'll give it three stars just for the hazard avoidance info, which is usually good during the day when there's plenty of users on the road. At night, when we like to drive, you're not going to get a lot of current reports. But that's all i can say good about the app. It's worthless for actually navigating, never has the same route as my Garmin, Google maps or gps built into the car. Most of the time it just says, 'can't find route'. ETA is way off when it does find a route.

Believe it or not this is one of the best apps that I have ever had a chance to work with. It's been almost two years now since a friend of mine told me about this application and ever since I installed Waze I deleted all of my other ones and left this one. I can tell this GPS app is one of the most accurate that I have seen in my life even Google GPS map is not so good. Strongly recommend everyone who cross path with Waze GPS map traffic app to install right away. It's worth it!!!

content: Waze does not keep track of my location, or of current traffic conditions. as does Google Maps. When I make a turn Waze has directed me to make, it can take up to three miles for Waze to notice that I made the turn. When a slowdown has cleared, Waze continues to report the slowdown and does not update my ETA. Also, many times, instead of naming the street where I am supposed to turn, Waze will instruct me to "turn left in 450 feet ". When the turn is imminent, Waze does not alert me.

Warrants 3.5 stars at this time. Pluses are 5-0 alerts, good hazard warnings. At long last there are lane advisement. Couldn't understand why Google Maps had it for years but this Google property didn't. However, I've had too many recent incidents where alternate routes could not be provided. This was always Waze's calling card. Always room for improvement. Keep it up.

Really good app but I'm missing some features like: having the ability to have offline maps, custom distance before an announcement like roadworks and others as now it's really short, would be nice to see services on the map when you're driving long distances and when's the next one. Also has issues with the three finger and ok waze as it doesn't even work for me, if you change between apps it drops the Spotify support which is annoying and you need to close and reopen the app to get it back... content: I use waze daily and it does a lot of things right (real time traffic/police/stalled vehicle reports) but the ads are obnoxious. What I mean is that while using the app waze feels the need to cover the entire map with a full screen ad. I know ads keep the app free but if the ads were the size of the traffic reports I feel that it would work out the same. Instead I am constantly missing turns because of these full screen ads. I will continue to use waze for what it does right but every full screen ad brings me closer to uninstalling.

I honestly think this is the most overrated app in the store. It has many nice features I like (avoiding toll roads based on the country, spotify integration, etc.) but... 1. I need to restart it every once in a while - seems like when the phone loses internet connection several times, Waze fails to reconnect. It will just show looking for connection forever. ALL the other apps reconnect without problems right away. I need to shut Waze down completely and turn it on again, then it works. 2. No junction view - this feature has been coming since forever and it is STILL not here, it makes driving in an unknown city a real pain. Literally all the other major players have it. No "route bar" - so I never know what is upcoming, where the traffic jam is. There are also many other small things, like it cannot estimate your position in a long tunnel and so on. So for me Waze is a good looking toy but there are better navigations out there (even tho they are not free).
Didn't show when there is a police roadblock.

Something must have happened with a recent update but I'm now visiting places I've never been to nor intended to visit with Waze! It's started taking some ridiculous circuitous routes and avoiding the common sense roads. Not always but enough to make it unreliable. A shame as when it was working it was near perfect.

routing logic is flawed, at least needs to remember when I manually change from its preferred route to my preferred route instead of changing back to its preference, then selecting a third route once it's apparent I'm not going on its route. needs to show up coming lane options on the freeways like Google maps does. speedometer needs to show the current speed using three colors, green when you are at the legal speed limit, red when over the limit and yellow when going under the limit.

An App I want to like better but even on a fast phone (note9) map lags actual position and it is EASY to miss turns! Also, the one stop trip limit, is - well - too limiting. Need to map out a journey that has multiple stops, not (almost) one by one. Really frustrating for voice commands as well. Google maps is WAY better. Not really all that much to like here, despite hype. Also, server response is very slow as well.

i used to really like the app but its been having issues for a really long time. ill have full bars and wifi and the app still wont fully load and it will say "searching for signal" or "searching for GPS" or itll start the GPS and not give me an ETA, its just weirdly glitchy. also i would like there to be some sort of organiz with saved locations. and have more options to save favorites. one is "work" okay well i have two jobs? they haven't fixed this app in years.

I asked Waze to take me to a Walmart tire center so it sent me to a graveyard 40 minutes away from my destination. After I got there and put in the correct address it immediately sent me to a dead-end road shortly up the road I was on. I've had no issues with the app up until this point but for it to fail this badly is unacceptable.

Please improve the Thai guiding speeches, so that it is easier to understand. It doesn't translate road, and it pronounces place names with American English accent instead of the Thai native accent. When it guides me to u-turn, it always tell to turn left or right twice instead of take u-turn at the left or right. It says road names in English instead of translating the word "road" when mentioning a road.

I was excited until my first directions. I live 300 yards from main road. It took me in the opposite direction only to circle the block behind my house adding a mile to get to the same corner. Totally didn't need to go around the block besides ending in the same direction. Useless!

Used to be good. Not sure what happened and why it changed, but can no longer receive correct ETA's and cannot follow a drive either. Frequent contacts do not show up and always have to "invite" a user who I know already has an account. Quite annoying- may switch back to Google Maps Edit: Waze has improved greatly. I haven't encountered any issues in the last year!

Good, but annoying that I get notified of railroad crossings and cant see the map whole these notifications are on the screen, even after I've passed the railroad. Also would like a button to quickly switch between north being up and the direction im facing being up. You can lock north up, but I'd like to switch it on the go like with google maps.
replyContent: We appreciate your feedback, Dustin! If you'd like to disable the railroad crossing alerts, just go to your Settings > Map display > Reports > Railroad crossing > toggle 'Alert me while driving' and/or 'Show on the map' to the off position. Hope this helps! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: i can't change the routes easily, and if i do pick the route I want, it will change the route without notifying me. there is no way to tell it i dont want to anywhere a semi can't. to plan a route i have to drop a bunch of extra stops along the way, or it reroutes on to routes my truck and horse trailer or a large camper can't go.

Good app but need some tweak on how it's aquring location. Sometimes when you are half(50%) WiFi range app says GPS connection lost not sure why? Specially on recent update when you are activating carpool ( before inviting riders) app says unknown failure no network connection but I have net connection. When I do pull to refresh then carpool got activated and I can invite rider s

I will give 5 stars after you solve the search problem! It is connected to my car via Android Auto. Until sometime ago everything worked flawless. Now, when I try to search any place, only the first letter can be entered and even that will disappear. So, I cannot go anywhere unless it is already in my favourites!! Please fix. Just to add this: waze people are 5 stars. They send me several emails to solve the problem. Nice indeed.
replyContent: Hi, Paulo! We're sorry to hear that you're having trouble using Waze on Android Auto. We'd like to look into this further, would you mind submitting more information about what you're experiencing here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Worst gps ever. So many commercials they should be sued for trying to distract drivers and everywhere I go it's endless re routing and u turns after following its direction

App is quite buggy particularly with Android Auto. It's not as responsive as Google Maps, taking time to detect GPS signals and at times, not detecting them at all making the app itself appearing to crash. It's a real. shame.... Also suggest using contrasting colours to clearly help identify what options users are selecting in the Android Auto interface. Its difficult to known what you're selecting when using the cars menu selector - in my case, a commander controller knob.

I used to love this app. I would recommend it to everyone but now it doesn't connect to GPS And when it does the app jumps around and put me in weird spots. My GPS works fine with other apps so I know it's not my phone. Just recently started happening and the update today didn't help. Fix this issue and it would be 5 stars.

I used to adore waze, now I've given up on it. it reacts far too slowly, so i am already past a turn before it shows it. it no longer gives the best routes. if i restart it then it gives a new route similar to what google maps gave in the first place. i dont want to use Google maps but until waze returns to being reliable it's my only option. i miss waze. i like the traffic warnings and ability to add my own warnings. please fix this app! clearly I'm not the only one suffering.
Hi, after several tries from 2 different phones, we were not able to download the app, it just kept downloading over and over, but nevwe finished
replyContent:
Hey there! We're sorry to hear that this issue is occurring. We'd like to learn more about what you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook?

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Probably the best navigation app around. But has had it's issues. On one journey it got fixated on a closed road and didn't reroute despite numerous notifications to tell me about it as if it wanted me to change the route manually. On arriving at the closed road there was an amusing build up of Prius's, as Ubers had been sent the same way as I had. Occasionally it doesn't pull new traffic data for routing away from traffic and end up in long delays.

I drive medical patients as an NEMT and I cannot say enough how much this app has helped me and my colleagues!! It warns us of everything!!! And calcutes the shortest routes, whether it's around traffic or thru it!! And now it shows the layout of the lanes as u come up to intersections, making this app #1!!! Anyone who uses it just remember to report as much as u can, it really does help others!!

Good app however does have a rather annoying fault. I use this app on a daily basis and I can't fault the Police/Speed camera updates and the user update screen is easy to use but it does crash a lot and normally and the most inconvenient time. Today it crashed twice during a three hour journey and by crashing I mean the program ends so you have to restart and then re-enter you destination admittedly you can do it from the memory but still very annoying. Like any navigation app it is very battery hungry so always use while charging.

Since last week there is a problem with the app, tried on multiple phones it simply won't work...it is stuck, doesn't navigate as required, doesn't find the position...tried it getting from Vienna to Romania and around Romania..no luck, not working.. it is a problem with the vignetts. If I travel from Austria to Romania and have selected that i have the austrian vignette, but not the hungarian, it avoids toll roads(highways) in hungary...this is bot optimal. there should be maybe a prompt..

Long time Wazer and after just buying a new car which supports Android Auto, I was able to use Waze and test the functionality in the car. I'm not impressed at all and prefer to use Google Maps. The pinned advertisements on my screen are intrusive and DANGEROUS. This is a pathetic attempt the advertise to drivers which can be distracting and annoying. Until Waze removes the advertisements, I cannot ever recommend this product. I would much rather pay to remove ads then to have no option.
it's good for travel thanks waze guiding me up to the last drop

I use WAZE all tge tine. Mostly Waze provides perfect directions and cautionary notifications. Sometimes however, I have found 1sf time directions get a bit skewed and Waze ends up taking me in circles back to where I began or where I should have stopped miles ago. For examples,. This happened today and it happened last week going to a funeral parlor I had never been to. Waze took me 20 minutes too far east before it told me to get off at the next exit.
replyContent: Hi Sheri, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We appreciate your review. If you run into any navigation issues like this again, please reach out to us for help. Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It takes too long to update your scores and standings. Sometimes days go by without an update. No option for reporting an accident in opposite direction. No option for E85 or other fuels when entering fuel prices. I also keep getting messages saying I need a cell phone signal to update fuel prices when I can clearly see that I have all 5 bars on my cell phone indicator.

The concept of the app is great, but, the UI is so heavily cluttered with information it's crazy. When you initially set it up you need to tweak some settings so that you get a clearer view of the road - showing other wazers on the app, like, really? I find it overwhelming at times when you just want to see a clean map!! Do like the live traffic and the fact the map can update showing a real time view of the situation ahead. Navigation wise it's OK, Google Maps normally uses the more 'conventional' and straight forward directions whereas this will take you on a joyride of shortcuts if you choose to. Hardly use the reporting feature as I'm so focused on driving on the road but I use this app in conjunction with my car sat nav to get those traffic updates. Route direction and planning can be adjusted and on the whole the big buttons make it easy to use. Find it odd how closing the app keeps it running in the background and you need to manually close it using the power button?!?

I've used Waze for a while and it was good, but lately it has been horrible. It reroutes to longer slower routes, but when you ignore the change it continues to reroute to the bad route for quite some time. We had left Des Moines for northern WY and it tried to reroute through Nebraska instead of SD. We ignored reroute, but it kept trying to send us through Nebraska for an hour, to the point that after driving for 2 hrs the total drive time was more than when we left Des Moines. Back to gmaps.

used to be a great app. love the concept and to be able to interact with other wazer but the app has went down hill. I really hope you fix it. It's my choice over other apps. But if I were to find a app that does the same things your is supposed to do I would dump your app because of all the issues. I think when google took over is when the app went downhill. sad update 4/13 finally work g again. 071319 still doesn't show the route end up switching over to Google maps. please fix it.

Does not stay connected to Android Auto when phone goes into sleep mode. Used to be easy to fix in settings but this option seems not to be available in the Android version anymore. Found it buried in phone app permissions but it make no a bit of difference, this resulted in u sage driving I had to constantly take pmy phone out of sleep mode to get any directions. Will be uninstalling

Cannot log into my account. Terrible UX and experience. Just as bad as Google Maps. Constantly sends me through dangerous intersections instead of sending me the way that I want to go no matter how many times I told it that I don't want to take certain routes. What are more it constantly sends me the most ridiculous ways instead of the direct way. Jesus Christ MapQuest was better!
replyContent:
Hi Melissa, we‚Äôre disappointed to hear you are having routing issues. We'd like to hear more  details about this. To best assist, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze would have been the greatest navigation app if it wasn't for the constant notification of "Red light camera reported ahead" at every major intersection. I have disabled all notifications and put the app on mute, yet Waze continues to remind me of the fact that every intersection in my city has a red light camera, pausing my music app in the process. Who the heck runs a red light, and why aren't we allowed to shut this rediculous announcements up?!

Disappointed. Routing is somewhat suspect, at least in the UK, and the App is no good for electric vehicles, no detail about charge points hence planning long runs is unnecessarily complicated. Tends to send you down near impassable narrow country lanes in the interests of a "fast" route or Motorways that you know will have major traffic problems. City navigation is also poor and no 3d buildings to help with orientation.

Too laggy. it takes forever to calculate a route, even if the destination is on the same road about 10 meters away, not due to poor connection either. also the "car" doesn't accurately follow your actual location, it lags a few seconds while google maps works fine on the same device - not gps issue. if you change direction and start driving, the speedometer accurately registers your speed however the "car" on the app remains stationary for about 15 seconds of driving. same issue on other devices

Have been using waze for years now, it's become part of my husband and my routine unlock carüëâstart carüëâseat belt üëâset up waze&spotifyüëâput in reverse and go. Suggestions: Be able to place warning icon on map other than where you first tap the icon. If I'm driving, notice an unmarked issue (police car hidden) unless I see the police ahead of time and have it ready to submit or take hand off wheel to mark as I'm passing the situation I'm reporting, the icon position on the map is inaccurate.

went connected with Pandora, I NEVER want to see the black Pandora "Accessory" splash screen...like never...please remove it when tryijg to get traffic updates and directions where I need to go. Otherwise the app is good. I do wish there were less buttons to push to report things on the road, and the carpool reminds are annoying. I already to carpool with ny family, so I won't be taking on strangers. Give me the option to opt out.

Lots of useful features that are missing in other GPS apps, such as road speed limit, speedo and warning. Community-based info and broadcast facility which is truly inspired. My criticism is that the UI is not very intuitive, with buttons in weird places or sometimes not there at all. The voice selection screen doesn't play a short sample either, which I think is a necessity. Configurable colours and fonts ought to be available for the map display. However, a very good app.

Amazing app wish I would have installed long time ago does so many useful things I never would have even thought about before best easiest user friendly gps system that I've ever used. And tons of settings that you can change that normal ones don't give you an option for like the recording voices for your directions and being able to link music to the app that works along with it.

It repeatedly fails to redirect away from stand stills caused by accidents. Useless! Today was the last straw! It told me to take a highway that was blocked by an accident miles and miles long. It is only good to tell you that you are screwed! Cannot be trusted. Google maps is perhaps the better option.

We almost got into accident because of this app since I need to close the advertisement that keeps on popping and covers the entire screen so I cannot focus on driving, and we also missed most of the turns because of this. The ads are very frequent and it's already annoying.

no gps I have used Waze for years! 3 weeks ago this app lost gps and I have tried everything. it is now the most useless app on my phone. It cant find me, it shows random routes and the ETA is nowhere close. today I tried one more time and had to pull over and go to gmaps because I was literally lost. i wrote for help and they insist they can't reproduce as if it is user error. really? Ive been a 2-3x/day user for 5 years. i KNOW how to use it.

Love it! Best navigation app ever. I travel out of town quite intensively and use it for every trip...love all the police alerts and last night was my best experience yet! I was traveling through West Virginia in route to Kentucky and got an alert 30 minutes prior that there was standstill traffic due to an accident and I was instantly rerouted to a detour. initially I was skeptical but I did it...even saw the accident and the backup traffic and saved 45 min or more off my trip at 2AM! Pleased!

Used to work great, but starting a few weeks ago, it has barely functioned. App constantly loses connection, or says that there is no network connection. GPS keeps lagging, routes keep shutting down & it's not keeping up w/ alerts, turns or where I actually am anymore at all and has gotten worse over last couple weeks. I am using through my Android auto app in my car and wondering if recent Android update might have caused the issue. Either way it's completely non-functional now. Pls fix!

Currently I'm getting no assistance on why this app when connected to Android auto is providing no GPS location! Began two months ago. Before then- worked fantastic!!! Now everytime I plug it in to mirror, I'm lucky to get accuracy for 2min at a time. Stand alone on the phone works great. Please fix! BTW Google maps works when connected to AA.

I like the app. I use this when I was in UK and whenever I go outside of Korea. But quite simply, it is unusuable in Korea. It gives me incorrect directions, i.e. telling me to go straight when there is no signal to go straight, etc etc. Had the same issue while using OSM. I like Waze, but I gotta use KakaoNavi while I'm staying in Korea. Any chance that you can fix the issue?

App has become very unreliable in Malaysia. This is my experience over the past year or so. I have reinstalled app many times and changed my phone (to a flagship, hence not a phone limitation) during this period. Constantly unable to search locations and navigate. Always receive 'something went wrong & Try again', especially during peak hours. Takes about 2 min to set up navigation vs. 10 seconds on Google maps. Almost as though Waze has insufficient bandwidth/ server capacity in the country.

Waze New version is getting slow response rather than the prior version. Directions shown confusing and must take router many times in order to get the right way. It looks waze new version is not suit proper for traffic and roads in Indonesia. It always shown detour moreover some roads which are block due to project, waze determined it right.. Please kindly to fix it up
replyContent: We're sorry to hear about your issue, Irsan. Please send us a private message on Facebook with the details and we'd be happy to investigate further. Thank you for the feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Would of given 5 stars in the past but lately it's been freezing and saying NO GPS signal, so I have to pull up and restart my whole phone! Also I've noticed it hasn't been taking me the quickest routes lately, seems to be throwing me into the deepest possible traffic it can find. Normally prefer to use over Google maps but I've had no choice but to start using them instead. Hopefully you guys sort out the bugs and give us an update soon. Ps. Should compensate us with some free score points lol
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this GPS issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Reinstalling and signing in stalls. Won't go forward from the "Yes it's me!" when I refuse to allow my contacts to be shared with Waze. I'll uninstall it again unless this is rectified soon. Simply not worth the bother. Only reinstalled it to link it with TuneIn Radio Pro in the first place. Google Maps is so much better and both are owned by Google in any case.

Doesn't speak notifications while on the phone. It did when I first installed it, but now it's quiet which leaves me to constantly look down to ensure I'm going the right way. Now it will exit once I leave out of the app.. I wish it would would like Google maps mad run in the background while using other applications üò†. I find myself using both apps just in case Waze timesout... Such a great app if it would work like it should.

Not 100% sure but I have noticed that it consistently priorities those routes which present more adds, even if the route is rather difficult or busier with compared to all other available alternatives. FYI I have correct settings. Google maps provide better routes almost every single time in all conditions. I have compared it with Google maps & my personal daily experience.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback, Syed! We'd love to hear more about your app experience and help with any issues or questions you may have. Please feel free to send us a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: When fully working on Android auto the app is great, but I find it has more glitches especially with speed indicator not always showing up or working via the app

Had to reinstall app due the its ability to function correctly. Once reinstalled I entered my phone number, then the code sent to me, then saw my account. Clicked "yes, that is me" it the. Told me that my account didn't exist!?! After trying a few more time and SEEING MY ACCOUNT it then erased everything saying I have no point as if it was a fresh account. Update: Only thing worst than this app is your support team. Please reread my email before responding again.

why my map disappeared in some places ? street and everything disappeared... and after go out off this locations, everything get right back, it's not about network or gps problem,becuase there is no error and i test it on diff phone on this special locations and everything is ok, test it with many solution like clear cache or reinstall app (even proxyüòÅ) any solution to fix it ?
Very convenient and useful

So, the "+": 1) It's convenient to see police, cameras and all other stuff on map. Google maps doesn't have this. That's it, this is all "+" :) "-": 1) Map SUCKS. Really. If u working as a delivery guy - I wouldn't suggest you this app, address coming up wrong, a lot of times. 2) Then it's more than 2-3 lines on road, it shows just 1 (there is no multiple lines, but it would be nore convenient...), so there are a lot of lines and it shows just: "make a left".. 3) Forget about destination sides

Traveling from Baltimore to Arlington, this genius app brought me through stop and go traffic in DC two times. I've never screamed at my phone louder than when I use waze. Often times the routes seem catered towards highway driving and busy roads as opposed to backroads... Definitely not optimal! +1 star for the amazing boy band voice is amazing.

Nearly involved in a terrible MVA because this app led me into opposite lane though i set to avoid difficult intersection. I am not familiar with Australia road that's why i need GPS; in this case, Waze is not reliable at all. Map is hard to read, voice indication is hard to follow, Need someone next me to read a map and guide me. Additionally, small roads are not existing either. No way to set a destination because i only know the destination only. Cute but disgusting
replyContent: We're so sorry to hear about your experience. Could you please message us on Facebook with more details about the route? We'd like to investigate further. Thank you for bringing these issues to our attention. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Use to be an AMAZING APP...until you married up with Googleü§î. I have a strong internet signal, BUT, I keep getting an error stating Waze can't connect to internet as of 10.24.20. Waze you've let Google hoodwink you & once very satisfied end users. I find it interesting that Google Maps is working, WAZE is NOT! Get RID of Google 4...5‚òÜüôã

content: This is very use full app for driving allover the world

- search results not in geographical order... Let that sink in, I mean for a GPS app to show local, next state, next county, local, 2 States over, ... - as if search reaults weren't confusing enough, ads take up half your screen as soon as you stop, -now, when you get close, you can't confirm you're where you want to be because Waze wants you to take a pic of your destination. Oh how quickly Waze went from being helpful to making you feel like a product.

Please think for countries that the comprehensive system does not allow access to many programs. You are our country of waze just with the filter that wastes a lot of time. Meanwhile, excellent excellent excellence.

Waze app is totally cool..I downloaded it a few times to compare it to Google maps..the only thing I didnt like about Waze is that anytime it tells me to exit and I dont it does not recognize that I am still in the highway and not the feeder road like Google maps can..other than that I give thumbs up..but for now I find Google maps to be more accurate..
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Johnny! We're always looking for ways to improve our product and your Waze experience. If you'd like to share ideas and/or feature requests, feel free to leave us a note in our suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I used to love this app for traffic management but now it is having GPS issues. It has difficulty determining my exact location, so it often misses turn instructions. Google Maps is tracking perfectly, so it's probably not a device issue or a satellite issue. If Google Maps had hazard reporting and cookie monster's voice, I would probably switch permanently.

It's a great app! Used it all the time when I lived in WA State & loved it!!! Between Waze & my Navigator I could find the places I needed to be & get there on time. Don't own a car now & that's my only reason for uninstalling the app. If I start driving again, I will definitely reinstall it!!!
Always show long road, with tolls

Paid user with 1 year experience with Waze app Positive: It works when you open up app in town with internet available, no problem. Nightmares: it doesn't work when you're trying to open the app out of town without internet available. It's dumb move and huge bummer. The app just show blue screen and then crashes.. you're just a sitting duck in the car with dark outdoors. If you're planning to drive long distance without restarting phone or accidentally closed app, this app is for you.

This app is really "creative" because it directs you through streets like you'd never imagine, all this to avoid traffic obstructions, the chief one being traffic. When I first used it, I found it too frustrating but perhaps because I have it on a better Smartphone that seems to have made the difference.

Waze used to be great, but now it has a lot of technical issues and I'm considering to switch back to Google Maps. 1. Takes a long time to calculate route. 2. Unable to find network or comes to an error even though my network works fine. 3. Shows that I'm on a wrong lane when I'm following the GPS correctly and goes into reroute mode after that. 4. Reroute takes so long and often causes to miss nearest turns. 5. Often crashes and exits automatically.

The app itself is very good, especially for couriers and taxi drivers. My reason for 2 stars is because there is no way to use night mode or dark mode, the normal interface causes screen burns especially on Samsung high end phones. Anyone with OLEAD screens be very careful if using it for more than 4 to 8 hours a day 7 or 6 days a week, you will see screen burns!

Was a great app, seems to still be as long as your not using a galaxy S8 or above, or using this thing on Android Auto. There is an effective "fix" which is disconnect the phone from AA and turn off power saving mode that will get you the navigation back but you will need a separate phone mount and charger but no play music....I contacted support and they basically told me to make sure I had my GPS enabled and also make sure I had my phone connected to the Android auto head unit. So no fix soon.

Was excited to accept the update today (4.51.1.1), believing that my issues were finally being addressed. Nope. Not even slightly. Anytime the map is visible, the whole phone continues to bog down and move extremely slowly, hanging and freezing. But if I go into any of the Waze settings screens, everything moves smoothly. Clearing data and/or reinstalling does nothing. Glad I had the presence of mind to backup an older version (4.39.0.4) that still runs smoothly. Going back to that. üëéüèø

12/19/19 - UPDATE: Seems bugs have been fixed - THANK YOU! Loving it again! This app worked GREAT on Android Auto until a few months ago & now it has become VERY UNRELIABLE. I thought it might be my phone, but now that I see other reviewers saying similar things, I also wanted to bring it up bc I loved this app until it started acting like this. It's so frustrating now, so PLEASE FIX IT!!!!

It's OK for navigation. Use it to see hazards and police. Since updating, I can no longer see shared drives properly. I see the planned route the friend is taking with arrival time and that's it. Used to see the friends icon and traveling. Can't send message to friend but can receive. If I share a drive, I have to keep my phone awake on Waze for it to stay linked or it disconnects when getting gas etc. and I take my phone in to pay. Can't be the background app.

This app really sucks. It doesn't work at all. Black screen freezes and don't navigate. Since update. This app need to be updated. Google maps shows option to avoid highways on android auto. Waze too much hassle. When driving can't be fiddling with take cord off charger on android auto to look for avoid highways in settings. Not safe Waze update the app for safety to choose on interface with android auto.

I want to say that this is the best GPS and navigation app ever, but I can't. I have tried over and over to get this app to do what I want it to but it has too many features that do not serve my needs. On my drive into work I use waze to avoid traffic but it will usually direct me into traffic on a different route. There is a setting to avoid difficult intersections, when I set a specific intersection as difficult it would find other paths to drive me into that same intersection.
replyContent: Hi Liam, thanks for your feedback. Since Waze is a crowd-sourced real-time navigation app, it's possible to get a non-optimal route. But if this is reoccurring despite correct settings for the same place and time, please submit a ticket with the route details: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9557145?hl=en

content: Have been using Waze for about 5 years and always been happy with it. However fir the last month or so it has this annoying glitch when it's showing all traffic announcements from the area despite I have ticked to only show the announcements on route. Is there any fix to that? I have the latest version and have deleted, reinstalled, cleared cache etc, nothing helps
replyContent: Hey Dzintars, thank you for bringing this issue to our attention. We'd like to look into it further, can you please message us on Facebook with more details and a screenshot of the issue? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app used to be great, but as of a few updates ago it stopped connecting to GPS. "No GPS- Showing approximate location" no matter where I am. I had to detour myself 30 minutes out of the way because Waze couldn't connect to GPS and I didn't know that the freeway was closed for several exits. Tried uninstalling, etc. etc.... Nothing worked. Guess it's time to find a new navigation app. So disappointed.
replyContent:
Hey, Katie! If you're having trouble with your GPS, we'd love to help you fix that. Take a look at this guide for more details on resolving this problem: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051?hl=en Let us know how that goes.

content: Waze how has been my navigator Choice while driving Lyft. But recently it has been offering really poor route navigation. Using the taxi profile, l enabled "easy intersection" feature. It's still tries to have me take difficult intersections cross Main arterials. While using this app for Lyft driving, it is having me take out of the way routes causing passengers to question the navigation and my professionalism.

This app truly used to be brilliant. I used to recommend Waze to everyone. But since Google have bought it the app has become questionable. Just today I witnessed it guide multiple drivers (including myself) to a dangerous off-limits road. It's just disappointing. Before Google, the main thing Waze got wrong was pronunciation. I hope the original team make another independent navigation app!

the ultimate GPS carpool locating people in your area or the area in which you are choosing to go including restaurants stores and much more speedometer as well as the radar detection from the help of other app users. If you need a ride you can easily locate others if you are willing to give her a ride you can easily find others to help. It saved me a great deal I had got the app and my daily trip of 35 mile commute easily found a carpool thanks

Have been using Waze for years but since the update I HATE IT. This banner stays at the bottom of the screen forcing you to choose a destination and when you put it in landscape, it takes up a huge part of the map!! What were you guys thinking???? I thought updates were supposed to IMPROVE things??!!
replyContent: Hi Kimberly, thank you for the feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze.
