content: The app does not work properly. It always cause me to lost. Always took longer route that's having traffic jam. üòÉ

Crashes or freezes Android Auto on my 2020 Subaru Forester every time I try to connect it via Android Auto to my Samsung Galaxy S10. Every other app that says it is Android Auto compatible works fine. I constantly get a message telling me that Waze hasn't been setup for the first time yet on my device, but I literally use Waze all the time in stand-alone mode in my work truck. Everything has its most updates, I'm using the cable that came with the phone, I don't see why this doesn't just work.
replyContent: Hi, Josh! We'd love to help you resolve this problem. Please click here to submit more information about the issue you're experiencing with Waze and Android Auto: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I have multiple routes I can take when leaving my home for work, choosing the wrong one can add up to 20 min. 4 mos ago the Waze app started giving me this "ROUTING SERVER TIMEOUT" error and won't give me my route until I'm almost 1/2 way to work...which does me no good. I have to use another, more reliable, app to help me get to work now. BTW that popular GPS app has no problem opening and giving me a route, so not my phone or signal. It's a shame, I had preferred Waze...when it works.

It used to work great. Clear app, it shows speeds limit and driving speed, communicated events on the way. When GPS signal is good. But some how since October, this GPS signal does not work anymore properly anymore. (Seems fine on Google maps.). Uninstalling and re install did not help either. I can not trust information to arrive anymore ahead of events. App resets itself 3 time ms in 40 mins drive and positioning can be updated 3-4 times in that interval

It's not too bad. Disconnects occasionally, or can't find location, even while the phones connection is fine, and it has a lot of trouble with long distances. I occasionally have to swap over to Google maps for longer trips. But Waze has a better UI and provides more data, which is probably part of it's functionality issue. Like, it tries to preload every accident and shouldered car between one state to another. But it certainly works overall.

Great functionality.. Good to have quick reporting of traffic & other aspects. Lags in ability to accurately predict quantum of traffic & this correctly estimating time to destination. Google maps much more authentic in that aspect. Another aspect, doesn't accurately capture the exact vehicle orientation at the start... & you may end up heading the wrong way for the first few hundred metres... Needs to be faster in recognizing once the GPS has moved few metres

The new function of the guided lane with highlight arrows is great but I i find that the go straight on display is unnecessary and could be misleading. There's also some bug like lagging and early turning prompt when the turn is 300m away. This occurred only after the new update. please fix these issues as a GPS thats not functioning properly can pose serious danger on the roads. Thanks

the app is not as reliable as google maps. i thought they're both belong to the same parent?! when searching for directions, the app always says "opps, something went wrong". took a long time to load directions, but when i use google maps the directions can be loaded instantly. This means it has nothing to do with slow data speed but rather Waze's server problem! Please fix this and be up to par with Google maps!

Edit: I am uninstalling. I have had it. I enjoyed the fact that the app shows points of interest, roadworks etc but when it made me miss my appointment with my surgeon that was almost the end. For crying out loud the app took me all over town down ridiculous streets in the middle of freaking nowehere past my destination and tried to take me to the other side of town!! Yes! I put the right address in! Yesterday was the last straw. I entered my destination and began (knowing exactly the quickest route and where to go) and almost immediately it wanted me to go down down bloody side streets in the wrong direction! I'm a programmer so before you start thinking UE forget it. Don't contact me, don't ask me for more information. I'm done. Was great - now unusable. SM-N975F
replyContent: Hi Felicity, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this map issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Using waze for a couple of years. Good but there are some annoying issues with the latest versions. If you put a destination and then close the screen, and don't start moving within 2 min, waze will close. Yes I've set all permissions and to allow runing in background and not to optimize for battery usage and same. For a motorcyclist this is super annoying since you put your destination, gear up and leave and then realize your not hearing any instructions. Same issue with my co-worker as well.

Decent app, but the ads during GPS navigation are dangerous, and irresponsible.  Also navigation info passed from other apps (such as Drivemode) is treated only as a location search, forcing the driver to stop, and manually begin navigation.  This is light weight, so good for my phone, but Google Maps is easier, and SAFER to use.

Though overall this app does its job well (baring the occasional crash mid-route), I am incredibly frustrated by the voice command feature, which I use heavily to remain hands-free. Some of the pain points include : - Needs me to repeat a few times before it registers. - Doesn't register voice input unless you wait 3 seconds after the beep. - ask for confirmation, even when it accurately heard 99% of the time. - doesn't handle interruptions as well as alexa or Google assistant

Thought this would be good. But annoying to enter adresses. Hard to get it running, meaning entering and saving addresses. Don' t really like the interface. Please keep working on it. I know as it matures, it will be a great Gmaps replcement. Will try it again maybe next year.
replyContent:
Hi Steve, thank you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about the issues you're experiencing, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: App now unusable! The latest update has rendered this app useless. Constantly loses location, shows black screens and restarts all over the place. Just what you need when you are approaching a critical road junction! Ridiculous! Am now going to have to dig out my old Tomtom as I can no longer depend on this app.

The map is horrible to read. Make the colors more vibrant. use blue red and purple like pilot vision. Get rid of the emoji heads! Make the map actually zoom on your vehicle. The Arrow moves too slow to your actual location. Voice activate zoom in map or zoo out. To report an incident or warning also make voice activated... say "Waze Assistance" for voice activation..

UPDATE: I have determined the map/GPS issues are from an update to Android Auto. The screen blacks out and locks, then the location services stop or sleep. When you touch the screen, location services start again and the maps update. The GPS service does not run in the background when using Android Auto as of the Oct 31st update. The issues are not Waze and I have adjusted my review accordingly.

I prefer WAZE over g-maps for many reasons. The alerts are a great. The interaction with other wazers and the ability to see them on the road is a great touch. Ability to make side trips to get grub or other needs and continue on. Taking pictures of the destination for other wazers. To warn drivers following of tlroad hazards, heavy traffic and jams. Emergeny service and police railroad crossings and a whole lot more.

mostly good! occassional glitch but not often. I prefer Waze to any other GPS I have used--and I've tried them all. I always come back to WAZE. It is smart and accurate unless unexpected construction. I appreciate the ability to report road closures and other things that affect driving. Thank you Waze!

Terrible...just terrible. I live in LA so theres alot of traffic. I kid you not, Waze will pick the longest hardest weirdest route to save you 30 seconds and In fact it just ends up taking 20 min longer. I loooove how when Waze gives you a wierd route and youre like "that doesnt make sence, ill just go the normal way" and when you do and the route is recalculated your ETA actually goes down.......what???? Why were you giving me the longest route? Why are there never cops where pins say they are?
Wonderful navigation system. Although I'd like how to provide further detailed analysis or updates on real time road conditions.

Up until about 2 days ago it was 5 star but now on Android auto it won't show correct location, map won't auto zoom, alerts don't appear. Checked settings, reinstalled and still the same. Google maps in same car still works the same. ***Update Jan 5, for the last few days it's been working again so back to 5 stars***

Great app. Works brilliantly. Would be great if we could add KNOWN police/mobile speed camera sites that stay there on to the map to warn drivers to keep speed down. Also adding parking/rest sites on roads would be great. Especially as the vans like hiding on parking spots and on top of bridges or behind them on single and dual carriageways and motorways.

My go-to for going anywhere. As great as it may be, it is not perfect. 1) As an EV driver, why am I forced to choose a fuel grade and have Gas Stations as a top shortcut on Android Auto. 2) HOV lane, I need only know where I am exiting highway. On a regular basis I'm told to exit HOV only to enter a mile ahead. In some cases I fight my way through lanes of traffic to get to HOV only to find out I need to exit highway in a quarter mile. Extremely. Frustrating.

I don't know what happened to this app, it was great but lately it tells me it'll take me X time to arrive and it's never even close, it can say 20 minutes and I'll arrive after 1 hour and 20 Minutes, it happens again and again on the same and on different rodes. And another thing, in traffic it just makes you drive in circles, so you'll feel that maybe you didn't stand in traffic! (It kept me stuck in traffic for 4 hours one time until I stopped listening to it)
replyContent: Hi John, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze was great, a few years back. Now it's gimmicky (I don't need it to connect to Spotify or earn "points"), doesn't work consistently (no gps found), it's permissions are worrisome (enable access to Contacts to work?), and the UI is cluttered (it's always been, though). No longer useful.

It is better than Google maps at avoiding traffic but still very weak routing algorithm compared to non free apps. You will still stuck in traffic for no reason when there are empty roads next to you. Moreover intersections on highways are very badly illustrated and very difficult to know where to go sometimes. For a free app is perfect but far off professional grade ones.

2/18/2021 Louisiana, Roads have been closed for 3 days due to a freeze. The roads started opening along with businesses, waze did not know what roads where open. I opened Google Maps and it was on point. Its been a good run Waze, but the addition of ads and you not being on point is not doing it for me anymore. Google is seeing to my needs.
replyContent: Hi Jacob, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I think this app is good but it needs a lot of updates. It give you directions and re route you but don't tell you why it is doing so. You just know your route was changed and the later you see it was an accident or construction. Just let me know why and give me the option to say yes reroute or stay on the same path.
You can map chat,can choose to be be visible to other drivers carpool, and get police alerts and traffic alerts & more!

Just started using this. I like some of the features but there really needs to be a home button that let's you access your saved places and history so you dont have to close and reopen the app. Once it automatically puts you in map mode you can't get out unless you close the app.

Best GPS app I've had, I love the alerts and how you can edit what types of roads you want to avoid and such. Very reliable and it warns you way before you have to turn. Unlike google maps it tells you where your first turn is instead of saying "go west" and the turn doesnt just pop up out of no where.

It's crashing. I tried it on different phones, different occasions, in time period of half year. If it doesn't crash, it freezes. It's pretty annoying in the middle of heavy fraffic in unknown city, no matter how good the navigation is. So, it's uninstalled and never again.
Very bad apps compared to google maps..

Overall it's a good app, but my google pixel 2 phone, seems that recently the direction icon will not point the way your driving down the road. It actually points up and goes sideways. I can unplug it from my vehicle and plug it back in and sometimes it fixes it. But it's not my vehicle as I can run the app without being plugged into my vehicle and the screen is showing the same error on my phone.
replyContent: Hey there, Robert! We're sorry to hear that this issue is occurring. We'd like to investigate this further, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Speedometer and warnings!!

Love it!!! Update: this little guy is awesome. I can type in my destination and it pops right up. The only negative thing I've had is that on a couple occasions it has taken me somewhere way outta the way by about 10-15 miles, to where we had to stop and ask for directions or go to Google maps. Other than this little glich it's amazing!
This obviously is the best app as everyone says. I wish/hope if voice commands become available to report and confirm incidents while driving.

Was good, until the last update. They did an update this week and ever since it's been searching for networks constantly,even when I have full bars. Also it has changed some personal setting, very annoying. I'll add more stars if they fix their update. Update: Their support got back with me pretty quickly but everything they suggested i had all ready done. In frustration i uninstalled and downloaded again. That has fixed the problem, proving it was their side and not my carrier's.

it's incredibly annoying. Voice commands are locked to the US which is a major Dick Small move. Let me activate and deactivate them, don't region lock them. Account security is more invasive than the USA on a small country with reserves of oi... I mean human rights issues.. Not only do they want my phone number but they also check my contacts. I have 2 phones and I can't link my account on both because of different contacts. The only good thing are cop markers...

For all its positives, the fact that I cant download offline maps for an an area is the flaw I can't live with. Where I travel, data service is sketchy. Lost signal and map stops updating..... another issue: Why does it always say I found you account, then error and tell me to setup a new account ? all this after I am texted a code to verify who I am ?

Best GPS app there is when it comes to traffic conditions. Google maps is a little better when it comes to address pin-point accuracy and and side of the road information (not enough of a difference to matter much unless you are a ride share driver), but for general driving for medium to long trips and navigating traffic conditions - WAZE is the best there is and it's FREE. Don't waste your $$ on a Garmin or Tom-Tom, the WAZE app is all you need and better than both in my opinion.

the suggested directions are, often, the longest, when it's rainy it's almost impossible to use, if you decide to take another dorection that seems better, the app try to bring you back on the route calculated at the beginning. I'm keep using the app only because you can check the speed limits on the streets, and it advice you if there are speed cameras UP: thank to your directions, I'm ended up in a no traffic zone and to get out from there I had to make an outlaw turn. Useless and dangerous.

I absolutely love using Waze!I really like how it is the social media of navigating around your local areas and or anywhere you might be traveling but what I do not like is how sometimes it does not give you various routes based on traffic or based on distance and another thing that I really don't like is it takes forever and tells you when to turn at the very last second.... Other than those things I think the app is fantastic bucking use a little bit of improvement.......

Just ok. Biggest miss - No obvious controls to pause or cancel navigation especially while driving. Google had severely limited controls, if any, for this app. Huge window on map sometimes covers up areas i want to see, can't move window. Can't shut off the #@$* audio instructions, especially while driving. Nothing like having Google, Waze, car & phone all competing for the audio at the same time!

Pretty good, but for the love of all that is holy add a multi-stop feature to planned drives and make the multi-stop feature more accessible when planning an immediate drive. It also has issues syncing to Google calendar, and none of my events show up at all. Otherwise it's pretty great! I love that it has a speedometer (very useful when our dash lightbulb burnt out unexpectedly!) and connects to music so you don't have to switch apps while driving.

Use it everyday for work, but when I updated it there is no longer a speed camera selection.you can mark dead animals and debris on the road which I really don't care about but not the speed cameras anymore. Thats the main reason I got this app. Will be going elsewhere unless its put back on. I do 1,000+ miles a week and you took away the best feature on the whole navigational system.
replyContent: Hi Charlie, thank you for your feedback. The option to report a speed camera is no longer available in the app. If there's a missing stationary speed camera, please let us know the precise location and any additional information, and we'll look into it. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I wish I could give it negative stars as this app sucks. It doesn't give clear cut directions, takes you through every toll and the long way. Whoever gives Waze it's directions has as much directional skills as a 3 year old. It's frustrating and doesn't do anything for you. I suggest google maps or take your chances with getting lost they are both equally bad options.

A few quirks because it dont always show which side of the road the destination is. Always show in center of road which is irritating living in a heavy populated city. Furthermore the advertisements is irritating and annoying. The banner stay up tooooo long obscuring view of directions. And staying on pandora malfunctions more than it should. Have to constantly open it up lagging the performance of the app which links with towbook, another irritating thing. Otherwise i like the app in general

Uninstalled it, was an awesome app. The speed shown, told me about speed traps when not using it a nav. Wish Google maps did that. But the issue is, since the update Android 11. Waze would work and not work. Hit and miss. I travel a lot, same route. So I use it for proper speed and the traps. Fix it! I rather have waze than Google.
replyContent: Hi Ervin, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this update issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Much better than Google Maps, in my opinion. I love that I can report things/hazards in real time with just a few taps and that I can see the reports of other users. Very user friendly and map/route data has always been accurate, thus far, in my experience.
Love the app. Much better than you know who!

Annoying as all get-out. WHILE I'M DRIVING, it keeps telling me it's going to shut down. When I'm in traffic, it's not a good time to babysit a whiny app. Uninstalled. Anything good about WAZE is outweighed by an annoyance people have been screaming about for at least two years. EDIT: the developers asked me to send them a private message on Facebook -- a sewer I have no intention of ever using.
replyContent: Hi Fred, thanks for bringing this issue to our attention. We'd like to look into this further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with more details and a screenshot of the issue? Thanks again! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Previous problems with not picking up a GPS signal seem to have rectified by itself...not sure it's anything I did! The app is functioning well and keeps me updated about the best route to take, based on any delay causing factors. It does though, take me to odd/difficult right turns with traffic both sides and refuses to use a shorter route at some one or two specific places, otherwise, it is perfect. Oh...and yes, it seems to permit saving only limited number of 'favourites', for some reason!?
replyContent:
Hi Mathew, thanks for the review. Adjusting your phone's location settings might help with the GPS issue. Simply follow the instructions on this guide: tinyurl.com/p7j9m7o
For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Superb for beating traffic. It always gets me there fastest. I only have 2 reservations - one cannot at least download the map part to save some data and it is insufficiently customised for the South African market. For example, our fuel prices are government regulated and the same price. But Waze wants me to find "the cheapest gas". No such thing here.

Latest update crashes when car mode is on. Looks like Waze released an unstable version. It's really such a shame because this has been such great  navigation software for years. If this latest version (early January) refuses to load (brief flash, no errors and Waze not running) then it's most likely that you're using a car dock application which turns on car mode. Uncheck the option to force car mode in your car dock application and Waze should return to running normally.   Waze - can you please look into this oversight? Not everyone wants to run Android Auto and custom car home applications have been around since Android 4. Thanks.
Keep telling me they cant find my route. WAZE IS PISSING ME OFF
replyContent:

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Usually reliable, but it just had me go around in a loop for 10 minutes all to end up where I originally was.

content: This is a good navigation app. But there are several minuses for me: there are no multiline road support and sometimes it can't build a route to a long distance. For example, I've tried to build a route from Krak√≥w, Poland to Makarska, Croatia and I couldn't do it for some reason.

I've had so many issues with Waze using Android Auto on my Galaxy S10 5G in the past few months that I gave up using Waze. Waze kept either not GPSing correctly or didn't GPS at all, coming up with "No network connection" (yet my streaming music is playing correctly) and/or a blank white or black map. Tried multiple fixes but nothing worked and same issues occurred with different vehicles. Google maps doesn't have any of these issues

Go back to normal app quit behavior!! Later versions of app are rigged to trick you into letting it run in background all the time, draining your battery and privacy. It has its own non-standard quit button now hidden on a side screen, and it's buggy. Standard Android quit method does not work. This is an obnoxious nuisance.

Used to be good. And then one night it was spouting out ridiculous directions that weren't real, telling me to turn on streets that weren't there. I sent numerous help requests, and was told to check with the community editors who apparently make the routes. I kept telling them I was getting directions that were nonsense, and there was no way somebody would have actually made these routes, but the help desk was useless. Deleted the app and have gone back to Google Maps instead.

Dropped another star. Keep getting big issues with Waze tracking my location. Drove for 5 miles down a motorway with it having little idea where I was. Not much use when it is supposed to be navigating my journey. This needs to be seriously looked into especially when Google Maps and VW Nav both have no issues in this area.
replyContent: Hi David, we're here to help. Have you tried these GPS troubleshooting steps? tinyurl.com/yabujh54 If the issue continues after completing these steps, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can investigate further. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Love the app, but it continues to run after I close out of it, which is a total drain to my battery. After closing, the app notification remains and I'm unable to turn it off by the available Switch Off option. It does nothing when I click on the notification. I have to actually reopen the app and close it again to get it to finally shut off. However, if I'm in a hurry it's easy to forget to go through this extra step and the app drains my battery in no time.

Love the app #1 for daily use. Love the car stopped, police reported, and speed limit notifications. But can't give it more than 3 stars.ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è I ride motorcycles. It's nearly impossible to input alerts while riding. Makes me think about the people using this while driving. They might as well be texting or updating FB, in regards to my safety. One second of a drivers eyes off the road, kills Riders. Drivers already "didn't see" the bike they wrecked into. I see too many close calls due to phones
replyContent:
Hi Kris, thank you for sharing your concerns with us. We completely agree with you that safety should be a priority when driving. You can submit reports safely while driving by using the Google Assistant option. More info here: tinyurl.com/vgvbuat
For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Not a bad GPS app but it has some issues. First and worst is having an ad pop up and cover half the screen when you're trying to see where you're going. Second and kind of funny, it calls WA, 'Western Australia' instead of 'Washington' when I'm getting directions in Washington state.

It has been good. It has given me a few good shortcuts. Today it was terrible, the arrow was pointing the wrong way, most of the time it thought I was off the road and often it thought I was on the wrong road. Added 10 minutes to a 25 minute journey. Switched to Google maps which worked fine. Can't use this app if it's not reliable.

Waze is a great app, with excellent functionality and routing. But then they brought in paid points of interest such as McDonalds' restaurants and petrol stations. Ok, annoying but I can deal with that. Now there's constant banner ads that try to direct you to nearby businesses, taking up 1/3 the screen. It destroys the experience. See you later Waze.

TERRIBLE APP!! it literally puts you on the route with the must traffic!! google maps is much much MUCH BETTER!! yesterday i had to sit in an hour and a half of traffic in the morning and two hours and ten minutes of traffic in the afternoon to get to and from work!! i googled Google maps and it took me 50 mins this morning. don't use waze!!! so Google maps all the way!!

Crashing. This thing works great for years but in the last month or two crashes continually. I think it is running in the background and then it crashes and is no longer there. I have uninstalled and reinstalled multiple times and I have given it all permissions available. I have removed from battery optimization.

No question..This app has helped me through some trying times on the rds...we travel a lot & has saved us with notifications, detours, side rds, hell back rds we thought would take us waaaaaaaaaay off track & out of the way because we knew the route we were taking, & traveled many many times lol But even then has never failed us...the alternative route it took us on to Florida landed us at our destination 20 min earlier than expected üòÉ Love it!! Keep modifying, we'll be here to support!
Just awful I tried to search up a place and I couldn't and I deleted the app and redownload and now I can't log back into my account and all my favorites places are gone thank you so much for that!

I live in Chile and i have had trouble with the routes that the app recommended, in the same day this happened: 1) it asked me go against the traffic in a highly dangerous main road 2) it took me to a cliff through a secondary road that was supposed to be faster, but it didn't lead to anywhere but possibly death. All this happened in one day, in between vi√±a del mar and re√±aca.

content: maps traffic status is not correct. The car on the map does not move if the waze application does not have focus. for ex in a split screen mode if we are running YouTube and waze side by side and we touch the you tube app, waze map navigation animation freezes and car stops moving, however the voice navigation keeps running but the animation stops.

My son and I were on a 5,000 mile motorcycle trip and my GPS system crashed.  I had Waze on my phone and began using it and it never failed us. Also, it never failed to avoid freeway travel,  which is what we wanted. Plus, it gave us speed limit and traveling speed. I will use Waze and forget about a gps system for the time being.

What is happening with this app? It used to be great but now it takes very long to find a route and when it does it seems to lose track of where I am, as if it looses connection to the satellites and can't reconnect and then gives me directions as if I was on a different road. I was using this very often but had to go back to Google Maps which is presently working better than waze.

I thought its just me until I read all the recent reviews only to realise its a global issue. Waze used to be good. Nowadays its taking too long to calculate. It doesn't work indoors and when I am out stopping at the roadside, it takes forever to load and always give error. I had to restart a few times. Wasting my time.

Seems to put me in the right and fastest direction everytime without taking me down roads that are closed, flooded, under construction, ect.....i used google maps forever till i gave this a shot and it definitely will never steer u in the wrong direction like google has fir me at times. My dashboard lights dont work right now either, so i cant see how fast im going at night without using a light to look at the speedometer, so what i truly love most is that it has a built in speedometer. Saved me

When I go into Android Auto on my cars display and select Waze the whole screen goes blank and no longer responds to anything. I waited over 5 minutes for something up happen and nothing ever did. If I would try and open the Waze app on my phone it would show the splash screen and the app would then immediately close. Eventually my car's display would reboot itself or I'd have to restart my car for the display to boot up again., If I selected Waze again the same thing would happen.

content: I used to use this app all the time a couple of weeks ago it was a fantastic app I just loved it. howevet, now when I try to utilize the app it won't even navigate for me; it gives me wrong directions and everything is all messed up on the app; maybe it has the coronavirus and it's delusional, so I have to uninstall it because it's no good for me anymore. this is really disappointing.

content: Once Great App Going Downhill Fast. Interface is so much better than Google maps, but Waze is no longer reliable. Frequently tells me to turn on location services when they're already on and set to high accuracy. Today kept saying waiting for network whole way home. was sending me in normal route, probably cached, even though that route was bumper to bumper. Switched to Google Maps and it correctly redirected me. The other day guided me to an intersection that doesn't exist.

This app is GREAT! AREAS FOR IMPROVEMENT: - Removing visual ads appearing on Small phone screens with small text. Can be extremely dangerous distraction while on road Especially if youre directionally challenged or anxious driver. SUGGESTION: Try few seconds audio ad instead or to display all ads After reached destination! - Please simplify process for multiple driving locations & use better details in describing the reached destination- is it on the Left or Right side? Google does this well

Worst app ever. If you live in the San Deigo area avoid at all costs. Has sent me on several wild goose chases that were so far out of my way I couldnt get to my appt on time, had to pay a $5 toll on top of it. Use Google maps instead and save yourself the trouble. Uninstalling it NOW!!!

Do not use this app. It is only useful for checking traffic but is very poor in giving direction. I was caught by traffic officer because of this app. The route is delay. The right turn direction i followed as instructed is not accurate. It happened to me twice on two different route. Two thumbs down for you. Use google maps instead of waze.

I like the app, but I'm giving it two stars because I think it makes driving more dangerous. They need to go further to minimize the number of times the screen needs to be tapped. "Ok waze" has never actually worked for me at all. If I ask it for directions, I've never been able to get them, simply, without having to stare at the screen and tap at least a few times. So how many people has this app killed?

It's okay. Great features like pins and alert customization, but missing features from other Navi apps. I also get constant server timeouts when plotting long trips (only 2+ hours), which means I need another Navi app open too if I still want to use Waze's pins, which is obnoxious and doesn't happen in Google Maps. Fix and add a few things and it'll be perfect. Also, options for truck drivers like height for low bridges, hazmat, parkways, and weigh stations would be excellent.

For the past six months or so, this app just has absolutely no idea where I am. I actually use it as a joke to show people for a laugh. I have precise location settings enabled for the app, I've reinstalled etc and Google Maps knows exactly where I am, but Waze will stick me anywhere between 50m - 5 miles in the wrong place almost every time. On rare occasions it will momentarily get my location right while driving, only to start glitching out and resetting constantly, making it utterly useless.
replyContent: Hey Jack, thanks for bringing this issue to our attention. We'd like to investigate further. To best assist, please message us on Facebook with all the details. Thanks again! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great, another app that alerts speeders where there's a speed trap... helping the very same idiots who cause accidents and bad traffic for speeding in the first place

It's GPS is horrible. Made me exit and re enter the highways around sydeny at every exit. Most painful experience iv had. Now I only use it for police detection but even that dosnt warn me correctly and expects me to have my phone in view when driving. App closes after 15 minuets on no activity as well making this app way to hands on when driving it's not very safe. Hardly use it any more

If you love being directed to recieving docks and closed locations, then this is the app for you! nothing better than spending 45 minutes driving on convoluted routes ("to avoid traffic") only to find that your destination is no longer in business or you've arrived at the receiving docks and not the front doors..
Most of the time, it changed the route suddenly for few seconds then come back to the original route without my car moving an inch!!!

Great app, use to be a better a couple of years ago when it took you on the back roads when needed. They still need to configure some things like when its OK to go on the main roads and take the back roads. As sometimes the main road will be clear and waze will still want to take you on the more indirect longer route. But its FREE so not bad!!

Doesnt do the one thing its supposed to. Everyone knows this app is inferior in every aspect to google maps. The only reason you would use this app is to redirect you around traffic backups but somehow it fails at this too. It took us right into a backup that had been there for over an hour and couldve easily been avoided. There is zero point in using this app. Highly recommend NOT using.
replyContent: Hi Michael, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Very useful app and very informative! This app reminds you of your current speed and the potential risk of going over the Speed Limit. ‚úîÔ∏èYou can help others by reporting debris; report emergency road-side vehicles; potholes; weather conditions; crashes; slow to stand still traffic; even POLICE (wether obvious ones or elusive "invisible" one's hiding if someone can catch them beforehand); and much more. I've been heavily dependant on this app to help me navigate to where I need to go while being safe and "complying with the law" (lol). You can also manage what time you want to arrive to your destination and set reminders to let you remind you when to leave your current location at certain time(s). Once you set a navigation path it'll plan out your drive before you and notating when certain hazards or critical points of interest are reported to better plan out your drive. I'm saying this app is very useful and very reliable! The only downside is 'reported officers' warning notifications aren't really that reliable, as one that tends to speed sometimes. Reason being, as one who tends to look at the road while driving much more than their phone, "Oh I know, a millennial that actually follows rules -rare", I set notifications for cops on volume high to be warned in advance. But this app only warns you of 'reported officers' in too much of a short notice: usually within mere seconds of being in proximity of the officers location where you're more than likely spotted already going above the speed limit and caught by said officer...not useful. If this app can update that feature and warn drivers way in advance like a two-mile warning of 'reported officers' "...that'll be greeaattt..." Other than that, I have no complaints! Great useful app. (5 out of 5 üçï) ...maybe one less pizza, I love me some pizza!

Does not always select the quickest, shortest, or most efficient routes. It keeps trying to route me onto a toll road, despite the settings to avoid toll roads. On a daily basis, I can save nearly 10 minutes by ignoring it's directions. Too many taps to change routes, or to report hazards, making it dangerous to use while driving.

Waze is really good at telling you when to turn or exit at the worst moment, including after you pass the exit or intersection. Then the app needs to recalculate a new alternative route because its crappy decision of not telling you when you should have turned. It has stupid features that makes unnecessary sounds and has built in games for when your driving around... because apparently driving is a game to waze. I'm only giving it 2 stars because I do like the boy band voice & the cute logo.

Does not work properly even on Android Auto. Please add sensible options like closing Waze. Smaller Notifications with a X to close and ability to add voices without the need for root or hacks. Why would you make this impossible? Perhaps this is all intended to annoy drivers and promote the move to Google maps. Disappointed!

I liked it until it kept turning on randomly in my handbag when connecting to blutooth in the car and i couldnt seem to turn that annoying function off. Had to uninstall and re install, hopefully it stops now August 2020, uninstalling after waze sent me miles out of my way 3 times in the last 3 trips. Was driving past the signs clearly showing the way home, frustrating
Best free GPS!

I am a long time user but getting increasingly annoyed as it no longer locks the map orientation with North at the top of the screen. I can switch it back temporarily, but if I then search for an alternative route it's back to showing my current direction at the top. Please fix this ASAP

This app helped me so much. From traffic to a small pot hole in the road. I know some people when they would hit that pot hole, they would get a flat tire. Wouldn't it be nice to know ahead of time????.... Hecks yah. Just try it for one trip instead of google maps. You will love it. I hardly go to google maps because of how great of an app this is.

A bit ago I replaced my GMaps abuse w/ Waze except when going to new places cause Waze takes too long to recalibrate after a turn or redirect, aside from that I was in love. I have a bad sense of direction so I always set the map when I drive just in case & Waze became my new default. Doesn't work recently! It will give me initial directions but doesn't move once I start going which is useless. Checked permissions, uninstalled & reinstalled...nothing. Sad day. 2 ‚≠ê for our time together. RIP.

Google has been ruining this app. It wasn't the most stable before, but now they're just slowly eroding its functionality. This is doubly so when you connected to Android auto. Now that Waze insists on using Google Assistant, you need to use the phrase OK Google for both Google Assistant, Google maps, and Waze. This means that Waze will not understand any of your reporting, because Google Assistant thinks you are talking to it. I don't know why they got rid of the phrase OK Waze. Stupid.

Used to be good, but now it's so slow it takes ages to do anything, places ads over map WHILE YOU'RE DRIVING, if the volume's set at the wrong level you have to pull over and go through 2 screens of settings to change it even though less necessary audio options are available on 1st audio settings screen. I closed my app a week ago on a drive once I got to a route I knew and it now won't update my location, so sets routes starting 10 miles away. Help centre wouldn't load, nor submit error.
replyContent: Hi Rob, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more about this routing issue to investigate further. To best assist, could you please submit a ticket ? Here's we to submit it: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9557145?hl=en Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: 1. Wasn't showing the shortest route, discovered this since 2 months back. 2. Most of the time it just keep loading, forever loading and searching for route. When I switch to Google map, it works just fine. It can't be my phone.

Well how can you get anything better than this. I use this up all over the Europe never fails (just make sure you're phone connected to network/Internet). I'm very satisfied always. God bless you all for this up. It's FREE and just helping people and drivers all over the world üåé. Thank you again Waze!!!.

Waze has been my go-to navigation app for years but with the most recent update or two, its totally unusable on my Pixel 2. It now looses GPS constantly, has trouble getting routing, claims network issues when my phone has full bars of coverage, and is just plain unstable sometimes locking up both my phone and my car's Android Auto. Of course, whenever it's misbehaving, Google Maps works with no problems. Please fix this, Waze!

Incredibly slow to boot up. Depending on the time of day it simply will refuse to generate a route. The app is incapable of interacting with Google Calendar in order to notify when to leave for planned rides. Google Maps is superior in every single way.

This app is a hit and miss. When it's working (75% of the time). It's great and does what it says. when it doesn't work it's trash. Sometimes my arrow on the map doesn't move or my speedo dissapears. But when it works it's is a fantastic app. Beats google maps anyday. I also think that you need to add school zones in. It's a must. Waze has saved me from so many speed cameras. Please add school zones for Australia. Most modern car navigation systems show school zones. My parents Volvo shows it.
replyContent: Hi Anthony, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about these issues to investigate further. To do so, please submit debug logs to us and create a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I used to love this app, and now it's trash. It often drops me off in the middle of the street instead of an address, the maps turns while in driving making me think I need to turn around. Edited to add: I actually did what you asked and nobody is even looked at the message. I am beyond frustrated and going back to Google maps.
replyContent: Hey Ray, we're disappointed to hear about you bad experience and would like to help. To best assist, please send us a private message on Facebook with more details. Thank you for the feedback! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: At first everything was fine. But after several updates, the program demonstrates phenomenal stupidity! He drives in circles to the center, provide idiotic routes, warns about traffic jams too late. That is, first you are driven into the center of traffic jams, and after 10 minutes they kill you with messages that very heavy traffic is 200 meters forward. Control shot to the head! :(

On the motorola G6 play (brand new phone), OS version Android 9. waze is connecting to GPS way to much when I'm trying to go on a route and because of that it shows an approximate location. I have to mention that the phone had a factory data reset, app have all the permissions and the location is activated. also the device had no physical damage. With google maps I have no issue and is bothering me because I used this app for a few years and you make it whorse.

I love it more than google maps! Waze is more than a GPS! The features I use the most are speed tracking and hazard alerts. You can't beat the real time updates. The most helpful tool in Waze is the planned trips, that lets you look at a locations busiest times and find the best time to leave. Waze will reroute you in some weird back ways but it saves time so much time.

Sometimes Waze don't work well. On 7th June 2019, Waze told me that it takes 55 minutes (normally it does) to reach a destination but that day was a Friday after a public holiday so the traffic was smooth. I also specified the same destination in Google Maps, which told me that it takes 25 minutes. Guess which was correct? Indeed, Google Maps was the correct one. Waze is supposed to take realtime traffic into calculation but it definitely failed that time.

App has been working great on and off. It has really been hit or miss when trying to report hazards on the road or police officers in the area. It works and doesn't work... I use the Ford Sync3 system on a 2019 F-150; hasn't been showing speedometer with the last update, or Google update. Quite frustrating... UPDATE: waze support got back to me. They said all Ford vehicles experiencing this issue, should be fixed in the next update. I'll update my review accordingly
replyContent:
We're sorry to hear that you're having trouble using Waze with Android Auto. We'd like to look into this further, would you mind submitting more information about this issue here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I use this with Lyft, and it's consistently telling me the wrong pick up area when itll get the correct addresses location wrong. it'll get the correct drop off area wrong, like in a different apt complex or a block away, a few doors down, on the other side of a fence, the wrong store, also if you could bring up the address of the drop off location before I'm at 0ft of the drop off, that'd be great ... fix that and if Google maps sucks, I'll switch back

Half of the time, waze is trying to connect to GPS causing me to restart the app aftrr serveral minutes. Then out the second half of the time, I know for a fact the ETA is wrong. I know its wrong because it wants to take me through a choke point that each time I try to go through it, my ETA ends up doubling. There needs to be an app update or something, becuase these issues are going to push me away to another app.

I like it, but the freaking thing doesn't give enough time to signal a turn properly, the voice fades in when I use it. I've been fairly clear that it's happening but NOTHING HAS Been done to rectify the situation, a 1/4 mile heads up on a turn or a voice that doesn't fade in when on a rute would be GREAT.

Waze, It is a great App, show the way to my destination. The App need a bit of improvement, it still not stable at times, easily disturb my other reception and can not function well, redirect wrong location, when come to location it does not show whether is on the left or right of the road, and slow on directions arrow pointing, mean poor in actual or specific location. Appreciate so much for your creation to help us enjoy our driving. Have a great day ahead! Thank you.

Was great...The app was working great for over a year. Today on my 11 hour trip from Minneapolis to Detroit it completely crashed on me. The routing server went offline for me and I was forced to use Google maps, which added an hour and 20 minutes to my trip. This is a huge let down.

It got worse lately. The app takes a lot of time to get my connection and my location (even while using WiFi) and when it finally gets them, I often get a server communication error (especially during the hours when the traffic gets heavier)

Was good and now it's mediocre. Doesn't show alternate routes anymore. Only one routing option is available. Two days back the routing it suggested was twice longer than it should be. I've double checked this error on 3 phones. Still the same. Suspect server was down. Unreliable.

A terrible navigation app on par with Google Maps. When there's an incident on the roads these Maps just send you on the outskirts of where the incident was leaving you in total gridlock rather than being smart and sending you on a different route altogether. And when they say another route is quicker it is usually incorrect and takes even longer it says 9 minutes faster but then takes half an hour. Sat navs were better 10 years ago the old tom toms and garmin's so much better back then.

To begin, i work for food delivery and it's vital for me to have accurate route guidance. Whilst the speedometer function is useful especially if your car's speedometer is broken, i frequently have problems with Waze not knowing what side of the street i am on and sending me to incorrect addresses. Volunteers that work on fixing the map problems do not always fix these issues. If an actual creator of the app could take the time to cross reference some of these reported addresses, that'd be good.
You can find place better blindfolded.

Better than Garmin i wish I'd never spent the money. Really works better if waters can remember to take notes and go back in the app to make notes. However, being able to make notes on-the-fly with the mic (speech to text) is good, like "use your blonker you clowns! Or, accident on i-23 all lanes closed because some idiot doesn't know how to drive!stuck here for past 30min!!. Or things like that.

I used Waze all the time until recently, it crashed, it keeps loosing my SUV on the map, recalculates, black screens etc etc etc. Google maps works perfectly so I know it's not my phone. 2 days ago I was driving from Vegas to LA so I gave it a try...impossible to use, had to go back to google maps. I like the police feature but cant use it. Now can someone from Waze answer us, the users!!! Since Waze keeps quiet can Google maps add more features like the police icons. I know Waze belongs to Goog

Ive been at my wits end with map apps latley. Between apple maps and google maps neither of them are capable of giving proper directions. But waze on the other hand is the worst by far. Tried for a few days and just get led in circles for hours (literally) And getting sent the opposite direction constantly. Tried setting it up to avoid "difficult intersections" and was immediatly lead to a left turn with no lights that took over 25 minutes to get past. Worst gps ever.

I attempted to install Waze on my new phone, but it REQUIRES access to all of my contacts. So I uninstalled it. There is no reason for Waze to require access to all of my contacts' information. It is a location app and has never needed to know my dad's phone number to show me where I'm going.

Searching new routes used to be quick and great. Now i get very limited route options and they do not refresh quickly. Also, remove carpool! Or give me the option to take it off the app. Very inconievent when trying to set new route but accidently click the carpool button that takes up half the screen or activates with the slightest touch on the right side of screen.

I never heard about Waze before. I was needing to go to my cousin's to help care for her after surgery and i haven't been at her house before until August 2019 and she said to use this gps. I fell in love with it, keeping me informed of all pot holes, broke down vehicles, wrecks, POLICE, detours, even road blocks, it lets me know everything. Would recommend this app for everyone. Thank you Waze for keeping me informed of everything ahead of me. Keep up the great work.

Damages the phones battery..battery saver is on.. and the phone still does not charge properly since Im using waze, in short it is a good navigation but it uses way too much battery that kills your battery. I've already stopped using it on my iPhone and trying it on android with the battery saver on but there is no difference. Phone heats up to touch and back of the phone feels very hot and that is where the battery is. There is no point for waze to try defending this as it can not be defended.
replyContent: Hi, Ali! Thanks for the feedback. Please note that there is a Battery Saver mode you can activate. More info here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7433873 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Having loads of problems with the maps being completely useless lately, maps can not find loads of post codes and takes me to locations that do not exist, or down wrong roads away from my target addresses. I have had to stop using Waze at present. New addresses are always an issue but lately Waze map can not even pick up basic post codes. What is going on.??? It was a good app but so dissapointing of late. I have had to go back to using google maps oh my word. Stunned. From the UK.

I've always used whatever Nav App came with my phone. usually Google Map this App was AMAZIMGLY better!! It was extremely accurate. The only time it had to recalculate was when we were in a twisty curvy mountain road part of our trip. It gave heads up for road hazards, accidents, sneaky hidden cops and disabled vehicles on the side of the road. It tells your speed and the speed limits as you travel. May even use it for my daily drive to work now!

The app interface is very good, the navigation software is top tier, in my opinion, and the voices are great. However i wish there were more variety in what they say, if there is traffic, when we reach our destination, and so on, i wish that they would have lots of options in what they say, to make the journey funnier, cooler and more magical. My point is that i wish they would have 3 or 5 sentences to choose from when the app says something. I hope you would consider my idea.

The periodic auto-center is annoying. It needs a street address to bookmark a location, it is impossible to bookmark a place on the field or in a forest. On the other hand, if the GPS information is not accurate, it does not mind showing the car moving with 100 km/h on the field or through a forest, in the middle if nowhere.

Initially, this app was in my view the best nav tech going. However in the past 6 months the GPS tracking lags in Android Auto and it is no longer accurate, to the point that I have added miles on to my journey because the app is not up to speed. The features are fantastic, the app in general is superb (When it is working), but it now requires some serious attention/updates before it really goes down the pan.

App typically works great, tells you when there will be traffic, police, etc., well when someone else reports it.  The only issue I have had is every once in a while I try to get a route, and it takes 5 minutes to give you the directions.

Been using Waze for about a year now on my Oneplus 6t on Tmobile's network. After reinstalling the app multiple times I continue have connectivity issues. This often happens when I'm either transitioning from WI-FI to LTE or starting from mobile data, it will take about 5 minutes to find the "network". I have developer mode on with mobile data always active so the app should always be tied to data. I enjoy the app, I would give it five stars if it had the reliability of google maps.

App constantly stops and redirect on the wrong way, in order to get the right direction it is necessary to move at leas 20 ft and then it gi es a long arounf route when theres much more direct routes. NOW IS EVEN WORSE!!! It stops in the middle of driving just out of the blue. I have uninstalled and reinstalled couple times, recalibrated my compass but nothing seems to work

content: I downloaded waze because I heard that it doesn't take you around the world to get to a straight shot destination. For the first 6 to 8 months it was a great app. I'm not sure what has been going on with the pass three months but this app is about worse than google maps. It lead me around the world like google maps. I feel that it's no purpose of this app honestly besides the police warnings.

Ever since the latest update the app just stopped working. Whenever i connect to my androidauto they keep prompting me that i have not setup the app and kept asking me to "set-up" before i could use. After goimg through the "set-up" all my previous settings were gone and have to go through all the "set-up" and settings every single time i connect to my car.
replyContent: Hi ZhiPing, thanks for reaching out. Thanks for reporting this Android Auto issue. We are currently working on a fix for this new bug. We appreciate your patience during this time. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Sometimes I'm inputting many addresses in order to quickly check potential travel times between several locations, and I'd like a faster way to turn off the sound from the map screen for when I do this. This used to be a feature in an older version. Going into the settings to turn off and then later turn on sound again is a lot.

Keeps shutting down. it will take several minutes to open and then just quites or changes the chosen route. then it clocks...and clocks...searching for satellite...clocks...turns black...shuts down. this has been happening for several months. i think the most disappointing thing is when you really need the app it faulters. I used to think this was the best app but now i cant trust it.

Have been using this for years and love it. Will give it 5 stars when you make a patch for the new android 11 that just released. As soon as I updated my phone waze quit working. It just sits there like I'm not moving anywhere and won't update my location as I drive. Please hurry and make a patch, I hate using Google maps lol
replyContent: Hi Jake, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this issue you‚Äôre experiencing to help. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: While trying to overlook the cartoonish interface this app took me 32 miles out of my way and ultimately tried to send me through a soybean field near Blue Springs, Missippi. My destination was the Toyota plant there but Waze could not locate it. If you try this app be sure you have a full tank ( or battery ).

Android version glitching too often. For a driving app designed to limit phone interaction this app seems to crash/freeze/glitch or generally "wig out" far too often. Reinstalling usually solves the problem, but hard to do when you are driving, stuck in traffic, and juet want to find an alternate route.

The app was working fine for almost 2 years with my Samsung S10 with Android 10 but now android 11 paired with a Ford sync 3, then all of a sudden, no on screen speedlimit, no driving icon, and it tracks slowly. But after turning it on and off several times and using"maps", without any issues, , it will then decide to maybe work. I am not sure what Waze changed, but change it back Also tried multiple reboots and calibrating gps in maps, download the gps test and it shows alot of satellites,

content: I use this app a lot. I loved it but I have experienced some troubles lastly. First, it wanted me to go through a 1.30 min route while maps gave me a 50 min route which worked great. Then it couldnt find the route from Malaga to Madrid. Finally there is a Speed trap near my house that for a period of time it wouldnt show. Also, I hate the way it warns you about Speed traps. If you are goind under the speed limit it doesnt warn you, so if you accelerate when passing you get caught.

content: I used to love and swear by this app as an Uber driver of 4 years. Now I mostly swear AT it. Since I moved to the Tampa/St. Pete area from San Diego, something has gone very wrong with Waze. The app is sending me off on odd routes that have my passengers questioning me, and having me go to extraordinary lengths to make a simple U-turn! I noticed that there has not been an update posted for a long time, and I think you guys need to do a serious, thorough de-bugging of Waze. As in, right now!
replyContent:
