For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: What great and very reliable app for driving or even just finding a place to grab a cup of coffee or anything. My only criticism would be that you can not map your own routes, how Google Maps lets you. It would be a major asset if this could be included. One more thing, everyone need to contribute so we all have the most up to date information for our trips. -Smith

I give up on Waze for the moment, although I really like the idea and its features. GPS is not working with it, rendering it useless. I get a signal when (and only when) I am outside, but not even in my car connected via Android Auto. Location is all over the place but the road I am driving on and updates once every other minute I don't get why this poses such a huge issue, when other navigation apps or Google Maps having no issue getting a signal even inside my house.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issues you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps from the Help Center a try: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Was experiencing problems where the printing for the maps would not load on my device, and whenever I went by the location where major construction had been going on for at least a month, it didn't show up on my Waze app, don't have a clue why these 2 problems occurred...
Very useful and very acurate

Google Maps ain't got nothin on this. Love how it gives me the best route and routinely updates to let me know when things hazards and roadblocks are going to be a hindrance. Like that fellow Wazers can report things like an object in the road, a pulled over car , ice on the road, and even cops on the route. Who wouldn't love that? Try it!

This started out well, but I have way too many bugs with it. As in voice commands that never ever work. Or taking the longest route to the destination is another issue. Don't waste your time with this app unless you're just watching it for cops. If you're trying to find someone you're unfamiliar with use the native Google maps.

I've been recommending Waze for the last two years but a few days ago I noticed for the first time that my 1year old phone has suffered screen burn of the icon on the lower right side plus red lines from the top to the middle of the screen! I'm really upset! How can this be happening with an app as successful as Waze?! I've looked online and I am not the first user this has happened to either. Waze responded with "contact Samsung" which is rubbish as Waze is the only app that has left an imp

Was excellent, exceptional even, but latest version caused it to be inoperative. Just spinning, apologizes, asks me to try again, and goes back to spinning... I have done several uninstall/reinstall, restarted my phone several times... 2 stars because this was the best, consistent driving app out there which meant the developers knew their stuff.. so I believe they can fix it... UPDATE: after some some more install/uninstall, the app went back to 100% functional. Thank you developers!!!

They should allow toggle off the annoying "car parked on the side of the road' alerts which come about 15 per mile on the interstate and are absolutely useless. Many of these cars are abandoned that are pulled way off the shoulder anyhow. Plus, I'm not pulling off the road 99.99999% of the time. I can see cars that are on the side of the road. Also it suggests a restaurant to me that's 12 mi away instead of the one that is 1.2 mi away. These are lazy programmers.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Almost everything about this app is great. I like the set up and the customization. But it could be a bit more accurate than getting you near an address. Also dont expect much out of the voice commands since they are going to be unusable about 80%-90% of the time due to endless updates.

the extra features are cool like managing spotify and showing your speed and showing alerts. But it does a p!ss poor job of it core function , which is to navigate you to your destination. It takes me an average 30% longer than if I would have used google maps, or it takes you to the wrong place. Will NEVER use it again to take me to a place I dont know

I use this app multiple times a day. The single best driving app in the world. Love the speedometer, speed limit info, notifications if you are going too fast, alerts for police, and of course the phenomenal routing functions. Now with better voice control for reporting police, traffic and road hazards via Google Assistant, it's unquestionablely the best driving app. Only thing it's missing are time variable speed limits for school zones with lower speed limits during certain hours. Fix that!

Been using it for a while thru AA on my SEAT Leon. Had been working nicely, but for the last week it takes ages to find my location. Google Maps finds it instantly so its not and issue with my phone. Also, when the guidance shows a roundabout, the arrow goes the wrong way around the roundabout, which is slightly annoying for countries that drive on left.

I used to love this app, used it all the time, switched phones and it wouldn't let me log in, was associated with my google account, but told me there was no e-mail associated. That phone was recalled and got this one and now whenever i open the app it asks to get started or log in and either option brings me to the user agreement and crashes...have uninstalled and reinstalled countless times. What happened to them.

I love Waze!!! Gets me where I need to go in the shortest time possible AND tells me where police are spotted on my route as well as road construction and hazards and I can tell others behind me where they are as well and let's face it, that's just a great way to be a good human! I don't see a reason to use any other map app!!!

Awesome when it works, horrible when it doesn't. Waze has been a great app so far until the app stops receiving my GPS location even with the correct settings. I have encountered a few incidents where the app stopped calculating my route and I am forced to stop by the side of the road to fix it but eventually I am unable to. Hopefully a fix to accurately locate our GPS will be updated soon because it is sometimes frustrating if it stops working during our drive.

This used to be my most-used app, but unfortunately the quality has been in steep decline recently to the point that it is now literally unusable. As someone who drives A LOT, I depended on Waze every day while it was working. But all this week it has been locking up on "Calculating Route". I've emailed Tech Support multiple times each day from my phone and their only advice is to verify my phone isn't on Airplane Mode

I drove down to Georgia 2 weeks ago from Pennsylvania, I too was having issues with the network and calculations and or shutting down on it's own while driving. Now I'm planning to go to Ocean City, Maryland and it's telling me it can't find any routes for it.Again, I will be traveling from Pennsylvania. please fix, I plan on going down to Maryland this week for the 4th of July.
Probably the best gps ever!!!

I like the directions on the Waze App. , but I don't like the carpool function that comes up when I am driving. It asks about carpooling in the middle of giving directions & it is annoying because you can't see the directions on your screen. You could get into an accident because of this .

Adding a star to reflect recent improvements. - Samsung Note 9 - 1/4 times it will show the map briefly before swapping it out with a black screen overlaid with the prompts captions, speedometer. Almost every morning it sees heavy traffic on the highway and recommends I take the service road, except there is light to no traffic and I stay on the highway, only for Waze to then annoy me because it thinks I'm driving 110km/h in a 50km/h speed limit zone on the service road. Why?

Actually, I'm a heavy user of this social-based navigation apps. From several years ago. But during long holiday festive season (Eid Mubarak) here in Indonesia where people use to go driving long distance inter-city, I found so many mistake on route planning & failure to estimate the time of arrival (ETA). I know it's purely the dynamic data, but statistically the big-data apps supposed to be able to analize many dynamics on the route, start from early driving plan, right? Need improvement.

Shame the server keeps going down and Waze's part-time social media service isn't really there to issue any updates about the service failure. Great when it works, but recently there has been too much downtime. Google Maps has the uptime, so I think I'll return to that.

Great GPS app! Simple & Intuitive interface. Finds *correct* destinations. Many useful functions (Reports, Wazers, Traffic etc) and lots of user choices to select - the big one being able to use the Male navigation voice. Awesome! I'm not exactly sure, but I thought Waze had a dark mode in previous versions(?), but it's not in this version. I hope the Waze Team considers implementing it. Otherwise, great job overall. This is my go-to gps app. Thank you, Waze Team!

I had downloaded this because of Cookie monster. What happened!?!?! Also, the app doesn't allow much time before the notification(s) to turn. The last use, last destination, I was taken in a circle before I got to the place, then it told me a residential area was the optometrist office... But cookie monster... Come on!

Last sunday I went to durdle door beach with two other families from hayes London and its turn out a difference of one and half hour between us as I'm using waze and they using normal car GPS. WAZE IS SIMPLE AMAZING

Great for community reports but it stops there! This app is great for speed limits, speed cameras, police and other hazards. I wish I could keep using this nav for this reason but unfortunately the actual navigation and maps aren't very good and do not match to Google Maps. The input of addresses and destinations is very old fashioned and not modern or as good as Google Maps. Navigation isn't very trust worthy, I find it takes me down a lot of small back roads rather than actual quicker roads.

Was great, but with the latest updates is getting slower, and slower and slower. A real piece of junk! can't calculate more than 500km distance! Amazing for an app that used to be good! Google maps is 1 million times better!!!!

The current updates are seriously faulty. It's takes you to a wrong road. Most times it have problem connecting to a GPS ... Most addresses in kyiv are not captured. It will be nice if the application is made English friendly for user who don't hear a native language in a foreign country. I dont understand Russian language here in kyiv Ukraine and there's no option to switch to English and the streets names all appear in Russian language making it difficult for English users.

Great app, gives an almost accurate eta to location. Only downside was when we started to travel on the holy week, it gave us routes that are two times longer. I mean, don't you guys have historical data about the traffic of a certain location on special occasions?. Our eta of 6 hours became 15 hours, even then an eta of 6 hours is already questionable for travelling to Ilocos. It assumed that we will travel an average of 100km/h. Pls fix this thx.
We are in desperate need of a SPEED CAMERA alert!!!!

I use Facebook messenger as my main means of communicating with clients and prospective clients and I travel A LOT as well so I'm always using Waze when I'm not familiar with an area. If Waze is running and I get a FB call, Waze completely crashes to the point of needing a full restart of my device. I'm on the Note9 now but it also did this on my S7 edge and my S8+. PLEASE fix this as I strongly dislike Google maps but have been forced to use it more and more. Rating will go up if you fix it. üëç

The app never worked, I installed it twice, everytime I typed in a location to go to, it kept saying "no network available". I had this app recommended to me because ever since I've moved to Dallas TX google maps has been spotty at times. But at least google maps works most of the time, this app didnt work at all...
replyContent: Hi Garth, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this network issue you're experiencing to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This used to be the gold standard of navigation apps, but lately it hasn't been able to locate me, and by considerable distances at times. It just showed me being in a town in New Hampshire I've never heard of, but I'm in Boston. I hope they fix this issue because the app is useless to me otherwise.

Waze used to be by far the best navigational app available on Android but whatever update they have pushed out has destroyed it. The refresh rate has become terrible and has made me miss junctions on lots of occasions now. The car regularly jumps on and off roads and is wrong nearly every time you look at it now. If this is fixed I will bump it back up to where it should be.

I love Waze navigation. I would love to give 5 stars, but they need to update the functionality with Android auto to be able to report hazards with voice so that I am not messing with the car radio screen. Other than that, this is an excellent app and I would recommend it to everyone looking for GPS navigation on their phone!

A relatively great app, but it doesn't always show major delays and accidents that are all over the news (I'm in New Orleans). It often changes routes while I'm already on one same I end up taking twice as long to get there or I get lost. Most of the time though it is accurate and very useful for avoiding bad traffic, accidents, and road closures that aren't shown on Google maps.

Extra star for battery usage. You have to dig into settings to turn off annoying "vehicle on side of road" alerts without turning off navigation. Very easy to turn off navigation audibles with "Alerts Only" selection. Should also have "Navigation Only" selection as that is primary function. Would be nice to have settable volume "muting" level for other audio. Still want to hear music/news. You cant select route based on distance. It added 70 miles to a 320 mile trip one way but not the other.
replyContent:
Hi, Lorin! Thanks for the feedback. Please note that you can turn specific alerts off by tapping Search > Settings > Alerts & reports > Reports. 


For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: its a great app for navigation but its mainly hard to try and help out with the community. the community wont really accept all your changes and focuses on only communiting to work. i expected more from the community but every time i made a court near my house the same person wpuld remove. i give a 4/5 for greatness but 2/5 for community.

It works pretty well and the connection seems more stable than Google Maps. Would give 5 stars but it just is not as intuitive as Google..in that it does not learn repetitive routes as well. Also not as good with multiple destinations in a single trip.

This was once a revolutionary GPS app, but those days are long gone. I assume Google downgraded it to encourage people to move to Maps, but continuous crashing while on route, trouble calculating future trips, excessive verbal warnings, nannyware and other dangerous add-ons that require you to interact with the phone while driving... I'm not sure why Google didn't just capitalize on what was working rather than destroying it in favor of their inferior product.

Ever since updated the app. Waze has not been useful, as I choose an off route without toll. Waze decided to guide me to a toll route. Waze has not been friendly in terms of money, keep wanna lead me into paying tolls that are unnecessary to go to, when you have another route without paying toll... What is this waze? I'm seriously piss man, I'm changing to Google maps. K, thanks, bye.
replyContent: Hi Daniel, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Don't waste your time downloading this apps. It brought me to difference location in Sungai Petani Kedah. My friend also almost died after the apps bring him to the cliff.

love this app as my family travels quite frequently but the latest update is horrible. it will not calculate directions at all. I have tried everything from shutting the app down, foreclosing it even uninstalled and reinstalled. still does not work! Would rather use Waze but currently stuck with just Google maps! please fix soon& I will change my rating!

Would have been 5 stars but 2 things let it down. First is we can't choose the distance to be notified by police and mobile speed cam.ATM ITS TOO short . Already seen it before you tell me, thats too late. Second is I can't report a hazard on the opposite side on motorway or local roads. That might save someone's life.
replyContent: Hi there! Thanks for the review. Other side reporting is already available by voice using the Google Assistant! One of our primary focuses is investing in voice to create a safer and better experience for our users. We appreciate your feedback! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: totally not friendly user.always lag and make my phone hot when use

A very handy app when you need to go somewhere but sometimes the GPS cannot be tracked and then it will cause some problems. And sometimes the route will change by itself for no reason (but it rarely happens nowadays). And furthermore, especially on KL roads‚Äìwhere we need to take the exact right streets to head to where we needed, may be very confusing‚Äì it does not help when the navigation app only tells u to go straight when there are many routes ahead of you.
Waze Up! Great App!

This app has given me nothing but problems for the last 2 months. I have been travelling a lot and desperately needed GPS. Waze was constantly losing connection, blacking out on the dashboard, not remembering the routes, etc. I nearly missed a flight because of the issues I was having.

Never use this app to navigate to hiking trails. It's gotten me lost twice now. I've ended up almost an hour from where the trail really is. Once it lead me to a closed if access road, the second time I almost ended up in private property in the middle of nowhere. Will never use this app outside of the city again.
replyContent: Hi Alexander, we're sorry to hear about you bad experience. If you send us a private message on Facebook with the route details we'd be happy to look into it. Thanks for bringing this to our attention. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It was good, used to be a fantastic app. Now though, it freezes constantly in my car ('17 Escape with Android Auto & Sync 3), it never retains the car settings, the speed indicator disappears, and display constantly zooms to the maximum. I've seen other similar complaints on other sites, I hope this gets fixed soon. It would be nice to have the old reliability back.
replyContent: Hi James, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this Android Auto issue to investigate further. To do so, please submit debug logs to us and create a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great Fun App; but one Niggly issue! Waze is basically a more fun version of Google Maps, with more details; such as Speed, Police and Cool Sprites for your character. It's Brilliant! The one issue i have is with the 're-route' chirp that comes up; as i usually go a slightly different route than Waze expects. It's very loud and caught me off guard when i first heard it. Can an option be introduced to turn that off?

Data Hog! I use this app daily, and it's great for navigation, but this past month, its data usage has more than quadrupled!! My app usage is the same every month: last month it used 135 MB of data, but since April 4, it's used 553 MB of data! Anyone else having this issue?

It is a good app, but the map of my area (semi-autonomous Kurdistan Region in particular, and Iraq in general) is very old and not updated. Many of locations and housing projects are not in the map which have been built in 2013! Please update the maps. Thank you!

After chatting with I guess what would be tech support and trying various things to correct the issue. This app just doesn't work like it should. It either can't find a route or the search times out. Whether it's linked through my car or just running off my phone this app has issues. I couldn't tell you exactly what it is about waze but I never really cared for it the plain simple Google maps I always liked more.

Goodbye Googly Maps! I have new Waze to get around now. not only does it navigate and alert you minute to minute on changes on your route, but it connects you to riders and drivers going the same route. so if you need a ride, you can carpool and if you're driving, you can give rides. Best app ever!

I love this app! It tells you where and how long traffic is, finds places apps like Google maps can't, alerts you when you speed (I have a black box so it's perfrct) and even tells you where speed traps are. HOWEVER the most recent update absoloutley DRAINS battery life! I went for a two hour drive, starting on 70% (usually drains like 15% an hour on my Samsung s8 if that) but 1h30mins in my phone died mid drive!! It's the same with my boyfriends phone and a few of my friends

Good map/navigator app. Occasionally, Waze crashes my phone and/or uses too many resources. The app needs some tweaking. It's difficult to plan a drive with more than 1 stop. Other Waze screens have a circular navigation, meaning that you end up back on the same screen after without making progress/edits, etc.

A good app. I wish that the posted/actual speed field was either larger on the map or had it's own screen for those times, the majority for me, when you don't need a map. It would be nice to have the ability to set an audible alert and maybe make the actual speed blink red to catch my eye Otherwise it's a very user friendly app.

love the interface and features, but it's so buggy that it's becoming unusable. it constantly crashes, frequently won't connect to gps, or the network. half the time even when it does finally connect, it will act like it hasn't, still saying waiting for network and not updating the eta.

It gets lost too often and what's up with the 1990s graphics? They are AWFUL! Has anyone there ever taken a look at Lexus, Kia or Hyundai GPS maps? They are great compared to Waze! This goes for Google Maps, too. Their graphics are at least a big step up from Waze, but no where near standard equipment on the three makes we drive.

We invite you to submit any app ideas and changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. content: The ultimate GPS thus far for me!

Google Map is stealing the WAZE ideas. I had seen one feature on Google that Waze has had for a while. Waze is totally driven by its users adding or removing data. So it is dependent on the users to accurately report. There is some automation that might be able to be pulled from devices such as speed and direction. So somethings that I would like to see and I have similar responses from others that also use Waze. Stopped vehicle on shoulder????? Which one Object Hazard in the road????? W

Waze did not live up to the hype. It frequently sent us a longer way around than Google Maps on both local journeys as well as longer ones. I have now stopped using it as a result. It was occasionally more helpful due to alerts about short term roadworks or hold ups but that didnt compensate for having sent us the wrong way in the first place...
Easy to use, great app.

Every time I open this to use it with my Lyft and Uber half of the time it shuts down and tells me that waze app has closed and to send feedback. This is getting ridiculous and I have removed ways from both of my apps and have gone back to Google Maps because I need something that works 100% of the time not something that kicks me out every 5 minutes. Please fix this ASAP as I will have to remove this app because it's worthless to me right now

This used to be my favorite map. It works good as a stand alone. The past month it rarely works with Android Auto. It will show the right direction then it acts like it has no clue where you are. It zooms in and out. The direction will be right, but the location of your vehicle will be backwards or searching for a signal.

I'm leaving a 3 star because I'm tired of constantly having to respond to the app that I'm not interested in carpooling! Also, I don't always have the highest confidence that Waze is choosing the best route. As a suggestion, it would be nice if I could have a choice to silence the app unless the proposed route deviates from my daily usual route or when I'm with in a mile of my home or work location. update. the Waze service is awful.app turns off and won't run in background or while screen isoff

Was my go to favourite app for driving. But recently very buggy and keeps freezing while driving on normal navigation routes. Works fine on it's own but when connected on android auto it freezes. Samsung note 8. Tried formatting my phone checked data reception.. neither have any effect. Until issue resolved I've switched to Google maps..
replyContent: Hi, Tom! We‚Äôre sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We're happy to look into this further. Would you mind reporting this problem here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze doesn't seem to update their maps at all. I've been given directions multiple times to places that have been closed for years. That's why I ended up uninstalling it. It doesn't give you enough warning for when you have to make multiple turns, either. Also, the popups really make it hard to check which turn you need to take.
The map are incorrect.. always point out to wrong direction.. there are one time the map give us direction to the river instead of our destination

It stopped loading. Like wont do anything for any routes just says that it timed out. This is the only app that isn't working on my phone. It wont connect to anything. I used to love this app even if it would drain my battery. But now it's a useless drain.

being asked several times daily in spotify to connect to waze. click on the cross. new window where I'm asked if I really want to turn off the connection. turning off... being asked again 5 min later. deinatalled now, though I would have liked to try it. hope this helps. this way of pushing is not appreciated

I've used Google maps and Waze. I like that Waze uses both contributed data from active users AND data pulled from users (speed). Waze saved me from at least a one hour delay on our trip home this past week. Even though there was no report of an accident, Wave projected the traffic speed and have me a detour. Turned out there was a major accident and Wave saved us from sitting in traffic for a very long time...!!

Does not work well with Android Auto. Navigation drops while driving using Android Auto, navigation seems to not know where you are. If your phone is unlocked the whole time it's fine, but in Android Auto mode your phone is sleeping most of the time. I have to use Google Maps. I prefer waze because of real time traffic alerts and other hazards.

Love this app! The fact that its user driven and still works is awesome!!!!! If your looking for a far better driving experience than Google maps,look no further, this app allows the user to post in real time what lies ahead on any given plotted route!! The more people who actually use the app the better it gets!! So don't be shy post away!

Been using since 2014, I use this app for work everyday, as I drive all day longer to different homes. I have loved it, but I had to switch back to google maps. I NEED to know which side of the road my destination is on. I'm done crossing though traffic or pulling away to make a U turn because such a huge app lacks the basic feature to indicate the side of the road the destination is on. I'm done!!!!

I love this app! Though, some of the alerts are annoying, e.g. "WATCH OUT! Vehicle on shoulder ahead" (so i turned off that type of alert). It has rerouted me a very stupid way a couple times so I just ignore reroutes now. I usually keep it on to alert for police, track how long my commute is, and traffic alerts. The random popup ad for carpooling or something is really annoying when you're trying to glance real quick to check the app.

Maybe you have a problem with your apps. Right now. Maybe you need to fix your locator issue, a lot of my co rider here in phillippines experienced this problem, Waze are going to locate you in a defferent location, until you found out that there is a easy way on the location that you looking for. Fu k this Apps. Waste of TimE
replyContent: Hi Gemini, we'd be happy to help you with that. Please send us a private message on Facebook with more details about your issue. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: The app will no longer function properly unless you have an active route. The icon that represents your car will not orient properly and will look as if you are driving backwards or sideways and location lags behind. If you have an active route, it works correctly but no longer will display your speed. Update: Upgraded my phone to the S21. Continue to have the same problems. Waze works fine on the phone but not when connected to Sync 3 in my F150. Sent error logs to Waze and opened a ticket.
replyContent: Hi Gary, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about these issues with the car icon, speed and orientation to investigate further. To do so, please submit debug logs to us and create a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: What happened?! Waze used to be my go-to navigation app. However, lately it has failed tremendously. Closes as soon as I open the app. Can't find routes to places. Doesn't even attempt to search for routes. It's like Waze just fell apart. So sad.
replyContent: Hi Ashley, we're sorry to hear that. Try reinstalling the app and make sure that you're using the latest app version. Please add an email address to your account before reinstalling (Menu > Settings > Account & Login > email). If the issue continues, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can further investigate: https://m.me/waze

content: Cannot customize routes. Takes up too much storage space on my phone.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback, Dino. We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or need assistance resolving an issue that may be occurring, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I use this everyday, even if I know where om going. I love that it accurately tells us about speed and red light cameras. Most times the cop alerts are accurate too. Giving directions can be improved, I feel like it tells you too late sometimes on where to turn. It'll tell you way before and then not remind you when you get closer. It made me go 2 NJ twice already. Needs to improve on road closures as well. Great app otherwise though.

Could be great but has a huge downfall. Every, and I mean every 2h+ journey the app will crash and you will have no idea unless you are constantly checking the screen, which makes it so easy to miss a junction and add unnecessary time to your journey.

This app is good for the mindless that need elementary guidance without detail. But for those such as myself that like to see route options and plan ahead, you will be disappointed. Route overviews are very general. You have no idea where this app plans to take you and it gives no detail at all for planned trips, which is kinda why you plan a trip in the 1st place. The real time info from other wazers is great. But the ability to know what's around me w/o being led blindly is why I'll use google

Waze used to work fine with Android Auto, but not anymore. Map wont load, meanwhile, Google maps work flawlessly. Waze via phone works fine, but it's frustrating when you're not sure if every update will break the app. It'll be nice if there's an option to increase the font size and speed limit size in Android Auto. It's a shame, because Waze is better at routing and is generally more accurate of the two apps.

I've had Waze for about over a year and I love the app it's shows almost everything you'd want while you're driving but there's a reason I've given it 2 stars and that won't change unless they fix the issue many people are having with the app. the app just doesn't know where I am when I start it up or "no GPS found". I get this literally every single time I start the app... Not much use if I can't use the app....the app has good features but if i can't use the app then why keep the app...
Frequently no live update on roadblocks

The concept is great. I find it to be a little distracting utilizing the social features of the app. Also, WAZE should had a button to push for dangerous drivers. This could alert others to look out for vehicles that are driving unsafe such as intoxicated drivers.

I've tried to use this app a couple times over the years every time it seems like it works then it doesn't at all. Won't responded to action requests. Says it will hide routes but doesn't. Can't delete easily if at all. Uninstalling it for the 4th time maybe next time see you in 2019?

App did not show the tonnes of construction projects on the route it was showing me to take. I was also shocked that a message popped on on the app, while I am driving, telling me that the app can calculate the cost of toll roads. I am driving I don't want to interact with messages that pop up, plus it's illegal to physically interact with a cellphone while driving.
Fantastic app...all you need for navigation.

Waze seems like a good app but it gives you a time estimate that can change slowly throughout your trip. Where Waze estimates you'll be on time or early to your destination, throughout the duration of journey it has chosen for you the time can change from you being on time to being 30 minutes late. I'd rather use Google at least it's consistent and more accurate with estimated time of arrival. Waze is ridiculous.

it's a great app no doubt. The algorithm is often suggesting the main arteries but is not considering paths made with back streets or secondary roads. it's suggesting the main 3 options or almost, day in, day out. I wish we could register a path that we found so it can be requested or taken into consideration when required. Also, the idea of showing petrol prices along the way is great, but they are days or weeks old which means useless. why not integrating with an App like Fuelcheck NSW?

Just absolutely bugged lately. I have force quit, uninstalled, reinstalled, toggled mobile data, wifi, location services... Pretty much everything... Half the time no maps load at all, sometimes it can't find routes... in the middle of freaking Atlanta where every single carrier has perfect service pretty much everywhere...

I have used waze for years and have loved it. But recently in the past month I will be driving to a destination and my gps will starts to reroute in the middle of the drive. Ill take a left turn and then I'll hear the reroute noise and it'll say I went the complete wrong way, which makes me panic because I could have swore it told me to turn left, and then it may reroute two more times before it goes back to the original route and confirms I was supposed to go left. Not happy anymore
replyContent: Hi Audrey, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this issue you're having to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I updated my Waze app and it doesn't work like it use to now. it freezes mid trip and u end up missing ur turn. I had to constantly stop on the side of the road for the app to work again then continue with the journey. I didn't have this issue before the update, I prefer the previous version as this current app has too many issues and I've been lost or late on my trips due to the delays.

Great GPS app. It has features such as notifying you where police or red light cameras are. It shows the speed limit and speed you're going to provide real-time ETA's. You can send your exact location to someone via text so they see where you're driving as you're driving even without the app installed. But UI is not user friendly and routes sometimes are the longest way or rarely wrong completely (this happened only once when a detour happened on the interstate that made everyone exit).
Israel doesn't exist in my Waze and I only downloaded the app because I wanted to browse through Israel. Why is that?
replyContent: Hi, Nils! Hmm, Waze should be working in Israel. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I like the app as it is user friendly and easy to use, however as of late it's been giving terrible directions; unnecessary and really weird diversions and reroutes. The ETA will recalculate after the reroutes (which always involve getting OFF of a major highway and normal route) are ignored and will often be 15-30 minutes shorter over only a 1 hour drive. Not sure what the deal is but I'm going to have to stop using Waze at least for a couple months until this is fixed.

In theory this is a great app, I love the fact users can warn others of traffic, potholes etc. In reality it's so glitchy it's impossible to use. When I open the app it takes ages to actually find my destination and sometimes I have to restart the app a few times, the car on the map doesn't follow the journey properly so it's thinks you're somewhere else which again means restarting the app or using Google maps instead. I want an app I can rely on and I can't rely on Waze.

A brilliant SatNav app, that keeps you updated with traffic and incidents based on other users and reporting! Quicker and more up to date than my local radio! My only bit of bad feedback is the adverts - I get that the app needs to earn money, but can you not have the Ads come up in the middle of the journey, cover the whole app and prevent the voice navigation to work? It's illegal to touch your phone while driving to shut the ad, it means the app is useless till you can pull over and close it
It's a very helpful app to have. Save you time When this accident it tells you take to alternate route quick.That way you need it. üëç

absolutely the worst navigation app I've ever used because the voice recognition and hands-free are both completely useless. I don't understand how this app can be such a failure in that respect now that Google owns it. I have literally screamed my throat raw trying to get this thing to understand me when it's in my windshield mount and I'm driving and the phone is out of my reach. Only useful for spotting red light cameras and speed traps when you already know where you're going.

Great app but developers ignoring some critical issues... Love the app and now won't drive on the highway without it, but two really important issues are being ignored in the suggestion box: 1. Speed limit is completely illegible as it's too small (ignored in suggestion box for nearly 5 years!) 2. Reporting things while driving not easy enough to see what you're doing (words/pics too small) Both issues are safety critical as they require you to take your eyes off the road for too much time.

I use it a lot. The directions are not that good but I use it for police alerts and such. Thing is, although Waze will show police on the screen, only half the time it will verbally alert on it. Also, it doesn't seem to matter what sound setting it is on because it does a very poor job of verbally telling directions, even if all alerts and direction voice is on.
replyContent:
Hi Kent, thank you for bringing this to our attention. Would you mind sharing more details with us about these sound issues in a private message on Facebook? Thank you. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I used to always rely on Waze but now when I sign it it shows my account, asks if it's my account (shows the name and picture) but when I click "yes, it's me" it tells me the account is not found. So it appears my account was removed it corrupted somehow maybe. I can no longer use Waze, unless I sign up again, which I don't want to do. It was good while it lasted.

I was about to give this app a raving review until a thing came up a candy treat something (im not 5) popped up then something else immediately after. Then as i was getting closer to home taking the most logical route the app was trying to divert me over 3 miles (when i pulled into the road) and it was still 2.1 miles when i pulled up on my drive with the home icon right next to my other icon. Clearly has some issues. May change my rating if things improve.

New update made the voice to talk much much less. This is terrible. In a trip which it should have talked half the way, it only talked for 3 single sentence. I used to use the voice and not looking into map and it went well all the time. It was talking and showing me the way. But now after recently updates I went 3 wrong turns because the voice was silent and didn't talk when it should've

LOVE how map is displayed, easy option for alternative routes, construction alerts & real time road closures/crashes/slow downs, & especially love the way it displays the speed limit & current speed. However the app has some major issues.1: Force closes or randomly shuts down w/out explination which has happened on all my devices android & apple alike. 2:does not save my destination from inactivity. 3: Has Ads! these are distracting (even if it's only at a stop).Very disappointed. Note 9/ipad 10

I've used Waze for over a year now and its been great. now suddenly the voice started crackling then completely stopped speaking through android auto. I sell cars for a living and have seen the same thing with customers who use both android auto and apple car play. this needs fixes asap. I used to recommend the app to all my customers and now I will tell them to use Google maps. that will not change till it's fixed. then I will update my rating and review.
Download the app twice doesn't show map wasting my time

used on iphone and worked great. now on galaxy 9+ and it crashes regularly. i drive 60k miles per year and rely heavily on gps. but last 9 months since on android, it seems to crash on long trips and just closes. other times its told me ive arrived and ive been up to a mile of course. also, it only tells you sometimes which side of the road your destination is on. when you have 4 lanes of traffic, you need this info, and need it ahead of time. addresses arent always visible from street.

Routing can be pretty poor at times, and doesnt always send you the quickest way. Voice commands are woeful, no interlocks when in menus so when trying to report traffic it often tries to change my destination! Would love the ability to allow toll roads only if saving X minutes of a journey. Ended up buying a tomtom.
Very-very bad apps. Always wrong place arrived!!! üò°üò°üò°
I love thi app easy tu use police warnings The best is free

Good app for getting where you need to be. More navigation voices would be nice. I hate how the carpool option keeps popping up with no way to disable it. This feature isn't used in my area. More customization for views and vehicles, plus ability to fix map issues (wrong speed limits, etc) faster. I'm already a map guide but will never reach level 5 or whatever is needed to change important things that are wrong.

Chooses routes that make no sense and contradicts itself. Tells you to turn a certain direction, you turn that direction and *beep* wrong way make a u turn or circle the block. Also the last update is causing the map to become a blank black screen. Everything else is visible except the map. I am a map-oriented person and a delivery driver so this a deal breaker for me. Fix this or I will be uninstalling!
replyContent: Hi there, we're sorry to hear about your issue. Please send us a private message on Facebook with the details and we'd be happy to look into it further for you. Thank you for bringing this to our attention. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I've been using Waze for a few years now and I think it's a better alternative to Gmaps as it shows accidents, potholes and the ever important cop speed traps. That being said, the recent update which encloses the full screen view option with a quick search is no good. Previous version that showed the entire screen was much better and easier for viewing for cars that do not have Android Auto. Aside from that I use it nearly every day!

I finally uninstalled Waze today solely because of it's annoying, deceptive car pool garbage. A very tiny fraction of people actually want to use something like that and VAST majority of them seek it out. I routinely accidentally bring up that stupid menu when trying to quickly leave traffic info. After doing a side by side comparison, oher maps are just as good and up to date with traffic without shoving a feature few want down your throat.

Great app!!! The estimated time of arrive (ETA) is within 5 minutes of time projected. I would like to see more alternative & accurate routes instead of going the LONG way to an unknown. destination. On reports I have all of them (show on map & alert me while driving) but it does not alert me but show the police icon.

I have been using some different GPS making apps and at times they could be frustrating. Slow to respond and update driving directions when it is too late to make your turn with some of them. Downloaded Waze to try it. Glad I did. Way better than any of the Others I tried. Traffic reports are quicker with hazards and police actions. This is going to remain my permanent mapper. Google is fine for looking at street level but not as good as Wave for driving instructions.

Talks way too long about every turn... Then it randomly doesn't say anything and you outright miss the turn. No difficult left turns? Yep. The option is on but it gives at least one every single trip. I've timed trips using Waze against Google Maps going to routine locations. Every. Single. Time. Waze is the slower route. Every time. Then, there are the ads that block half the navigation screen as you have a turn approaching. Missed turn yet again. Worst navigation app I have ever used.

What was one my go-to app for driving is now useless.  Consistently 'searching for network' makes it impossible to use and I need navigation for work.  Google maps work perfectly, imagine that.  Going by searching my problem on the internet, I am not the only one with this problem.  Samsung Galaxy S7

Used to love this app and it was the only navigation/traffic app I used until I noticed a few weeks ago it's waaaaaaayyyyyyyy off when it comes to traffic. Luckily it's overstating instead of understating how long it'll take but I'm showing up to work a half hour early when I could be spending that time with my family instead of panicking and rushing out the door. I have recently been double-checking other nav apps to see what their estimates are and they are my "normal" covid commute.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for contacting us and reporting this issue. We'd like to hear more about this traffic issue. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Generally very good. Two things which bug me though: the map can be a bit laggy sometimes, for example at roundabouts or motorway junctions, and that can cause some confusion. Also, when confronted with a closed road it's not that straightforward to mark this on the map and force a reroute. Occasionally the app will take me on a strange diversion which I assume is intended to avoid traffic but the roads are actually clear...
Always great with directions and other road conditions.

The app once worked great, however integration with Android Auto is terrible. It's slow to update location while driving, the orientation is usually sideways, and lately the screen will occasionally flicker off altogether and then come back on a couple seconds later. On the other hand Google Maps works fine with Android Auto, so I doubt the problem is integration with the vehicle's Chevrolet cpu. Hopefully the bugs get fixed!

Good idea and have great features but they are most of the time semi accurate. Example: speed camera few km away from me, well you get alert when you are approaching from behind, but won't when you are coming from where camera is pointed, when I see first camera is flawed how can I trust when I come across one somewhere else. Why don't you just have camera alert, no matter whichever direction it's facing. And speed limit is accurate in 60-70% of the time, big margin for error.
replyContent: Hi Renato, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see for speed alerts to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Was my go to app for navigation and commute, but I'm guessing a recent update changed the dependability with Android Auto. I've had to switch back to using Google Maps for now due to constant lagging, unable to track my location, horrible GPS location accuracy, and freezing when searching for an address. I dont use facebook so sending a "private message" is not an option. I know Waze has developers that can fix these problems without a debugging log. At least I would hope.
replyContent: Hi Daniel, thank you for your feedback. We are aware of the issue and our team is working to fix it as soon as possible. Please feel free to reach out to us with any issues or question using this contact form: tinyurl.com/ruvjkpu

content: The update on Sept 17, 2019 has now made this app totally useless. For whatever reason the navigation map is now locked in place (this is with the North Lock function OFF). The map never rotates or pivots to align the map in the direction of the drive so often you will see yourself going sideways on a road that cuts off because of the width of your screen. Then the map adjustment is flaky and jerky and constantly either shows you off the road or on a different street. FIX IT OR PULL IT DOWN.

I prefer this to my Google maps as it is so in depth and allows me to get to my destination without fear of the arrow getting stuck or lost. Easy to use, amazing interface and clear direction at all times. So many options to make it personalised to your own preferences I. E the arrow can be changed, it informs you about speed cameras, or police etc. EXCELLENT App, highly recommended (humbly in my own opinion)

This map is way easier to read and understand then the other maps I have used. I love that the people on the road are helping each other keep it up to date. The information when there is trouble in the road is instant and very helpful. Specialy when there is an accident and the map automatically informs you there is a better route to take if we wanted. I would like different voices then they have but they are still fun at times.

I think the update really screwed everything up! It can't even connect to my GPS anymore, and that's the whole point of navigation! I use this app for the police warnings and in - app speedometer/ speed limit reminders, and I hate to say it, but I might be going to Google maps for a bit. Waze... Get you stuff together!

Was a solid 4 until the latest update in November, now on a Pixel 1 with android auto it almost continuously interrupts the music with voice prompts that do not say anything.  Making navigation unusable if you are playing anything else on android auto.  Works fine when not navigating.  Now it is unusable as a navigation tool.

I love this app. Directions are clear and I have been rerouted many times allowing me to miss huge traffic jams. I do have a issue where it often freezes the first time you connect it to Android auto. The actual freeze happens after you choose your location and it opens the map to direct you. then it is stuck at a spot and not actually following you. at this moments (after driving few km without it unfreezing) I change to Google Maps.

Don't get me wrong, I like Waze. But some things could sure be better. Adjusting the volume is multiple clicks, a drag, another click. While driving. Safety shortcuts to common functions such as this would be more than welcome. Instead every update states the same changes as the prior (not helpful and lazy). Fix the bugs, please. But please also make changes that improve the safety of using Waze. Easy volume or even using the phone volume buttons is just one example.

Pop-up advertisements in a navigation App! Are you kidding? It is so distracting to have to those ads pop-up. I would say that it is dangerous. I can't believe that some cities have 'officially' tied up with Waze to provide them traffic information. I cannot recommend this App to anyone. Stick with Google Maps.

Every single time I enter an address to navigate to, the map disappears and is all black. Upon further investigation, it looks like this issue has been happening since 2017, and has still not been fixed. Can't trust this app at work. Going back to Google Maps. Other than that, it has awesome potential. Using Samsung Galaxy A31.
replyContent: Hi Ryan, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more about this blank map issue you're experiencing with the app to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I have tried everything to get this app to find my gps, I even factory reset my phone, I use Google maps and have no issues (except I hate it), I tried what you said to do and nothing worked, I love this app please make it work again, I need navigation!!!! If it helps I have a Samsung note 3
replyContent: Hi Karyn, thank you for the review. We're happy to help you with your issue. Please adjust you phone's location setting to connect Waze to GPS. Here's how: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6083679?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: While a helpful app, my biggest problem is that I am unable to pinpoint my home address in the map. I am also (ALWAYS!!! in Waze and other navigation apps) given directions from the street I live BY, not where I actually live. This is extremely annoying. I have sent feedback through the app and NOTHING has been done to correct these issues.

Great app! Way better than google maps! There is only one issue I have during last months: after the sistem update of my Huawei Mate 20 pro to EMUI 10.1.0 version its New split screen feature is not supported by Waze. Was waiting for any update of Waze to support it, but without any success so far. Please fix it guys! Thanks in advance!

I like fact you and report stuff and other like police or wrecks. But big drawl backs battery hog and it kept saying GPS was turned off a lot or thought we middle of snowy feld. But worst thing I told be stand still traffic at last minute due to wreck. And report it said 30mins. Now if would told me that we could took another route. But noooo told me we was got stop by stand still traffic. I will be un installing. I wonder why made log into Facebook just reconnect to GPS at one point

Had high hopes and the map is good and I looked the look of it. However, Waze requires you to handle your phone while driving waaaay too much. There are popups that block your map until you click to clear them off. And popups like "red light camera" warning that doesn't auto clear off. Also, the Spotify doesn't connect right, I have it connected in Spotify and Waze constantly says I need to connect it. Way too much having to pay attention to my phone while driving so back to Google maps for me!

This app has just crashed hard, can't ever recover my account, cant save home or work addresses, I just got the brand new Galaxy J7 Neo2 and it's still acting the same as it did in my Galaxy J3, Has problems pulling up local addresses, always a random state first, before you have to click over to "Places", Uninstalled Again!!

It's ok, I have found that when I am connected to android auto and my phone locks after a few mkns of inactivity, waze doesn't pick up and carry on with my location. It stops at the last moment in time my phone was unlocked. That's not good when you're relying on it to navigate.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, Karl! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue with Android Auto. We'd like to investigate this a occurrence a bit further, would you mind submitting more information here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It will make you go out of your way and add 2-3 miles to your route that is 10 minutes if it thinks it saves you 10 seconds. Also be ready to zigzag thru town with waze and/or take rough terrain, back roads, you name it! Lastly the box for directions and informations on Android auto takes half the screen. Whoever is in charge of their UX/UI need to teleport to 21st century.

LOVE WAZE!!! Google Maps cannot hold a candle to WAZE, which is reliable, finds creative/safe ways to get around traffic jams, and I trust that I am not being mislead (unlike Google Maps that would constantly take me out of the way/mislead me to a residential neighborhood while searching for a business). I enjoy the feedback regarding "police ahead" / "watch out, car on the shoulder" etc., which, if you are quick enough, verify by the touch of a button if indeed those instances are occurring.

It's mostly great, with one glaring flaw: route numbers. I don't know how road naming works in the rest of the world, but in New England, most of our "numbered routes" also have "local names" which can vary by town or county despite the route number staying constant. Often, only the numbers and not the local names appear on signs. But except for major divided highways, Waze refuses to use anything but the local names. This is a SERIOUS problem for navigation!

Love this app, very useful. The only issue is sharing your drive while using android auto or apple carplay. there isnt a way to share the drive this way, and if you do so before you connect to android auto, it will share properly, untill you stop for gas. The navigation completely stops once a-auto shuts off. The drive share is very handy for quickly and easily letting family members know where you are on the trip, and I can see employers liking this function for drivers as well.

A recent update has caused the app to appear lost - almost like satellite info is bad. My car arrow does not point to the road I'm on. Sometimes my car arrow turns into a blue dot with an area shadow around it. The voice directions are 200 ft behind the written directions - tells me to turn after I've already passed the street. Please revert to previous version. More info: It's only broken when it is connected via USB to Android Auto.

Hasn't worked right with Android auto since at least October. Used daily for a year and a half until then. Same issues as everyone else, no network, GPS doesn't work most of the time, no traffic alerts. Uninstalled/reinstalled and recent updates didn't help. Works if I only use the phone app but every other nav app I've tried works with AA just fine. Uninstalled, maybe I'll try it again someday.

This app needs to be updated because it is giving us wrong directions and we end up loosing clients. Sometimes It points you to turn to the left when you have to turn right. It sometimes you have arrived but the destination is about 500 meters away. I have tried to update on my side but it's just not working right. Thanks
replyContent:
That sounds a bit frustrating, Chris. We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We're happy to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Dear Mr. Waze, I have no serious issues with you, the only suggestion I have is that you provide alternate routes when driving towards our destination on the map and it shows a huge traffic jam. Do not drive us right into the jam and add more minutes to our commute, also please no pop ads obstructing the map view. Thank you.

I used to use this all rhe time when i had an iphone. Now that i switched to Android I find that I can't listen to podcasts using the Pocket Casts app. The podcast plays but voice instructions from Waze are silent. It looks like Waze is set up to only work with Castbox, which I prefer not to use. If they ever fix this I'll redo my review. I don't use facebook and never will so i guess I'm out of luck.
replyContent: Hi Don, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this podcast issue to investigate further. To best assist, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I only drive occasional but always use Waze. It does seen to route around the jams. One thing I would love to see is that Waze advises us on the best lane to be in. As a passage this morning, we were stuck in a long queue (using Waze) which turned out to be a left turn lane, whereas we wanted to go straight on.

This app is useless for me. Even though I put in my full address to my home, it takes me to the very start of the road, which is 5 miles away, across the canal. When looking at the destination on the map, Waze actually ignores my house number. Google Maps, Apple Maps, and MapQuest doesn't do this.

Waze is pretty much impossible to get working. Always no GPS, but how come google maps works fine on same phone ?? Also it reroutes itself randomly and sometimes not helpfully at all, on the rare times it does work. I mean you can be going down a long straight open road without any turnings for a while and it says "rerouting". It's getting worse and worse. It's confusing with the directions. A year ago it was better than google maps but now it's gone backwards in my experience anyway.

Would be better if I could mute red light camera notifications. I use this app on my commutes to make sure I can be routed around any unexpected delays, but it insists on interrupting or talking over my audio at every single red light camera, which are common near me, so I have to drive with alerts off, which defeats most of the purpose of the app. It also heavily prefers the paid tollway for even very short trips, which is a bit silly.
replyContent: Hi Katherine,thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze. We invite you to submit your request for a setting to disable the red light camera alerts to Waze's suggestion box for consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This is an excellent app. The only reason I can't give it 5 stars is because you cannot receive audio alerts of speed cameras if your traveling under the limit. Therefore if your in a variable speed limit zone reduced to 50, you don't get an alert as your under the 70mph usual speed limit. I've also accelerated when a slow driver pulled over 0.2mi from the camera, had to hit the brake as no audio alert about camera due to slower speeds of car in front. This needs to be changed.

This app performance has gone downhill. Frequent "uh oh" error message popped up while finding the address. Too slow in renavigating new routes when i went the wrong direction. Worst nightmare for users who are bad with directions. Forced me to switch to Google Maps halfway through my drive. Never improved after so long. Considering to uninstall it soon if this problem is not fixed soon.

First the bad - The app feels very cluttered sometime with animations and unnecessary bubbles. Need to tone that down. Its also sometimes very confusing to use the carpool. They need to make is more streamlined. Now the good - very smooth performance and shows correct routes. Traffic info is good and helpful. I would prefer to see the alternate route suggestion highlighted on map instead of just showing as text.

Provides better real-time info than Google Maps, but isn't always as accurate. Baffles me why the annoying 'car info' glitch still hasn't been fixed after years of user complaints. The prompt just keeps reappearing unnecessarily even after I've entered my information and takes up valuable screen real estate for no good reason. Google should really combine the best of Waze and Google Maps into one single app; pointless keeping the two separate since they own both.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback, Adrian. We'd be happy to look into this further. Please send us a private message on Facebook with more details about your issue. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It was an amazing app but for the last few months everytime I used it, it always give me more longer route.

This app used to be flawless. I used it on my drive to Florida in December and it was superb. Now it is damn near useless. Most of the time it doesn't find my location. Searches take forever and the map constantly blibs in and out. Please fix.
replyContent: Hi Carlos, thanks for your review. We'd like to hear more about your navigation and searching issues to investigate further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Thought this was a good app used it for a couple of long journeys no problem but used it last week to take my daughter to an introductory session at Longbridge school in Berwick upon tweed and the app took me into an entrance that was last used 30 years ago so uninstalled the app it's really a shame as I drive for a living as a chauffeur and i can't have my clients dropped off at the wrong destination .

If I can give a minus star, I would! Horrible app! Just horrible! I continuously received pop ups! Not regular pop ups for store products or electronics... noo... my Internet would pop up randomly and it would be pornography!!!! My son uses my phone sometimes! I'd be more angry if he saw anything! Thank God he did not, he's only 6!! I couldn't figure out what it was until I finally deleted this app and the pop ups stopped! I understand the meaning of ads/pop ups, but C'MON! TERRIBLE APP!!

It's good, but too slow. Should give more clear directions.. like stay in the middle lane. Or lanes 2 and 3. Or left or right ect. In Malaysia some roads have 3 or four points of exits and it tells you to stay left or right? 2 options for 4 exits? It's confusing. .. or say take the next left earlier on.. it's often too late.. and the map sometimes doesn't correct. So it's running slower than real time.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback, Steve! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or need help resolving an issue that may be occurring, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

Great app, but I recently was able to use the voice of The Cookie Monster as my Waze Voice and loved it, a couple days back it automatically/randomly went back to one of the the built-in Waze Voices. How can I switch back to the voice of cookie monster? I don't see an option for that now. Also a recommendation for future updates, when users want to select a Waze voice that's already in the app, play a sample of the voice so users know what they are getting into, trust me, Amy is annoying af üòÇ

I used to love Waze. I have Android Auto in my car, and even though I don't really navigate with GPS, I loved being able to see speed traps and traffic up ahead.  But as of the latest update, they now force auto-zoom. If you try to zoom, it'll reset to auto in ~15 seconds. To zoom, you have to tap the ¬± button to split it into separate + and - buttons, which reverts to the ¬± again within ~1 second. This seems pointless, why not just have a permanant + and - button? Then if you press either one, or slide the ¬± button up/down, it zooms at WARP speed! WAY too distracting while driving! Just separate + and - like Google Maps!!  Aside from that, the app is now COMPLETELY UNUSABLE: It forcefully zooms out WAY too far! Driving home at 67mph, I could see the bridge along my commute that was EIGHT MILES ahead! Even at 37 I can see the names of SEVEN TOWNS in the distance!! It's like my GPS is for a damn BOEING, not a car!!  I literally cannot use Waze until they fix this, it's useless now. Split the damn + and - into two buttons, auto-zoom need to be MUCH closer, and give me the option to DISABLE that when I want! I sent debug logs too, now please, FIX IT!

While the app is nice, it is frustrating that the they really have this habit off messing up some functions that worked perfectly before. Now this has come with the forced Google Assistant. Previously I could say an address and just drive there. Now the Google Assistant is forced on us, it doesn't understand a thing - I really mean it, I was not able to set a single address even once (I'm in Hungary). So now my usual workflow is this: I forget that the function to say an address doesn't work anymore, I start driving, tap the mic and say the address as usual, realize it's the assistant now and it will not understand it, then I try to close it but it sticks, and then I'm finally typing the address while driving in traffic - so much for safety.
replyContent: Hi Gergely, we appreciate your feedback. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We invite you to submit the idea of adding Hungarian as another language recognized by Google Assistant to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

content: Same problem as others, with latest update it no longer seems able to accurately locate where I am or what direction I'm travelling. It works fine if I set Google navigation working in the background then all of a sudden the problem resolves. It's really getting annoying having to run Google navigation everytime I want to use Waze

I love this app. It lets me know what time I'm gonna be at my destination to the minute. It lets me know about road hazards, police, and traffic. Not to mention which way is fastest. It has never got me loss. And when I was lost, I would turn in my Waze app and it would get out of being lost.

Was great now mile's and hours out of the way since Google ruined it. Ever since Google bought this they have slowly been destroying it to where it's not even worth having anymore. Now Google maps takes me direct to my destination in 9 hours and 30 minutes or 650 miles, where Waze takes me 12 hours and another hundred miles or more out of the way without even suggesting the shortest fastest route. The app has become worthless.

Decent app but the traffic updates are hit and miss, occasionally the map has patches missing, but worst of all there are adverts that pop up while navigating! Ads pop up and cover the map so you have to clear them away while driving, which is not safe. How is this app "editor's choice"?

I downloaded this app to record my voice for navigation. When driving, it doesn't use my voice to say "turn left" or any of the other ones I recorded. I've saved all the recordings, selected my own voice and still nothing. I even watched a couple tutorials on how to use the feature for the waze app so I KNOW I did it right. Very disappointed
replyContent: Hi Jade, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this voice issue to investigate further. To do so, please create a ticket for this issue: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9557145?hl=en Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: My only complaint is the car on the side of the road ahead hazard. Seems completely useless. Another thing they could do is allow you to go back over the route you travelled to report hazards you didn't have time to report while you were driving... Otherwise, Waze is the ways to go!

This used to be a great app. I uninstalled it today after weeks of malfunctions. It can no longer find my work address. It has told me to travel on closed roads. At least 50% of the time it can't find any route and gives me an error message. Truly useless.

Was extremely useful until it stopped being accurate. Why can't you send reports about construction or traffic once you're SAFELY at your destination? The app has not shown construction anywhere I've run into it causing me to be late for work a few times lately. Before people were reporting just fine. There's always users around, but this app is useless if you can't report things unless you're sitting in that exact area. How dangerous and ridiculous.
replyContent: Hi Lauren, thank you for your feedback. We completely understand your concern. Please note that you must be as close as possible to the incident when reporting it. To report hand free and safely, you can use Google Assistant. Here's how: tinyurl.com/y8c8spjs For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Consistently over zealous on arrival times. 95% of the time you will arrive later than Waze expects. likes to route you to impossible left turns. Half the time you open the app you get no traffic or road reports until you close and reopen. The app is only good as a way of alerting you to police ahead or crashes that aren't yet on Google Maps.

Every time you stop at a light or stop sign an ad will pop up, then periodically, waze will ask "have you seen ads from these companies?" then list 4 companies. like it's my job to fuel waze's greed for profit over a functioning app. I can only assume this is one of the reasons the app is so slow. it'll make sure to rip through your data usage too. just use Google maps instead.

This is a great navigation app. but it's too heavy!! for example if you want to see the direction overview and zoom in & out, you would be in a trouble! specially when you are driving. movement on map isn't operated softly.

Have had multiple occurances of Waze getting lost on straight roads and multiple cases of being lost for hours because Waze cannot direct itself properly. Was once lost in backstreets of London for over an hour because it kept changing it's mind as to what direction to go in and couldn't comprehend that a road was closed despite being 'community driven' and there being 20,000 users in the area. Maps outdated, directs to go left down a pedestrian only path. Signal is regularly weak. Do not use!!

content: I used to love this app but now it not accurate at all. I put the address in and it will take me to wrong location. It happened multiple time, I checked the address and make sure everything was correct but still same results. Why is it SO difficult to change your start location?!?! It takes me half an hour every time as it's so unnecessarily hidden. Please add a separate icon for this right where you select your destination. I would use this every day if it had that.

content: Works good when traveling.
Best navigation app.

While driving from Grafton Illinois to Minneapolis we were in a lot of areas where Waze was not connecting to the network. However Google Maps worked just fine in the same areas. in all areas we had four bars on our cell phone. we also ran into areas where Waze just drops on us and leaves us not knowing where to go. When we try to re-enter the route it says the servers are busy or some error like that. Waze was my App of choice for the last 3 years. I can no longer rely on Waze.

Experience driving like you've never experienced it before. Know when your coming up to speed camera's, hidden or fixed at traffic lights. Same with red light cameras also. Its interactive so you can put your own points of interest for other Wazers to see and use. Whether it be plotting a hidden speed camera or debris on the highway or broken down vehicle. This driving experience is in your hands.

content: By far the most useful app on my phone, I love that each user can add different reports to the live map for others to see and be made aware of. Simple things like road closure, hazard, car crash and banked up traffic. Although i do use it for the cameras and police feature mainly it still does not take away from the other useful reports other WAZE Users can add to the map. I live in SE Melbourne, Australia and when I first decided to use the app i thought I bet hardly anyone around me uses it but I was proved wrong pretty fast as I could personally see other users on the live maps and so many reports being made and updated so frequently. Compared to my in car GPS Unit, this app gets used so much more, well basically I have pretty much stopped using the GPS Unit all together besides for the function it has to see my baby girl in tin her car seat in the backseats with the wireless baby cam it came with. MUST HAVE APP FOR EVERYBODY! SPREAD THE LOVE FOR WAZE! GLAD MY MATE RECOMMENDED IT, GOOGLE MAPS AND CAR GPS ARE NOW REDUNDANT!

content: Great app except that i don't think it has offline capabilities... So if for example i lose my signal during the navigation what happens? The other day it got a bit confused of the routes because of this... If you add the option to navigate with only the gps on, then 5 stars from me!!!

This app was the best app for driving. It was talking and you could drive without looking on your phone.
