I love this app! I can tell me what time i need to leave inorder to reach my destination for the time that i specify. It rakes into account current traffic conditions and sends me alerts for leaving a bit earlier or later so that i reach my destination when i want to. It gives me heads up for objects in the roadway or construction. It rarely, if ever sends me to the wrong location. I recommend it to everyone, especially highway/interstate commuters!

Great App, have been using Waze for a few months now and I think everyone should be using it! One thing for developers can you please add more user statistics. Total kms driven for the week and total for lifetime would be great. Being able to see other users kms and points etc. At the moment to see kms driven I have to log onto the website. I think more acheivements should be added too. Examples - Miles/kms driven - 1000/10000/50000 etc. Obeying traffic rules (speeds) Keep it up!

The last few weeks to a month, the app has been freezing or telling me there is no GPS signal. You have to close it down and restart it. Hopefully this will be fixed soon.

It's ok as far as map/traffic apps go, just be forewarned that the time to destination changes continuously when stuck in traffic, as one would expect. This GPS always good ! just a little adjustnent to other places . Does not work well with android.

needs calibration, delayed, slow and bogged down. too many features/settings added. super slow ineffective app compared to what if was 3 years ago. gone way downhill. the only benefit is it keeps up with road closures and traffic. seems to crash alot, close randomly for no reason, "calculating routes..." seems to take several minutes and sometimes never quits(freezes up) compared to years ago took under 10 seconds.

Great idea, but the app has a lot of bugs, especially when there are multiple riders.. moreover no one cares to respond to the issue raised. Some bugs are reduced, but looks like the rules of car pooling with multiple car poolers need to be more flexible.. maybe a flexible range needs to be established to reduce drop out of the second rider.

I've used Waze for ages, it gets me to my destination, avoiding traffic jams, roadworks and other obstacles. I'm really surprised when I mention it to people that they've never heard of it. It's social travel that keeps us in the loop with other drivers on the same roads. Thanks Waze and all you lovely Wazers xx Edit Fri 5th March. See above. Still awesome.

Easy to use, yes, but, I really wish it had a few more options, one, to stay off of parkways, rather than just staying off toll roads, two, a truck route, and three, a way to avoid, or reroute around certain roads and/or bridges.

I love most of the features, but my main frustration is that they will release some voices for limited use only. Maybe I want to keep that voice as my main voice. Futurewise, I find it funny that Google maps is slowly stealing away some of the things that differentiate the Waze app. I prefer the way that Google maps shows which lane to be in. I prefer Waze for virtually other other navigation feature.

I hate this app. It does not use any common sense. I don't want to drive 10 miles out of the way to save 2 minutes. Heck, I don't want to drive 5 miles out of the way. And I definitely don't want to drive through some uninhabited back road, or rough dangerous looking neighborhoods just to save a few minutes. Uninstalled this stupid app.

I like Waze over others except in one area. I can not get to stay on top of other apps while running. This is a major problem when I need to use other apps or access to home screen while enroute. There seems no setting to enable that and app settings and permissions doesn't have it as a feature to enable. Unfortunately that makes it a backup or route check and not a very good navigation tool.

I dont know why everytime it will not run in the background when screen is locked. I ride a motorcycle and really depend on maps for navigation to places and most time i didn't look at the map, instead i listen to the voice direction. The previous version was perfect as it doesnt shut down even when my phone is locked. But nowadays when it interagates with spotify, spotify will work on screen lock but waze will shut down. Can you please look in to this

content: Worse than Google Maps in London, UK. Despite Waze's reputation I have found that on multiple drives every week in and around London Waze will consistently choose slower routes than Google Maps. Google owns Waze and all that data gets brought into Google Maps but Google Maps has the advantage of tracking all the other Google Maps drivers journeys, providing far more accurate journey times and quicker routes.

My favourite app. I use it daily. I wanted to give 5 stars but I think 4 are enough because: 1. I have an issue with login/signout. untill now I am not sure what account I am using or how many accounts I have. I was using a Galaxy S8, LG K4 2017, HUAWEI P9. And my actual device is a Galaxy A5 2017. Thanks.

Great app but in Android auto too much the screen is used up on useless things like a blue gradiant on the top. You guys need to overhaul the Android auto screen completely. Also regardless of if i say show speed limit always or not the app only shows me the speed limit when it wants to.

Tried this as an alternative to Google maps, which I'm often having trouble with. Turns out Waze is completely unusable, incomprehensible and hopelessly outdated. I mistakenly thought Waze was "the other big one", but this utter mess of a failed app is a joke. Don't waste your time, you'll just get frustrated.

content: I had no problems with Waze at first then changed phones and it went pretty bad. Back with a functional phone again (Samsung) and it seems it was never the Waze app but the phone interfering with it. I never thought that was possible. I'm loving Waze again and haven't got a bad word.

Only thing missing now is the feature to share driving location from within Android Auto In-Car display. I always have to start Waze on my phone, get the required route, share the drive, and then I can finally connect to my car. I have tried assessing Waze on my phone when connected to my car, but it doesn't let me enter the app. Really inconvenient if I'm already on the go.

This app has gone crazy! It continually announces distance travelled and average times etc. even when it is turned off. I have erased it several times but the problem persists. I have turned it off, turned off sound, turned off notices etc and the problem cannot be overridden. I can't find a solution on line so goodbye Waze. Too bad, I really liked it but the announcements go off and very inconvenient times.

This app is highly unreliable. It takes FOREVER to reroute leaving you scrambling to figure out where you're suppose to be going. AND more times than not it says the server is down. Prefer Google maps, it may not show me where cops are not at least I can depend on it to work!

Have used a few times now in my car, in parallel with a built in sat nav ( 2012 SEAT). which is obviously not particularly live and a bit out of date. The warnings of hazards ahead works well and can get average road speed ahead based on other waze users. Has on a number of occasions given a better choice of route than the other satnav. areas for improvement are... not always easy to tell which direction on the carriageway has a problem. uses the phone battery significantly.

App is just okay. My speedometer and waze don't agree. Inconsistent alerts, sometimes audible sometimes nothing. Disconnects my phone calls. Have to use on board navigation and doesn't run through my car sound system like Android Auto. Uninstalling the app. Sad that it was not an improvement or a convenience.

Tried using it in Saint-Petersburg, Russia, because it's supported by Android auto while Yandex navigator (popular and most functional in Russia) is not. So, my standard commute work-home in a traffic busy evening: google maps ETA 1h15m, Yandex ETA 1h10m and waze ETA 0h!30!m. I tried waze just for fun (it wasn't) and spent like 1h30m instead of waze's half-hour promise. Absolutely unusable for traffic busy cities of Russia. Google maps lag behide yandex but at least they have close-to-real ETAs.

Keeps thinking I'm driving the wrong way. The only way to calibrate the compass is by using Google maps. Speedometer has disappeared, and the zoom keeps referring to fully zoomed in, not zooming out some at highway speed like it used to. The wrong way thing causes it to constantly recalculate and makes it unusable. I have to switch back to Google maps until this is fixed. Running the latest version on an s10.

content: EDIT: in the latest version, Waze GPS localization is now better (if keeping the phone power saving OFF). There still some moments where the localization lags behind but the app is now usable. Please keep improving it, some features are great. Also, please add the option to flag a forced deviation on the road (due to roadworks), at the moment I can flag either roadworks or map errors, but a forced deviation is different and worth flagging to other users to save their time. Thanks

content: Downloaded this app a week ago. This app has the potential to be amazing but currently it's just garbage & a waste of space on my phone. It drains your battery extremely quickly, it takes you to the wrong locations, takes you the longest route possible & it constantly looses connection with the network. It lost connection several times in the last 4 days then yesterday it completely lost connection & has been stuck that way since.

The app is a little too cartoony for me. I personally do not like the built in drop pins advertising some stores. Routes well. I have noticed that my music player column will drop when the voice guidance comes on. I will have to turn up the music each time.
replyContent:
Hi, Andrew! Thank you for the review, we appreciate the feedback. If you have any more feedback on the app, feel free to to let us know through Facebook. We would love to hear from you.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It's fine and did everything it said it did, I only have one very RAGE inducing complaint though, you can't save more than one favorites location saved. If you already have favourite a location and want to add another you found along the way for later, it is EXTREMELY Difficult to do so Also, the time shown on the app is very much wrong and doesn't follow local time

Used to be my number 1 GPS application on the go whenever i wanted to head somewhere i am not familiar with. However recently it keeps loading and unable to detect my location. It even take me to a road where the it takes a few minutes longer to my destination when o rely on it to avoid jams, in the end i trusted my guts and go with the road i predict for not being congested and beat waze it's ETA. I am writing this review it's because i care and i would hope there will be a change in Waze.

Why did they change it ? When I select the addres bar I want to start typing not go to another imput window. When I hit go I expect it to go not require more input. Was great then added more steps to start navigatin. I only use it as the passenger and it irritates me how long it takes to slog through the GUI . Watching 5mph traffic is better.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback. We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you're experiencing an issue with Waze, we'd love to help you with that. Feel free to leave us a private message on Facebook with more details of what's occurring. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: My customers can count on my arrival time. They always joke with me that they can set their clock by my arrival time. Waze is my secret sauce. I am amazed at how your platform (AI & ML) can take into account traffic conditions and my lead-foot in generating my ETA. I wonder if it could predict when I will get lucky? Seriously, Waze is the best!

Great product, but so unstable in android auto (the only way I can use it realistically) that I have to find a new navigation app. Waze memory leaks so hard that it crashes my phone multiple time per drive. Have submitted back reports many times. Fix this and I'm happy to return my review to five stars.

I have used this app for a few years now. The friends feature is rather broken for me now. my wife has the app but despite us both being in each others contacts the app has no idea. i have no other friends either despite then being contacts lol. It can also go a bit loopy when signal is lost and needs to be closed and reopened. Recently it has started to find new routes just before exits. The persistent speed limit sign is very handy and if it wasn't for this i would be back on Google maps.

Waze is fun, as long as you don't need accuracy. It will take you on wild goose chases, it told me to take a right when I got to work today, my job site is on the left, it's fun, but I don't need games when I navigate. Second time I've Uninstalled, I'm done!
replyContent: Hi Ed, thank you for your feedback. We hope to see you return to Waze in the future, as we‚Äôre always looking to improve. Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to be fine but has been completely messing up GPS the last few times I've used it and provided awful directions.

App is pretty good, but... You need a button that says "CLEAR", so when you're driving and someone has "police" checked on the map, but nothing's there when YOU go through the same location. Need a way to update it and clear it off ASAP. ALSO... I took a shortcut and "Waze" REFUSED to accept MY path and would ONLY try to make me go it's way!!! JUST NO!!! It should automatically adjust no matter what!update*** It's ur app, u pass it on! + Put back in characters. It's boring now.
replyContent: Hi Debbie, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. content: An absolute essential while on roads while in USA. Amazingly accurate and prompt guidance and notifications. The rerouting capabilities of this app is very useful and ofcourse the hazard and other notification to maneuver right in time. Even the most complex interactions are easy when Waze is on. Highly recommended.

Used Waze years ago. Never let me down and was the best GPS/route application EVER! However, I do wish they would make it trucker friendly (CDL DRIVERS NEED THIS APP FOR THAT DESPERATELY!). (truck routes, bridge high etc.). Logged many miles with this app, until I needed a truck GPS. Now that I'm back over the road, I am forced to use Google maps, since I don't possess a truck GPS (knowing Google owns Waze now and has integrated many of it's features) I'm going to give it another go....

It is cool app to use when it works. But takes quite bit of data plan compared to Google maps or any other app and also have few bugs to be addressed. Not able to edit the pool ride pricing. my first ride end up calculating as free ride and did not give an option to update or set my own requirement. Few riders also complained that it did not work few days.

This app is very dangerous. Gave me incredibly wrong directions, like on every turn it was telling me to go in the opposite direction from where I needed to go. If I needed to turn left it would tell me to take a right; if I had to take a highway west, it would tell me to take it east and so on. Luckily I had printed directions also and I had to pull over every time to look at them. Very dangerous. I am uninstalling this app right away.

It was fun while it lasted but apparently the developers have stopped updating it because it constantly crashes and loses GPS signal. if it will work at the beginning it will eventually freeze up before I reach my destination. very unreliable now.
Wonderfull experince with this App, it took me saftly to and from my destination without incident. "Love This App".

Had this installed on my Huawei Mate 9 recently. Within 4 weeks use, the app started acting weirdly with some media volume window suddenly appearing and I was unable to make it go. Phone also became quite hot on a 2 hour journey using the app. Phone then began restarting by itself until finally the phone blacked out and would not restart. A factory reset failed to work and professional engineers could not repair it. The phone was working well gor 18 months before this and always had latest update

Fine app when used on a phone, but terrible experience when interfacing with 2018 Subaru media units. Functionality on the media unit display via Android Auto was problematic, ie disappearing report traffic button after changing navigation route and lack of navigating to point on map. Also a counterproductive bug report process when it came to diagnosing Android Auto media unit problems, requiring steps impossible during a normal drive. More fun to use than Google Maps, but not reliably better.

This is not a quality navigation app. Being acquired by Google, doesn't make it better. Some routes planed with Waze are neither fast, nor short, especially in my country. One positive thing about this app is the function to get notifications on road events and police, but that is an unreliable feature as it sometimes just do not notify with voice, but only display icon on the map.
replyContent: Hi Kamen, thanks for bringing up these issues. We'd like to look into it further. To best assist, please send us a private message on Facebook with more details. Thanks again! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This used to be my favorite app. But as of the last few months, it's been pretty much just absolute garbage. From the app searching for routes but going back to default and saying "the server timed out", to the app also just flat out crashing in the middle of navigation. It's basically useless to me now.

When using Waze be very careful! Waze has the ability to absolutely, positively get you killed. Some of the directions it provides are very dangerous especially if you dont know the area in which you are driving. My advice - shrink the map to see where Waze is taking you. While the route Waze provides might save you a minute or two it is absolutely not worth it. Just remember you dont need to follow Waze exactly. If the directions seem unsafe keep driving until you feel safe then follow Waze.

I'm not sure what happened whether the update on Skip side or Waze side broke the application. When I tap on the destination in Skip, it redirects to Waze then it gives me directions to where I want to go but now, I have to type in the address manually every time. If the devs see this review, please look into it and find the root cause then fix it. Thank you.

On 10/05/19 we got slapped with toll roads IN SPITE of having chosen Avoid Toll Roads way in advance. If you have a passenger with you screen capture the directions. We wished we did. This is the second time Waze LIED about no tolls. Wonder if they are getting kickbacks from the state lying about tolls. Will use alternate directions.

I enjoyed the app for a long time until it started saying people driving to me from an hour away would arrive in 10 minutes. And now its nearly impossible to correctly add a stop along a route!!!! Change it back to the old way of adding stops. This is horrible.

This is easily one if the worst apps I have ever had the displeasure of using. Wayne promises a wide variety of tools to make it the best GPS out there. it states that it can calculate traffic, find alternate routes, and mark obstacles like pot holes and police on your route. In each of these regarded Waze fails miserably. good luck to you if your using this app the creators should be ashamed if themself for peddling such a terrible product.

The Waze service on Android Auto could use some attention: 1. The speed limit needs to be a large icon/don't; make the same size as Google Maps speed limit in Android Auto. 2. In Android Auto, directions for upcoming turns and road names does not complete, it will just stop, almost like being interrupted mid sentence. Please address these issues.

Good mostly. I like the alerts and usually works well. But lately it's been off. No warning about up coming turns. Last week it took me the longest route possible and while driving on the course set by it, it kept changing the route. So I'm hoping it gets better but I find it unreliable for the moment
replyContent: Hi Fodder, we're happy to help. Try reinstalling the app and make sure that you're using the latest app version. content: Last update ruined this app! Notifications are late, you're on top of a hazard/police car before you're notified; can no longer look ahead on route to see upcoming reports; üëç/üëé with running count was easier to use and more useful than current "still there/not still there" option, especially when driving: your music feature is useless. Very disappointed in how this app works now!

content: Getting tired on your "uh oh" and "error searching network" messages. It getting more frequent after update like everytime you used it. Even when these error seem resolved on screen, route displayed but not the road or traffic status. I hope the review is not just for your reading purpose but action instead. You used to be the best, don't turn your waze to waste pls

This app has turned to garbage... I loved waze, I have been having the same issue most are having; annoying ads, constant drops in GPS, maps taking 5 minutes or more to load. Nothing seems to be done to fix it, so i have to resort to google maps. I will have to saldly continue using google until waze decides to address and fix these app breaking problems.

Was excellent in the beginning. However the last few months, the app does not keep up with the vehicle. At times, jumping to completely different routes to what I am on! Lags at times. Just not as reliable anymore. Used to love using it.
replyContent:

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Brilliant satnav. There are only 2 downsides. 1st its not offline. 2nd it crashes on routes longer than 300 miles (at least on my phone). Still I'm giving 5 star because real time traffic update is fantastic. Especially when you have active drives on same road while your journey. Reporting issues/problems on road is easy and intuitive. I can recommend this satnav application to every one with decent mobile contract - 1GB per month is more than enough for this app. Download it NOW! Be Happy!

Almost useless! Perhaps some stupid regulations, but Waze removed petrol prices even when searching for gas stations + the removal of speed traps notifications. Now it just a random navigation app without offline navigation and with slooow interface in heavy traffic, extremely limited interoperability for ways to manage a big number of POI. Totally disappointing!

ü§ó I love my Waze-GPS. I would highly recommend Waze-GPS. Easy to use and very accurate on directions. Advises warnings of road conditions like accidents and police ahead. Great GPS for someone that's going on vacation. If you don't have was downloaded on your phone it's great. I use it everyday and it has not failed me yet for 3 years. üòÅ

Hello! BC of the limit I'll quickly give just couple Pros/Cons. So Pro: Easy for the most part to use. Pro: App does have save for later trips. Big Con: It's extremely & for anyone new in using apps like this, basically Impossible to figure out how to use the save as a favorite secton (üíó say more but ya knw) lastly a IMO suggestion, I'd love to see a feature added giving us an option to in realtime save routes.

Been using this app for aboit 4 yrs now....used to be great, reliable..now its horrible. Totally unreliable - frequently forgets your trip if you switch to another app, and is no longer navigating you, but you dont know that and end up past your turns. Also it frequently does not give instructions in time to make turns when it is actually navigating you. And, finally it is horrible about getting you started in the right direction, the maps is zoomed so far in, with no compass or street names.
sent to wrong locations a few times

Fantastic, its basically a verry accurate Maps app that has all of the capabilities of google maps or apple maps, but also allows you to find out where all of the speed cameras, police, roadworks and even pot holes for those low guys out there. Hugely recommend this app why would you not use it, never worry about a speeding ticket again, you wont get one!

Lots of power, zero accountability. Routes hundreds of cars simultaneously through tiny neighborhoods not meant for rush hour traffic. Stuck 10s of minutes at single stop signs which were not meant for handling high volume traffic flow. Constantly see other cars not let people out of their own driveways. The exerience creates miserable drivers who would have been better off on main roads or freeways, and miserable neighborhood residents. No one wins.

Long time user. It's got worse over time. Just like others mentioned: GPS loses connectivity, direction is not correct sometimes, not appearing on the correct road, and taking FOREVER to get the route needed. I'm switching to Google Maps because it's a GPS that actually works.

I would give this app zero stars, if possible. Waze used to be my navigation app of choice, but updates have caused major failures. It reroutes me for no reason and sends me miles out of my way. Distance is incorrect and all notifications occur AFTER the correct turn. The police ahead notification is useless if I've already passed the officer. It's also added an average of 15 minutes additional time to my trips the past several times I've used the app.

content: Had the app for a few months. With the ability to mark roadworks etc is good. However you can only report on the route you are travelling, so if a road is close off a junction you pass you can't report it. The update for music integration has ruined it, cannot connect with Spotify anymore.

Been using waze super apps for 3 yrs, indication of turning eg: 5km turn right/left was clear , but recent update was terrible so many indication arrow that doesn't match the road marking, while travelling in highway expect driver to turn left/ right in 100m,. Have to uninstalled everyday, to get to the original, reliable waze apps, feeling frustrated

content: Just giving it 3 star because it's a cool app and has good potential, however the gps tracking hardly works anymore. Great a year ago, but now loses gps signal every 5 minutes causing me to miss more exits than I can count, loses signal under other roads/bridges and wont find you until you close and rerun the app from beginning, very annoying!

love this app but I have a hefty suggestion : FIX : add to route. I love all the police warning, object in road, hazard warnings. But adding a stop is NOT intuitive and the results from said searches are awful. so much so, that you literally need to go to Google maps. results for things like gas station on an already established route show you unrelated, and mostly unsorted results! unacceptable considering shared logistics /ownership (AFAIK). 5 star app, 3.5 star after considering secondary

content: I've been using this since the beginning. I've noticed the app had gotten unstable over the last 6+ months and does not load correctly. Every time i open the app I have to Force Stop it then reopen it, otherwise it does not load correctly. It either loads to a blank white screen or will be waiting for the network when I try to navigate.

This app is a lifesaver. Warned us ample time in advance of a foreign object on the road. Was able to avoid a collision with a wooden object about 1 metre x 15 cm which would have definitely made an abrupt end to our vacation. Highly recommended.

It's great to get live updates from real people who use the app. Friendly interface, takes a little getting used to if You're only familiar with iOS, well worth the learning curve though. Admittedly I still use Google maps to find locations initially, but then just copy and paste the address two Waze.

Great app. I kinda like it better than maps. It's very informant! Let's u know about accidents ahead of u before u even see it. Therefore maybe making it easier & less time consuming if u have to b somewhere...like work! Also good to know when police are around so u can slow down & save yourself a ticket! Even let's u know of something blocking traffic. All around great app! Highly recommend!!

I didn't realize you had to view reports only from the map. I was mad at first because there's no option like a shortcut to see all reports around your location, but you just have to zoom in and out of the map to see reports I guess, or am I missing something? 5 stars when this is implemented.

Lately the app has been taking strange routes. Through neighborhoods, down alleys, and lots of unnecessary turns. It evens refuses to change to the direct route in the list. It suggested a route going down something I don't think qualified as a street. If you are trying to get users to stop using the app it's working.

content: Wouldn't let to remove the report!! If for example police is not there anymore, but the report thing is still on the road, that makes it very inaccurate! And when reporting, it should allow to change the location, as you can't realy do it while you driving, so again, it will not be very accurate when you will do it when you stop in a little while...

content: Love the way waze warns users of upcoming things on the way, specially cops, but hate the way keeps logging you off and have to create new password and stuff every time I use it, to the developers, do not ask me to email you to help me with this issue, just fix it and make everyone happy, I am sure I am not the only one tired of annoying updates that all it does is get things worse!
replyContent: Hi Louis, we're sorry to hear about your issue and appreciate the feedback. Sending us details about the issue will help us solve it quicker. Feel free to contact us via Facebook private message. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: WAZE has saved me from countless delays due to construction, accidents, and weather. Well worth the price. Oh, wait...it's FREE!!! Hardly seems fair to the developer! Tried Google Maps...hated it. She never stops yammering!! Certainly makes for distracted driving.

will not connect to spotify no matter what I try. Directions in my use have also been inaccurate, slow and it's less reliable at finding addresses in the first place than other mapping services. Idea behind it is good and useful but not worth the downsides, especially considering a lot of the reporting functions are being added to google maps anyway.

The list is endless. GPS/network randomly lose signal while driving. Fonts shrink to unreadable sizes for weird reasons. Crazy algorithm which should prioritize routes based on ETA/traffic, somehow decides to always avoid highway even when the box is unchecked, then takes me through the worst roads. GPS positioning lags behind real time so that I already passed a turn/exit before noticing. And my favorite: having you drive long distance when your destination is right in front of you.

content: Since the Mayor decided to extend the congestion charge I have noticed Waze now gives the toll option only - even if you have it on your settings to avoid any charge!? So back to Google Maps as we still get the free route. Really disappointed and will no longer recommend to others. Don't bother with this app anymore, seems like they have sold out.

Unstable in routing calculation. Mostly when I check a route about 2000km, the one I am interested , it does not do the calculation of the route. Always pop up a message that something went wrong! Rarely I can see this 2000Km route calculated. Without stability and Android Auto not supporting Sygic makes me disappointed for google services.

Offers routes with indication of issues on the route but you can not expand it so see what it is. It could be an accident but you can not see it .Also seems heavy on data usage. Would be better if I could tell it which route to go by setting my own Via.

content: I love it, it's a great app so I can travel. I have no since of direction at all. I love that waze tells you where to turn long before you're supposed to turn, it gives you plenty time to turn where you need to go! Best app ever!

Please reply if possible. I have Galaxy Tab S2 with Android 10 and for some reason only Waze does not work. I mean I checked all the settings. GPS shows my location correctly but the driving and road tracking do not work! Shows connecting to GPS showing approximate location o something like that... Why is that? Other GPS programs works fine, but I really need Waze because it's the best. Maybe there is some solution that I don't see here? Will change the rating to 5 üåü for any help! :)

content: Things I like, it's completely free, I can help with making it better, other Wazer's tell me things like hazards, policemen traps, has GPS speed and speed limits (sometimes wrong, but I can get them fixed). Works on both android auto & apple car play, can be set to night mode, but you have to really search for that feature. I can help with making the map/app better. We use it all the time. I don't notice the amount of internet it uses, I can not be very much.

This app is a privacy nightmare.....you can only delete one history item at a time, at least with Google maps you can delete your while history at one time. Just realized this app was keeping my history going back for 5 years.....I am not going delete one history item at a time for hundreds of items, I'll just delete the whole account and set up a new one..... VERY POOR DESIGN

This app is so stupid. I love the fact that it gives you traffic updates but its gotten us lost on the last 3 road trips. It gives you obscure routes then reroutes and reroutes until you're in the middle of nowhere. Don't trust this app route info, it's the worst map I've ever used!!!!
replyContent: We're so sorry to hear about your bad experience, Mary. Could you please send us the route details via Facebook private message? We'd like to look into this further. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Tried it did not like it, in my view google map is more simpler and straight to point. too much distraction while driving for me on waze, sorry. plus the fact that it tries to keep you moving from back road to another is not always a good thing as if you wait few more minutes behind traffic in original route you get there quicker. anyway keep you moving (even if it takes longer to get to distination ) is not bad for all I guess i.e for taxi driver:)

Always gets me where I need to go without getting pulled over & helps me warn people about potholes and other road dangers. Low-profile tires are a B to maintain... Just wish the carpool function could be more on-demand: Let people ask for an immediate ride to a pre-input destination? Just because riders are going somewhere doesn't mean the route Waze planned will intersect with yours. Missing out on a lot of riders when really we're going to the same place. Should pull bus. info from GMaps too

I don't know what's going on but the past few months the GPS has just been all over the place. Getting off and on exits on highways for no reason, going through unnecessary areas, and not being able to catch up with itself after leaving a parking space (just to name a few). It's become dangerous.
