content: the best GPS app period. would be great if it had settings that would only suggest new routes based on percentages of a faster route. On a trip it would only suggest a route if it were a minimum of 5%, 10%, or 20% etc. faster. Sometimes on a 2 hour trip it will have you leave the Freeway just to save 3 mins. This setting would avoid this. Also wish it would provide road alerts without having a destination, just while idle and open. I use Waze every time I drive great app!

Best interactive map app available. Consistently gives better directions and quicker routes than Google (Yes I know Google bought them, but it still performs better). Sometimes I have both running at the same time just to check. Also, the user interface is more intuitive, and reporting features are far superior.

Worst navigation I have seen. It drives me to go around without any reason. I drive straight e.g. In road A, it directs me to go out of A into B and then re-enter A. That way is more difficult, more distance, slower etc. I kept going straight in B which was easier etc. Speed limits are wrong, it doesn't notify every time i exceed the limit and so on. Stupid app. I uninstall it.

I love my Waze app! BUT I have been trying to log into my account on my new phone, I put in my phone number, hit login, it brought up my username & all, I clicked on yes, it's me & it has been saying connecting with the circle going around forever now.. I even tried updating my app.. I just want to get into my account! Please fix!!! I have emailed support & opened a ticket for help.. Hopefully once fixed I will deff give 5 stars!!

I like this app but it is very buggy. often stops running, on long distances says it can't find a route, even though the previous week it worked. On long routes often just stops working usually just as you need the next directional instruction. But dont be put off if you can put up with the issues the information is great and very useful. Using Andriod version.

I never leave home without switching Waze on. Waze directs me all the way and makes me avoid massive traffic congestions. It keeps me updated on the traffic flow and at the same time am able to search for nearest petrol stations and places of interest nearby or on the way. The developers may want to look into "New Drive" with an option which one we wish to go first and continue with the drive. Thank you and Waze has been of great help to me.

Needs a commercial vehicle setting... keeps routing my work truck onto "No Commercial Vehicles Allowed" routes and then I have to double back losing time and struggle to find a new route while driving because Waze won't stop rerouting back to same route ü§¨ I'm gonna try the taxi setting and see how that works out... if not it's back to Google maps
replyContent: Hi Michel, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit this commercial vehicle setting idea to the Waze suggestion box for careful consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

content: I enjoy Waze but it takes age to calculate routes over about 30 minutes long, chooses the weirdest routes (wants me to go north so I can get to work south, +15 minutes out of the way). The carpool adverts are annoying. The speed limit advisory isn't accurate at all. I do like the notifications though. I run Google Maps for navigation and let Waze sit in the background for the alerts.

I'll give 3 because of the following reasons: 1. the carpool list takes forever to pull data 2. Connecting to Android car play sometimes doesnt pull the destination route and crashes. 3. The app UI needs to support pickup and dropoff smart notifications so that the user doesnt need to open the app, and go the specific carpool ride and click on navigate to and choose the options.

This app would get 5 stars if it had the double tap, hold, and slide up and down to zoom like Google Maps does. The zoom + and - button is annoying, and the pinch-to-zoom is difficult as well because it needs two fingers. It would be nice have the single finger double tap and slide to zoom in the overview and centered displays. PLEASE ADD!

Love this and would give 5* if it wasn't for the intrusive info ads while driving. Not helpful when your trying to see where your going and have an ad in the way for McDonald's saying it's 4 miles away. Then you have to take your hands off the wheel to swipe it off..Not very safe
Very great app for use always.

I would like to see the app upgrade to using your camera to record you driving. In case of accident. Coming up on exits maybe like garmen have exit pop up showing direction. Sometimes is difficult to see. Also, if traffic ahead is at a standstill. Have tell you then ask for alternative routes so you dont be stuck in accident.

The best GPS app I tried ever. usually I use it on my car vertical android screen, and the experience would be better if I'd can change the speedometer position. Now the speedometer is on the left bottom of the screen, and I need to down my eyes to see that. if there would was option to change it to left upper position, would be perfect to me. Thanks!

Best navigation app at the moment. However, it's not perfect: when you drive through a longer tunnel and you lose GPS signal, it will not update the speed and distance. Since my car's navigation still works, I assume waze could have an algorithm that estimates the speed based on the acceleration sensor and update the distance traveled.

Waze is the best and my favourite navigation app. I love the traffic alerts and waze will navigate around it. Same with alerts for police and hazards. But to give it 5 stars I would need it to have not just car navigation but walking and cycling etc. Like google maps does. Another feature which wont affect my review is being able to enable something in settings to give someone the ability to navigate to where I am. Without me having to know exactly where I am to tell them. Got ideas on how.

Great app! Great need to add options for potholes & speedbumps and information about changing lanes in advance.It would be good to have junctions marked different colour for easy identification.I have more suggestions, please contact me if you want more details. Now Like I phone üì± maps tells you red-light and Give way to stop ‚úã sings comes so so good

Used to be good. Now too many ads that block the screen. Navigate home...."would you like to visit McDonald Automotive?" Uh, no...."would you like to visit compass credit union?" No. I want to go HOME!..."would you like to visit John Elway automotive?" You know, I was wanting to get home for dinner, but come to think of it, I should suddenly buy a new car!! Lame.

Could never find gps using android on samsung 7. No problem with gps on Google drive. First Waze FAQ dealt with this problem and had a detailed set of instructions on how to fix it if you had an iphone. For android all it said was to contact network admin. Using Vetizon LTE so that is a joke. Uninstalled and back to using Google drive which has no gps isdues.
I have not used..get.

Waze has always had a lag issue with me. The GPS marker is always a few seconds behind where I'm actually at in real time. It makes it difficult to navigate in areas where the streets are so close together. Google Maps has never presented lag problems to me.

This is one best navigation app I've ever come across. Everything is covered in Waze..the speedometer is very accurate, being able to know ahead of time when there are hazards or police along my route, the new addition of being able to control my music app without having to leave out Waze and being able to ask for assistance through the app is pretty awesome i haven't had to use that function yet thankfully...the whole app is so simple to use its a must have

Better than Google maps, but has bugs. Every time I open it, it has connection issues and I have to close the app and restart it before it can find routes. Lately it will not connect at all, and at the worst possible time, while Google maps will at least calculate routes. Very disappointed.

Doesn't calculate route and there's always an error when trying to get an address. I've had to reopen about 10 times. A couple times it just closes by itself and it won't navigate me! Continuously says oops something went wrong. I've uninstalled and reinstalled and now it won't even open. States that there is a connection issue.

Constantly tries to route me in circles to get on Parkways around my area. I don't like to use these roads since they are windy with limited visibility. The app doesn't learn anything from my driving habits, Constantly barking commands to U-turn to get back where I just came from. Pretty much rendering it useless.
replyContent: Hi John, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. To have the "avoid parkways" option added to the app, please submit it to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Loved using this app for past 3 months even though there are few defects. Waze was a great and cheapest alternative to commute to work. Now its becoming painful using this app. keep getting Network error 101. I checked with few colleagues they have the same problem. I then reported to waze Support, sent logs but never resolved. it's been a week. I really wonder why this defect still exists in production!

Waze used to be good, but in recent months it's just unusable. 9 out of 10 times it has difficulty to find a route and keep loading forever or just straight out fail to connect. Looks like Google is abandoning Waze and focusing on Google Map instead. Google Map is fast to load and doesn't over promise the arrival time. I've given Waze enough time but they don't seem to be capable of fixing the apparent issues for several months, so they deserve this poor rating at least for this version.

I normally love this and I love it in my car however recently I find I have to shut it off because of the new feature of railroad track alerts. There should be a setting that allows you to turn that off. I live in an area where everywhere I go there's a railroad track in its constantly going off and it makes no sense for me to keep listening to it. After reply and a bunch of tries, finally got it to work. Thank you.
replyContent:
We understand how that can be frustrating, Lisa. Here's some good news: you can disable the alerts. Just go to your Settings > Map display > Reports > Railroad crossing > toggle 'Alert me while driving' and/or 'Show on the map' to the off position. Hope this helps!

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is great! A suggestion I have is when I'm using Android auto and experience congestion, traffic, construction etc.. I want to be able to tap that icon once to start it, and then when it ends, tap it again. I find that just touching the icon to alert other wazers doesn't let you show the full length of how long and bad the problem is. Touch to start, touch again to stop.

Nooooo!! Waze has worked perfectly for a few years now but since the recent update it can never find network even though my phone signal is perfect and even on WiFi. It did this a few years ago and it was so annoying and then it got fixed but has started again :( can't use Waze unless I restart my whole phone almost every time I try and use it now!
replyContent: We're here for you, Heidi! Please message us on Facebook so we can look into your issue further. Thanks you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: A very helpful way to outsmart traffic
Id give it five but its not telling me where the speed cameras are prior to leaving or the inability to search along the trip first to see any hazards.

Not very user friendly. I can't figure out how to look at the directions to see what states I'm passing thru omw home from Oregon to arkansas. You can't really zoom out on the map to see ANYTHING. It's really poorly made and awful. I deleted 30 minutes after I installed it because it's not easy to use.

One of the Best Navigation App. Suggest to add a Zoom Out ( with custom set Zoom factor If possible ) feature as We may need to zoom out to see with enlarge view the direction of our destination we are heading to from our existing location. It helps driver to decide the better move off direction towards its destination. Sometimes making a U turn is faster than follow the instructed direction which at times go a big round. Thank you !
No offline maps makes it useless. Waze and gmaps should merge taking the best from each.

Installed and straight away my street has the wrong name. Then it sent me the wrong way( the long way on a trip approximate 90km) then it crashed froze my phone. Phone must be unlocked to use in car and uses phone GPS instead of the cars GPS. So useless. It's easier to just use Google maps instead.

We love Waze! With other drivers constantly updating traffic, construction, road hazards and (possibly most importantly) police location, it beats any other map app we've ever used. The only real down fall we've run across is in rural areas it seems like not as many people use Waze yet. That means all the extras that make the app so awesome are pretty much useless. You still get directions but that's about it. Also, when we went out of Texas to Denver, Co, NO ONE used it.
replyContent: We appreciate your feedback, Amanda! We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or have feature requests you'd like to submit to us, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Been using Waze for years now. The app used to be brilliant, worked great and was wonderful with routing around traffic. However ever since Google bought it, its been down hill. Halfway through driving the app randomly crashes. Upon opening it takes an age to get GPS and load all it needs to. Waze has now become, slow and unreliable. I used evangelise Waze to others but now i can't given it performance. Waze was a great experiment in community collaboration in traffic, sad they ruined it

This app is amazing I've used it for years my biggest problem is that I drive a commercial truck and can not use certain roads and highways. I wish there was a way to select that we were in a truck instead of a private car. That's my only complaint about this app. Other than that its perfect.

it was working fine, but recently it keeps crashing on me which has resulted in me missing exits and having to find alternative routes. now the routing server isn't responding. it's constantly always having the find internet connection even when my data is on and I'm perfectly capable of using other apps. now I have to go back to Google maps, because at least it locks my location into place.

This was an awesome Idea and would get 5 stars if it wasn't convoluted with ads. Why did you ruin such an awesome app Google? It has awesome features but you had to go and put all the cr@p in there. Please offer a paid version and I would gladly pay for the great product without the ads....For the love of God Please stop with the ads....ads ads ads ads ads ads ads ads ads ads oh so so annoying. Distracting drivers is what you are doing don't make me dust off the ol' Rand McNally  please. It is like the cave man gowning into human, and after the ads having no hair and living in a tree (car) house because he was distracted by your ads. - After note, you should update your pictures to show all the ads associated with the app on Google play that would be a fair representation of what you will get. Hell contact me and I will provide them for you for free.

This was one of my favorite apps when I had an apple phone. When you download it for Android or Samsung, make sure you check your settings. If you don't it won't work right. Once you give it access to your location and other things, it works perfect. I used it all the time again. Thanks Waze!
replyContent:
Hi Don, thank you for your feedback. We'd love to hear more about the issues you're experiencing, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: As much as I like this app, I can't use it as it makes the phone extremely hot after using for a while. It's so hot that the phone will just go off in the middle of a trip. Happened to me a few times in USA and I lost navigation. You can use google maps for days continuously and no adverse effect on your phone. I don't know what's causing this, but I hope it's fixed.
replyContent:
Hi, thank you for your feedback. We'd like to hear more about this issue you're experiencing with the phone overheating. To best assist, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This Is an amazing app! It tells you ahead of time if there's any traffic or danger like potholes in the road or cars pulled on the side, or even police officers hidden away in the trees, not that I would need to know where they were cuz I don't speed. But people tend to slam their brakes on when they do see them. The only thing I'd have to say that this app needs to work on is to be warned about these hazards quicker. I get the warning as I'm practically on top of them.

It was a great app on my old phone (a Galaxy S8) through Android Auto but having just upgraded to a Galaxy S10 the location is completely flaky. It is constantly resetting the map to where I was 5 minutes ago or to a street I was never even on. It is not the location service on my phone as Google Maps has no issues knowing where I am during my drive. Please sort this out as I much prefer Waze (when working) to Google Maps.

Hassle to register but, other than that, I've been loving it. Been trying to add places as I can like fast food, banks, and gas stations. I think the overview map could be a little more detailed with places like that. The way you can integrate YouTube Music and Google Assistant is very convenient.

Trash, this app used to be good, now it'll make you drive 15 miles out of the way, make you turn into a subdivision to U turn and drive in the opposite direction. I used to think this app took you the fastest route, but what took me 25 minutes on Waze, only took me 10 minutes on google maps. Would never recommend this app to anyone.

Not seeing why everyone is SO enamoured with this app. It shoves Facebook in your face like it you don't have it your a 2nd class citizen. It's a Google app now, but there's no way I can see to transfer all of my gmaps info over. The interface is childish. I can't get the nickname I want (not even sure why I need a nickname?). It just doesn't look like a grown-up app to me.
Great app could u make more famous sound alike eg ozzy osbourne or others

When using Waze through android Auto, my phone has to be set to vibrate. If my phone's ringer is switched on, every 3-5 seconds the audio of whatever I'm listening to cuts out for a second or so. Fairly annoying. Waze on Apple Carplay is also much better to look at and easier to read compared to Android Auto.

Overall pretty good. Interface a bit tedious - could make controls and options more easily accessible. Instructions and map movement a bit slow - easy to miss a turn. Google maps reacts faster. Navigation would be much improved if you had an option to quickly see the next direction instruction, rather than waiting for it to come up. Also very annoying that during navigation the map is rigidly fixed in the current direction of travel, rather than leading into the upcoming direction.

Inconsistent. Often gets confused as to where I am. Can sometimes take me the most convoluted way and not due to traffic congestion. Got me very lost and confused (glitching and telling me to make u turns back the way I came) in some shady neighborhoods. Also, struggles to recenter itself and the indicating arrow points in the opposite direction of the direction I am going. Very disappointed. This used to be my favorite GPS app.

CLOSER TO PERFECTION THAN MOST!!!!! Waze is by far one of the better GPS apps out there, for the EVERYDAY GPS user! However, there are a few improvements, more like tweaks, that I feel, once addressed/fixed would put Waze, FAR ABOVE THE REST!! The BIGGEST PET PEEVE I have concerning the App., is a simple one, which conveniently should equal, a simple fix! The fact that the app. limits users, TO PRE-PROGRAM ONLY 2 DESTINATIONS, is so FRUSTRATING for users who need to input more stops than 2.

I would have loved to have used this app, however, with the constant bugs, refusal to display arrival times, traffic patterns, or save a planned drive (all of the advertised intended functions), I decided to uninstall. Will not be using or recommending this app in the future.

The accident and traffic recognition needs a serious revamp. I was driving home on a long journey and it updated my navigation saying there was an accident up ahead but it was over an hour away. We finally get to where the accident was and there was multiple reports that showed traffic, cops and an accident but yet we cruised thru like nothing was there. This has been an issue I've noticed in the past before from Waze. Please work on getting this more accurate.

Horrific. Installed in a desperate search for something better than Google maps and was sorely disappointed. Never connects to GPS, forever presenting extremely distracting irrelevant information like candy points or whatever it is while you're trying to drive, can never seem to find my "gps" despite having full bars for signal, data and location. Had this app recommended to me by loads of people. Shame they're all wrong. think I'll stick to Google maps, awful app. Dont use.

I've been having similar issues with waze as Ken Migawi. I stopped using this app and now I'm using Google Maps. Although when waze wasn't having all these problematic issues, it was great, especially in the sense that the app is very interactive. I initially came to the app store to see if perhaps my version of waze was outdated but it is up to date. I hope all the glitches get fixed soon.... ...or perhaps this is some conspiracy because the pooooolice don't want commuters using the app! ü§£

When I login, app can never find my account and I have to start all over again. This happens when I switch phones. What's the point of having an account if it just gets lost "in the stratosphere". Find my account and I'll give the app 5 stars. Otherwise, it's somewhat pointless due to many other navigation apps.
I can track down the location

I really like it. With that being said the random invasive ads that pop up blocking navigation when I'm near a change in direction like an exit or a turn is really problematic. If it wasn't for the alerts and community support, I'd uninstall this without looking back given all the other options out there (vehicles, apps, and standalones).

This app is a hit or miss, technically it functions ok but it has failed miserably many times at finding alternative routes that are available to the destinations to save time or avoid traffic, It has been very dissapointing over 10 times of my usage, seems like it relies on the driver's input to come up with routes, takes you on a wild chase further into other traffic, seems like GPS is delayed

Really disappointed, I used to use this all the time driving but recently it has stopped working properly. The route line marker would have odd gaps. Only the parts of the map that was previously loaded would appear. Locations that were never encountered prevously would not load map data, so I'd be driving on a regional highway and suddenly loose the map with no idea where to stop and change to google maps. I thought reinstalling the app would fix my problems but now there is no map at all.
replyContent: Hi Alex, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to help with this map issue you‚Äôre experiencing. To best assist with this, can you please submit debug logs and create a ticket for this issue? Here‚Äôs how to do this: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It used be great for years but recently the app has crashed so many times that I started using Google maps again. Every time I select "Jane voice including street names" it goes to other voice option which doesn't tell the street names. It got really annoying and I uninstalled the app! Hopefully they fix it so I can start using it again,btw I use Google pixel 2xl.

GOOGLE maps ALWAYS GETS ME LOST! I have never had an issue like that with this app. I love everything about it,especially that anyone that knows of a new road opening,closure, even shortcuts can alert admin so they can verify and update accordingly. I have depended on this app since I found out my directionally challenged daughter uses it...all I can say is FOR MYSELF THIS IS AWESOME!

Directions were overcomplicated at times. Too many added turns to what should've been fairly simple trips. It did this in Dallas and in the Paris area. It's not reliable. Example: took me off a main road to go through a neighborhood only to get back on the same main road.
replyContent: Hi Kimberly, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I am very satisfied with this app. It works really nice, like a real navigation softver with so many gadgets and options in real time. I was delighted when I saw that Zoran Modli did the voice for Serbian language. Unfortunately, he past away today and that is why I'm writing this review. Thank you Waze for saving a memory of such a visionary man who was more than radio host, more than a DJ, more than a new technology promoter, more than an airplane pilot... One of kind, Zoran Modli and Waze.

Worst travel app I've ever used. I'm in Boston, and I've been trying for 10 minutes to get a route to DC. It keeps timing out and this is not the first time it's done this, and with multiple locations. I've even updated it, and it still wont work. I dont even know why I keep attempting to use this. Google Maps will always be my go to.

Still can't show new info in regards to this pandemic for even something as simple as store hours. Something that really sets Google Maps apart in these circumstances. Also, other suggestions to really become the go-to maps application is to have destination suggestions based on searches and such. That's something that's really handy in GMaps. Don't hide locations that are closed, instead show them, but have those up to date current info about it being closed due to the pandemic, like GMaps.

It would be better if I had the option to not receive or silence notifications about red light cameras. I mostly use navigation apps for my commute so I am more familiar with the location of red light cameras than Waze is, especially since on one stretch there are 8 traffic signals 6 of which have cameras and only at the most 3 get mentioned by Waze. I figure that is because they are so close together as it is a stretch no more than 3 miles long. Then also when reporting a road closure it would help if there was a accident option instead of using hazard for the reason.

Waze went mad on my way from Romania to Czech Republic. While on the highway around Budapest it kept indicating that i should turn around although i was on the right and the only way to Prague. I thought it had a bad moment. But, on my way back home, from Prague to Romania waze went mad again. Instead of guiding me to the highway, it took me to side ways to the countryside. I had to use google maps to find the right way out of Prague. So, dear Waze, googbye!

Great app. Very helpful to have alerts on upcoming risks and hazards on the road. Having speedometer with speed limit is also very useful. Pretty accurate arrival time based on current traffic. Only issue I have is that it is difficult to say which way to go when coming out of a parking lot.

I love Waze carpool BUT not the app. The biggest grievance I have is the clear lack of "rules" for carpooling. Some days the regular two people I carpool with can both request a ride home from me. Other days only one of them can. This leads to one person Venmo-ing me money for the ride or not being paid all together. When I emailed support about this issue they responded with "everything is working just fine!"

I love Waze! I used this app everyday with no issues. Recently, however it has given my phone screen burn!! The orange 'Report Button' never changes color- even at night. I can see the button on my screen even in other apps. There is no option to remove the 'Report Button' so I have to stop using Waze. Be careful- Waze's Report Button can damage your screen! Please let us remove the Report Button and I will change my review to 5 stars!

Having given it a few months testing as an alternative to Google Maps I'd say it's not even close to being competition. The interface looks dated, Google Calendar address imports don't work for 'Planned Drives', it doesn't support Google Music or YouTube Music integration and favourites don't sync with Google saved places.  With Google Maps adopting more Waze features like speed cameras, incident reporting and speed limits on the way soon I can't see it being long before Waze just fizzles out or gets merged with GM.
A little too aggressive. Not too flexible. Subbern. Tested in a long trip against G. Maps. The last offered better solutions.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback. We're always looking for ways to improve our product. If you'd like to share more about your Waze experience or need assistance resolving an issue that may be occurring, feel free to reach out to us through a private message on Facebook.

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Love the app, but it works differently between Apple and Android.   Especially when giving turn instructions. On Apple, it says turn left onto market Street, on Android it does not say the street name.   This sometimes requires one to visually check phone for street name. Will this be fixed?

I deliver food and even in the same overall region as Google is Wade manages to be wrong as much as 40% of the time. It is horrible at letting you know where you are going is a hotel and will place you in some random location in its general vicinity. Obvious side streets are ignored while the app pushes you through extremely poorly paved streets and overly complicated directions that do not save time. The other night it pointed me towards the freeway where there was an accident instead of through obvious major streets which would have saved me time. Google has literally all this information. This is unforgivable.

Used to be OK, but the devs are not responding to user problems and are unwilling to fix even crashes. E.g. the app crashes whenever car mode is activated (a NATIVE ANDROID FEATURE) and bugs about the issue are closed and flagged as "invalid". Also they don't pay attention to landscape mode at all, which many users prefer. Navigation often tries to go on much more complex and longer route for 1-2 minutes gain for a 30min drive which in the end turns out to be slower in reality, and then very slow to recognize a much simpler, faster and shorter route even when we go that way instead of what the app wants... Quality seems to degrade over time instead of increasing.

Helps us with good traffic alerts, objects,vehicles on road. The app needs to support offline maps when there is no internet access like garages/no signal areas. For Waze pool, the pickup location may not be a safe location and can be in middle of intersection. When phone is connected to Android Auto, I can not open Waze on phone and there is no way to confirm arrival on car screen or navigate to destination location of pool from home screen. Adding/ deleting multiple destinations is harder.

I love love love this app. I never give reviews but I had to give this app one. waze got me from one end of the country to the other with no glitches or incorrect information. I have told everyone I know to download this now! well done to the creators!

Love Waze! I have been using it for years. I use it when I am just drive places even though i know where i am going so that i can see if there are any problems on the road. It has definitely saved me time when there has been an accident which caused a huge back up. It gave me another route that got me to my destination very close to when I was supposed to arrive in the first place. The only problem that I have had is when I got my new phone I could not get my account back so I lost my addresses.

Waze was fantastic until last update. Does not do real time drive updates anymore. Signal is spotty in app now always refreshing to find location. Amazingly Google maps works perfectly. Looks like we're being forced over to Google maps with Google sending out glitchy updates to waze. I knew Google wanted to merge the 2 apps but it appears as though they're going to make Waze unusable to force us over.

Hi, my phone is android version. I can't use Waze apps already two three week and more, because it said: "No GPS. Showing approximate location".üòî I have updated. I already have open my "location access", "WiFi", "mobile data" and try more times "restart and shutdown my phone open again", still be like that "No GPS". Please solve this problems, because I love use this Waze apps, thanksüôáüèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
replyContent: Hi Mark, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Well, here we go again. Worked great for about 6 months. Now we're back to constantly losing GPS, random sideways movement, etc., while using with Android Auto. So disappointing. Looks like I'm heading back to Google Maps for good. So unacceptable for an app used by millions...
replyContent: Hi Kevin, we're sorry to hear about your issue. If you send us a private message on Facebook, we'd be happy to look into it! Thank you for the feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Won't flip the screen when the phone is upside down. The only way that my phone will stay in the mount is upside down, due to the charging cables. I tried disabling auto zoom and standing disabling "prevent auto lock" but it made no difference. Guess I'm going back to Google Maps.

I like this app. The features are plentiful without being over the top. I like the abundance of options to personalise the experience. Will there be an Australian girl and guy's accent in future? That would be the cherry on top for me and plenty of other Aussie Wazers I'm sure. Thanks.

Gave this app plenty of chances over the past 4 months and i am uninstalling now after it directed me the long way out of my subdivision and then it would not listen to my search instructions after i cussed it out. Also tried to resume the trip for today after i started heading to my doctor appointment. The screen was showing "calculating route" ad naseum. Good thing uber took me to this location last week so at least i knew where i was going. Im going with a higher rated app! Farewell!

The best Satellite navigation app around. Not perfect, but with a few minor modifications it would remove the need to consider using any other navigation system period. It could use the ability to add current location to favorites. Recently I've been experiencing less then ideal routes. For example, I ignored a left turn which is located 35 metres from the departure location and the drive time difference is over 20 minutes regardless of traffic.

It was good. now I am looking for a new app. after some updates the sound alerts that I use most work once in a while. Also it is very annoying because everytime I start to drive this app automaticaly make a route to some place in bookmarks. It makes me lose time canceling it all the time. I hate it. Traffic jams in the map are not acurate and sometimes it shows traffic jam and the route is totaly free. Lack of features like artists voices and fancy icons like ones for example in Yandex Drive.

Used to be a great app. But feeling disappointed recently. Keep unable to detect GPS or Sesrching for network even the GPS already set to high accuracy (able to play games that using gps) and data is working fine. Additionally, the app load very slow. Hope the next update will improve on current issue.

Ridiculous! Most of the time the app loses connection almost as soon as I start driving and hangs at the starting point. If I do manage to make it work, I don't get proper directions. Turn left in 60 metres means nothing when I'm not given the street name. Useless!!

Always takes me the fastest route on my commute - never the same way two days in a row! One feature that could be improved is the average speed check zones - it would be great to display the user's average speed since they've been in the check zone, as well as the speed limit within the zone.

This app is good for short travels when you know where your are going and you needb to take the best route. Our family thinks it is still one step back of apps like Google Maps for one reason. When you travel on a Expressway you need to know the lane you should use to take your exit or to keep going efficiently through your route. Sometimes you have 6 or more lanes and you need to make your transitions with enough time. We love the app but we have had to many lost exits.

I can't even download the app. It gets to 100% completed and installing then just reloads and goes back to the beginning and continues like that until you have to give up. I've tried numerous times over the past few weeks to download it. All other apps I can download fine so it's just this one. Please fix this

Waze on your phone is great especially the police reports. Waze with Android Auto... Utter Garbage. Why ruin a good thing? The New Android Auto Update broke it. Waze update does not fix any relevant issues at all. Problems such as: 1. No Network Connection even when phone is showing good LTE connection. 2. The map cannot locate you properly. (Some users fixed it by switching to Google Maps and back to Waze) A better fix is to not update your Android Auto or to go back to the previous version.

Map doesn't rotate with phone, so display is upside down. Compass setting makes no difference. Also directions for next turn come rather late, leaving me in doubt of when to make a turn. Doesn't warn of traffic jams or offer alternate route. The final straw was entering a destination that's 45 minutes away and the app showed it on the map but said it couldn't find a route to get there! Bye bye, Waze.

meh. works but not across different phones. ie-my work phone and personal phone can't use the same account? Thats pretty dumb... also used for a trip out of state and now says can't find a route back home, the same way we came? WTH is that? also new update has killed the map view on my personal phone, just a blue triangle in a white field and has constant router time out errors. Really not worth the aggravation of spending 45mins trying to update and reload this app to not even be able to use it

The app is good it gives me warning of what is ahead BUT there is one thing I have against it. When I report something on the road it appears there for 15 minutes then vanished on map. The stupid thing is the hazard was still on the road. But tiny god waze knows everything they took it out. WHAT WAS THE REASON OF REPORTING IF YOU GOING TO ERASE IT IN 15 MINUTES???? If ya'll fix that trash I'll give you your the rest 3 stars but is the sucker stay like that. I'm staying like that.

I've had this app for a couple of years and it used to work very well. The last couple of months the map works very slow and screen is very erratic. Also sometimes when set a destination it would stop giving directions. This caused me some problems when I was going to places I'm not clear on the exact directions.
Great app. I find it easier the Google Maps. But they have taken away the functionality of reporting speed traps

Used to work really well. Since an update with either android auto (Phone) the waypoints disappear if you receive or make a call or message. This is really frustrating as the adverts still work so clearly getting an advert onscreen is more important than getting you to your destination. Come on Waze (Google) sort this out. Using a Pixel 2XL

good app once you figure out how to keep it running. the only con, is that notifications do not occur soon enough. Most of the time you are already upon the incident (police, accident, road hazard) before getting a notification.

Cons: I can't say is the best, just because my options on maps is to "avoid toll roads" is set in my Waze options but these app still taking me through toll roads. I have put it to the test because I now the location I am going to there is a way to avoid toll but this app still selecting the road that has a toll. Pros: Excellent in spoting police. Excellent in spoting problems on all roads. Excellent in mapping streets and rendering the map. Very useful to find services in unfamiliar places.

I was totally dold on waze ,in English accent, awesome and complete and advanced accuracy BUT on I-25 (thunder dome ,ha:), but it stopped, unable to load a total FUBAR ,disappointed i uninstalled and made Google talk UK ,ha but extremely different, slow advanced notice but reliable is important. I was in network and perhaps waze may have an idea ,death as i switched over ,i don't think was intended:)-- 4.4 to a 1 and I may try again? From Colorado

It is really good navigation, I tried for some time the Google Maps, but Waze is really better. Now, I am using Waze on Android auto with my Mazda 3 (2019) and it haven't got touch screen. And when I want see some place on the map or when I want to see whole way, I cannot move with map. And when I want to stop navigation, it is really complicated - too much steps!

Accurate directions but have a connection problem with this app. If you start driving from a wifi connection and you get out of range it will start having network connection errors and you have to restart your app in the middle of driving in order to get rid of the connection errors. Contact tech support only to get automated email help. I need a person just in case if automation dont It would be helpful to add multiple stops especially if you run a route. This app only allows 2 stops maximum.

It was a very great App, but now is like a billboard when you stop the vehicle and you can't see the route correctly, lost lot of notifications of some speed cameras (I pass everyday near three that other apps notify but waze don't), and when you run out of signal is completely useless (why we can't use offline maps), please take this feedbacks as possible ways to improve, thanks
replyContent: Hi Ruben, thanks for providing feedback. We'd like to hear more details about your issues with receiving speed camera notifications, losing your signal and with viewing the route in the app to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app. Although there is some direction glitches, and has sent me in the wrong direction a couple of times, otherwise I like it. I like that I can send my route to others. Plus you can see other "Wazers" on the map.

Update: v4.56.0.2 is even worse, frequently crashing in Android Auto. Waze v4.55.3.0 frequently displays my car drifting sideways on the freeway. Waze looses my current location every few minutes and takes it awhile to position me correctly on the map. Switching to Google Maps when Waze fails show perfect positioning and car direction. Back to Waze and the location problems start anew.
Always taking the long way.
replyContent: Hi, Alvin! Routing issues like this happen because the system works on real time and average statistics. We suggest that you take the suggested route a few times so that Waze can learn from it. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Been using this app for more than 2 years, I think it will improved more than ever. But what I got here is lagging 70% of the time when I need to hurry, and still directing me (a biker) to follow a bike restricted area. Traffic prediction is very poor in my area.

Great app when it comes to your Waze community, everything happening on the road we know about. Does re-route you in circles at times when another, quicker route is directly in front of you. That can be annoying and very time consuming if your completely lost. Other than that it's very beneficial, definitely helpful, two thumbs up.

userName: Dan At the bottom of the garden
content: Needs couple of things changing. Needs the UK distance settings to say 'min' and 'mil', not 'min'/mi as the the latter is easily confused with miles and minutes, often at a glance (which is all you can do when driving) it's easy to mix the up. Also needs the icons to more accurate. For example, when you are coming up to an A road/motorway that splits, it often shows it as a turn, rather than simply getting in one lane or the other, a similar issue when a road bears left or right! DANGEROUS!
Excellent app....been using it since...sometimes it just throughs you off a street or two away.....but that is rare..love it

Does not let you choose a different route option. I put in this destination I need to go to and it's telling me 57 minutes but I put it in on Google maps and Google maps is only 20 minutes. Also unless you live in a big city where a bunch of people use this it's pointless to have in order to know if there are cops traffic or accidents.

I had hoped that after moving from a Moto G4 on Nougat to a MotoG7Play and Android Pie, this app would stop crashing: it didn't. Pity, because the features are excellent. It's not good if it crashes every 100 miles and it neither responds to voice control nor restarts where you left off. I'll go back to plain old Google Maps for navigating, which doesn't crash......ever.

I tried again after one year just for fun. it's still doesn't have basic things like lane assist, but has many ads. The speedometer with it's alert is a good thing, but it's not smart, and doesn't know the time based speed limits. The traffic and congestion infos are not true. still some map errors and unknown closures.

It's a good app. However, it recently took me into congestion charge zones in London despite having "avoid tolls" ticked, now i have an ¬£80 fine. Waze could definitely make it clearer when you're about to go on a tolled road. Also, when using Waze with Android Auto, I've noticed it doesn't always display what number exit I need to take on a roundabout. Sometimes it does, other times it doesn't. Also the font to display that number is tiny!
replyContent: Hi Jordan, thank you for contacting us. We'd like to review and discuss the toll and Android Auto issues with you to help. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with details regarding these issues? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Broken on update. Lost all location history. App can't find GPS even though it has permission and GPS is on. App page says it involves ads now; that's a deal breaker for me. This app always was cockeyed. It will send you 10 miles around in a loop instead of just putting you on an on ramp right next to your start point. NEVER Use This App In Chicago!! The "crowd sourced" (who? I have met 1 person who uses this, years ago) data is available in other apps as well.

content: Waze sucks now. Takes too long calculating route, loses route and has to recalculate when swapping to any other app. Takes forever finding network. I have to run both waze and google maps in case waze decides to flake out. Plus my reviews keep disappearing. f'n google. Waze team should go talk to maps team to learn how to make a gps app again. used to be much better, but as with all things google, it's gone waze downhill fast.

App it has a lot of potential but it still have too much bugs to be useful especially on longer roots. For exm. when you come to other countrie it changes language to that countrie language. After few hours of use it just freezes and loses the destination so you need to deselect it. Sometimes it can not connect at all so you can not get any navigation. Also it doesn't offer you to much of possible roots, especially on longer roots you can not select some common roots like on other navigations.

Best GPS and more! The accuracy of Waze compared to the factory installed navigation system in my car is like night and day. Waze gets me to my destination quickly, avoids traffic accidents, alerts to speed cameras, shows me where car accident are and re-routes my direction plus lets you know if a car is disabled on the shoulder of the road and alerts me AHEAD OF TIME!! My GPS navigation takes me around the scenic route and so far out of the way that I now use Waze üíØ percent. I LOVE this app!!

awesome App gets me where I'm going to quicker when i listen to it thought it was crazy a few times and didn't listen to it and was stuck in traffic for long periods of time.upadte traffic in real time by other users shows where cops are so u know when to slow down tons of options and fun things they offer every so often playing games collecting stuff would recommend for any body.

If you commute a lot then this is the maps app you need. What I love is that you can set it to know your vehicle type, say if it has HOV stickers and it will optimize routes. Also the gamification is compelling. My major gripe is that when using it with AndroidAuto it still uses your phone GPS and not the vehicle's. which causes more battery drain (Google maps behaves properly)

Actually, I like the apps, but everytime I want to log into my account on new phone, it always says "my account lost into stratosphere". What the hell? My last account full with my colleagues & customers location and it just dissapear in the stratosphere? Oh please, just fix this issue, it is so annoying.

Deleted because If you start in a wrong way it wont tell you to turn around but instead takes you to longer route. Compass does not not start where youre facing so you wont know where to even start driving. It doesnt give specific turns like Google Map when the address youre going to is in a huge Plaza. Only the Police Report is best about this app.

Waze has always been a reliable partner in my line ride sharing experience. It always helps to find an optimal route to get me from point A to point Z. It would be helpful, however, to show more than just 3 options for routes. üòÄ

I use this app atleast 6 or 7 years ago, I love waze so much and i trust waze so much, even keep searching network, i also nvr blame waze, i tell myself is my line problem, until this few day, keep cant find thr router for me, i change operator i also nvr suspect is waze problem. but too bad after i change operator still same problem, and i try google map, it was very smooth at google map, really very disapointed to waze

I drove from Mphs to Va & back. Sometimes it is on point with police radar & occassionally it was too late with the notice or no notice at all. Maybe not enough Wazers at the time but I doubt it on I-40. It was valuable but not reliable enough to avoid getting pulled over. I didn't get a ticket because I realized I couldn't rely on the app so I stayed the speed limit.

I think I'll stick with Google Maps for now.

content: Used to like this app, but wrong routes, telling me i reached my destination when i hadn't, many difficulties on acquiring a network connection, forgetting my destination, having to enter my destination up to 5 times, and these annoying ads that cover the map, made it into an unpleasant app.

It's great because it tells you about speed traps. But it's horrible at alternate routes anytime there's traffic. If it ever tells you to get off the highway don't do it. every time I do it I sit there and watch the cars on the highway slowly go by while I sit stopped in traffic. I was an extra half hour late for work because of the alternate route to take me around traffic. I would have saved myself a half hour by staying on the highway

content: Love the app, the speed camera, and other alerts are brilliant, the only issue that I have is when I exit at a junction the next command is in 900 feet at the roundabout take the 2nd exit, yet as soon as the command has finished it says the same thing again, I think that's ridiculous nobody can forget what exit off a roundabout to take in a split second, just a minor tweek please to stop this very annoying thing happening would be great

I'm not sure whether it's the app or my Android Auto, but this app has just stopped in the middle of my trip both times I've used it. It shows I need to turn on a road that I've been on for 2 or more miles and doesn't give any more directions. But, on the bright side, the directions up to that point are very easy to follow.

Doesn't work since "update" I've used this app for YEARS. I use it multiple times per day. content: the app is amazingggg and I'm so addicted to it will driving in Tehran !!! but, I found some bugs in my new phone ( samsung A70 ) . the app show your location totally wrong while you're driving and you cant fix it unless you rest the phone and you should be lucky not to face it again !!! This app really works, and it's easy to use. I use it for my daily commute and it alerts me to all sorts of hazards, pigs, roadkill, cars pulled over, etc. It is surprisingly good. It allows for the ability to confirm or cancel alerts which keeps the information updated and accurate.

This is the first time I've used this app, it took me right to the home I wanted. I was very surprised to see & hear how accurate it was and even posts how fast I was going. It shows red if you are exceeding the speed limit and that was spot on too. I love the app and gave it 5 stars which is well deserved!

I used to love this app and now I can't stand it for several reasons. 1) when turning, it doesn't tell you the name of the road so you are forced to look down at your phone (distracting the driver). 2) it doesn't tell you ahead of time that you reached your destination, it just all the sudden tells you, gives you no time to stop or change lanes in the middle of town. 3) it also doesn't tell you what side your destination is on! Sadly, google does it better now :*(

I give it 5 cuz it's well supported, nice interface, fast. But one problem - while I drive, when it asks me if the thread is still there, it's waaay before I reach the location - I have no visibility of the object - cops, accident, etc.. - I'm not a sniper with X-ray vision - momma & papa made me with base extras only.. When I reach the location of the happening - the dialogue buttons dissappear. I'd be more helpful to you & other users if this is fixed.

You can only add one additional stop it seems. There is no clear indication for where to adjust the settings. You also cannot change which of the two stops you want to go to first. I'm a utility locator and I thought this would be a better alternative to Google Maps as I travel to around 30+ locations a day.

content: over 8 years and still use. no matter where i travel in the world, take my phone with me. waze help me when either use a rental car or an taxi driver who has no idea how to quickly reach my destination. just make sure you have a data plan for roaming active. top app! congrats to those designers!

It's a feature-rich app but a SERIOUS drain on battery, plus makes the phone hot. No offline mode either, and it's constantly using your data, so it can show ads based on your location and route. Unusual search feature too, it doesn't have an option to set both start and end points, just the destination

My favorite feature by far is being able to report speed traps and hidden police officers. even if I know where I'm going I still turn on the app so I can get live updates. I only wished more people used it because some stuff is missed when an area is not reported.

Great app. Use instead of Google, thought I think Google owns Waze now. Too much talking over my stereo. Needs a feature to minimize talking without just muting. Needs easier way of marking Hazzards along route. Mostly needs a website to suggest improvements without trolling endless forums...not everyone is a programmer or wants to read 8000 pages to see if a suggestion was already made. A website and a 3 line form. Is that so hard?

It was a great app. But after integration with google voice typing(in the right corner of search line) it became much slower with annoying pauses and google sounds. Also I can't turn it off. I choose this app when it was different in all details and solutions from google navigation. Now they have same voice typing. Using Google satellite images is the next step?

content: The app has been very buggy recently and keeps getting worse. I have to enter my destination 3 or 4 times before it works. It also has been, at times, not defaulting to the shortest route even though I have that option selected.

content: Probably was the best app of its kind. Unfortunately last several updates really destroyed it. As an example: in Navigation - Avoid Toll Road and Avoid Freeways, are disabled. So according to these choices, waze should not avoid freeways and/or toll roads. But No! Because a stupid developrr choose to disregards these options(I don't know why are there anymore) and regardless of your choice, will still avoid any freeways and toll roads if you do not select different passes. I'll use Google maps!

This used to contain more information. Now it will only alert on general details. "Watch out, there's a car on the shoulder ahead." That's great, but is it on the right or left shoulder? There's no way I can plan to avoid something if I don't know which side of the road it's on. Same with crashes. No information on whether to get to the left or right, just that there's a crash ahead. It's about the same as google maps at this point. Nothing stands out that makes this any better.

Just drove. Cape Town to Durban. I must say.. well impressed by this app. Few things here and there that could be added or improved but if you want to get to your destination safe... Trust this app. kudos. An overview map that can be referred to. Current overview map closes to quick. Heads Up on Tolls (and pricing perhaps)

Error calculating route. Works on my morning commute, then never works on the way home. Error.... Error.... Error. Even a full device reboot doesn't fix the problem. I like the app for the crowdsourced warnings but I've gone back to Google Maps since it actually is reliable and works

3 because of the street names language cannot be changed. It's even worse, when you're trying to search for some address, and Waze gives you suggestions... In local language, which you obviously don't understand. I'm the same time Waze is a very nice navigation app.

Android auto issue : After the last update. When I get call Waze is not able to keep up with my location. My icon change from car to dot and it stays on the map where I received the call, untill the end of the call and map don't move at all Fix this and I'll give 5* I really love this app. Also the railroad crossing is annoying. Have options to disable that notification. Thanks Finally the Oct-2020 update solve the issue I had during calls. It's working fine now

Last version updated is not really precise. I often got your direction into a small alley that is almost impossible to go through. Eventhough I chose a common or popular building, it directed me to their backways (dense residental areas). Why don't create a custom road option that enable feature to avoid small alley for cars? Just like you did in your "Avoid Ferries" or "Avoid freeways" and "Dirt Roads" kinda thing. Thanks!

content: Sometimes "Rerouting" is a bit slow and you miss the turn before your new route is established /displayed. Also, when you choose/enter a destination, it always asks "Go now?" Yes, now! That's why I entered it instead of using the "Planning a trip" tool. A slight annoyance to me personally, üòÇ.

love the app and community powered hazard alerts, however it crashes half the time I try to use the app and often cannot load until closed and its cache cleared multiple times. Using an LG V30S Update 3/15/20: App will now not load any route, times out trying to find one. Completely useless as an app, hate to have to uninstall but it no longer performs its basic functions.

When Waze is running in Android Auto, all calls and message notifications coming in are blocked , disabled. This is a serious glitch and degrade to Android Auto functions. Until Waze fixes this serious flaw , Google Maps trumps it hands down. My wife used Waze on Android Auto in the car. Many of her other Apps running in her phone got their settings messed up after the mobile was unplugged from the Android Auto system of the car. It was exasperating going through each affected apps to reset.

Full bar 4g connection but still showing searching for gps, especially during peak hour. Tried Google map and it start my route instantly after pressed. Compare Waze with Google map, Waze layout give clear instructions and easy to see.
