content: Would be nice to see lane information, just like Google Maps, especially now that Google owns Waze. For example, which lane to stay on during GPS navigation. Also, alternate routes seem to have gotten worse lately. The alternate routes it suggests end up making me later in the long run.

2 months ago -After using this app for almost two years I am now about to crack! It won't let me log in, took over five times to change my password, then it didn't recognize my email address. The best part was it recognized my phone# but continuously says that something went wrong and lost in the stratosphere. Support is useless, they keep sending me the same email to solve the problems that I don't have. Update 5/8/2019 - still no support from Waze lol... they only care about ads that pay them!

I'd like to be able to use waze, it has some great features. It doesn't connect to GPS reliably, often can't route or drops the route. Waze has similar issues whether running on my phone or tablet. Niether device have issues running Google Maps, so I doubt the devices are the problem.
replyContent: Hi Gary, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: a must for drives of any length. downsides are that reports can sometimes be inaccurate, and you cant decline a report in your area. if the devs are worried about tricksters, why not put a point system where you have to have X amount of points to decline a report? you also cant delete an accidental report. i get that reports disappear after a certain amount of time, but its rediculous to be redirected when someone accidentally closes a lane. please! its 2019!

The app is very helpful and quite accurate. I'm an Uber driver and I find it very useful. I really cannot do without it. The only downside is that it's a bit slow to launch. It will occasionally tell you to take a one-way lane with oncoming traffic...for this you just need to keep your eyes open.

I like the latest update. It shows turn by turn direction on the top left of screen while navigating. Really nice safety implementation. Speed limit signs while driving very tiny, can't see it. Would love to see larger sign. And be able to remove current mph below it. Lastly, would like to see more colors, and 3d building, on maps.

Overall i like the app however, lately it buffers when starting trips. Also drive history is missing. I worked with tech support but they arent very helpful. After a week of communication they say they knew about the problem the whole time but dont have a timeline of when it will be fixed! Please fix this issue!! I need my drive history for work!
replyContent: Hi Amy, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: At first, I thought it was great. Then, I tried to plan multi-leg routes. It fails badly. When I ask for help, it says, "Sorry, I can't help you with that!" Yeah, and I can't help you with a better review. Keep your routes to point A to B, only. If you want multi-leg planning, use Google Maps.

Pretty good but it needs some refinement. Reports don't always show up, i would have to restart the app to get it to update. Also, the bluetooth option needs to match ios. there's no support for bluetooth on android. Lastly, we need an option to stop automatic navigation to home or work once we open the app during the week days.
Very good just what I need

It constantly freezes on my old phone, but this could be due to the fact that I use it on an ancient Android 4.4.2. On a newer system it should work well, I guess, but with my device (Samsung Galaxy Grand 2 LTE) it isn't reliable, so I can't use it.

Can't look at a trip easily from a place other than the place you are located. Please make this easier. After 15 minutes of trying to figure it out .... I'm done with Waze. I'll go to Maps even though I'm not a big fan, but at least its controls are much easier to use.

I love this app. It is way better than Google maps even though Google bought Waze in 2013. It has a feature to detect police up ahead. The other feature that I like is it can alert me when I am speeding. It can be set for 5 mph over, 10 over or percent over the speed limit. It also has many more useful features.

Since last update this app gives me bogus instructions, and has no idea what my location is. It was trying to direct me from about 6 blocks from my current location on the start of my drive, and near the end of my drive it told me to make several lefts and a u turn that i ignored that i knew were wrong. WHY? What happened? Used to be good app.

Great for directions esp when delay causes a reroute. But I'd prefer larger speed limit info. I like how it turns red if you go over limit. I'd like to see larger "exit number" in the centre of roundabout detail and for it to be positioned in top right corner (not top left ) at least for uk drivers. Also I'd prefer a better menu and more easily accessible so I can change destination or to add a stop or amend route eg via a shop. A laybys or parking pull in en route marker would also be useful.

The routing could be better. I know my route to work, how many miles it is and how long it takes. I used that as a test. Waze's shortest route is 5 miles longer, puts you in more traffic, and takes more time. Positives are that it will get you there and community support to inform others of hazards and such.

Good routes but not the easiest to use, esp with Android Auto. Car direction on screen often confusing and slow to react to new car direction. When had to ignore part of waze route, due eg to road closure, didn't seem to be able to recalculate a new route. Found it difficult to enter a destination. Android auto Screen froze me out twice in one day. Had to revert to car sat nav. Shame as it definitely choose the best/quickest routes through London, unlike Google or my car sat nav.

A very nice alternative to Google Maps especially it runs in 60 frame rate (it looks stunning). One thing that needs to be improved is the voice command feature. It will not auto-detect when it's running on Android Auto.

It seems that sometimes gets wrong about the car position and issues wrong instructions (maybe since the last update or perhaps just yesterday). Also, Google Maps shows more useful data (e.g. the number of the next highway exit to take) and is less intrusive (e.g. if I manually move the map, it doesn't rollback my change in a few seconds, it simply waits until I touch "recentre", so I can browse the map along several semaphores)
replyContent: Hi Ciriaco, thanks for the review. We'd like to get more details about your issue with the wrong position and instructions. Please send us a private message on Facebook so we can look into it. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to be great and I still prefer it over Google maps but I don't think I'd feel comfortable traveling with the issues im having with waze lately. Unless I have the app 100% open and on my screen it loses network connection somehow and starts missing turns or stops directing completely. Until i put it back on my screen but if I flip over to a text message or something it starts fumbling. Then once I get to a destination and stop for a few minutes and try to put a new location in it won't

App now says unable to locate route???? When I researched online says server may be busy. In my opinion that makes it unreliable. I used to love this app until this happened. Put in address to come home from Florida and got the message. Not cool.
replyContent: We're sorry to hear about your bad experience, D. Beach. If you message us on Facebook with more details about this route, we'd be happy to look into this issue further. Thank you for the feedback! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I wanted to like this app. I really did. I have put up with a lot of frustration. Read the negative reviews. I have shared their aggravation. Tonight I selected my home address and Waze directed me to my office. I CLEARLY selected my home address. I didn't realize I had gone 20+ minutes out of the way because it was dark and I am still learning a new area. I could go on, but I am running out of character space. Tonight was the last straw. This app needs some work.
replyContent: Hi John, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. If you run into routing issues again, please private message us on Facebook or reach out to us in the app so we can assist. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great app and functionality!

Carpool - Nice concept but buggy implementation & worst support. Stay away! Concept wise its good. They patch you up with ppl on same regular route and you can carpool. However, there are so many bugs in the application and the support dept is so pathetic that I stay away from this app now. Their patching algorithm just assumes that you can take any path from your home to work. No matter what distance or time it may take. Only motive is to patch up. Customer support is a big joke! No use!

Would have rated 5 stars but when I had to reset my phone, Waze didn't recognize me and had to start as a new user after using the app for several years. Love being provided best routes around traffic and like helping others by warning them about traffic and potholes. Also like that people cannot lie for long as they will be discredited so when there is a car up ahead warning, but no car, I very gladly say the truth and there wasn't or vs if there is.

I used to like using this app as a back up to Google Maps as it has an absurd highway bias. But lately this app has had problems making routes, problems finding my location and problems taking me to the correct address. You know there are problems when it takes you to a different street than your destination.

Had been working ok then something changed. Doesn't do anything right anymore when connected to android auto in Ford F-150. Doesn't show continuous location. Doesn't zoom in and out automatically based on speed. Doesn't display screen icons for incidents, police etc. Does show annoying little angry bird looking characters that are a distraction that I hate. Does mute music unnecessarily when it feels like it.üòñüò§üò¨
replyContent:
Hi Karl, thank you for reporting these app issues. We'd like to hear more about this to assist. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Great overall as usual but the 11/20 update came with a chronic notification but. Even when using Waze via Android Auto, a notification comes up in the Notification menu and is constantly notifying regarding the status of the drive. This continuously interrupts your music listening. To get around it long press the notification and stop all notifications and the problem is solved until the next update
Better on alley roads and tolls. Always updated when it comes to traffics, police checkpoints, cameras and accidents.

Waze reported a route that should take 16 mins, while driving the route it "updates" the time and tells me it will take 50 mins instead. Taking local at the start would have taken 30 mins... Very annoyed that Waze did not have the correct time and only updates while I was already stuck on the highway.

My favorite GPS! It helps me and I can help others. I love being able to report situations, roadblocks to help other drivers. I love being redirected when I report a roadblock. I love the options to avoid tolls, roads, etc. Just love it! Very helpful!

I would not be able to go to places that I had never gone to before without this app. I don't get lost anymore. Or waste gas. Best app ever for anyone who drives. And if you love exploring new stores or branches of the same store in different locations this is essential.

It used to work great until the latest update. Now i have the same problem everyone else is having with android auto. Map freezes and loses gps. Recent places disappear. Map gets stuck sideways etc. Funny thing is google maps has been spreading the word since last week that it has new features like speed traps, etc. and now waze is gaving issues... how covienient.

I never gave Waze permission to change certain phone settings. Ever since I downloaded the Waze app, I now get this black screen that covers my whole screen whenever ANY of my apps are running that says 'SWIPE SCREEN TO UNLOCK App Running'. It's extremely annoying especially when I'm doing rideshare and I need the screen on the entire time so I can see turn by turn. I cannot figure out how to turn off this setting anywhere in my phone. I need to get rid of it!

I've been trying waze as an alternative to Google maps while travelling around doing my job, the alerts for roadworks, safety cameras etc are great and seem very accurate. A couple of things that would be helpful and make me switch permanently to waze The ability to see alternative routes, Google maps shows these with the routes in grey and a pop up message saying how much slower or quicker the route is and it helps me often to avoid traffic. Some postcodes arent recognised, but Google does.

this new update screwed something up. it was working just fine before this update but now all i get is an error message and tells to try again and just spins. i was literally sitting in the parking lot of the address i wanted to goto and it could not find it and i got the error message but if i added as an extra stop before my destination, it would find everything just fine. Please Fix whatever you screwed up in this update because i cant use it if it can't find the location or connect.

Total Garbage. The apps functions well but misses one critical aspect that is a safety issue. When I type an address and it autocompmetes and then try to tap it, it doesn't fill out the remainder. This renders it as a waste of time. I don't have time or 16 lives to spare if I get in an accident due to the incompetent app not performing the simplist of features. But hey, it does tell me cops are down the road as i'm swerving across 4 lanes of traffic because the Arbys address won't autofil
replyContent: Hi Zachary, thanks for reaching out. We'd like to hear more details about this auto-fill issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. To best assist with this, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Used to be a good apps for navigation. But recently the funtions are declining showing poor choice of routes for destination and confusing roads

Such a shame! This used to be the best GPS app when it first came out and before Google got it and turned it into a trash with every so called update. Now, searching for gps, keeps reloading and goes haywire jumping all over the place instead of finding the line on the fwy. 3 hr round-trip I drove today and it couldn't find the way to a set DEST. USLESS! What a disappointment and whomever is behind programming these updates to this app needs to get fired like yesterday! Get it together already!!

I like this app and will keep using it but i don't like the fact it replaces Google Assistant when the app is running. Google Assistant does far more than the "OK Waze" assistant does and it becomes disabled when Waze is running. So if I want to text someone hands-free I have to ask Waze to shut down so Google Assistant will listen again. Also, I love how Google Maps stays active in a little picture-in-picture window when it's in the background. Can't find any way to make Waze do that.

This app is the absolute best driving map there is! It is so user friendly and informative. I feel completely safe while driving and this app is very quick to update information and warnings. As long as all of the Wazers continue to be pro-active and send reports...this app will grow... In popularity and effectiveness! I recommend this app to everybody I know and a lot of us are drivers for work. Thank you to Waze and all of my fellow Wazers for keeping me safe (#avoidingtickets)!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
I love the Waze app I just wish they would let you know which side of the road your destination would be on

I have lost my account several times due to me being clumsy with phones and having to switch, I even create a new account and it instantly told me "sorry we must have lost your account it must be out in the stratosphere somewhere"...... The GPS signal doesn't register or is constantly switching on and off every 10secs or so, this app has gone from the best and most reliable to completely and utterly useless, very sad indeed going from gold to lead.....

Android auto maps in denmark is very unstable. Since I downloaded Waze, I have been so delighted with the results. Police, road works etc is spot on. I depend on maps to get around and to this day, Waze has always been prompt and spot on. From an old man, Thank you for Waze.

Good but it needs options for driving trucks, not just car, motorbike and taxi. As a truck driver it would be very handy to have a vehicle height option so I can stop being sent on roads with low underpasses that I can't get under. Very frustrating and sometimes very dangerous to try and turn around and navigate another route

With the recent few updates, I always encountered calculation error even I used the same route to go home. I had to re-try few times to make it work. I use a Sony phone. Please solve it. Last time it seldom happen.

You know what I hate? When I push the go button, and then I have to push the go button again? Instead of pushing the go button multiple time... how about adding a stop button so you can stop navigation without exiting the app. Oh and I like the voices with accents. We need more. No Latino accent voices?
replyContent:
Hi Jarom, thanks you for your feedback. We invite you to submit these ideas to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I especially like the fact that it provides information about traffic ahead. one thing it could do better is to be able to note construction zones on a long term basis. i.e. it might tell you about traffic ahead, but not say anything about the construction.

This app sucks. 1)Often routs way the heck out of the way 2) IMPOSSIBLE to make the voice repeat last instruction. Total full stop bang head on desk fail. 3)Often won't show traffic congestion so I STILL need the scroogle app along side 4) sometimes refuse to give voice prompts even when sound/alerts et to on. 5) You can't select a destination off map, only off the list, which is impossible when there are 14 Burger Kings on the list. Why can I just touch one on the dam map??? Fail.

I have used this app more than 3 years, and I have changed my phone to pexel 4 this time. At this moment, to use this app on pixel4 is slightly difficult because pixel 4 does not have to open option button on it. So if I want to log in to my accoumt on Waze, it is not easy. So i would like to ask you to change the user IF on android Q. The current deaign is not wasy to uaw this app. Thank you.
TRUCK OPTION Entered everything, got account set up, and the only driving options for this "trucker GPS app" is car, motorcycle, etc. NO TRUCK OPTION We ain't tiny, guys
replyContent:
Hey there! Waze currently doesn't offer routing for larger vehicles. However, we're always looking for ways to improve our product and welcome you to submit your request to our suggestion box for further consideration: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I really like this app, it's very fast and simple to use, and I love that it gives you feedback on car crashes and delays. However, I would like if they had an option to show if you're driving through a sketchy area. Although it might be faster, I don't want to drive through a sketchy neighborhood just because it's a little bit quicker. If there was the option to decide on this feature that would be awesome! I also wish that there was more of a variety of voices.

This app would be great if only: 1/ Postcodes meant anything in navigating. I'm never sure if I'm going to the right place. 2/ It was less greedy. Why the hell does Waze drink my battery flat in such little time and overheat my phone until it cooks (that's with only Soundcloud running for music - and no, it's not Soundcloud doing it) 3/ There was better indication that you're taking an exit which runs parallel to the highway. It's completely unclear when you look at the route line. Sort it.

I like Waze and find it necessary driving in CA. BUT it has a few issues.. 1) it has me take an exit only to reenter at same exit. I am not missing any traffic and fighting to get bk on in same heavy traffic. 2) I've missed exits cause it says "Stay in the HOV lane" and HOV doesn't exit n can't get over in heavy traffic quick eno. 3) Other times it does opposite #2 n says to exit the HOV lane just to get rt back in HOV at next HOV entrance. It gets stuck doing this.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out to us. We'd like to hear more to investigate these issues to help. To do so, we request that you please submit debug logs and create a ticket: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6270063?hl=en&ref_topic=6262587 Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It tells you where the police are and if there's anything you really need to watch out for too many people are reporting things that aren't really there. Also if you get into an area the GPS doesn't tell you where to go. It sent you in circles. I have to switch over from Waze to Google Maps and Google Maps will get me out. Also always needs to be updated more often because it's starting to screw up and there's no updates for it. You need to keep up with the updates
replyContent: Hi Tammy, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: i don't know if it's a tactic used since google bought waze, but i feel like some of the app features are not working aswell as before . Also, it kept "searching for network" randomly and it was not able to find an adress where i always drive to. i reinstalled the app with no success as i could not even log in again using facebook. i verified the app permissions in android and gave out all permission except phone calls and then it worked. it should prompt instead letting the user figure that out

Today has a fairly nice afternoon, at least there us no snow or rain. The temperature in Milton Keynes is fabulous, hopefully the weather will remain like how it currently is. Apparently, this WAZE app. is extremely useful and user friendly. Everyone can learn to enjoy this GPS applet, absolutely not a major quantity of time is needed. No one could possibly point the finger at you while you try to enjoy yourself. Hopefully I will altter several words while this downloading process takes place.

Doesn't work very well in Android Auto with Samsung Note 9. Map keeps freezing. Unfreezes sometimes if I unlock the phone, but cant keep doing that while driving. Also for some reason the screen doesnt always allow touch input. Not the car's fault, have used a differnt phone without issue in the past. Sounds like a problem with the app's permissions for the Note 9.

Two things, there should be an option to switch from mph to kph as Canadians only use kph. The other thing is, it's giving warnings for things like hazards, or police or construction that aren't really there in real time, which is annoying. So a fix for these things would make me keep using this app! 3 stars for now!

So far not that gr8 as much as i heard. In the mid of a busy road with minimum speed 30-40 miles when it says you have reached your destination what would one do ! Suggestion: your destination will be on right side or left side so that one can prepare him/herself for parking and help others drive safe too or in dark when to find house direction too Often dont show whole page instead just mark on a map &have to drive by listening rather then driving and playing to get the screeb map in order.

Ever since Google bought Waze, it has become a terrible app. Just as useless as Google Maps. My trip got delayed 20mins because it decided to choose stupid routes. Also, searching for alternative routes has become worse. Anything that Google touches now just SUCKS. YouTube has become purely ads, Edge is now better than Chrome, and the search engine just pushes ads and makes it hard to find results like in the old days.

content: I have been using Waze now for a couple of years and it's been great but now it's draining my battery like crazy. I can start out my trip with a full battery by the time I get to my destination I got less than a 50% battery left and the app keeps crashing I have uninstalled it and reinstalled it and now I can't even log in before the app crashes. Please update and fix this

Needs a lot of work, would prefer it to update as frequently as Google maps with alternative routes in transit instead of having to select ahead of time. Regularly lags out while in use requiring a phone restart to fix. Will report no GPS while other apps have no issues while waze is out. EDIT: No way to respond to map issues, you need to allow us to respond in the email or link or Google account to the app.

This is coming off my phone. While driving and using the map for directions junk covers the screen (and the needed map) with stupid questions and creates what I see as quite a hazard. Never had this with good old GPS or Google maps. I was driving while this happened and needed to see the map!

I did love the app but the search bar at the bottom is too big. While horizontal it covers 1/3 of the screen. I have a galaxy note 10+ which has a big screen so the search bar is humongous! I don't understand why there is a search bar then another search button next to a carpool button. The buttons are useless especially if you never carpool. Please add a hide feature.

content: love the app BUT I shouldnt have to manually shut it down from my apps in settings. if I dont, it uses countless amounts of data despite me closing the app from running in the background. I have a note 9 and have never encountered this problem before my upgrade, hope it gets fixed asap! when it does, I will gladly change it to 5 stars üòä

Could be better on memory and update roads status speed. The timings and suroundings for traffic jams needs improvements. Update: why good options not last long? It is complicate to explain the use cases. But the most annoying thing is that it is the most battery drainer from store, it will remain in the back till you remain very fast without. If started without gps it will stuck everytime but i think this is a known issue for years. Was best startup till was bought.
replyContent: Hi Cosmin, we appreciate your feedback. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook with more details about your question? We're happy to help! Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is way more accurate than google maps for road construction and detours especially. My city is undergoing a major reconstruction of the main interstate through the city so theres a ton a road closures, detours, and new traffic patterns. I was really tired of google maps not being updated with closures and traffic patterns until months after they started. So i switched to Waze and its so much better. Its updated within hours of a traffic change. Even nightly road closures are pretty accurate

One issue I had on a recent trip was that it didn't alert me when an exit was over the State line. Would like to see this change made. I was traveling from Maine to Maryland and back. Was confusing as I was going from PA to NJ on a road I wasn't familiar with. :(

Everyone kept telling me use Waze better than Google navigator. I live in NC and finally decided to give it a try to get to Florida after Florence hit. To my dismay it kept saying no route found yet Google found me three alternative routes to get around route 95 closures. If you like it great, for me it's useless.

Hi, I am using the latest version of waze but it stopped working since couple of days back. When I search for a location, the voice assistant says handing over to waze but then a circle keeps on rotating and nothing happens. Then I have to go back to home and then use Google maps instead. I am using bmw 5 series with idrive 7. Please help. I have tried uninstalling and reinstalling but still the same issue.
replyContent: Hey there, Rajiv! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We'd like to learn more about this occurrence, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I tried to use the app on 1/18/19 and was once again disappointed. Error message said it couldn't connect to GPS....I'm done with it. I install waze whenever taking a road trip. I'm usually very satisfied until today. Will not stay connected .....got to be A bug.

One of the best navigation apps around. I use it everday on my car's Android system to get where I am going. I love the community reporting features that tell me about police, potholes, stopped vehicles and so forth. It also navigates through sides strets during slow traffic such as rush hours.
Garbage, it doesn't work any more.
Great info from other users along the way. On cloudy days don't rely on 'actual' speed.

this app is good !! works well !! many options but !! there is one slight problem !!Waze does not have an offline version map for offline uses !! It required data for access !! I resided in Ontario Canada-----if I travel to America then my phone will not work !!--this will affects the Waze too...yeah !!see!! this is the problem.

Best app I have downloaded. Had it a couple weeks. This is what the cb was in the 70s. I wish there was a walkie talkie feature to talk to other users, communicate further, like to get around an idiot in the left lane, or tell them a sideroad you know to avoid a bad spot. And how do I get registered status? Thanks!

I love Waze. It is accurate. I love that we can update the roads and road conditions real time. The only negative is mine would not open for a while, however, I had very little space left on my Galaxy S9+. I had to Uninstall and reinstall. Instead all of my addresses and coodos.

usually it's a great app but when you need it, it will let you down. today I've lost at least 1 hour because, despite having avoid highway off and avoid toll roads off, waze decided that the shortes route is not on the highway because i didn't add my tolls on waze. It's a crappy option. if i checked that i want to go on the highway and that i want to use roads that have separate taxes I SHOULD NOT HAVE TO ADD EVERY FREAKING TOLL TO GET THE SHORTEST ROUTE.

Used to live the app. It used to direct me to the door but now stops and says you're here. Doesn't even tell me if location is on the left or right side. Nor give the address which it used to do. After using Waze since it's first release I'm switching back to Navigate and Google Maps.

content: Awesome App!! I have been using WAZE for about 8 months. It is so incredibly detailed and allows so much personal customization. Very accurate! Much more informative then any other Map Application I've ever used. I LOVE WAZE!!!!! Thank You to the developers!! (I generally do not comment when rating apps. But this one is to great to stay silent)

I Do Love This App but definitely needs some attention. I am no longer getting a voice alert when approaching speed trap and red light cameras. I also believe the destination marker should be smaller to better justify what side of street destination is on. Also take a gamble and include a black amoled mode to help with battery consumption

content: Waze itself is great and getting better every day... BUT the Android auto experience is looong way behind and what makes it even worse is that you can't use waze on your phone with all the features, while connected to AA. Another problem is that compared to Google Maps which can utilize the in car antenna and telemetry to know your exact position (even in tunnels and close proximity narrow streets) waze uses only the phone's GPS, which is inaccurate. Please focus on AA as well.

content: I only use this with Android Auto. I really like the display. The map is more readable at a glance than Google maps. It is great for commuting. The notifications are great. When working through Android Auto, adding a new destination is difficult if not impossible or I just don't know how to use it.

I really like how much this app can notify me of on my route, but had too many issues to keep using it. The app shut down 3 times on a 600 mile journey, and when I re-launched it, I had to search again for my destination. I also had problems searching for things like gas stations along my route.

Love Waze, but unusable with Android Auto. I recently started having problem with Waze when using Android Auto. It will completely lose where I am at on the map like it can't get a GPS lock. But if I switch to Google Maps and then back in Android Auto, it starts working again. Also if I unplug from Android Auto it works without issue. It's only a problem when using Android Auto with my phone which is a Galaxy S9. We have a Galaxy Note 9 and S10e that it works perfectly with.

It's a really good app for the road it tells u if a broken on the side of the road and it will say car on the shoulder of the Rd and it's tell's your speed and if cop''s r around only one it doesn't pick it is dot for 18wheelers but other than that I'm happy with this app it's the best app I found it's the truth I'm not bull******* or pulling to one's leg i would recommend it they need to make more apps like this1 and not some bull**** apps like they have out there this app is da real deal

Something really wrong with waze recently, its loosing its GPS signal very often, rerouting again and again, and very bad routs in New York, will make you go a longer route in New York area - I know the streets well, but use waze anyway as it shows the cameras, but takes you down routes that take much longer & makes no sense to go that far,

content: The navigation app that I started using was Google Maps, and it helped enough. Well, as a mail carrier I started using Circuit to help me deliver my packages. But, the new idiotic thing that it's doing, is to tell you to turn left...and then it recalibrates itself AT THE LAST SECOND and tells you to turn right! content: Just found a major irk that could be fixed next time. It's about the reporting of incidents/obstructions on roads. Especially for highways, there should be an icon with numbers(lane numbers) so when people report they can just press the icon with a number..instead of just a general accident.then the driver has to write in the comments which lanes etc.

Do yourself a favor a switch to Waze. I can manage my trips easily, I'm notified of everything happening on my route in real time. It updates to continually give me the fastest or best route available and I can easily search for food, gas stations (including best prices on gas), and shops on my route. O honestly run it for drives I don't need directions for also so I can get all the updates on what is happening right now on the road.

Absolute garbage. Can't figure out where you are, half the time. Gives arbitrary instructions to turn onto roads that are nowhere near you. When it finally does figure out where you are, it redirects you off-route into standstill traffic even though your original route was clear. Completely useless.

Worked great up until 3 days ago. Gps keeps dropping out and then comes back on several times during trips with customers. Takes me on the highway only to take the next exit or takes me off the hight way only to bring me back on. went back to G maps today. no issuses. but when it works its great. will be on G for a while.

They have removed hands-free search input via saying, "OK, Waze," and voice recognition no longer works after tapping the microphone icon. Searches must be entered manually. Waze is now much more unsafe to use while driving. ADDENDUM You can use Google Assistant for voice navigation...unless you switched it off because it is annoying and intrusive. They have needlessly changed a 5-star app to near-useless.

Not sure if it's a glitch or what because I always check to keep this app updated. I hope this can be fixed as I use to promote waze to anyone who I believed may benefit from being a wazer. C'mon

This app used to be my go to. With update before last it won't find the route properly - tells me Waze is connecting to gps and please proceed to the highlighted area - I'm on the route in the highlighted area already and the map is floating all over the place!!!! Sad that you broke this app because I really did love it. I'm on my Samsung Note 8 - don't want to go to Google Maps but looks like I will have to- please PLEASE GET THIS FIXED

Great app. I want to know what's going on up ahead if I'm stuck in traffic so I can decide to re-route or re-schedule, or if I should call and tell someone I'm running late. And I'm always sorry if I don't re-route exactly the way the app tells me to re-route. The wazers know best. 'Nice to be part of the community even while I'm driving all by myself.
I have used this app since it came out in Europe and US love it.

This has been my goto Nav app for years. just recently I am having issues. it works fine the first time you use it after a reboot. then when you open it again it has issues or sometimes doesn't open and I have to force stop it. Sometimes I have to reboot the phone to get it working again. Please fix this issue.

Waze is by far my absolute favourite GPS system. Not only is it in real-time with an active community with users, it also has fully customizable features plus, its free! If Google Play had more than a five star rating, Waze GPS would still get all of them, without a doubt!

I love the ability to report road activities! Car on side of road; hazards in lane; lane closures and Radar Check Activity! Wazer reports help me a lot, therefore, I report too! The interface is okay, once you get used to it. I listen to Spotify and it's interlaced with Waze.

this was a great app for really good directions... but I waited till I was almost in town so I wouldn't waste my battery... so I decided to turn my gps on and use waze... then that's when the problem happened I tried hands free telling waze where I was going and I had it wouldn't do anything nor would it let me type in the location box... as I was getting closer to my destination... I wouldn't recommend this app...

As much as I love this app, I also hate it for two major reasons. #1. Go to work. Go. Yes go. GO NOW! You have to press a "go" button like three times. Yes, I want to go right now. Not tomorrow. Not next week. Just start the navigation already! #2. Sometimes doesn't give the best route. It's 2020. Yet I often ignore the advice of Waze, go a different way, watch it recalculate, ignore it's advice again, recalculate, and estimated drive time continues to drop. Waze should know better than me.

I like the features but Waze causes Android Auto to freeze my Mazda 3's infotainment system. This forces me to pull over and turn my car off and then on again to reset it. It's so unstable i can't trust it till it's fixed. I had to go back to Google maps.

Waze is awesome but it should have option to exclude certain routes because there are times when I am in a commercial vehicle and I am not allowed in certain road ways but I can't tell Waze to find another route. Second problem is when Waze gets into a problem and says it cant find a location or it does not work but Google maps does. Then miles down the road Waze finds it when I try later.

I suggest that whenever the GPS link is cut coz of weak signal it must base it's instructions and resume where the last "my location" the GPS recorded.

content: the app is very helpful by showing the best roots, where hazards are, integration with other apps, and showing you close hot spots, and other extensive features. however the best part is that it records your past travels, accumulating points as you go and unlocking rewards yet cosistinlty makes you have to create a new account, losing all progress and preventing you from being able to recover it. the new account overwrites your last, and prevents you from using the same email and usernames.

What Waze does well is tell you when there is police or hazards. What it sucks at is actually using that information to give you better directions. I've been stuck in traffic on the wrong side of a highway one too many times. I can't wait for Google to cannibalize this apps useful features. Gets 2 stars only because I can avoid tickets.

would rate higher but quicker routes recommended by this app is not the best. Almost everytime i use a recommended route, I'm stuck in heavier traffic. the pop ups for gas, etc is dangerous for someone like me who have adhd and is trying to focus on getting to my destination. Also, navigation is too sensitive which causes me to miss turns

There's nothing quite like Waze for the user reports, which makes it a must-use despite many glaring bugs. App overall is difficult to use with Android Auto tho it's gotten better. It's several times slower than Google maps at pretty much everything. Takes way too many button clicks to start navigation, and you have to wait for it to load the route completely each time before clicking Go which sucks.

Incredibly frustrating that it will provide a route to a destination, but not provide a return route. I have attempted on several occasions bit to no avail. please fix this. It makes absolutely no sense and I have lost many hours because Waze cannot calculate a route. I've had this problem for almost a year. Always the same 4 destinations. This is the primary reason I won't rate this app any higher.

Have been using the app for 8 years, everything has been great until it crashed mid drive 3/22/21. When attempting to open the app again, it kept closing itself and opening itself within milliseconds. It now won't recognize my email, username, etc. when attempting to log in and basically is telling me to create a new account. This means I lost all save addresses on my account, but the app doesn't open still other than to just immediately close itself.
replyContent: Hi, Chris! We're sorry to hear about this problem with your account. We've looked into this issue and have verified that the app is working as intended. If you're still experiencing issues though please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: It's Way Better than Google Maps as Google doesn't actively announce police, cars on the shoulder of the road, railway crossings and debris on the road. There was a large piece of retread tire on the road and other's were swerving to keep from hitting it. As I watched ahead I was aware of how other's were driving and I avoided that area.

i dont use Waze only in the weekend's. i love using it. but since some time when i turn on waze and my gps, seems like wase has an issue picking up my gps. Like a red see through circle in an area that has had a certain amount of accidents. Or Blue where there has been a siting of police 4 times in the last month or 2. Or traffic or... Very practical app when driving around places you are not familiar with. it's maps are quite explicit and clear. Voices of the guides are always clear. sometimes there are things you would like to learn how to do, but u cant. fixing bugs is not really easy. i totally recommend this app.

Waze is a very good GPS app way better than Google Drive I don't know what happened to GPS on Google but it definitely downhill! Waze will tell you if there's a car stopped on the side of the road. content: Okay, so this is awkward. I have been an abide Wazer for more than 5 years..... I never thought about adding a review of the app only because I felt that I never had the time. I would have given this app a 4 star review until today; hell, I used it over Google Maps! After the previous update though, things have changed. I used the app, as I do, for my long distance runs to see relatives and discovered that the GPS Triangulation has become ruined by the update. This means that where the app was capable of figuring out that you were within a specific radius of the current GPS tag and then taking your trajectory and momentum into account to determine your actual location and heading, to provide a fluid navigation experience; the current update has caused this software logic to crash and become nonfunctional. This leaves the app continually updating, eating data, and more importantly guessing your location and then altering your directions to redirect you to the route that you are already on. I was able to make it to my prime location the first time by ignoring the app inconsistencies and using the directions that I already knew. But then when I attempted to use the app to direct me to a short distance trip for coffee, it recommended so many wrong turns, and u-turns to correct for the wrong turns which it had just directed me, I became irate and was only able to successfully reach my destination through spoken directions given by my mother! If it wasn't for my mother I might still be lost in the journey to get coffee!!! So after my most harrowing of coffee runs and most irate of trips I was glad I didn't chuck my phone from the window going down the highway!!! This app is by definition unusable due to the poor quality of the previous software update. I am surprised Google allowed it to go live in this sort of disrepair. For that reason I am submitting a One Star review while sipping cold brew coffee and re-downloading google maps over Wi-Fi..... Because like I said, this app ate sooo much data having a stupid day that I am going to have to conserve the rest so I don't wind up paying for extra gigs from my provider!!! Thanks Waze.... You really DIDN'T help me!!!!

But bread and butter functions like rerouting & road information are perfect.

Waze has eliminated the ability for users to lock the zoom at their preferred level, meaning that users in urban areas can't view their next turn because the roads all blend together. Or the screen is constantly moving, not showing me what I need and being distracting. No one needs to see the whole northern hemispher. This once imperative app I used daily for years is now useless. It was probably a big data generator for Google, too. Goodbye, Waze.

Also it show longer ETA for non-tolled roads compared to tolls road but once we decide to use non-tolled road, sometimes we arrive faster or at the same time as the suggested tolled road. The only reason I use Waze over Google Maps is that I find the routes and next exit on Waze are much clearer.

Waze has gone down. I started a drive where it was only an hour initially followed the route as instructed only for it to take 2hours to make it home. And there wasn't a route change. No there wasn't an accident. Plus I can't stop calls during driving. Need a drive auto response

replyContent: Hi, Constantine! Thanks for the feedback. There is an option to turn off railroad crosing alerts, just open Waze > Tap Search > Settings > Map display > Reports > Railroad crossing > toggle 'Alert me while driving' to off. This app used to be good, recently it hasn't been detecting my location AT ALL and telling me im places I'm not and using the incorrect location when calculating my routes. Causing me to be late on many occasions or get lost. It takes longer than it should to correct it's self as well.
Sometimes give u wrong direction
The clarity of directions given is extremely important and helpful.

Good at navigating a single route, but light on features eg. It doesn't do multi-destination, like Google Maps. This is a huge miss for anything other than casual use. The app is quite likely to take you down a dirt road & even sometimes down city centre bus lanes User experience isn't great because (ironically) navigating around the app is very poor Overall, disappointing
replyContent: Hi Chris, thank you for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze experience. We invite you to submit any app changes you wish to see to the Waze suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: For 3 months google maps has gotten me lost when I've had to go far to visit a friend. Finally I had enough and downloaded Waze gps. I should've done it a long time ago. Waze gave me excellent directions and I was able to get to my destination without a hitch. Thank you Waze....

Worked OK for some time, now it's back to the blank maps, stuttering display when it does sort of work .... On Ford Sync 3 fully updated and Android 9 ... And it still refuses to work properly ... Even when android auto and Google maps do !!!! .... Had enough of this and will not be using again as I need something which is reliable !!!!
replyContent: Hi John, thanks for reaching out about your issue with seeing a blank map. We'd like to hear more details about this to investigate further and help. To do so, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I absolutely love the Waze app. It keeps up with my overly chaotic work schedule helping to let me know ahead of time it's almost time to leave for work. Waze keeps up with all the latest traffic updates making sure my commute to and from work is smooth and painless. I highly recommend the Waze Navigation app if you tend to me a time cruncher for most or all events or have issues arriving on time to work.

[EDITED] After applying the last update, the minor problems were 99,9% solved; only the avatar that is still frequently dissapear. Major request: More detail maps: the name of the main & small streets, also alleys, if possible. Overall, a nice & very useful App! Thank You, Devs!üëçüèª[/EDITED] ‚Ä¢ Last update ruined its good work in which it persistently encountered error on user personalization -- it got crashed everytime I changed & customized the existing user data to update my password & avatar.
replyContent: Hey, Henry! We're sorry to hear that you're experiencing this issue. We'd like to learn more about what's occurring, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Come on guys! When is someone going to produce a navigation app far ALL road users. Moped riders need the ability to avoid other high speed roads, not just Freeways. Also having an option to configure the top speed of your vehicle will make for more accurate ETA data. Marginally better than some pay per use apps. Its 'OK' but could be great.

My experience with Waze is in relation to the Mazda android auto interface. It's pretty good at what it does and the hazard features etc are pretty handy. I'd like to see it remember routes after the car has been turned off and on again (e.g.stopped at ships or to get petrol) I'm not sue if it's Waze or Mazda's issue, but lack of touch screen support (when stationary) is a bit annoying. [Edit] Waze seems to remember routes after car turned off occasionally, now. Biggest headache now is voice navigation issue: I give a command, the command appears as said on the nav screen, the address Waze offers is the street only, not the number, which is an issue on those long roads. (May be Mazda, may be Google, may be Waze)

It does everything you can think of and then some . I love the Cop up ahead warning it tells you gas stations gas prices fish GPS app is by far the most amazing one you could possibly download. I recommend everybody should have this and when it comes to the speedometer the speedometer they have that tells you how fast you were going is OnPoint it is dead accurate I hope this was helpful

I like this app until Waze came out with the Waze carpool app. Now my phone appears to be hijacked. Constantly I am bombarded with very loud annoying ads trying to take me to Google Play to download this stupid app that I won't use, don't want, and I'm sick of hearing it's loud music blaring when people are sleeping!

Never seen one bug, sometimes I get to the location earlier than the predicted time if it's not exactly correct, combined with the ability to see/report road hazards, heavy traffic, police traps and more. The only thing google maps has that is better is a constant display of the optimal lane.

Low volume issue using Waze. Often happens at least a few times a month in which Waze app on android phone will speak directions at low sound level. now, I have a new car and same issue continues to happen in android auto. I've tried restarting phone üì± and issue lingers until one day it resolves itself to my surprise. Would love some feedback on how to troubleshoot this if there is a workaround.

I used to rely heavily on Waze, however with all its glitches and faults it is now a hazard and dangerous to use. I notice from many other reviews that the complaints are common, but also that the responses from Waze is the same automated one every time. You guys really need to fix the bugs if you want anyone to use your app successfully.

I use it every morning and afternoon to and from work. Most days it's fine for traffic. The other day it took me straight into a situation where they closed down the highway due to an accident. There's another highway that was not suggested when I ckd all the options. I was pretty frustrated.
replyContent: Hi, Orna! Thank you for your feedback. We understand how that can be frustrating. We'd love to hear more about the issues you're experiencing, would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: AFAICT Guest accounts are no longer available so there's no good way to try it out. That's an instant uninstall.
replyContent: Hi Carl, thanks for reaching out. You actually can still use the app as a guest. When installing the app, choose "Get Started" and then "Sign up later". We do encourage you to create an account to save favorites and more. But you do not have to create an account if you don't want to. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Over all it's a good app I use it all the time. I do wish however that it would do more than just show on screen the intended path like google maps will tell you and show you how many lanes there is and which one you should be in because sometimes it give you a last second correction because your in the wrong lane and you miss your turn

The loss of "ok Waze" to set a destination is huge. As a commercial driver I often need to change my destination while already driving, with distracted driving laws I cannot touch my phone while driving. Loosing the voice activation means I now have to pull over and park to legally change my destination. For me Waze lost the biggest feature that set it apart from most other GPS apps or units.
replyContent: Hi Hino, we completely understand your concern. Have you tried using Google Assistant to search hand free? Here's how: tinyurl.com/y8c8spjs For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Google maps is so much better

Doesn't allow for no tolls even though I select no toll route. Doesn't allow a change in route option while plugged to the car. Maps is buggy. Sent me to the wrong destination twice, but google maps got me there with the same addresd plugged in. No option to intentionally re-route to avoid traffic - instead it sends me in a circle back to the traffic I was trying to avoid. Ads pop up that distract while navigating/driving. The last 2 updates removed my ability to post warnings to other drivers.

Please make it available on your next update to check off a box to completely avoid a specific road. If I could set it to completely avoid a specific road, it would instantly become the best navigation app ever. I never want to drive on I-4 in the Orlando area ever again. Your app would not allow me to do this.

Overall great. I just wish that I could turnoff alerts for "Red Light Camera ahead" because I don't care. Also, would be nice if you could indicate "road closed for construction." It gets the major ones (somehow...but I don't know how it gets entered), but not all of the smaller ones.

did not find the quickest way to our destination. Added at least an hour and traffic was not an issue. Liked the police alerts. Map screen would go away every so often causing me to have to find it . Not great while driving.

STOP REMOVING CLOSED ROAD. I revently moved house, in my new town there is a road 1 week into a 6 week closure. Many people, myself included keep reporting the road closed but waze keeps removing it. I try to drive around it but waze keeps sending me right to the close road. Completely useless garbage app, if we say a road is closed, that means it's closed. Stop removing it!!!! I don't know this area yet, it would be nice if waze would help but apparently thats not the idea of this app.

Used to work great. Now with the latest update, constant freezes with Android auto. No speedometer as well. Also I live near 3 red light cameras. I know that they are there!! GIVE THE OPTION TO MUTE RED LIGHT CAMERAS!! I will be using Google maps until this is fixed. NOT a fan of Google maps bit at least it works everytime I need it.
replyContent: Hi Brian, thanks for your feedback. We'd like to hear more details about this speedometer issue you‚Äôre experiencing to investigate further. To do so, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Far better than a dedicated GPS device.

this needs more work. I've tested it on two 2hr plus trips and each time it has dropped the route. it also loses it's way when you take a diversion, it can't recalculate and reconnect. it's not good out of internet range. Back to Google Maps in the meantime.

Until the last update it actually worked very good, but today it literally navigated me into the traffic jam even that it was labeled on the map, but when the road is clear, it suddenly can navigate you through the longest route possible. Something is clearly wrong here.

Needs to show ZIP code It has a lot of good fearures like the ability to see and mark police and accidents. Unfortunately, if you're in a metropolitan area that has the same address listed 3 times, not being able to comfirm the ZIP code can lead you to the wrong place. Twice.

I love the app and I try to update it so others can be helped by my info... One suggestion... You need to add Optimus Prime and Megatron on the list of names as what would be better for automobiles. I know I'd love to have megatron telling me what to do and where to drive.

Everything is gone... I've been a Waze user for years and years and thusly had loads of saved addresses and settings. One day when I opened it my entire account was gone. My saved addresses, my points, my setting, my status - literally everything. I can't depend on this app anymore and that sucks. (Was fine until the update in July 2020.)
replyContent: Hi Deedee, we're sorry to hear that. Let's get this fixed for you! Please send us a private message on Facebook with your username. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Helps me save time by allowing me to see the fastest route. I really like that it will tell me if there is an accident or if traffic is backed up. And you can also alert other Waze users of things that may impact them if they decide to go in that direction. In my opinion, it is way better than using Google maps.

Why does after the recent updates..Gps is always difficult to detect? Always took very long to show the navigation route. After many times force close the app..then only will the navigation route line appear. Works so fine in the past..just open the app..enter the address..navigation route appears..then off u go. Now..so frustrating. Is it bug or something? Pls do something to make it as effective and effecient as before.
replyContent: Hi Muhd, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: When using with android auto Like another user mentioned, waze all of the sudden stopped showing my speed, the speed limit, map does not adjust zoom with speed, i am a blue dot, and just acting erratic since a few days ago. content: Beats TomTom anytime! This free to use Sat Nav is fantastic, it will only get better with more users. Personally I would like to have the option to add things to it, ie Heavy Rain Excessive Surface Water etc. Also a quick button to add road closure, or accident on other side of road. Little tweaks , but thats a personal taste, but I love it.

Disappointed with the app... Decided to try it around town before using it on my upcoming road trip. The routes it took were indirect and several times it had me driving past my destination and then having me lap the block before arriving. I like the layout so I would try it again in the future. Oh. I couldnt get it to work w android auto.

I am having a hard time using this app for the past few months. I already swapped phones with my wife, but it's still the same. Waze app cannot connect to the GPS, and with that I cannot see my destination when driving. It is indeed a big hassle for me as a Grab driver. Hoping for your immediate action. Thank you.
replyContent: Hi Victor, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Good ideas, inconsistent execution. I appreciate that Waze can give me time estimates and route suggestions that take into account that I'm carpooling. Otherwise I find it busier and chattier than Google Maps, with less clear and less timely directions. I also really want Waze Carpool to work but so far the user base along my commute isn't very good and most riders I see aren't active users.

Waze is amazing!! There is no other directions app that comes close to its accuracy & quality! It (and God!) got me 2 1/2 hours from home to my vaca destination in torrential rain in the dark on unfamiliar routes. Goodbye forever, unreliable Mapquest. I HIGHLY recommend Waze!!

I've used waze for many years, practically everyday even just going to/from work as it's saved me a number of times to navigate unexpected jams,. "In waze we trust!". One of the most dependable apps I had. However, recently moved from iphone 6s to Pixel 4A and I can barely get the app to open. It simply comes up, enter address and crashes...restart & crash. Very disappointed. Pls pls fix! (Rated 2 (not 1) stars for past glory.)
replyContent: Hi Mike, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this app crash issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Too many bugs for the android version of this app. App shuts down abruptly, sometimes doesn't start the navigation even though the internet is working. Used to work much smoother until few months ago. Google maps is much more stable than this although surprisingly they are both Google products

When i first launch the app it will shut down my phone. This is an intermittent issue. My phone will give off a lound high pitched chirp and such down when the map is loading. This only happens with this app. Waze has refused to offer any support even after multiple attempts of contacting them for support. The last representative was actually quite insulting.
The UI is good everything is good this is the best navigation app I have ever used but itacks one thing offline maps

Not sure if it's an android auto issue or it's waze itself, but at times the map area is all white or all black. This makes it a little difficult to see what's happening around me. Mapwise, the Maps app still works fine, so I can still see a map & traffic data

content: App works, when it wants to. Use this app minimum 2 times a day, to and from work, even though it's a 17 minute drive one way. At least 1 of those 2 the app is trying to find GPS for some reason, just started happening about a week ago. I have to keep closing and opening the app until it works. Otherwise I love it.

content: App was good. Seems google getting it's hands on it is all down hill. Nice work googleü§£ü§£ not. Seems to me that you are killing this app on purpose as no company can stuff a perfectly working app this bad unless it is on purpose. One day an option works next day it doesn't. And from all reviews all to common. Guess we all will have to wait for a new app like waze to be put out on the market from a new player üëç

1st I've always been a big fan of "The Waze App", but it seems to be becoming to commerized. I wanted to answer there question regarding the ads. They didn't offer all usual options. The ads are ok, but they pop up at a critical time in filling directions. Trust me this app. has lots to offer!
