content: This app PUTS GOOGLE MAPS TO Fing shame!! Google maps will take u straight into a CLOSE ROAD AND OR STRAIGHT INTO A ROAD OR ROADS THAT NO LONGER EVEN EXIST!! HAS happened to me more then once with Google maps and kn I love Google nothing like that at all but u cant use them both at same time and in all aspects this app. Is better then Google maps

Location constantly dropped out, several times it didnt tell me when to turn. As I was doing a Postmates delivery, I used the navigation button in the Fleet app to take me to the drop off address, Waze instead took me to a LITTLE CEASARS in the OPPOSITE direction of the drop off address. This app is worse than Maps, uninstalling and going back to Google. At least Google takes me to the proper address.

Ways used to be good. Now it reroutes you in unnecessary paths to alleviate the main flow of traffic elsewhere. Halfway through my road trip it's saying that it cannot find a route. It's been doing this for the last two states. Absolute garbage

Unreliable if you are looking for the shortest, fastest route and will have errors when rotating from portrait to landscape mode or even connecting to its own network, and will send you on random detours that save you neither time nor distance. When going on a 6 hour trip, Waze added an hour detour compared to a more direct (faster, shorter, safer) Google Maps route. Waze is useful for their alerts, but when traveling somewhere new, far away, or fast; it is better to use Google Maps in general.

Great app overall. Gives real time updates which is excellent for avoiding traffic jams. Accurate appox 95% of the time, so be mindful of that. In addition, if you are not a comfortable driver i would recommend enabling the "avoid difficult intersections as waze takes you down lots of side streets which bring you out onto busy main roads which you often have to edge your way out of to cross over and continue your journey.

Terrible sometimes. Doesn't understand many of the map details. Tells me to go past an easy left turn in order to a difficult u turn. Locks up on occasion. Hitting back exits the app instead of just exiting nav mode. Often adds to the frustration of driving in traffic instead of helping.

This app was horrible when I first started using it, then it was pretty good for a long time, now it's utter garbage again. Every time I open it to find directions to a place an error occurs, so I have to shut it down and then reopen it. Literally every time. You need to get yourselves together Waze. Unacceptable.

App crashes too often to be used as a reliable source for navigating. Love being able to report road hazards, but not worth it when your directions just freeze and you don't even realize it in time. Going back to Google Maps. :\

A continually helpful app, having used it for years. Finds almost every destination I want and guides me there with ease. Has the occasional issue when maps are incorrect, but has the facility to flag these and thanks to the map editor community, these are updated. Waze has some excellent features that assist with making driving easier and safer by working together.

My experience with Waze App was always good, but the reason why I quit using it is because a friend of mine was recently killed in a car crash by a wrong way driver with a suspended license (It is said that he blamed Waze for instructing him to turn onto the wrong road that lead to this crash).
I love the way waze lets you know whats ahead so you can take alternate routes to your destination. Thank you Waze .

Would be amazing software, if the official roadworks were still visible. Also some routing options don't follow any logic, directing to longer routes, closed roads and narrow paths. Every suggested route has to be checked first with Google Maps if I want to get somewhere with optimized kms and time.

What is Google doing to waze. It is getting super crappy. Doesn't sit on top, constantly crashes, which is oh so awesome when driving, doesn't know where you are when you start, (guess which way to turn) and closes when I call anyone or if I get a call through my cars bluetooth. I have been a huge lover and fan of waze since its creation. Why Google, you suck.
replyContent:
Hi Deborah, we‚Äôre disappointed to hear you had a negative app experience but appreciate your feedback. We'd like to hear more about this issue you're experiencing with the app crashing. To best assist, please send us a private message on Facebook. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Was a really good app but lately when I want to go to home or work or anywhere it wants to take me the most indirect route instead of how it always took me years ago. Find myself not using it anymore because it's not working properly and I can't trust the route it's taking me.
replyContent: Hi there, thank you for the feedback. We always try to find the best route for our Wazers but if you notice a recurring issue with a route, please let us know by sending us a private message on Facebook: m.me/waze We'd be happy to look into it. Also, you may find your favorites route by checking alternate routes. Here's how: tinyurl.com/y22mbhag

content: I absolutely love this app, aside from the cool graphics I love that I can rely on this app to help ke figure when the best times to start driving are, for my daily carpooling needs (I regularly have two to three people riding with me to work) and even happier that I can use this to navigate while using the Lyft driver app. The best part of this may qctually be the Wazer users, notifications of traffic, accidents and contrstuction zone reports help. Cannot stress how much I love this app!

I can't consciously give this app a perfect score because there is one thing in particular I really wish it would do that I think would make the app so much better. I want to be able to rate the directions I am given. Sometimes it completely fails and takes me to the wrong place and I want to give a rating on that and maybe even correct the location

Great app, use it more than Google Maps due to the current speed/speed limit indicators when connected to an Android Auto head unit. User interface while unique could do with a modern refresh. Biggest gripe at the moment is that the when navigating with Waze connected to Mazda CX-9 Android Auto, and Waze is in the background, the physical navigation button in my car brings up the car navigation software on the screen instead of Waze. When navigating with Google maps this works well.

I have used Waze for years and have loved it. That being said, the last 6 months have been really bad. Almost always have connection issues now and I feel lucky if it actually finds a route or actually connects to the server. I hope they fix it soon. Loved the app, but I need to be able to count on it.

Very useful, use it everyday. Just small issue on my Samsung galaxy note 9 where gps will fail to connect when there is full service and location services are turned on. Also it seems to be playing catch up lately, it will be late on some directions and when they are missed it will take those precious seconds and minutes sometimes to re route and when it does it slows down quickly

Used to be great now it's a giant headache. For over a month now constantly will not find a GPS signal unless I restart my phone. Even then it may drop out. Thought it was my phone. So I just got a brand new Samsung Galaxy s20 ultra. Still does it. I've tried all the fixes, clear cache, battery settings location settings uninstalling reinstalling the app.
replyContent: Hi Justin, we're sorry to hear about your issue. Please check you phone's location settings and make sure that GPS is enabled on your app. Here's how: tinyurl.com/tpnaxwv If the issue continues, please contact us via Facebook private message so we can investigate further. Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: My go to app for driving. Wish it had "find my car", and it would be perfect. Maybe can be added later or added to existing app. Just thinking how to improve a great driving app without adding another app for large cities I'm not familiar with. Thinking ahead guys and thanks for Waze. By the way, I've been using Waze for seven years and wouldn't consider using anything else. It even gets me all around Disneyworld!!!!!!!!!!

Please update app to let user know which side of the street the location is on prior to arrival. It currently states you've arrived at your destination or something to the like. It would be helpful if the direction stated your destination is coming up on the left or right.

A very versatile navigation app! I use it every chance I get everyday. It's highly accurate at estimating arrival time and suggesting departure times for planned drives. I'd only recommend that they PLEASE add a feature within the app to schedule recurring drives. It would be so handy to get a daily departure time suggestion without having to set it up everyday üôè.

Used to always use waze all the time, but more and more these days it reroutes you miles along tiny back roads to save 3mins but it ends up taking you 20mins more, can there be an option to ask before rerouting or only do if it saves you more than X mins. I think the issue is that it thinks unclassified roads you can do 60mph on which you usually can't.

Best navigation app I've used so far. easy to understand and blows my mind with all the info it gives on what's happening on the road e.g. pot holes, stopped vehicles and even if the police is up ahead. I don't speed but I'm sure that encourages others to drive safely. 5 stars for me!
Changes route instantly to save time is NOT a good navigation feature. Having the option is ok but not "INSTANTLY".

Used to be my go to Navigation because of the traffic reports and speed limit info. Google maps is catching you up in this regard. Exiting Waze when reaching destination has always been irritating with its pop up window after pushing the back key, now its the reason I have switched to Google who have a "Done navigation" button to exit their app making existing simpler. When reaching my destination i want close the app quickly and exit my car. Waze extra step is annoying. Hope you sort this out.

this app was great to use last year where you were able to add celebrity voices into it. In future updates,please add the celebrity voices to it so we don't have to root our phones to get the celebrity voices back. I loved using Arnold Schwarzenegger voiceüòî.disapointed you guys took it out.

I've been using this app for over a year and it's been great however in the last week it has gotten exceptionally buggy. It keeps read calculating and trying to send me down dead end on the same route I go everyday. I don't know what's up with the app, I haven't changed any settings this is just randomly happening

Used to be fantastic, now just OK. Positives: App enables me to drive at a sensible speed without being booked for speeding, still works OK as a navigation app, integrates Spotify well. Negatives: App developers have lost focus on the two core features that made this app great - finding the fastest possible route & avoiding speeding fines. App now seems to route main roads when back roads or "rat runs" are quicker, no focus on improving police reporting features - stinks of political influence.

It would be good if the app allow me to save several location and view them in map view, as sometimes i need to know am i near to my favourite location. And the searching feature still can be improved by searching by gesture i.e. sliding an alphabet or stg to directly search for some places. For example, slide P to search for nearest petrol station (for me whose language cannot be recognised by phone XD)

This app has not only saved me several speeding tickets, it has literally saved my life. Real life story: I was traveling down hwy35s in Austin when I was trying to change radio stations the Waze app told me " watch out object on road ahead" that's when I looked up and was a hair away from ramming the guy in front of me. Turns out he hit a dishwasher that fell off a truck. Thank you Waze.

Waze lost my original account. They still haven't acknowledged, let alone solved, issue adding comments to user generated points on map or to show a road closure without having to physically go to that road myself first. Waze is easy to use to get from A to B but, relies on user updates. If a user has inaccurately shown a road closure too short, then Waze is useless giving an accurate route. And if I and others cannot correct the issue then Waze is useless to me. Customer service team = useless.

I use Waze on a daily basis and I enjoyed using it. After the last update, with Android Auto it loses the GPS connection continuously. I can't navigate with it anymore. It takes more than 20 sec to get the connection back after losing it and it last 5 sec, then lost connection again and a blue dot shows up and so on and so forth. Today I discovered a workaround that is insane. I have to start a navigation with Google Maps alongside with Waze and then it keeps the connection up. FIX IT ASAP!!

Great app, love the speed limit markings. However, there is a bug when making Bluetooth calls when the app is running. While on call, I get the most annoying beeps. Sounds setting are on mute, and mute while on call is enabled. Please fix this!

Good app but it crashes a lot and is less stable than Google maps on my note 9. Also there is no auditory warning for speed cameras if travelling below the road speed limit. This is an issue in the UK where we have variable speed traps. For example I have been travelling at 60mph on a road which usually has a 70mph limit but with variable speed traps displaying 50mph, this has landed me with a fine due to waze not warning me of the trap.

Not working well since last update. Now it crashes more, says it can't find the network, takes forever to build routes, builds the wrong route and takes me down roads I know are not faster. Last update also broke the volume during a call, it's super loud now, louder than the call I'm on, and it can't be adjusted.

(Reviewing this as a carpool driver, comparing the Scoop) Pros: - Waze lets you choose any time of day/night you want to carpool. Scoop is limited to just mornings and late afternoons. - Waze lets you choose your riders; Scoops tries to assign them (only when it fails and shortlists them would you get to choose) Cons: - Waze places super high priority on the route of the first carpooler in the route. Ergo you rarely ever get a 2nd or 3rd carpooler.

Whilst the app isn't bad the support/web site around the app is not as helpful as it might be for people evaluating the product... Also:- * Cannot submit feedback to the 'main' website without an account * While a voice 'type' can be selected, there is no preview available of the voice * There should be options to set an alert at a point *before* the speed limit is reached * The interface is not particularly clear; sometimes a swipe from the left edge doesn't actually bring up the info/settings page. Thanks.

content: I love love love this app! I enjoy knowing that things are ahead of me before I have an opportunity to discover it on my own when it saves me time, money, gas, speeding tickets, or the chance of an accident. I do not condone speeding, but as a result of monitoring the road, I have been known to have a heavier foot at moments, so it keeps me alert and aware of what it is that I'm doing behind the wheel.

ETA is often more optimistic than realistic but arrival can even be sooner than estimated.Estimates are within +- 10%. Many times it tried ti send me via the inner city which caused significant delays, but after ovverriding it many times it "learned" my preferred routes. You can find a faster route by overriding but just the same you can run into a traffic jam. Recommended even in your home city it can be helpful to avoid unexpected traffic jams. For long rides I prefer google maps though.
Excellent for immediate use, but doesn't help if you want to plan journey if not current location.

content: It doesn't reroute at all. If I miss an exit or have some errands on the way and take another route, this app doesn't reroute and let me choose another route for my destination. It sticks to the initial route and insists on taking a U-turn or come back to initial route. Annoying.

Works pretty well, without a compelling reason to use this instead of Google Maps. I have an electric vehicle and strongly request that the devs add a setting to turn off everything related to petrol (gas) stations - I just don't need it!

i love waze. but one thing that bothers me is that the ETA always seems to be how long it should take. not really an actual ETA based on current traffic conditions. then it will update your ETA to later times as you are now trapped in horrific traffic. im looking at the numerous reports on my route and wondering how it thinks i could possibly make the ETA im being told. i don't understand why a more realistic ETA cant be suggested before departure when the app has all this live traffic data.

I installed Waze 3 months ago because of its Android Auto integration and Camera Alert features. I gave it a test drive and none of the 5 cameras was detected! I uninstalled it straight away. content: really impressed with this app & thoroughly recommend it. 2 minor gripes are that Spotify doesn't connect properly, it works but not as intended as it keeps saying no connection, the other little problem is this works with Tune in radio but won't work with the paid for pro version, if these get fixed then I would happily give the the full 5 stars.

Speedometer broken momentarily and Waze is invaluable just for that function. Waze is also much easier to use than maps, allows for media control on screen, traffic and police locations as well as being accurate left or right and within 50'. In my experience, best GPS I've used in the 28 years or so since GPS replaced the triangulated, mostly marine use Loran. Wtg developers!

Far too many screen taps required to do things when otherwise trying to concentrate - Recording a vehicle stopped on the hard shoulder should be ONE tap on the screen, not the FIVE taps that it currently takes. content: After running Google Maps and Waze side by side for a few months, Google Maps was the more accurate and better navigation app for me. Waze recommended some strange routes that always took longer than it anticipated. I'll be sticking to my old faithful, Google Maps.

But ads pop up so often and fill half the screen when they do (i am in an urban area with slow speed limits and lots of small stops) that i have trouble using the ap safely. Please make an ad-free version because i want to use waze. Without it, this app is not safe.

The only reason I'm giving two stars is because this is the best of a bad situation can someone please develop a navigation app that actually works correctly most of the time I'll even settle for most of the time what is the big problem with developing a navigation app that actually works this app sends you on completely wrong route so don't ever trust this app 100%. The only thing that really makes this app shine above the rest is the cop feature if it wasn't for that I wouldn't be using it

content: ***TIME ZONE NOTIFICATION *** This is a very convenient app. Will get you where you going for the most part. I will say it lacks in informing you that/if your destination is in a different time zone. So when your planning a trip you will not know/notice your ETA doesn't fall under the timezone your traveling towards.

App is very good but it does have some onerous rerouting at times. The app would benefit with: 1. An option to use your phones system TTS voices. 2. Road sign option, these really help on busy motorways & junctions 3. Junction View option 4. 3D buildings are helpful for navigation in urban areas 5. Terrain maps option, very useful for countryside navigation. If Waze latest info, CoPilot voice navigation and signs with Sygic maps and graphics were all one app then the ultimate nav app wow.

used to be good. brightness is pinned at max with no option to dim unless you want to manually turn on battery saver every time you drive. will definitely cause burn on an OLED display. I loved this app but I'll be going back to Google maps due to this terrible design. get with the times, waze. everyone has OLED displays now.

The idea is nice and the app used to be. However, recently it just hasn't been working. It lags, it disconnects, just overall not worth the concern while also trying to drive. I went back to Google Maps.

Waze is very good when it works. Since I have installed id I used it for couple of days and "No GPS signal" error is constant. All other navigation programs that I use are getting my exact position, while Waze just remains frozen. It even calculates route from my frozen position. Quite disappointed. Hopefully a fix is on the way.

content: Very happy with app and use it all the time even for just traffic and destination updates. Pretty accurate
I deleted the app after it took us on a 30 min detour, including some rough parts of Chicago.
Best app by far!

I thought Waze was supposed to take traffic conditions into account when calculating a route. It clearly does not. Today, I decided to follow Waze's directions home from work. Waze decided that the Interstates near me would be the fastest. I crawled along in traffic congestion at speeds between 0 to 7 mph on one Interstate and between 15 to 20 mph on the second. I usually take a combination of state highways and county roads where traffic can slow but not like on the Interstates.

Overall a good Sat Nav app. Better than Google maps. Good that it makes you aware of hazards and speed guns too. I was also impressed with the fact it shows you the cheapest place to fill up nearby. It would be good if it also showed cheapest parking nearby!
Fun app and I like that you can receive and report things for others to know. Wish I could put avoid roundabouts though!

It's not doesn't show up on my kenwood dmx7705s. It has work in the pass now it not showing up. I found out that Waze is doing away with some of their business with car head units. I fine this really annoying because it leave my phone on the dash and it overheats my phone. Now I can't use my head unit the way I wanted to use it for.

One change I would make would be to set it up so it does not need to update voice commands uoon start up as frequently, or, configure it so I can still dictate an address, without having to wait for the voice commands to be updated.
Very helpful when trying to locate new places.

I NEVER Car Pool, so it's frustrating, and dangerous to have popups while I'm driving asking me about carpooling! That should be a one time, offline option! Seems to lose WiFi connection more than Google Maps. Be nice if it was clear on which side of divided highway the cop or accident is.

was an awesome app on trip to Memphis. Got me exactly where I was going. No problems then it crashed and kept crashing. So deleted it and reinstalled it because I really liked it. Now all it will do is crash. Sorry gotta give you 2 stars. Would be 5 if it continued to work, but it doesn't at all.
Waze is one app I can't live without, I love everything about it, it's accuracy it's unmatched. Great app
Accurate!! Avoids traffic, when possible. Great for speed zones, police activity, directional maneuvers, etc!

Uses less power than Google Maps. Has ads but I love that they only pop up when you're stopped and go away when you start driving again. One suggestion: have the voice tell whether the destination is on the left or right

Bad to worse.

content: Latest update extremely unstable, frequent crashes/reloads and GPS tracking now very poor (meanwhile other GPS apps work fine so not the device). Worked flawlessly for many years prior to this; I am left trying to figure out how to downgrade to a previously working version.

Waze has helped me on countless opportunities. I love the police alerts and the directions to avoid congestion as much as possible. It is irritating when people post a notification multiple times instead of just confirming whether or not someone else's reported alert is still present. Good app. Very useful! My only issue is whenever I route my waze to a destination, it tells me to go other ways as optional routes, but they don't guide me to my direct path. If there was a way to turn off the suggestive turns, that'd be super!

I use this app sooo much!! Its pretty good. It can be improved in a couple of things. Like it would be so awesome if the weather was on the maps as well... if the weather radar was also here I think it would be the perfect app if ur a driver..

content: Very useful for navigation & road alerts. It did help me figure routes that I haven't taken & other roads to travel. We hope that the developer will endeavor to rectify the shortcomings and bring back the option for fastest route instead of long winded routes.

I wish it did more like Google map and told me which lane to get it. Like in Atlanta it said turn right on exit ## but google map would say turn right in 3rd lane so I knew where to be. content: Kept me aware of my surroundings in advance

I've tried to reinstall the apps, even master reset, and yet it couldn't solve the problem. any expert has experience it before please provide some solution for me. I'm currently using Samsung galaxy note 8, all the location setting and improve accuracy setting is on yet can't connect to gps. URGENT help pls

This 3 star review is only relevant for the Samsung Galaxy S3. Ignore it if your phone resembles anything modern. It works all right but if you don't have it plugged into something it drains the battery extremely quicky (but then again, what navigation app on these phones does)? You'll also want to kill any other running apps before you launch it. This app might finally push me to upgrade.

I taught Gugle map was the best of all until I download this app . Gosh I think this is the best GPS app in the world . Even in my country where buy some roads are closed this app could tell you that this road is one way . Also some roads which are newly constructed waze app has already picked it but ....Gugle map always flops when ever you drive pass a new constructed road . Waze is the best because it gives a lot of informations when driving example ( Traffic , Police , Accident etc)

Not a bad app always use it. however,there are a lot of things missing, for example: traffic lights out report unable to do on Android auto and also when reporting roadworks they do not place on the map. Notifications are buggy too does not warn me of upcoming hazards.

Every free app is only as good as its community; luckily, Waze has a very active one and thanks to that it can provide the most recent road information in any country. Definitely a must-have, even if you like your in-car navigation.

IMO the best satnav app out there. Love the information it gives you when driving. Are definitely a wazer now. Only criticism is that i drive a van whereby speed limits on national speed limit roads are less for my vehicle. Please could you have an option for selecting vehicle type such as van and display the correct speed limit for my vehicle on NS roads. Also height of vehicle to avoid low bridges, other than that will only ever use waze now and drive around the country approximately 1000 pw

Waze Goes Crazy! App is fun AND frustrating- not sure why, but sometimes my nav with Waze is so off it's unreal. Ex: used app to avoid traffic on major freeway due to an accident. Waze led me on a scenic detour that made me 30 MIN LATE! Finally at the office a co worker (who left later but stayed on the freeway) was only 10 MIN late. Other ex: street driving thru LA traffic pulling maneuvers like unprotected left turn on major highways. App itself is dope but I need it for nav so...:/

As a user for 5+ years, I've got to concur with the most recent reviews. How to grab defeat from the jaws of victory. From trying to write this review, to being constantly logged out from app upgrades, to username not recognised in the mobile app, to not able to login via the web portal, to trying to verify my credentials after an app upgrade and getting a 'Connecting' message that never completes, to not recognising my email address on password reset or fails due to a very poor Android Auto integration that insists on running as if I am a new user. Time to dust of the actual requirements; reliability, ease of use and works every time!

I love this app it is great. It is better than Google maps. the only thing I wish this app could do Is I can save locations on it label the location and put a star or heart for favorites. I would love to be able to do that if this app has that capability let me know because I don't know it

Not as good as it once was. Often at times it routes me to areas where the traffic is heavier when there are alternate routes that would take less time. The fuel prices are not accurate at all and many times go weeks without being updated.
With this app...you will never feel alone because other drivers are always there to give the heads up for what lays ahead. üòÉüòä üëç

Confusing colors path. Where's the warning colors? Who decided to use light blue highlight for night and purple for day. Whether traffic is slow to 45mph color is still violet and traffic flowing 65mph to 75mph is still same color path. The path should change color according to how fast the traffic is going. Eat. Light blue or green for light traffic. Amber for moderate traffic and red for heavy traffic and or traffic jams. Those colors use in the app doesn't correspone to DOT type of warning

Everything about this application is the absolute best except for the fact that it drains the battery of your cell phone so fast that my 8 hour shift is not compatible with Waze because it burns out my battery in less than 4 hours. Other than that it's the best app out there regarding GPS and maps and real-time and all the other stuff that it does except for the fact that it drains the battery at a rate of never seen anything drain at.

Route keep on changing in the middle of a drive.

content: Very useful app, you can report anything. Driving would be way easier if everyone would report speed camera vans, road closures or other events. The best part is that the app monitors your speed and if there's a jam report it will redirect the other users on different routes to avoid traffic jams. Big thumbs up and 5 stars.

After long-time of using Waze I realize how stressed out driving has become. The twists and turns that you have people go on only to save a few minutes is outrageous. I no longer using this application Google has a much better platform it doesn't put you through a complete trying to get from point a to point b.

Thanks for this wonderful app. At first, I was afraid to use it because I thought it will give me a wrong way but WAZE proved that I am wrong. We arrived at our destination safe and faster than I thought. I will use it again and again and will continue to recommend this app to my friends especially to those who love to travel. Thank you again WAZE üòäüëç.

content: This app is great with ETA and Alternate routes when traffic is heavy. The only issues I have are the map editing process and the police alert. Maps I have edited for my work were never approved (the app still want me to go behind a building and through a wall) and police cars are often on the move (not standing still).

I've emailed support several times with ongoing glitches. Response is always to reinstall üôÑ. Still the best crowdsourced traffic app. 1. Nokia 6.1 has months long issue of the in-navigation search function not scrolling so I can't access it - portrait view only. 2. Same phone, landscape view, keyboard minimizes to leave half the navigation map blank black. Have to exit to all apps then reselect, or exit waze altogether.

Lately Waze is having a lot of critical issues. No network, no server connection, error calculating routes and so on. Terrible issues for an app that is dubbed as best navigation app. Google Maps on the other hand is very stable though it doesn't have much friendly features like Waze. Hope your team could figure this out soon enough. Thanks.

The navigation is not comprehensive in getting to your destination,no voice direction,it just so boring using it,I almost had an accident because I was trying to navigate my way to the rider yesterday. Pls work on the efficiency of the map,it so frustrating.

I love this app! But.. I hope you guys at Waze know what kind of capabilities you really have! I personally love this app more than Google itself, but if you had a little more personal things added then it would be even better. For example, more voices like the cookie monster voice would be amazing. Like add the navigator from the forza horizon game! Anyways I'm just giving ideas, but this is a really great app.

One of the best app out there, i am only giving 3star as they have speed alert on every street but no options to change alert sound and is only one soft beep. They app has heaps of potential to be great if that alone changes. Receiving speed alert can greatly reduce communities speeding fine. please implement properly as everything is in place for it.

Need to mater the speed limit sign bigger in the app. It's too small and needs to be bigger and very easy to tell the speed limit a a quick glance. Also if it had Lan prompts telling you which lane to be in then when driving like google maps. Then it would be the ultimate app!!

Needs truck routing (some of us would buy that from you)

Quite good navigation, I temporarily switched from Sygic and stayed with Waze. :) I would just welcome some information about future speed limit change on the road (e.g. that in 1000 speed limit will be reduced to 50). This should not be a big problem, as you already know where the speed limit is changing... :) I will then rate 5* ;)

I love this ap! I'm so grateful to my real estate agent for telling me about it because it's so much better than Google! I love the notifications about barriers and other things (police, etc). The navigation voice is very pleasant as well. I also love all of the other features of the ap, such as the ability to accrue points.

Waze is AMAZING!!! This is my go to app over google maps anyday! The only thing I dont care for is when trying to send an alert for traffic or disabled car on the shoulder or a officer ect. Im already a half mile down the road from passing the problem. It still a awesome app!

This is the best Navigation map app. their is even Google dosen't compare due to the face I get my direction fast Google could not find my location and I would have to keep restarting that app as with this app (waze) it gives my location the 1st time every time along with my direction to were I need to go and more accurately then any other I have used. Thank you Waze

Been using app almost 2 years... Very good maps and directions. Map editors are best with resolving issues quickly. Wants me to take I-95 over the GWB from CT to NJ 99.9% of the time. I prefer Tappanzee so I put in stop at Tappanzee Bridge before going into NJ. Invite all my friends to use Waze application for current road conditions and traffic.

I hope i could post some screenshots here. Seems like someone from the developer's side messed this up with the last update. FIX IT

content: So much more reliable than car built in SatNav

Generally good for the daily commute or longer journeys when my Wife needs the TomTom. Only two criticisms so far: with units set to miles, anything under 1/4 mile should be in yards not feet, and in tunnels please use the phone sensors to get a better location - it's not rocket science to use accelerometers to work out distance traveled (inertial navigation systems used that back in the 1970s)

Not as good as it used to be. The car touch screen does not react to the map as required. Cannot use the icon for traffic situations. Needs an upgrade. The app is good otherwise, the map itself is very good. When it has been sorted I will give 5 stars.

Great App! I use every day to navigate to and from work. I love the interaction between users-- gives accurate up-to-date information about traffic jams and accidents. Saved me from getting stuck in gridlock traffic multiple times. Keep up the great work!

This app has become a danger to myself and family. This will tell you to turn right while you're doing 60 miles an hour as you're passing the roads are supposed to turn on. My whole day is filled with u-turns, slamming on the brakes to try to make my turn. Waze wants me to videotape my phone while it does it. Surely someone is smart enough to figure it out
replyContent: Hi Jimmie, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this issue. You can try reducing difficult turns in your routes by adjusting the settings. To do so, tap Search> Settings> Navigation> Under "Routing", turn on "Reduce difficult intersections". For further assistance, please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Another good app ruined by Google. used to give police warnings at about 1 half to 1 mile away. Now you're lucky if you get ye warning at one tenth of a mile. Also the opportunity to confirm police presence goes away before you can even see the police car sometimes. I will be looking elsewhere.
replyContent: Hi Lewis, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: This app used to be good, but this latest update has screwed it up. All it does is freezes, and won't give you proper directions. I'm not sure if it's due to the serious lag that's happening. This was my go to, but I guess I have to go back to google maps.

content: Does not work on android. I had this app when I had an apple and loved it. With my new android phone, it just couldn't keep track of where I was, made us miss exits completely and just flat out didn't work. Had to open up Google maps instead to get us to our destination.

Latest update fixed it for about 1 mile before it got stuck again. No longer have heads up direction (the ability to select direction you are looking is gone) I use waze 99.9% of the time through my vehicles built in Android auto (2016 Chevrolet Colorado). Google maps & the built in navigation work just fine, just not waze.

voice command mostly doesn't work. keeps on saying updating voice commands. so I have to type it in. Then I get a prompt that says don't type while driving. Well if your app works right I wouldn't have too. then when I finally get the address and then hit go it says oops something went wrong try again later. I'm so tired of using this app time to go

Great and quick directions, I drive a dump truck and I wish you guys could have some flashing lights like a flashing barrel in the app so when your coming up to construction or there is construction sometimes you don't see the little yellow triangle with the hat on it if able to be developed. Maybe the same for police blinking blue. Thank you Gary A

This is the only app i trust and use regularly for navigation and traffic update. I just wished it could show designated speed of all the roads on a small bubble(Just like Highway Number or Name is shown on the map). I also wished if the bubble showing current speed had an option to be moved on right side of the screen because it normally gets obstructed by my steering wheel while i keep it on dock, Everytime i need to peek to see my current speed while driving which is quite risky all the time.

Idea of this App is great just doesn't work 80% of time I have had waze3 installed on my android phone for a number of years. 20% of the time the app voice over of warnings and directions works but 80% of the time it doesn't! I don't understand why in the comment side of the map I am unable to advise of roadworks but can mark police / Road closures / accidents. Its been like this for years now and no matter what I try to do it still unreliable..such a shame.
replyContent: Hey Ash, we're happy to help! You can report construction on the route by tapping the report button > Hazard > On road. content: All I can say is Nice App. All the options are just what you will enjoy using. Especially the one that says "Police Spotted Ahead" . Plus its voice activated. Listen to music or the updated news options. Give it a spin, you'll see what I mean..

I'LL NEVER USE GOOGLE MAPS OR THE GPS BUILT INTO MY CAR, AND NEVER GET A TICKET AGAIN!!! Besides being MUCH more accurate than Google Maps or my GPS... having MY SPEED vs SPEED LIMIT on screen + an audible alert if I'm going 10mi over, AND audible alerts for hazards/police/traffic/more...I can drive more safely and 100% worryfree!!! BONUS= my friend's & I can track each other's progress/ETA's on group trips too!!! I COULDN'T LOVE THIS APP MORE!!!

keeps searching for. network and when it isnt doing that it freezes up and you have to wait for it to completely restart. Was great ..now I wonder if they are trying to push people to Google maps instead!!!

Hi Fellow Wazers! I love ALL the different options Waze has. Been a Wazer for quite some time, over google maps & mapquest (which are both acceptable maps). I just havn't been misdirected on Waze so far like the other 2. S'times tho, now that I'm thinking about it, Waze's "MPH" has been off. I'm thinking maybe the actual posted speed limits change? Not sure if that's even possible, but really, it's fine... as long as I keep an eye on the posted signs. lOl Thanx Waze!

Edit for 7/1/2020: BRING BACK THE MOODS (and the cat mood too d:) Best naviagation app to use. Love the features. Seems like Google might start killing this off with the Google maps updates they've been pushing out. I honestly hope waze stays, I just prefer this UI and just about everything about this over gMaps. (just wish I could sync the directions with gear s3 smartwatch).

I love this whole concept and I feel happy every day that my carpoolers and I are keeping one or two more vehicles off the road and out of rush hour traffic. My criticism is that pickup and drop off spots are not always safe places to pull over. One time the app had me picking someone up on a highway entrance ramp.

Bring back the ability to add friends without Facebook. I have no interest in using Facebook, nor do most of my contacts.  Strangely enough, Waze has added 3 friends for me.  Many people I know use Waze and I can't add them as friends due to lack of Facebook.  I know I can share my ETA via SMS, but it is cumbersome.  Scout will allow me to add Buddies without Facebook and I think Waze needs to bring that back.

I like the app, and have been using for quite a few years now travelling all over the UK & Europe. It would be good to be able to plan by excluding a road, say like the M25 without excluding all motorways. Personally I'd like a paid version to remove the adverts which can be annoying and distracting.

For me it was a battery killer and most of the "road conditions" were just annoying flagging up "obstructions" and speed cameras. All that work it was doing and use of data and battery for something not useful. It was impossible to turn off the notifications.

I'm using Waze in the landscape screen orientation. After the bar with My Waze and Carpool was fixed at the bottom of the screen, added to the search bar that I do not know if I can hide also, the map effective height has decreased by over 35%. This is terrible utilization of the screen space. I'd like to be able to hide the Carpool and My Waze bar and make the search bar floatable. Please let me use my entire screen for the map while driving.
replyContent: Hi Vadim, thanks for your feedback. We're always looking to improve the Waze. The search bar cannot be hidden. We understand the inconvenience. content: This is a great app. The only thing I would like to to see is a truck route. As a professional driver this ap helps a lot. The only problem I have is that it sends cars on the Truck bypass. It says Truck Bypass for a reason. Cars don't belong there and just cause accidents.

Extremely disappointed with this app. It recommends sub optimal routes and has very poor point to point navigation. Often will not tell you to turn until you are just at or past turns. Has trouble connecting to GPS even with reliable connection. Would not recommend.

Good, but could be even better I have used this app for a few years now and find it very reliable, both in terms of finding the optimum route and calculating the ETA. content: Was is good. It needs to improve on determining which direction to go once a passenger is picked up if you are using the app for ride sharing. That first turn is critical because it gives a first impression to the passenger.

lately Waze has been unreliable, not able to find connection constantly. i like it better than Google because it used to be very accurate to when and where i was going but now i get no connection or just spins to get me started. i have to shut down too many times.

Also does it make sense to have a press and hold dialog box to report an accident or traffic? I'm using Pixel 2 XL

content: I would rate this 5 star but I think you should be able to drop a pin within 1km radius of location if there was a car accident or if there's police ahead. I had to turn left because I wasn't allowed to go straight so i Was not able to notify other waze users there was an accident ahead.

After being alerted by Google maps that traffic on my way to work was light and then i would end up sitting on the highway in "light traffic." I found Waze and i honestly tell everyone, this is the ALL TIME BEST APP EVER. I worship this app. I don't leave my driveway without being set in my Waze. One thing that maybe a future update could add is more routes than just three, but not a big deal. Waze is worth gold, not stars. Thank you Waze

I love waze, more adaptive to current situations than Google & great warnings but as a prev reviewer said, would be helpful if they were repeated, even once. Latest update caused issues - select a destination & it searches for a route but then goes back to the general map of your current location without a route & when you try to select destination again - nothing - the map just defaults. VERY frustrated! Update: as per Peter A review- also having GPS connect issues, restarting app fixes it.
replyContent: Hi Jennifer, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Worst app ever. It blocks user accounts without any reasons. There is no customer support as well. It blocked my first account. I didn't want to create another one. But I risked creating another account and within 2 days they have blocked it again. No refunds given for any ride which you give by spending your time. Please do not waste time on this stupidest and cheapest app ever made. Thanks.

waze is awesome. it even told me there was road kill in the road... best maps out there. tells you if police are radaring & if camera lights or school zones...it tells you everything!! saved my ass more than once! & its fun how you get to choose your own car that shows on map while your driving. choose the navigation voice, yup its really cool. i love waze!

Require email login now.. deleted all of my addresses without option to transfer from prior login. Poor estimation of drive timing in urban traffic, often underestimated. Integration with Android auto is suboptimal, with too frequent popups, poor placement of driving instruction overlayed over the map you're trying to look at, ok but definitely not perfect UI on the car display. At least it's free? But Google is definitely utilizing the data we drivers provide so is that really free???

content: I think I may have solved these problems. Changed my phone and tinkered around (whilst not under pressure) and I think it's all straight. It kept trying to send me through fields and didn't seem to know where I was. I've knocked off the "always show north on map" and it works.

content: love this app for long trips, keeping track of current speed limits a big plus! Hazard warnings, speed cameras all worked well. Only minus was that the app crashed, had to restart my phone (Android) , was good after that tho. Intuitive app, recommended.

content: I really hope Waze sees this review but I have two suggestions 1 after you enter a destination and you're on route when you try to scroll ahead even if you're heading 20 plus miles on the same road it automatically Scrolls you back to your current location so every time I make the map smaller so that I could see further away it send me back again to current location. and 2nd when you click on reports ahead is there anyway you could click on the actual report because it's not always updated

It would be nice if you added an option to silence directions when driving home when you get within different ranges of your house (User set preference/distance). So say when i get within 2 miles of my house it will go silent so i can enjoy the music without interruption. It would be nice to have a reload option from Android Auto also just in case you forget to turn on you GPS. That way once you turn on your GPS you can refresh/exit Waze (what ever works best to pick up the GPS without having to disconnect reconnect the phone while driving.

This app is more reliable in dead zones (no service), easier navigation throughout, visually more appealing and is great flagging anything on the road. I recommend this app to all my family/friends every time and anyone still using Apple or Google maps, hands down.

best app I have now! alot better than my Garmin and Tomtom.. all hazards and camera locations etc are 100% spot on, I drive over 2000miles per week so this will be invaluable to my clean licence! maybe in the future a van selection could be added as speed limits are mostly different from cars..And also an average speed indicator when in a reported zone? come on people get this app and work together!

I have been using this app and adding road changes, closures and other information. Everyone I show it to is very impressed. If you have a passenger they can even add road risks and things. I definitely recommend this.

Will not re-route me when I go off course. It just keeps telling me to go back to the original course. Which is not what I want to do. I want to drive in a different direction and have the map remap it for me just like Google does. I would also like to see writtenturn by turn directions of my route like Google does. I like the integration of Spotify and Pandora. I like that you can find restaurants and gas stations with prices along your route.

Waze has been super lagging these days . At times like today it took about half an hour for it to start detecting the gps signal . And even if it has started navigating, its navigatuin is delayed after i took on the wrong direction . Its been really annoying and disappointing !!! Appreciate if your team can fix this frustrating issue !!!

Was hoping that account recovery would be easier. No, still have to sign up with a new account every time I upgrade phones. ( Same number!!) No off line map option. Not every place has cell coverage. Mountains and desert especially.

As the delivery driver I rely on my GPS to get me to customers houses. The app constantly tells me to make a u-turn or says that I'm at the location when I'm a quarter of a mile away or it will send me in one direction and then halfway through turn around and send me in a different direction

content: Waze is very accurate

Used to be fine now totally useless, GPS constantly falls over and maps freeze so I now use Google Maps. I guess there is no investment as I expect Google will eventually try to move all users over to Goigle Maps which would mark the end of Waze. This is my opinion only but I hope Google will invest in a fix

I don't understand why my Waze is different then my wife's... We can put in the same place and get completely different directions every time and my eta is never accurate, even after checking all the settings are the same..ie traffic and fastest route etc. Going to try reinstalling.. Again

Better than any dedicated satnav I've used. For long journeys I just plug it into the cig socket. You can see reports by other users about events on the road and make reports yourself. You can even see other waze users. Got me down south and back and all round that area, over 500 miles all told no problems.

I'm only giving this 1 star to get the developers' attention. It would be very, very useful if when using voice commands, it would list the search results with numbers and allow us to vocally choose the destination.

Began using the Waze app for more details when traveling out of town , but found even more useful in town as well, warning of objects in the road plus the bonus of ride sharing! It not only is a financial benefit but also helps relax the ride by having someone to chat with. More people ought to consider the carpool app too!!

Very disappointed! Waze use to be the greatest. but now when I get phone calls Waze freezes and it won't let me go back to the navigation I have to force close the app and start completely over. please fix because I work as a professional driver and I really enjoy using this app

I gotta admit I only used it for a day or 2 then I went back to my trusty old Google Maps. I saw nothing wrong w/this App off hand. In fact, I'm sure it's great. I just would prefer to stay w/what I know already & Gmaps is at the top of my comfort zone.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We appreciate your feedback and hope you decide to give us another try in the future. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Only used it a couple of times and it totally sent me in wrong direction. I was trying to get to a car dealership that has been at that location for years. I gave it one more try a few days later. It didn't even have the names of the streets right. I wanted to like this app. I want an alternative to Google maps. Sadly, this is not it.

installed this bc Ford SYNC system wouldn't work correctly. It's not very user friendly, not intuitive at all. After 10 minutes trying to figure out how to get destination input from one destination to another, I got sooo frustrated with it. I deleted this POS app and just use Google maps on phone

Waze used to be a great app but I don't know what had happened. Instead of just being a guide it constantly want me to take longer routes even if the traffic isn't that terrible. Sometimes I feel the app is more confused than I am.

Even though Google bought Waze and I prefer the waze interface. I would like to suggest two things to the devs however; 1) I'd like to have radio button shortcuts to reports. The ability to select specific shortcuts to have embedded/visible on the map view for easier reporting whilst driving by skipping the steps assoicated with making a report. 2) an option to report dangerous/wreckless/impaired drivers and input reg number with direct reporting to police. Idiots would probably abuse this tho.

GPS functionality is bugged, often times it just will not sync and it will have no idea where I am. I know cause I switch to google maps and its perfectly fine and the GPS tracking is on point there. I have a OnePlus6. Otherwise, would be a decent navigation app for drivers.

I've already submitted a bug report and didn't get a good response for a while. Since v4.65, a user who installed [not updated] the app with no account cannot use it because the EULA doesn't show up when the app opens. Instead, the user is greeted with an empty map. The way to fix this [at least as of v4.68] is to pretend to sign in to an account, because that of all places is where the EULA shows up. In future versions of the app, please show a EULA right after the GPS permission request.

App is good near urban centers but differs greatly when converging on selected address on rural destinations taking you in the wrong direction. Don't trust directions for rural addresses. Use alternate map routing software on phone or vehicle. Taken many kilometers away from destination many times. Don't use unless in a city.

content: best navigation of my life with too many features thanks to the developers. I think they can improve more by showing the prices of fuel in tank station and car parking feature where we had parked our car and also showing the exact lane which we need to take in highway in another screen like in tom tom then would be the no. 1 navigation....

Great app but dont drive while you have passangers as youll be endangering their lives. Waze has always suffered from the same problem for years, broadcasting ads that take up the screen that wont go away until you press something. Theyre's a new notification now and its brilliantly dangerous. Now i am informed when they're is a nearby waze driver and this notification travels with you blocking the whole way until that waze driver is no where near you. Amazingly stupid.

Honda CRV 2018 Android Auto Why does the horizon of the map, while navigating, have a semi-transparent bar that covers the edge of the map? Make this go away. Copy Apple CarPlay. This makes it harder to use safely. I can't see where I am going when you cover up the map up ahead!

Awesome app.. Only need it when i see traffic.. Gets me around it in ways I would normally get lost trying to get around.. But I still use my mind and my skill of direction so I dont become like this useless next generation.. They go to the same place 3 times a week but still confused how to get there just because they pulled over to get gas... SMH.. Just learned what that even means.. Figured I'd use it..

This app is owesome It's been long I have it but I tested it today and it worked perfectly, I was driving over to the speed limit and the notification of what's ahead of you helped me to avoid being on the wrong side of the law.! I would give ten stars If given a choice

Application is missing important features, when running in Android auto. They are available only in standard version. I will appreciate at least something like "I am not a driver mode". Otherwise the only possibility to use the feature is to stop Android auto and change to standard .

Never use Google again.. Love, love the batman voice over by far! I really enjoy that the more you use it, being loyal, the more things that pop up that you don't know about because I LOVE surprises.. Great app!! I use it every day. Love the eta feature. Always trying to see if I can knock off a min or two. Would like something like a 3D mode that shows hills, maybe red lights, and even stop signs. And would like to see other ppl update their info more frequently such as gas station gas prices and times of operation. I would definitely recommend this app to anyone not just for traveler's.

I am a commercial driver with twenty years under my belt. Don't mean to toot my own horn, just proud of what I do. This app is amazing if you are traveling. If there is an accident on the highway, it will automatically give you an option to take detour. I love this feature. It has helped me a number of times. That's just my two cents. Y'all travel safely!!

I love the app. And depend on it daily as I'm directionally challenged. If I miss a turn, it will continue to direct me back to where I should have turned. I wish it would just pick up from where I am and direct me from the new starting point. Aside from that, it's GREAT. Thank you.
Lousy app. Got me lost all the time. Google is much better.

content: I still prefer Google Map. I tried Waze once, but since it is strictly user-centric, I doubt it always reports traffic conditions, while I believe Google map is satellite-fed, and except for weather and data connection, seems to provide real traffic conditions. I stand to be corrected.

I got this to plan calm rides to work and around the city on my vespa. I set it to avoid highways and it kept sending me straight down the 10 for my ride to work. There doesn't seem to be a way of manually adjusting the route. Meh. Useless to me. Wasted my time downloading it.

I've only been here a little while now I have enjoyed of seeing what happens on the Roads before you get there like traffic, police, vehicles on the side of the road is Such a wonderful tool to have while you're driving. It is important to understand the navigations once you are driving to not to be distracted.

It's a good app, I like the fact that road users can share hazards etc immediately. There's been an update through Android auto side of things which is a bit of a pain, it puts the info screen in the way and squashes the map. Why can't we move the info screen accross or resize it? A bit of customisation here wouldn't go a miss.

The app has gotten a lot better in the last couple of years. The road updates from other users is a big plus. Also the ability to add stops along the way helps plan a trip easier. My only complaint is the ads, but they only come on when you're at a stop, and go away just as quickly. I just don't like ads in general, so that's my complaint

Amazingly poor quality coding. Breaks on every android is update. Poor quality. Clearly coded by poor quality coders who have no experience in automotive coding. better than google maps. tho my brother had it, updated where a cop was, and then that same cop followed him to a gas station, waited, and continued following him for an additional 10 minutes. The best road app I have ever used, even tells you where pot holes are or stranded vehicles in the hard shoulder of the motorway, it is way ahead of Google maps which is slowly catching up with some of the features you have here.

content: Have used Waze for a couple of years. Loved it until the recent Android Auto update killed it. Very buggy now running through Android Auto. Navigation screen freezes after calling up a destination. Get an intial Let's Go direction but that's it. Too bad. It was great.

Dear Waze creator, My only complaint about waze is that when ever there's traffic you cant see it real clean. It does show but under of the the main purple or blue line. An when you get get boom it shows red but its alreadyto late lol..wish it could be almost like the Google one were the traffic is exactly an it show red or yellow an you could see from far when you zoom out or in... please fix that...

Way more functional and sleek than Google Maps. Some locations are incorrect but some are incorrect on Google Maps too. I'm a delivery driver and use this app about 10 hours a day and it is invaluable to me. The gas prices, hazard reports, and ability to upload pictures of locations are super helpful.

When it works it's the best driving app by far but it's lagging at the moment, particularly when using the future planning feature. Never had any trouble with it before so hope it's a short-term problem that's being addressed.

****Never accurate with camera info. no longer able to report cameras.***** Cannot keep waze on top meaning when you take or call someone the phone locks and you have to unlock it while driving to see directions. Sometimes waze will give you a direction that's blatantly longer just so it makes it look like they giving a better direction.

used it on my recent trip from VA to Ohio, froze repeatedly, even after I cleared the cache, uninstalled it , restarted my phone, and reinstalled it. I use to love this app, now I am just disappointed, hope you can find out what is going on.

I LOVE this App!!!!! The traffic and police reports are awesome. The only thing I would recommend would be to be able to reappointment to and make reports voice activated. Otherwise, you need a co-pilot to contribute.

Widget for Samsung Galaxy phones does not work. You can load it but can't open it. Too many steps to get to the search bar and input an address. Can't add an address to favorites from the map page, you have to go to another page to input it from memory as a favorite or a special category like home or work. Steps need to be simplified to make it faster to get your instructions to where you are going. Many times it takes me way out of the way, adding several unnecessary miles to my trip.

Who needs a radar detector? Not me, not when using waze. I simply love this app. Keeps me updated in real time , where traffic is, police, accidents, debris on the road, cars pulled over on the side of the road, gas station locations, and so much more! I just don't know how I ever got along without this incredible app! Great job guys!
I am a minicab driver I have been used for last 5 years. I recommend 5 star

If you are still using Google Maps, please give Waze a try. I was late for my first day of work because Google Maps took me to the wrong location. The HR lady told me about Waze and I have used it ever since. It's more accurate, tells you if a cop is posted somewhere. I LOVE it...just wanted to share

I love how Waze allows the community of wazers to mark when there is a cop radaring ahead of you! This app has saved me from getting a ticket more than once or twice that's for sure. I dont reccomend getting this app just so u can disobey the speed limit as it is not 100% accurate about the cops all the time. It just helps a lot when u have a long drive on the interstate to keep you constantly aware of your speed. One of my best apps on my phone! Would definitely recommend this free app!

Works, but can be very frustrating. No obvious menu. Hard to change start point when not from "home". Not good when I'm in a hurry to get to my volunteer emergency activities. Not intuitive. I like it when I'm secure it is set up correctly.
love this app. have not seen anything like it. tells me when cars are broke down on the side of the road , crashes ahead. detours,animals or police ahead. you can report too. bad weather and more.

Really important feature missing from the android auto version, where we can't indicate a road is closed along a route, to get rerouted. It's available when on mobile. A little dangerous because it means i have to unplug the phone, open it on the device, set the road closed and then reconnect to the car.

The latest update has forced us to use Google voice instead of simple voice. It no longer shows youthe address you have spoken in the search bar and instead goes straight to the first result which is usually wrong and there is no way to preview the address you have spoken. An option to revert to the previous implementation is desperately needed as the voice search function is now basically useless.

content: App looks marginally useful, but I need something I can set once and let it automate and that I can verify that it's set. After scouring every setting/help menu, I see no way to set planned time to leave reminders to repeat. Nor do I see a way to plan a trip out more than 7 days. Maybe something in Waze's interaction with Calendars intends to substitute for viewing such notifications within the Waze app. In any case, it's not "easy" to find, & I already wasted enough time here. Uninstall.

Logging in through Google keeps me as Guest Wazer and brings network connection errors. Reached out to support month ago with no response. Sad. So one star until I can login into my account again which is a pretty essential thing.
