content: Very good experience, within a year, I had a small problem within a small city of Fayetteville, NC. We couldn't gind a location, but perhaps it wasn't listed. We've been to NOLA, ATL, -ATLANTIC CITY and we're 100% satisfied. AF.

This app USE TO BE good. now everytime I try to use it, it gives me "something went wrong" error. you have to back out, go back in 3 or 4 times until it gives you directions. your app sucks now! thanks.

where did you go? we were driving along together for about 6 months and then i did yr update and poof! you were gone! I've tried every left, right and round-about to find you to no avail. "no gps". "searching for gps". meanwhile google maps is speeding along the gps hwy. so. I'm saying good bye.
This used to be an amazing app. After the last update it's completely unusable!! No connection. Map rotates constantly. Has you listed on the wrong streets. You need to fix this or I'm gone!!

I use it almost every day for yob. This is rly good app... Sometimes it does not show shorter roads in routes, so i have to use google maps. Very god thing is speed cams, and you can mark police so other can see them on map. On my Redmi note 8t, it loose gps signal when i call or receive call, and battery drain is high, so the phone have to be pluged all the time in charger.

Every time there's an update, glitches occur. The newest update of adding an automatic battery saver mode while charging keeps messing up my Android auto - I've disabled the power saver several times and it always changes back. Battery saver mode makes the GPS background data to be disabled, which is pretty essential for a GPS program.

No longer notes closed streets! Waze is routing me right in to closed major streets (closed for weeks due to construction) in heavily congested areas in a major city because it no longer allows for user input when streets are closed (at least from Android auto interface) Rerouting seems changed, stays on same route even when driver makes repeated choices that are not part of route. Very disappointing.

since jan 2019 update waze crashes upon opening app when the phone is in car mode. 3 users submitted bug reports about the issue. They were closed with no resolution stating they don't bug check against third party apps. car mode is a android os function not a third party app. in order to use waze with car mode android auto must be installed. this is not ok as in my jurisdiction i must use car mode now i cannot use it so that i can use waze.

I consider this app essential for anyone taking road trips. It always gets me where I want to go, it helped me avoid a ladder that was strewn across the highway, and finds a way around traffic jams. I turn this on even when I know my way to my destination because of the info it provides.

I have a bug on my mi 10. It takes approx. 30 mins for the gps to detect the location and running. Before that, it will not be able to pin point my exact location. This is very nuisance whenever I drive.
replyContent: Hi Nazreen, thanks for reaching out. Let's see if some troubleshooting helps with this GPS issue. Please try these steps from our GPS Help Center article: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Doesn't tell you how to beep at other waxers. The directions are off, a lot of the time, by more than 50 ft, and you aren't shown which side of the street your destination is on until it's too late. Other than that, it's a great app.

Waze is excellent. I use it alot for my job and it's so reliable and easy to understand what I really like is that it notifies you of stopped cars and police officers in the area. I love waze. I have no complaints about waze.
I don't know how we survived without waze before the Smartphone.

Not working consistently last week. I've used this app for many years on.various phones. Now, the app didn't work on any device multiple times throughout the day? I've updated and still routing times out. Is the app going down? Very frustrating for those of us that count on you. Please fix!

after many years of using this map as my daily driver, i am deleting this app for good and going back to maps. The dev is complacent, quality went to bed. 1. turning accuracy is atrocious. Turning directions only shows one arrow when there are many forks, UNSAFE 2. distance in search results does not match actual trip, it lies and not reliable 3. Description of highway/exiy signs usually don't match. UNSAFE! Come on! I will tolerate GMaps even though it doesnt have an auto center feature BOYCOTT

Updated review- update to app recently installed and it appears to have fixed the issues mentioned below. Back to 5 stars! -- Great app but as others have mentioned mine has also recently stopped working correctly when connected thru Android auto since a recent update. Position on the map constantly rotates, map is sluggish to refresh and not acurate, and the speedometer has disappeared from mine as well. Vehicle arrow also occasionally displays as sideways or crooked and not pointing up.
replyContent:
Hi, Eric! We're sorry to hear that you're having trouble using Waze with Android Auto. We'd like to look into this further, would you mind submitting more information about this issue here: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/7451079?hl=en

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: I love how Waze allows all of us to report traffic conditions and hazards, and I like receiving a personalized report that shows how many fellow Wazers I helped. Based on these live reports, Waze generates alternative routes to help me avoid traffic and saved me from being late to work numerous times. This app is free but I would pay for it!

The app takes a long time to find a route and I have to shut down the app multiple times to get it going properly. Also, sometimes the keyboard blocks the search bar at the bottom and sometimes I have to exit the app again. Not a bad app, but its not my number one choice just yet.

Great most of the time, but lately the speed limit has been incorrect. It shows the speed limit is 30 miles an hour faster than it is and that I'm going 30 miles faster than I am. I would really like to see it give me a couple of different options on the route I choose. Sometimes I don't like the route it chooses for me. It would be even better if it would let me draw the route that I want to take.

Crashes all the time. Walking out the door going from wifi to 4G breaks it. Often becomes unresponsive forcing me to kill the app and start over. Sometimes reboots my phone at crucial times when i leave work and need to know which way to turn to avoid traffic. The spotify connection doesnt work until i launch full Spotify app so i have to switch apps while driving causing more instability. The button to start your trip is half cutoff making pressing it a daily chore.

Works well, mostly intuitive user interface. Limited to only connecting w. friends through Facebook, boo:( App has an annoying bug: all notifications result in suppressing audio of other apps running synchronously that produce media (sound) : however this also concerns any type of waze-notification that doesn't even HAVE an audio. This results in severe disruption of e.g. Spotify music, Audible listening-books etc. when taking turns, passing a speedcam etc. Please fix this! :)
Can see where speed traps are before you get to them! Sneaky little blood suckers! can be detected money suckers met their match..

I really tried to like waze. I tried several times on both android and apple but my experience was awful! It kept giving me really stupid directions, making me go around and around for nothing so I gave up, once again on this thing. I'll keep togoogle maps.

Used Waze pre-G, believe acquired to not loose "location" data a G "must". Love the real time traveler updates with police, accidents, slow downs, the only real differentiator here. The police notices are quick and remarkably accurate, yet traffic slowdowns rarely appear < caught in one. Re-routing to shorten time is almost non-existent and simply taking a faster route causes Waze to constantly insist return to original. Longer trips only 1 route shown. Dedicated GPS always better for best time

The only app I use for directions because Google is trash. However I'm now lost in downtown Seattle because I, like an idiot, trusted the app for the 5th time to save my parking spot. Every time I use the save my spot option it NEVER saves it. It's been 3 hours that I've been searching this time. Thank WAZE. Fix this issue please.
replyContent: Hi Nathan, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Awesome app always does it's job

I like what they have a whole lot. Big fan!! But it would be sooooo much better if they offered a step by step direction like google(hate google) maps does. I'm not a fan of google period!! That's why I went with Waze. Waze also did not work in Cumberland Maryland today and google maps did(very frustrating). I was extremely disappointed by this!! I will rate it higher when it offers step by step directions and works in western Maryland.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for reaching out. You actually can view directions in steps. Here's how: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/6273629?hl=en If you still need assistance with this feature, please message us on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Fails every time to automatically reconnect to its network every time it disconnects from an unreliable connection. Requires the app to be restarted before it will reconnect. Also doesn't send through reports that are made when offline, even though it claims it will.

Freezes randomly while in use (screen app unresponsive, no more current location updates, freezes again after closing the app and starting it again). Other navigation apps work without hitches. Used to work properly last year, new updates or implementation on Android 8.0 made it unusable.

Since the last update, the app doesn't work well. 1. Can't report an issue from the app. I enter, and nothing appears. 2. When driving, the navigation arrow and the screen don't orient to the direction I'm going. Pixel 3 android 11 I have pics to send you showing the problem
replyContent: Hi there, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your issue. We'd like to investigate this further, could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: the updated music interface is horrible. it now requires additional screen touches to open, change song, and requires to be minimized to see the map at normal color. it is much safer and convenient to have the music interface always displayed while viewing the driving map in it's normal configuration

The app has basics missing apart from the speedometer. Can't use mic to speak because whatever I say in English it types and searches in Hindi because I am in India though my language is set as English (US). And no option provided to change that. Isn't that really stupid.

Would rate it higher if it allowed a simple way to retain and view previous trips taken (like my alternative map software does). Current procedure is very clunky & limited 'Open the Waze Map Editor and log into your Waze account. Click Drives to view your drives...' but, sadly 'from the previous 14 days only. However, depending on the servers, sometimes routes can be only be viewed from the previous few days.' Maybe I should run Waze & my other app together?
replyContent:
Hi, we understand your disappointment, regarding viewing previous trips but appreciate your feedback. Feel free to share any changes you would like to see in the app by submitting to Waze‚Äôs suggestion box: https://waze.uservoice.com/forums/59223-waze-suggestion-box

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Long time user...this app is buggy as hell...I use Android auto. Have Waze on autostart whitelist . It stays stuck at last working location, meanwhile Google maps works fine. Waze won't pick up location and screen won't change and update with change in physical location... Research tells me downgrading to previous apk will work. I will delete this version and downgrade to an old one

there is a bit of lag between the GPS location and actual location when you're driving, unless you can actually see the screen while driving, the audio isn't sufficient. speed cameras and other aids in the app is quite helpful for daily commutes.

Recent update now getting pointless navigation popups on the phone even though Waze is running via Android Auto on my headunit. Also on Android Auto there is no way for Waze to request or search locations from your Contacts. The ability to do so appears to work as a standalone app but this defeats the purpose of Android Auto navigation.
Always off the gps when using this

When first started using the app it was good however recently gone drastically downhill. Takes a very long time starting up and finding your start point and stops tracking midpoint , tries to recalculate but can't.. have to close and open app several times to get it up and running again.

The directions are always clear and simple. Much better than other apps available. Tells you how long you'll be in traffic, option to re-route. Without WAZE i would be totally lost! Literally! Have no idea what i did before WAZE. Love the option of male/female voice & different accents.

Really would like to see a vehicle option for us people who drive trucks over 10,000 pounds and have to go different routes because of it, there are many weight and height restricted roads that we can't go down and would be great to find an app that caters to our much needed GPS that caters to our need for a route that doesn't bring us down restricted roads!! Thank you

Awesome so far, but one thing I would like to see changed is the ability to pick a spot on the screen and add whatever the problem is from your list AFTER we stop somewhere. I drive a truck and we can't so much as even look at our phones or the camera will bust us. That would make this app 100√ó better.

I like the app,easy directions easy to see and understand. I've had a problem twice with losing internet connection and once getting lost. The other problem is when you know an easier route and it won't let you reroute.And of course no direction it's just pick out destination and put in and hope you know fairly where you're heading.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback, Pamela. We'd love to hear more about the issues you're experiencing. Would you mind sending us a private message on Facebook? For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Only Navi app I use, always reliable and it's fun trying to beat the arrival times. I think the voice controls could use an improvement, doesn't always respond when I want to report an accident or something like that.

Update 2/23. I don't use Facebook s I can't use the link you suggested. Very simple to use but as others mentioned, after I ask to navigate to a location, I'd like to voice confirm it. Not have to look away from the road and tap the screen. Isn't that the point of Android Auto? Hands-free?
replyContent: Hi Joe, thank you for taking the time to provide your review. We're always looking to improve your experience with Waze. We appreciate your feedback. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Accurate as best as possible. There have been times I've been given the long scenic tour but overall 95% of the time taken me where I needed to go. The hazard alerts are a great feature and on one occasion I was able to avoid an accident when alerted to hazard on road. The hazard was a bumper on the center lane.

Amazing GPS app! LOVE the heads up on hidden cops, crashes up ahead and objects on the road. Avoided a dresser on the fwy, one time with that heads up. I don't mind when it takes me off the fwy (take surface streets); when it's jammed with traffic for a faster route.

This s the best app that I really feel comfortable driving. has everything .pics,3Ds map multicolor list of different voices that you select at your choice.adds suggestion of Ads for discounts good places to enjoyed.speed limits anousment.., alert of any incident on the road & police alert in the area.wow excellent.I Loved it

It would be great if: we could indicate where debris and huge potholes are located in the breakdown lanes. Why? I realize that most states have fines in place for tow truck drivers who don't clean up debris from an accident. Missouri isn't one of these states. Huge chunks of bumpers and other car parts are left in breakdown lanes for a year and longer. They also don't fill in potholes in the breakdown lanes. It is dangerous to have your car breakdown in Missouri. Please give us these options.

id be lost without it!! Literally!! I hate driving and I always have. Especially if its somewhere ive never been before. I get lost easily and get very frustrated! i used to just say eff it and go home! This app is so easy to use that it's impossible for even me to get lost! I dont get as frustrated, and I feel like it makes me a better driver. i love that it tells me which lane to stay in. I'll never enjoy driving, but with this app, I dont mind driving to places i don't know.You cannot be lost!

Love this app so much!! Love the "time to leave" notifications for trips. The only improvement that I would like to see is searching for something would show you options on your route and how much time it will add if you have to vear of route. Google Maps does this well.

Absolutely horrible. I'm forced to use ways by my tow fleet. Ever since all drivers were forced to start using it the dispatch radio is constantly going off because of how lost waze is making the drivers. Waze is great at picking a complicated and convoluted route, a 5minute drive can easily become a 10minute drive if you go by what waze tells you. The constant pop up ads are a major distraction. The road hazard and traffic warnings are often off and delayed, making that feature useless. Pathetic

Totally pointless app. Easier to use Google maps instead. Links to my Kenwood stereo for navigation and crashes. Phone has to be unlocked screen on and visable to the sky for the GPS. Doesn't use car GPS. So if you need your battery to charge just forget it. Your phone will die using this app in the car

This app give incorrect directions frequently and in more than one occasion had sent me to the wrong place or directions change after I have already followed what it originally told me to do. It's great for red light cameras and such but for REAL directions, stick to Google Maps.
replyContent:
Hi Terrance, we are sorry to hear that! Thanks for bringing this to our attention. Would you mind sharing some more details with us in a Facebook private message? We would like to investigate this issue. 

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: No longer works. Everytime I try to get directions it says "network connection failure". Doesn't matter what network I use, doesn't matter that I cleared cache, uninstalled, reinstalled, etc. Too bad, it used to be better than google maps, but it's unusable now.

Not good. Waze keeps dropping out trying to locate GPS most of the time, screen goes black/green. Funny though when you start Google maps first it seems to rectify it self. Waze was fine until the last couple of updates. When are you going to fix the issues you know about.

The app is good but unreliable, at times it will just disconnect from my GPS and will not reconnect. I can understand if I was underground or was in a tunnel but it does it at random times. As you can imagine it can very frustrating and dangerous where you don't know where you are and your sat nav disconnects.
replyContent:

For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze is great. Where have you been all my life? ... oh wait maybe you needed directions to get to my house ..haha Anyway, I can always count on Waze to get me where I am going and back home again while also avoiding traffic whenever possible. Waze has made those old Garmin GPS electronics a thing of the past. Thank you Waze for never steering me wrong üòÅüëçüèΩ

Useful app, but has issues on my Galaxy S10 where it does not activate GPS location when connected via Android Auto. If I activate Google Maps first via Android Auto, then switch to Waze it works fine. If you can fix this bug it would make it a 5-star rating from me. Thanks.

I pretty much like the whole app. I like the characters, bright colors, and voice over to tell driver to be aware. Sometimes though, directions are off. That I would like to see improvement in the near future. Thank you Waze. :)

It used to be super reliable.... Thats out the window! The app ALWAYS crashes after the first start and then it works. I had it crash twice in a row, but it does it once, guaranteed. Not sure what youve done to it, but a rollback seems betterthan ''new features''
replyContent: Hi Adrian, we're sorry to hear about your issue. Please try reinstalling the app and make sure you are using the latest app version. If the issue continues, please send us a private message on Facebook so we can investigate further. Thank you! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Waze gets 5 stars when it is working, but the app has become horribly unreliable. GPS seems to be always wayyyy behind where I actually am, then it catches up and gets stuck again. Love the traffic alerts and hazard repprting, but the app is becoming unsuitable for regular use.

Every time I open the app it keeps saying searching for network. I have read so many fixes online but nothing seems to work! It worked fine on my S10E but I got the new Razor and it hasn't worked since. Can someone please help me? I am so frustrated!

content: Used to love this app. Cookie Monster was the best voice. He should be made permanent. The voices now are horrible! Find a different app to use. Turn by turns used to be accurate and end destinations, now it's off.
replyContent: Thanks for the review, Christina! We're happy to help with any issues you may have. Please feel free to send us a private message on Facebook. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Recently waze is always lagging and always showing me messages like "Waze is connecting to GPS", "No GPS. Showing approximate location" or "Uh no. There is an error...". Whereas there is no problem with the GPS when i switch to Google Map. It is getting more and more unrealiable! Pls do something about it.

Very nice, and accurate routing. The road hazard, police, and traffic congestion warnings can't be beat. So glad i found it.üòé The gas price function is pretty much useless, prices usually shown can be up to 8 days old. Otherwise, it would get 5 üåü

Waze it's very good GPS app,but I'm not satisfied with it's accuracy,it always says you're arrived while you're one house before,or 100m-150m away.This can put one's life at risk by taking him/her to a wrong address.As people can mistake him/her for a criminal.Another thing it takes time to read the directions,when you have just started it,and sometimes on the highways it delays to tell you where to offramp,and that leads to miss the exit road,and become lost.If you can just improve that pls

content: The "play sound to phone speaker" option is no longer working. I use Waze via Android auto, and now in the last few weeks, the waze audio is playing through my car speakers and not my phone speakers. It annoys me when I drive as my music keeps turning low all the time so waze can speak or beep. Please make the play sound to phone speakers work again, so I can listen to my music uninterrupted in my car audio again, and Waze on my phone audio. This is the main reason I use waze over maps.

Is there any chance you can update this app for android users. Used to be fine no issues at all, now it lags all the time. It never catches up and when it eventually does catch up with your location, it freezes again. Please Help!
replyContent: Hi Paul, we're happy to help! Please try reinstalling the app and make sure that you're using the latest app version. If these issue continue, please message us on Facebook and we'd be happy to look into it further. Thank you. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Everytime I get or make a phone call it no longer automatically goes back to the app. This is not convenient or safe. It had an option to check but that option is now gone. Please fix!r first trip took me to the wrong location 5 miles away.

Trying to avoid (or getting sucked into) driving through an unsafe neighborhood on way frm work and avoid spending 2+ hrs stuck in bumper to bumper traffic. Heard this app has better options than google maps but this is no better. I can't even add to the navigation preferances. Lame.

I've been using this app for some time now and loved it but as many reviewers stated this app has become unstable. I get a constant error there is no network connection. Please fix this issue as I would hate to uninstall. It's back to Google maps which works just fine.

What is going on? This app is horrendous! It was working so smooth but my last few trips have been a nightmare. Map location is off, app doesnt want to find addresses and gives error messages on screen. I will have to delete the app until this problem gets resolved.

my experience with waze is mixed. the Best rerouting algorithms, difficult to add comments but I understand a voice command is in the maybe not so distant future. i have been a Waze user for over 5 years but I don't have a Facebook account. SO no user name gets transferred whenever I get a new device. functions on the 4+ range but entering information and inability to transfer user information is a 1-2

I love Waze, and sometimes I prefer it to gmaps. Notwithstanding, the team should work on the timezones for accuracy when giving the estimated time of arrival. It would be awesome if Waze calculated the ETA even before crossing timezones as you cruise. Thanks for the outstanding work.

My second favorite is Waze. It tells you what speed you are going and the speed limit. Also tells you what lane you should be in. Gives you an estimated time of arrival and tells you about upcoming police. It also tells you where gas stations are. It tells you where traffic is at a standstill and road closures. It's not very efficient when searching for a route it takes longer than Google Maps does to fine one. It suggests the best time to leave.

If u can include option best routes for coding vehicles.. And some inputs we can send like info of location to have it in your updates.. Like old and new addresses but same loacation.. Some establishment use new address but they much more known and easy to find in their old address. Like (s&r commonwealth) their delivery address used "Kareila - Commonwealth" that ur apps didn't know.

Lately I've been questioning whether the data is true and having to double check with Google Maps. It crashes often with frequent error messages. The alerts are extremely helpful, especially when communicating danger ahead.
Love it! The best navigation app!! üëçüèº

Created a new account and was unable to change password. Tried everything imaginable, no luck at all. If you log out, you can't log back in. You have to start over from scratch and create a new account. Too much of a pain. I'll stick with Google Maps.

I like this way better then any other Navigation app I've used. The only issue I've had was yesterday when it took me a completely different way to my girls house and 2 of the roads were closed and it took me 55 mins instead of 20 mins to get to her house.

Been using Waze for approx 6 years now. After updates within the last several months, I noticed that having the phone connected to Android Auto on my Challenger or Audi, it would freeze, not autozoom and lag with the current location. Changed resolution to 720P on Android Auto developer settings, turned off power modes (although Android 11 eliminated that), my fix was to find the older version and install.. updates have not fixed this issue.. also happens on IOS version.
replyContent: Hi Ruben, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to hear more about this Android Auto issue to investigate further. Could you please send us a private message on Facebook? Thanks. For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Using with Android Auto and latest update has screwed up the car audio, when you connect a route, every couple seconds the volume changes from the car audio volume level to the Waze notification volume level, it's unusable. If you cancel the route the switching volume stops even though Waze is still running.

The app used to work but now it works intermittently. I am using it thru my android auto on my Samsung S8. Half the time its like it can't find a gps signal. It will jump around all over the map or freeze. But as soon as I switch it over to Google maps everything works just fine.

Too many warnings about cars on the side of the road probably 60% of those warnings are meaningless! Police warnings if you follow road rules are useless and distracting. Doesn't do a good job on re-routing for traffic jams as the regular Google maps (unless I'm missing a setting). Plan to continue to use the traditional Google maps.

Before now! I rate it 5 But in last month I found it eating my mobile data, every time open it, at least 50 to 100 Mb of data losing!!! Why! I used it about 15-20 times a day and found 2-3 Gb mobile data losing!!!! Searcing on it and found NOTHING!!!! Is Anyone to help???

Great app, unless you want to get from A to B, then it's useless. On the rare occasions when it can actually find GPS it has no clue where you are. Just this morning I did a 40mi trip, it kept searching for GPS, I was about 7-8 min away from my destination when it came to its senses. It tells you to turn right in the middle of a straight road, told me to take the 2nd exit at the roundabout when the nearest one was 3 mi away. Used to be great, I loved it, now it's useless
replyContent: We appreciate your review, Orazsu. To fix the GPS issue, please follow these steps: tinyurl.com/ydbf57pk Let us know how it goes by sending us a private message on Facebook. Thanks! For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Love this app. I would 've been so lost w/o it! It tells u where to go and turn before the fact so u dont miss any. Very clear instructions and repeats them quickly for when u need to make a turn or an exit on the highway. I highly recommend!!! Thank you developers!

Absolutely amazing how when I attempt to log into my account by verifying my phone number with a code that you sent me, it says you can't verify my account but fail to provide any other ways to access my account. Waze used to be the leader in navigation but now that Google Maps provides you with police and accident alerts in their native app, Waze seems to be useless, and not allowing me to log into my existing account just proved why I'll stick with Google's stock app even though they own Waze.
It keeps me from getting lost.

I've had to reinstall Waze 3 times already. There are tons of glitches. The GPS is a hit or miss sometimes it takes ilu the right way and other times it takes u to roads that are closed its frustrating. I've sent tons of tickets but nothing has happened.

I had rated the app 5 stars before but I needed to change it because as soon as I did my waze app started not connecting to Gps and finding the routes I take on a daily basis. I'm not sure why it started doing this again but please fix it, might be time to find another app.
replyContent: Hi Rosa, thanks for contacting us. We'd like to help with this GPS issue you're having. Please give these troubleshooting steps a try from our Help Center: https://support.google.com/waze/answer/9909051 For further assistance please contact us here: https://m.me/waze

content: Works great. Would be much better without the annoying ads that cover 1/2 the screen whenever you come to a stop. Give us the option to turn of the carpool feature as well since it isn't relevant to everyone. Go back to your origins of focusing on providing directions and real time traffic information.

Something has changed with this app. In recent weeks I have been having to close the app completely before I can pull up another route. And the routes are rediculous; it takes you all the way around something to bring you back to the same street you were previously but there is no reason why.

I had the app at 5 stars until the last update; it worked flawlessly. Now when I start the app it can't figure out where I am. The phone version of waze is great, but the android auto version needs a lot of work. Many features that make the phone version so great are just not there. even adding a stop has just been added, but not to the same degree as the phone version. content: Tries to take you onto MOD roads! Generally waze is pretty useful, but today, going to Conford in Hampshire it tried to route me via MOD land roads at Longmoor.
